  (8550, 10, 19, 31, 'And Barzillai the Gileadite came down from Rogelim, and went over Jordan with the king, to conduct him over Jordan.', '&para; 1~01271~ 3~01569~ 5~03381~ 7~07274~, 10~05674~ 11~03383~ 14~04428~, 16~07971~ 19~03383~.'),
  (12897, 18, 1, 19, 'And, behold, there came a great wind from the wilderness, and smote the four corners of the house, and it fell upon the young men, and they are dead; and I only am escaped alone to tell thee.', '3~0935~ 5~01419~ 6~07307~ 7~05676~ 9~04057~, 11~05060~ 13~0702~ 14~06438~ 17~01004~, 20~05307~ 24~05288~, 28~04191~; 33~04422~ 36~05046~'),
  (2261, 2, 26, 21, 'And their forty sockets of silver; two sockets under one board, and two sockets under another board.', '2~0705~ 3~0134~ [4] 5~03701~; 6~08147~ 7~0134~ 9~0259~ 10~07175~, 12~08147~ 13~0134~ 15~0259~ 16~07175~.'),
  (19061, 24, 4, 25, 'I beheld, and, lo, there was no man, and all the birds of the heavens were fled.', '1~07200~, [4 5] 7~0120~, 11~05775~ 14~08064~ 16~05074~.'),
  (7264, 9, 2, 17, 'Wherefore the sin of the young men was very great before the LORD: for men abhorred the offering of the LORD.', '2~02403~ 6~05288~ 8~03966~ 9~01419~ 10~06440~ 12~03068~: 14~0582~ 15~05006~ 17~04503~ 20~03068~.'),
  (13658, 18, 32, 21, 'Let me not, I pray you, accept any man''s person, neither let me give flattering titles unto man.', '6~05375~ 8~0376~ 9~06440~, 15~03655~ 17~0120~.'),
  (7956, 9, 28, 7, 'Then said Saul unto his servants, Seek me a woman that hath a familiar spirit, that I may go to her, and inquire of her. And his servants said to him, Behold, there is a woman that hath a familiar spirit at Endor.', '&para; 1~0559~ 2~07586~ 5~05650~, 6~01245~ 9~0802~ 11~01172~ 14~0178~, 18~03212~ 22~01875~ 27~05650~ 28~0559~ [32 33] 35~0802~ 37~01172~ 40~0178~ 42~05874~.'),
  (3311, 3, 19, 25, 'And in the fifth year shall ye eat of the fruit thereof, that it may yield unto you the increase thereof: I am the LORD your God.', '3~02549~ 4~08141~ 7~0398~ 10~06529~ 15~03254~ 19~08393~ [22] 24~03068~ 26~0430~.'),
  (11819, 14, 29, 19, 'Moreover all the vessels, which king Ahaz in his reign did cast away in his transgression, have we prepared and sanctified, and, behold, they are before the altar of the LORD.', '3~03627~, 5~04428~ 6~0271~ 9~04438~ 12~02186~ 15~04604~, 18~03559~ 20~06942~, [24] 25~06440~ 27~04196~ 30~03068~.'),
  (14292, 19, 26, 10, 'In whose hands is mischief, and their right hand is full of bribes.', '2~03027~ [3] 4~02154~, 8~03225~ 10~04390~ 12~07810~.'),
  (29344, 49, 5, 24, 'Therefore as the church is subject unto Christ, so let the wives be to their own husbands in every thing.', '0~235~ 1~5618~ 3~1577~ 5~5293~ 7~5547~, 8~2532~ [9] 9~3779~ 11~1135~ [12] 15~2398~ 16~435~ 17~1722~ 19~3956~.'),
  (2519, 2, 34, 18, 'The feast of unleavened bread shalt thou keep. Seven days thou shalt eat unleavened bread, as I commanded thee, in the time of the month Abib: for in the month Abib thou camest out from Egypt.', '&para; 1~02282~ 4~04682~ 7~08104~. 8~07651~ 9~03117~ 12~0398~ 14~04682~, 17~06680~ 21~04150~ 24~02320~ 25~024~: 29~02320~ 30~024~ 33~03318~ 35~04714~.'),
  (7674, 9, 17, 49, 'And David put his hand in his bag, and took thence a stone, and slang it, and smote the Philistine in his forehead, that the stone sunk into his forehead; and he fell upon his face to the earth.', '1~01732~ 2~07971~ 4~03027~ 7~03627~, 9~03947~ 12~068~, 14~07049~ [15] 17~05221~ 19~06430~ 22~04696~, 25~068~ 26~02883~ 29~04696~; 32~05307~ 35~06440~ 38~0776~.'),
  (17535, 21, 12, 3, 'In the day when the keepers of the house shall tremble, and the strong men shall bow themselves, and the grinders cease because they are few, and those that look out of the windows be darkened,', '2~03117~ 5~08104~ 8~01004~ 10~02111~, 13~02428~ 14~0582~ 16~05791~ 20~02912~ 21~0988~ 25~04591~, 30~07200~ 33~0699~ 35~02821~,'),
  (24926, 42, 1, 22, 'And when he came out, he could not speak unto them: and they perceived that he had seen a vision in the temple: for he beckoned unto them, and remained speechless.', '0~1161~ 4~1831~, 6~1410~ 7~3756~ 8~2980~ 10~846~: 11~2532~ 13~1921~ 14~3754~ 17~3708~ 19~3701~ 20~1722~ 22~3485~: 23~2532~ 24~846~ 25~2258~ 26~1269~* 28~846~, 29~2532~ 30~1265~ 31~2974~.'),
  (15322, 19, 88, 5, 'Free among the dead, like the slain that lie in the grave, whom thou rememberest no more: and they are cut off from thy hand.', '0~02670~ 3~04191~, 6~02491~ 8~07901~ 11~06913~, 14~02142~ 21~01504~ 24~03027~.'),
  (9263, 11, 15, 6, 'And there was war between Rehoboam and Jeroboam all the days of his life.', '3~04421~ 5~07346~ 7~03379~ 10~03117~ 13~02416~.'),
  (23879, 40, 21, 43, 'Therefore say I unto you, The kingdom of God shall be taken from you, and given to a nation bringing forth the fruits thereof.', '0~5124~ 1~1223~ 2~3004~ 4~5213~ 5~3754~,* 7~932~ 9~2316~ 12~142~ 13~575~ 14~5216~, 15~2532~ 16~1325~ 19~1484~ 21~4160~ 23~2590~ 24~846~.'),
  (18462, 23, 41, 2, 'Who raised up the righteous man from the east, called him to his foot, gave the nations before him, and made him rule over kings? he gave them as the dust to his sword, and as driven stubble to his bow.', '2~05782~ 4~06664~ [5] 8~04217~, 9~07121~ 13~07272~, 14~05414~ 16~01471~ 17~06440~ [21] 22~07287~ 24~04428~? 26~05414~ [27] 30~06083~ 33~02719~, [34] 36~05086~ 37~07179~ 40~07198~.'),
  (23334, 40, 7, 8, 'For every one that asketh receiveth; and he that seeketh findeth; and to him that knocketh it shall be opened.', '0~1063~ 2~3956~ 4~154~ 5~2983~; 6~2532~ 9~2212~ 10~2147~; 11~2532~ 15~2925~ 19~455~.'),
  (3284, 3, 18, 28, 'That the land spue not you out also, when ye defile it, as it spued out the nations that were before you.', '2~0776~ 6~06958~ 10~02930~ 15~06958~ 17~01471~ [19] 20~06440~'),
  (4822, 4, 33, 56, 'Moreover it shall come to pass, that I shall do unto you, as I thought to do unto them.', '[6] 9~06213~ 14~01819~ 16~06213~'),
  (15622, 19, 105, 7, 'He is the LORD our God: his judgments are in all the earth.', '[1] 3~03068~ 5~0430~: 7~04941~ [8] 12~0776~.'),
  (28462, 46, 4, 13, 'Being defamed, we entreat: we are made as the filth of the world, and are the offscouring of all things unto this day.', '1~987~, 3~3870~: 6~1096~ 7~5613~ 9~4027~ 12~2889~, [13 14] 16~4067~ 19~3956~ 20~2193~ 22~737~.'),
  (13316, 18, 19, 10, 'He hath destroyed me on every side, and I am gone: and mine hope hath he removed like a tree.', '2~05422~ 6~05439~, 10~03212~: 13~08615~ 16~05265~ 19~06086~.'),
  (22134, 28, 2, 20, 'I will even betroth thee unto me in faithfulness: and thou shalt know the LORD.', '3~0781~ 8~0530~: 12~03045~ 14~03068~.'),
  (18589, 23, 45, 19, 'I have not spoken in secret, in a dark place of the earth: I said not unto the seed of Jacob, Seek ye me in vain: I the LORD speak righteousness, I declare things that are right.', '3~01696~ 5~05643~, 8~02822~ 9~04725~ 12~0776~: 14~0559~ 18~02233~ 20~03290~, 21~01245~ 25~08414~: 28~03068~ 29~01696~ 30~06664~, 32~05046~ 36~04339~.'),
  (30574, 62, 2, 8, 'Again, a new commandment I write unto you, which thing is true in him and in you: because the darkness is past, and the true light now shineth.', '0~3825~, 2~2537~ 3~1785~ 5~1125~ 7~5213~, 9~3739~ 10~2076~ 11~227~ 12~1722~ 13~846~ 14~2532~ 15~1722~ 16~5213~: 17~3754~ 19~4653~ 21~3855~, 22~2532~ 24~228~ 25~5457~ 26~2235~ 27~5316~.'),
  (7416, 9, 9, 18, 'Then Saul drew near to Samuel in the gate, and said, Tell me, I pray thee, where the seer''s house is.', '&para; 1~07586~ 3~05066~ 5~08050~ 6~08432~ 8~08179~, 10~0559~, 11~05046~ 16~0335~ 18~07200~ 19~01004~ [20]'),
  (22470, 30, 6, 11, 'For, behold, the LORD commandeth, and he will smite the great house with breaches, and the little house with clefts.', '3~03068~ 4~06680~, 8~05221~ 10~01419~ 11~01004~ 13~07447~, 16~06996~ 17~01004~ 19~01233~.'),
  (12167, 15, 6, 7, 'Let the work of this house of God alone; let the governor of the Jews and the elders of the Jews build this house of God in his place.', '2~05673~ 4~01791~ 5~01005~ 7~0426~ 8~07662~; 11~06347~ 14~03062~ 17~07868~ 20~03062~ 21~01124~ 22~01791~ 23~01005~ 25~0426~ 26~05922~ 28~0870~.'),
  (12821, 17, 7, 5, 'Then the king Ahasuerus answered and said unto Esther the queen, Who is he, and where is he, that durst presume in his heart to do so?', '2~04428~ 3~0325~ 4~0559~ 6~0559~ 8~0635~ 10~04436~, 20~04390~ 23~03820~ 25~06213~'),
  (1640, 2, 5, 3, 'And they said, The God of the Hebrews hath met with us: let us go, we pray thee, three days'' journey into the desert, and sacrifice unto the LORD our God; lest he fall upon us with pestilence, or with the sword.', '&para; 2~0559~, 4~0430~ 7~05680~ 9~07122~ 14~03212~, 18~07969~ 19~03117~ 20~01870~ 23~04057~, 25~02076~ 28~03068~ 30~0430~; 33~06293~ 37~01698~, 41~02719~.'),
  (8234, 10, 8, 18, 'And Benaiah the son of Jehoiada was over both the Cherethites and the Pelethites; and David''s sons were chief rulers.', '1~01141~ 3~01121~ 5~03077~ [6 7] 10~03774~ 13~06432~; 15~01732~ 16~01121~ 19~03548~.'),
  (27979, 45, 2, 1, 'Therefore thou art inexcusable, O man, whosoever thou art that judgest: for wherein thou judgest another, thou condemnest thyself; for thou that judgest doest the same things.', '&para; 0~1352~ 2~1488~ 3~379~, 4~5599~ 5~444~, 6~3956~ 10~2919~: 11~1063~ 12~3739~ 13~1722~ 14~2919~ 15~2087~, 17~2632~ 18~4572~; 19~1063~ 22~2919~ 23~4238~ 26~846~.'),
  (15330, 19, 88, 13, 'But unto thee have I cried, O LORD; and in the morning shall my prayer prevent thee.', '5~07768~, 7~03068~; 11~01242~ 14~08605~ 15~06923~'),
  (19508, 24, 23, 15, 'Therefore thus saith the LORD of hosts concerning the prophets; Behold, I will feed them with wormwood, and make them drink the water of gall: for from the prophets of Jerusalem is profaneness gone forth into all the land.', '2~0559~ 4~03068~ 6~06635~ 9~05030~; 13~0398~ 16~03939~, 20~08248~ 22~04325~ 24~07219~: 28~05030~ 30~03389~ 32~02613~ 34~03318~ 38~0776~.'),
  (8536, 10, 19, 17, 'And there were a thousand men of Benjamin with him, and Ziba the servant of the house of Saul, and his fifteen sons and his twenty servants with him; and they went over Jordan before the king.', '[1 2] 4~0505~ 5~0376~ 7~01145~ 11~06717~ 13~05288~ 16~01004~ 18~07586~, 21~06240~ 22~02568~* 23~01121~ 26~06242~ 27~05650~ 33~06743~ 34~03383~ 35~06440~ 37~04428~.'),
  (26871, 43, 19, 31, 'The Jews therefore, because it was the preparation, that the bodies should not remain upon the cross on the sabbath day, (for that sabbath day was an high day,) besought Pilate that their legs might be broken, and that they might be taken away.', '&para; 1~2453~ 2~3767~, 3~1893~ 5~2258~ 7~3904~, 8~3363~ 10~4983~ 11~3306~ 12~3363~ 13~3306~ 14~1909~ 16~4716~ 17~1722~ 20~4521~, 21~1063~* 23~1565~ 25~4521~ 26~2258~ 28~3173~ 29~2250~,) 30~2065~ 31~4091~ 32~2443~ 33~846~ 34~4628~ 37~2608~, 38~2532~ [39] 44~142~.'),
  (9302, 11, 16, 11, 'And it came to pass, when he began to reign, as soon as he sat on his throne, that he slew all the house of Baasha: he left him not one that pisseth against a wall, neither of his kinsfolks, nor of his friends.', '9~04427~, 14~03427~ 17~03678~, [18] 20~05221~ 23~01004~ 25~01201~: 27~07604~ 32~08366~ 35~07023~, 39~01350~, 43~07453~.'),
  (10956, 13, 21, 14, 'So the LORD sent pestilence upon Israel: and there fell of Israel seventy thousand men.', '2~03068~ 3~05414~ 4~01698~ 6~03478~: 9~05307~ 11~03478~ 12~07657~ 13~0505~ 14~0376~.'),
  (19933, 24, 39, 1, 'In the ninth year of Zedekiah king of Judah, in the tenth month, came Nebuchadrezzar king of Babylon and all his army against Jerusalem, and they besieged it.', '&para; 2~08671~ 3~08141~ 5~06667~ 6~04428~ 8~03063~, 11~06224~ 12~02320~, 13~0935~ 14~05019~ 15~04428~ 17~0894~ 21~02428~ 23~03389~, 26~06696~'),
  (23094, 38, 14, 17, 'And it shall be, that whoso will not come up of all the families of the earth unto Jerusalem to worship the King, the LORD of hosts, even upon them shall be no rain.', '[4] 9~05927~ [11] 13~04940~ 16~0776~ 18~03389~ 20~07812~ 22~04428~, 24~03068~ 26~06635~, 33~01653~.'),
  (28588, 46, 10, 5, 'But with many of them God was not well pleased: for they were overthrown in the wilderness.', '0~235~ 1~1722~ 2~4119~ 4~846~ 5~2316~ 6~2106~ 7~3756~ 9~2106~: 10~1063~ 13~2693~ 14~1722~ 16~2048~.'),
  (5068, 5, 5, 9, 'Thou shalt not bow down thyself unto them, nor serve them: for I the LORD thy God am a jealous God, visiting the iniquity of the fathers upon the children unto the third and fourth generation of them that hate me,', '4~07812~ 9~05647~ 14~03068~ 16~0430~ [17] 19~07067~ 20~0410~, 21~06485~ 23~05771~ 26~01~ 29~01121~ 32~08029~ 34~07256~ [35] 39~08130~'),
  (28985, 47, 9, 13, 'Whiles by the experiment of this ministration they glorify God for your professed subjection unto the gospel of Christ, and for your liberal distribution unto them, and unto all men;', '1~1223~ 3~1382~ 5~5026~ 6~1248~ 8~1392~ 9~2316~ 10~1909~ 11~5216~ 12~3671~ 13~5292~ 14~1519~ 16~2098~ 18~5547~, 19~2532~ [21] 22~572~ 23~2842~ 24~1519~ 25~846~, 26~2532~ 27~1519~ 28~3956~ [29]'),
  (17825, 23, 8, 9, 'Associate yourselves, O ye people, and ye shall be broken in pieces; and give ear, all ye of far countries: gird yourselves, and ye shall be broken in pieces; gird yourselves, and ye shall be broken in pieces.', '&para; 0~07489~ 4~05971~, 11~02865~; 14~0238~, 15~03605~ 18~04801~ 19~0776~: 20~0247~ 28~02865~; 29~0247~ 37~02865~.'),
  (10591, 13, 8, 8, 'And Shaharaim begat children in the country of Moab, after he had sent them away; Hushim and Baara were his wives.', '1~07842~ 2~03205~ [3] 6~07704~ 8~04124~, 9~04480~ 14~07971~; 15~02366~ 17~01199~ [18] 20~0802~.'),
  (2315, 2, 28, 17, 'And thou shalt set in it settings of stones, even four rows of stones: the first row shall be a sardius, a topaz, and a carbuncle: this shall be the first row.', '3~04390~ 6~04396~ 8~068~, [9] 10~0702~ 11~02905~ 13~068~: [14 15] 16~02905~ [17 18] 20~0124~, 22~06357~, 25~01304~: [26 28] 30~0259~ 31~02905~.'),
  (8658, 10, 22, 48, 'It is God that avengeth me, and that bringeth down the people under me,', '[1] 2~0410~ 4~05414~ 5~05360~* 10~03381~ 12~05971~'),
  (895, 1, 31, 18, 'And he carried away all his cattle, and all his goods which he had gotten, the cattle of his getting, which he had gotten in Padanaram, for to go to Isaac his father in the land of Canaan.', '3~05090~ 6~04735~, 10~07399~ 14~07408~, 16~04735~ 19~07075~, 23~07408~ 25~06307~, 28~0935~ 30~03327~ 32~01~ 35~0776~ 37~03667~.'),
  (5665, 5, 28, 48, 'Therefore shalt thou serve thine enemies which the LORD shall send against thee, in hunger, and in thirst, and in nakedness, and in want of all things: and he shall put a yoke of iron upon thy neck, until he have destroyed thee.', '3~05647~ 5~0341~ 8~03068~ 10~07971~ 14~07458~, 17~06772~, 20~05903~, 23~02640~ [26] 30~05414~ 32~05923~ 34~01270~ 37~06677~, 41~08045~'),
  (2650, 2, 38, 12, 'And for the west side were hangings of fifty cubits, their pillars ten, and their sockets ten; the hooks of the pillars and their fillets of silver.', '3~03220~ 4~06285~ [5] 6~07050~ 8~02572~ 9~0520~, 11~05982~ 12~06235~, 15~0134~ 16~06235~; 18~02053~ 21~05982~ 24~02838~ [25] 26~03701~.'),
  (26930, 43, 21, 16, 'He saith to him again the second time, Simon, son of Jonas, lovest thou me? He saith unto him, Yea, Lord; thou knowest that I love thee. He saith unto him, Feed my sheep.', '1~3004~ 3~846~ 4~3825~ 7~1208~, 8~4613~, [9] 11~2495~, 13~25~ 14~3165~? 16~3004~ 18~846~, 19~3483~, 20~2962~; 21~4771~ 22~1492~ 23~3754~ 25~5368~ 26~4571~. 28~3004~ 30~846~, 31~4165~ 32~3450~ 33~4263~.'),
  (19734, 24, 31, 34, 'And they shall teach no more every man his neighbour, and every man his brother, saying, Know the LORD: for they shall all know me, from the least of them unto the greatest of them, saith the LORD: for I will forgive their iniquity, and I will remember their sin no more.', '3~03925~ 7~0376~ 9~07453~, 12~0376~ 14~0251~, 15~0559~, 16~03045~ 18~03068~: 23~03045~ 27~06996~ 32~01419~ 35~05002~ 37~03068~: 41~05545~ 43~05771~, 47~02142~ 49~02403~'),
  (12353, 16, 3, 17, 'After him repaired the Levites, Rehum the son of Bani. Next unto him repaired Hashabiah, the ruler of the half part of Keilah, in his part.', '0~0310~ 2~02388~ 4~03881~, 5~07348~ 7~01121~ 9~01137~. 12~03027~ 13~02388~ 14~02811~, 16~08269~ 19~02677~ 20~06418~ 22~07084~, 25~06418~.'),
  (24576, 41, 9, 27, 'But Jesus took him by the hand, and lifted him up; and he arose.', '0~1161~ 1~2424~ 2~2902~ 3~846~ 6~5495~, 8~1453~ 9~846~ 10~1453~; 11~2532~ 13~450~.'),
  (13678, 18, 33, 19, 'He is chastened also with pain upon his bed, and the multitude of his bones with strong pain:', '&para; 2~03198~ 5~04341~ 8~04904~, 11~07230~ 12~07379~* 15~06106~ 17~0386~ [18]'),
  (24036, 40, 25, 18, 'But he that had received one went and digged in the earth, and hid his lord''s money.', '0~1161~ 4~2983~ 5~1520~ 6~565~ 8~3736~ 9~1722~ 11~1093~, 12~2532~ 13~613~ 14~846~ 15~2962~ 16~694~.'),
  (7919, 9, 26, 7, 'So David and Abishai came to the people by night: and, behold, Saul lay sleeping within the trench, and his spear stuck in the ground at his bolster: but Abner and the people lay round about him.', '1~01732~ 3~052~ 4~0935~ 7~05971~ 9~03915~: 12~07586~ 13~07901~ 14~03463~ 17~04570~, 20~02595~ 21~04600~ 24~0776~ 27~04763~: 29~074~ 32~05971~ 33~07901~ 35~05439~'),
  (21, 1, 1, 21, 'And God created great whales, and every living creature that moveth, which the waters brought forth abundantly, after their kind, and every winged fowl after his kind: and God saw that it was good.', '1~0430~ 2~01254~ 3~01419~ 4~08577~, 7~02416~ 8~05315~ 10~07430~, 13~04325~ 16~08317~, 19~04327~, 22~03671~ 23~05775~ 26~04327~: 28~0430~ 29~07200~ [31 32] 33~02896~.'),
  (15470, 19, 95, 7, 'For he is our God; and we are the people of his pasture, and the sheep of his hand. To day if ye will hear his voice,', '&para; [2] 4~0430~; [7] 9~05971~ 12~04830~, 15~06629~ 18~03027~. 20~03117~ 24~08085~ 26~06963~,'),
  (28307, 45, 14, 11, 'For it is written, As I live, saith the Lord, every knee shall bow to me, and every tongue shall confess to God.', '0~1063~ 3~1125~, [4] 5~1473~ 6~2198~, 7~3004~ 9~2962~ 10~3754~,* 11~3956~ 12~1119~ 14~2578~ 16~1698~, 17~2532~ 18~3956~ 19~1100~ 21~1843~ 23~2316~.'),
  (9690, 12, 6, 8, 'Then the king of Syria warred against Israel, and took counsel with his servants, saying, In such and such a place shall be my camp.', '&para; 2~04428~ 4~0758~ 5~03898~ 7~03478~, 10~03289~ 13~05650~, 14~0559~, 16~06423~ 18~0492~ 20~04725~ [21 22] 24~08466~.'),
  (28676, 46, 12, 26, 'And whether one member suffer, all the members suffer with it; or one member be honoured, all the members rejoice with it.', '0~2532~ 1~1535~ 2~1520~ 3~3196~ 4~3958~, 5~3956~ 7~3196~ 10~4841~; 11~1535~ 12~1520~ 13~3196~ 15~1392~, 16~3956~ 18~3196~ 21~4796~.'),
  (13127, 18, 11, 10, 'If he cut off, and shut up, or gather together, then who can hinder him?', '3~02498~, 6~05462~, 9~06950~, 13~07725~'),
  (5813, 5, 32, 49, 'Get thee up into this mountain Abarim, unto mount Nebo, which is in the land of Moab, that is over against Jericho; and behold the land of Canaan, which I give unto the children of Israel for a possession:', '2~05927~ 5~02022~ 6~05682~, [7] 8~02022~ 9~05015~, [11] 14~0776~ 16~04124~, [18] 20~06440~ 21~03405~; 23~07200~ 25~0776~ 27~03667~, 30~05414~ 33~01121~ 35~03478~ 38~0272~:'),
  (10854, 13, 16, 26, 'For all the gods of the people are idols: but the LORD made the heavens.', '3~0430~ 6~05971~ [7] 8~0457~: 11~03068~ 12~06213~ 14~08064~.'),
  (29025, 47, 11, 20, 'For ye suffer, if a man bring you into bondage, if a man devour you, if a man take of you, if a man exalt himself, if a man smite you on the face.', '0~1063~ 2~430~, 5~1536~ 6~2615~ 7~5209~ 9~2615~, 12~1536~ 13~2719~ [14] 17~1536~ 18~2983~ [19 20] 23~1536~ 25~1869~, 28~1536~ 29~1194~ 30~5209~ 31~1519~ 33~4383~.'),
  (20432, 25, 4, 3, 'Even the sea monsters draw out the breast, they give suck to their young ones: the daughter of my people is become cruel, like the ostriches in the wilderness.', '3~08577~ 5~02502~ 7~07699~, 10~03243~ 14~01482~: 16~01323~ 19~05971~ [20 21] 22~0393~, 25~03283~ 28~04057~.'),
  (5224, 5, 11, 10, 'For the land, whither thou goest in to possess it, is not as the land of Egypt, from whence ye came out, where thou sowedst thy seed, and wateredst it with thy foot, as a garden of herbs:', '2~0776~, 6~0935~ 8~03423~ [10] 14~0776~ 16~04714~, 21~03318~, 24~02232~ 26~02233~, 28~08248~ [29] 32~07272~, 35~01588~ 37~03419~:'),
  (26256, 43, 5, 31, 'If I bear witness of myself, my witness is not true.', '&para; 0~1437~ 1~1473~ 3~3140~ 4~4012~ 5~1683~, 6~3450~ 7~3141~ 8~2076~ 9~3756~ 10~227~.'),
  (17435, 21, 6, 9, 'Better is the sight of the eyes than the wandering of the desire: this is also vanity and vexation of spirit.', '0~02896~ [1] 3~04758~ 6~05869~ 9~01980~ 12~05315~: [14] 16~01892~ 18~07469~ 20~07307~.'),
  (873, 1, 30, 39, 'And the flocks conceived before the rods, and brought forth cattle ringstreaked, speckled, and spotted.', '2~06629~ 3~03179~ 6~04731~, 9~03205~ 10~06629~ 11~06124~, 12~05348~, 14~02921~.'),
  (20461, 25, 5, 10, 'Our skin was black like an oven because of the terrible famine.', '1~05785~ 3~03648~ 6~08574~ 7~06440~ 10~02152~ 11~07458~.'),
  (27417, 44, 13, 39, 'And by him all that believe are justified from all things, from which ye could not be justified by the law of Moses.', '0~2532~ 1~1722~ 2~5129~ 3~3956~ 5~4100~ 7~1344~ 8~575~ 10~3956~, 12~3739~ 14~1410~ 15~3756~ 17~1344~ 18~1722~ 20~3551~ 22~3475~.'),
  (21578, 26, 42, 17, 'He measured the north side, five hundred reeds, with the measuring reed round about.', '1~04058~ 3~06828~ 4~07307~, 5~02568~ 6~03967~ 7~07070~, 10~04060~ 11~07070~ 13~05439~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (17437, 21, 6, 11, 'Seeing there be many things that increase vanity, what is man the better?', '&para; 2~03426~ 3~07235~ 4~01697~ 6~07235~ 7~01892~, [9] 10~0120~ 12~03148~?'),
  (23217, 40, 3, 15, 'And Jesus answering said unto him, Suffer it to be so now: for thus it becometh us to fulfil all righteousness. Then he suffered him.', '0~1161~ 1~2424~ 2~611~ 3~2036~ 4~4314~ 5~846~, 6~863~ [7 10] 11~737~: 12~1063~ 13~3779~ 15~4241~ 16~2076~* 17~2254~ 19~4137~ 20~3956~ 21~1343~. 22~5119~ 24~863~ 25~846~.'),
  (27169, 44, 7, 37, 'This is that Moses, which said unto the children of Israel, A prophet shall the Lord your God raise up unto you of your brethren, like unto me; him shall ye hear.', '0~3778~ 1~2076~ 3~3475~, 4~3588~ 5~2036~ 8~5207~ 10~2474~, 12~4396~ 13~450~ 15~2962~ 16~5216~ 17~2316~ 19~450~ 21~5213~ 22~1537~ 23~5216~ 24~80~, 25~5613~ 27~1691~; 28~846~ 31~191~.'),
  (11728, 14, 25, 15, 'Wherefore the anger of the LORD was kindled against Amaziah, and he sent unto him a prophet, which said unto him, Why hast thou sought after the gods of the people, which could not deliver their own people out of thine hand?', '2~0639~ 5~03068~ 7~02734~ 9~0558~, 12~07971~ 16~05030~, 18~0559~ 24~01875~ 27~0430~ 30~05971~, 34~05337~ 37~05971~ 41~03027~?'),
  (16678, 20, 10, 13, 'In the lips of him that hath understanding wisdom is found: but a rod is for the back of him that is void of understanding.', '&para; 2~08193~ 7~0995~ 8~02451~ 10~04672~: 13~07626~ [14] 17~01460~ 22~02638~ 24~03820~.'),
  (20725, 26, 13, 8, 'Therefore thus saith the Lord GOD; Because ye have spoken vanity, and seen lies, therefore, behold, I am against you, saith the Lord GOD.', '2~0559~ 4~0136~ 5~03069~; 9~01696~ 10~07723~, 12~02372~ 13~03577~, [17] 20~05002~ 22~0136~ 23~03069~.'),
  (30316, 59, 2, 7, 'Do not they blaspheme that worthy name by the which ye are called?', '0~987~ 1~3756~ 2~846~ 3~987~ 5~2570~ 6~3686~ 7~1909~ 10~5209~ 12~1941~?'),
  (7600, 9, 15, 33, 'And Samuel said, As thy sword hath made women childless, so shall thy mother be childless among women. And Samuel hewed Agag in pieces before the LORD in Gilgal.', '1~08050~ 2~0559~, 5~02719~ 8~0802~ 9~07921~, 13~0517~ 15~07921~ 17~0802~. 19~08050~ 20~08158~ 21~090~ 23~08158~ 24~06440~ 26~03068~ 28~01537~.'),
  (26451, 43, 8, 55, 'Yet ye have not known him; but I know him: and if I should say, I know him not, I shall be a liar like unto you: but I know him, and keep his saying.', '0~2532~ 2~1097~ 3~3756~ 4~1097~ 5~846~; 6~1161~ 7~1473~ 8~1492~ 9~846~: 10~2532~ 11~1437~ 14~2036~ 15~3754~,* 17~1492~ 18~846~ 19~3756~, 22~2071~ 24~5583~ 25~3664~ 27~5216~: 28~235~ 30~1492~ 31~846~, 32~2532~ 33~5083~ 34~846~ 35~3056~.'),
  (22379, 30, 1, 6, 'Thus saith the LORD; For three transgressions of Gaza, and for four, I will not turn away the punishment thereof; because they carried away captive the whole captivity, to deliver them up to Edom:', '1~0559~ 3~03068~; 5~07969~ 6~06588~ 8~05804~, 11~0702~, 16~07725~ [17 18] 24~01540~ 26~08003~ 27~01546~, [30] 31~05462~ 33~0123~:'),
  (4109, 4, 13, 29, 'The Amalekites dwell in the land of the south: and the Hittites, and the Jebusites, and the Amorites, dwell in the mountains: and the Canaanites dwell by the sea, and by the coast of Jordan.', '1~06002~ 2~03427~ 5~0776~ 8~05045~: 11~02850~, 14~02983~, 17~0567~, 18~03427~ 21~02022~: 24~03669~ 25~03427~ 28~03220~, 32~03027~ 34~03383~.'),
  (5737, 5, 31, 3, 'The LORD thy God, he will go over before thee, and he will destroy these nations from before thee, and thou shalt possess them: and Joshua, he shall go over before thee, as the LORD hath said.', '1~03068~ 3~0430~, 7~05674~ 8~06440~ [10] 13~08045~ 15~01471~ 17~06440~ 22~03423~ [24] 25~03091~, 29~05674~ 30~06440~ 34~03068~ 36~01696~.'),
  (3098, 3, 13, 41, 'And he that hath his hair fallen off from the part of his head toward his face, he is forehead bald: yet is he clean.', '6~04803~ 10~06285~ 13~07218~ 16~06440~, [18] 20~01371~: [21 22] 24~02889~.'),
  (13548, 18, 29, 7, 'When I went out to the gate through the city, when I prepared my seat in the street!', '&para; 3~03318~ 6~08179~ 9~07176~, [10] 12~03559~ 14~04186~ 17~07339~!'),
  (26756, 43, 16, 15, 'All things that the Father hath are mine: therefore said I, that he shall take of mine, and shall shew it unto you.', '1~3956~ 2~3745~ 4~3962~ 5~2192~ 6~2076~ 7~1699~: 8~1223~ 9~5124~ 10~2036~, 11~3754~ 14~2983~ 15~1537~ 16~1699~, 17~2532~ 19~312~ [20] 22~5213~.'),
  (25323, 42, 9, 10, 'And the apostles, when they were returned, told him all that they had done. And he took them, and went aside privately into a desert place belonging to the city called Bethsaida.', '&para; 0~2532~ 2~652~, 6~5290~, 7~1334~ 8~846~ 10~3745~ 13~4160~. 14~2532~ 16~3880~ 17~846~, 20~5298~ 21~2398~ 22~2596~* 23~1519~ 25~2048~ 26~5117~ 30~4172~ 31~2564~ 32~966~.'),
  (5089, 5, 5, 30, 'Go say to them, Get you into your tents again.', '0~03212~ 1~0559~ 4~07725~ 8~0168~ 9~07725~.'),
  (6170, 6, 13, 10, 'And all the cities of Sihon king of the Amorites, which reigned in Heshbon, unto the border of the children of Ammon;', '3~05892~ 5~05511~ 6~04428~ 9~0567~, 11~04427~ 13~02809~, 16~01366~ 19~01121~ 21~05983~;'),
  (30835, 66, 7, 9, 'After this I beheld, and, lo, a great multitude, which no man could number, of all nations, and kindreds, and people, and tongues, stood before the throne, and before the Lamb, clothed with white robes, and palms in their hands;', '0~3326~ 1~5023~ 3~1492~, 4~2532~, 5~2400~, 7~4183~ 8~3793~, 9~3739~ 11~3762~ 12~1410~ 13~705~ 14~846~,* 15~1537~ 16~3956~ 17~1484~, 18~2532~ 19~5443~, 20~2532~ 21~2992~, 22~2532~ 23~1100~, 24~2476~ 25~1799~ 27~2362~, 28~2532~ 29~1799~ 31~721~, 32~4016~ 34~3022~ 35~4749~, 36~2532~ 37~5404~ 38~1722~ 39~846~ 40~5495~;'),
  (12079, 15, 2, 43, 'The Nethinims: the children of Ziha, the children of Hasupha, the children of Tabbaoth,', '1~05411~: 3~01121~ 5~06727~, 7~01121~ 9~02817~, 11~01121~ 13~02884~,'),
  (20912, 26, 20, 8, 'But they rebelled against me, and would not hearken unto me: they did not every man cast away the abominations of their eyes, neither did they forsake the idols of Egypt: then I said, I will pour out my fury upon them, to accomplish my anger against them in the midst of the land of Egypt.', '2~04784~ 6~014~ 8~08085~ 15~0376~ 17~07993~ 19~08251~ 22~05869~, 26~05800~ 28~01544~ 30~04714~: 33~0559~, 37~08210~ 39~02534~ 43~03615~ 45~0639~ 50~08432~ 53~0776~ 55~04714~.'),
  (2065, 2, 20, 9, 'Six days shalt thou labour, and do all thy work:', '0~08337~ 1~03117~ 4~05647~, 6~06213~ 9~04399~:'),
  (27343, 44, 11, 20, 'And some of them were men of Cyprus and Cyrene, which, when they were come to Antioch, spake unto the Grecians, preaching the Lord Jesus.', '0~1161~ 1~5100~ 2~1537~ 3~846~ 4~2258~ 5~435~ 7~2953~ 8~2532~ 9~2956~, 10~3748~, 14~1525~ 15~1519~ 16~490~, 17~2980~ 18~4314~ 20~1675~, 21~2097~ 23~2962~ 24~2424~.'),
  (25755, 42, 19, 10, 'For the Son of man is come to seek and to save that which was lost.', '0~1063~ 2~5207~ 4~444~ 6~2064~ 8~2212~ 9~2532~ 11~4982~ 15~622~.'),
  (14386, 19, 33, 11, 'The counsel of the LORD standeth for ever, the thoughts of his heart to all generations.', '1~06098~ 4~03068~ 5~05975~ 7~05769~, 9~04284~ 12~03820~ 14~01755~ 15~01755~.'),
  (22315, 29, 1, 15, 'Alas for the day! for the day of the LORD is at hand, and as a destruction from the Almighty shall it come.', '0~0162~ 3~03117~! 6~03117~ 9~03068~ [10] 12~07138~, 16~07701~ 19~07706~ 22~0935~.'),
  (11156, 13, 28, 5, 'And of all my sons, (for the LORD hath given me many sons,) he hath chosen Solomon my son to sit upon the throne of the kingdom of the LORD over Israel.', '4~01121~, 7~03068~ 9~05414~ 11~07227~ 12~01121~,) 15~0977~ 16~08010~ 18~01121~ 20~03427~ 23~03678~ 26~04438~ 29~03068~ 31~03478~.'),
  (29796, 54, 5, 17, 'Let the elders that rule well be counted worthy of double honour, especially they who labour in the word and doctrine.', '&para; 0~515~ 2~4245~ 4~4291~ 5~2573~ 8~515~ 10~1362~ 11~5092~, 12~3122~ 15~2872~ 16~1722~ 18~3056~ 19~2532~ 20~1319~.'),
  (1451, 1, 47, 26, 'And Joseph made it a law over the land of Egypt unto this day, that Pharaoh should have the fifth part; except the land of the priests only, which became not Pharaoh''s.', '1~03130~ 2~07760~ 5~02706~ 8~0127~ 10~04714~ 13~03117~, [14] 15~06547~ 19~02569~ [20] 21~07535~ 23~0127~ 26~03548~ [28] 31~06547~.'),
  (20735, 26, 13, 18, 'And say, Thus saith the Lord GOD; Woe to the women that sew pillows to all armholes, and make kerchiefs upon the head of every stature to hunt souls! Will ye hunt the souls of my people, and will ye save the souls alive that come unto you?', '1~0559~, 3~0559~ 5~0136~ 6~03069~; 7~01945~ [10] 12~08609~ 13~03704~ 16~03027~ 17~0679~,* 19~06213~ 20~04555~ 23~07218~ 26~06967~ 28~06679~ 29~05315~! 32~06679~ 34~05315~ 37~05971~, 41~02421~ 43~05315~ 44~02421~ [45 46]'),
  (27759, 44, 23, 9, 'And there arose a great cry: and the scribes that were of the Pharisees'' part arose, and strove, saying, We find no evil in this man: but if a spirit or an angel hath spoken to him, let us not fight against God.', '0~1161~ 2~1096~ 4~3173~ 5~2906~: 6~2532~ 8~1122~ [9 10] 13~5330~ 14~3313~ 15~450~, 17~1264~, 18~3004~, 20~2147~ 21~3762~ 22~2556~ 23~1722~ 24~5129~ 25~444~: 26~1161~ 27~1487~ 29~4151~ 30~2228~ 32~32~ 34~2980~ 36~846~, 38~2313~ 39~3361~ 40~2313~'),
  (22416, 30, 3, 12, 'Thus saith the LORD; As the shepherd taketh out of the mouth of the lion two legs, or a piece of an ear; so shall the children of Israel be taken out that dwell in Samaria in the corner of a bed, and in Damascus in a couch.', '1~0559~ 3~03068~; 6~07462~ 8~05337~ 11~06310~ 14~0738~ 15~08147~ 16~03767~, 19~0915~ 22~0241~; 26~01121~ 28~03478~ 31~05337~ 33~03427~ 35~08111~ 38~06285~ 41~04296~, 44~01833~ [45] 47~06210~.'),
  (28748, 46, 15, 14, 'And if Christ be not risen, then is our preaching vain, and your faith is also vain.', '0~1161~ 1~1487~ 2~5547~ 3~1453~ 4~3756~ 5~1453~, 6~686~ [7] 8~2257~ 9~2782~ 10~2756~, 11~2532~ 12~5216~ 13~4102~ [14] 14~1161~ 15~2532~ 16~2756~.'),
  (23625, 40, 14, 18, 'He said, Bring them hither to me.', '0~1161~ 1~2036~, 2~5342~ 3~846~ 4~5602~ 6~3427~.'),
  (365, 1, 15, 1, 'After these things the word of the LORD came unto Abram in a vision, saying, Fear not, Abram: I am thy shield, and thy exceeding great reward.', '&para; 0~0310~ 2~01697~ 4~01697~ 7~03068~ 8~01961~ 10~087~ 13~04236~, 14~0559~, 15~03372~ 17~087~: [19] 21~04043~, [22] 24~03966~ 25~07235~ 26~07939~.'),
  (6926, 7, 14, 10, 'So his father went down unto the woman: and Samson made there a feast; for so used the young men to do.', '&para; 2~01~ 4~03381~ 7~0802~: 9~08123~ 10~06213~ 13~04960~; 19~0970~ 21~06213~.'),
  (8803, 11, 2, 25, 'And king Solomon sent by the hand of Benaiah the son of Jehoiada; and he fell upon him that he died.', '1~04428~ 2~08010~ 3~07971~ 6~03027~ 8~01141~ 10~01121~ 12~03077~; 15~06293~ 20~04191~.'),
  (16877, 20, 16, 28, 'A froward man soweth strife: and a whisperer separateth chief friends.', '1~08419~ 2~0376~ 3~07971~ 4~04066~: 7~05372~ 8~06504~ 10~0441~.'),
  (14139, 19, 18, 12, 'At the brightness that was before him his thick clouds passed, hail stones and coals of fire.', '2~05051~ [3 4] 9~05645~ 10~05674~, 11~01259~ [12] 14~01513~ 16~0784~.'),
  (8058, 10, 2, 2, 'So David went up thither, and his two wives also, Ahinoam the Jezreelitess, and Abigail Nabal''s wife the Carmelite.', '1~01732~ 3~05927~ 7~08147~ 8~0802~ 10~0293~ 12~03159~, 14~026~ 15~05037~ 16~0802~ 18~03761~.'),
  (2498, 2, 33, 20, 'And he said, Thou canst not see my face: for there shall no man see me, and live.', '2~0559~, 4~03201~ 6~07200~ 8~06440~: 13~0120~ 14~07200~ 17~02425~.'),
  (21341, 26, 34, 19, 'And as for my flock, they eat that which ye have trodden with your feet; and they drink that which ye have fouled with your feet.', '[1 2] 4~06629~, 6~07462~ 11~04823~ 14~07272~; 17~08354~ 22~04833~ 25~07272~.'),
  (10505, 13, 6, 43, 'The son of Jahath, the son of Gershom, the son of Levi.', '1~01121~ 3~03189~, 5~01121~ 7~01647~, 9~01121~ 11~03878~.'),
  (488, 1, 19, 27, 'And Abraham gat up early in the morning to the place where he stood before the LORD:', '&para; 1~085~ 4~07925~ 7~01242~ 10~04725~ 13~05975~ 14~06440~ 16~03068~:'),
  (23630, 40, 14, 23, 'And when he had sent the multitudes away, he went up into a mountain apart to pray: and when the evening was come, he was there alone.', '0~2532~ 4~630~ 6~3793~ 7~630~, 10~305~ 11~1519~ 13~3735~ 14~2398~ 15~2596~ 16~4336~: 17~1161~ 20~3798~ 22~1096~, 24~2258~ 25~1563~ 26~3441~.'),
  (16787, 20, 14, 6, 'A scorner seeketh wisdom, and findeth it not: but knowledge is easy unto him that understandeth.', '&para; 1~03887~ 2~01245~ 3~02451~, [5 6] 9~01847~ [10] 11~07043~ 15~0995~.'),
  (3919, 4, 7, 64, 'One kid of the goats for a sin offering:', '0~0259~ 1~08163~ 4~05795~ 8~02403~:'),
  (25364, 42, 9, 51, 'And it came to pass, when the time was come that he should be received up, he stedfastly set his face to go to Jerusalem,', '&para; 0~1161~ 4~1096~, 5~1722~ 7~2250~ 9~4845~ 11~846~ 15~354~ 16~2532~,* 17~846~ 19~4741~ 20~846~ 21~4383~ 23~4198~ 24~1519~ 25~2419~,'),
  (4214, 4, 16, 15, 'And Moses was very wroth, and said unto the LORD, Respect not thou their offering: I have not taken one ass from them, neither have I hurt one of them.', '1~04872~ 3~03966~ 4~02734~, 6~0559~ 9~03068~, 10~06437~ 14~04503~: 18~05375~ 19~0259~ 20~02543~ 26~07489~ 27~0259~'),
  (24858, 41, 15, 21, 'And they compel one Simon a Cyrenian, who passed by, coming out of the country, the father of Alexander and Rufus, to bear his cross.', '0~2532~ 2~29~ 3~5100~ 4~4613~ 6~2956~, 9~3855~, 10~2064~ 12~575~ 14~68~, 16~3962~ 18~223~ 19~2532~ 20~4504~, 21~2443~ 22~142~ 23~846~ 24~4716~.'),
  (9014, 11, 8, 21, 'And I have set there a place for the ark, wherein is the covenant of the LORD, which he made with our fathers, when he brought them out of the land of Egypt.', '3~07760~ 6~04725~ 9~0727~, [11] 13~01285~ 16~03068~, 19~03772~ 22~01~, 27~03318~ 30~0776~ 32~04714~.'),
  (28536, 46, 7, 33, 'But he that is married careth for the things that are of the world, how he may please his wife.', '0~1161~ 4~1060~ 5~3309~ 10~3588~ 13~2889~, 14~4459~ 17~700~ [18] 19~1135~.'),
  (30080, 58, 6, 20, 'Whither the forerunner is for us entered, even Jesus, made an high priest for ever after the order of Melchisedec.', '0~3699~ 2~4274~ 3~1525~ 4~5228~ 5~2257~ 6~1525~, [7] 8~2424~, 9~1096~ 12~749~ 13~1519~ 14~165~ 15~2596~ 17~5010~ 19~3198~.'),
  (23924, 40, 22, 42, 'Saying, What think ye of Christ? whose son is he? They say unto him, The son of David.', '0~3004~, 1~5101~ 2~1380~ 3~5213~ 4~4012~ 5~5547~? 6~5101~ 7~5207~ 9~2076~? 11~3004~ 13~846~, [14 15] 17~1138~.'),
  (22904, 38, 1, 17, 'Cry yet, saying, Thus saith the LORD of hosts; My cities through prosperity shall yet be spread abroad; and the LORD shall yet comfort Zion, and shall yet choose Jerusalem.', '0~07121~ 2~0559~, 4~0559~ 6~03068~ 8~06635~; 10~05892~ 12~02896~ 17~06327~; 20~03068~ 23~05162~ 24~06726~, 28~0977~ 29~03389~.'),
  (15312, 19, 87, 2, 'The LORD loveth the gates of Zion more than all the dwellings of Jacob.', '1~03068~ 2~0157~ 4~08179~ 6~06726~ 11~04908~ 13~03290~.'),
  (29051, 47, 12, 13, 'For what is it wherein ye were inferior to other churches, except it be that I myself was not burdensome to you? forgive me this wrong.', '0~1063~ 1~5101~ 3~2076~ 4~3739~ 7~2274~ 8~5228~ 9~3062~ 10~1577~, 11~1508~ [12 13] 14~3754~ 15~1473~ 16~846~ 17~2655~ 18~3756~ 19~2655~ 21~5216~? 22~5483~ 23~3427~ 24~5026~ 25~93~.'),
  (5504, 5, 22, 28, 'If a man find a damsel that is a virgin, which is not betrothed, and lay hold on her, and lie with her, and they be found;', '2~0376~ 3~04672~ 5~05291~ [6 7] 9~01330~, 13~0781~, 16~08610~ 20~07901~ 26~04672~;'),
  (29837, 55, 1, 12, 'For the which cause I also suffer these things: nevertheless I am not ashamed: for I know whom I have believed, and am persuaded that he is able to keep that which I have committed unto him against that day.', '0~1223~ 2~3739~ 3~156~ 4~3958~ 5~2532~ 6~3958~ 8~5023~: 9~235~ 11~1870~ 12~3756~ 13~1870~: 14~1063~ 16~1492~ 17~3739~ 20~4100~, 21~2532~ 23~3982~ 24~3754~ 26~2076~ 27~1415~ 29~5442~ 32~3450~ 36~3866~ 37~1519~ 38~1565~ 39~2250~.'),
  (13846, 18, 39, 3, 'They bow themselves, they bring forth their young ones, they cast out their sorrows.', '1~03766~ 5~06398~ 8~03206~, 11~07971~ 13~02256~.'),
  (26037, 42, 24, 32, 'And they said one to another, Did not our heart burn within us, while he talked with us by the way, and while he opened to us the scriptures?', '0~2532~ 2~2036~ 5~240~ 6~4314~,* 7~2258~ 8~3780~ 9~2257~ 10~2588~ 11~2545~ 12~1722~ 13~2254~, 14~5613~ 16~2980~ 18~2254~ 19~1722~ 21~3598~, 22~2532~ 23~5613~ 25~1272~ 27~2254~ 29~1124~?'),
  (18152, 23, 26, 13, 'O LORD our God, other lords beside thee have had dominion over us: but by thee only will we make mention of thy name.', '1~03068~ 3~0430~, [4] 5~0113~ 6~02108~ 10~01166~ [13] 20~02142~ 23~08034~.'),
  (23523, 40, 12, 24, 'But when the Pharisees heard it, they said, This fellow doth not cast out devils, but by Beelzebub the prince of the devils.', '0~1161~ 3~5330~ 4~191~ [5] 7~2036~, 8~3778~ [9] 10~1544~ 11~3756~ 13~1544~ 14~1140~, 15~1508~ 16~1722~ 17~954~ 19~758~ 22~1140~.'),
  (4102, 4, 13, 22, 'And they ascended by the south, and came unto Hebron; where Ahiman, Sheshai, and Talmai, the children of Anak, were. (Now Hebron was built seven years before Zoan in Egypt.)', '2~05927~ 5~05045~, 7~0935~ 9~02275~; 11~0289~, 12~08344~, 14~08526~, 16~03211~ 18~06061~, [19] 21~02275~ 23~01129~ 24~07651~ 25~08141~ 26~06440~ 27~06814~ 29~04714~)'),
  (18971, 24, 1, 16, 'And I will utter my judgments against them touching all their wickedness, who have forsaken me, and have burned incense unto other gods, and worshipped the works of their own hands.', '3~01696~ 5~04941~ 8~05921~ 11~07451~, 14~05800~ 19~06999~ 21~0312~ 22~0430~, 24~07812~ 26~04639~ 30~03027~.'),
  (9834, 12, 10, 33, 'From Jordan eastward, all the land of Gilead, the Gadites, and the Reubenites, and the Manassites, from Aroer, which is by the river Arnon, even Gilead and Bashan.', '1~03383~ 2~08121~ 3~04217~,* 6~0776~ 8~01568~, 10~01425~, 13~07206~, 16~04520~, 18~06177~, [20] 23~05158~ 24~0769~, 26~01568~ 28~01316~.'),
  (657, 1, 24, 62, 'And Isaac came from the way of the well Lahairoi; for he dwelt in the south country.', '&para; 1~03327~ 2~0935~ 5~0935~ 9~0883~; 12~03427~ 15~05045~ 16~0776~.'),
  (15503, 19, 98, 4, 'Make a joyful noise unto the LORD, all the earth: make a loud noise, and rejoice, and sing praise.', '&para; 3~07321~ 6~03068~, 9~0776~: 13~06476~, 15~07442~, 17~02167~'),
  (3245, 3, 17, 5, 'To the end that the children of Israel may bring their sacrifices, which they offer in the open field, even that they may bring them unto the LORD, unto the door of the tabernacle of the congregation, unto the priest, and offer them for peace offerings unto the LORD.', '5~01121~ 7~03478~ 9~0935~ 11~02077~, 14~02076~ 17~06440~ 18~07704~, 23~0935~ 27~03068~, 30~06607~ 33~0168~ 36~04150~, 39~03548~, 41~02076~ [43] 44~08002~ 45~02077~ 48~03068~.'),
  (10998, 13, 23, 7, 'Of the Gershonites were, Laadan, and Shimei.', '2~01649~ [3] 4~03936~, 6~08096~.'),
  (30510, 61, 1, 15, 'Moreover I will endeavour that ye may be able after my decease to have these things always in remembrance.', '0~2532~ 1~1161~ 3~4704~ 5~5209~ 8~2192~ 9~3326~ 10~1699~ 11~1841~ 13~4160~ 15~5130~ 16~1539~ 18~3420~.'),
  (30661, 62, 5, 21, 'Little children, keep yourselves from idols. Amen.', '1~5040~, 2~5442~ 3~1438~ 4~575~ 5~1497~. 6~281~.'),
  (2956, 3, 8, 34, 'As he hath done this day, so the LORD hath commanded to do, to make an atonement for you.', '3~06213~ 5~03117~, [6] 8~03068~ 10~06680~ 12~06213~, 16~03722~'),
  (10748, 13, 12, 20, 'As he went to Ziklag, there fell to him of Manasseh, Adnah, and Jozabad, and Jediael, and Michael, and Jozabad, and Elihu, and Zilthai, captains of the thousands that were of Manasseh.', '2~03212~ 4~06860~, 6~05307~ 10~04519~, 11~05734~, 13~03107~, 15~03043~, 17~04317~, 19~03107~, 21~0453~, 23~06769~, 24~07218~ 27~0505~ [29] 31~04519~.'),
  (25607, 42, 15, 6, 'And when he cometh home, he calleth together his friends and neighbours, saying unto them, Rejoice with me; for I have found my sheep which was lost.', '0~2532~ 3~2064~ 4~1519~* 5~3624~, 8~4779~ [9] 10~5384~ 11~2532~ 12~1069~, 13~3004~ 15~846~, 16~4796~ 18~3427~; 19~3754~ 22~2147~ 23~3450~ 24~4263~ 25~3588~ 27~622~.'),
  (28632, 46, 11, 16, 'But if any man seem to be contentious, we have no such custom, neither the churches of God.', '0~1161~ 3~1536~ 4~1380~ 6~1511~ 7~5380~, 8~2249~ 9~2192~ 10~3756~ 11~5108~ 12~4914~, 13~3761~ 15~1577~ 17~2316~.'),
  (3790, 4, 4, 42, 'And those that were numbered of the families of the sons of Merari, throughout their families, by the house of their fathers,', '4~06485~ 7~04940~ 10~01121~ 12~04847~, 15~04940~, 18~01004~ 21~01~,'),
  (14126, 19, 17, 14, 'From men which are thy hand, O LORD, from men of the world, which have their portion in this life, and whose belly thou fillest with thy hid treasure: they are full of children, and leave the rest of their substance to their babes.', '1~04962~ [2 3] 5~03027~, 7~03068~, 9~04962~ 12~02465~, [13 14] 16~02506~ [18] 19~02416~, 22~0990~ 24~04390~ 27~06840~ [28] 31~07646~ 33~01121~, 35~03240~ 37~03499~ [40] 43~05768~.'),
  (20637, 26, 9, 6, 'Slay utterly old and young, both maids, and little children, and women: but come not near any man upon whom is the mark; and begin at my sanctuary. Then they began at the ancient men which were before the house.', '0~02026~ 1~04889~ 2~02205~ [3] 4~0970~, 6~01330~, 9~02945~, 11~0802~: 15~05066~ 17~0376~ [20] 22~08420~; 24~02490~ 27~04720~. 30~02490~ 33~02205~ 34~0582~ [36] 37~06440~ 39~01004~.'),
  (9582, 12, 2, 23, 'And he went up from thence unto Bethel: and as he was going up by the way, there came forth little children out of the city, and mocked him, and said unto him, Go up, thou bald head; go up, thou bald head.', '3~05927~ 7~01008~: 13~05927~ 16~01870~, 19~03318~ 20~06996~ 21~05288~ 25~05892~, 27~07046~ 30~0559~ 34~05927~, 37~07142~; 39~05927~, 42~07142~.'),
  (4879, 4, 35, 28, 'Because he should have remained in the city of his refuge until the death of the high priest: but after the death of the high priest the slayer shall return into the land of his possession.', '4~03427~ 7~05892~ 10~04733~ 13~04194~ 16~01419~ 17~03548~: 19~0310~ 21~04194~ 24~01419~ 25~03548~ 27~07523~ 29~07725~ 32~0776~ 35~0272~.'),
  (13488, 18, 26, 12, 'He divideth the sea with his power, and by his understanding he smiteth through the proud.', '1~07280~ 3~03220~ 6~03581~, 10~08394~ 11~08394~* 13~04272~ 16~07293~.'),
  (3934, 4, 7, 79, 'His offering was one silver charger, the weight whereof was an hundred and thirty shekels, one silver bowl of seventy shekels, after the shekel of the sanctuary; both of them full of fine flour mingled with oil for a meat offering:', '1~07133~ [2] 3~0259~ 4~03701~ 5~07086~, 7~04948~ [9] 11~03967~ 13~07970~ [14] 15~0259~ 16~03701~ 17~04219~ 19~07657~ 20~08255~, 23~08255~ 26~06944~; 27~08147~ 30~04392~ 33~05560~ 34~01101~ 36~08081~ 40~04503~:'),
  (16436, 20, 1, 27, 'When your fear cometh as desolation, and your destruction cometh as a whirlwind; when distress and anguish cometh upon you.', '2~06343~ 3~0935~ 5~07722~ 6~07584~,* 9~0343~ 10~0857~ 13~05492~; 15~06869~ 17~06695~ 18~0935~'),
  (25554, 42, 13, 23, 'Then said one unto him, Lord, are there few that be saved? And he said unto them,', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~2036~ 2~5100~ 3~4314~ 4~846~, 5~2962~, 8~3641~ 9~1487~ 11~4982~? 12~1161~ 14~2036~ 16~846~,'),
  (30374, 59, 5, 4, 'Behold, the hire of the labourers who have reaped down your fields, which is of you kept back by fraud, crieth: and the cries of them which have reaped are entered into the ears of the Lord of sabaoth.', '0~2400~, 2~3408~ 5~2040~ 6~3588~ 9~270~ 10~5216~ 11~5561~, 12~3588~ 14~575~ 15~5216~ 19~650~, 20~2896~: 21~2532~ 23~995~ 28~2325~ 30~1525~ 31~1519~ 33~3775~ 36~2962~ 38~4519~.'),
  (8021, 9, 31, 5, 'And when his armourbearer saw that Saul was dead, he fell likewise upon his sword, and died with him.', '3~05375~ 4~03627~* 5~07200~ 7~07586~ 9~04191~, 11~05307~ 15~02719~, 17~04191~'),
  (25175, 42, 6, 17, 'And he came down with them, and stood in the plain, and the company of his disciples, and a great multitude of people out of all Judaea and Jerusalem, and from the sea coast of Tyre and Sidon, which came to hear him, and to be healed of their diseases;', '0~2532~ 3~2597~ 4~3326~ 5~846~, 7~2476~ 8~1909~ 10~5117~ 11~3977~,* 12~2532~ 14~3793~ 16~846~ 17~3101~, 18~2532~ 20~4183~ 21~4128~ 23~2992~ 25~575~ 26~3956~ 27~2449~ 28~2532~ 29~2419~, 30~2532~ 34~3882~ 36~5184~ 37~2532~ 38~4605~, 39~3739~ 40~2064~ 42~191~ 43~846~, 44~2532~ 47~2390~ 48~575~ 49~846~ 50~3554~;'),
  (7548, 9, 14, 33, 'Then they told Saul, saying, Behold, the people sin against the LORD, in that they eat with the blood. And he said, Ye have transgressed: roll a great stone unto me this day.', '2~05046~ 3~07586~, 4~0559~, 7~05971~ 8~02398~ 11~03068~, 15~0398~ 18~01818~. 21~0559~, 24~0898~: 25~01556~ 27~01419~ 28~068~ 32~03117~.'),
  (19290, 24, 13, 15, 'Hear ye, and give ear; be not proud: for the LORD hath spoken.', '0~08085~ 4~0238~; 7~01361~: 10~03068~ 12~01696~.'),
  (16589, 20, 7, 5, 'That they may keep thee from the strange woman, from the stranger which flattereth with her words.', '3~08104~ 7~02114~ 8~0802~, 11~05237~ [12] 13~02505~ 16~0561~.'),
  (14215, 19, 22, 2, 'O my God, I cry in the daytime, but thou hearest not; and in the night season, and am not silent.', '2~0430~, 4~07121~ 7~03119~, 10~06030~ 16~03915~, 20~01747~.'),
  (24593, 41, 9, 44, 'Where their worm dieth not, and the fire is not quenched.', '0~3699~ 1~846~ 2~4663~ 3~5053~ 4~3756~, 5~2532~ 7~4442~ 8~4570~ 9~3756~ 10~4570~.'),
  (3455, 3, 24, 4, 'He shall order the lamps upon the pure candlestick before the LORD continually.', '2~06186~ 4~05216~ 7~02889~ 8~04501~ 9~06440~ 11~03068~ 12~08548~.'),
  (15596, 19, 104, 16, 'The trees of the LORD are full of sap; the cedars of Lebanon, which he hath planted;', '1~06086~ 4~03068~ 6~07646~ [7 8] 10~0730~ 12~03844~, 16~05193~;'),
  (10468, 13, 6, 6, 'And Uzzi begat Zerahiah, and Zerahiah begat Meraioth,', '1~05813~ 2~03205~ 3~02228~, 5~02228~ 6~03205~ 7~04812~,'),
  (27261, 44, 9, 29, 'And he spake boldly in the name of the Lord Jesus, and disputed against the Grecians: but they went about to slay him.', '0~2532~ 2~2980~ 3~3955~ 4~1722~ 6~3686~ 9~2962~ 10~2424~, 11~2532~ 12~5037~* 13~4802~ 14~4314~ 16~1675~: 17~1161~ 20~2021~ 22~337~ 23~846~.'),
  (5715, 5, 30, 1, 'And it shall come to pass, when all these things are come upon thee, the blessing and the curse, which I have set before thee, and thou shalt call them to mind among all the nations, whither the LORD thy God hath driven thee,', '&para; 9~01697~ 11~0935~ 15~01293~ 18~07045~, 22~05414~ 23~06440~ 28~07725~ [29] 31~03824~ 35~01471~, 38~03068~ 40~0430~ 42~05080~'),
  (25413, 42, 10, 38, 'Now it came to pass, as they went, that he entered into a certain village: and a certain woman named Martha received him into her house.', '&para; 0~1161~ 4~1096~, 5~1722~ 6~846~ 7~4198~, 8~2532~ 9~846~ 10~1525~ 11~1519~ 13~5100~ 14~2968~: 15~1161~ 17~5100~ 18~1135~ 19~3686~ 20~3136~ 21~5264~ 22~846~ 23~1519~ 24~846~ 25~3624~.'),
  (10925, 13, 19, 10, 'Now when Joab saw that the battle was set against him before and behind, he chose out of all the choice of Israel, and put them in array against the Syrians.', '2~03097~ 3~07200~ 6~04421~ 11~06440~ 13~0268~, 16~0977~ 20~0977~ 22~03478~, [25] 27~06186~ 28~07125~ 30~0758~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (15091, 19, 76, 1, 'To the chief Musician on Neginoth, A Psalm or Song of Asaph. In Judah is God known: his name is great in Israel.', '&para; [0 3~05329~ 5~05058~, 7~04210~ [8] 9~07892~ 11] 11~0623~ 13~03063~ [14] 15~0430~ 16~03045~: 18~08034~ [19] 20~01419~ 22~03478~.'),
  (3800, 4, 5, 3, 'Both male and female shall ye put out, without the camp shall ye put them; that they defile not their camps, in the midst whereof I dwell.', '1~02145~ 3~05347~ 7~07971~, 8~02351~ 10~04264~ 13~07971~ 17~02930~ 20~04264~, 23~08432~ 24~0834~ 26~07931~.'),
  (28499, 46, 6, 16, 'What? know ye not that he which is joined to an harlot is one body? for two, saith he, shall be one flesh.', '0~2228~? 2~1492~ 3~3756~ 4~3754~ 8~2853~ 11~4204~ 12~2076~ 13~1520~ 14~4983~? 15~1063~ 16~1417~, 18~5346~, 20~2071~ 21~3391~ 22~1519~* 23~4561~.'),
  (4448, 4, 23, 27, 'And Balak said unto Balaam, Come, I pray thee, I will bring thee unto another place; peradventure it will please God that thou mayest curse me them from thence.', '1~01111~ 2~0559~ 4~01109~, 5~03212~, 11~03947~ 14~0312~ 15~04725~; 19~03474~ 20~05869~* 21~0430~ 25~06895~'),
  (5948, 6, 5, 8, 'And it came to pass, when they had done circumcising all the people, that they abode in their places in the camp, till they were whole.', '8~08552~ 9~04135~ 12~01471~, 15~03427~ 21~04264~, 25~02421~.'),
  (31044, 66, 19, 11, 'And I saw heaven opened, and behold a white horse; and he that sat upon him was called Faithful and True, and in righteousness he doth judge and make war.', '&para; 0~2532~ 2~1492~ 3~3772~ 4~455~, 5~2532~ 6~2400~ 8~3022~ 9~2462~; 10~2532~ 13~2521~ 14~1909~ 15~846~ [16] 17~2564~ 18~4103~ 19~2532~ 20~228~, 21~2532~ 22~1722~ 23~1343~ 26~2919~ 27~2532~ 29~4170~.'),
  (15148, 19, 78, 26, 'He caused an east wind to blow in the heaven: and by his power he brought in the south wind.', '4~06921~ 6~05265~ 9~08064~: 13~05797~ 16~05090~ 19~08486~.'),
  (21765, 27, 1, 19, 'And the king communed with them; and among them all was found none like Daniel, Hananiah, Mishael, and Azariah: therefore stood they before the king.', '2~04428~ 3~01696~ 11~04672~ 14~01840~, 15~02608~, 16~04332~, 18~05838~: 20~05975~ 22~06440~ 24~04428~.'),
  (19511, 24, 23, 18, 'For who hath stood in the counsel of the LORD, and hath perceived and heard his word? who hath marked his word, and heard it?', '3~05975~ 6~05475~ 9~03068~, 12~07200~ 14~08085~ 16~01697~? 19~07181~ 21~01697~, 23~08085~ [24]'),
  (29276, 49, 3, 9, 'And to make all men see what is the fellowship of the mystery, which from the beginning of the world hath been hid in God, who created all things by Jesus Christ:', '0~2532~ 2~5461~ 3~3956~ [4] 5~5461~ 6~5101~ [7] 9~2842~ 12~3466~, 13~3588~ 14~575~ 19~165~ 22~613~ 23~1722~ 24~2316~, 25~3588~ 26~2936~ 28~3956~ 29~1223~ 30~2424~ 31~5547~:'),
  (1910, 2, 14, 16, 'But lift thou up thy rod, and stretch out thine hand over the sea, and divide it: and the children of Israel shall go on dry ground through the midst of the sea.', '3~07311~ 5~04294~, 8~05186~ 10~03027~ 13~03220~, 15~01234~ 19~01121~ 21~03478~ 23~0935~ 25~03004~ [26] 29~08432~ 32~03220~.'),
  (23484, 40, 11, 15, 'He that hath ears to hear, let him hear.', '2~2192~ 3~3775~ 5~191~, 8~191~.'),
  (23287, 40, 5, 43, 'Ye have heard that it hath been said, Thou shalt love thy neighbour, and hate thine enemy.', '&para; 2~191~ 3~3754~ 7~4483~, 10~25~ 11~4675~ 12~4139~, 13~2532~ 14~3404~ 15~4675~ 16~2190~.'),
  (17517, 21, 10, 15, 'The labour of the foolish wearieth every one of them, because he knoweth not how to go to the city.', '1~05999~ 4~03684~ 5~03021~ 12~03045~ 16~03212~ 19~05892~.'),
  (3431, 3, 23, 24, 'Speak unto the children of Israel, saying, In the seventh month, in the first day of the month, shall ye have a sabbath, a memorial of blowing of trumpets, an holy convocation.', '0~01696~ 3~01121~ 5~03478~, 6~0559~, 9~07637~ 10~02320~, 13~0259~ [14] 17~02320~, 22~07677~, 24~02146~ 26~08643~ 30~06944~ 31~04744~.'),
  (1783, 2, 10, 1, 'And the LORD said unto Moses, Go in unto Pharaoh: for I have hardened his heart, and the heart of his servants, that I might shew these my signs before him:', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~04872~, 6~0935~ 9~06547~: 13~03513~ 15~03820~, 18~03820~ 21~05650~, 25~07896~ 28~0226~ 29~07130~'),
  (10987, 13, 22, 15, 'Moreover there are workmen with thee in abundance, hewers and workers of stone and timber, and all manner of cunning men for every manner of work.', '[1 2] 3~06213~ 4~04399~* 8~07230~, 9~02672~ 11~02796~ 13~068~ 15~06086~, 21~02450~ 26~04399~.'),
  (1586, 2, 3, 2, 'And the angel of the LORD appeared unto him in a flame of fire out of the midst of a bush: and he looked, and, behold, the bush burned with fire, and the bush was not consumed.', '2~04397~ 5~03068~ 6~07200~ 11~03827~ 13~0784~ 17~08432~ 20~05572~: 23~07200~, 27~05572~ 28~01197~ 30~0784~, 33~05572~ [34] 36~0398~.'),
  (12235, 15, 8, 25, 'And weighed unto them the silver, and the gold, and the vessels, even the offering of the house of our God, which the king, and his counsellors, and his lords, and all Israel there present, had offered:', '1~08254~ 5~03701~, 8~02091~, 11~03627~, [12] 14~08641~ 17~01004~ 20~0430~, 23~04428~, 26~03289~, 29~08269~, 32~03478~ [33] 34~04672~, 36~07311~:'),
  (8423, 10, 15, 27, 'The king said also unto Zadok the priest, Art not thou a seer? return into the city in peace, and your two sons with you, Ahimaaz thy son, and Jonathan the son of Abiathar.', '1~04428~ 2~0559~ 5~06659~ 7~03548~, [8 9] 12~07200~? 13~07725~ 16~05892~ 18~07965~, 21~08147~ 22~01121~ 25~0290~ 27~01121~, 29~03083~ 31~01121~ 33~054~.'),
  (20834, 26, 16, 63, 'That thou mayest remember, and be confounded, and never open thy mouth any more because of thy shame, when I am pacified toward thee for all that thou hast done, saith the Lord GOD.', '3~02142~, 6~0954~, 9~06610~ 11~06310~ 14~06440~ 17~03639~, 21~03722~ 29~06213~, 30~05002~ 32~0136~ 33~03069~.'),
  (9310, 11, 16, 19, 'For his sins which he sinned in doing evil in the sight of the LORD, in walking in the way of Jeroboam, and in his sin which he did, to make Israel to sin.', '2~02403~ 5~02398~ 7~06213~ 8~07451~ 11~05869~ 14~03068~, 16~03212~ 19~01870~ 21~03379~, 25~02403~ 28~06213~, 31~03478~ 33~02398~.'),
  (25052, 42, 3, 15, 'And as the people were in expectation, and all men mused in their hearts of John, whether he were the Christ, or not;', '&para; 0~1161~ 3~2992~ 6~4328~, 7~2532~ 9~3956~ 10~1260~ 11~1722~ 12~846~ 13~2588~ 14~4012~ 15~2491~, 16~3379~ 17~846~ 18~1498~ 20~5547~, 22~3379~;'),
  (12293, 15, 10, 32, 'Benjamin, Malluch, and Shemariah.', '0~01144~, 1~04409~, [2] 3~08114~.'),
  (6132, 6, 11, 19, 'There was not a city that made peace with the children of Israel, save the Hivites the inhabitants of Gibeon: all other they took in battle.', '4~05892~ 7~07999~ 10~01121~ 12~03478~, 15~02340~ 17~03427~ 19~01391~: [21] 23~03947~ 25~04421~.'),
  (7949, 9, 27, 12, 'And Achish believed David, saying, He hath made his people Israel utterly to abhor him; therefore he shall be my servant for ever.', '1~0397~ 2~0539~ 3~01732~, 4~0559~, 9~05971~ 10~03478~ 11~0887~ 13~0887~ 20~05650~ 22~05769~.'),
  (30222, 58, 11, 34, 'Quenched the violence of fire, escaped the edge of the sword, out of weakness were made strong, waxed valiant in fight, turned to flight the armies of the aliens.', '0~4570~ 2~1411~ 4~4442~, 5~5343~ 7~4750~ 10~3162~, 12~575~ 13~769~ 16~1743~, 17~1096~ 18~2478~ 19~1722~ 20~4171~, 23~2827~ 25~3925~ 28~245~.'),
  (13303, 18, 18, 18, 'He shall be driven from light into darkness, and chased out of the world.', '3~01920~ 5~0216~ 7~02822~, 9~05074~ 13~08398~.'),
  (16097, 19, 121, 7, 'The LORD shall preserve thee from all evil: he shall preserve thy soul.', '1~03068~ 3~08104~ 7~07451~: 10~08104~ 12~05315~.'),
  (27163, 44, 7, 31, 'When Moses saw it, he wondered at the sight: and as he drew near to behold it, the voice of the Lord came unto him,', '0~1161~ 1~3475~ 2~1492~ [3] 5~2296~ 8~3705~: 9~1161~ 11~846~ 13~4334~ 15~2657~ [16] 18~5456~ 21~2962~ 22~1096~ 23~4314~ 24~846~,'),
  (10482, 13, 6, 20, 'Of Gershom; Libni his son, Jahath his son, Zimmah his son,', '1~01647~; 2~03845~ 4~01121~, 5~03189~ 7~01121~, 8~02155~ 10~01121~,'),
  (28190, 45, 9, 19, 'Thou wilt say then unto me, Why doth he yet find fault? For who hath resisted his will?', '2~2046~ 3~3767~ 5~3427~, 6~5101~ 9~2089~ 11~3201~? 12~1063~ 13~5101~ 15~436~ 16~846~ 17~1013~?'),
  (6497, 6, 24, 14, 'Now therefore fear the LORD, and serve him in sincerity and in truth: and put away the gods which your fathers served on the other side of the flood, and in Egypt; and serve ye the LORD.', '2~03372~ 4~03068~, 6~05647~ 9~08549~ 12~0571~: 15~05493~ 17~0430~ 20~01~ 21~05647~ 25~05676~ 28~05104~, 31~04714~; 33~05647~ 36~03068~.'),
  (24836, 41, 14, 71, 'But he began to curse and to swear, saying, I know not this man of whom ye speak.', '0~1161~ 2~756~ 4~332~ 5~2532~ 7~3660~, [8] 10~1492~ 11~3754~* 12~3756~ 13~5126~ 14~444~ 16~3739~ 18~3004~.'),
  (15236, 19, 81, 10, 'I am the LORD thy God, which brought thee out of the land of Egypt: open thy mouth wide, and I will fill it.', '[1] 3~03068~ 5~0430~, 7~05927~ 12~0776~ 14~04714~: 17~06310~ 18~07337~, 22~04390~'),
  (2918, 3, 7, 34, 'For the wave breast and the heave shoulder have I taken of the children of Israel from off the sacrifices of their peace offerings, and have given them unto Aaron the priest and unto his sons by a statute for ever from among the children of Israel.', '2~08573~ 3~02373~ 6~08641~ 7~07785~ 10~03947~ 13~01121~ 15~03478~ 19~02077~ 23~08002~, 26~05414~ 29~0175~ 31~03548~ 35~01121~ 38~02706~ 40~05769~ 44~01121~ 46~03478~.'),
  (23381, 40, 8, 26, 'And he saith unto them, Why are ye fearful, O ye of little faith? Then he arose, and rebuked the winds and the sea; and there was a great calm.', '0~2532~ 2~3004~ 4~846~, 5~5101~ 7~2075~ 8~1169~, 13~3640~? 14~5119~ 16~1453~, 18~2008~ 20~417~ 21~2532~ 23~2281~; 24~2532~ 26~1096~ 28~3173~ 29~1055~.'),
  (14487, 19, 37, 28, 'For the LORD loveth judgment, and forsaketh not his saints; they are preserved for ever: but the seed of the wicked shall be cut off.', '2~03068~ 3~0157~ 4~04941~, 6~05800~ 9~02623~; 12~08104~ 14~05769~: 17~02233~ 20~07563~ 24~03772~.'),
  (28629, 46, 11, 13, 'Judge in yourselves: is it comely that a woman pray unto God uncovered?', '0~2919~ 1~1722~ 2~846~ 3~5213~:* 5~2076~ 6~4241~ 9~1135~ 10~4336~ 12~2316~ 13~177~?'),
  (18823, 23, 59, 14, 'And judgment is turned away backward, and justice standeth afar off: for truth is fallen in the street, and equity cannot enter.', '1~04941~ 4~05253~ 5~0268~, 7~06666~ 8~05975~ 10~07350~: 12~0571~ 14~03782~ 17~07339~, 19~05229~ 20~03201~ 21~0935~.'),
  (25229, 42, 7, 22, 'Then Jesus answering said unto them, Go your way, and tell John what things ye have seen and heard; how that the blind see, the lame walk, the lepers are cleansed, the deaf hear, the dead are raised, to the poor the gospel is preached.', '0~2532~ 1~2424~ 2~611~ 3~2036~ 5~846~, 8~4198~, 10~518~ 11~2491~ 13~3739~ 16~1492~ 17~2532~ 18~191~; 19~3754~ 22~5185~ 23~308~, 25~5560~ 26~4043~, 28~3015~ 30~2511~, 32~2974~ 33~191~, 35~3498~ 37~1453~, 40~4434~ 44~2097~.'),
  (10747, 13, 12, 19, 'And there fell some of Manasseh to David, when he came with the Philistines against Saul to battle: but they helped them not: for the lords of the Philistines upon advisement sent him away, saying, He will fall to his master Saul to the jeopardy of our heads.', '2~05307~ [3] 5~04519~ 7~01732~, 10~0935~ 13~06430~ 15~07586~ 17~04421~: 20~05826~ 25~05633~ 28~06430~ 30~06098~ 31~07971~ 34~0559~, 37~05307~ 40~0113~ 41~07586~ [43 45] 47~07218~.'),
  (10025, 12, 17, 34, 'Unto this day they do after the former manners: they fear not the LORD, neither do they after their statutes, or after their ordinances, or after the law and commandment which the LORD commanded the children of Jacob, whom he named Israel;', '2~03117~ 4~06213~ 7~07223~ 8~04941~: 10~03373~ 13~03068~, 15~06213~ 19~02708~, 23~04941~, 27~08451~ 29~04687~ 32~03068~ 33~06680~ 35~01121~ 37~03290~, 40~07760~ 41~08034~* 42~03478~;'),
  (17594, 22, 4, 3, 'Thy lips are like a thread of scarlet, and thy speech is comely: thy temples are like a piece of a pomegranate within thy locks.', '1~08193~ [2] 5~02339~ 7~08144~, 10~04057~ [11] 12~05000~: 14~07541~ [15] 18~06400~ 21~07416~ 22~01157~ 24~06777~.'),
  (23847, 40, 21, 11, 'And the multitude said, This is Jesus the prophet of Nazareth of Galilee.', '0~1161~ 2~3793~ 3~3004~, 4~3778~ 5~2076~ 6~2424~ 8~4396~ 9~575~ 10~3478~ 12~1056~.'),
  (9610, 12, 3, 26, 'And when the king of Moab saw that the battle was too sore for him, he took with him seven hundred men that drew swords, to break through even unto the king of Edom: but they could not.', '3~04428~ 5~04124~ 6~07200~ 9~04421~ 12~02388~ 16~03947~ 19~07651~ 20~03967~ 21~0376~ 23~08025~ 24~02719~, 27~01234~ [28] 31~04428~ 33~0123~: 36~03201~'),
  (11539, 14, 17, 7, 'Also in the third year of his reign he sent to his princes, even to Benhail, and to Obadiah, and to Zechariah, and to Nethaneel, and to Michaiah, to teach in the cities of Judah.', '3~07969~ 4~08141~ 7~04427~ 9~07971~ 12~08269~, [13] 15~01134~, 18~05662~, 21~02148~, 24~05417~, 27~04322~, 29~03925~ 32~05892~ 34~03063~.'),
  (18337, 23, 35, 8, 'And an highway shall be there, and a way, and it shall be called The way of holiness; the unclean shall not pass over it; but it shall be for those: the wayfaring men, though fools, shall not err therein.', '2~04547~ 8~01870~, 13~07121~ 15~01870~ 17~06944~; 19~02931~ 23~05674~ [27 28] 33~01980~, 35~0191~, 38~08582~ [39]'),
  (27837, 44, 25, 25, 'But when I found that he had committed nothing worthy of death, and that he himself hath appealed to Augustus, I have determined to send him.', '0~1161~ 2~1473~ 3~2638~ 5~846~ 7~4238~ 8~3367~ 9~514~ 11~2288~, 12~1161~ 13~2532~ 15~846~ 17~5127~ 18~1941~ 19~4575~, 22~2919~ 24~3992~ 25~846~.'),
  (3689, 4, 2, 26, 'And his host, and those that were numbered of them, were threescore and two thousand and seven hundred.', '2~06635~, 7~06485~ [10] 11~08346~ 13~08147~ 14~0505~ 16~07651~ 17~03967~.'),
  (23139, 39, 3, 9, 'Ye are cursed with a curse: for ye have robbed me, even this whole nation.', '[1] 2~0779~ 5~03994~: 9~06906~ [11] 14~01471~.'),
  (18129, 23, 25, 2, 'For thou hast made of a city an heap; of a defenced city a ruin: a palace of strangers to be no city; it shall never be built.', '3~07760~ 6~05892~ 8~01530~; [9] 11~01219~ 12~07151~ 14~04654~: 16~0759~ 18~02114~ 22~05892~; 25~05769~ 27~01129~.'),
  (25036, 42, 2, 51, 'And he went down with them, and came to Nazareth, and was subject unto them: but his mother kept all these sayings in her heart.', '0~2532~ 3~2597~ 4~3326~ 5~846~, 6~2532~ 7~2064~ 8~1519~ 9~3478~, 10~2532~ 11~2258~ 12~5293~ 14~846~: 15~2532~ 16~846~ 17~3384~ 18~1301~ 19~3956~ 20~5023~ 21~4487~ 22~1722~ 23~846~ 24~2588~.'),
  (8228, 10, 8, 12, 'Of Syria, and of Moab, and of the children of Ammon, and of the Philistines, and of Amalek, and of the spoil of Hadadezer, son of Rehob, king of Zobah.', '1~0758~, 4~04124~, 8~01121~ 10~05983~, 14~06430~, 17~06002~, 21~07998~ 23~01909~, 24~01121~ 26~07340~, 27~04428~ 29~06678~.'),
  (27973, 45, 1, 27, 'And likewise also the men, leaving the natural use of the woman, burned in their lust one toward another; men with men working that which is unseemly, and receiving in themselves that recompense of their error which was meet.', '0~5037~ 1~3668~ 2~2532~ 4~730~, 5~863~ 7~5446~ 8~5540~ 11~2338~, 12~1572~ 13~1722~ 14~846~ 15~3715~ 18~240~ 19~1519~;* 20~730~ 21~1722~ 22~730~ 23~2716~ 27~808~, 28~2532~ 29~618~ 30~1722~ 31~1438~ 33~489~ 35~846~ 36~4106~ 37~3739~ 39~1163~.'),
  (8138, 10, 4, 11, 'How much more, when wicked men have slain a righteous person in his own house upon his bed? shall I not therefore now require his blood of your hand, and take you away from the earth?', '4~07563~ 5~0582~ 7~02026~ 9~06662~ 10~0376~ 14~01004~ 17~04904~? 23~01245~ 25~01818~ 28~03027~, 32~01197~ 35~0776~?'),
  (12817, 17, 7, 1, 'So the king and Haman came to banquet with Esther the queen.', '&para; 2~04428~ 4~02001~ 5~0935~ 7~08354~ 9~0635~ 11~04436~.'),
  (19230, 24, 10, 20, 'My tabernacle is spoiled, and all my cords are broken: my children are gone forth of me, and they are not: there is none to stretch forth my tent any more, and to set up my curtains.', '1~0168~ 3~07703~, 7~04340~ 9~05423~: 11~01121~ 14~03318~ [19] [21 22] 26~05186~ 28~0168~ 34~06965~ 36~03407~.'),
  (17387, 21, 3, 19, 'For that which befalleth the sons of men befalleth beasts; even one thing befalleth them: as the one dieth, so dieth the other; yea, they have all one breath; so that a man hath no preeminence above a beast: for all is vanity.', '3~04745~ 5~01121~ 7~0120~ 8~04745~ 9~0929~; 12~0259~ 13~04745~ 18~04194~, 20~04194~ 22~02088~; 27~0259~ 28~07307~; 32~0120~ 35~04195~ 38~0929~: [41] 42~01892~.'),
  (20583, 26, 6, 11, 'Thus saith the Lord GOD; Smite with thine hand, and stamp with thy foot, and say, Alas for all the evil abominations of the house of Israel! for they shall fall by the sword, by the famine, and by the pestilence.', '&para; 1~0559~ 3~0136~ 4~03069~; 5~05221~ 8~03709~, 10~07554~ 13~07272~, 15~0559~, 16~0253~ 20~07451~ 21~08441~ 24~01004~ 26~03478~! 30~05307~ 33~02719~, 36~07458~, 40~01698~.'),
  (2234, 2, 25, 34, 'And in the candlestick shall be four bowls made like unto almonds, with their knops and their flowers.', '3~04501~ [4 5] 6~0702~ 7~01375~ 11~08246~, [12] 14~03730~ 17~06525~.'),
  (27092, 44, 5, 17, 'Then the high priest rose up, and all they that were with him, (which is the sect of the Sadducees,) and were filled with indignation,', '&para; 0~1161~ 3~749~ 5~450~, 6~2532~ 8~3956~ 11~4862~ 12~846~, 13~3588~* 15~5607~ 17~139~ 20~4523~,) 23~4130~ 25~2205~,'),
  (8081, 10, 2, 25, 'And the children of Benjamin gathered themselves together after Abner, and became one troop, and stood on the top of an hill.', '&para; 2~01121~ 4~01144~ 7~06908~ 8~0310~ 9~074~, 12~0259~ 13~092~, 15~05975~ 18~07218~ 21~01389~.'),
  (16590, 20, 7, 6, 'For at the window of my house I looked through my casement,', '&para; 3~02474~ 6~01004~ 8~08259~ 11~0822~,'),
  (28004, 45, 2, 26, 'Therefore if the uncircumcision keep the righteousness of the law, shall not his uncircumcision be counted for circumcision?', '0~3767~ 1~1437~ 3~203~ 4~5442~ 6~1345~ 9~3551~, 10~3049~ 11~3780~ 12~846~ 13~203~ 15~3049~ 16~1519~ 17~4061~?'),
  (24024, 40, 25, 6, 'And at midnight there was a cry made, Behold, the bridegroom cometh; go ye out to meet him.', '0~1161~ 2~3571~ 3~3319~ 6~2906~ 7~1096~, 8~2400~, 10~3566~ 11~2064~; 14~1831~ 15~1519~ 16~529~ 17~846~.'),
  (21964, 27, 7, 22, 'Until the Ancient of days came, and judgment was given to the saints of the most High; and the time came that the saints possessed the kingdom.', '0~05705~ 2~06268~ 4~03118~ 5~0858~ 6~01768~,* 8~01780~ 10~03052~ 13~06922~ 17~05946~; 20~02166~ 21~04291~ 24~06922~ 25~02631~ 27~04437~.'),
  (10840, 13, 16, 12, 'Remember his marvellous works that he hath done, his wonders, and the judgments of his mouth;', '0~02142~ 2~06381~ 7~06213~, 9~04159~, 12~04941~ 15~06310~;'),
  (19013, 24, 3, 2, 'Lift up thine eyes unto the high places, and see where thou hast not been lien with. In the ways hast thou sat for them, as the Arabian in the wilderness; and thou hast polluted the land with thy whoredoms and with thy wickedness.', '1~05375~ 3~05869~ 7~08205~, 9~07200~ 10~0375~ 15~07693~ 19~01870~ 22~03427~ 27~06163~ 30~04057~; 34~02610~ 36~0776~ 39~02184~ 43~07451~.'),
  (7634, 9, 17, 9, 'If he be able to fight with me, and to kill me, then will we be your servants: but if I prevail against him, and kill him, then shall ye be our servants, and serve us.', '3~03201~ 5~03898~ 10~05221~ 17~05650~: 21~03201~ 25~05221~ 32~05650~, 34~05647~'),
  (24026, 40, 25, 8, 'And the foolish said unto the wise, Give us of your oil; for our lamps are gone out.', '0~1161~ 2~3474~ 3~2036~ 6~5429~, 7~1325~ 8~2254~ 9~1537~ 10~5216~ 11~1637~; 12~3754~ 13~2257~ 14~2985~ 17~4570~.'),
  (27927, 44, 28, 12, 'And landing at Syracuse, we tarried there three days.', '0~2532~ 1~2609~ 2~1519~ 3~4946~, 5~1961~ [6] 7~5140~ 8~2250~.'),
  (15278, 19, 84, 10, 'For a day in thy courts is better than a thousand. I had rather be a doorkeeper in the house of my God, than to dwell in the tents of wickedness.', '2~03117~ 5~02691~ [6] 7~02896~ 10~0505~. 13~0977~ 16~05605~ 19~01004~ 22~0430~, 25~01752~ 28~0168~ 30~07562~.'),
  (2386, 2, 29, 45, 'And I will dwell among the children of Israel, and will be their God.', '3~07931~ 4~08432~ 6~01121~ 8~03478~, 13~0430~.'),
  (16720, 20, 11, 23, 'The desire of the righteous is only good: but the expectation of the wicked is wrath.', '&para; 1~08378~ 4~06662~ [5] 7~02896~: [8] 10~08615~ 13~07563~ [14] 15~05678~.'),
  (18289, 23, 33, 1, 'Woe to thee that spoilest, and thou wast not spoiled; and dealest treacherously, and they dealt not treacherously with thee! when thou shalt cease to spoil, thou shalt be spoiled; and when thou shalt make an end to deal treacherously, they shall deal treacherously with thee.', '&para; 0~01945~ 4~07703~, [7] 9~07703~; 12~0898~, 17~0898~ 23~08552~ 25~07703~, 29~07703~; [30] 36~05239~ 39~0898~, 43~0898~'),
  (3978, 4, 9, 8, 'And Moses said unto them, Stand still, and I will hear what the LORD will command concerning you.', '1~04872~ 2~0559~ 6~05975~, 10~08085~ 13~03068~ 15~06680~'),
  (27982, 45, 2, 4, 'Or despisest thou the riches of his goodness and forbearance and longsuffering; not knowing that the goodness of God leadeth thee to repentance?', '0~2228~ 2~2706~ 4~4149~ 6~846~ 7~5544~ 8~2532~ 9~463~ 10~2532~ 11~3115~; 13~50~ 14~3754~ 16~5543~ 18~2316~ 19~71~ 20~4571~ 21~1519~ 22~3341~?'),
  (6097, 6, 10, 27, 'And it came to pass at the time of the going down of the sun, that Joshua commanded, and they took them down off the trees, and cast them into the cave wherein they had been hid, and laid great stones in the cave''s mouth, which remain until this very day.', '7~06256~ 11~0935~ 14~08121~, [15] 16~03091~ 17~06680~, 22~03381~ 25~06086~, 27~07993~ 31~04631~ 36~02244~, 38~07760~ 39~01419~ 40~068~ 43~04631~ 44~06310~, [45 46] 49~06106~ 50~03117~.'),
  (889, 1, 31, 12, 'And he said, Lift up now thine eyes, and see, all the rams which leap upon the cattle are ringstreaked, speckled, and grisled: for I have seen all that Laban doeth unto thee.', '2~0559~, 4~05375~ 7~05869~, 9~07200~, 12~06260~ 14~05927~ 17~06629~ [18] 19~06124~, 20~05348~, 22~01261~: 26~07200~ 29~03837~ 30~06213~'),
  (13060, 18, 8, 22, 'They that hate thee shall be clothed with shame; and the dwelling place of the wicked shall come to nought.', '2~08130~ 6~03847~ 8~01322~; 11~0168~ 15~07563~ 19~0369~.'),
  (14616, 19, 45, 10, 'Hearken, O daughter, and consider, and incline thine ear; forget also thine own people, and thy father''s house;', '&para; 0~08085~, 2~01323~, 4~07200~, 6~05186~ 8~0241~; 9~07911~ 13~05971~, 16~01~ 17~01004~;'),
  (8089, 10, 3, 1, 'Now there was long war between the house of Saul and the house of David: but David waxed stronger and stronger, and the house of Saul waxed weaker and weaker.', '&para; 3~0752~ 4~04421~ 7~01004~ 9~07586~ 12~01004~ 14~01732~: 16~01732~ 17~01980~ 18~02390~ 20~02390~, 23~01004~ 25~07586~ 26~01980~ 27~01800~ 29~01800~.'),
  (17190, 20, 27, 12, 'A prudent man foreseeth the evil, and hideth himself; but the simple pass on, and are punished.', '&para; 1~06175~ [2] 3~07200~ 5~07451~, [6] 7~05641~ [9] 11~06612~ 13~05674~, [14] 16~06064~.'),
  (9421, 11, 20, 5, 'And the messengers came again, and said, Thus speaketh Benhadad, saying, Although I have sent unto thee, saying, Thou shalt deliver me thy silver, and thy gold, and thy wives, and thy children;', '2~04397~ 4~07725~, 6~0559~, 8~0559~ 9~01130~, 10~0559~, 14~07971~ 17~0559~, 20~05414~ 23~03701~, 26~02091~, 29~0802~, 32~01121~;'),
  (819, 1, 29, 20, 'And Jacob served seven years for Rachel; and they seemed unto him but a few days, for the love he had to her.', '1~03290~ 2~05647~ 3~07651~ 4~08141~ 6~07354~; 9~05869~ [12] 14~0259~ 15~03117~, 20~0160~'),
  (822, 1, 29, 23, 'And it came to pass in the evening, that he took Leah his daughter, and brought her to him; and he went in unto her.', '7~06153~, 10~03947~ 11~03812~ 13~01323~, 15~0935~ 22~0935~'),
  (26546, 43, 11, 8, 'His disciples say unto him, Master, the Jews of late sought to stone thee; and goest thou thither again?', '[0] 1~3101~ 2~3004~ 4~846~, 5~4461~, 7~2453~ 9~3568~ 10~2212~ 12~3034~ 13~4571~; 14~2532~ 16~5217~ 17~1563~ 18~3825~?'),
  (16820, 20, 15, 4, 'A wholesome tongue is a tree of life: but perverseness therein is a breach in the spirit.', '&para; 1~04832~ 2~03956~ [3] 5~06086~ 7~02416~: 9~05558~ [11] 13~07667~ 16~07307~.'),
  (27801, 44, 24, 16, 'And herein do I exercise myself, to have always a conscience void of offence toward God, and toward men.', '0~1161~ 1~5129~ 2~1722~ 4~778~ 5~846~, 7~2192~ 8~1275~ 10~4893~ 13~677~ 14~4314~ 15~2316~, 16~2532~ [17] 18~444~.'),
  (21102, 26, 25, 10, 'Unto the men of the east with the Ammonites, and will give them in possession, that the Ammonites may not be remembered among the nations.', '2~01121~ 5~06924~ 8~05983~ 9~01121~,* 12~05414~ 15~04181~, 18~05983~ 19~01121~ 22~02142~ 25~01471~.'),
  (4727, 4, 32, 3, 'Ataroth, and Dibon, and Jazer, and Nimrah, and Heshbon, and Elealeh, and Shebam, and Nebo, and Beon,', '0~05852~, 2~01769~, 4~03270~, 6~05247~, 8~02809~, 10~0500~, 12~07643~, 14~05015~, 16~01194~,'),
  (21974, 27, 8, 4, 'I saw the ram pushing westward, and northward, and southward; so that no beasts might stand before him, neither was there any that could deliver out of his hand; but he did according to his will, and became great.', '1~07200~ 3~0352~ 4~05055~ 5~03220~, 7~06828~, 9~05045~; 13~02416~ 15~05975~ 16~06440~ [19 21] 24~05337~ 28~03027~; 31~06213~ 35~07522~, 38~01431~.'),
  (9044, 11, 8, 51, 'For they be thy people, and thine inheritance, which thou broughtest forth out of Egypt, from the midst of the furnace of iron:', '[2] 4~05971~, 7~05159~, 11~03318~ 14~04714~, 17~08432~ 20~03564~ 22~01270~:'),
  (25711, 42, 18, 9, 'And he spake this parable unto certain which trusted in themselves that they were righteous, and despised others:', '&para; 0~1161~ 2~2036~ 3~2532~* 4~5026~ 5~3850~ 6~4314~ 7~5100~ 8~3588~ 9~3982~ 10~1909~ 11~1438~ 12~3754~ 14~1526~ 15~1342~, 16~2532~ 17~1848~ 18~3062~:'),
  (28754, 46, 15, 20, 'But now is Christ risen from the dead, and become the firstfruits of them that slept.', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~3570~ 2~1453~ 3~5547~ 4~1453~ 5~1537~ 7~3498~, [8] 9~1096~ 11~536~ 15~2837~.'),
  (18966, 24, 1, 11, 'Moreover the word of the LORD came unto me, saying, Jeremiah, what seest thou? And I said, I see a rod of an almond tree.', '&para; 2~01697~ 5~03068~ 9~0559~, 10~03414~, 12~07200~ 16~0559~, 18~07200~ 20~04731~ 24~08247~.'),
  (22037, 27, 10, 13, 'But the prince of the kingdom of Persia withstood me one and twenty days: but, lo, Michael, one of the chief princes, came to help me; and I remained there with the kings of Persia.', '2~08269~ 5~04438~ 7~06539~ 8~05975~ 10~0259~ 12~06242~ 13~03117~: 16~04317~, 17~0259~ 20~07223~ 21~08269~, 22~0935~ 24~05826~ 28~03498~ 30~0681~ 32~04428~ 34~06539~.'),
  (11720, 14, 25, 7, 'But there came a man of God to him, saying, O king, let not the army of Israel go with thee; for the LORD is not with Israel, to wit, with all the children of Ephraim.', '2~0935~ 4~0376~ 6~0430~ 9~0559~, 11~04428~, 15~06635~ 17~03478~ 18~0935~ 23~03068~ [24] 27~03478~, [28 30] 33~01121~ 35~0669~.'),
  (25768, 42, 19, 23, 'Wherefore then gavest not thou my money into the bank, that at my coming I might have required mine own with usury?', '0~1302~ 1~2532~ 2~1325~ 3~3756~ 4~1325~ 5~3450~ 6~694~ 7~1909~ 9~5132~, 10~2532~ 13~2064~ 14~1473~ 15~302~ 17~4238~ 19~846~ 20~4862~ 21~5110~?');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (28786, 46, 15, 52, 'In a moment, in the twinkling of an eye, at the last trump: for the trumpet shall sound, and the dead shall be raised incorruptible, and we shall be changed.', '0~1722~ 2~823~, 3~1722~ 5~4493~ 8~3788~, 9~1722~ 11~2078~ 12~4536~: 13~1063~ 17~4537~, 18~2532~ 20~3498~ 23~1453~ 24~862~, 25~2532~ 26~2249~ 29~236~.'),
  (27412, 44, 13, 34, 'And as concerning that he raised him up from the dead, now no more to return to corruption, he said on this wise, I will give you the sure mercies of David.', '0~1161~ 3~3754~ 5~450~ 6~846~ 7~450~ 8~1537~ 10~3498~, [11] 13~3371~ 14~3195~ 15~5290~ 16~1519~ 17~1312~, 19~2046~ 22~3779~ 23~3754~,* 26~1325~ 27~5213~ 29~4103~ 30~3741~ 32~1138~.'),
  (12010, 14, 36, 8, 'Now the rest of the acts of Jehoiakim, and his abominations which he did, and that which was found in him, behold, they are written in the book of the kings of Israel and Judah: and Jehoiachin his son reigned in his stead.', '2~03499~ 5~01697~ 7~03079~, 10~08441~ 13~06213~, 18~04672~ [23] 24~03789~ 27~05612~ 30~04428~ 32~03478~ 34~03063~: 36~03078~ 38~01121~ 39~04427~'),
  (24271, 41, 2, 1, 'And again he entered into Capernaum after some days; and it was noised that he was in the house.', '&para; 0~2532~ 1~3825~ 3~1525~ 4~1519~ 5~2584~ 6~1223~ [7] 8~2250~; 9~2532~ 12~191~ 13~3754~ 15~2076~ 16~1519~ 18~3624~.'),
  (11959, 14, 34, 17, 'And they have gathered together the money that was found in the house of the LORD, and have delivered it into the hand of the overseers, and to the hand of the workmen.', '4~05413~ 6~03701~ 9~04672~ 12~01004~ 15~03068~, 18~05414~ 22~03027~ 25~06485~, 29~03027~ 32~06213~ 33~04399~.*'),
  (19322, 24, 14, 20, 'We acknowledge, O LORD, our wickedness, and the iniquity of our fathers: for we have sinned against thee.', '1~03045~, 3~03068~, 5~07562~, [6] 8~05771~ 11~01~: 15~02398~'),
  (5340, 5, 15, 15, 'And thou shalt remember that thou wast a bondman in the land of Egypt, and the LORD thy God redeemed thee: therefore I command thee this thing to day.', '3~02142~ 8~05650~ 11~0776~ 13~04714~, 16~03068~ 18~0430~ 19~06299~ 23~06680~ 26~01697~ 28~03117~.'),
  (26364, 43, 7, 21, 'Jesus answered and said unto them, I have done one work, and ye all marvel.', '0~2424~ 1~611~ 2~2532~ 3~2036~ 5~846~, 8~4160~ 9~1520~ 10~2041~, 11~2532~ 12~2296~ 13~3956~ 14~2296~.'),
  (15422, 19, 92, 2, 'To shew forth thy lovingkindness in the morning, and thy faithfulness every night,', '2~05046~ 4~02617~ 7~01242~, 10~0530~ 12~03915~,'),
  (6355, 6, 19, 27, 'And turneth toward the sunrising to Bethdagon, and reacheth to Zebulun, and to the valley of Jiphthahel toward the north side of Bethemek, and Neiel, and goeth out to Cabul on the left hand,', '1~07725~ 4~08121~ 5~04217~ 6~01016~, 8~06293~ 10~02074~, 14~01516~ 16~03317~ 20~06828~ 22~01025~, 24~05272~, 27~03318~ 29~03521~ 33~08040~,'),
  (27770, 44, 23, 20, 'And he said, The Jews have agreed to desire thee that thou wouldest bring down Paul to morrow into the council, as though they would inquire somewhat of him more perfectly.', '0~1161~ 2~2036~ 3~3754~,* 5~2453~ 7~4934~ 9~2065~ 10~4571~ 11~3704~ 15~2609~ 16~3972~ 18~839~ 19~1519~ 21~4892~, 22~5613~ 25~3195~ 26~4441~ 27~5100~ 28~4012~ 29~846~ 31~197~.'),
  (10193, 12, 23, 20, 'And he slew all the priests of the high places that were there upon the altars, and burned men''s bones upon them, and returned to Jerusalem.', '2~02076~ 5~03548~ 9~01116~ [11] 15~04196~, 17~08313~ 18~0120~ 19~06106~ 23~07725~ 25~03389~.'),
  (1161, 1, 39, 7, 'And it came to pass after these things, that his master''s wife cast her eyes upon Joseph; and she said, Lie with me.', '&para; 5~0310~ 7~01697~, 10~0113~ 11~0802~ 12~05375~ 14~05869~ 16~03130~; 19~0559~, 20~07901~'),
  (8759, 11, 1, 34, 'And let Zadok the priest and Nathan the prophet anoint him there king over Israel: and blow ye with the trumpet, and say, God save king Solomon.', '2~06659~ 4~03548~ 6~05416~ 8~05030~ 9~04886~ 12~04428~ 14~03478~: 16~08628~ 20~07782~, 22~0559~, 24~02421~ 25~04428~ 26~08010~.'),
  (22520, 31, 1, 1, 'The vision of Obadiah. Thus saith the Lord GOD concerning Edom; We have heard a rumour from the LORD, and an ambassador is sent among the heathen, Arise ye, and let us rise up against her in battle.', '&para; 1~02377~ 3~05662~. 5~0559~ 7~0136~ 8~03069~ 10~0123~; 13~08085~ 15~08052~ 18~03068~, 21~06735~ 23~07971~ 26~01471~, 27~06965~ 33~06965~ 37~04421~.'),
  (20124, 24, 48, 35, 'Moreover I will cause to cease in Moab, saith the LORD, him that offereth in the high places, and him that burneth incense to his gods.', '5~07673~ 7~04124~, 8~05002~ 10~03068~, 13~05927~ 17~01116~, 22~06999~ 25~0430~.'),
  (26585, 43, 11, 47, 'Then gathered the chief priests and the Pharisees a council, and said, What do we? for this man doeth many miracles.', '0~3767~ 1~4863~ 4~749~ 5~2532~ 7~5330~ 9~4892~, 10~2532~ 11~3004~, 12~5101~ 14~4160~? 15~3754~ 16~3778~ 17~444~ 18~4160~ 19~4183~ 20~4592~.'),
  (7241, 9, 1, 22, 'But Hannah went not up; for she said unto her husband, I will not go up until the child be weaned, and then I will bring him, that he may appear before the LORD, and there abide for ever.', '1~02584~ 4~05927~; 7~0559~ 10~0376~, [11 15] 18~05288~ 20~01580~, [22] 25~0935~ 30~07200~ 31~06440~ 33~03068~, 36~03427~ 37~05704~ 38~05769~.'),
  (23613, 40, 14, 6, 'But when Herod''s birthday was kept, the daughter of Herodias danced before them, and pleased Herod.', '0~1161~ 2~2264~ 3~1077~ 5~71~, 7~2364~ 9~2266~ 10~3738~ 12~3319~ 13~1722~,* 14~2532~ 15~700~ 16~2264~.'),
  (24448, 41, 6, 31, 'And he said unto them, Come ye yourselves apart into a desert place, and rest a while: for there were many coming and going, and they had no leisure so much as to eat.', '0~2532~ 2~2036~ 4~846~, 5~1205~ 6~5210~ 7~846~ 8~2398~ 9~2596~* 10~1519~ 12~2048~ 13~5117~, 14~2532~ 15~373~ 17~3641~: 18~1063~ 20~2258~ 21~4183~ 22~2064~ 23~2532~ 24~5217~, 25~2532~ 28~3761~ 29~2119~ 32~3761~ 34~5315~.'),
  (585, 1, 23, 10, 'And Ephron dwelt among the children of Heth: and Ephron the Hittite answered Abraham in the audience of the children of Heth, even of all that went in at the gate of his city, saying,', '1~06085~ 2~03427~ 3~08432~ 5~01121~ 7~02845~: 9~06085~ 11~02850~ 12~06030~ 13~085~ 16~0241~ 19~01121~ 21~02845~, [22] 27~0935~ 30~08179~ 33~05892~, 34~0559~,'),
  (7464, 9, 11, 12, 'And the people said unto Samuel, Who is he that said, Shall Saul reign over us? bring the men, that we may put them to death.', '&para; 2~05971~ 3~0559~ 5~08050~, [7] 10~0559~, 12~07586~ 13~04427~ 16~05414~ 18~0582~, 25~04191~.'),
  (16801, 20, 14, 20, 'The poor is hated even of his own neighbour: but the rich hath many friends.', '&para; 1~07326~ 3~08130~ 8~07453~: 11~06223~ [12] 13~07227~ 14~0157~.'),
  (4740, 4, 32, 16, 'And they came near unto him, and said, We will build sheepfolds here for our cattle, and cities for our little ones:', '&para; 3~05066~ 7~0559~, 10~01129~ 11~06629~ 12~01448~ 15~04735~, 17~05892~ 21~02945~:'),
  (29983, 58, 1, 4, 'Being made so much better than the angels, as he hath by inheritance obtained a more excellent name than they.', '&para; 1~1096~ 3~5118~ 5~2909~ 7~32~, 8~3745~ 13~2816~ 16~1313~ 17~3686~ 18~3844~ 19~846~.'),
  (5998, 6, 7, 16, 'So Joshua rose up early in the morning, and brought Israel by their tribes; and the tribe of Judah was taken:', '&para; 1~03091~ 4~07925~ 7~01242~, 9~07126~ 10~03478~ 13~07626~; 16~07626~ 18~03063~ 20~03920~:'),
  (20181, 24, 50, 6, 'My people hath been lost sheep: their shepherds have caused them to go astray, they have turned them away on the mountains: they have gone from mountain to hill, they have forgotten their restingplace.', '1~05971~ 4~06~ 5~06629~: 7~07462~ 13~08582~, 18~07725~ [19] 21~02022~: 24~01980~ 26~02022~ 28~01389~, 31~07911~ 33~07258~.'),
  (8913, 11, 6, 9, 'So he built the house, and finished it; and covered the house with beams and boards of cedar.', '2~01129~ 4~01004~, 6~03615~ 9~05603~ 11~01004~ 13~01356~ 15~07713~ 17~0730~.'),
  (21299, 26, 33, 10, 'Therefore, O thou son of man, speak unto the house of Israel; Thus ye speak, saying, If our transgressions and our sins be upon us, and we pine away in them, how should we then live?', '&para; 3~01121~ 5~0120~, 6~0559~ 9~01004~ 11~03478~; 14~0559~, 15~0559~, 18~06588~ 21~02403~ [22] 28~04743~ 35~02421~?'),
  (24163, 40, 27, 24, 'When Pilate saw that he could prevail nothing, but that rather a tumult was made, he took water, and washed his hands before the multitude, saying, I am innocent of the blood of this just person: see ye to it.', '0~1161~ 1~4091~ 2~1492~ 3~3754~ 6~5623~ 7~3762~, 8~235~ [9] 10~3123~ 12~2351~ 14~1096~, 16~2983~ 17~5204~, 19~633~ [20] 21~5495~ 22~561~ 24~3793~, 25~3004~, 27~1510~ 28~121~ 29~575~ 31~129~ 33~5127~ 35~1342~: 36~3700~ 37~5210~ [38 39]'),
  (29678, 53, 2, 1, 'Now we beseech you, brethren, by the coming of our Lord Jesus Christ, and by our gathering together unto him,', '&para; 0~1161~ 2~2065~ 3~5209~, 4~80~, 5~5228~ 7~3952~ 9~2257~ 10~2962~ 11~2424~ 12~5547~, 13~2532~ [14] 15~2257~ 17~1997~ 18~1909~ 19~846~,'),
  (1836, 2, 12, 15, 'Seven days shall ye eat unleavened bread; even the first day ye shall put away leaven out of your houses: for whosoever eateth leavened bread from the first day until the seventh day, that soul shall be cut off from Israel.', '0~07651~ 1~03117~ 4~0398~ 6~04682~; 7~0389~ 9~07223~ 10~03117~ 14~07673~ 15~07603~ 19~01004~: 22~0398~ 24~02557~ 27~07223~ 28~03117~ 31~07637~ 32~03117~, 34~05315~ 37~03772~ 40~03478~.'),
  (30012, 58, 3, 1, 'Wherefore, holy brethren, partakers of the heavenly calling, consider the Apostle and High Priest of our profession, Christ Jesus;', '&para; 0~3606~, 1~40~ 2~80~, 3~3353~ 6~2032~ 7~2821~, 8~2657~ 10~652~ 11~2532~ 13~749~ 15~2257~ 16~3671~, 17~5547~ 18~2424~;'),
  (13550, 18, 29, 9, 'The princes refrained talking, and laid their hand on their mouth.', '1~08269~ 2~06113~ 3~04405~, 5~07760~ [6] 7~03709~ 10~06310~.'),
  (7905, 9, 25, 37, 'But it came to pass in the morning, when the wine was gone out of Nabal, and his wife had told him these things, that his heart died within him, and he became as a stone.', '7~01242~, 10~03196~ 13~03318~ 15~05037~, 18~0802~ 20~05046~ 23~01697~, 26~03820~ 27~04191~ 28~07130~ [33] 35~068~.'),
  (21702, 26, 47, 14, 'And ye shall inherit it, one as well as another: concerning the which I lifted up mine hand to give it unto your fathers: and this land shall fall unto you for inheritance.', '3~05157~ 5~0376~ 9~0251~: [10] 15~05375~ 17~03027~ 19~05414~ 23~01~: 26~0776~ 28~05307~ 32~05159~.'),
  (29463, 50, 4, 5, 'Let your moderation be known unto all men. The Lord is at hand.', '0~1097~ 1~5216~ 2~1933~ 4~1097~ 6~3956~ 7~444~. 9~2962~ [10] 12~1451~.'),
  (9873, 12, 12, 15, 'Moreover they reckoned not with the men, into whose hand they delivered the money to be bestowed on workmen: for they dealt faithfully.', '2~02803~ 6~0582~, 9~03027~ 11~05414~ 13~03701~ 16~05414~ 18~04399~: 21~06213~ 22~0530~.'),
  (6540, 7, 1, 24, 'And the spies saw a man come forth out of the city, and they said unto him, shew us, we pray thee, the entrance into the city, and we will shew thee mercy.', '2~08104~ 3~07200~ 5~0376~ 7~03318~ 11~05892~, 14~0559~ 17~07200~ 23~03996~ 26~05892~, 30~06213~ 32~02617~.'),
  (3595, 3, 27, 20, 'And if he will not redeem the field, or if he have sold the field to another man, it shall not be redeemed any more.', '5~01350~ 7~07704~, 12~04376~ 14~07704~ 16~0312~ 17~0376~, 22~01350~'),
  (25071, 42, 3, 34, 'Which was the son of Jacob, which was the son of Isaac, which was the son of Abraham, which was the son of Thara, which was the son of Nachor,', '[2 3] 5~2384~, [8 9] 11~2464~, [14 15] 17~11~, [20 21] 23~2291~, [26 27] 29~3493~,'),
  (215, 1, 9, 9, 'And I, behold, I establish my covenant with you, and with your seed after you;', '4~06965~ 6~01285~ 12~02233~ 14~0310~;'),
  (19997, 24, 42, 13, 'But if ye say, We will not dwell in this land, neither obey the voice of the LORD your God,', '3~0559~, 7~03427~ 10~0776~, 12~08085~ 14~06963~ 17~03068~ 19~0430~,'),
  (6542, 7, 1, 26, 'And the man went into the land of the Hittites, and built a city, and called the name thereof Luz: which is the name thereof unto this day.', '2~0376~ 3~03212~ 6~0776~ 9~02850~, 11~01129~ 13~05892~, 15~07121~ 17~08034~ 19~03870~: [21] 23~08034~ 27~03117~.'),
  (29303, 49, 4, 15, 'But speaking the truth in love, may grow up into him in all things, which is the head, even Christ:', '0~1161~ 3~226~ 4~1722~ 5~26~, 8~837~ 9~1519~ 10~846~ 13~3956~, 14~3739~ 15~2076~ 17~2776~, [18] 19~5547~:'),
  (13671, 18, 33, 12, 'Behold, in this thou art not just: I will answer thee, that God is greater than man.', '[1] 6~06663~: 9~06030~ 12~0433~ 14~07235~ 16~0582~.'),
  (28207, 45, 10, 3, 'For they being ignorant of God''s righteousness, and going about to establish their own righteousness, have not submitted themselves unto the righteousness of God.', '0~1063~ 3~50~ 5~2316~ 6~1343~, 7~2532~ 9~2212~ 11~2476~ 13~2398~ 14~1343~, 15~5293~ 16~3756~ 18~5293~ 21~1343~ 23~2316~.'),
  (30130, 58, 9, 9, 'Which was a figure for the time then present, in which were offered both gifts and sacrifices, that could not make him that did the service perfect, as pertaining to the conscience;', '0~3748~ [1] 3~3850~ 4~1519~ 6~2540~ 8~1764~, 9~2596~ 10~3739~ 12~4374~ 13~5037~ 14~1435~ 15~2532~ 16~2378~, 18~1410~ 19~3361~ 20~5048~ 25~3000~ 26~5048~, 29~2596~ 31~4893~;'),
  (16564, 20, 6, 15, 'Therefore shall his calamity come suddenly; suddenly shall he be broken without remedy.', '3~0343~ 4~0935~ 5~06597~; 6~06621~ 10~07665~ 12~04832~.'),
  (10733, 13, 12, 5, 'Eluzai, and Jerimoth, and Bealiah, and Shemariah, and Shephatiah the Haruphite,', '0~0498~, 2~03406~, 4~01183~, 6~08114~, 8~08203~ 10~02741~,'),
  (17481, 21, 8, 14, 'There is a vanity which is done upon the earth; that there be just men, unto whom it happeneth according to the work of the wicked; again, there be wicked men, to whom it happeneth according to the work of the righteous: I said that this also is vanity.', '&para; 1~03426~ 3~01892~ 6~06213~ 9~0776~; 13~06662~ [14] 18~05060~ 22~04639~ 25~07563~; 28~03426~ 29~07563~ [30] 34~05060~ 38~04639~ 41~06662~: 43~0559~ 46~01571~ [47] 48~01892~.'),
  (13790, 18, 37, 12, 'And it is turned round about by his counsels: that they may do whatsoever he commandeth them upon the face of the world in the earth.', '3~02015~ 5~04524~ 8~08458~: 12~06467~ 15~06680~ 19~06440~ 22~08398~ 25~0776~.'),
  (26846, 43, 19, 6, 'When the chief priests therefore and officers saw him, they cried out, saying, Crucify him, crucify him. Pilate saith unto them, Take ye him, and crucify him: for I find no fault in him.', '0~3753~ 3~749~ 4~3767~ 5~2532~ 6~5257~ 7~1492~ 8~846~, 11~2905~, 12~3004~, 13~4717~ [14] 15~4717~ [16] 17~4091~ 18~3004~ 20~846~, 21~2983~ 22~5210~ 23~846~, 24~2532~ 25~4717~ [26] 27~1063~ 28~1473~ 29~2147~ 30~3756~ 31~156~ 32~1722~ 33~846~.'),
  (27045, 44, 4, 7, 'And when they had set them in the midst, they asked, By what power, or by what name, have ye done this?', '0~2532~ 4~2476~ 5~846~ 6~1722~ 8~3319~, 10~4441~, 11~1722~ 12~4169~ 13~1411~, 14~2228~ 15~1722~ 16~4169~ 17~3686~, 18~4160~ 19~5210~ 20~4160~ 21~5124~?'),
  (23513, 40, 12, 14, 'Then the Pharisees went out, and held a council against him, how they might destroy him.', '&para; 0~1161~ 2~5330~ 4~1831~, 6~2983~ 8~4824~ 9~2596~ 10~846~, 11~3704~ 14~622~ 15~846~.'),
  (2571, 2, 35, 35, 'Them hath he filled with wisdom of heart, to work all manner of work, of the engraver, and of the cunning workman, and of the embroiderer, in blue, and in purple, in scarlet, and in fine linen, and of the weaver, even of them that do any work, and of those that devise cunning work.', '3~04390~ 5~02451~ 7~03820~, 9~06213~ 13~04399~, 16~02796~, 21~02803~, 25~07551~, 27~08504~, 30~0713~, 32~08438~ 33~08144~,* 37~08336~, 41~0707~, [42] 46~06213~ 47~03605~ 48~04399~, 53~02803~ 55~04284~.'),
  (17550, 22, 1, 4, 'Draw me, we will run after thee: the king hath brought me into his chambers: we will be glad and rejoice in thee, we will remember thy love more than wine: the upright love thee.', '0~04900~ 4~07323~ 5~0310~ 8~04428~ 10~0935~ 14~02315~: 18~01523~ 20~08055~ 25~02142~ 27~01730~ 30~03196~: 32~04339~ 33~0157~'),
  (18082, 23, 22, 21, 'And I will clothe him with thy robe, and strengthen him with thy girdle, and I will commit thy government into his hand: and he shall be a father to the inhabitants of Jerusalem, and to the house of Judah.', '3~03847~ 7~03801~, 9~02388~ 13~073~, 17~05414~ 19~04475~ 22~03027~: 28~01~ 31~03427~ 33~03389~, 37~01004~ 39~03063~.'),
  (450, 1, 18, 22, 'And the men turned their faces from thence, and went toward Sodom: but Abraham stood yet before the LORD.', '2~0582~ 5~06437~ 9~03212~ 11~05467~: 13~085~ 14~05975~ 15~05750~ 16~06440~ 18~03068~.'),
  (14140, 19, 18, 13, 'The LORD also thundered in the heavens, and the Highest gave his voice; hail stones and coals of fire.', '1~03068~ 3~07481~ 6~08064~, 9~05945~ 10~05414~ 12~06963~; 13~01259~ [14] 16~01513~ 18~0784~.'),
  (1078, 1, 36, 33, 'And Bela died, and Jobab the son of Zerah of Bozrah reigned in his stead.', '1~01106~ 2~04191~, 4~03103~ 6~01121~ 8~02226~ 10~01224~ 11~04427~'),
  (13676, 18, 33, 17, 'That he may withdraw man from his purpose, and hide pride from man.', '3~05493~ 4~0120~ [5 6] 7~04639~, 9~03680~ 10~01466~ 12~01397~.'),
  (6347, 6, 19, 19, 'And Haphraim, and Shihon, and Anaharath,', '1~02663~, 3~07866~, 5~0588~,'),
  (20864, 26, 18, 6, 'And hath not eaten upon the mountains, neither hath lifted up his eyes to the idols of the house of Israel, neither hath defiled his neighbour''s wife, neither hath come near to a menstruous woman,', '[0] 3~0398~ 6~02022~, 10~05375~ 12~05869~ 15~01544~ 18~01004~ 20~03478~, 23~02930~ 25~07453~ 26~0802~, 30~07126~ 33~05079~ 34~0802~,'),
  (27523, 44, 16, 24, 'Who, having received such a charge, thrust them into the inner prison, and made their feet fast in the stocks.', '0~3739~, 2~2983~ 3~5108~ 5~3852~, 6~906~ 7~846~ 8~1519~ 10~2082~ 11~5438~, 12~2532~ 13~805~ 14~846~ 15~4228~ 16~805~ 17~1519~ 19~3586~.'),
  (23071, 38, 13, 3, 'And it shall come to pass, that when any shall yet prophesy, then his father and his mother that begat him shall say unto him, Thou shalt not live; for thou speakest lies in the name of the LORD: and his father and his mother that begat him shall thrust him through when he prophesieth.', '[6] 8~0376~ 11~05012~, 14~01~ 17~0517~ 19~03205~ 22~0559~ 28~02421~; 31~01696~ 32~08267~ 35~08034~ 38~03068~: 41~01~ 44~0517~ 46~03205~ 49~01856~ 54~05012~.'),
  (9717, 12, 7, 2, 'Then a lord on whose hand the king leaned answered the man of God, and said, Behold, if the LORD would make windows in heaven, might this thing be? And he said, Behold, thou shalt see it with thine eyes, but shalt not eat thereof.', '2~07991~ 5~03027~ 7~04428~ 8~08172~ 9~06030~ 11~0376~ 13~0430~, 15~0559~, [17] 19~03068~ 21~06213~ 22~0699~ 24~08064~, 27~01697~ 31~0559~, 35~07200~ [36] 39~05869~, 43~0398~'),
  (13011, 18, 6, 24, 'Teach me, and I will hold my tongue: and cause me to understand wherein I have erred.', '0~03384~ 7~02790~: 12~0995~ 16~07686~.'),
  (3439, 3, 23, 32, 'It shall be unto you a sabbath of rest, and ye shall afflict your souls: in the ninth day of the month at even, from even unto even, shall ye celebrate your sabbath.', '[1 2] 6~07676~ 8~07677~, 12~06031~ 14~05315~: 17~08672~ [18] 21~02320~ 23~06153~, 25~06153~ 27~06153~, 30~07673~ 32~07676~.'),
  (6771, 7, 9, 10, 'And the trees said to the fig tree, Come thou, and reign over us.', '2~06086~ 3~0559~ 7~08384~, 8~03212~ [10] 11~04427~'),
  (26035, 42, 24, 30, 'And it came to pass, as he sat at meat with them, he took bread, and blessed it, and brake, and gave to them.', '0~2532~ 4~1096~, 5~1722~ 6~846~ 9~2625~ 10~3326~ 11~846~, 13~2983~ 14~740~, 16~2127~ [17] 18~2532~ 19~2806~, 21~1929~ 23~846~.'),
  (9777, 12, 9, 13, 'Then they hasted, and took every man his garment, and put it under him on the top of the stairs, and blew with trumpets, saying, Jehu is king.', '2~04116~, 4~03947~ 6~0376~ 8~0899~, 10~07760~ [11] 16~01634~ 19~04609~, 21~08628~ 23~07782~, 24~0559~, 25~03058~ 27~04427~.'),
  (13039, 18, 8, 1, 'Then answered Bildad the Shuhite, and said,', '&para; 1~06030~ 2~01085~ 4~07747~, 6~0559~,'),
  (11419, 14, 10, 15, 'So the king hearkened not unto the people: for the cause was of God, that the LORD might perform his word, which he spake by the hand of Ahijah the Shilonite to Jeroboam the son of Nebat.', '2~04428~ 3~08085~ 7~05971~: 10~05252~ 13~0430~, 16~03068~ 18~06965~ 20~01697~, 23~01696~ 26~03027~ 28~0281~ 30~07888~ 32~03379~ 34~01121~ 36~05028~.'),
  (26308, 43, 6, 36, 'But I said unto you, That ye also have seen me, and believe not.', '0~235~ 2~2036~ 4~5213~, 5~3754~ 6~3708~ 7~2532~ 9~3708~ 10~3165~, 11~2532~ 12~4100~ 13~3756~.'),
  (23927, 40, 22, 45, 'If David then call him Lord, how is he his son?', '0~1487~ 1~1138~ 2~3767~ 3~2564~ 4~846~ 5~2962~, 6~4459~ 8~2076~ 9~846~ 10~5207~?'),
  (2818, 3, 4, 18, 'And he shall put some of the blood upon the horns of the altar which is before the LORD, that is in the tabernacle of the congregation, and shall pour out all the blood at the bottom of the altar of the burnt offering, which is at the door of the tabernacle of the congregation.', '3~05414~ [4] 7~01818~ 10~07161~ 13~04196~ [15] 16~06440~ 18~03068~, [20] 23~0168~ 26~04150~, 30~08210~ 33~01818~ 36~03247~ 39~04196~ 43~05930~, [45 46] 48~06607~ 51~0168~ 54~04150~.'),
  (18609, 23, 47, 1, 'Come down, and sit in the dust, O virgin daughter of Babylon, sit on the ground: there is no throne, O daughter of the Chaldeans: for thou shalt no more be called tender and delicate.', '&para; 1~03381~, 3~03427~ 6~06083~, 8~01330~ 9~01323~ 11~0894~, 12~03427~ 15~0776~: [16 17] 19~03678~, 21~01323~ 24~03778~: 29~03254~ 31~07121~ 32~07390~ 34~06028~.'),
  (10367, 13, 2, 53, 'And the families of Kirjathjearim; the Ithrites, and the Puhites, and the Shumathites, and the Mishraites; of them came the Zareathites, and the Eshtaulites.', '2~04940~ 4~07157~; 6~03505~, 9~06336~, 12~08126~, 15~04954~; 18~03318~ 20~06882~, 23~0848~.'),
  (26120, 43, 2, 10, 'And saith unto him, Every man at the beginning doth set forth good wine; and when men have well drunk, then that which is worse: but thou hast kept the good wine until now.', '0~2532~ 1~3004~ 3~846~, 4~3956~ 5~444~ 8~4412~ 11~5087~ 12~2570~ 13~3631~; 14~2532~ 15~3752~ 19~3184~, 20~5119~ 24~1640~: [25] 26~4771~ 28~5083~ 30~2570~ 31~3631~ 32~2193~ 33~737~.'),
  (7211, 8, 4, 14, 'And the women said unto Naomi, Blessed be the LORD, which hath not left thee this day without a kinsman, that his name may be famous in Israel.', '2~0802~ 3~0559~ 5~05281~, 6~01288~ [7] 9~03068~, 13~07673~ 16~03117~ 19~01350~, 22~08034~ 25~07121~ 27~03478~.'),
  (12215, 15, 8, 5, 'Of the sons of Shechaniah; the son of Jahaziel, and with him three hundred males.', '2~01121~ 4~07935~; 6~01121~ 8~03166~, 12~07969~ 13~03967~ 14~02145~.'),
  (23328, 40, 7, 2, 'For with what judgment ye judge, ye shall be judged: and with what measure ye mete, it shall be measured to you again.', '0~1722~ 1~3739~ 2~1063~ 3~2917~ 5~2919~, 9~2919~: 10~2532~ 11~1722~ 12~3739~ 13~3358~ 15~3354~, 19~488~ 21~5213~ 22~488~.'),
  (15292, 19, 85, 12, 'Yea, the LORD shall give that which is good; and our land shall yield her increase.', '2~03068~ 4~05414~ [5 7] 8~02896~; 11~0776~ 13~05414~ 15~02981~.'),
  (23241, 40, 4, 22, 'And they immediately left the ship and their father, and followed him.', '0~1161~ 2~2112~ 3~863~ 5~4143~ 6~2532~ 7~846~ 8~3962~, 10~190~ 11~846~.'),
  (6387, 6, 20, 8, 'And on the other side Jordan by Jericho eastward, they assigned Bezer in the wilderness upon the plain out of the tribe of Reuben, and Ramoth in Gilead out of the tribe of Gad, and Golan in Bashan out of the tribe of Manasseh.', '4~05676~ 5~03383~ 7~03405~ 8~04217~, 10~05414~ 11~01221~ 14~04057~ 17~04334~ 21~04294~ 23~07205~, 25~07216~ 27~01568~ 31~04294~ 33~01410~, 35~01474~ 37~01316~ 41~04294~ 43~04519~.'),
  (2854, 3, 5, 19, 'It is a trespass offering: he hath certainly trespassed against the LORD.', '[1] 4~0817~: 7~0816~ 8~0816~ 11~03068~.'),
  (9726, 12, 7, 11, 'And he called the porters; and they told it to the king''s house within.', '2~07121~ 4~07778~; 7~05046~ [8] 11~04428~ 12~01004~ 13~06441~.'),
  (19225, 24, 10, 15, 'They are vanity, and the work of errors: in the time of their visitation they shall perish.', '[1] 2~01892~, [3] 5~04639~ 7~08595~: 10~06256~ 13~06486~ 16~06~.'),
  (8554, 10, 19, 35, 'I am this day fourscore years old: and can I discern between good and evil? can thy servant taste what I eat or what I drink? can I hear any more the voice of singing men and singing women? wherefore then should thy servant be yet a burden unto my lord the king?', '[1] 3~03117~ 4~08084~ 5~08141~ 6~01121~: [7] 10~03045~ 12~02896~ 14~07451~? 17~05650~ 18~02938~ 19~0834~ 21~0398~ 23~0834~ 25~08354~? 28~08085~ 32~06963~ 35~07891~ 38~07891~? 43~05650~ 47~04853~ 50~0113~ 52~04428~?'),
  (5397, 5, 18, 7, 'Then he shall minister in the name of the LORD his God, as all his brethren the Levites do, which stand there before the LORD.', '3~08334~ 6~08034~ 9~03068~ 11~0430~, 15~0251~ 17~03881~ [18] 20~05975~ 22~06440~ 24~03068~.'),
  (14860, 19, 64, 1, 'To the chief Musician, A Psalm of David. Hear my voice, O God, in my prayer: preserve my life from fear of the enemy.', '&para; [0 3~05329~, 5~04210~ 7] 7~01732~ 8~08085~ 10~06963~, 12~0430~, 15~07879~: 16~05341~ 18~02416~ 20~06343~ 23~0341~.'),
  (30541, 61, 3, 3, 'Knowing this first, that there shall come in the last days scoffers, walking after their own lusts,', '&para; 0~1097~ 1~5124~ 2~4412~, 3~3754~ 6~2064~ 7~1909~ 9~2078~ 10~2250~ 11~1703~, 12~4198~ 13~2596~ 14~846~ 15~2398~ 16~1939~,'),
  (17019, 20, 21, 26, 'He coveteth greedily all the day long: but the righteous giveth and spareth not.', '1~0183~ 2~08378~ 5~03117~ 9~06662~ 10~05414~ 12~02820~'),
  (13340, 18, 20, 5, 'That the triumphing of the wicked is short, and the joy of the hypocrite but for a moment?', '2~07445~ 5~07563~ [6] 7~07138~, 10~08057~ 13~02611~ [14] 17~07281~?'),
  (20496, 26, 1, 23, 'And under the firmament were their wings straight, the one toward the other: every one had two, which covered on this side, and every one had two, which covered on that side, their bodies.', '3~07549~ [4] 6~03671~ 7~03477~, 9~0802~ 12~0269~: 14~0376~ 16~08147~, 18~03680~ 21~02007~, 24~0376~ 26~08147~, 28~03680~ 31~02007~, 33~01472~.'),
  (2925, 3, 8, 3, 'And gather thou all the congregation together unto the door of the tabernacle of the congregation.', '1~06950~ 5~05712~ 6~06950~ 9~06607~ 12~0168~ 15~04150~.'),
  (20379, 25, 3, 16, 'He hath also broken my teeth with gravel stones, he hath covered me with ashes.', '3~01638~ 5~08127~ 8~02687~, 11~03728~ 14~0665~.'),
  (4229, 4, 16, 30, 'But if the LORD make a new thing, and the earth open her mouth, and swallow them up, with all that appertain unto them, and they go down quick into the pit; then ye shall understand that these men have provoked the LORD.', '3~03068~ 4~01254~ 7~01278~, 10~0127~ 11~06475~ 13~06310~, 17~01104~, [21] 27~03381~ 28~02416~ 31~07585~; 35~03045~ 38~0582~ 40~05006~ 42~03068~.'),
  (6251, 6, 15, 42, 'Libnah, and Ether, and Ashan,', '0~03841~, 2~06281~, 4~06228~,');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (10347, 13, 2, 33, 'And the sons of Jonathan; Peleth, and Zaza. These were the sons of Jerahmeel.', '2~01121~ 4~03129~; 5~06431~, 7~02117~. 11~01121~ 13~03396~.'),
  (14552, 19, 41, 1, 'To the chief Musician, A Psalm of David. Blessed is he that considereth the poor: the LORD will deliver him in time of trouble.', '&para; [0 3~05329~, 5~04210~ 7] 7~01732~ 8~0835~ [9] 12~07919~ 14~01800~: 16~03068~ 18~04422~ 21~03117~ 23~07451~.'),
  (11128, 13, 27, 11, 'The eighth captain for the eighth month was Sibbecai the Hushathite, of the Zarhites: and in his course were twenty and four thousand.', '1~08066~ [2] 5~08066~ 6~02320~ [7] 8~05444~ 10~02843~, 13~02227~: 17~04256~ [18] 19~06242~ 21~0702~ 22~0505~.'),
  (25556, 42, 13, 25, 'When once the master of the house is risen up, and hath shut to the door, and ye begin to stand without, and to knock at the door, saying, Lord, Lord, open unto us; and he shall answer and say unto you, I know you not whence ye are:', '1~302~ 2~575~* 3~3739~ 7~3617~ 10~1453~, 11~2532~ 13~608~ 16~2374~, 17~2532~ 19~756~ 21~2476~ 22~1854~, 23~2532~ 25~2925~ 28~2374~, 29~3004~, 30~2962~, 31~2962~, 32~455~ 34~2254~; 35~2532~ 38~611~ 40~2046~ 42~5213~, 44~1492~ 45~5209~ 46~3756~ 47~4159~ 49~2075~:'),
  (20327, 25, 1, 8, 'Jerusalem hath grievously sinned; therefore she is removed: all that honoured her despise her, because they have seen her nakedness: yea, she sigheth, and turneth backward.', '0~03389~ 2~02399~ 3~02398~; 7~05206~: 10~03513~ 12~02107~ 17~07200~ 19~06172~: 22~0584~, 24~07725~ 25~0268~.'),
  (5575, 5, 26, 3, 'And thou shalt go unto the priest that shall be in those days, and say unto him, I profess this day unto the LORD thy God, that I am come unto the country which the LORD sware unto our fathers for to give us.', '3~0935~ 6~03548~ 12~03117~, 14~0559~ 18~05046~ 20~03117~ 23~03068~ 25~0430~, 29~0935~ 32~0776~ 35~03068~ 36~07650~ 39~01~ 42~05414~'),
  (13259, 18, 16, 12, 'I was at ease, but he hath broken me asunder: he hath also taken me by my neck, and shaken me to pieces, and set me up for his mark.', '3~07961~, 9~06565~: 13~0270~ [14] 17~06203~, 22~06327~, 26~06965~ 29~04307~.'),
  (22529, 31, 1, 10, 'For thy violence against thy brother Jacob shame shall cover thee, and thou shalt be cut off for ever.', '&para; [1] 2~02555~ 5~0251~ 6~03290~ 7~0955~ 9~03680~ 16~03772~ 18~05769~.'),
  (20157, 24, 49, 21, 'The earth is moved at the noise of their fall, at the cry the noise thereof was heard in the Red sea.', '1~0776~ 3~07493~ 6~06963~ 9~05307~, 12~06818~ 14~06963~ 17~08085~ 20~05488~ 21~03220~.'),
  (16717, 20, 11, 20, 'They that are of a froward heart are abomination to the LORD: but such as are upright in their way are his delight.', '&para; 5~06141~ 6~03820~ [7] 8~08441~ 11~03068~: [13 15] 16~08549~ [18] 19~01870~ [20] 22~07522~.'),
  (8113, 10, 3, 25, 'Thou knowest Abner the son of Ner, that he came to deceive thee, and to know thy going out and thy coming in, and to know all that thou doest.', '1~03045~ 2~074~ 4~01121~ 6~05369~, 9~0935~ 11~06601~ 15~03045~ 18~04161~ 22~04126~ 23~03996~,* 26~03045~ 30~06213~.'),
  (15035, 19, 73, 6, 'Therefore pride compasseth them about as a chain; violence covereth them as a garment.', '1~01346~ 7~06059~; 8~02555~ 9~05848~ [11] 13~07897~.'),
  (2707, 2, 39, 38, 'And the golden altar, and the anointing oil, and the sweet incense, and the hanging for the tabernacle door,', '2~02091~ 3~04196~, 6~04888~ 7~08081~, 10~05561~ 11~07004~, 14~04539~ 17~0168~ 18~06607~,'),
  (19382, 24, 17, 16, 'As for me, I have not hastened from being a pastor to follow thee: neither have I desired the woeful day; thou knowest: that which came out of my lips was right before thee.', '6~0213~ [8] 10~07462~ 12~0310~ 17~0183~ 19~0605~ 20~03117~; 22~03045~: 26~04161~ 29~08193~ [31] 32~05227~ 33~06440~.'),
  (22895, 38, 1, 8, 'I saw by night, and behold a man riding upon a red horse, and he stood among the myrtle trees that were in the bottom; and behind him were there red horses, speckled, and white.', '1~07200~ 3~03915~, 7~0376~ 8~07392~ 11~0122~ 12~05483~, 15~05975~ 19~01918~ [21] 24~04699~; 26~0310~ [28 29] 30~0122~ 31~05483~, 32~08320~, 34~03836~.'),
  (12140, 15, 4, 21, 'Give ye now commandment to cause these men to cease, and that this city be not builded, until another commandment shall be given from me.', '0~07761~ 2~03705~ 3~02942~ 5~0989~ 6~0479~ 7~01400~ 9~0989~, 12~01791~ 13~07149~ 15~03809~ 16~01124~, 17~05705~ [18] 19~02941~ 22~07761~ 24~04481~.'),
  (19415, 24, 18, 22, 'Let a cry be heard from their houses, when thou shalt bring a troop suddenly upon them: for they have digged a pit to take me, and hid snares for my feet.', '2~02201~ 4~08085~ 7~01004~, 11~0935~ 13~01416~ 14~06597~ 20~03738~ 22~07745~ 23~07882~* 25~03920~ 28~02934~ 29~06341~ 32~07272~.'),
  (11976, 14, 35, 1, 'Moreover Josiah kept a passover unto the LORD in Jerusalem: and they killed the passover on the fourteenth day of the first month.', '&para; 1~02977~ 2~06213~ 4~06453~ 7~03068~ 9~03389~: 12~07819~ 14~06453~ 17~06240~ [18] 18~0702~ 21~07223~ 22~02320~.'),
  (12553, 16, 9, 33, 'Howbeit thou art just in all that is brought upon us; for thou hast done right, but we have done wickedly:', '[2] 3~06662~ 8~0935~ 14~06213~ 15~0571~, 20~07561~:'),
  (29885, 55, 3, 16, 'All scripture is given by inspiration of God, and is profitable for doctrine, for reproof, for correction, for instruction in righteousness:', '0~3956~ 1~1124~ [2] 7~2315~, 8~2532~ [9] 10~5624~ 11~4314~ 12~1319~, 13~4314~ 14~1650~, 15~4314~ 16~1882~, 17~4314~ 18~3809~ 19~1722~ 20~1343~:'),
  (25877, 42, 21, 37, 'And in the day time he was teaching in the temple; and at night he went out, and abode in the mount that is called the mount of Olives.', '0~1161~ 4~2250~ 6~2258~ 7~1321~ 8~1722~ 10~2411~; 11~1161~ 13~3571~ 16~1831~, 18~835~ 19~1519~ 21~3735~ 24~2564~ [25 26] 28~1636~.'),
  (1809, 2, 10, 27, 'But the LORD hardened Pharaoh''s heart, and he would not let them go.', '2~03068~ 3~02388~ 4~06547~ 5~03820~, 8~014~ 12~07971~.'),
  (27099, 44, 5, 24, 'Now when the high priest and the captain of the temple and the chief priests heard these things, they doubted of them whereunto this would grow.', '0~1161~ 1~5037~ 2~5613~ 4~2409~ 5~2532~ 7~4755~ 10~2411~ 11~2532~ 14~749~ 15~191~ 16~5128~ 17~3056~, 19~1280~ 20~4012~ 21~846~ 22~302~ 23~5101~* 24~5124~ 26~1096~.'),
  (10873, 13, 17, 2, 'Then Nathan said unto David, Do all that is in thine heart; for God is with thee.', '1~05416~ 2~0559~ 4~01732~, 5~06213~ [8] 11~03824~; 13~0430~ [14]'),
  (13295, 18, 18, 10, 'The snare is laid for him in the ground, and a trap for him in the way.', '1~02256~ [2] 3~02934~ 8~0776~, 11~04434~ 16~05410~.'),
  (9069, 11, 9, 10, 'And it came to pass at the end of twenty years, when Solomon had built the two houses, the house of the LORD, and the king''s house,', '&para; 7~07097~ 9~06242~ 10~08141~, 12~08010~ 14~01129~ 16~08147~ 17~01004~, 19~01004~ 22~03068~, 25~04428~ 26~01004~,'),
  (25821, 42, 20, 28, 'Saying, Master, Moses wrote unto us, If any man''s brother die, having a wife, and he die without children, that his brother should take his wife, and raise up seed unto his brother.', '0~3004~, 1~1320~, 2~3475~ 3~1125~ 5~2254~, 6~1437~ 8~5100~ 9~80~ 10~599~, 11~2192~ 13~1135~, 14~2532~ 15~3778~ 16~599~ 18~815~, 19~2443~ 20~846~ 21~80~ 23~2983~ 25~1135~, 26~2532~ 28~1817~ 29~4690~ 31~846~ 32~80~.'),
  (18051, 23, 21, 7, 'And he saw a chariot with a couple of horsemen, a chariot of asses, and a chariot of camels; and he hearkened diligently with much heed:', '2~07200~ 4~07393~ [5] 7~06776~ 9~06571~, 11~07393~ 13~02543~, [14] 16~07393~ 18~01581~; 21~07181~ 22~07182~ 24~07227~ 25~07182~:'),
  (12381, 16, 4, 13, 'Therefore set I in the lower places behind the wall, and on the higher places, I even set the people after their families with their swords, their spears, and their bows.', '1~05975~ 5~08482~ 6~04725~ 7~0310~ 9~02346~, [10] 14~06706~ 15~06708~,* 18~05975~ 20~05971~ 23~04940~ 26~02719~, 28~07420~, 31~07198~.'),
  (2285, 2, 27, 8, 'Hollow with boards shalt thou make it: as it was shewed thee in the mount, so shall they make it.', '0~05014~ 2~03871~ 5~06213~ 10~07200~ 14~02022~, 18~06213~ [19]'),
  (30357, 59, 4, 4, 'Ye adulterers and adulteresses, know ye not that the friendship of the world is enmity with God? whosoever therefore will be a friend of the world is the enemy of God.', '1~3432~ 2~2532~ 3~3428~, 5~1492~ 6~3756~ 7~3754~ 9~5373~ 12~2889~ 13~2076~ 14~2189~ 16~2316~? 17~302~ 18~3739~* 19~3767~ 21~1511~ 22~1014~* 24~5384~ 27~2889~ 28~2525~ 30~2190~ 32~2316~.'),
  (16092, 19, 121, 2, 'My help cometh from the LORD, which made heaven and earth.', '1~05828~ [2] 5~03068~, 7~06213~ 8~08064~ 10~0776~.'),
  (29444, 50, 3, 7, 'But what things were gain to me, those I counted loss for Christ.', '0~235~ 2~3748~ 3~2258~ 4~2771~ 6~3427~, 7~5023~ 9~2233~ 10~2209~ 11~1223~ 12~5547~.'),
  (21133, 26, 27, 3, 'And say unto Tyrus, O thou that art situate at the entry of the sea, which art a merchant of the people for many isles, Thus saith the Lord GOD; O Tyrus, thou hast said, I am of perfect beauty.', '1~0559~ 3~06865~, 8~03427~ 11~03997~ 14~03220~, [15 16] 18~07402~ 21~05971~ 23~07227~ 24~0339~, 26~0559~ 28~0136~ 29~03069~; 31~06865~, 34~0559~, [36] 38~03632~ 39~03308~.'),
  (31021, 66, 18, 12, 'The merchandise of gold, and silver, and precious stones, and of pearls, and fine linen, and purple, and silk, and scarlet, and all thyine wood, and all manner vessels of ivory, and all manner vessels of most precious wood, and of brass, and iron, and marble,', '1~1117~ 3~5557~, 4~2532~ 5~696~, 6~2532~ 7~5093~ 8~3037~, 9~2532~ 11~3135~, 12~2532~ 14~1040~, 15~2532~ 16~4209~, 17~2532~ 18~4596~, 19~2532~ 20~2847~, 21~2532~ 22~3956~ 23~2367~ 24~3586~, 25~2532~ 27~3956~ 28~4632~ 30~1661~, 31~2532~ 33~3956~ 34~4632~ 35~1537~ 37~5093~ 38~3586~, 39~2532~ 41~5475~, 42~2532~ 43~4604~, 44~2532~ 45~3139~,'),
  (8395, 10, 14, 32, 'And Absalom answered Joab, Behold, I sent unto thee, saying, Come hither, that I may send thee to the king, to say, Wherefore am I come from Geshur? it had been good for me to have been there still: now therefore let me see the king''s face; and if there be any iniquity in me, let him kill me.', '1~053~ 2~0559~ 3~03097~, 6~07971~ 9~0559~, 10~0935~ 15~07971~ 19~04428~, 21~0559~, 25~0935~ 27~01650~? [28 30] 31~02896~ [34 36] 43~07200~ 45~04428~ 46~06440~; 50~03426~ [51] 52~05771~ 57~04191~'),
  (9540, 11, 22, 52, 'And he did evil in the sight of the LORD, and walked in the way of his father, and in the way of his mother, and in the way of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, who made Israel to sin:', '2~06213~ 3~07451~ 6~05869~ 9~03068~, 11~03212~ 14~01870~ 17~01~, 21~01870~ 24~0517~, 28~01870~ 30~03379~ 32~01121~ 34~05028~, 37~03478~ 39~02398~:'),
  (23717, 40, 17, 7, 'And Jesus came and touched them, and said, Arise, and be not afraid.', '0~2532~ 1~2424~ 2~4334~ 4~680~ 5~846~, 6~2532~ 7~2036~, 8~1453~, 9~2532~ 10~5399~ 11~3361~ 12~5399~.'),
  (27661, 44, 20, 19, 'Serving the Lord with all humility of mind, and with many tears, and temptations, which befell me by the lying in wait of the Jews:', '0~1398~ 2~2962~ 3~3326~ 4~3956~ 7~5012~, 8~2532~ 10~4183~ 11~1144~, 12~2532~ 13~3986~, 14~3588~ 15~4819~ 16~3427~ 17~1722~ 21~1917~ 24~2453~:'),
  (18513, 23, 42, 24, 'Who gave Jacob for a spoil, and Israel to the robbers? did not the LORD, he against whom we have sinned? for they would not walk in his ways, neither were they obedient unto his law.', '1~05414~ 2~03290~ 5~04933~ 6~04882~,* 8~03478~ 11~0962~? 15~03068~, 18~02098~ 21~02398~? 24~014~ 26~01980~ 29~01870~, 33~08085~ 36~08451~.'),
  (21136, 26, 27, 6, 'Of the oaks of Bashan have they made thine oars; the company of the Ashurites have made thy benches of ivory, brought out of the isles of Chittim.', '[0] 2~0437~ 4~01316~ 7~06213~ 9~04880~; 11~01323~ 14~0839~ 16~06213~ 18~07175~ [19] 20~08127~, [21] 25~0339~ 27~03794~.'),
  (10936, 13, 20, 2, 'And David took the crown of their king from off his head, and found it to weigh a talent of gold, and there were precious stones in it; and it was set upon David''s head: and he brought also exceeding much spoil out of the city.', '1~01732~ 2~03947~ 4~05850~ 7~04428~ 11~07218~, 13~04672~ 16~04948~ 18~03603~ 20~02091~, [22 23] 24~03368~ 25~068~ 33~01732~ 34~07218~: 37~03318~ 39~03966~ 40~07235~ 41~07998~ 45~05892~.'),
  (29285, 49, 3, 18, 'May be able to comprehend with all saints what is the breadth, and length, and depth, and height;', '2~1840~ 4~2638~ 5~4862~ 6~3956~ 7~40~ 8~5101~ [9] 11~4114~, 12~2532~ 13~3372~, 14~2532~ 15~899~, 16~2532~ 17~5311~;'),
  (25224, 42, 7, 17, 'And this rumour of him went forth throughout all Judaea, and throughout all the region round about.', '0~2532~ 1~3778~ 2~3056~ 3~4012~ 4~846~ 6~1831~ 7~1722~ 8~3650~ 9~2449~, 10~2532~ 11~1722~ 12~3956~ 16~4066~.'),
  (11196, 13, 29, 24, 'And all the princes, and the mighty men, and all the sons likewise of king David, submitted themselves unto Solomon the king.', '3~08269~, 7~01368~, 11~01121~ 14~04428~ 15~01732~, 17~05414~ 18~08478~* 19~03027~ 20~08010~ 22~04428~.'),
  (6992, 7, 17, 5, 'And the man Micah had an house of gods, and made an ephod, and teraphim, and consecrated one of his sons, who became his priest.', '2~0376~ 3~04318~ 6~01004~ 8~0430~, 10~06213~ 12~0646~, 14~08655~, 16~04390~ 17~03027~* 18~0259~ 21~01121~, 25~03548~.'),
  (8429, 10, 15, 33, 'Unto whom David said, If thou passest on with me, then thou shalt be a burden unto me:', '2~01732~ 3~0559~, 7~05674~ 15~04853~'),
  (16980, 20, 20, 17, 'Bread of deceit is sweet to a man; but afterwards his mouth shall be filled with gravel.', '&para; 0~03899~ 2~08267~ [3] 4~06156~ 7~0376~; 9~0310~ 11~06310~ 14~04390~ 16~02687~.'),
  (30852, 66, 8, 9, 'And the third part of the creatures which were in the sea, and had life, died; and the third part of the ships were destroyed.', '0~2532~ 3~5154~ 6~2938~ 7~3588~ 9~1722~ 11~2281~, 13~2192~ 14~5590~, 15~599~; 16~2532~ 19~5154~ 22~4143~ 24~1311~.'),
  (25058, 42, 3, 21, 'Now when all the people were baptized, it came to pass, that Jesus also being baptized, and praying, the heaven was opened,', '&para; 0~1161~ 2~537~ 4~2992~ 6~907~ 7~1722~,* 11~1096~, 13~2424~ 14~2532~ 16~907~, 17~2532~ 18~4336~, 20~3772~ 22~455~,'),
  (10104, 12, 19, 35, 'And it came to pass that night, that the angel of the LORD went out, and smote in the camp of the Assyrians an hundred fourscore and five thousand: and when they arose early in the morning, behold, they were all dead corpses.', '&para; 6~03915~, 9~04397~ 12~03068~ 14~03318~, 16~05221~ 19~04264~ 22~0804~ 24~03967~ 25~08084~ 27~02568~ 28~0505~: 33~07925~ 36~01242~, [39] 41~04191~ 42~06297~.'),
  (15185, 19, 78, 63, 'The fire consumed their young men; and their maidens were not given to marriage.', '1~0784~ 2~0398~ 5~0970~; 8~01330~ 13~01984~.'),
  (25632, 42, 15, 31, 'And he said unto him, Son, thou art ever with me, and all that I have is thine.', '0~1161~ 2~2036~ 4~846~, 5~5043~, 6~4771~ 7~1488~ 8~3842~ 9~3326~ 10~1700~, 11~2532~ 12~3956~ 15~1699~ 16~2076~ 17~4674~.'),
  (5843, 5, 33, 27, 'The eternal God is thy refuge, and underneath are the everlasting arms: and he shall thrust out the enemy from before thee; and shall say, Destroy them.', '1~06924~ 2~0430~ [3 4] 5~04585~, [8] 10~05769~ 11~02220~: 16~01644~ 18~0341~ 20~06440~ 24~0559~, 25~08045~ [26]'),
  (29756, 54, 3, 9, 'Holding the mystery of the faith in a pure conscience.', '0~2192~ 2~3466~ 5~4102~ 6~1722~ 8~2513~ 9~4893~.'),
  (5762, 5, 31, 28, 'Gather unto me all the elders of your tribes, and your officers, that I may speak these words in their ears, and call heaven and earth to record against them.', '0~06950~ 5~02205~ 8~07626~, 11~07860~, 15~01696~ 17~01697~ 20~0241~, 22~05749~ 23~08064~ 25~0776~ 27~05749~'),
  (19679, 24, 30, 3, 'For, lo, the days come, saith the LORD, that I will bring again the captivity of my people Israel and Judah, saith the LORD: and I will cause them to return to the land that I gave to their fathers, and they shall possess it.', '3~03117~ 4~0935~, 5~05002~ 7~03068~, 12~07725~ 14~07622~ 17~05971~ 18~03478~ 20~03063~, 21~0559~ 23~03068~: 30~07725~ 33~0776~ 36~05414~ 39~01~, 43~03423~'),
  (17016, 20, 21, 23, 'Whoso keepeth his mouth and his tongue keepeth his soul from troubles.', '&para; 1~08104~ 3~06310~ 6~03956~ 7~08104~ 9~05315~ 11~06869~.'),
  (22829, 36, 2, 15, 'This is the rejoicing city that dwelt carelessly, that said in her heart, I am, and there is none beside me: how is she become a desolation, a place for beasts to lie down in! every one that passeth by her shall hiss, and wag his hand.', '[1] 3~05947~ 4~05892~ 6~03427~ 7~0983~, 9~0559~ 12~03824~, [14] [16 17] 19~0657~ 26~08047~, 30~02416~ 34~04769~! 39~05674~ 42~08319~, [43] 44~05128~ 46~03027~.'),
  (2152, 2, 23, 3, 'Neither shalt thou countenance a poor man in his cause.', '3~01921~ 5~01800~ 9~07379~.'),
  (4769, 4, 33, 3, 'And they departed from Rameses in the first month, on the fifteenth day of the first month; on the morrow after the passover the children of Israel went out with an high hand in the sight of all the Egyptians.', '2~05265~ 4~07486~ 7~07223~ 8~02320~, 11~02568~ 12~06240~* 13~03117~ 16~07223~ 17~02320~; 20~04283~ 23~06453~ 25~01121~ 27~03478~ 29~03318~ 32~07311~ 33~03027~ 36~05869~ 40~04714~.'),
  (14712, 19, 51, 12, 'Restore unto me the joy of thy salvation; and uphold me with thy free spirit.', '0~07725~ 4~08342~ 7~03468~; 9~05564~ [11 12] 13~05081~ 14~07307~.'),
  (29317, 49, 4, 29, 'Let no corrupt communication proceed out of your mouth, but that which is good to the use of edifying, that it may minister grace unto the hearers.', '0~4550~ 1~3956~ 2~3361~* 3~4550~ 4~3056~ 5~1607~ 7~1537~ 8~5216~ 9~4750~, 10~235~ 12~1536~ 14~18~ 15~4314~ 17~5532~ 19~3619~, 20~2443~ 23~1325~ 24~5485~ 27~191~.'),
  (30802, 66, 5, 7, 'And he came and took the book out of the right hand of him that sat upon the throne.', '0~2532~ 2~2064~ 3~2532~ 4~2983~ 6~975~ 8~1537~ 11~1188~ 15~2521~ 16~1909~ 18~2362~.'),
  (13901, 18, 41, 4, 'Will he make a covenant with thee? wilt thou take him for a servant for ever?', '2~03772~ 4~01285~ 9~03947~ 13~05650~ 15~05769~?'),
  (2448, 2, 32, 5, 'And when Aaron saw it, he built an altar before it; and Aaron made proclamation, and said, To morrow is a feast to the LORD.', '2~0175~ 3~07200~ [4] 6~01129~ 8~04196~ 9~06440~ 12~0175~ 14~07121~, 16~0559~, 18~04279~ [19] 21~02282~ 24~03068~.'),
  (26672, 43, 13, 27, 'And after the sop Satan entered into him. Then said Jesus unto him, That thou doest, do quickly.', '0~2532~ 1~3326~ 3~5119~ 4~5596~* 5~4567~ 6~1525~ 7~1519~ 8~1565~. 9~3767~ 10~3004~ 11~2424~ 13~846~, 14~3739~ 16~4160~, 17~4160~ 18~5032~.'),
  (587, 1, 23, 12, 'And Abraham bowed down himself before the people of the land.', '1~085~ 3~07812~ 5~06440~ 7~05971~ 10~0776~.'),
  (16298, 19, 142, 3, 'When my spirit was overwhelmed within me, then thou knewest my path. In the way wherein I walked have they privily laid a snare for me.', '2~07307~ 4~05848~ 9~03045~ 11~05410~. 14~0734~ 15~02098~ 17~01980~ 21~02934~ 23~06341~'),
  (17472, 21, 8, 5, 'Whoso keepeth the commandment shall feel no evil thing: and a wise man''s heart discerneth both time and judgment.', '1~08104~ 3~04687~ 5~03045~ 7~07451~ 8~01697~: 12~02450~ 13~03820~ 14~03045~ 16~06256~ 18~04941~.'),
  (17660, 22, 8, 11, 'Solomon had a vineyard at Baalhamon; he let out the vineyard unto keepers; every one for the fruit thereof was to bring a thousand pieces of silver.', '0~08010~ 3~03754~ 5~01174~; 8~05414~ 10~03754~ 12~05201~; 14~0376~ 17~06529~ 21~0935~ 23~0505~ [24] 26~03701~.'),
  (22133, 28, 2, 19, 'And I will betroth thee unto me for ever; yea, I will betroth thee unto me in righteousness, and in judgment, and in lovingkindness, and in mercies.', '3~0781~ 8~05769~; 12~0781~ 17~06664~, 20~04941~, 23~02617~, 26~07356~.'),
  (26536, 43, 10, 40, 'And went away again beyond Jordan into the place where John at first baptized; and there he abode.', '0~2532~ 2~565~ 3~3825~ 4~4008~ 5~2446~ 6~1519~ 8~5117~ 9~3699~ 10~2491~ 12~4412~ 13~907~ 14~2258~;* 15~2532~ 16~1563~ 18~3306~.'),
  (23362, 40, 8, 7, 'And Jesus saith unto him, I will come and heal him.', '0~2532~ 1~2424~ 2~3004~ 4~846~, 5~1473~ 7~2064~ 9~2323~ 10~846~.'),
  (8140, 10, 5, 1, 'Then came all the tribes of Israel to David unto Hebron, and spake, saying, Behold, we are thy bone and thy flesh.', '&para; 1~0935~ 4~07626~ 6~03478~ 8~01732~ 10~02275~, 12~0559~, 13~0559~, [16] 18~06106~ 21~01320~.'),
  (29124, 48, 3, 6, 'Even as Abraham believed God, and it was accounted to him for righteousness.', '&para; 1~2531~ 2~11~ 3~4100~ 4~2316~, 5~2532~ 8~3049~ 10~846~ 11~1519~ 12~1343~.'),
  (15301, 19, 86, 8, 'Among the gods there is none like unto thee, O Lord; neither are there any works like unto thy works.', '&para; 2~0430~ [3 4] 10~0136~; [12 15] 19~04639~.'),
  (26158, 43, 3, 23, 'And John also was baptizing in Aenon near to Salim, because there was much water there: and they came, and were baptized.', '0~1161~ 1~2491~ 2~2532~ 3~2258~ 4~907~ 5~1722~ 6~137~ 7~1451~ 9~4530~, 10~3754~ 12~2258~ 13~4183~ 14~5204~ 15~1563~: 16~2532~ 18~3854~, 19~2532~ 21~907~.'),
  (6396, 6, 21, 8, 'And the children of Israel gave by lot unto the Levites these cities with their suburbs, as the LORD commanded by the hand of Moses.', '2~01121~ 4~03478~ 5~05414~ 7~01486~ 10~03881~ 12~05892~ 15~04054~, 18~03068~ 19~06680~ 22~03027~ 24~04872~.'),
  (4505, 4, 26, 11, 'Notwithstanding the children of Korah died not.', '2~01121~ 4~07141~ 5~04191~'),
  (29126, 48, 3, 8, 'And the scripture, foreseeing that God would justify the heathen through faith, preached before the gospel unto Abraham, saying, In thee shall all nations be blessed.', '0~1161~ 2~1124~, 3~4275~ 4~3754~ 5~2316~ 7~1344~ 9~1484~ 10~1537~ 11~4102~, 15~4283~ 17~11~, [18] 18~3754~, 19~1722~ 20~4671~ 21~1757~ 22~3956~ 23~1484~ 25~1757~.'),
  (22193, 28, 7, 6, 'For they have made ready their heart like an oven, whiles they lie in wait: their baker sleepeth all the night; in the morning it burneth as a flaming fire.', '4~07126~ 6~03820~ 9~08574~, 14~0693~: 16~0644~ 17~03463~ 20~03915~; 23~01242~ 25~01197~ 28~03852~ 29~0784~.'),
  (27463, 44, 15, 5, 'But there rose up certain of the sect of the Pharisees which believed, saying, That it was needful to circumcise them, and to command them to keep the law of Moses.', '0~1161~ 3~1817~ 4~5100~ 5~575~ 7~139~ 10~5330~ 12~4100~, 13~3004~, 14~3754~ 17~1163~ 19~4059~ 20~846~, 21~5037~ 23~3853~ [24] 26~5083~ 28~3551~ 30~3475~.'),
  (15225, 19, 80, 18, 'So will not we go back from thee: quicken us, and we will call upon thy name.', '5~05472~ 8~02421~ 13~07121~ 16~08034~.'),
  (8888, 11, 5, 2, 'And Solomon sent to Hiram, saying,', '1~08010~ 2~07971~ 4~02438~, 5~0559~,'),
  (5407, 5, 18, 17, 'And the LORD said unto me, They have well spoken that which they have spoken.', '2~03068~ 3~0559~ 8~03190~ [9 10] 14~01696~.'),
  (13993, 19, 5, 11, 'But let all those that put their trust in thee rejoice: let them ever shout for joy, because thou defendest them: let them also that love thy name be joyful in thee.', '7~02620~ 10~08055~: 13~05769~ 16~07442~, 19~05526~ 25~0157~ 27~08034~ 29~05970~'),
  (24936, 42, 1, 32, 'He shall be great, and shall be called the Son of the Highest: and the Lord God shall give unto him the throne of his father David:', '0~3778~ 2~2071~ 3~3173~, 4~2532~ 7~2564~ 9~5207~ 12~5310~: 13~2532~ 15~2962~ 16~2316~ 18~1325~ 20~846~ 22~2362~ 24~846~ 25~3962~ 26~1138~:'),
  (25961, 42, 23, 12, 'And the same day Pilate and Herod were made friends together: for before they were at enmity between themselves.', '0~3739~ 1~1161~ 2~846~ 3~1722~* 4~2250~ 5~4091~ 6~2532~ 7~2264~ 9~1096~ 10~5384~ 11~240~ 12~3326~* 13~5037~:* 14~1063~ 15~4391~ 17~5607~ 18~1722~ 19~2189~ 20~4314~ 21~1438~.'),
  (13236, 18, 15, 24, 'Trouble and anguish shall make him afraid; they shall prevail against him, as a king ready to the battle.', '0~06862~ 2~04691~ 6~01204~; 9~08630~ 14~04428~ 15~06264~ 18~03593~.'),
  (8952, 11, 7, 10, 'And the foundation was of costly stones, even great stones, stones of ten cubits, and stones of eight cubits.', '2~03245~ [3 4] 5~03368~ 6~068~, 8~01419~ 9~068~, 10~068~ 12~06235~ 13~0520~, 15~068~ 17~08083~ 18~0520~.'),
  (14956, 19, 69, 12, 'They that sit in the gate speak against me; and I was the song of the drunkards.', '3~03427~ 5~08179~ 6~07878~ [11] 13~05058~ 16~08354~ 17~07941~.*'),
  (11109, 13, 26, 24, 'And Shebuel the son of Gershom, the son of Moses, was ruler of the treasures.', '1~07619~ 3~01121~ 5~01647~, 7~01121~ 9~04872~, [10] 11~05057~ 14~0214~.'),
  (25564, 42, 13, 33, 'Nevertheless I must walk to day, and to morrow, and the day following: for it cannot be that a prophet perish out of Jerusalem.', '0~4133~ 1~3165~ 2~1163~ 3~4198~ 5~4594~, 6~2532~ 8~839~, 9~2532~ [11] 12~2192~: 13~3754~ 16~1735~ 17~3756~* 20~4396~ 21~622~ 23~1854~ 24~2419~.'),
  (28617, 46, 11, 1, 'Be ye followers of me, even as I also am of Christ.', '&para; 0~1096~ 2~3402~ 4~3450~, 6~2531~ 8~2504~ [9] 11~5547~.'),
  (26020, 42, 24, 15, 'And it came to pass, that, while they communed together and reasoned, Jesus himself drew near, and went with them.', '0~2532~ 4~1096~, 6~1722~ 7~846~ 8~3656~ [9] 10~2532~ 11~4802~, 12~2424~ 13~846~ 14~2532~ 15~1448~, 18~4848~ 19~846~.'),
  (17733, 23, 3, 17, 'Therefore the Lord will smite with a scab the crown of the head of the daughters of Zion, and the LORD will discover their secret parts.', '2~0136~ 7~05596~ 12~06936~ 15~01323~ 17~06726~, 20~03068~ 22~06168~ 25~06596~.'),
  (21453, 26, 38, 19, 'For in my jealousy and in the fire of my wrath have I spoken, Surely in that day there shall be a great shaking in the land of Israel;', '3~07068~ [4] 7~0784~ 10~05678~ 13~01696~, 17~03117~ 22~01419~ 23~07494~ 26~0127~ 28~03478~;'),
  (17735, 23, 3, 19, 'The chains, and the bracelets, and the mufflers,', '1~05188~, 4~08285~, 7~07479~,'),
  (823, 1, 29, 24, 'And Laban gave unto his daughter Leah Zilpah his maid for an handmaid.', '1~03837~ 2~05414~ 5~01323~ 6~03812~ 7~02153~ 9~08198~ [10] 12~08198~.');
