VALUES
  (3910, 4, 7, 55, 'His offering was one silver charger of the weight of an hundred and thirty shekels, one silver bowl of seventy shekels, after the shekel of the sanctuary; both of them full of fine flour mingled with oil for a meat offering:', '1~07133~ [2] 3~0259~ 4~03701~ 5~07086~ 8~04948~ 11~03967~ 13~07970~ [14] 15~0259~ 16~03701~ 17~04219~ 19~07657~ 20~08255~, 23~08255~ 26~06944~; 27~08147~ 30~04392~ 33~05560~ 34~01101~ 36~08081~ 40~04503~:'),
  (445, 1, 18, 17, 'And the LORD said, Shall I hide from Abraham that thing which I do;', '2~03068~ 3~0559~, 6~03680~ 8~085~ 11~0834~ 13~06213~;'),
  (25334, 42, 9, 21, 'And he straitly charged them, and commanded them to tell no man that thing;', '0~1161~ 3~2008~ 4~846~, 6~3853~ [7] 9~2036~ 11~3367~ 13~5124~;'),
  (17369, 21, 3, 1, 'To every thing there is a season, and a time to every purpose under the heaven:', '&para; [2 4] 6~02165~, 9~06256~ 12~02656~ 15~08064~:'),
  (157, 1, 6, 19, 'And of every living thing of all flesh, two of every sort shalt thou bring into the ark, to keep them alive with thee; they shall be male and female.', '4~02416~ 7~01320~, 8~08147~ [11] 14~0935~ 17~08392~, [20] 21~02421~ 27~02145~ 29~05347~.'),
  (8332, 10, 13, 8, 'So Tamar went to her brother Amnon''s house; and he was laid down. And she took flour, and kneaded it, and made cakes in his sight, and did bake the cakes.', '1~08559~ 2~03212~ 5~0251~ 6~0550~ 7~01004~; 12~07901~. 15~03947~ 16~01217~, 18~03888~ [19] 22~03823~ 25~05869~, 28~01310~ 30~03834~.'),
  (4059, 4, 11, 30, 'And Moses gat him into the camp, he and the elders of Israel.', '1~04872~ 2~0622~ 6~04264~, 10~02205~ 12~03478~.'),
  (2719, 2, 40, 7, 'And thou shalt set the laver between the tent of the congregation and the altar, and shalt put water therein.', '3~05414~ 5~03595~ 8~0168~ 11~04150~ 14~04196~, 17~05414~ 18~04325~'),
  (1328, 1, 43, 33, 'And they sat before him, the firstborn according to his birthright, and the youngest according to his youth: and the men marvelled one at another.', '2~03427~ 4~06440~, 6~01060~ 10~01062~, 13~06810~ 17~06812~: 20~0582~ 21~08539~ 22~0376~ 24~07453~.'),
  (18693, 23, 51, 11, 'Therefore the redeemed of the LORD shall return, and come with singing unto Zion; and everlasting joy shall be upon their head: they shall obtain gladness and joy; and sorrow and mourning shall flee away.', '2~06299~ 5~03068~ 7~07725~, 9~0935~ 11~07440~ 13~06726~; 15~05769~ 16~08057~ [17 18] 21~07218~: 24~05381~ 25~08342~ 27~08057~; [28] 29~03015~ 31~0585~ 34~05127~.'),
  (24684, 41, 11, 33, 'And they answered and said unto Jesus, We cannot tell. And Jesus answering saith unto them, Neither do I tell you by what authority I do these things.', '0~2532~ 2~611~ 4~3004~ 6~2424~, 7~1492~ 8~3756~ 9~1492~. 10~2532~ 11~2424~ 12~611~ 13~3004~ 15~846~, 16~3761~ 18~1473~ 19~3004~ 20~5213~ 21~1722~ 22~4169~ 23~1849~ 25~4160~ 27~5023~.'),
  (4427, 4, 23, 6, 'And he returned unto him, and, lo, he stood by his burnt sacrifice, he, and all the princes of Moab.', '2~07725~ 8~05324~ 12~05930~, 17~08269~ 19~04124~.'),
  (12593, 16, 10, 35, 'And to bring the firstfruits of our ground, and the firstfruits of all fruit of all trees, year by year, unto the house of the LORD:', '2~0935~ 4~01061~ 7~0127~, 10~01061~ 13~06529~ 16~06086~, 17~08141~ 19~08141~, 22~01004~ 25~03068~:'),
  (232, 1, 9, 26, 'And he said, Blessed be the LORD God of Shem; and Canaan shall be his servant.', '2~0559~, 3~01288~ [4] 6~03068~ 7~0430~ 9~08035~; 11~03667~ 13~01961~ 15~05650~.'),
  (4580, 4, 27, 20, 'And thou shalt put some of thine honour upon him, that all the congregation of the children of Israel may be obedient.', '3~05414~ [4] 7~01935~ 13~05712~ 16~01121~ 18~03478~ 21~08085~.'),
  (5220, 5, 11, 6, 'And what he did unto Dathan and Abiram, the sons of Eliab, the son of Reuben: how the earth opened her mouth, and swallowed them up, and their households, and their tents, and all the substance that was in their possession, in the midst of all Israel:', '3~06213~ 5~01885~ 7~048~, 9~01121~ 11~0446~, 13~01121~ 15~07205~: 18~0776~ 19~06475~ 21~06310~, 25~01104~, 28~01004~, 31~0168~, 35~03351~ [37] 40~07272~, 43~07130~ 46~03478~:'),
  (9543, 12, 1, 2, 'And Ahaziah fell down through a lattice in his upper chamber that was in Samaria, and was sick: and he sent messengers, and said unto them, Go, inquire of Baalzebub the god of Ekron whether I shall recover of this disease.', '1~0274~ 3~05307~ 6~07639~ 10~05944~ [12] 14~08111~, 17~02470~: 20~07971~ 21~04397~, 23~0559~ 26~03212~, 27~01875~ 29~01176~ 31~0430~ 33~06138~ 37~02421~ 40~02483~.'),
  (8783, 11, 2, 5, 'Moreover thou knowest also what Joab the son of Zeruiah did to me, and what he did to the two captains of the hosts of Israel, unto Abner the son of Ner, and unto Amasa the son of Jether, whom he slew, and shed the blood of war in peace, and put the blood of war upon his girdle that was about his loins, and in his shoes that were on his feet.', '2~03045~ 5~03097~ 7~01121~ 9~06870~ 10~06213~ [13] 16~06213~ 19~08147~ 20~08269~ 23~06635~ 25~03478~, 27~074~ 29~01121~ 31~05369~, 34~06021~ 36~01121~ 38~03500~, 41~02026~, 43~07760~ 45~01818~ 47~04421~ 49~07965~, 51~05414~ 53~01818~ 55~04421~ 58~02290~ [60] 63~04975~, 67~05275~ [69] 72~07272~.'),
  (22573, 32, 3, 6, 'For word came unto the king of Nineveh, and he arose from his throne, and he laid his robe from him, and covered him with sackcloth, and sat in ashes.', '1~01697~ 2~05060~ 5~04428~ 7~05210~, 10~06965~ 13~03678~, 16~05674~ 18~0155~ 22~03680~ [23] 25~08242~, 27~03427~ 29~0665~.'),
  (18516, 23, 43, 2, 'When thou passest through the waters, I will be with thee; and through the rivers, they shall not overflow thee: when thou walkest through the fire, thou shalt not be burned; neither shall the flame kindle upon thee.', '3~05674~ 5~04325~, [7 8] 14~05104~, 18~07857~ 22~03212~ 23~01119~ 25~0784~, 30~03554~; 34~03852~ 35~01197~'),
  (30740, 66, 2, 7, 'He that hath an ear, let him hear what the Spirit saith unto the churches; To him that overcometh will I give to eat of the tree of life, which is in the midst of the paradise of God.', '2~2192~ 4~3775~, 7~191~ 8~5101~ 10~4151~ 11~3004~ 14~1577~; 16~846~ 18~3528~ 21~1325~ 23~5315~ 24~1537~ 26~3586~ 28~2222~, 29~3739~ 30~2076~ 31~1722~ 33~3319~ 36~3857~ 38~2316~.'),
  (8401, 10, 15, 5, 'And it was so, that when any man came nigh to him to do him obeisance, he put forth his hand, and took him, and kissed him.', '[3] 7~0376~ 9~07126~ [10 11] 15~07812~, 18~07971~ 20~03027~, 22~02388~ 25~05401~'),
  (6051, 6, 9, 8, 'And they said unto Joshua, We are thy servants. And Joshua said unto them, Who are ye? and from whence come ye?', '2~0559~ 4~03091~, [6] 8~05650~. 10~03091~ 11~0559~ [15] 19~0370~ 20~0935~'),
  (14176, 19, 18, 49, 'Therefore will I give thanks unto thee, O LORD, among the heathen, and sing praises unto thy name.', '4~03034~ 8~03068~, 11~01471~, 14~02167~ 17~08034~.'),
  (24558, 41, 9, 9, 'And as they came down from the mountain, he charged them that they should tell no man what things they had seen, till the Son of man were risen from the dead.', '0~1161~ 2~846~ 4~2597~ 5~575~ 7~3735~, 9~1291~ 10~846~ 11~2443~ 14~1334~ 16~3367~ 18~3739~ 21~1492~, 22~3752~ 23~1508~ 24~5207~ 26~444~ 28~450~ 29~1537~ 31~3498~.'),
  (18010, 23, 18, 4, 'For so the LORD said unto me, I will take my rest, and I will consider in my dwelling place like a clear heat upon herbs, and like a cloud of dew in the heat of harvest.', '1~03541~ 3~03068~ 4~0559~ 11~08252~, 15~05027~ 19~04349~ 22~06703~ 23~02527~ 25~0216~, [26] 29~05645~ 31~02919~ 34~02527~ 36~07105~.'),
  (14290, 19, 26, 8, 'LORD, I have loved the habitation of thy house, and the place where thine honour dwelleth.', '0~03068~, 3~0157~ 5~04583~ 8~01004~, 11~04725~ 14~03519~ 15~04908~.'),
  (6939, 7, 15, 3, 'And Samson said concerning them, Now shall I be more blameless than the Philistines, though I do them a displeasure.', '1~08123~ 2~0559~ 5~06471~ 10~05352~ 13~06430~, 16~06213~ 19~07451~.'),
  (10633, 13, 9, 10, 'And of the priests; Jedaiah, and Jehoiarib, and Jachin,', '3~03548~; 4~03048~, 6~03080~, 8~03199~,'),
  (19253, 24, 11, 18, 'And the LORD hath given me knowledge of it, and I know it: then thou shewedst me their doings.', '&para; 2~03068~ 6~03045~ [7 8] 11~03045~ [12] 15~07200~ 18~04611~.'),
  (912, 1, 31, 35, 'And she said to her father, Let it not displease my lord that I cannot rise up before thee; for the custom of women is upon me. And he searched, but found not the images.', '2~0559~ 5~01~, 9~02734~ 10~05869~* 12~0113~ 15~03201~ 17~06965~ 19~06440~; 22~01870~ 24~0802~ [25] 30~02664~, 32~04672~ 35~08655~.'),
  (9945, 12, 15, 12, 'This was the word of the LORD which he spake unto Jehu, saying, Thy sons shall sit on the throne of Israel unto the fourth generation. And so it came to pass.', '[1] 3~01697~ 6~03068~ 9~01696~ 11~03058~, 12~0559~, 14~01121~ 16~03427~ 19~03678~ 21~03478~ 24~07243~ [25]'),
  (15001, 19, 71, 16, 'I will go in the strength of the Lord GOD: I will make mention of thy righteousness, even of thine only.', '3~0935~ 5~01369~ 8~0136~ 9~03069~: 13~02142~ 16~06666~, [17]'),
  (17265, 20, 30, 5, 'Every word of God is pure: he is a shield unto them that put their trust in him.', '1~0565~ 3~0433~ [4] 5~06884~: [7] 9~04043~ 15~02620~'),
  (10027, 12, 17, 36, 'But the LORD, who brought you up out of the land of Egypt with great power and a stretched out arm, him shall ye fear, and him shall ye worship, and to him shall ye do sacrifice.', '2~03068~, 6~05927~ 10~0776~ 12~04714~ 14~01419~ 15~03581~ 19~05186~ 20~02220~, 24~03372~, 29~07812~, 36~02076~.'),
  (9292, 11, 16, 1, 'Then the word of the LORD came to Jehu the son of Hanani against Baasha, saying,', '&para; 2~01697~ 5~03068~ 8~03058~ 10~01121~ 12~02607~ 14~01201~, 15~0559~,'),
  (22581, 32, 4, 4, 'Then said the LORD, Doest thou well to be angry?', '1~0559~ 3~03068~, 6~03190~ 9~02734~?'),
  (18493, 23, 42, 4, 'He shall not fail nor be discouraged, till he have set judgment in the earth: and the isles shall wait for his law.', '3~03543~ 6~07533~, 10~07760~ 11~04941~ 14~0776~: 17~0339~ 19~03176~ 22~08451~.'),
  (4969, 5, 2, 25, 'This day will I begin to put the dread of thee and the fear of thee upon the nations that are under the whole heaven, who shall hear report of thee, and shall tremble, and be in anguish because of thee.', '1~03117~ 4~02490~ 6~05414~ 8~06343~ 13~03374~ 18~05971~ [19 19~06440~ 20] 24~08064~, 27~08085~ 28~08088~ 33~07264~, 37~02342~ 40~06440~.'),
  (3315, 3, 19, 29, 'Do not prostitute thy daughter, to cause her to be a whore; lest the land fall to whoredom, and the land become full of wickedness.', '2~02490~ 4~01323~, 11~02181~; 14~0776~ 17~02181~, 20~0776~ 22~04390~ 24~02154~.'),
  (27034, 44, 3, 22, 'For Moses truly said unto the fathers, A prophet shall the Lord your God raise up unto you of your brethren, like unto me; him shall ye hear in all things whatsoever he shall say unto you.', '0~1063~ 1~3475~ 2~3303~ 3~2036~ 4~4314~ 6~3962~ 7~3754~,* 9~4396~ 10~450~ 12~2962~ 13~5216~ 14~2316~ 16~450~ 18~5213~ 19~1537~ 20~5216~ 21~80~, 22~5613~ 24~1691~; 25~846~ 28~191~ 29~2596~ 31~3956~ 32~302~ 33~3745~ 35~2980~ 36~4314~ 37~5209~.'),
  (8500, 10, 18, 14, 'Then said Joab, I may not tarry thus with thee. And he took three darts in his hand, and thrust them through the heart of Absalom, while he was yet alive in the midst of the oak.', '1~0559~ 2~03097~, 6~03176~ 9~06440~. 12~03947~ 13~07969~ 14~07626~ 17~03709~, 19~08628~ 23~03820~ 25~053~, [28] 30~02416~ 36~0424~.'),
  (27395, 44, 13, 17, 'The God of this people of Israel chose our fathers, and exalted the people when they dwelt as strangers in the land of Egypt, and with an high arm brought he them out of it.', '1~2316~ 3~5127~ 4~2992~ 6~2474~ 7~1586~ 8~2257~ 9~3962~, 10~2532~ 11~5312~ 13~2992~ 14~1722~ 18~3940~ 19~1722~ 21~1093~ 23~125~, 24~2532~ 25~3326~ 27~5308~ 28~1023~ 30~1806~ 31~846~ 33~1537~ 34~846~.'),
  (23773, 40, 19, 1, 'And it came to pass, that when Jesus had finished these sayings, he departed from Galilee, and came into the coasts of Judaea beyond Jordan;', '&para; 0~2532~ 4~1096~, [5] 6~3753~ 7~2424~ 9~5055~ 10~5128~ 11~3056~, 13~3332~ 14~575~ 15~1056~, 16~2532~ 17~2064~ 18~1519~ 20~3725~ 22~2449~ 23~4008~ 24~2446~;'),
  (30179, 58, 10, 30, 'For we know him that hath said, Vengeance belongeth unto me, I will recompense, saith the Lord. And again, The Lord shall judge his people.', '0~1063~ 2~1492~ 6~2036~, 7~1557~ [8] 10~1698~, 11~1473~ 13~467~, 14~3004~ 16~2962~. 17~2532~ 18~3825~, 20~2962~ 22~2919~ 23~846~ 24~2992~.'),
  (26564, 43, 11, 26, 'And whosoever liveth and believeth in me shall never die. Believest thou this?', '0~2532~ 1~3956~ 2~2198~ 3~2532~ 4~4100~ 5~1519~ 6~1691~ 7~599~ 8~165~ 9~3364~* 10~1519~* 11~599~. 13~4100~ 14~5124~?'),
  (435, 1, 18, 7, 'And Abraham ran unto the herd, and fetched a calf tender and good, and gave it unto a young man; and he hasted to dress it.', '1~085~ 2~07323~ 5~01241~, 7~03947~ 9~01241~ 10~01121~* 11~07390~ 13~02896~, 15~05414~ [16] 20~05288~; 23~04116~ 25~06213~'),
  (17474, 21, 8, 7, 'For he knoweth not that which shall be: for who can tell him when it shall be?', '2~03045~ 11~05046~'),
  (5882, 6, 2, 7, 'And the men pursued after them the way to Jordan unto the fords: and as soon as they which pursued after them were gone out, they shut the gate.', '2~0582~ 3~07291~ 4~0310~ 7~01870~ 9~03383~ 12~04569~: 19~07291~ 20~0310~ 24~03318~, 26~05462~ 28~08179~.'),
  (23995, 40, 24, 28, 'For wheresoever the carcase is, there will the eagles be gathered together.', '0~1063~ 1~3699~ 2~1437~ 3~4430~ 4~5600~, 5~1563~ 6~4863~ 8~105~ 11~4863~.'),
  (30404, 60, 1, 14, 'As obedient children, not fashioning yourselves according to the former lusts in your ignorance:', '0~5613~ 1~5218~ 2~5043~, 3~3361~ 7~4964~ 9~4386~ 10~1939~ 11~1722~ 12~5216~ 13~52~:'),
  (9928, 12, 14, 24, 'And he did that which was evil in the sight of the LORD: he departed not from all the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, who made Israel to sin.', '2~06213~ [3 5] 6~07451~ 9~05869~ 12~03068~: 14~05493~ 19~02403~ 21~03379~ 23~01121~ 25~05028~, 28~03478~ 30~02398~.'),
  (21849, 27, 4, 3, 'How great are his signs! and how mighty are his wonders! his kingdom is an everlasting kingdom, and his dominion is from generation to generation.', '0~04101~ 1~07260~ [2] 4~0852~! 6~04101~ 7~08624~ [8] 10~08540~! 12~04437~ [13] 15~05957~ 16~04437~, 19~07985~ [20] 21~05974~ 22~01859~ 24~01859~.'),
  (5434, 5, 20, 1, 'When thou goest out to battle against thine enemies, and seest horses, and chariots, and a people more than thou, be not afraid of them: for the LORD thy God is with thee, which brought thee up out of the land of Egypt.', '&para; 3~03318~ 5~04421~ 8~0341~, 10~07200~ 11~05483~, 13~07393~, [14] 16~05971~ 17~07227~ 22~03372~ 27~03068~ 29~0430~ [30] 36~05927~ 40~0776~ 42~04714~.'),
  (669, 1, 25, 7, 'And these are the days of the years of Abraham''s life which he lived, an hundred threescore and fifteen years.', '[2] 4~03117~ 7~08141~ 9~085~ 10~02416~ 13~02425~, 15~08141~ 16~03967~ 18~02568~ 19~07657~* 20~08141~* 21~08141~.'),
  (6256, 6, 15, 47, 'Ashdod with her towns and her villages, Gaza with her towns and her villages, unto the river of Egypt, and the great sea, and the border thereof:', '0~0795~ 3~01323~ 6~02691~, 7~05804~ 10~01323~ 13~02691~, 16~05158~ 18~04714~, 21~01419~ 22~01366~* 23~03220~, 26~01366~ [27]'),
  (23914, 40, 22, 32, 'I am the God of Abraham, and the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob? God is not the God of the dead, but of the living.', '0~1473~ 1~1510~ 3~2316~ 5~11~, 6~2532~ 8~2316~ 10~2464~, 11~2532~ 13~2316~ 15~2384~? 16~2316~ 17~2076~ 18~3756~ 20~2316~ 23~3498~, 24~235~ 27~2198~.'),
  (26107, 43, 1, 48, 'Nathanael saith unto him, Whence knowest thou me? Jesus answered and said unto him, Before that Philip called thee, when thou wast under the fig tree, I saw thee.', '0~3482~ 1~3004~ 3~846~, 4~4159~ 6~1097~ 7~3165~? 8~2424~ 9~611~ 10~2532~ 11~2036~ 13~846~, 14~4253~ 16~5376~ 17~5455~ 18~4571~, 21~5607~ 22~5259~ 25~4808~, 27~1492~ 28~4571~.'),
  (15599, 19, 104, 19, 'He appointed the moon for seasons: the sun knoweth his going down.', '&para; 1~06213~ 3~03394~ 5~04150~: 7~08121~ 8~03045~ 11~03996~.'),
  (24680, 41, 11, 29, 'And Jesus answered and said unto them, I will also ask of you one question, and answer me, and I will tell you by what authority I do these things.', '0~1161~ 1~2424~ 2~611~ 4~2036~ 6~846~, 8~1905~ 9~2504~ 10~1905~ 12~5209~ 13~1520~ 14~3056~, 15~2532~ 16~611~ 17~3427~, 18~2532~ 21~2046~ 22~5213~ 23~1722~ 24~4169~ 25~1849~ 27~4160~ 29~5023~.'),
  (29467, 50, 4, 9, 'Those things, which ye have both learned, and received, and heard, and seen in me, do: and the God of peace shall be with you.', '1~5023~, 2~3739~ 4~3129~ 5~2532~ 6~3129~, 7~2532~ 8~3880~, 9~2532~ 10~191~, 11~2532~ 12~1492~ 13~1722~ 14~1698~, 15~4238~: 16~2532~ 18~2316~ 20~1515~ 22~2071~ 23~3326~ 24~5216~.'),
  (5464, 5, 21, 11, 'And seest among the captives a beautiful woman, and hast a desire unto her, that thou wouldest have her to thy wife;', '1~07200~ 4~07633~ 6~03303~ 7~08389~* 8~0802~, 12~02836~ 19~03947~ 22~0802~;'),
  (8592, 10, 21, 4, 'And the Gibeonites said unto him, We will have no silver nor gold of Saul, nor of his house; neither for us shalt thou kill any man in Israel. And he said, What ye shall say, that will I do for you.', '2~01393~ 3~0559~ 10~03701~ 12~02091~ 13~05973~ 14~07586~, 18~01004~; 24~04191~ 26~0376~ 28~03478~. 31~0559~, 35~0559~, [36] 39~06213~'),
  (24377, 41, 5, 3, 'Who had his dwelling among the tombs; and no man could bind him, no, not with chains:', '0~3739~ 1~2192~ [2] 3~2731~ 4~1722~ 6~3419~; 7~2532~ 9~3762~ 10~1410~ 11~1210~ 12~846~, 14~3777~ 16~254~:'),
  (20708, 26, 12, 19, 'And say unto the people of the land, Thus saith the Lord GOD of the inhabitants of Jerusalem, and of the land of Israel; They shall eat their bread with carefulness, and drink their water with astonishment, that her land may be desolate from all that is therein, because of the violence of all them that dwell therein.', '1~0559~ 4~05971~ 7~0127~, 9~0559~ 11~0136~ 12~03069~ 15~03427~ 17~03389~, [18] 21~0776~ 23~03478~; 26~0398~ 28~03899~ 30~01674~, 32~08354~ 34~04325~ 36~08078~, 39~0776~ 42~03456~ 47~04393~, 51~02555~ 56~03427~'),
  (5691, 5, 29, 6, 'Ye have not eaten bread, neither have ye drunk wine or strong drink: that ye might know that I am the LORD your God.', '3~0398~ 4~03899~, 8~08354~ 9~03196~ 12~07941~: 16~03045~ [19] 21~03068~ 23~0430~.'),
  (10474, 13, 6, 12, 'And Ahitub begat Zadok, and Zadok begat Shallum,', '1~0285~ 2~03205~ 3~06659~, 5~06659~ 6~03205~ 7~07967~,'),
  (18657, 23, 49, 12, 'Behold, these shall come from far: and, lo, these from the north and from the west; and these from the land of Sinim.', '3~0935~ 5~07350~: 11~06828~ 15~03220~; 20~0776~ 22~05515~.'),
  (19358, 24, 16, 13, 'Therefore will I cast you out of this land into a land that ye know not, neither ye nor your fathers; and there shall ye serve other gods day and night; where I will not shew you favour.', '3~02904~ 8~0776~ 11~0776~ 14~03045~ [16] 20~01~; 25~05647~ 26~0312~ 27~0430~ 28~03119~ 30~03915~; 35~05414~ 37~02594~.'),
  (19665, 24, 29, 21, 'Thus saith the LORD of hosts, the God of Israel, of Ahab the son of Kolaiah, and of Zedekiah the son of Maaseiah, which prophesy a lie unto you in my name; Behold, I will deliver them into the hand of Nebuchadrezzar king of Babylon; and he shall slay them before your eyes;', '1~0559~ 3~03068~ 5~06635~, 7~0430~ 9~03478~, 11~0256~ 13~01121~ 15~06964~, 18~06667~ 20~01121~ 22~04641~, 24~05012~ 26~08267~ 31~08034~; 35~05414~ 39~03027~ 41~05019~ 42~04428~ 44~0894~; 48~05221~ 52~05869~;'),
  (3111, 3, 13, 54, 'Then the priest shall command that they wash the thing wherein the plague is, and he shall shut it up seven days more:', '2~03548~ 4~06680~ 7~03526~ [8 9] 12~05061~ [13] 17~05462~ 20~07651~ 21~03117~ 22~08145~:'),
  (1216, 1, 41, 16, 'And Joseph answered Pharaoh, saying, It is not in me: God shall give Pharaoh an answer of peace.', '1~03130~ 2~06030~ 3~06547~, 4~0559~, [5 6] 9~01107~: 10~0430~ 12~06030~ 13~06547~ 15~06030~ 17~07965~.'),
  (2213, 2, 25, 13, 'And thou shalt make staves of shittim wood, and overlay them with gold.', '3~06213~ 4~0905~ [5] 6~07848~ 7~06086~, 9~06823~ 12~02091~.'),
  (23289, 40, 5, 45, 'That ye may be the children of your Father which is in heaven: for he maketh his sun to rise on the evil and on the good, and sendeth rain on the just and on the unjust.', '0~3704~ 3~1096~ 5~5207~ 7~5216~ 8~3962~ 9~3588~ 11~1722~ 12~3772~: 13~3754~ 15~393~ 16~846~ 17~2246~ 19~393~ 20~1909~ 22~4190~ 23~2532~ 26~18~, 27~2532~ 29~1026~ 30~1909~ 32~1342~ 33~2532~ 36~94~.'),
  (12117, 15, 3, 11, 'And they sang together by course in praising and giving thanks unto the LORD; because he is good, for his mercy endureth for ever toward Israel. And all the people shouted with a great shout, when they praised the LORD, because the foundation of the house of the LORD was laid.', '5~06030~ 7~01984~ 10~03034~ 13~03068~; [15 16] 17~02896~, 20~02617~ [21] 23~05769~ 25~03478~. 29~05971~ 30~07321~ 33~01419~ 34~08643~, 37~01984~ 39~03068~, 42~03245~ 45~01004~ 48~03068~ 50~03245~.'),
  (15905, 19, 118, 27, 'God is the LORD, which hath shewed us light: bind the sacrifice with cords, even unto the horns of the altar.', '0~0410~ [1] 3~03068~, 8~0215~: 9~0631~ 11~02282~ 13~05688~, [14] 17~07161~ 20~04196~.'),
  (12530, 16, 9, 10, 'And shewedst signs and wonders upon Pharaoh, and on all his servants, and on all the people of his land: for thou knewest that they dealt proudly against them. So didst thou get thee a name, as it is this day.', '1~05414~ 2~0226~ 4~04159~ 6~06547~, 11~05650~, 16~05971~ 19~0776~: 22~03045~ 26~02102~ 32~06213~ 35~08034~, [37 38] 40~03117~.'),
  (10989, 13, 22, 17, 'David also commanded all the princes of Israel to help Solomon his son, saying,', '&para; 0~01732~ 2~06680~ 5~08269~ 7~03478~ 9~05826~ 10~08010~ 12~01121~, [13]'),
  (30501, 61, 1, 6, 'And to knowledge temperance; and to temperance patience; and to patience godliness;', '0~1161~ 1~1722~ 2~1108~ 3~1466~; 4~1161~ 5~1722~ 6~1466~ 7~5281~; 8~1161~ 9~1722~ 10~5281~ 11~2150~;'),
  (6522, 7, 1, 6, 'But Adonibezek fled; and they pursued after him, and caught him, and cut off his thumbs and his great toes.', '1~0137~ 2~05127~; 5~07291~ 6~0310~ 9~0270~ 13~07112~ 15~03027~ 16~0931~ 19~07272~.'),
  (15962, 19, 119, 55, 'I have remembered thy name, O LORD, in the night, and have kept thy law.', '&para; 2~02142~ 4~08034~, 6~03068~, 9~03915~, 12~08104~ 14~08451~.'),
  (23951, 40, 23, 23, 'Woe unto you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! for ye pay tithe of mint and anise and cummin, and have omitted the weightier matters of the law, judgment, mercy, and faith: these ought ye to have done, and not to leave the other undone.', '0~3759~ 2~5213~, 3~1122~ 4~2532~ 5~5330~, 6~5273~! 7~3754~ 10~586~ 12~2238~ 13~2532~ 14~432~ 15~2532~ 16~2951~, 17~2532~ 19~863~ 21~926~ [22] 25~3551~, 26~2920~ 27~2532~,* 28~1656~, 29~2532~ 30~4102~: 31~5023~ 33~1163~ 36~4160~, 38~3361~ 40~863~ 42~2548~ 43~863~.'),
  (11473, 14, 13, 11, 'And they burn unto the LORD every morning and every evening burnt sacrifices and sweet incense: the shewbread also set they in order upon the pure table; and the candlestick of gold with the lamps thereof, to burn every evening: for we keep the charge of the LORD our God; but ye have forsaken him.', '2~06999~ 5~03068~ 7~01242~ 10~06153~ 12~05930~ 14~05561~ 15~07004~: 17~04635~ 18~03899~ [19 22] 25~02889~ 26~07979~; 29~04501~ 31~02091~ 34~05216~ 37~01197~ 39~06153~: 42~08104~ 44~04931~ 47~03068~ 49~0430~; 53~05800~'),
  (19246, 24, 11, 11, 'Therefore thus saith the LORD, Behold, I will bring evil upon them, which they shall not be able to escape; and though they shall cry unto me, I will not hearken unto them.', '&para; 2~0559~ 4~03068~, 8~0935~ 9~07451~ 17~03201~ 19~03318~; 24~02199~ 30~08085~'),
  (18967, 24, 1, 12, 'Then said the LORD unto me, Thou hast well seen: for I will hasten my word to perform it.', '1~0559~ 3~03068~ 8~03190~ 9~07200~: 13~08245~ 15~01697~ 17~06213~'),
  (9367, 11, 18, 18, 'And he answered, I have not troubled Israel; but thou, and thy father''s house, in that ye have forsaken the commandments of the LORD, and thou hast followed Baalim.', '2~0559~, 6~05916~ 7~03478~; 12~01~ 13~01004~, 18~05800~ 20~04687~ 23~03068~, 27~03212~ 28~0310~* 29~01168~.'),
  (20808, 26, 16, 37, 'Behold, therefore I will gather all thy lovers, with whom thou hast taken pleasure, and all them that thou hast loved, with all them that thou hast hated; I will even gather them round about against thee, and will discover thy nakedness unto them, that they may see all thy nakedness.', '4~06908~ 7~0157~, 13~06149~, [16] 20~0157~, [23] 27~08130~; 31~06908~ 34~05439~ 39~01540~ 41~06172~ 47~07200~ 50~06172~.'),
  (23720, 40, 17, 10, 'And his disciples asked him, saying, Why then say the scribes that Elias must first come?', '0~2532~ 1~846~ 2~3101~ 3~1905~ 4~846~, 5~3004~, 6~5101~ 7~3767~ 8~3004~ 10~1122~ 11~3754~ 12~2243~ 13~1163~ 14~4412~ 15~2064~?'),
  (5077, 5, 5, 18, 'Neither shalt thou commit adultery.', '4~05003~.'),
  (30767, 66, 3, 5, 'He that overcometh, the same shall be clothed in white raiment; and I will not blot out his name out of the book of life, but I will confess his name before my Father, and before his angels.', '2~3528~, 4~3778~ 7~4016~ 8~1722~ 9~3022~ 10~2440~; 11~2532~ 13~1813~ 14~3364~ 16~1813~ 17~846~ 18~3686~ 20~1537~ 22~976~ 24~2222~, 25~2532~ 28~1843~ 29~846~ 30~3686~ 31~1799~ 32~3450~ 33~3962~, 34~2532~ 35~1799~ 36~846~ 37~32~.'),
  (5022, 5, 4, 12, 'And the LORD spake unto you out of the midst of the fire: ye heard the voice of the words, but saw no similitude; only ye heard a voice.', '2~03068~ 3~01696~ 9~08432~ 12~0784~: 14~08085~ 16~06963~ 19~01697~, 21~07200~ 23~08544~; 24~02108~ [25 26] 28~06963~.'),
  (27743, 44, 22, 23, 'And as they cried out, and cast off their clothes, and threw dust into the air,', '0~1161~ 2~846~ 4~2905~, 5~2532~ 7~4495~ [8] 9~2440~, 10~2532~ 11~906~ 12~2868~ 13~1519~ 15~109~,'),
  (22908, 38, 1, 21, 'Then said I, What come these to do? And he spake, saying, These are the horns which have scattered Judah, so that no man did lift up his head: but these are come to fray them, to cast out the horns of the Gentiles, which lifted up their horn over the land of Judah to scatter it.', '1~0559~ 4~0935~ 7~06213~? 10~0559~, 11~0559~, [13] 15~07161~ 18~02219~ 19~03063~, 21~06310~ 23~0376~ 26~05375~ 28~07218~: 32~0935~ 34~02729~ 38~03034~ 40~07161~ 43~01471~, 46~05375~ [47] 48~07161~ 51~0776~ 53~03063~ 55~02219~'),
  (17434, 21, 6, 8, 'For what hath the wise more than the fool? what hath the poor, that knoweth to walk before the living?', '4~02450~ 5~03148~ 8~03684~? 12~06041~, 14~03045~ 16~01980~ 19~02416~?'),
  (27055, 44, 4, 17, 'But that it spread no further among the people, let us straitly threaten them, that they speak henceforth to no man in this name.', '0~235~ 1~3363~ 3~1268~ 4~3363~ 5~4119~ 6~1909~* 7~1519~ 9~2992~, 12~547~ 13~546~ 14~846~, 17~2980~ 18~3371~ 20~3367~ 21~444~ 22~1909~ 23~5129~ 24~3686~.'),
  (8522, 10, 19, 3, 'And the people gat them by stealth that day into the city, as people being ashamed steal away when they flee in battle.', '2~05971~ 3~0935~ 6~01589~ 8~03117~ 11~05892~, 13~05971~ 15~03637~ 17~01589~ 20~05127~ 22~04421~.'),
  (1336, 1, 44, 7, 'And they said unto him, Wherefore saith my lord these words? God forbid that thy servants should do according to this thing:', '2~0559~ 6~01696~ 8~0113~ 10~01697~? 12~02486~ 15~05650~ 17~06213~ 21~01697~:'),
  (25401, 42, 10, 26, 'He said unto him, What is written in the law? how readest thou?', '0~1161~ 1~2036~ 2~4314~ 3~846~, 4~5101~ 6~1125~ 7~1722~ 9~3551~? 10~4459~ 12~314~?'),
  (18426, 23, 39, 5, 'Then said Isaiah to Hezekiah, Hear the word of the LORD of hosts:', '&para; 1~0559~ 2~03470~ 4~02396~, 5~08085~ 7~01697~ 10~03068~ 12~06635~:'),
  (23754, 40, 18, 17, 'And if he shall neglect to hear them, tell it unto the church: but if he neglect to hear the church, let him be unto thee as a heathen man and a publican.', '0~1161~ 1~1437~ 6~3878~ 7~846~, 8~2036~ [9] 12~1577~: 13~2532~ 14~1161~* 15~1437~ 19~3878~ 21~1577~, 24~2077~ 26~4671~ 27~5618~ 30~1482~ 31~2532~ 33~5057~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (29702, 53, 3, 8, 'Neither did we eat any man''s bread for nought; but wrought with labour and travail night and day, that we might not be chargeable to any of you:', '0~3761~ 3~5315~ 5~5100~ 6~3844~* 7~740~ 9~1432~; 10~235~ 11~2038~ 12~1722~ 13~2873~ 14~2532~ 15~3449~ 16~3571~ 17~2532~ 18~2250~, 19~4314~ 21~1912~ 22~3361~ 24~1912~ 26~5100~ 28~5216~:'),
  (26640, 43, 12, 45, 'And he that seeth me seeth him that sent me.', '0~2532~ 3~2334~ 4~1691~ 5~2334~ 8~3992~ 9~3165~.'),
  (11538, 14, 17, 6, 'And his heart was lifted up in the ways of the LORD: moreover he took away the high places and groves out of Judah.', '2~03820~ 5~01361~ 8~01870~ 11~03068~: 15~05493~ 18~01116~ 20~0842~ 23~03063~.'),
  (20493, 26, 1, 20, 'Whithersoever the spirit was to go, they went, thither was their spirit to go; and the wheels were lifted up over against them: for the spirit of the living creature was in the wheels.', '2~07307~ 5~03212~, 7~03212~, [9 10] 11~07307~ 13~03212~; 16~0212~ 19~05375~ 21~05980~ 25~07307~ 29~02416~ [30] 33~0212~.'),
  (26124, 43, 2, 14, 'And found in the temple those that sold oxen and sheep and doves, and the changers of money sitting:', '0~2532~ 1~2147~ 2~1722~ 4~2411~ 7~4453~ 8~1016~ 9~2532~ 10~4263~ 11~2532~ 12~4058~, 13~2532~ 17~2773~ 18~2521~:'),
  (27589, 44, 18, 16, 'And he drave them from the judgment seat.', '0~2532~ 2~556~ 3~846~ 4~575~ 7~968~.'),
  (22243, 28, 10, 9, 'O Israel, thou hast sinned from the days of Gibeah: there they stood: the battle in Gibeah against the children of iniquity did not overtake them.', '&para; 1~03478~, 4~02398~ 7~03117~ 9~01390~: 12~05975~: 14~04421~ 16~01390~ 19~01121~ 21~05932~ 24~05381~'),
  (22406, 30, 3, 2, 'You only have I known of all the families of the earth: therefore I will punish you for all your iniquities.', '4~03045~ 8~04940~ 11~0127~: 15~06485~ 20~05771~.'),
  (5997, 6, 7, 15, 'And it shall be, that he that is taken with the accursed thing shall be burnt with fire, he and all that he hath: because he hath transgressed the covenant of the LORD, and because he hath wrought folly in Israel.', '[4] 8~03920~ 12~02764~ 15~08313~ 17~0784~, 27~05674~ 29~01285~ 32~03068~, 37~06213~ 38~05039~ 40~03478~.'),
  (769, 1, 27, 38, 'And Esau said unto his father, Hast thou but one blessing, my father? bless me, even me also, O my father. And Esau lifted up his voice, and wept.', '1~06215~ 2~0559~ 5~01~, 9~0259~ 10~01293~, 12~01~? 13~01288~ [15] 20~01~. 22~06215~ 24~05375~ 26~06963~, 28~01058~.'),
  (16771, 20, 13, 15, 'Good understanding giveth favour: but the way of transgressors is hard.', '&para; 0~02896~ 1~07922~ 2~05414~ 3~02580~: 6~01870~ 8~0898~ [9] 10~0386~.'),
  (13106, 18, 10, 11, 'Thou hast clothed me with skin and flesh, and hast fenced me with bones and sinews.', '2~03847~ 5~05785~ 7~01320~, 10~07753~ 13~06106~ 15~01517~.'),
  (9730, 12, 7, 15, 'And they went after them unto Jordan: and, lo, all the way was full of garments and vessels, which the Syrians had cast away in their haste. And the messengers returned, and told the king.', '2~03212~ 3~0310~ 6~03383~: 11~01870~ [12] 13~04392~ 15~0899~ 17~03627~, 20~0758~ 23~07993~ 26~02648~. 29~04397~ 30~07725~, 32~05046~ 34~04428~.'),
  (20014, 24, 43, 8, 'Then came the word of the LORD unto Jeremiah in Tahpanhes, saying,', '&para; 3~01697~ 6~03068~ 8~03414~ 10~08471~, 11~0559~,'),
  (27752, 44, 23, 2, 'And the high priest Ananias commanded them that stood by him to smite him on the mouth.', '0~1161~ 3~749~ 4~367~ 5~2004~ 9~3936~ 10~846~ 12~5180~ 13~846~ 16~4750~.'),
  (3626, 4, 1, 17, 'And Moses and Aaron took these men which are expressed by their names:', '&para; 1~04872~ 3~0175~ 4~03947~ 6~0582~ 9~05344~ [11] 12~08034~:'),
  (11674, 14, 23, 9, 'Moreover Jehoiada the priest delivered to the captains of hundreds spears, and bucklers, and shields, that had been king David''s, which were in the house of God.', '1~03077~ 3~03548~ 4~05414~ 7~08269~ 9~03967~ 10~02595~, 12~04043~, 14~07982~, [16 17] 18~04428~ 19~01732~, [21] 24~01004~ 26~0430~.'),
  (5290, 5, 13, 12, 'If thou shalt hear say in one of thy cities, which the LORD thy God hath given thee to dwell there, saying,', '&para; 3~08085~ [4] 6~0259~ 9~05892~, 12~03068~ 14~0430~ 16~05414~ 19~03427~ 21~0559~,'),
  (12022, 14, 36, 20, 'And them that had escaped from the sword carried he away to Babylon; where they were servants to him and his sons until the reign of the kingdom of Persia:', '4~07611~ 7~02719~ 10~01540~ 12~0894~; 16~05650~ 21~01121~ 24~04427~ 27~04438~ 29~06539~:'),
  (30695, 65, 1, 7, 'Even as Sodom and Gomorrha, and the cities about them in like manner, giving themselves over to fornication, and going after strange flesh, are set forth for an example, suffering the vengeance of eternal fire.', '1~5613~ 2~4670~ 3~2532~ 4~1116~, 5~2532~ 7~4172~ 8~4012~ 9~846~ 11~5125~ 12~3664~* 13~5158~, 18~1608~, 19~2532~ 20~565~ 21~3694~ 22~2087~ 23~4561~, 27~4295~ 29~1164~, 30~5254~ 32~1349~ 34~166~ 35~4442~.'),
  (18223, 23, 29, 21, 'That make a man an offender for a word, and lay a snare for him that reproveth in the gate, and turn aside the just for a thing of nought.', '3~0120~ 5~02398~ 8~01697~, 12~06983~ 16~03198~ 19~08179~, 22~05186~ 24~06662~ 29~08414~.'),
  (7361, 9, 7, 2, 'And it came to pass, while the ark abode in Kirjathjearim, that the time was long; for it was twenty years: and all the house of Israel lamented after the LORD.', '5~03117~ 7~0727~ 8~03427~ 10~07157~, 13~03117~ 15~07235~; 19~06242~ 20~08141~: 24~01004~ 26~03478~ 27~05091~ 28~0310~ 30~03068~.'),
  (12371, 16, 4, 3, 'Now Tobiah the Ammonite was by him, and he said, Even that which they build, if a fox go up, he shall even break down their stone wall.', '1~02900~ 3~05984~ [4] 6~0681~, 9~0559~, 14~01129~, 17~07776~ 19~05927~, 24~06555~ 26~068~ 27~02346~.'),
  (16777, 20, 13, 21, 'Evil pursueth sinners: but to the righteous good shall be repayed.', '&para; 0~07451~ 1~07291~ 2~02400~: 6~06662~ 7~02896~ 10~07999~.'),
  (11737, 14, 25, 24, 'And he took all the gold and the silver, and all the vessels that were found in the house of God with Obededom, and the treasures of the king''s house, the hostages also, and returned to Samaria.', '[1 2] 5~02091~ 8~03701~, 12~03627~ 15~04672~ 18~01004~ 20~0430~ 22~05654~, 25~0214~ 28~04428~ 29~01004~, 31~08594~ 32~01121~, 34~07725~ 36~08111~.'),
  (17665, 23, 1, 2, 'Hear, O heavens, and give ear, O earth: for the LORD hath spoken, I have nourished and brought up children, and they have rebelled against me.', '&para; 0~08085~, 2~08064~, 5~0238~, 7~0776~: 10~03068~ 12~01696~, 15~01431~ 18~07311~ 19~01121~, 23~06586~'),
  (6005, 6, 7, 23, 'And they took them out of the midst of the tent, and brought them unto Joshua, and unto all the children of Israel, and laid them out before the LORD.', '2~03947~ 7~08432~ 10~0168~, 12~0935~ 15~03091~, 20~01121~ 22~03478~, 26~03332~ 27~06440~ 29~03068~.'),
  (10090, 12, 19, 21, 'This is the word that the LORD hath spoken concerning him; The virgin the daughter of Zion hath despised thee, and laughed thee to scorn; the daughter of Jerusalem hath shaken her head at thee.', '[1] 3~01697~ 6~03068~ 8~01696~ 12~01330~ 14~01323~ 16~06726~ 18~0959~ [20] 24~03932~; 26~01323~ 28~03389~ 30~05128~ 32~07218~ 34~0310~.'),
  (28719, 46, 14, 25, 'And thus are the secrets of his heart made manifest; and so falling down on his face he will worship God, and report that God is in you of a truth.', '0~2532~ 1~3779~ 2~1096~ 4~2927~ 6~846~ 7~2588~ 8~1096~ 9~5318~; 10~2532~ 11~3779~ 13~4098~ 14~1909~ [15] 16~4383~ 19~4352~ 20~2316~, 22~518~ 23~3754~ 24~2316~ 25~2076~ 26~1722~ 27~5213~ 30~3689~.'),
  (7789, 9, 21, 10, 'And David arose, and fled that day for fear of Saul, and went to Achish the king of Gath.', '&para; 1~01732~ 2~06965~, 4~01272~ 6~03117~ 8~06440~ 10~07586~, 12~0935~ 14~0397~ 16~04428~ 18~01661~.'),
  (11861, 14, 30, 25, 'And all the congregation of Judah, with the priests and the Levites, and all the congregation that came out of Israel, and the strangers that came out of the land of Israel, and that dwelt in Judah, rejoiced.', '3~06951~ 5~03063~, 8~03548~ 11~03881~, 15~06951~ 18~0935~ 20~03478~, 23~01616~ 26~0935~ 29~0776~ 31~03478~, 34~03427~ 36~03063~, 37~08055~.'),
  (17307, 20, 31, 14, 'She is like the merchants'' ships; she bringeth her food from afar.', '4~05503~'' 5~0591~; 7~0935~ 9~03899~ 11~04801~.'),
  (22647, 33, 5, 5, 'And this man shall be the peace, when the Assyrian shall come into our land: and when he shall tread in our palaces, then shall we raise against him seven shepherds, and eight principal men.', '[2] 6~07965~, 9~0804~ 11~0935~ 14~0776~: 19~01869~ 22~0759~, 26~06965~ 29~07651~ 30~07462~, 32~08083~ 33~05257~ 34~0120~.'),
  (6231, 6, 15, 22, 'And Kinah, and Dimonah, and Adadah,', '1~07016~, 3~01776~, 5~05735~,'),
  (3769, 4, 4, 21, 'And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~01696~ 5~04872~, 6~0559~,'),
  (16565, 20, 6, 16, 'These six things doth the LORD hate: yea, seven are an abomination unto him:', '1~08337~ [2] 5~03068~ 6~08130~: 8~07651~ [9] 11~08441~ 13~05315~:'),
  (9388, 11, 18, 39, 'And when all the people saw it, they fell on their faces: and they said, The LORD, he is the God; the LORD, he is the God.', '4~05971~ 5~07200~ [6] 8~05307~ 11~06440~: 14~0559~, 16~03068~, [18] 20~0430~; 22~03068~, [24] 26~0430~.'),
  (22256, 28, 11, 7, 'And my people are bent to backsliding from me: though they called them to the most High, none at all would exalt him.', '2~05971~ 4~08511~ 6~04878~ 11~07121~ 16~05920~, 19~03162~ 21~07311~ [22]'),
  (5411, 5, 18, 21, 'And if thou say in thine heart, How shall we know the word which the LORD hath not spoken?', '3~0559~ 6~03824~, 10~03045~ 12~01697~ 15~03068~ 18~01696~?'),
  (3394, 3, 22, 20, 'But whatsoever hath a blemish, that shall ye not offer: for it shall not be acceptable for you.', '[0] 4~03971~, [5] 9~07126~: 15~07522~'),
  (13471, 18, 25, 1, 'Then answered Bildad the Shuhite, and said,', '&para; 1~06030~ 2~01085~ 4~07747~, 6~0559~,'),
  (7974, 9, 28, 25, 'And she brought it before Saul, and before his servants; and they did eat. Then they rose up, and went away that night.', '2~05066~ [3] 4~06440~ 5~07586~, 7~06440~ 9~05650~; 13~0398~. 17~06965~, 20~03212~ 22~03915~.'),
  (1814, 2, 11, 3, 'And the LORD gave the people favour in the sight of the Egyptians. Moreover the man Moses was very great in the land of Egypt, in the sight of Pharaoh''s servants, and in the sight of the people.', '2~03068~ 3~05414~ 5~05971~ 6~02580~ 9~05869~ 12~04714~. 15~0376~ 16~04872~ [17] 18~03966~ 19~01419~ 22~0776~ 24~04714~, 27~05869~ 29~06547~ 30~05650~, 34~05869~ 37~05971~.'),
  (2214, 2, 25, 14, 'And thou shalt put the staves into the rings by the sides of the ark, that the ark may be borne with them.', '3~0935~ 5~0905~ 8~02885~ 11~06763~ 14~0727~, 17~0727~ 20~05375~'),
  (7530, 9, 14, 15, 'And there was trembling in the host, in the field, and among all the people: the garrison, and the spoilers, they also trembled, and the earth quaked: so it was a very great trembling.', '3~02731~ 6~04264~, 9~07704~, 14~05971~: 16~04673~, 19~07843~, 22~02729~, 25~0776~ 26~07264~: 32~0430~ 33~02731~.'),
  (28387, 46, 1, 8, 'Who shall also confirm you unto the end, that ye may be blameless in the day of our Lord Jesus Christ.', '0~3739~ 1~950~ 2~2532~ 3~950~ 4~5209~ 5~2193~ 7~5056~, [8 11] 12~410~ 13~1722~ 15~2250~ 17~2257~ 18~2962~ 19~2424~ 20~5547~.'),
  (26167, 43, 3, 32, 'And what he hath seen and heard, that he testifieth; and no man receiveth his testimony.', '0~2532~ 1~3739~ 4~3708~ 5~2532~ 6~191~, 7~5124~ 9~3140~; 10~2532~ 12~3762~ 13~2983~ 14~846~ 15~3141~.'),
  (25022, 42, 2, 37, 'And she was a widow of about fourscore and four years, which departed not from the temple, but served God with fastings and prayers night and day.', '0~2532~ 1~3778~ [2] 4~5503~ 6~5613~ 7~3589~ 9~5064~ 10~2094~, 11~3739~ 12~868~ 13~3756~ 14~575~ 16~2411~, 18~3000~ [19] 21~3521~ 22~2532~ 23~1162~ 24~3571~ 25~2532~ 26~2250~.'),
  (22764, 35, 2, 7, 'Shall they not rise up suddenly that shall bite thee, and awake that shall vex thee, and thou shalt be for booties unto them?', '4~06965~ 5~06621~ 8~05391~ 11~03364~ 14~02111~ 21~04933~'),
  (8454, 10, 16, 21, 'And Ahithophel said unto Absalom, Go in unto thy father''s concubines, which he hath left to keep the house; and all Israel shall hear that thou art abhorred of thy father: then shall the hands of all that are with thee be strong.', '1~0302~ 2~0559~ 4~053~, 6~0935~ 9~01~ 10~06370~, 14~03240~ 16~08104~ 18~01004~; 21~03478~ 23~08085~ 27~0887~ 30~01~: 34~03027~ [38] 42~02388~.'),
  (17007, 20, 21, 14, 'A gift in secret pacifieth anger: and a reward in the bosom strong wrath.', '&para; 1~04976~ 3~05643~ 4~03711~ 5~0639~: 8~07810~ 11~02436~ 12~05794~ 13~02534~.'),
  (6493, 6, 24, 10, 'But I would not hearken unto Balaam; therefore he blessed you still: so I delivered you out of his hand.', '2~014~ 4~08085~ 6~01109~; 9~01288~ 11~01288~: 14~05337~ 19~03027~.'),
  (23718, 40, 17, 8, 'And when they had lifted up their eyes, they saw no man, save Jesus only.', '0~1161~ 5~1869~ 6~846~ 7~3788~, 9~1492~ 11~3762~, 12~1508~ 13~2424~ 14~3441~.'),
  (2182, 2, 23, 33, 'They shall not dwell in thy land, lest they make thee sin against me: for if thou serve their gods, it will surely be a snare unto thee.', '3~03427~ 6~0776~, 11~02398~ 17~05647~ 19~0430~, 25~04170~'),
  (1331, 1, 44, 2, 'And put my cup, the silver cup, in the sack''s mouth of the youngest, and his corn money. And he did according to the word that Joseph had spoken.', '1~07760~ 3~01375~, 5~03701~ 6~01375~, 9~0572~ 10~06310~ 13~06996~, 16~07668~ 17~03701~. 20~06213~ 24~01697~ 26~03130~ 28~01696~.'),
  (21572, 26, 42, 11, 'And the way before them was like the appearance of the chambers which were toward the north, as long as they, and as broad as they: and all their goings out were both according to their fashions, and according to their doors.', '2~01870~ 3~06440~ [5] 8~04758~ 11~03957~ [13] 14~01870~ 16~06828~, 19~0753~ [21] 24~07341~ 25~03651~: 30~04161~ [31] 36~04941~, 41~06607~.'),
  (3888, 4, 7, 33, 'One young bullock, one ram, one lamb of the first year, for a burnt offering:', '0~0259~ 1~01241~ 2~06499~, 3~0259~ 4~0352~, 5~0259~ 6~03532~ 9~01121~ 10~08141~, 14~05930~:'),
  (7862, 9, 24, 16, 'And it came to pass, when David had made an end of speaking these words unto Saul, that Saul said, Is this thy voice, my son David? And Saul lifted up his voice, and wept.', '&para; 6~01732~ 10~03615~ 12~01696~ 14~01697~ 16~07586~, 18~07586~ 19~0559~, [20] 23~06963~, 25~01121~ 26~01732~? 28~07586~ 30~05375~ 32~06963~, 34~01058~.'),
  (19278, 24, 13, 3, 'And the word of the LORD came unto me the second time, saying,', '2~01697~ 5~03068~ 11~08145~, 12~0559~,'),
  (15020, 19, 72, 11, 'Yea, all kings shall fall down before him: all nations shall serve him.', '2~04428~ 5~07812~ 9~01471~ 11~05647~'),
  (18272, 23, 32, 4, 'The heart also of the rash shall understand knowledge, and the tongue of the stammerers shall be ready to speak plainly.', '1~03824~ 5~04116~ 7~0995~ 8~01847~, 11~03956~ 14~05926~ 17~04116~ 19~01696~ 20~06703~.'),
  (7828, 9, 23, 11, 'Will the men of Keilah deliver me up into his hand? will Saul come down, as thy servant hath heard? O LORD God of Israel, I beseech thee, tell thy servant. And the LORD said, He will come down.', '2~01167~ 4~07084~ 7~05462~ 10~03027~? 12~07586~ 14~03381~, 17~05650~ 19~08085~? 21~03068~ 22~0430~ 24~03478~, 28~05046~ 30~05650~. 33~03068~ 34~0559~, 38~03381~.'),
  (4962, 5, 2, 18, 'Thou art to pass over through Ar, the coast of Moab, this day:', '4~05674~ 6~06144~, 8~01366~ 10~04124~, 12~03117~:'),
  (30226, 58, 11, 38, '(Of whom the world was not worthy:) they wandered in deserts, and in mountains, and in dens and caves of the earth.', '1~3739~ 3~2889~ 4~2258~ 5~3756~ 6~514~:) 8~4105~ 9~1722~ 10~2047~, 11~2532~ [12] 13~3735~, 14~2532~ [15] 16~4693~ 17~2532~ 18~3692~ 21~1093~.'),
  (10163, 12, 22, 10, 'And Shaphan the scribe shewed the king, saying, Hilkiah the priest hath delivered me a book. And Shaphan read it before the king.', '1~08227~ 3~05608~ 4~05046~ 6~04428~, 7~0559~, 8~02518~ 10~03548~ 12~05414~ 15~05612~. 17~08227~ 18~07121~ 20~06440~ 22~04428~.'),
  (21663, 26, 45, 24, 'And he shall prepare a meat offering of an ephah for a bullock, and an ephah for a ram, and an hin of oil for an ephah.', '3~06213~ 6~04503~ 9~0374~ 12~06499~, 15~0374~ 18~0352~, 21~01969~ 23~08081~ 26~0374~.'),
  (14998, 19, 71, 13, 'Let them be confounded and consumed that are adversaries to my soul; let them be covered with reproach and dishonour that seek my hurt.', '3~0954~ [4] 5~03615~ 8~07853~ 11~05315~; 15~05844~ [16] 17~02781~ 19~03639~ 21~01245~ 23~07451~.'),
  (7622, 9, 16, 20, 'And Jesse took an ass laden with bread, and a bottle of wine, and a kid, and sent them by David his son unto Saul.', '1~03448~ 2~03947~ 4~02543~ [5] 7~03899~, 10~04997~ 12~03196~, 14~0259~ 15~05795~ 16~01423~,* 18~07971~ [19] 20~03027~ 21~01732~ 23~01121~ 25~07586~.'),
  (30255, 58, 12, 27, 'And this word, Yet once more, signifieth the removing of those things that are shaken, as of things that are made, that those things which cannot be shaken may remain.', '0~1161~ [2] 3~2089~ 5~530~, 6~1213~ 8~3331~ 14~4531~, 15~5613~ 20~4160~, 21~2443~ 25~3361~ 27~4531~ 29~3306~.'),
  (5817, 5, 33, 1, 'And this is the blessing, wherewith Moses the man of God blessed the children of Israel before his death.', '&para; [2] 4~01293~, 6~04872~ 8~0376~ 10~0430~ 11~01288~ 13~01121~ 15~03478~ 16~06440~ 18~04194~.'),
  (7699, 9, 18, 16, 'But all Israel and Judah loved David, because he went out and came in before them.', '2~03478~ 4~03063~ 5~0157~ 6~01732~, 10~03318~ 13~0935~ 14~06440~'),
  (9404, 11, 19, 9, 'And he came thither unto a cave, and lodged there; and, behold, the word of the LORD came to him, and he said unto him, What doest thou here, Elijah?', '&para; 2~0935~ 6~04631~, 8~03885~ 13~01697~ 16~03068~ [17] 22~0559~ 29~0452~?'),
  (21522, 26, 40, 36, 'The little chambers thereof, the posts thereof, and the arches thereof, and the windows to it round about: the length was fifty cubits, and the breadth five and twenty cubits.', '2~08372~ 5~0352~ 9~0361~ 13~02474~ 17~05439~: 19~0753~ [20] 21~02572~ 22~0520~, 25~07341~ 26~02568~ 28~06242~ 29~0520~.'),
  (13, 1, 1, 13, 'And the evening and the morning were the third day.', '2~06153~ 5~01242~ 8~07992~ 9~03117~.'),
  (5285, 5, 13, 7, 'Namely, of the gods of the people which are round about you, nigh unto thee, or far off from thee, from the one end of the earth even unto the other end of the earth;', '[0] 3~0430~ 6~05971~ [8] 10~05439~ 12~07138~ 17~07350~ [22] 23~07097~ 26~0776~ [30] 31~07097~ 34~0776~;'),
  (8940, 11, 6, 36, 'And he built the inner court with three rows of hewed stone, and a row of cedar beams.', '2~01129~ 4~06442~ 5~02691~ 7~07969~ 8~02905~ 11~01496~, 14~02905~ 16~0730~ 17~03773~.'),
  (4257, 4, 17, 8, 'And it came to pass, that on the morrow Moses went into the tabernacle of witness; and, behold, the rod of Aaron for the house of Levi was budded, and brought forth buds, and bloomed blossoms, and yielded almonds.', '&para; 8~04283~ 9~04872~ 10~0935~ 13~0168~ 15~05715~; 19~04294~ 21~0175~ 24~01004~ 26~03878~ 28~06524~, 31~03318~ 32~06525~, 34~06692~ 35~06731~, 37~01580~ 38~08247~.'),
  (4909, 5, 1, 11, '(The LORD God of your fathers make you a thousand times so many more as ye are, and bless you, as he hath promised you!)', '1~03068~ 2~0430~ 5~01~ 9~0505~ 10~06471~ 14~03254~ [16] 18~01288~ 23~01696~'),
  (20495, 26, 1, 22, 'And the likeness of the firmament upon the heads of the living creature was as the colour of the terrible crystal, stretched forth over their heads above.', '2~01823~ 5~07549~ 8~07218~ 12~02416~ [13] 16~05869~ 19~03372~ 20~07140~, 22~05186~ 25~07218~ 26~04605~.'),
  (13690, 18, 33, 31, 'Mark well, O Job, hearken unto me: hold thy peace, and I will speak.', '1~07181~, 3~0347~, 4~08085~ 9~02790~, 13~01696~.'),
  (24672, 41, 11, 21, 'And Peter calling to remembrance saith unto him, Master, behold, the fig tree which thou cursedst is withered away.', '0~2532~ 1~4074~ 4~363~ 5~3004~ 7~846~, 8~4461~, 9~2396~, 12~4808~ 13~3739~ 15~2672~ 18~3583~.'),
  (22380, 30, 1, 7, 'But I will send a fire on the wall of Gaza, which shall devour the palaces thereof:', '3~07971~ 5~0784~ 8~02346~ 10~05804~, 13~0398~ 15~0759~'),
  (1094, 1, 37, 6, 'And he said unto them, Hear, I pray you, this dream which I have dreamed:', '2~0559~ 5~08085~, 10~02472~ 14~02492~:'),
  (7002, 7, 18, 2, 'And the children of Dan sent of their family five men from their coasts, men of valour, from Zorah, and from Eshtaol, to spy out the land, and to search it; and they said unto them, Go, search the land: who when they came to mount Ephraim, to the house of Micah, they lodged there.', '2~01121~ 4~01835~ 5~07971~ 8~04940~ 9~02568~ 10~0582~ 13~07098~, 14~01121~ 16~02428~, 18~06881~, 21~0847~, 23~07270~ 26~0776~, 29~02713~ 33~0559~ 36~03212~, 37~02713~ 39~0776~: 43~0935~ 45~02022~ 46~0669~, 49~01004~ 51~04318~, 53~03885~'),
  (16742, 20, 12, 14, 'A man shall be satisfied with good by the fruit of his mouth: and the recompense of a man''s hands shall be rendered unto him.', '&para; 1~0376~ 4~07646~ 6~02896~ 9~06529~ [11] 12~06310~: 15~01576~ 18~0120~ 19~03027~ 22~07725~'),
  (25555, 42, 13, 24, 'Strive to enter in at the strait gate: for many, I say unto you, will seek to enter in, and shall not be able.', '0~75~ 3~1525~ 4~1223~ 6~4728~ 7~4439~: 8~3754~ 9~4183~, 11~3004~ 13~5213~, 15~2212~ 18~1525~, 19~2532~ 20~2480~ 21~3756~ 23~2480~.'),
  (17600, 22, 4, 9, 'Thou hast ravished my heart, my sister, my spouse; thou hast ravished my heart with one of thine eyes, with one chain of thy neck.', '4~03823~, 6~0269~, [7] 8~03618~; 13~03823~ 15~0259~ 18~05869~, 20~0259~ 21~06060~ 24~06677~.'),
  (22972, 38, 7, 1, 'And it came to pass in the fourth year of king Darius, that the word of the LORD came unto Zechariah in the fourth day of the ninth month, even in Chisleu;', '&para; 7~0702~ 8~08141~ 10~04428~ 11~01867~, [12] 14~01697~ 17~03068~ 20~02148~ 23~0702~ [24] 27~08671~ 28~02320~, [29] 31~03691~;'),
  (12698, 16, 13, 18, 'Did not your fathers thus, and did not our God bring all this evil upon us, and upon this city? yet ye bring more wrath upon Israel by profaning the sabbath.', '0~06213~ 3~01~ 6~0935~ 9~0430~ 10~0935~ 13~07451~ 19~05892~? 22~0935~ 23~03254~ 24~02740~ 26~03478~ 28~02490~ 30~07676~.'),
  (20212, 24, 50, 37, 'A sword is upon their horses, and upon their chariots, and upon all the mingled people that are in the midst of her; and they shall become as women: a sword is upon her treasures; and they shall be robbed.', '1~02719~ [2] 5~05483~, 9~07393~, 15~06153~ [17] 20~08432~ 28~0802~: 30~02719~ [31] 34~0214~; 39~0962~.'),
  (20852, 26, 17, 18, 'Seeing he despised the oath by breaking the covenant, when, lo, he had given his hand, and hath done all these things, he shall not escape.', '2~0959~ 4~0423~ 6~06565~ 8~01285~, 13~05414~ 15~03027~, 18~06213~ [21] 25~04422~.'),
  (25783, 42, 19, 38, 'Saying, Blessed be the King that cometh in the name of the Lord: peace in heaven, and glory in the highest.', '0~3004~, 1~2127~ [2] 4~935~ 6~2064~ 7~1722~ 9~3686~ 12~2962~: 13~1515~ 14~1722~ 15~3772~, 16~2532~ 17~1391~ 18~1722~ 20~5310~.'),
  (5091, 5, 5, 32, 'Ye shall observe to do therefore as the LORD your God hath commanded you: ye shall not turn aside to the right hand or to the left.', '2~08104~ 4~06213~ 8~03068~ 10~0430~ 12~06680~ 18~05493~ 22~03225~ 26~08040~.'),
  (17090, 20, 24, 2, 'For their heart studieth destruction, and their lips talk of mischief.', '2~03820~ 3~01897~ 4~07701~, 7~08193~ 8~01696~ 10~05999~.'),
  (29185, 48, 5, 7, 'Ye did run well; who did hinder you that ye should not obey the truth?', '2~5143~ 3~2573~; 4~5101~ 6~348~ 7~5209~ 10~3982~ 11~3361~ 12~3982~ 14~225~?'),
  (24257, 41, 1, 32, 'And at even, when the sun did set, they brought unto him all that were diseased, and them that were possessed with devils.', '0~1161~ 1~1096~ 2~3798~, 3~3753~ 5~2246~ 7~1416~, 9~5342~ 10~4314~ 11~846~ 12~3956~ 14~2192~ 15~2560~, 16~2532~ 22~1139~.'),
  (28641, 46, 11, 25, 'After the same manner also he took the cup, when he had supped, saying, This cup is the new testament in my blood: this do ye, as oft as ye drink it, in remembrance of me.', '3~5615~ 4~2532~ [5 6] 8~4221~, 9~3326~ 12~1172~, 13~3004~, 14~5124~ 15~4221~ 16~2076~ 18~2537~ 19~1242~ 20~1722~ 21~1699~ 22~129~: 23~5124~ 25~4160~, 28~302~ 29~3740~ 30~4095~ [31] 32~1519~ 33~364~ 35~1699~.'),
  (16904, 20, 17, 22, 'A merry heart doeth good like a medicine: but a broken spirit drieth the bones.', '&para; 1~08056~ 2~03820~ 4~03190~ [5] 7~01456~: 10~05218~ 11~07307~ 12~03001~ 14~01634~.'),
  (22785, 35, 3, 8, 'Was the LORD displeased against the rivers? was thine anger against the rivers? was thy wrath against the sea, that thou didst ride upon thine horses and thy chariots of salvation?', '2~03068~ 3~02734~ 6~05104~? [7] 9~0639~ 12~05104~? [13] 15~05678~ 18~03220~, 22~07392~ 25~05483~ [26] 28~04818~ 30~03444~?'),
  (11185, 13, 29, 13, 'Now therefore, our God, we thank thee, and praise thy glorious name.', '3~0430~, 5~03034~ 8~01984~ 10~08597~ 11~08034~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (21336, 26, 34, 14, 'I will feed them in a good pasture, and upon the high mountains of Israel shall their fold be: there shall they lie in a good fold, and in a fat pasture shall they feed upon the mountains of Israel.', '2~07462~ 6~02896~ 7~04829~, 11~04791~ 12~02022~ 14~03478~ 17~05116~ 22~07257~ 25~02896~ 26~05116~, [28] 30~08082~ 31~04829~ 34~07462~ 37~02022~ 39~03478~.'),
  (6925, 7, 14, 9, 'And he took thereof in his hands, and went on eating, and came to his father and mother, and he gave them, and they did eat: but he told not them that he had taken the honey out of the carcase of the lion.', '2~07287~ 6~03709~, 9~03212~ 10~0398~, 12~01980~ 15~01~ 17~0517~, 20~05414~ 25~0398~: 28~05046~ 34~07287~ 36~01706~ 40~01472~ 43~0738~.'),
  (20274, 24, 51, 53, 'Though Babylon should mount up to heaven, and though she should fortify the height of her strength, yet from me shall spoilers come unto her, saith the LORD.', '1~0894~ 4~05927~ 6~08064~, 11~01219~ 13~04791~ 16~05797~, [17] 17~0227~ 21~07703~ 22~0935~ 25~05002~ 27~03068~.'),
  (17364, 21, 2, 22, 'For what hath man of all his labour, and of the vexation of his heart, wherein he hath laboured under the sun?', '2~01933~ 3~0120~ 7~05999~, 11~07475~ 14~03820~, 15~01931~ 18~06001~ 21~08121~?'),
  (28984, 47, 9, 12, 'For the administration of this service not only supplieth the want of the saints, but is abundant also by many thanksgivings unto God;', '0~3754~ 2~1248~ 4~5026~ 5~3009~ 6~3756~ 7~3440~ 8~2076~ 9~4322~* 11~5303~ 14~40~, 15~235~ 17~4052~ 18~2532~ 19~1223~ 20~4183~ 21~2169~ 23~2316~;'),
  (24964, 42, 1, 59, 'And it came to pass, that on the eighth day they came to circumcise the child; and they called him Zacharias, after the name of his father.', '0~2532~ 4~1096~, 6~1722~ 8~3590~ 9~2250~ 11~2064~ 13~4059~ 15~3813~; 16~2532~ 18~2564~ 19~846~ 20~2197~, 21~1909~ 23~3686~ 25~846~ 26~3962~.'),
  (2869, 3, 6, 15, 'And he shall take of it his handful, of the flour of the meat offering, and of the oil thereof, and all the frankincense which is upon the meat offering, and shall burn it upon the altar for a sweet savour, even the memorial of it, unto the LORD.', '3~07311~ 7~07062~, 10~05560~ 14~04503~, 18~08081~ 23~03828~ [25] 29~04503~, 32~06999~ [33] 36~04196~ [37] 39~05207~ 40~07381~, [41] 43~0234~ 48~03068~.'),
  (23371, 40, 8, 16, 'When the even was come, they brought unto him many that were possessed with devils: and he cast out the spirits with his word, and healed all that were sick:', '0~1161~ 2~3798~ 4~1096~, 6~4374~ 8~846~ 9~4183~ 14~1139~: 15~2532~ 18~1544~ 20~4151~ [22] 23~3056~, 24~2532~ 25~2323~ 26~3956~ 28~2192~ 29~2560~:'),
  (18474, 23, 41, 14, 'Fear not, thou worm Jacob, and ye men of Israel; I will help thee, saith the LORD, and thy redeemer, the Holy One of Israel.', '0~03372~ 3~08438~ 4~03290~, [5] 7~04962~ 9~03478~; 12~05826~ 14~05002~ 16~03068~, 19~01350~, 22~06918~ 24~03478~.'),
  (10358, 13, 2, 44, 'And Shema begat Raham, the father of Jorkoam: and Rekem begat Shammai.', '1~08087~ 2~03205~ 3~07357~, 5~01~ 7~03421~: 9~07552~ 10~03205~ 11~08060~.'),
  (2106, 2, 21, 24, 'Eye for eye, tooth for tooth, hand for hand, foot for foot,', '0~05869~ 2~05869~, 3~08127~ 5~08127~, 6~03027~ 8~03027~, 9~07272~ 11~07272~,'),
  (1357, 1, 44, 28, 'And the one went out from me, and I said, Surely he is torn in pieces; and I saw him not since:', '2~0259~ 4~03318~ 9~0559~, 10~02963~ 15~02963~; 19~07200~ 21~02008~:'),
  (416, 1, 17, 15, 'And God said unto Abraham, As for Sarai thy wife, thou shalt not call her name Sarai, but Sarah shall her name be.', '&para; 1~0430~ 2~0559~ 4~085~, 7~08297~ 9~0802~, 13~07121~ 15~08034~ 16~08297~, 17~03588~ 18~08283~ [19] 21~08034~ [22]'),
  (19908, 24, 38, 4, 'Therefore the princes said unto the king, We beseech thee, let this man be put to death: for thus he weakeneth the hands of the men of war that remain in this city, and the hands of all the people, in speaking such words unto them: for this man seeketh not the welfare of this people, but the hurt.', '2~08269~ 3~0559~ 6~04428~, 12~0376~ 16~04191~: 18~03651~ 20~07503~ 22~03027~ 25~0582~ 27~04421~ 29~07604~ 32~05892~, 35~03027~ 39~05971~, 41~01696~ 43~01697~ 48~0376~ 49~01875~ 52~07965~ 55~05971~, 58~07451~.'),
  (14449, 19, 36, 2, 'For he flattereth himself in his own eyes, until his iniquity be found to be hateful.', '2~02505~ 7~05869~, 10~05771~ 12~04672~ 15~08130~.'),
  (7689, 9, 18, 6, 'And it came to pass as they came, when David was returned from the slaughter of the Philistine, that the women came out of all cities of Israel, singing and dancing, to meet king Saul, with tabrets, with joy, and with instruments of music.', '&para; 7~0935~, 9~01732~ 11~07725~ 14~05221~ 17~06430~, 20~0802~ 22~03318~ 25~05892~ 27~03478~, 28~07891~ 30~04246~, 32~07125~ 33~04428~ 34~07586~, 36~08596~, 38~08057~, 41~07991~'),
  (4337, 4, 20, 21, 'Thus Edom refused to give Israel passage through his border: wherefore Israel turned away from him.', '1~0123~ 2~03985~ 4~05414~ 5~03478~ 6~05674~ 9~01366~: 11~03478~ 13~05186~'),
  (20655, 26, 10, 13, 'As for the wheels, it was cried unto them in my hearing, O wheel.', '3~0212~, 6~07121~ 11~0241~, 13~01534~.'),
  (22263, 28, 12, 2, 'The LORD hath also a controversy with Judah, and will punish Jacob according to his ways; according to his doings will he recompense him.', '1~03068~ 5~07379~ 7~03063~, 10~06485~ 11~03290~ 15~01870~; 19~04611~ 22~07725~'),
  (8396, 10, 14, 33, 'So Joab came to the king, and told him: and when he had called for Absalom, he came to the king, and bowed himself on his face to the ground before the king: and the king kissed Absalom.', '1~03097~ 2~0935~ 5~04428~, 7~05046~ 13~07121~ 15~053~, 17~0935~ 20~04428~, 22~07812~ 26~0639~ 29~0776~ 30~06440~ 32~04428~: 35~04428~ 36~05401~ 37~053~.'),
  (17920, 23, 13, 5, 'They come from a far country, from the end of heaven, even the LORD, and the weapons of his indignation, to destroy the whole land.', '1~0935~ 4~04801~ 5~0776~, 8~07097~ 10~08064~, [11] 13~03068~, 16~03627~ 19~02195~, 21~02254~ 24~0776~.'),
  (6662, 7, 6, 1, 'And the children of Israel did evil in the sight of the LORD: and the LORD delivered them into the hand of Midian seven years.', '&para; 2~01121~ 4~03478~ 5~06213~ 6~07451~ 9~05869~ 12~03068~: 15~03068~ 16~05414~ 20~03027~ 22~04080~ 23~07651~ 24~08141~.'),
  (13946, 18, 42, 15, 'And in all the land were no women found so fair as the daughters of Job: and their father gave them inheritance among their brethren.', '4~0776~ 7~0802~ 8~04672~ [9] 10~03303~ 13~01323~ 15~0347~: 18~01~ 19~05414~ 21~05159~ 22~08432~ 24~0251~.'),
  (4989, 5, 3, 8, 'And we took at that time out of the hand of the two kings of the Amorites the land that was on this side Jordan, from the river of Arnon unto mount Hermon;', '2~03947~ 5~06256~ 6~03947~ 9~03027~ 12~08147~ 13~04428~ 16~0567~ 18~0776~ [20] 23~05676~ 24~03383~, 27~05158~ 29~0769~ 31~02022~ 32~02768~;'),
  (15337, 19, 89, 2, 'For I have said, Mercy shall be built up for ever: thy faithfulness shalt thou establish in the very heavens.', '3~0559~, 4~02617~ 8~01129~ 10~05769~: 12~0530~ 15~03559~ 19~08064~.'),
  (21949, 27, 7, 7, 'After this I saw in the night visions, and behold a fourth beast, dreadful and terrible, and strong exceedingly; and it had great iron teeth: it devoured and brake in pieces, and stamped the residue with the feet of it: and it was diverse from all the beasts that were before it; and it had ten horns.', '0~0870~ 1~01836~ 3~01934~ 4~02370~* 7~03916~ 8~02376~, 10~0718~ 12~07244~ 13~02423~, 14~01763~ 16~0574~, 18~08624~ 19~03493~; 23~07260~ 24~06523~ 25~08128~: 27~0399~ 31~01855~, 33~07512~ 35~07606~ 38~07271~ 42~01932~ [43] 44~08133~ 45~04481~ 46~03606~ 48~02423~ [50] 51~06925~ 56~06236~ 57~07162~.'),
  (2222, 2, 25, 22, 'And there I will meet with thee, and I will commune with thee from above the mercy seat, from between the two cherubims which are upon the ark of the testimony, of all things which I will give thee in commandment unto the children of Israel.', '4~03259~ 10~01696~ 17~03727~, 19~0996~ 21~08147~ 22~03742~ [24] 25~05921~ 27~0727~ 30~05715~, [33] 40~06680~ 43~01121~ 45~03478~.'),
  (28101, 45, 6, 17, 'But God be thanked, that ye were the servants of sin, but ye have obeyed from the heart that form of doctrine which was delivered you.', '0~1161~ 1~2316~ 3~5485~, 4~3754~ 6~2258~ 8~1401~ 10~266~, 11~1161~ 14~5219~ 15~1537~ 17~2588~ 19~5179~ 21~1322~ 22~3739~ 23~1519~ 25~3860~.'),
  (29668, 53, 1, 3, 'We are bound to thank God always for you, brethren, as it is meet, because that your faith groweth exceedingly, and the charity of every one of you all toward each other aboundeth;', '2~3784~ 4~2168~ 5~2316~ 6~3842~ 7~4012~ 8~5216~, 9~80~, 10~2531~ 12~2076~ 13~514~, 14~3754~ 16~5216~ 17~4102~ 19~5232~, 20~2532~ 22~26~ 24~1538~ 25~1520~ 27~5216~ 28~3956~ 29~1519~ 31~240~ 32~4121~;'),
  (21382, 26, 36, 14, 'Therefore thou shalt devour men no more, neither bereave thy nations any more, saith the Lord GOD.', '3~0398~ 4~0120~ 8~07921~ 9~03782~* 11~01471~ 14~05002~ 16~0136~ 17~03069~.'),
  (17745, 23, 4, 3, 'And it shall come to pass, that he that is left in Zion, and he that remaineth in Jerusalem, shall be called holy, even every one that is written among the living in Jerusalem:', '[6 9] 10~07604~ 12~06726~, [14 15] 16~03498~ 18~03389~, 21~0559~ 22~06918~, [23] 28~03789~ 31~02416~ 33~03389~:'),
  (12184, 15, 7, 2, 'The son of Shallum, the son of Zadok, the son of Ahitub,', '1~01121~ 3~07967~, 5~01121~ 7~06659~, 9~01121~ 11~0285~,'),
  (21952, 27, 7, 10, 'A fiery stream issued and came forth from before him: thousand thousands ministered unto him, and ten thousand times ten thousand stood before him: the judgment was set, and the books were opened.', '1~05135~ 2~05103~ 3~05047~ 6~05312~ 7~04481~ 8~06925~ 10~0506~ 11~0506~ 12~08120~ 17~07240~ 20~07240~ 21~06966~ 22~06925~ 25~01780~ 27~03488~, 30~05609~ 32~06606~.'),
  (5536, 5, 24, 5, 'When a man hath taken a new wife, he shall not go out to war, neither shall he be charged with any business: but he shall be free at home one year, and shall cheer up his wife which he hath taken.', '&para; 2~0376~ 4~03947~ 6~02319~ 7~0802~, 12~03318~ 14~06635~, 19~05674~ 22~01697~: [23] 27~05355~ 29~01004~ 30~0259~ 31~08141~, 35~08055~ 37~0802~ 41~03947~.'),
  (28075, 45, 5, 12, 'Wherefore, as by one man sin entered into the world, and death by sin; and so death passed upon all men, for that all have sinned:', '0~5124~ 1~1223~,* 2~5618~ 3~1223~ 4~1520~ 5~444~ 6~266~ 7~1525~ 8~1519~ 10~2889~, 11~2532~ 12~2288~ 13~1223~ 14~266~; 15~2532~ 16~3779~ 17~2288~ 18~1330~ 19~1519~ 20~3956~ 21~444~, 22~1909~ 23~3739~ 24~3956~ 26~264~:'),
  (19647, 24, 29, 3, 'By the hand of Elasah the son of Shaphan, and Gemariah the son of Hilkiah, (whom Zedekiah king of Judah sent unto Babylon to Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon) saying,', '2~03027~ 4~0501~ 6~01121~ 8~08227~, 10~01587~ 12~01121~ 14~02518~, 16~06667~ 17~04428~ 19~03063~ 20~07971~ 22~0894~ 24~05019~ 25~04428~ 27~0894~) 28~0559~,'),
  (13162, 18, 12, 25, 'They grope in the dark without light, and he maketh them to stagger like a drunken man.', '1~04959~ 4~02822~ 6~0216~, 12~08582~ [14] 15~07910~ [16]'),
  (17685, 23, 1, 22, 'Thy silver is become dross, thy wine mixed with water:', '1~03701~ 4~05509~, 6~05435~ 7~04107~ 9~04325~:'),
  (20492, 26, 1, 19, 'And when the living creatures went, the wheels went by them: and when the living creatures were lifted up from the earth, the wheels were lifted up.', '4~02416~ 5~03212~, 7~0212~ 8~03212~ 10~0681~: 15~02416~ 18~05375~ 21~0776~, 23~0212~ 26~05375~.'),
  (30716, 66, 1, 3, 'Blessed is he that readeth, and they that hear the words of this prophecy, and keep those things which are written therein: for the time is at hand.', '&para; 0~3107~ [1] 4~314~, 5~2532~ 8~191~ 10~3056~ 13~4394~, 14~2532~ 15~5083~ 20~1125~ 21~846~ 22~1722~:* 23~1063~ 25~2540~ [26] 28~1451~.'),
  (30886, 66, 10, 9, 'And I went unto the angel, and said unto him, Give me the little book. And he said unto me, Take it, and eat it up; and it shall make thy belly bitter, but it shall be in thy mouth sweet as honey.', '0~2532~ 2~565~ 3~4314~ 5~32~, 7~3004~ 9~846~, 10~1325~ 11~3427~ 14~974~. 15~2532~ 17~3004~ 19~3427~, 20~2983~ [21] 22~2532~ 23~2719~ 24~846~ 25~2719~; 27~2532~ 29~4087~ 30~4675~ 31~2836~ 32~4087~, 33~235~ 36~2071~ 37~1722~ 38~4675~ 39~4750~ 40~1099~ 41~5613~ 42~3192~.'),
  (11669, 14, 23, 4, 'This is the thing that ye shall do; A third part of you entering on the sabbath, of the priests and of the Levites, shall be porters of the doors;', '[1] 3~01697~ 7~06213~; 10~07992~ 13~0935~ 16~07676~, 19~03548~ 23~03881~, [24 25] 26~07778~ 29~05592~;'),
  (16613, 20, 8, 2, 'She standeth in the top of high places, by the way in the places of the paths.', '1~05324~ 4~07218~ 7~04791~, 10~01870~ 13~01004~ 16~05410~.'),
  (20406, 25, 3, 43, 'Thou hast covered with anger, and persecuted us: thou hast slain, thou hast not pitied.', '2~05526~ 4~0639~, 6~07291~ 10~02026~, 14~02550~.'),
  (16527, 20, 5, 1, 'My son, attend unto my wisdom, and bow thine ear to my understanding:', '&para; 1~01121~, 2~07181~ 5~02451~, [6] 7~05186~ 9~0241~ 12~08394~:'),
  (17208, 20, 28, 3, 'A poor man that oppresseth the poor is like a sweeping rain which leaveth no food.', '&para; 1~07326~ 2~01397~ 4~06231~ 6~01800~ [7 8] 10~05502~ 11~04306~ 15~03899~.'),
  (2230, 2, 25, 30, 'And thou shalt set upon the table shewbread before me alway.', '3~05414~ 6~07979~ 7~03899~ 8~06440~ 10~08548~.'),
  (26561, 43, 11, 23, 'Jesus saith unto her, Thy brother shall rise again.', '0~2424~ 1~3004~ 3~846~, 4~4675~ 5~80~ 8~450~.'),
  (10751, 13, 12, 23, 'And these are the numbers of the bands that were ready armed to the war, and came to David to Hebron, to turn the kingdom of Saul to him, according to the word of the LORD.', '&para; [2] 4~04557~ 7~07218~ [8 9] 11~02502~ 14~06635~, [15] 16~0935~ 18~01732~ 20~02275~, 22~05437~ 24~04438~ 26~07586~ 32~06310~ 35~03068~.'),
  (7357, 9, 6, 19, 'And he smote the men of Bethshemesh, because they had looked into the ark of the LORD, even he smote of the people fifty thousand and threescore and ten men: and the people lamented, because the LORD had smitten many of the people with a great slaughter.', '&para; 2~05221~ 4~0376~ 6~01053~, 10~07200~ 13~0727~ 16~03068~, 19~05221~ 22~05971~ 23~02572~ 24~0505~ 28~07657~ 29~0582~: 32~05971~ 33~056~, 36~03068~ 38~05221~ [39] 42~05971~ 45~01419~ 46~04347~.'),
  (4410, 4, 22, 30, 'And the ass said unto Balaam, Am not I thine ass, upon which thou hast ridden ever since I was thine unto this day? was I ever wont to do so unto thee? And he said, Nay.', '2~0860~ 3~0559~ 5~01109~, [6] 10~0860~, 15~07392~ [18 19] 23~03117~? 26~05532~ 27~05532~ 30~06213~ 35~0559~,'),
  (11613, 14, 20, 17, 'Ye shall not need to fight in this battle: set yourselves, stand ye still, and see the salvation of the LORD with you, O Judah and Jerusalem: fear not, nor be dismayed; to morrow go out against them: for the LORD will be with you.', '[3] 5~03898~ 7~02063~ [8] 9~03320~ 11~05975~ [13] 15~07200~ 17~03444~ 20~03068~ 24~03063~ 26~03389~: 27~03372~ 31~02865~; 33~04279~ 35~03318~ 36~06440~ 40~03068~ [41 42]'),
  (18979, 24, 2, 5, 'Thus saith the LORD, What iniquity have your fathers found in me, that they are gone far from me, and have walked after vanity, and are become vain?', '1~0559~ 3~03068~, 5~05766~ 8~01~ 9~04672~ 16~07368~ 21~03212~ 22~0310~ 23~01892~, 27~01891~?'),
  (27145, 44, 7, 13, 'And at the second time Joseph was made known to his brethren; and Joseph''s kindred was made known unto Pharaoh.', '0~2532~ 1~1722~ 3~1208~ [4] 5~2501~ 8~319~ 10~846~ 11~80~; 12~2532~ 13~2501~ 14~1085~ 16~1096~ 17~5318~ 19~5328~.'),
  (8616, 10, 22, 6, 'The sorrows of hell compassed me about; the snares of death prevented me;', '1~02256~ 3~07585~ 6~05437~; 8~04170~ 10~04194~ 11~06923~'),
  (29488, 51, 1, 7, 'As ye also learned of Epaphras our dear fellowservant, who is for you a faithful minister of Christ;', '0~2531~ 1~3129~ 2~2532~ 3~3129~ 4~575~ 5~1889~ 6~2257~ 7~27~ 8~4889~, 9~3739~ 10~2076~ 11~5228~ 12~5216~ 14~4103~ 15~1249~ 17~5547~;'),
  (5487, 5, 22, 11, 'Thou shalt not wear a garment of divers sorts, as of woollen and linen together.', '3~03847~ 8~08162~, [9] 11~06785~ 13~06593~ 14~03162~.'),
  (24730, 41, 13, 2, 'And Jesus answering said unto him, Seest thou these great buildings? there shall not be left one stone upon another, that shall not be thrown down.', '0~2532~ 1~2424~ 2~611~ 3~2036~ 5~846~, 7~991~ 8~5025~ 9~3173~ 10~3619~? 12~863~ 13~3364~ 15~863~ 17~3037~ 18~1909~ 19~3037~, 20~3739~ 21~2647~ 22~3364~ 25~2647~.'),
  (11181, 13, 29, 9, 'Then the people rejoiced, for that they offered willingly, because with perfect heart they offered willingly to the LORD: and David the king also rejoiced with great joy.', '2~05971~ 3~08055~, 8~05068~, 11~08003~ 12~03820~ 15~05068~ 18~03068~: 20~01732~ 22~04428~ 24~08055~ 26~01419~ 27~08057~.'),
  (1803, 2, 10, 21, 'And the LORD said unto Moses, Stretch out thine hand toward heaven, that there may be darkness over the land of Egypt, even darkness which may be felt.', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~04872~, 7~05186~ 9~03027~ 11~08064~, 16~02822~ 19~0776~ 21~04714~, 23~02822~ [24] 27~04959~.'),
  (7550, 9, 14, 35, 'And Saul built an altar unto the LORD: the same was the first altar that he built unto the LORD.', '1~07586~ 2~01129~ 4~04196~ 7~03068~: 12~02490~ 13~04196~ 16~01129~ 19~03068~.'),
  (18344, 23, 36, 5, 'I say, sayest thou, (but they are but vain words) I have counsel and strength for war: now on whom dost thou trust, that thou rebellest against me?', '1~0559~, [2 3] [5 7] 8~08193~ 9~01697~) [10 11] 12~06098~ 14~01369~ 16~04421~: 22~0982~, 25~04775~'),
  (28086, 45, 6, 2, 'God forbid. How shall we, that are dead to sin, live any longer therein?', '1~1096~ 2~3361~.* 3~4459~ 6~3748~ 8~599~ 10~266~, 11~2198~ 13~2089~ 14~846~ 15~1722?~*'),
  (11563, 14, 18, 12, 'And the messenger that went to call Micaiah spake to him, saying, Behold, the words of the prophets declare good to the king with one assent; let thy word therefore, I pray thee, be like one of theirs, and speak thou good.', '2~04397~ 4~01980~ 6~07121~ 7~04321~ 8~01696~ 11~0559~, 14~01697~ 17~05030~ [18] 19~02896~ 22~04428~ 24~0259~ 25~06310~; 28~01697~ 35~0259~ 39~01696~ 41~02896~.'),
  (9330, 11, 17, 5, 'So he went and did according unto the word of the LORD: for he went and dwelt by the brook Cherith, that is before Jordan.', '2~03212~ 4~06213~ 8~01697~ 11~03068~: 14~03212~ 16~03427~ 19~05158~ 20~03747~, [22] 23~06440~ 24~03383~.'),
  (25072, 42, 3, 35, 'Which was the son of Saruch, which was the son of Ragau, which was the son of Phalec, which was the son of Heber, which was the son of Sala,', '[2 3] 5~4562~, [8 9] 11~4466~, [14 15] 17~5317~, [20 21] 23~1443~, [26 27] 29~4527~,'),
  (1906, 2, 14, 12, 'Is not this the word that we did tell thee in Egypt, saying, Let us alone, that we may serve the Egyptians? For it had been better for us to serve the Egyptians, than that we should die in the wilderness.', '[0] 4~01697~ 8~01696~ 11~04714~, 12~0559~, 15~02308~, 19~05647~ 21~04714~? [23 25] 26~02896~ 30~05647~ 32~04714~, 37~04191~ 40~04057~.'),
  (22532, 31, 1, 13, 'Thou shouldest not have entered into the gate of my people in the day of their calamity; yea, thou shouldest not have looked on their affliction in the day of their calamity, nor have laid hands on their substance in the day of their calamity;', '4~0935~ 7~08179~ 10~05971~ 13~03117~ 16~0343~; 22~07200~ 25~07451~ 28~03117~ 31~0343~, 34~07971~ [35] 38~02428~ 41~03117~ 44~0343~;'),
  (25154, 42, 5, 35, 'But the days will come, when the bridegroom shall be taken away from them, and then shall they fast in those days.', '0~1161~ 2~2250~ 4~2064~, 5~2532~ 6~3752~ 7~3566~ 11~522~ 12~575~ 13~846~, 15~5119~ 18~3522~ 19~1722~ 20~1565~ 21~2250~.'),
  (4858, 4, 35, 7, 'So all the cities which ye shall give to the Levites shall be forty and eight cities: them shall ye give with their suburbs.', '[0] 3~05892~ 7~05414~ 10~03881~ [11 12] 13~0705~ 15~08083~ 16~05892~: [18 20] 23~04054~.'),
  (21764, 27, 1, 18, 'Now at the end of the days that the king had said he should bring them in, then the prince of the eunuchs brought them in before Nebuchadnezzar.', '3~07117~ 6~03117~ 9~04428~ 11~0559~ 14~0935~ 19~08269~ 22~05631~ 23~0935~ 26~06440~ 27~05019~.'),
  (1453, 1, 47, 28, 'And Jacob lived in the land of Egypt seventeen years: so the whole age of Jacob was an hundred forty and seven years.', '1~03290~ 2~02421~ 5~0776~ 7~04714~ 8~07651~ 9~06240~* 10~08141~: 14~03117~ 15~02416~ 16~03290~ 19~03967~ 20~08141~ 21~0705~ 22~07651~ 23~08141~.'),
  (558, 1, 22, 7, 'And Isaac spake unto Abraham his father, and said, My father: and he said, Here am I, my son. And he said, Behold the fire and the wood: but where is the lamb for a burnt offering?', '1~03327~ 2~0559~ 4~085~ 6~01~, 8~0559~, 10~01~: 13~0559~, [15] 18~01121~. 21~0559~, 24~0784~ 27~06086~: [30] 32~07716~ 36~05930~?'),
  (10561, 13, 7, 18, 'And his sister Hammoleketh bare Ishod, and Abiezer, and Mahalah.', '2~0269~ 3~04447~ 4~03205~ 5~0379~, 7~044~, 9~04244~.'),
  (6372, 6, 19, 44, 'And Eltekeh, and Gibbethon, and Baalath,', '1~0514~, 3~01405~, 5~01191~,'),
  (14533, 19, 39, 12, 'Hear my prayer, O LORD, and give ear unto my cry; hold not thy peace at my tears: for I am a stranger with thee, and a sojourner, as all my fathers were.', '0~08085~ 2~08605~, 4~03068~, 7~0238~ 10~07775~; 14~02790~ 17~01832~: [20] 22~01616~ [25] 27~08453~, 31~01~ [32]'),
  (8924, 11, 6, 20, 'And the oracle in the forepart was twenty cubits in length, and twenty cubits in breadth, and twenty cubits in the height thereof: and he overlaid it with pure gold; and so covered the altar which was of cedar.', '2~01687~ 5~06440~ [6] 7~06242~ 8~0520~ 10~0753~, 12~06242~ 13~0520~ 15~07341~, 17~06242~ 18~0520~ 21~06967~ 25~06823~ 28~05462~ 29~02091~; [31] 32~06823~ 34~04196~ [35 37] 38~0730~.'),
  (8893, 11, 5, 7, 'And it came to pass, when Hiram heard the words of Solomon, that he rejoiced greatly, and said, Blessed be the LORD this day, which hath given unto David a wise son over this great people.', '6~02438~ 7~08085~ 9~01697~ 11~08010~, 14~08055~ 15~03966~, 17~0559~, 18~01288~ [19] 21~03068~ 23~03117~, 26~05414~ 28~01732~ 30~02450~ 31~01121~ 34~07227~ 35~05971~.'),
  (561, 1, 22, 10, 'And Abraham stretched forth his hand, and took the knife to slay his son.', '1~085~ 3~07971~ 5~03027~, 7~03947~ 9~03979~ 11~07819~ 13~01121~.'),
  (1072, 1, 36, 27, 'The children of Ezer are these; Bilhan, and Zaavan, and Akan.', '1~01121~ 3~0687~ [4] 6~01092~, 8~02190~, 10~06130~.'),
  (3570, 3, 26, 41, 'And that I also have walked contrary unto them, and have brought them into the land of their enemies; if then their uncircumcised hearts be humbled, and they then accept of the punishment of their iniquity:', '[1] 5~03212~ 6~07147~ 11~0935~ 15~0776~ 18~0341~; 20~0176~ 22~06189~ 23~03824~ 25~03665~, 29~07521~ 35~05771~:'),
  (4924, 5, 1, 26, 'Notwithstanding ye would not go up, but rebelled against the commandment of the LORD your God:', '2~014~ 5~05927~, 7~04784~ 10~06310~ 13~03068~ 15~0430~:'),
  (29332, 49, 5, 12, 'For it is a shame even to speak of those things which are done of them in secret.', '0~1063~ 2~2076~ 4~149~ 5~2532~ 7~3004~ 10~2931~ 13~1096~ 14~5259~ 15~846~ 17~2931~.'),
  (24175, 40, 27, 36, 'And sitting down they watched him there;', '0~2532~ 2~2521~ 4~5083~ 5~846~ 6~1563~;'),
  (19273, 24, 12, 15, 'And it shall come to pass, after that I have plucked them out I will return, and have compassion on them, and will bring them again, every man to his heritage, and every man to his land.', '6~0310~ 12~05428~ 15~07725~, 18~07355~ 25~07725~, 27~0376~ 30~05159~, 33~0376~ 36~0776~.'),
  (19847, 24, 35, 15, 'I have sent also unto you all my servants the prophets, rising up early and sending them, saying, Return ye now every man from his evil way, and amend your doings, and go not after other gods to serve them, and ye shall dwell in the land which I have given to you and to your fathers: but ye have not inclined your ear, nor hearkened unto me.', '2~07971~ 8~05650~ 10~05030~, 13~07925~ 15~07971~ [16] 17~0559~, 18~07725~ 22~0376~ 25~07451~ 26~01870~, 28~03190~ 30~04611~, 32~03212~ 34~0310~ 35~0312~ 36~0430~ 38~05647~ 44~03427~ 46~0127~ 50~05414~ 56~01~: 61~05186~ 63~0241~, 65~08085~'),
  (4548, 4, 26, 53, 'Unto these the land shall be divided for an inheritance according to the number of names.', '3~0776~ 6~02505~ 9~05159~ 13~04557~ 15~08034~.'),
  (7283, 9, 2, 36, 'And it shall come to pass, that every one that is left in thine house shall come and crouch to him for a piece of silver and a morsel of bread, and shall say, Put me, I pray thee, into one of the priests'' offices, that I may eat a piece of bread.', '[6] 11~03498~ 14~01004~ 16~0935~ [17] 18~07812~ 23~095~ 25~03701~ 28~03603~ 30~03899~, 33~0559~, 34~05596~ 40~0259~ 44~03550~, 48~0398~ 50~06595~ 52~03899~.'),
  (21540, 26, 41, 5, 'After he measured the wall of the house, six cubits; and the breadth of every side chamber, four cubits, round about the house on every side.', '2~04058~ 4~07023~ 7~01004~, 8~08337~ 9~0520~; 12~07341~ [14] 16~06763~, 17~0702~ 18~0520~, 20~05439~ 22~01004~ 25~05439~.'),
  (31107, 66, 22, 11, 'He that is unjust, let him be unjust still: and he which is filthy, let him be filthy still: and he that is righteous, let him be righteous still: and he that is holy, let him be holy still.', '3~91~, 7~91~ 8~2089~: 9~2532~ 13~4510~, 17~4510~ 18~2089~: 19~2532~ 23~1342~, 27~1344~ 28~2089~: 29~2532~ 33~40~, 37~37~ 38~2089~.'),
  (18605, 23, 46, 10, 'Declaring the end from the beginning, and from ancient times the things that are not yet done, saying, My counsel shall stand, and I will do all my pleasure:', '0~05046~ 2~0319~ 5~07225~, 9~06924~ [10 11] [15] 16~06213~, 17~0559~, 19~06098~ 21~06965~, 25~06213~ 28~02656~:'),
  (25513, 42, 12, 41, 'Then Peter said unto him, Lord, speakest thou this parable unto us, or even to all?', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~4074~ 2~2036~ 4~846~, 5~2962~, 7~3004~ 8~5026~ 9~3850~ 10~4314~ 11~2248~, 12~2228~ 13~2532~ 14~4314~ 15~3956~?'),
  (28992, 47, 10, 5, 'Casting down imaginations, and every high thing that exalteth itself against the knowledge of God, and bringing into captivity every thought to the obedience of Christ;', '1~2507~ 2~3053~, 3~2532~ 4~3956~ 6~5313~ 9~1869~ 10~2596~ 12~1108~ 14~2316~, 15~2532~ 18~163~ 19~3956~ 20~3540~ 21~1519~ 23~5218~ 25~5547~;'),
  (16044, 19, 119, 137, 'TZADDI. Righteous art thou, O LORD, and upright are thy judgments.', '&para; 1~06662~ [2] 5~03068~, 7~03477~ [8] 10~04941~.'),
  (28903, 47, 5, 10, 'For we must all appear before the judgment seat of Christ; that every one may receive the things done in his body, according to that he hath done, whether it be good or bad.', '0~1063~ 1~2248~ 2~1163~ 3~3956~ 4~5319~ 5~1715~ 8~968~ 10~5547~; 11~2443~ 13~1538~ 15~2865~ [18] 19~1223~ [20] 21~4983~, 22~4314~ 24~3739~ 27~4238~, 28~1535~ [29 30] 31~18~ 32~1535~ 33~2556~.'),
  (6269, 6, 15, 60, 'Kirjathbaal, which is Kirjathjearim, and Rabbah; two cities with their villages:', '0~07154~, [2] 3~07157~, 5~07237~; 6~08147~ 7~05892~ 10~02691~:'),
  (16919, 20, 18, 9, 'He also that is slothful in his work is brother to him that is a great waster.', '&para; 4~07503~ 7~04399~ 9~0251~ 15~01167~ 16~07843~.'),
  (11476, 14, 13, 14, 'And when Judah looked back, behold, the battle was before and behind: and they cried unto the LORD, and the priests sounded with the trumpets.', '2~03063~ 4~06437~, 7~04421~ [8] 9~06440~ 11~0268~: 14~06817~ 17~03068~, 20~03548~ 21~02690~ 24~02689~.'),
  (13015, 18, 6, 28, 'Now therefore be content, look upon me; for it is evident unto you if I lie.', '3~02974~, 4~06437~ [8 9] 10~06440~ 15~03576~.'),
  (4313, 4, 19, 19, 'And the clean person shall sprinkle upon the unclean on the third day, and on the seventh day: and on the seventh day he shall purify himself, and wash his clothes, and bathe himself in water, and shall be clean at even.', '2~02889~ [3] 5~05137~ 8~02931~ 11~07992~ 12~03117~, 16~07637~ 17~03117~: 21~07637~ 22~03117~ 25~02398~ 28~03526~ 30~0899~, 32~07364~ 35~04325~, 39~02891~ 41~06153~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (29172, 48, 4, 25, 'For this Agar is mount Sinai in Arabia, and answereth to Jerusalem which now is, and is in bondage with her children.', '0~1063~ 2~28~ 3~2076~ 4~3735~ 5~4614~ 6~1722~ 7~688~, 8~1161~ 9~4960~ 11~2419~ 12~3588~ 14~3568~, 15~1161~ 18~1398~ 19~3326~ 20~846~ 21~5043~.'),
  (25603, 42, 15, 2, 'And the Pharisees and scribes murmured, saying, This man receiveth sinners, and eateth with them.', '0~2532~ 2~5330~ 3~2532~ 4~1122~ 5~1234~, 6~3004~, 8~3778~ 9~3754~* 10~4327~ 11~268~, 12~2532~ 13~4906~ 15~846~.'),
  (4904, 5, 1, 6, 'The LORD our God spake unto us in Horeb, saying, Ye have dwelt long enough in this mount:', '1~03068~ 3~0430~ 4~01696~ 8~02722~, 9~0559~, 12~03427~ 14~07227~ 17~02022~:'),
  (20490, 26, 1, 17, 'When they went, they went upon their four sides: and they turned not when they went.', '2~03212~, 4~03212~ 7~0702~ 8~07253~: [9] 11~05437~ 15~03212~.'),
  (12300, 15, 10, 39, 'And Shelemiah, and Nathan, and Adaiah,', '1~08018~, 3~05416~, 5~05718~,'),
  (1596, 2, 3, 12, 'And he said, Certainly I will be with thee; and this shall be a token unto thee, that I have sent thee: When thou hast brought forth the people out of Egypt, ye shall serve God upon this mountain.', '2~0559~, [11 12] 14~0226~ 17~03588~ 20~07971~ 26~03318~ 28~05971~ 31~04714~, 34~05647~ 35~0430~ 38~02022~.'),
  (25168, 42, 6, 10, 'And looking round about upon them all, he said unto the man, Stretch forth thy hand. And he did so: and his hand was restored whole as the other.', '0~2532~ 4~4017~ 5~846~ 6~3956~, 8~2036~ 11~444~, 13~1614~ 14~4675~ 15~5495~. 16~1161~ 18~4160~ 19~3779~: 20~2532~ 21~846~ 22~5495~ 24~600~ 25~5199~ 26~5613~ 28~243~.'),
  (30005, 58, 2, 12, 'Saying, I will declare thy name unto my brethren, in the midst of the church will I sing praise unto thee.', '0~3004~, 3~518~ 4~4675~ 5~3686~ 7~3450~ 8~80~, 9~1722~ 11~3319~ 14~1577~ 18~5214~ 20~4571~.'),
  (583, 1, 23, 8, 'And he communed with them, saying, If it be your mind that I should bury my dead out of my sight; hear me, and entreat for me to Ephron the son of Zohar,', '2~01696~ 5~0559~, 8~03426~ 10~05315~ 14~06912~ 16~04191~ 20~06440~; 21~08085~ 24~06293~ 28~06085~ 30~01121~ 32~06714~,'),
  (6997, 7, 17, 10, 'And Micah said unto him, Dwell with me, and be unto me a father and a priest, and I will give thee ten shekels of silver by the year, and a suit of apparel, and thy victuals. So the Levite went in.', '1~04318~ 2~0559~ 5~03427~ 13~01~ 16~03548~, 20~05414~ 22~06235~ [23] 25~03701~ 28~03117~, 31~06187~ 33~0899~, 36~04241~. 39~03881~ 41~03212~.'),
  (23081, 38, 14, 4, 'And his feet shall stand in that day upon the mount of Olives, which is before Jerusalem on the east, and the mount of Olives shall cleave in the midst thereof toward the east and toward the west, and there shall be a very great valley; and half of the mountain shall remove toward the north, and half of it toward the south.', '2~07272~ 4~05975~ 7~03117~ 10~02022~ 12~02132~, [14] 15~06440~ 16~03389~ 19~06924~, 22~02022~ 24~02132~ 26~01234~ 29~02677~ 33~04217~ 37~03220~, [38 41] 43~03966~ 44~01419~ 45~01516~; 47~02677~ 50~02022~ 52~04185~ 55~06828~, 57~02677~ 62~05045~.'),
  (28575, 46, 9, 19, 'For though I be free from all men, yet have I made myself servant unto all, that I might gain the more.', '&para; 0~1063~ 3~5607~ 4~1658~ 5~1537~ 6~3956~ [7] 11~1402~ 12~1683~ 13~1402~ 15~3956~, 16~2443~ 19~2770~ 21~4119~.'),
  (2698, 2, 39, 29, 'And a girdle of fine twined linen, and blue, and purple, and scarlet, of needlework; as the LORD commanded Moses.', '2~073~ [3] 5~07806~ 6~08336~, 8~08504~, 10~0713~, 12~08438~ 13~08144~,* [14] 15~07551~ 16~04639~;* 19~03068~ 20~06680~ 21~04872~.'),
  (14972, 19, 69, 28, 'Let them be blotted out of the book of the living, and not be written with the righteous.', '3~04229~ 7~05612~ 10~02416~, 14~03789~ 17~06662~.'),
  (27535, 44, 16, 36, 'And the keeper of the prison told this saying to Paul, The magistrates have sent to let you go: now therefore depart, and go in peace.', '0~1161~ 5~1200~ 6~518~ 7~5128~ 8~3056~ 9~4314~ 10~3972~ 11~3754~,* 13~4755~ 15~649~ 16~2443~ 19~630~: 20~3568~ 21~3767~ 22~1831~, 24~4198~ 25~1722~ 26~1515~.'),
  (14861, 19, 64, 2, 'Hide me from the secret counsel of the wicked; from the insurrection of the workers of iniquity:', '0~05641~ 5~05475~ 8~07489~; 11~07285~ 14~06466~ 16~0205~:'),
  (9234, 11, 14, 8, 'And rent the kingdom away from the house of David, and gave it thee: and yet thou hast not been as my servant David, who kept my commandments, and who followed me with all his heart, to do that only which was right in mine eyes;', '1~07167~ 3~04467~ 4~07167~ 7~01004~ 9~01732~, 11~05414~ [15] 22~05650~ 23~01732~, 25~08104~ 27~04687~, 30~01980~ 31~0310~* 36~03824~, 38~06213~ [39] [41 42] 43~03477~ 46~05869~;'),
  (22969, 38, 6, 13, 'Even he shall build the temple of the LORD; and he shall bear the glory, and shall sit and rule upon his throne; and he shall be a priest upon his throne: and the counsel of peace shall be between them both.', '3~01129~ 5~01964~ 8~03068~; 12~05375~ 14~01935~, 17~03427~ 19~04910~ 22~03678~; 28~03548~ 31~03678~: 34~06098~ 36~07965~ 41~08147~.'),
  (18431, 23, 40, 2, 'Speak ye comfortably to Jerusalem, and cry unto her, that her warfare is accomplished, that her iniquity is pardoned: for she hath received of the Lord''s hand double for all her sins.', '0~01696~ 2~03820~ 4~03389~, 6~07121~ 11~06635~ 13~04390~, 16~05771~ 18~07521~: 22~03947~ 25~03068~ 26~03027~ 27~03718~ 31~02403~.'),
  (17178, 20, 26, 28, 'A lying tongue hateth those that are afflicted by it; and a flattering mouth worketh ruin.', '&para; 1~08267~ 2~03956~ 3~08130~ [4 6] 7~01790~ 12~02509~ 13~06310~ 14~06213~ 15~04072~.'),
  (23908, 40, 22, 26, 'Likewise the second also, and the third, unto the seventh.', '0~3668~ 2~1208~ 3~2532~, 4~2532~ 6~5154~, 7~2193~ 9~2033~.'),
  (29877, 55, 3, 8, 'Now as Jannes and Jambres withstood Moses, so do these also resist the truth: men of corrupt minds, reprobate concerning the faith.', '0~3739~* 1~1161~ 2~5158~ 3~2389~ 4~2532~ 5~2387~ 6~436~ 7~3475~, 8~3779~ 9~436~ 10~3778~ 11~2532~ 12~436~ 14~225~: 15~444~ 17~2704~ 18~3563~, 19~96~ 20~4012~ 22~4102~.'),
  (9379, 11, 18, 30, 'And Elijah said unto all the people, Come near unto me. And all the people came near unto him. And he repaired the altar of the LORD that was broken down.', '1~0452~ 2~0559~ 6~05971~, 8~05066~ 14~05971~ 16~05066~ 21~07495~ 23~04196~ 26~03068~ [27 28] 30~02040~.'),
  (21757, 27, 1, 11, 'Then said Daniel to Melzar, whom the prince of the eunuchs had set over Daniel, Hananiah, Mishael, and Azariah,', '1~0559~ 2~01840~ 4~04453~, 7~08269~ 10~05631~ 12~04487~ 14~01840~, 15~02608~, 16~04332~, 18~05838~,'),
  (10142, 12, 21, 15, 'Because they have done that which was evil in my sight, and have provoked me to anger, since the day their fathers came forth out of Egypt, even unto this day.', '3~06213~ [4 6] 7~07451~ 10~05869~, 13~04480~ 16~03707~, 19~03117~ 21~01~ 23~03318~ 26~04714~, 30~03117~.'),
  (17332, 21, 1, 8, 'All things are full of labour; man cannot utter it: the eye is not satisfied with seeing, nor the ear filled with hearing.', '1~01697~ [2] 5~03023~; 6~0376~ 7~03201~ 8~01696~ [9] 11~05869~ 14~07646~ 16~07200~, 19~0241~ 20~04390~ 22~08085~.'),
  (31038, 66, 19, 5, 'And a voice came out of the throne, saying, Praise our God, all ye his servants, and ye that fear him, both small and great.', '&para; 0~2532~ 2~5456~ 3~1831~ 5~1537~ 7~2362~, 8~3004~, 9~134~ 10~2257~ 11~2316~, 13~3956~ 14~846~ 15~1401~, 16~2532~ 19~5399~ 20~846~, 21~2532~ 22~3398~ 23~2532~ 24~3173~.'),
  (11034, 13, 24, 11, 'The ninth to Jeshuah, the tenth to Shecaniah,', '1~08671~ 3~03442~, 5~06224~ 7~07935~,'),
  (22973, 38, 7, 2, 'When they had sent unto the house of God Sherezer and Regemmelech, and their men, to pray before the LORD,', '3~07971~ 6~01004~ 8~0410~ 9~08272~ 11~07278~, 14~0582~, 16~02470~ 17~06440~ 19~03068~,'),
  (15816, 19, 112, 4, 'Unto the upright there ariseth light in the darkness: he is gracious, and full of compassion, and righteous.', '2~03477~ 4~02224~ 5~0216~ 8~02822~: [9 10] 11~02587~, 15~07349~, 17~06662~.'),
  (21061, 26, 23, 45, 'And the righteous men, they shall judge them after the manner of adulteresses, and after the manner of women that shed blood; because they are adulteresses, and blood is in their hands.', '2~06662~ 3~0582~, 6~08199~ 10~04941~ 12~05003~, 16~04941~ 20~08210~ 21~01818~; [24] 25~05003~, 27~01818~ [28] 31~03027~.'),
  (1704, 2, 7, 14, 'And the LORD said unto Moses, Pharaoh''s heart is hardened, he refuseth to let the people go.', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~04872~, 6~06547~ 7~03820~ [8] 9~03515~, 11~03985~ 15~05971~ 16~07971~.'),
  (10584, 13, 8, 1, 'Now Benjamin begat Bela his firstborn, Ashbel the second, and Aharah the third,', '&para; 1~01144~ 2~03205~ 3~01106~ 5~01060~, 6~0788~ 8~08145~, 10~0315~ 12~07992~,'),
  (24987, 42, 2, 2, '(And this taxing was first made when Cyrenius was governor of Syria.)', '[0] 1~3778~ 2~582~ 3~1096~ 4~4413~ 5~1096~ 7~2958~ 9~2230~ 11~4947~)'),
  (17510, 21, 10, 8, 'He that diggeth a pit shall fall into it; and whoso breaketh an hedge, a serpent shall bite him.', '2~02658~ 4~01475~ 6~05307~ 11~06555~ 13~01447~, 15~05175~ 17~05391~'),
  (21994, 27, 8, 24, 'And his power shall be mighty, but not by his own power: and he shall destroy wonderfully, and shall prosper, and practice, and shall destroy the mighty and the holy people.', '2~03581~ 5~06105~, 11~03581~: 15~07843~ 16~06381~, 19~06743~, 21~06213~, 24~07843~ 26~06099~ 29~06918~ 30~05971~.'),
  (6483, 6, 23, 16, 'When ye have transgressed the covenant of the LORD your God, which he commanded you, and have gone and served other gods, and bowed yourselves to them; then shall the anger of the LORD be kindled against you, and ye shall perish quickly from off the good land which he hath given unto you.', '3~05674~ 5~01285~ 8~03068~ 10~0430~, 13~06680~ 17~01980~ 19~05647~ 20~0312~ 21~0430~, 23~07812~ 30~0639~ 33~03068~ 35~02734~ 41~06~ 42~04120~ 46~02896~ 47~0776~ 51~05414~'),
  (14163, 19, 18, 36, 'Thou hast enlarged my steps under me, that my feet did not slip.', '2~07337~ 4~06806~ 9~07166~ 12~04571~.'),
  (3732, 4, 3, 35, 'And the chief of the house of the father of the families of Merari was Zuriel the son of Abihail: these shall pitch on the side of the tabernacle northward.', '2~05387~ 5~01004~ 8~01~ 11~04940~ 13~04847~ [14] 15~06700~ 17~01121~ 19~032~: [20] 22~02583~ 25~03409~ 28~04908~ 29~06828~.'),
  (1807, 2, 10, 25, 'And Moses said, Thou must give us also sacrifices and burnt offerings, that we may sacrifice unto the LORD our God.', '1~04872~ 2~0559~, 5~05414~ 6~03027~ 8~02077~ 11~05930~, 15~06213~ 18~03068~ 20~0430~.'),
  (17155, 20, 26, 5, 'Answer a fool according to his folly, lest he be wise in his own conceit.', '0~06030~ 2~03684~ 6~0200~, 10~02450~ 14~05869~.'),
  (5182, 5, 9, 19, 'For I was afraid of the anger and hot displeasure, wherewith the LORD was wroth against you to destroy you. But the LORD hearkened unto me at that time also.', '3~03025~ 4~06440~ 6~0639~ 9~02534~, 12~03068~ 14~07107~ 18~08045~ 22~03068~ 23~08085~ 28~06471~'),
  (15518, 19, 100, 1, 'A Psalm of praise. Make a joyful noise unto the LORD, all ye lands.', '&para; [0 1~04210~ 3] 3~08426~ 7~07321~ 10~03068~, 13~0776~.'),
  (14418, 19, 34, 21, 'Evil shall slay the wicked: and they that hate the righteous shall be desolate.', '0~07451~ 2~04191~ 4~07563~: 8~08130~ 10~06662~ 13~0816~.'),
  (22349, 29, 2, 29, 'And also upon the servants and upon the handmaids in those days will I pour out my spirit.', '4~05650~ 8~08198~ 11~03117~ 15~08210~ 17~07307~.'),
  (22081, 27, 11, 36, 'And the king shall do according to his will; and he shall exalt himself, and magnify himself above every god, and shall speak marvellous things against the God of gods, and shall prosper till the indignation be accomplished: for that that is determined shall be done.', '2~04428~ 4~06213~ 8~07522~; 12~07311~ 15~01431~ 19~0410~, 22~01696~ 24~06381~ 27~0410~ 29~0410~, 32~06743~ 35~02195~ 37~03615~: 42~02782~ 45~06213~.'),
  (26986, 44, 2, 21, 'And it shall come to pass, that whosoever shall call on the name of the Lord shall be saved.', '0~2532~ 5~2071~, [6] 7~302~ 8~3739~* 9~3956~ 11~1941~ 13~3686~ 16~2962~ 19~4982~.'),
  (25879, 42, 22, 1, 'Now the feast of unleavened bread drew nigh, which is called the Passover.', '&para; 0~1161~ 2~1859~ 5~106~ 7~1448~, 10~3004~ 12~3957~.'),
  (2907, 3, 7, 23, 'Speak unto the children of Israel, saying, Ye shall eat no manner of fat, of ox, or of sheep, or of goat.', '0~01696~ 3~01121~ 5~03478~, 6~0559~, 9~0398~ 13~02459~, 15~07794~, 18~03775~, 21~05795~.'),
  (23514, 40, 12, 15, 'But when Jesus knew it, he withdrew himself from thence: and great multitudes followed him, and he healed them all;', '0~1161~ 2~2424~ 3~1097~ [4] 7~402~ 9~1564~: 10~2532~ 11~4183~ 12~3793~ 13~190~ 14~846~, 15~2532~ 17~2323~ 18~846~ 19~3956~;'),
  (4123, 4, 14, 10, 'But all the congregation bade stone them with stones. And the glory of the LORD appeared in the tabernacle of the congregation before all the children of Israel.', '3~05712~ 4~0559~ 5~07275~ 8~068~. 11~03519~ 14~03068~ 15~07200~ 18~0168~ 21~04150~ 25~01121~ 27~03478~.'),
  (487, 1, 19, 26, 'But his wife looked back from behind him, and she became a pillar of salt.', '&para; 2~0802~ 4~05027~ 7~0310~, 12~05333~ 14~04417~.'),
  (21071, 26, 24, 6, 'Wherefore thus saith the Lord GOD; Woe to the bloody city, to the pot whose scum is therein, and whose scum is not gone out of it! bring it out piece by piece; let no lot fall upon it.', '2~0559~ 4~0136~ 5~03069~; 6~0188~ 9~01818~ 10~05892~, 13~05518~ 15~02457~ [16] 20~02457~ 24~03318~ 29~03318~ 30~05409~ 32~05409~; 35~01486~ 36~05307~'),
  (10903, 13, 18, 5, 'And when the Syrians of Damascus came to help Hadarezer king of Zobah, David slew of the Syrians two and twenty thousand men.', '3~0758~ 5~01834~ 6~0935~ 8~05826~ 9~01928~ 10~04428~ 12~06678~, 13~01732~ 14~05221~ 17~0758~ 18~08147~ 20~06242~ 21~0505~ 22~0376~.'),
  (3814, 4, 5, 17, 'And the priest shall take holy water in an earthen vessel; and of the dust that is in the floor of the tabernacle the priest shall take, and put it into the water:', '2~03548~ 4~03947~ 5~06918~ 6~04325~ 9~02789~ 10~03627~; 14~06083~ 19~07172~ 22~04908~ 24~03548~ 26~03947~, 28~05414~ [29] 32~04325~:'),
  (30359, 59, 4, 6, 'But he giveth more grace. Wherefore he saith, God resisteth the proud, but giveth grace unto the humble.', '0~1161~ 2~1325~ 3~3187~ 4~5485~. 5~1352~ 7~3004~, 8~2316~ 9~498~ 11~5244~, 12~1161~ 13~1325~ 14~5485~ 17~5011~.'),
  (16502, 20, 4, 3, 'For I was my father''s son, tender and only beloved in the sight of my mother.', '4~01~ 5~01121~, 6~07390~ 8~03173~ [9] 12~06440~ 15~0517~.'),
  (1821, 2, 11, 10, 'And Moses and Aaron did all these wonders before Pharaoh: and the LORD hardened Pharaoh''s heart, so that he would not let the children of Israel go out of his land.', '1~04872~ 3~0175~ 4~06213~ 7~04159~ 8~06440~ 9~06547~: 12~03068~ 13~02388~ 14~06547~ 15~03820~, 23~01121~ 25~03478~ 27~07971~ 30~0776~.'),
  (2619, 2, 37, 10, 'And he made the table of shittim wood: two cubits was the length thereof, and a cubit the breadth thereof, and a cubit and a half the height thereof:', '&para; 2~06213~ 4~07979~ [5] 6~07848~ 7~06086~: 9~0520~ [10] 12~0753~ 16~0520~ 18~07341~ 22~0520~ 25~02677~ 27~06967~'),
  (10906, 13, 18, 8, 'Likewise from Tibhath, and from Chun, cities of Hadarezer, brought David very much brass, wherewith Solomon made the brazen sea, and the pillars, and the vessels of brass.', '2~02880~, 5~03560~, 6~05892~ 8~01928~, 9~03947~ 10~01732~ 11~03966~ 12~07227~ 13~05178~, 15~08010~ 16~06213~ 18~05178~ 19~03220~, 22~05982~, 25~03627~ 27~05178~.'),
  (29972, 57, 1, 18, 'If he hath wronged thee, or oweth thee ought, put that on mine account;', '0~1487~ 1~1161~ 3~91~ 4~4571~, 5~2228~ 6~3784~ [7] 8~5100~, 9~1677~ 10~5124~ 11~1677~ 13~1698~;'),
  (6017, 6, 8, 9, 'Joshua therefore sent them forth: and they went to lie in ambush, and abode between Bethel and Ai, on the west side of Ai: but Joshua lodged that night among the people.', '0~03091~ 4~07971~: 7~03212~ 11~03993~, 13~03427~ 15~01008~ 17~05857~, 21~03220~ 23~05857~: 25~03091~ 26~03885~ 28~03915~ 29~08432~ 31~05971~.'),
  (11445, 14, 11, 22, 'And Rehoboam made Abijah the son of Maachah the chief, to be ruler among his brethren: for he thought to make him king.', '1~07346~ 2~05975~ 3~029~ 5~01121~ 7~04601~ 9~07218~, [10 11] 12~05057~ 15~0251~: [17 18] 22~04427~.'),
  (25885, 42, 22, 7, 'Then came the day of unleavened bread, when the passover must be killed.', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~2064~ 3~2250~ 6~106~, 7~3739~ 8~1722~ 9~3957~ 10~1163~ 12~2380~.'),
  (29808, 54, 6, 4, 'He is proud, knowing nothing, but doting about questions and strifes of words, whereof cometh envy, strife, railings, evil surmisings,', '2~5187~, 3~1987~ 4~3367~, 5~235~ 6~3552~ 7~4012~ 8~2214~ 9~2532~ 12~3055~, 13~3739~ 14~1537~* 15~1096~ 16~5355~, 17~2054~, 18~988~, 19~4190~ 20~5283~,'),
  (20571, 26, 5, 16, 'When I shall send upon them the evil arrows of famine, which shall be for their destruction, and which I will send to destroy you: and I will increase the famine upon you, and will break your staff of bread:', '3~07971~ 7~07451~ 8~02671~ 10~07458~, [15] 16~04889~, [17] 21~07971~ 23~07843~ 28~03254~ 30~07458~ 35~07665~ 37~04294~ 39~03899~:'),
  (1192, 1, 40, 15, 'For indeed I was stolen away out of the land of the Hebrews: and here also have I done nothing that they should put me into the dungeon.', '5~01589~ 9~0776~ 12~05680~: 18~06213~ 19~03972~ 23~07760~ 27~0953~.'),
  (25741, 42, 18, 39, 'And they which went before rebuked him, that he should hold his peace: but he cried so much the more, Thou son of David, have mercy on me.', '0~2532~ 4~4254~ 5~2008~ 6~846~, 7~2443~ 12~4623~: 13~1161~ 14~846~ 15~2896~ 17~4183~ 19~3123~, [20] 21~5207~ 23~1138~, 25~1653~ 27~3165~.'),
  (27247, 44, 9, 15, 'But the Lord said unto him, Go thy way: for he is a chosen vessel unto me, to bear my name before the Gentiles, and kings, and the children of Israel:', '0~1161~ 2~2962~ 3~2036~ 4~4314~ 5~846~, 8~4198~: 9~3754~ 10~3778~ 11~2076~ 13~1589~ 14~4632~ 16~3427~, 18~941~ 19~3450~ 20~3686~ 21~1799~ 23~1484~, 24~2532~ 25~935~, 26~5037~ 28~5207~ 30~2474~:'),
  (18030, 23, 19, 17, 'And the land of Judah shall be a terror unto Egypt, every one that maketh mention thereof shall be afraid in himself, because of the counsel of the LORD of hosts, which he hath determined against it.', '2~0127~ 4~03063~ 8~02283~ 10~04714~, 15~02142~ 19~06342~ 22~06440~ 25~06098~ 28~03068~ 30~06635~, 34~03289~'),
  (11170, 13, 28, 19, 'All this, said David, the LORD made me understand in writing by his hand upon me, even all the works of this pattern.', '[1 3] 5~03068~ 8~07919~ 10~03791~ [12] 13~03027~ [16] 19~04399~ 22~08403~.'),
  (9606, 12, 3, 22, 'And they rose up early in the morning, and the sun shone upon the water, and the Moabites saw the water on the other side as red as blood:', '4~07925~ 7~01242~, 10~08121~ 11~02224~ 14~04325~, 17~04124~ 18~07200~ 20~04325~ 24~05048~ [25] 26~0122~ 28~01818~:'),
  (18154, 23, 26, 15, 'Thou hast increased the nation, O LORD, thou hast increased the nation: thou art glorified: thou hadst removed it far unto all the ends of the earth.', '2~03254~ 4~01471~, 6~03068~, 9~03254~ 11~01471~: 14~03513~: [18] 19~07368~ [20] 23~07099~ 26~0776~.'),
  (5110, 5, 6, 18, 'And thou shalt do that which is right and good in the sight of the LORD: that it may be well with thee, and that thou mayest go in and possess the good land which the LORD sware unto thy fathers,', '3~06213~ [4 6] 7~03477~ 9~02896~ 12~05869~ 15~03068~: 20~03190~ 28~0935~ 30~03423~ 32~02896~ 33~0776~ 36~03068~ 37~07650~ 40~01~,'),
  (25718, 42, 18, 16, 'But Jesus called them unto him, and said, Suffer little children to come unto me, and forbid them not: for of such is the kingdom of God.', '0~1161~ 1~2424~ 2~4341~ 3~846~ [4 5] 7~2036~, 8~863~ 10~3813~ 12~2064~ 13~4314~ 14~3165~, 15~2532~ 16~2967~ 17~846~ 18~3361~: 19~1063~ 21~5108~ 22~2076~ 24~932~ 26~2316~.'),
  (12988, 18, 6, 1, 'But Job answered and said,', '&para; 1~0347~ 2~06030~ 4~0559~,'),
  (13366, 18, 21, 2, 'Hear diligently my speech, and let this be your consolations.', '0~08085~ 1~08085~ 3~04405~, 9~08575~.'),
  (11283, 14, 5, 7, 'And the priests brought in the ark of the covenant of the LORD unto his place, to the oracle of the house, into the most holy place, even under the wings of the cherubims:', '2~03548~ 4~0935~ 6~0727~ 9~01285~ 12~03068~ 15~04725~, 18~01687~ 21~01004~, 24~06944~ 25~06944~ [26 27] 30~03671~ 33~03742~:'),
  (17533, 21, 12, 1, 'Remember now thy Creator in the days of thy youth, while the evil days come not, nor the years draw nigh, when thou shalt say, I have no pleasure in them;', '&para; 0~02142~ 3~01254~ 6~03117~ 9~0979~, 12~07451~ 13~03117~ 14~0935~ 18~08141~ 20~05060~, 24~0559~, 28~02656~'),
  (20606, 26, 7, 20, 'As for the beauty of his ornament, he set it in majesty: but they made the images of their abominations and of their detestable things therein: therefore have I set it far from them.', '3~06643~ 6~05716~, 8~07760~ 11~01347~: 14~06213~ 16~06754~ 19~08441~ [20] 24~08251~ 29~05414~ 31~05079~'),
  (4682, 4, 31, 12, 'And they brought the captives, and the prey, and the spoil, unto Moses, and Eleazar the priest, and unto the congregation of the children of Israel, unto the camp at the plains of Moab, which are by Jordan near Jericho.', '2~0935~ 4~07628~, 7~04455~, 10~07998~, 12~04872~, 14~0499~ 16~03548~, 20~05712~ 23~01121~ 25~03478~, 28~04264~ 31~06160~ 33~04124~, [35] 37~03383~ [38] 39~03405~.'),
  (9261, 11, 15, 4, 'Nevertheless for David''s sake did the LORD his God give him a lamp in Jerusalem, to set up his son after him, and to establish Jerusalem:', '2~01732~ 6~03068~ 8~0430~ 9~05414~ 12~05216~ 14~03389~, 17~06965~ 19~01121~ 20~0310~ 24~05975~ 25~03389~:'),
  (13456, 18, 24, 11, 'Which make oil within their walls, and tread their winepresses, and suffer thirst.', '[0] 2~06671~ 3~0996~ 5~07791~, [6] 7~01869~ [8] 9~03342~, 12~06770~.'),
  (24643, 41, 10, 44, 'And whosoever of you will be the chiefest, shall be servant of all.', '0~2532~ 1~302~ 2~3739~ 3~5216~ 4~2309~ 5~1096~ 7~4413~, 9~2071~ 10~1401~ 12~3956~.'),
  (6727, 7, 8, 1, 'And the men of Ephraim said unto him, Why hast thou served us thus, that thou calledst us not, when thou wentest to fight with the Midianites? And they did chide with him sharply.', '&para; 2~0376~ 4~0669~ 5~0559~ 10~04100~ 11~06213~ 13~01697~, 16~07121~ 21~01980~ 23~03898~ 26~04080~? 30~07378~ 33~02394~.'),
  (26007, 42, 24, 2, 'And they found the stone rolled away from the sepulchre.', '0~1161~ 2~2147~ 4~3037~ 6~617~ 7~575~ 9~3419~.'),
  (19860, 24, 36, 9, 'And it came to pass in the fifth year of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah king of Judah, in the ninth month, that they proclaimed a fast before the LORD to all the people in Jerusalem, and to all the people that came from the cities of Judah unto Jerusalem.', '&para; 7~02549~ 8~08141~ 10~03079~ 12~01121~ 14~02977~ 15~04428~ 17~03063~, 20~08671~ 21~02320~, [22] 24~07121~ 26~06685~ 27~06440~ 29~03068~ 33~05971~ 35~03389~, 40~05971~ 42~0935~ 45~05892~ 47~03063~ 49~03389~.'),
  (5030, 5, 4, 20, 'But the LORD hath taken you, and brought you forth out of the iron furnace, even out of Egypt, to be unto him a people of inheritance, as ye are this day.', '2~03068~ 4~03947~ 9~03318~ 13~01270~ 14~03564~, [15] 18~04714~, 24~05971~ 26~05159~, [28 29] 31~03117~.'),
  (27776, 44, 23, 26, 'Claudius Lysias unto the most excellent governor Felix sendeth greeting.', '0~2804~ 1~3079~ 5~2903~ 6~2232~ 7~5344~ [8] 9~5463~.'),
  (30429, 60, 2, 14, 'Or unto governors, as unto them that are sent by him for the punishment of evildoers, and for the praise of them that do well.', '0~1535~ 2~2232~, 3~5613~ 8~3992~ 9~1223~ 10~846~ 11~3303~ 12~1519~ 13~1557~ 15~2555~, 16~1161~ 19~1868~ 24~17~.'),
  (6448, 6, 22, 15, 'And they came unto the children of Reuben, and to the children of Gad, and to the half tribe of Manasseh, unto the land of Gilead, and they spake with them, saying,', '2~0935~ 5~01121~ 7~07205~, 11~01121~ 13~01410~, 17~02677~ 18~07626~ 20~04519~, 23~0776~ 25~01568~, 28~01696~ 31~0559~,'),
  (11004, 13, 23, 13, 'The sons of Amram; Aaron and Moses: and Aaron was separated, that he should sanctify the most holy things, he and his sons for ever, to burn incense before the LORD, to minister unto him, and to bless in his name for ever.', '1~01121~ 3~06019~; 4~0175~ 6~04872~: 8~0175~ 10~0914~, 14~06942~ 16~06944~ 18~06944~, 22~01121~ 23~05704~ 24~05769~, 27~06999~ 28~06440~ 30~03068~, 32~08334~ 37~01288~ 40~08034~ 41~05704~ 42~05769~.'),
  (21118, 26, 26, 9, 'And he shall set engines of war against thy walls, and with his axes he shall break down thy towers.', '3~05414~ 4~04239~ 6~06904~ 9~02346~, 13~02719~ 17~05422~ 19~04026~.'),
  (3349, 3, 20, 26, 'And ye shall be holy unto me: for I the LORD am holy, and have severed you from other people, that ye should be mine.', '4~06918~ 10~03068~ [11] 12~06918~, 15~0914~ [18] 19~05971~,'),
  (21000, 26, 22, 15, 'And I will scatter thee among the heathen, and disperse thee in the countries, and will consume thy filthiness out of thee.', '3~06327~ 7~01471~, 9~02219~ 13~0776~, 16~08552~ 18~02932~'),
  (29241, 49, 1, 19, 'And what is the exceeding greatness of his power to us-ward who believe, according to the working of his mighty power,', '0~2532~ 1~5101~ [2] 4~5235~ 5~3174~ 7~846~ 8~1411~ 9~1519~ 10~2248~ 11~3588~ 12~4100~, 14~2596~ 16~1753~ 18~846~ 19~2479~ 20~2904~,'),
  (24137, 40, 26, 73, 'And after a while came unto him they that stood by, and said to Peter, Surely thou also art one of them; for thy speech bewrayeth thee.', '0~1161~ 1~3326~ 3~3397~ [6] 7~4334~ 10~2476~, 12~2036~ 14~4074~, 15~230~ 16~4771~ 17~2532~ 18~1488~ [19] 20~1537~ 21~846~; 22~2532~ 23~1063~* 24~4675~ 25~2981~ 26~1212~ 27~4160~ 28~4571~.*'),
  (6395, 6, 21, 7, 'The children of Merari by their families had out of the tribe of Reuben, and out of the tribe of Gad, and out of the tribe of Zebulun, twelve cities.', '1~01121~ 3~04847~ 6~04940~ [7] 11~04294~ 13~07205~, 18~04294~ 20~01410~, 25~04294~ 27~02074~, 28~06240~ 29~08147~* 30~05892~.'),
  (2453, 2, 32, 10, 'Now therefore let me alone, that my wrath may wax hot against them, and that I may consume them: and I will make of thee a great nation.', '4~03240~, 7~0639~ 10~02734~ 17~03615~ 22~06213~ 26~01419~ 27~01471~.'),
  (30894, 66, 11, 6, 'These have power to shut heaven, that it rain not in the days of their prophecy: and have power over waters to turn them to blood, and to smite the earth with all plagues, as often as they will.', '0~3778~ 1~2192~ 2~1849~ 4~2808~ 5~3772~, 6~3363~ 8~1026~ 9~5205~* 10~3363~ 11~1722~ 13~2250~ 15~846~ 16~4394~: 17~2532~ 18~2192~ 19~1849~ 20~1909~ 21~5204~ 23~4762~ 24~846~ 25~1519~ 26~129~, 27~2532~ 29~3960~ 31~1093~ 33~3956~ 34~4127~, 36~3740~ 37~1437~ 39~2309~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (14867, 19, 64, 8, 'So they shall make their own tongue to fall upon themselves: all that see them shall flee away.', '6~03956~ 8~03782~ 13~07200~ 17~05074~.'),
  (21907, 27, 5, 24, 'Then was the part of the hand sent from him; and this writing was written.', '0~0116~ 3~06447~ 6~03028~ 7~07972~ 8~04481~ 9~06925~; 11~01836~ 12~03792~ 14~07560~.'),
  (7250, 9, 2, 3, 'Talk no more so exceeding proudly; let not arrogancy come out of your mouth: for the LORD is a God of knowledge, and by him actions are weighed.', '0~01696~ 2~07235~ 4~01364~ 5~01364~; [7] 8~06277~ 9~03318~ 13~06310~: 16~03068~ [17] 19~0410~ 21~01844~, 25~05949~ 27~08505~.'),
  (9706, 12, 6, 24, 'And it came to pass after this, that Benhadad king of Syria gathered all his host, and went up, and besieged Samaria.', '&para; 6~0310~, 8~01130~ 9~04428~ 11~0758~ 12~06908~ 15~04264~, 18~05927~, 20~06696~ 21~08111~.'),
  (3631, 4, 1, 22, 'Of the children of Simeon, by their generations, after their families, by the house of their fathers, those that were numbered of them, according to the number of the names, by their polls, every male from twenty years old and upward, all that were able to go forth to war;', '2~01121~ 4~08095~, 7~08435~, 10~04940~, 13~01004~ 16~01~, 20~06485~ 26~04557~ 29~08034~, 32~01538~, 34~02145~ 36~06242~ 37~08141~ 38~01121~ 40~04605~, 47~03318~ 49~06635~;'),
  (18865, 23, 62, 2, 'And the Gentiles shall see thy righteousness, and all kings thy glory: and thou shalt be called by a new name, which the mouth of the LORD shall name.', '2~01471~ 4~07200~ 6~06664~, 9~04428~ 11~03519~: 16~07121~ 19~02319~ 20~05344~, 23~06310~ 26~03068~ 28~08034~.'),
  (26161, 43, 3, 26, 'And they came unto John, and said unto him, Rabbi, he that was with thee beyond Jordan, to whom thou barest witness, behold, the same baptizeth, and all men come to him.', '0~2532~ 2~2064~ 3~4314~ 4~2491~, 5~2532~ 6~2036~ 8~846~, 9~4461~, 10~3739~ 12~2258~ 13~3326~ 14~4675~ 15~4008~ 16~2446~, 18~3739~ 19~4771~ 21~3140~, 22~2396~, 24~3778~ 25~907~, 26~2532~ 27~3956~ [28] 29~2064~ 30~4314~ 31~846~.'),
  (15654, 19, 105, 39, 'He spread a cloud for a covering; and fire to give light in the night.', '1~06566~ 3~06051~ 6~04539~; 8~0784~ 11~0215~ 14~03915~.'),
  (14530, 19, 39, 9, 'I was dumb, I opened not my mouth; because thou didst it.', '2~0481~, 4~06605~ 7~06310~; 10~06213~ [11]'),
  (27901, 44, 27, 30, 'And as the shipmen were about to flee out of the ship, when they had let down the boat into the sea, under colour as though they would have cast anchors out of the foreship,', '0~1161~ 3~3492~ 5~2212~ 7~5343~ 9~1537~ 11~4143~, 12~2532~ 16~5465~ 18~4627~ 19~1519~ 21~2281~, 23~4392~ 25~5613~ 27~3195~ 29~1614~ 30~45~ 32~1537~ 34~4408~,'),
  (19355, 24, 16, 10, 'And it shall come to pass, when thou shalt shew this people all these words, and they shall say unto thee, Wherefore hath the LORD pronounced all this great evil against us? or what is our iniquity? or what is our sin that we have committed against the LORD our God?', '&para; 9~05046~ 11~05971~ 14~01697~, 18~0559~ 24~03068~ 25~01696~ 28~01419~ 29~07451~ [34] 36~05771~? [39] 41~02403~ 45~02398~ 48~03068~ 50~0430~?'),
  (28644, 46, 11, 28, 'But let a man examine himself, and so let him eat of that bread, and drink of that cup.', '0~1161~ 1~1381~ 3~444~ 4~1381~ 5~1438~, 6~2532~ 7~3779~ 10~2068~ 11~1537~ [12] 13~740~, 14~2532~ 15~4095~ 16~1537~ [17] 18~4221~.'),
  (29742, 54, 2, 10, 'But (which becometh women professing godliness) with good works.', '0~235~ 1~3739~* 3~4241~ 4~1135~ 5~1861~ 6~2317~) 7~1223~ 8~18~ 9~2041~.'),
  (4831, 4, 34, 9, 'And the border shall go on to Ziphron, and the goings out of it shall be at Hazarenan: this shall be your north border.', '2~01366~ 5~03318~ 7~02202~, 11~08444~ 17~02704~: 22~06828~ 23~01366~.'),
  (6402, 6, 21, 14, 'And Jattir with her suburbs, and Eshtemoa with her suburbs,', '1~03492~ 4~04054~, 6~0851~ 9~04054~,'),
  (23177, 40, 1, 23, 'Behold, a virgin shall be with child, and shall bring forth a son, and they shall call his name Emmanuel, which being interpreted is, God with us.', '0~2400~, 2~3933~ 6~2192~ 7~1722~* 8~1064~,* 9~2532~ 12~5088~ 14~5207~, 15~2532~ 18~2564~ 19~846~ 20~3686~ 21~1694~, 22~3739~ 24~3177~ 25~2076~, 26~2316~ 27~3326~ 28~2257~.'),
  (11189, 13, 29, 17, 'I know also, my God, that thou triest the heart, and hast pleasure in uprightness. As for me, in the uprightness of mine heart I have willingly offered all these things: and now have I seen with joy thy people, which are present here, to offer willingly unto thee.', '1~03045~ 4~0430~, 7~0974~ 9~03824~, 12~07521~ 14~03476~. 20~04339~ 23~03824~ 27~05068~ 35~07200~ 37~08057~ 39~05971~, 42~04672~ 46~05068~'),
  (25682, 42, 17, 17, 'And Jesus answering said, Were there not ten cleansed? but where are the nine?', '0~1161~ 1~2424~ 2~611~ 3~2036~, 5~2511~ 6~3780~ 7~1176~ 8~2511~? 9~1161~ 10~4226~ [11] 13~1767~?'),
  (16941, 20, 19, 7, 'All the brethren of the poor do hate him: how much more do his friends go far from him? he pursueth them with words, yet they are wanting to him.', '2~0251~ 5~07326~ 7~08130~ 14~04828~ 16~07368~ 20~07291~ [21 22] 23~0561~, [24] [26] [28 29]'),
  (1144, 1, 38, 20, 'And Judah sent the kid by the hand of his friend the Adullamite, to receive his pledge from the woman''s hand: but he found her not.', '1~03063~ 2~07971~ 4~05795~ 5~01423~ 7~03027~ 10~07453~ 12~05726~, 14~03947~ [15] 16~06162~ 19~0802~ 20~03027~: 24~04672~'),
  (3880, 4, 7, 25, 'His offering was one silver charger, the weight whereof was an hundred and thirty shekels, one silver bowl of seventy shekels, after the shekel of the sanctuary; both of them full of fine flour mingled with oil for a meat offering:', '1~07133~ [2] 3~0259~ 4~03701~ 5~07086~, 7~04948~ [9] 11~03967~ 13~07970~ [14] 15~0259~ 16~03701~ 17~04219~ 19~07657~ 20~08255~, 23~08255~ 26~06944~; 27~08147~ 30~04392~ 33~05560~ 34~01101~ 36~08081~ 40~04503~:'),
  (5863, 6, 1, 6, 'Be strong and of a good courage: for unto this people shalt thou divide for an inheritance the land, which I sware unto their fathers to give them.', '1~02388~ 6~0553~: 10~05971~ 16~05157~ 18~0776~, 21~07650~ 24~01~ 26~05414~'),
  (26904, 43, 20, 21, 'Then said Jesus to them again, Peace be unto you: as my Father hath sent me, even so send I you.', '0~3767~ 1~2036~ 2~2424~ 4~846~ 5~3825~, 6~1515~ [7] 9~5213~: 10~2531~ [11] 12~3962~ 14~649~ 15~3165~, 17~2504~ 18~3992~ 19~2504~ 20~5209~.'),
  (19909, 24, 38, 5, 'Then Zedekiah the king said, Behold, he is in your hand: for the king is not he that can do any thing against you.', '1~06667~ 3~04428~ 4~0559~, [7] 10~03027~: 13~04428~ [14] [16 17] 18~03201~ [20] 21~01697~'),
  (18356, 23, 36, 17, 'Until I come and take you away to a land like your own land, a land of corn and wine, a land of bread and vineyards.', '2~0935~ 6~03947~ 9~0776~ 13~0776~, 15~0776~ 17~01715~ 19~08492~, 21~0776~ 23~03899~ 25~03754~.'),
  (13736, 18, 35, 7, 'If thou be righteous, what givest thou him? or what receiveth he of thine hand?', '3~06663~, 5~05414~ 10~03947~ 14~03027~?'),
  (30557, 62, 1, 1, 'That which was from the beginning, which we have heard, which we have seen with our eyes, which we have looked upon, and our hands have handled, of the Word of life;', '&para; 1~3739~ 2~2258~ 3~575~ 5~746~, 6~3739~ 9~191~, 10~3739~ 13~3708~ 15~2257~ 16~3788~, 17~3739~ 21~2300~, 22~2532~ 23~2257~ 24~5495~ 26~5584~, 27~4012~ 29~3056~ 31~2222~;'),
  (15826, 19, 113, 4, 'The LORD is high above all nations, and his glory above the heavens.', '1~03068~ [2] 3~07311~ 6~01471~, [7] 9~03519~ 12~08064~.'),
  (17255, 20, 29, 22, 'An angry man stirreth up strife, and a furious man aboundeth in transgression.', '&para; 1~0639~ 2~0376~ 4~01624~ 5~04066~, 8~02534~ 9~01167~ 11~07227~ 12~06588~.'),
  (25598, 42, 14, 32, 'Or else, while the other is yet a great way off, he sendeth an ambassage, and desireth conditions of peace.', '1~1490~, 4~846~ 5~5607~ 6~2089~ 10~4206~, 12~649~ 14~4242~, 16~2065~ 17~4314~ 19~1515~.'),
  (9046, 11, 8, 53, 'For thou didst separate them from among all the people of the earth, to be thine inheritance, as thou spakest by the hand of Moses thy servant, when thou broughtest our fathers out of Egypt, O Lord GOD.', '3~0914~ 9~05971~ 12~0776~, [13 14] 16~05159~, 19~01696~ 22~03027~ 24~04872~ 26~05650~, 29~03318~ 31~01~ 34~04714~, 36~0136~ 37~03069~.'),
  (21891, 27, 5, 8, 'Then came in all the king''s wise men: but they could not read the writing, nor make known to the king the interpretation thereof.', '0~0116~ 1~05954~ 3~03606~ 5~04430~ 6~02445~ [7] 10~03546~ 11~03809~ 12~07123~ 14~03792~, 17~03046~ 20~04430~ 22~06591~'),
  (7234, 9, 1, 15, 'And Hannah answered and said, No, my lord, I am a woman of a sorrowful spirit: I have drunk neither wine nor strong drink, but have poured out my soul before the LORD.', '1~02584~ 2~06030~ 4~0559~, 7~0113~, [9] 11~0802~ 14~07186~ 15~07307~: 18~08354~ 20~03196~ 23~07941~, 27~08210~ 29~05315~ 30~06440~ 32~03068~.'),
  (6106, 6, 10, 36, 'And Joshua went up from Eglon, and all Israel with him, unto Hebron; and they fought against it:', '1~03091~ 3~05927~ 5~05700~, 8~03478~ 12~02275~; 15~03898~'),
  (3088, 3, 13, 31, 'And if the priest look on the plague of the scall, and, behold, it be not in sight deeper than the skin, and that there is no black hair in it; then the priest shall shut up him that hath the plague of the scall seven days:', '3~03548~ 4~07200~ 7~05061~ 10~05424~, [14] 17~04758~ 18~06013~ 21~05785~, [23 25] 27~07838~ 28~08181~ 33~03548~ 35~05462~ [37 39] 41~05061~ 44~05424~ 45~07651~ 46~03117~:'),
  (17923, 23, 13, 8, 'And they shall be afraid: pangs and sorrows shall take hold of them; they shall be in pain as a woman that travaileth: they shall be amazed one at another; their faces shall be as flames.', '4~0926~: 5~06735~ 7~02256~ 10~0270~ 17~02342~ 22~03205~: 26~08539~ 27~0376~ 29~07453~; 31~06440~ [32 34] 35~03851~.'),
  (9285, 11, 15, 28, 'Even in the third year of Asa king of Judah did Baasha slay him, and reigned in his stead.', '3~07969~ 4~08141~ 6~0609~ 7~04428~ 9~03063~ 11~01201~ 12~04191~ 15~04427~'),
  (12566, 16, 10, 8, 'Maaziah, Bilgai, Shemaiah: these were the priests.', '0~04590~, 1~01084~, 2~08098~: [4] 6~03548~.'),
  (201, 1, 8, 17, 'Bring forth with thee every living thing that is with thee, of all flesh, both of fowl, and of cattle, and of every creeping thing that creepeth upon the earth; that they may breed abundantly in the earth, and be fruitful, and multiply upon the earth.', '1~03318~ 6~02416~ [8] 13~01320~, [14] 16~05775~, 19~0929~, 24~07431~ 26~07430~ 29~0776~; 34~08317~ 37~0776~, 40~06509~, 42~07235~ 45~0776~.'),
  (24974, 42, 1, 69, 'And hath raised up an horn of salvation for us in the house of his servant David;', '0~2532~ 3~1453~ 5~2768~ 7~4991~ 9~2254~ 10~1722~ 12~3624~ 14~846~ 15~3816~ 16~1138~;'),
  (24273, 41, 2, 3, 'And they come unto him, bringing one sick of the palsy, which was borne of four.', '0~2532~ 2~2064~ 3~4314~ 4~846~, 5~5342~ 10~3885~, 13~142~ 14~5259~ 15~5064~.'),
  (30003, 58, 2, 10, 'For it became him, for whom are all things, and by whom are all things, in bringing many sons unto glory, to make the captain of their salvation perfect through sufferings.', '&para; 0~1063~ 2~4241~ 3~846~, 4~1223~ 5~3739~ [6] 8~3956~, 9~2532~ 10~1223~ 11~3739~ [12] 14~3956~, 16~71~ 17~4183~ 18~5207~ 19~1519~ 20~1391~, 22~5048~ 24~747~ 26~846~ 27~4991~ 28~5048~ 29~1223~ 30~3804~.'),
  (19307, 24, 14, 5, 'Yea, the hind also calved in the field, and forsook it, because there was no grass.', '2~0365~ 4~03205~ 7~07704~, 9~05800~ [10] 15~01877~.'),
  (7078, 7, 20, 17, 'And the men of Israel, beside Benjamin, were numbered four hundred thousand men that drew sword: all these were men of war.', '2~0376~ 4~03478~, 6~01144~, 8~06485~ 9~0702~ 10~03967~ 11~0505~ 12~0376~ 14~08025~ 15~02719~: [18] 19~0376~ 21~04421~.'),
  (25004, 42, 2, 19, 'But Mary kept all these things, and pondered them in her heart.', '0~1161~ 1~3137~ 2~4933~ 3~3956~ 5~5023~ 6~4487~,* 8~4820~ [9] 10~1722~ 11~846~ 12~2588~.'),
  (25833, 42, 20, 40, 'And after that they durst not ask him any question at all.', '0~1161~ 2~3765~ 4~5111~ 5~3765~ 6~1905~ 7~846~ 8~3762~ [9 11]'),
  (20784, 26, 16, 13, 'Thus wast thou decked with gold and silver; and thy raiment was of fine linen, and silk, and broidered work; thou didst eat fine flour, and honey, and oil: and thou wast exceeding beautiful, and thou didst prosper into a kingdom.', '3~05710~ 5~02091~ 7~03701~; 10~04403~ [11 12] 14~08336~ 15~08336~,* 17~04897~, 20~07553~; 23~0398~ 25~05560~, 27~01706~, 29~08081~: 33~03966~ 34~03302~, 38~06743~ 41~04410~.'),
  (29428, 50, 2, 21, 'For all seek their own, not the things which are Jesus Christ''s.', '0~1063~ 1~3956~ 2~2212~ 4~1438~, 5~3756~ 9~3588~ 10~2424~ 11~5547~.'),
  (388, 1, 16, 3, 'And Sarai Abram''s wife took Hagar her maid the Egyptian, after Abram had dwelt ten years in the land of Canaan, and gave her to her husband Abram to be his wife.', '1~08297~ 2~087~ 3~0802~ 4~03947~ 5~01904~ 7~08198~ 9~04713~, 10~07093~ 11~087~ 13~03427~ 14~06235~ 15~08141~ 18~0776~ 20~03667~, 22~05414~ 26~0376~ 27~087~ 31~0802~.'),
  (16187, 19, 135, 3, 'Praise the LORD; for the LORD is good: sing praises unto his name; for it is pleasant.', '0~01984~ 2~03050~; 5~03068~ [6] 7~02896~: 9~02167~ 12~08034~; [14 15] 16~05273~.'),
  (21467, 26, 39, 10, 'So that they shall take no wood out of the field, neither cut down any out of the forests; for they shall burn the weapons with fire: and they shall spoil those that spoiled them, and rob those that robbed them, saith the Lord GOD.', '4~05375~ 6~06086~ 10~07704~, 13~02404~ [14] 18~03293~; 22~01197~ 24~05402~ 26~0784~: 30~07997~ 33~07997~ 36~0962~ 39~0962~ 41~05002~ 43~0136~ 44~03069~.'),
  (25464, 42, 11, 46, 'And he said, Woe unto you also, ye lawyers! for ye lade men with burdens grievous to be borne, and ye yourselves touch not the burdens with one of your fingers.', '0~1161~ 2~2036~, 3~3759~ 5~5213~ 6~2532~, [7] 8~3544~! 9~3754~ 11~5412~ 12~444~ 14~5413~ 18~1419~, 19~2532~ 21~846~ 22~4379~ 23~3756~ 25~5413~ 27~1520~ 29~5216~ 30~1147~.'),
  (5229, 5, 11, 15, 'And I will send grass in thy fields for thy cattle, that thou mayest eat and be full.', '3~05414~ 4~06212~ 7~07704~ 10~0929~, 14~0398~ 17~07646~.'),
  (18189, 23, 28, 16, 'Therefore thus saith the Lord GOD, Behold, I lay in Zion for a foundation a stone, a tried stone, a precious corner stone, a sure foundation: he that believeth shall not make haste.', '2~0559~ 4~0136~ 5~03069~, 8~03245~ 10~06726~ 15~068~, 17~0976~ 18~068~, 20~03368~ 21~06438~ [22] 24~03245~ 25~04143~: 28~0539~ 32~02363~.'),
  (6057, 6, 9, 14, 'And the men took of their victuals, and asked not counsel at the mouth of the LORD.', '2~0582~ 3~03947~ 6~06718~, 8~07592~ [10] 13~06310~ 16~03068~.'),
  (29032, 47, 11, 27, 'In weariness and painfulness, in watchings often, in hunger and thirst, in fastings often, in cold and nakedness.', '0~1722~ 1~2873~ 2~2532~ 3~3449~, 4~1722~ 5~70~ 6~4178~, 7~1722~ 8~3042~ 9~2532~ 10~1373~, 11~1722~ 12~3521~ 13~4178~, 14~1722~ 15~5592~ 16~2532~ 17~1132~.'),
  (14782, 19, 57, 5, 'Be thou exalted, O God, above the heavens; let thy glory be above all the earth.', '2~07311~, 4~0430~, 7~08064~; [8] 10~03519~ [11] 15~0776~.'),
  (12398, 16, 5, 7, 'Then I consulted with myself, and I rebuked the nobles, and the rulers, and said unto them, Ye exact usury, every one of his brother. And I set a great assembly against them.', '2~04427~ 4~03820~, 7~07378~ 9~02715~, 12~05461~, 14~0559~ 18~05378~ 19~04855~, 21~0376~ 24~0251~. 27~05414~ 29~01419~ 30~06952~'),
  (20497, 26, 1, 24, 'And when they went, I heard the noise of their wings, like the noise of great waters, as the voice of the Almighty, the voice of speech, as the noise of an host: when they stood, they let down their wings.', '3~03212~, 5~08085~ 7~06963~ 10~03671~, 13~06963~ 15~07227~ 16~04325~, 19~06963~ 22~07706~, 24~06963~ 26~01999~, 29~06963~ 32~04264~: 35~05975~, 38~07503~ 40~03671~.'),
  (23222, 40, 4, 3, 'And when the tempter came to him, he said, If thou be the Son of God, command that these stones be made bread.', '0~2532~ 3~3985~ 4~4334~ 6~846~, 8~2036~, 9~1487~ 11~1488~ 13~5207~ 15~2316~, 16~2036~ 17~2443~ 18~3778~ 19~3037~ 21~1096~ 22~740~.'),
  (2667, 2, 38, 29, 'And the brass of the offering was seventy talents, and two thousand and four hundred shekels.', '2~05178~ 5~08573~ [6] 7~07657~ 8~03603~, 11~0505~ 13~0702~ 14~03967~ 15~08255~.'),
  (15787, 19, 109, 23, 'I am gone like the shadow when it declineth: I am tossed up and down as the locust.', '2~01980~ 5~06738~ 8~05186~: 14~05287~ 17~0697~.'),
  (881, 1, 31, 4, 'And Jacob sent and called Rachel and Leah to the field unto his flock,', '1~03290~ 2~07971~ 4~07121~ 5~07354~ 7~03812~ 10~07704~ 13~06629~,'),
  (9926, 12, 14, 22, 'He built Elath, and restored it to Judah, after that the king slept with his fathers.', '1~01129~ 2~0359~, 4~07725~ 7~03063~, 8~0310~ 11~04428~ 12~07901~ 15~01~.'),
  (11404, 14, 9, 31, 'And Solomon slept with his fathers, and he was buried in the city of David his father: and Rehoboam his son reigned in his stead.', '1~08010~ 2~07901~ 5~01~, 9~06912~ 12~05892~ 14~01732~ 16~01~: 18~07346~ 20~01121~ 21~04427~'),
  (6225, 6, 15, 16, 'And Caleb said, He that smiteth Kirjathsepher, and taketh it, to him will I give Achsah my daughter to wife.', '1~03612~ 2~0559~, 5~05221~ 6~07158~, 8~03920~ 14~05414~ 15~05915~ 17~01323~ 19~0802~.'),
  (19232, 24, 10, 22, 'Behold, the noise of the bruit is come, and a great commotion out of the north country, to make the cities of Judah desolate, and a den of dragons.', '2~06963~ 5~08052~ 7~0935~, 10~01419~ 11~07494~ 15~06828~ 16~0776~, 18~07760~ 20~05892~ 22~03063~ 23~08077~, [24] 26~04583~ 28~08577~.'),
  (5655, 5, 28, 38, 'Thou shalt carry much seed out into the field, and shalt gather but little in; for the locust shall consume it.', '2~03318~ 3~07227~ 4~02233~ 5~03318~ 8~07704~, 11~0622~ [12] 13~04592~ 14~0622~; 17~0697~ 19~02628~'),
  (12908, 18, 2, 8, 'And he took him a potsherd to scrape himself withal; and he sat down among the ashes.', '2~03947~ 5~02789~ 7~01623~ 13~03427~ 14~08432~ 16~0665~.'),
  (30210, 58, 11, 22, 'By faith Joseph, when he died, made mention of the departing of the children of Israel; and gave commandment concerning his bones.', '1~4102~ 2~2501~, 5~5053~, 7~3421~ 8~4012~ 10~1841~ 13~5207~ 15~2474~; 16~2532~ 18~1781~ 19~4012~ 20~846~ 21~3747~.'),
  (249, 1, 10, 14, 'And Pathrusim, and Casluhim, (out of whom came Philistim,) and Caphtorim.', '1~06625~, 3~03695~, 7~03318~ 8~06430~,) 10~03732~.'),
  (20019, 24, 43, 13, 'He shall break also the images of Bethshemesh, that is in the land of Egypt; and the houses of the gods of the Egyptians shall he burn with fire.', '2~07665~ 5~04676~ 7~01053~, [9] 12~0776~ 14~04714~; 17~01004~ 20~0430~ 23~04714~ 26~08313~ 28~0784~.'),
  (28497, 46, 6, 14, 'And God hath both raised up the Lord, and will also raise up us by his own power.', '0~1161~ 1~2316~ 2~1453~ 3~2532~ 5~1453~ 7~2962~, 8~2532~ 9~1825~ 10~2532~ 12~1825~ 13~2248~ 14~1223~ 16~846~ 17~1411~.'),
  (17245, 20, 29, 12, 'If a ruler hearken to lies, all his servants are wicked.', '&para; 2~04910~ 3~07181~ 5~08267~ 6~01697~,* 9~08334~ [10] 11~07563~.'),
  (2274, 2, 26, 34, 'And thou shalt put the mercy seat upon the ark of the testimony in the most holy place.', '3~05414~ 6~03727~ 9~0727~ 12~05715~ 15~06944~ 16~06944~ [17]'),
  (7501, 9, 13, 9, 'And Saul said, Bring hither a burnt offering to me, and peace offerings. And he offered the burnt offering.', '1~07586~ 2~0559~, 4~05066~ 7~05930~ 12~08002~. 15~05927~ 18~05930~.'),
  (28325, 45, 15, 6, 'That ye may with one mind and one mouth glorify God, even the Father of our Lord Jesus Christ.', '0~2443~ 2~1392~ 5~3661~ [6] 6~1722~ 7~1520~ 8~4750~ 9~1392~ 10~2316~, 11~2532~ 13~3962~ 15~2257~ 16~2962~ 17~2424~ 18~5547~.'),
  (26953, 44, 1, 14, 'These all continued with one accord in prayer and supplication, with the women, and Mary the mother of Jesus, and with his brethren.', '0~3778~ 1~3956~ 2~2258~ 3~4342~* 6~3661~ 8~4335~ 9~2532~ 10~1162~, 11~4862~ 13~1135~, 14~2532~ 15~3137~ 17~3384~ 19~2424~, 20~2532~ 21~4862~ 22~846~ 23~80~.'),
  (289, 1, 11, 20, 'And Reu lived two and thirty years, and begat Serug:', '1~07466~ 2~02421~ 3~08147~ 5~07970~ 6~08141~, 8~03205~ 9~08286~:'),
  (30701, 65, 1, 13, 'Raging waves of the sea, foaming out their own shame; wandering stars, to whom is reserved the blackness of darkness for ever.', '0~66~ 1~2949~ 4~2281~, 6~1890~ 8~1438~ 9~152~; 10~4107~ 11~792~, 13~3739~ 15~5083~ 17~2217~ 19~4655~ 20~1519~ 21~165~.'),
  (10208, 12, 23, 35, 'And Jehoiakim gave the silver and the gold to Pharaoh; but he taxed the land to give the money according to the commandment of Pharaoh: he exacted the silver and the gold of the people of the land, of every one according to his taxation, to give it unto Pharaohnechoh.', '1~03079~ 2~05414~ 4~03701~ 7~02091~ 9~06547~; 12~06186~ 14~0776~ 16~05414~ 18~03701~ 22~06310~ 24~06547~: 26~05065~ 28~03701~ 31~02091~ 34~05971~ 37~0776~, 40~0376~ 44~06187~, 46~05414~ [47] 49~06549~.'),
  (18078, 23, 22, 17, 'Behold, the LORD will carry thee away with a mighty captivity, and will surely cover thee.', '2~03068~ 6~02904~ 9~01397~ 10~02925~, 13~05844~ 14~05844~'),
  (22564, 32, 2, 7, 'When my soul fainted within me I remembered the LORD: and my prayer came in unto thee, into thine holy temple.', '2~05315~ 3~05848~ 7~02142~ 9~03068~: 12~08605~ 14~0935~ 19~06944~ 20~01964~.'),
  (13209, 18, 14, 19, 'The waters wear the stones: thou washest away the things which grow out of the dust of the earth; and thou destroyest the hope of man.', '1~04325~ 2~07833~ 4~068~: 7~07857~ 11~05599~ [12] 15~06083~ 18~0776~; 21~06~ 23~08615~ 25~0582~.'),
  (29659, 52, 5, 22, 'Abstain from all appearance of evil.', '0~567~ 1~575~ 2~3956~ 3~1491~ 5~4190~.'),
  (19450, 24, 21, 1, 'The word which came unto Jeremiah from the LORD, when king Zedekiah sent unto him Pashur the son of Melchiah, and Zephaniah the son of Maaseiah the priest, saying,', '&para; 1~01697~ 5~03414~ 8~03068~, 10~04428~ 11~06667~ 12~07971~ 15~06583~ 17~01121~ 19~04441~, 21~06846~ 23~01121~ 25~04641~ 27~03548~, 28~0559~,'),
  (9100, 11, 10, 13, 'And king Solomon gave unto the queen of Sheba all her desire, whatsoever she asked, beside that which Solomon gave her of his royal bounty. So she turned and went to her own country, she and her servants.', '1~04428~ 2~08010~ 3~05414~ 6~04436~ 8~07614~ 11~02656~, 14~07592~, [16] 18~08010~ 19~05414~ 23~04428~ 24~03027~. 27~06437~ 29~03212~ 33~0776~, 37~05650~.'),
  (2245, 2, 26, 5, 'Fifty loops shalt thou make in the one curtain, and fifty loops shalt thou make in the edge of the curtain that is in the coupling of the second; that the loops may take hold one of another.', '0~02572~ 1~03924~ 4~06213~ 7~0259~ 8~03407~, 10~02572~ 11~03924~ 14~06213~ 17~07097~ 20~03407~ [22] 25~04225~ 28~08145~; 31~03924~ 34~06901~ 35~0802~ 37~0269~.'),
  (24081, 40, 26, 17, 'Now the first day of the feast of unleavened bread the disciples came to Jesus, saying unto him, Where wilt thou that we prepare for thee to eat the passover?', '&para; 0~1161~ 2~4413~ [3] [6 7] 9~106~ 11~3101~ 12~4334~ 14~2424~, 15~3004~ 17~846~, 18~4226~ 20~2309~ 23~2090~ 25~4671~ 27~5315~ 29~3957~?'),
  (10213, 12, 24, 3, 'Surely at the commandment of the LORD came this upon Judah, to remove them out of his sight, for the sins of Manasseh, according to all that he did;', '3~06310~ 6~03068~ [8] 10~03063~, 12~05493~ [13] 17~06440~, 20~02403~ 22~04519~, 28~06213~;'),
  (15179, 19, 78, 57, 'But turned back, and dealt unfaithfully like their fathers: they were turned aside like a deceitful bow.', '2~05472~, 5~0898~ 8~01~: 12~02015~ 15~07423~ 16~07198~.'),
  (19038, 24, 4, 2, 'And thou shalt swear, The LORD liveth, in truth, in judgment, and in righteousness; and the nations shall bless themselves in him, and in him shall they glory.', '3~07650~, 5~03068~ 6~02416~, 8~0571~, 10~04941~, 13~06666~; 16~01471~ 18~01288~ 27~01984~.'),
  (12697, 16, 13, 17, 'Then I contended with the nobles of Judah, and said unto them, What evil thing is this that ye do, and profane the sabbath day?', '2~07378~ 5~02715~ 7~03063~, 9~0559~ 13~07451~ 14~01697~ [15] 19~06213~, 21~02490~ 23~07676~ 24~03117~?'),
  (13276, 18, 17, 7, 'Mine eye also is dim by reason of sorrow, and all my members are as a shadow.', '1~05869~ 4~03543~ 8~03708~, 12~03338~ [13] 16~06738~.'),
  (9299, 11, 16, 8, 'In the twenty and sixth year of Asa king of Judah began Elah the son of Baasha to reign over Israel in Tirzah, two years.', '2~08141~ 3~06242~ 4~08337~ 5~08141~ 7~0609~ 8~04428~ 10~03063~ 12~0425~ 14~01121~ 16~01201~ 18~04427~ 20~03478~ 22~08656~, 24~08141~.'),
  (15206, 19, 79, 12, 'And render unto our neighbours sevenfold into their bosom their reproach, wherewith they have reproached thee, O Lord.', '1~07725~ 4~07934~ 5~07659~ 8~02436~ 10~02781~, 14~02778~ 17~0136~.'),
  (14090, 19, 14, 1, 'To the chief Musician, A Psalm of David. The fool hath said in his heart, There is no God. They are corrupt, they have done abominable works, there is none that doeth good.', '&para; [0 3~05329~, [4 5] 7] 7~01732~ 9~05036~ 11~0559~ 14~03820~, [15 16] 18~0430~. 21~07843~, 25~08581~ 26~05949~, [27 28] 31~06213~ 32~02896~.'),
  (10673, 13, 10, 6, 'So Saul died, and his three sons, and all his house died together.', '1~07586~ 2~04191~, 5~07969~ 6~01121~, 10~01004~ 11~04191~ 12~03162~.'),
  (25370, 42, 9, 57, 'And it came to pass, that, as they went in the way, a certain man said unto him, Lord, I will follow thee whithersoever thou goest.', '&para; 0~1161~ 4~1096~, 7~846~ 8~4198~ 9~1722~ 11~3598~, 13~5100~ [14] 15~2036~ 16~4314~ 17~846~, 18~2962~, 21~190~ 22~4671~ 23~302~ 24~3699~ 25~565~.'),
  (21438, 26, 38, 4, 'And I will turn thee back, and put hooks into thy jaws, and I will bring thee forth, and all thine army, horses and horsemen, all of them clothed with all sorts of armour, even a great company with bucklers and shields, all of them handling swords:', '5~07725~, 7~05414~ 8~02397~ 11~03895~, 17~03318~, 21~02428~, 22~05483~ 24~06571~, 28~03847~ 31~04358~ [32 34] 36~07227~ 37~06951~ [38] 39~06793~ 41~04043~, 45~08610~ 46~02719~:');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (24207, 40, 28, 2, 'And, behold, there was a great earthquake: for the angel of the Lord descended from heaven, and came and rolled back the stone from the door, and sat upon it.', '0~2532~, 1~2400~, 3~1096~ 5~3173~ 6~4578~: 7~1063~ 9~32~ 12~2962~ 13~2597~ 14~1537~ 15~3772~, 17~4334~ 20~617~ 22~3037~ 23~575~ 25~2374~, 26~2532~ 27~2521~ 28~1883~ 29~846~.'),
  (2093, 2, 21, 11, 'And if he do not these three unto her, then shall she go out free without money.', '3~06213~ 6~07969~ 13~03318~ 14~02600~ 16~03701~.'),
  (183, 1, 7, 23, 'And every living substance was destroyed which was upon the face of the ground, both man, and cattle, and the creeping things, and the fowl of the heaven; and they were destroyed from the earth: and Noah only remained alive, and they that were with him in the ark.', '3~03351~ 5~04229~ 10~06440~ 13~0127~, 15~0120~, 17~0929~, 21~07431~, 24~05775~ 27~08064~; 31~04229~ 34~0776~: 36~05146~ 37~0389~ 38~07604~ [39] 42~0834~ [43] 48~08392~.'),
  (16310, 19, 143, 8, 'Cause me to hear thy lovingkindness in the morning; for in thee do I trust: cause me to know the way wherein I should walk; for I lift up my soul unto thee.', '3~08085~ 5~02617~ 8~01242~; 14~0982~: 18~03045~ 20~01870~ 21~02098~ 24~03212~; 28~05375~ 30~05315~'),
  (29683, 53, 2, 6, 'And now ye know what withholdeth that he might be revealed in his time.', '0~2532~ 1~3568~ 3~1492~ 5~2722~ 6~1519~ 7~846~ 10~601~ 11~1722~ 12~1438~ 13~2540~.'),
  (386, 1, 16, 1, 'Now Sarai Abram''s wife bare him no children: and she had an handmaid, an Egyptian, whose name was Hagar.', '&para; 1~08297~ 2~087~ 3~0802~ 4~03205~ 6~03808~ 7~03205~: 12~08198~, 14~04713~, 16~08034~ [17] 18~01904~.'),
  (4967, 5, 2, 23, 'And the Avims which dwelt in Hazerim, even unto Azzah, the Caphtorims, which came forth out of Caphtor, destroyed them, and dwelt in their stead.)', '2~05761~ 4~03427~ 6~02699~, [7] 9~05804~, 11~03732~, 14~03318~ 17~03731~, 18~08045~ 21~03427~'),
  (27349, 44, 11, 26, 'And when he had found him, he brought him unto Antioch. And it came to pass, that a whole year they assembled themselves with the church, and taught much people. And the disciples were called Christians first in Antioch.', '0~2532~ 4~2147~ 5~846~, 7~71~ 8~846~ 9~1519~ 10~490~. 11~1161~ 15~1096~, 18~3650~ 19~1763~ 20~846~ 22~4863~ 23~1722~ 25~1577~, 26~2532~ 27~1321~ 28~2425~ 29~3793~. 30~5037~ 32~3101~ 34~5537~ 35~5546~ 36~4412~ 37~1722~ 38~490~.'),
  (30599, 62, 3, 4, 'Whosoever committeth sin transgresseth also the law: for sin is the transgression of the law.', '&para; 0~3956~ 1~4160~ 2~266~ 3~4160~ 4~458~* 5~2532~ 7~458~: 8~2532~ 9~266~ 10~2076~ 15~458~.'),
  (27962, 45, 1, 16, 'For I am not ashamed of the gospel of Christ: for it is the power of God unto salvation to every one that believeth; to the Jew first, and also to the Greek.', '&para; 0~1063~ 2~1870~ 3~3756~ 4~1870~ 7~2098~ 9~5547~: 10~1063~ 12~2076~ 14~1411~ 16~2316~ 17~1519~ 18~4991~ 21~3956~ 23~4100~; 26~2453~ 27~4412~, 28~5037~ 29~2532~ 32~1672~.'),
  (20660, 26, 10, 18, 'Then the glory of the LORD departed from off the threshold of the house, and stood over the cherubims.', '2~03519~ 5~03068~ 6~03318~ 10~04670~ 13~01004~, 15~05975~ 18~03742~.'),
  (25848, 42, 21, 8, 'And he said, Take heed that ye be not deceived: for many shall come in my name, saying, I am Christ; and the time draweth near: go ye not therefore after them.', '0~1161~ 2~2036~, 4~991~ 7~4105~ 8~3361~ 9~4105~: 10~1063~ 11~4183~ 13~2064~ 14~1909~ 15~3450~ 16~3686~, 17~3004~ 18~3754~,* 19~1473~ 20~1510~ [21] 22~2532~ 24~2540~ 26~1448~: 28~4198~ 29~3361~ 30~3767~ 31~3694~ 32~846~.'),
  (22587, 32, 4, 10, 'Then said the LORD, Thou hast had pity on the gourd, for the which thou hast not laboured, neither madest it grow; which came up in a night, and perished in a night:', '1~0559~ 3~03068~, 7~02347~ 10~07021~, 17~05998~, 21~01431~; 27~03915~ 28~01121~,* 30~06~ 33~03915~ 34~01121~:*'),
  (4326, 4, 20, 10, 'And Moses and Aaron gathered the congregation together before the rock, and he said unto them, Hear now, ye rebels; must we fetch you water out of this rock?', '1~04872~ 3~0175~ 4~06950~ 6~06951~ 8~06440~ 10~05553~, 13~0559~ 16~08085~ 19~04784~; 22~03318~ 24~04325~ 28~05553~?'),
  (28648, 46, 11, 32, 'But when we are judged, we are chastened of the Lord, that we should not be condemned with the world.', '0~1161~ 4~2919~, 7~3811~ 8~5259~ 10~2962~, 11~3363~ 13~2632~ 14~3363~ 16~2632~ 17~4862~ 19~2889~.'),
  (28711, 46, 14, 17, 'For thou verily givest thanks well, but the other is not edified.', '0~1063~ 1~4771~ 2~3303~ 4~2168~ 5~2573~, 6~235~ 8~2087~ 9~3618~ 10~3756~ 11~3618~.'),
  (30952, 66, 14, 10, 'The same shall drink of the wine of the wrath of God, which is poured out without mixture into the cup of his indignation; and he shall be tormented with fire and brimstone in the presence of the holy angels, and in the presence of the Lamb:', '1~2532~ 2~846~ 3~4095~ 4~1537~ 6~3631~ 9~2372~ 11~2316~, 12~3588~ 15~2767~ 17~194~ 18~1722~ 20~4221~ 22~846~ 23~3709~; 24~2532~ 28~928~ 29~1722~ 30~4442~ 31~2532~ 32~2303~ 35~1799~ 38~40~ 39~32~, 40~2532~ 43~1799~ 46~721~:'),
  (24823, 41, 14, 58, 'We heard him say, I will destroy this temple that is made with hands, and within three days I will build another made without hands.', '0~3754~* 1~2249~ 2~191~ 3~846~ 4~3004~ 5~3754~,* 6~1473~ 8~2647~ 9~5126~ 10~3485~ 15~5499~, 16~2532~ 17~1223~ 18~5140~ 19~2250~ 22~3618~ 23~243~ 26~886~.'),
  (10623, 13, 8, 40, 'And the sons of Ulam were mighty men of valour, archers, and had many sons, and sons'' sons, an hundred and fifty. All these are of the sons of Benjamin.', '2~01121~ 4~0198~ 6~01368~ 7~0582~ 9~02428~, 10~01869~ 11~07198~,* 14~07235~ 15~01121~, 17~01121~ 18~01121~, 20~03967~ 22~02572~. [25] 28~01121~ 30~01144~.'),
  (15418, 19, 91, 14, 'Because he hath set his love upon me, therefore will I deliver him: I will set him on high, because he hath known my name.', '5~02836~ 11~06403~ 18~07682~, 22~03045~ 24~08034~.'),
  (28552, 46, 8, 9, 'But take heed lest by any means this liberty of yours become a stumblingblock to them that are weak.', '0~1161~ 2~991~ 3~3381~ 6~4458~ 7~3778~ 8~1849~ 10~5216~ 11~1096~ 13~4348~ 18~770~.'),
  (6122, 6, 11, 9, 'And Joshua did unto them as the LORD bade him: he hocked their horses, and burnt their chariots with fire.', '1~03091~ 2~06213~ 7~03068~ 8~0559~ 11~06131~ 13~05483~, 15~08313~ 17~04818~ 19~0784~.'),
  (10691, 13, 11, 10, 'These also are the chief of the mighty men whom David had, who strengthened themselves with him in his kingdom, and with all Israel, to make him king, according to the word of the LORD concerning Israel.', '&para; [2] 4~07218~ 8~01368~ 10~01732~ 13~02388~ 19~04438~, [20] 23~03478~, 27~04427~, 31~01697~ 34~03068~ 36~03478~.'),
  (6687, 7, 6, 26, 'And build an altar unto the LORD thy God upon the top of this rock, in the ordered place, and take the second bullock, and offer a burnt sacrifice with the wood of the grove which thou shalt cut down.', '1~01129~ 3~04196~ 6~03068~ 8~0430~ 11~07218~ 14~04581~, 18~04634~, 20~03947~ 22~08145~ 23~06499~, 25~05927~ 28~05930~ 31~06086~ 34~0842~ 39~03772~.'),
  (25919, 42, 22, 41, 'And he was withdrawn from them about a stone''s cast, and kneeled down, and prayed,', '0~2532~ 1~846~ 3~645~ 4~575~ 5~846~ 6~5616~ 8~3037~ 9~1000~, 10~2532~ 12~5087~ 13~1119~,* 15~4336~,'),
  (30292, 59, 1, 10, 'But the rich, in that he is made low: because as the flower of the grass he shall pass away.', '0~1161~ 2~4145~, 3~1722~ 5~846~ 8~5014~: 9~3754~ 10~5613~ 12~438~ 15~5528~ 19~3928~.'),
  (12864, 17, 9, 21, 'To stablish this among them, that they should keep the fourteenth day of the month Adar, and the fifteenth day of the same, yearly,', '1~06965~ [2] 8~06213~ 10~06240~ 11~0702~* 12~03117~ 15~02320~ 16~0143~, 19~06240~ 20~02568~* 21~03117~ 25~08141~ 26~08141~,*'),
  (1303, 1, 43, 8, 'And Judah said unto Israel his father, Send the lad with me, and we will arise and go; that we may live, and not die, both we, and thou, and also our little ones.', '1~03063~ 2~0559~ 4~03478~ 6~01~, 7~07971~ 9~05288~ 15~06965~ 17~03212~; 21~02421~, 24~04191~, [29] 33~02945~.'),
  (9613, 12, 4, 2, 'And Elisha said unto her, What shall I do for thee? tell me, what hast thou in the house? And she said, Thine handmaid hath not any thing in the house, save a pot of oil.', '1~0477~ 2~0559~ 8~06213~ 11~05046~ 14~03426~ 18~01004~? 21~0559~, 23~08198~ 30~01004~, 33~0610~ 35~08081~.'),
  (12615, 16, 11, 18, 'All the Levites in the holy city were two hundred fourscore and four.', '2~03881~ 5~06944~ 6~05892~ [7] 9~03967~ 10~08084~ 12~0702~.'),
  (3329, 3, 20, 6, 'And the soul that turneth after such as have familiar spirits, and after wizards, to go a whoring after them, I will even set my face against that soul, and will cut him off from among his people.', '2~05315~ 4~06437~ 5~0413~ 10~0178~, 12~0310~ 13~03049~, 17~02181~ 18~0310~ 23~05414~ 25~06440~ 28~05315~, 33~03772~ 35~07130~ 37~05971~.'),
  (2394, 2, 30, 7, 'And Aaron shall burn thereon sweet incense every morning: when he dresseth the lamps, he shall burn incense upon it.', '1~0175~ 3~06999~ 5~05561~ 6~07004~ 8~01242~: 11~03190~ 13~05216~, 17~06999~'),
  (28928, 47, 6, 14, 'Be ye not unequally yoked together with unbelievers: for what fellowship hath righteousness with unrighteousness? and what communion hath light with darkness?', '1~1096~ 2~3361~ 5~2086~ 7~571~: 8~1063~ 9~5101~ 10~3352~ 12~1343~ 13~2532~ 14~458~? 15~1161~ 16~5101~ 17~2842~ 19~5457~ 20~4314~ 21~4655~?'),
  (19958, 24, 40, 8, 'Then they came to Gedaliah to Mizpah, even Ishmael the son of Nethaniah, and Johanan and Jonathan the sons of Kareah, and Seraiah the son of Tanhumeth, and the sons of Ephai the Netophathite, and Jezaniah the son of a Maachathite, they and their men.', '2~0935~ 4~01436~ 6~04708~, 8~03458~ 10~01121~ 12~05418~, 14~03110~ 16~03129~ 18~01121~ 20~07143~, 22~08304~ 24~01121~ 26~08576~, 29~01121~ 31~05778~ 33~05200~, 35~03153~ 37~01121~ 40~04602~, 44~0582~.'),
  (13620, 18, 31, 23, 'For destruction from God was a terror to me, and by reason of his highness I could not endure.', '1~0343~ [2] 3~0410~ [4] 6~06343~ 14~07613~ 16~03201~'),
  (28184, 45, 9, 13, 'As it is written, Jacob have I loved, but Esau have I hated.', '0~2531~ 3~1125~, 4~2384~ 7~25~, 8~1161~ 9~2269~ 12~3404~.'),
  (4671, 4, 31, 1, 'And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~01696~ 5~04872~, 6~0559~,'),
  (28125, 45, 7, 18, 'For I know that in me (that is, in my flesh,) dwelleth no good thing: for to will is present with me; but how to perform that which is good I find not.', '0~1063~ 2~1492~ 3~3754~ 4~1722~ 5~1698~ 7~5123~, 8~1722~ 9~3450~ 10~4561~,) 11~3611~ 12~3756~ 14~18~: 15~1063~ 17~2309~ 19~3873~ 21~3427~; 22~1161~ [23] 25~2716~ 29~2570~ 31~2147~ 32~3756~.'),
  (13475, 18, 25, 5, 'Behold even to the moon, and it shineth not; yea, the stars are not pure in his sight.', '4~03394~, 7~0166~ 11~03556~ 14~02141~ 17~05869~.'),
  (29419, 50, 2, 12, 'Wherefore, my beloved, as ye have always obeyed, not as in my presence only, but now much more in my absence, work out your own salvation with fear and trembling.', '&para; 0~5620~, 1~3450~ 2~27~, 3~2531~ 5~5219~ 6~3842~ 7~5219~, 8~3361~ 9~5613~ 10~1722~ 11~3450~ 12~3952~ 13~3440~, 14~235~ 15~3568~ 16~4183~ 17~3123~ 18~1722~ 19~3450~ 20~666~, 22~2716~ 24~1438~ 25~4991~ 26~3326~ 27~5401~ 28~2532~ 29~5156~.'),
  (30502, 61, 1, 7, 'And to godliness brotherly kindness; and to brotherly kindness charity.', '0~1161~ 1~1722~ 2~2150~ 4~5360~; 5~1161~ 6~1722~ 8~5360~ 9~26~.'),
  (9601, 12, 3, 17, 'For thus saith the LORD, Ye shall not see wind, neither shall ye see rain; yet that valley shall be filled with water, that ye may drink, both ye, and your cattle, and your beasts.', '2~0559~ 4~03068~, 8~07200~ 9~07307~, 13~07200~ 14~01653~; 17~05158~ 20~04390~ 22~04325~, 26~08354~, 31~04735~, 34~0929~.'),
  (25339, 42, 9, 26, 'For whosoever shall be ashamed of me and of my words, of him shall the Son of man be ashamed, when he shall come in his own glory, and in his Father''s, and of the holy angels.', '0~1063~ 1~302~ 2~3739~ 4~1870~ 6~3165~ 7~2532~ 9~1699~ 10~3056~, 12~5126~ 13~1870~ 15~5207~ 17~444~ 19~1870~, 20~3752~ 23~2064~ 24~1722~ 26~846~ 27~1391~, 28~2532~ [29 30] 31~3962~, 32~2532~ 35~40~ 36~32~.'),
  (19302, 24, 13, 27, 'I have seen thine adulteries, and thy neighings, the lewdness of thy whoredom, and thine abominations on the hills in the fields. Woe unto thee, O Jerusalem! wilt thou not be made clean? when shall it once be?', '2~07200~ 4~05004~, 7~04684~, 9~02154~ 12~02184~, [13] 15~08251~ 18~01389~ 21~07704~. 22~0188~ 26~03389~! 32~02891~? [34 35] 36~0310~ [37] 37~05750~?'),
  (3508, 3, 25, 34, 'But the field of the suburbs of their cities may not be sold; for it is their perpetual possession.', '2~07704~ 5~04054~ 8~05892~ 12~04376~; [15] 17~05769~ 18~0272~.'),
  (18270, 23, 32, 2, 'And a man shall be as an hiding place from the wind, and a covert from the tempest; as rivers of water in a dry place, as the shadow of a great rock in a weary land.', '2~0376~ 8~04224~ 11~07307~, 14~05643~ 17~02230~; 19~06388~ 21~04325~ 25~06724~, 28~06738~ 31~03515~ 32~05553~ 35~05889~ 36~0776~.'),
  (18937, 23, 66, 6, 'A voice of noise from the city, a voice from the temple, a voice of the LORD that rendereth recompense to his enemies.', '1~06963~ 3~07588~ 6~05892~, 8~06963~ 11~01964~, 13~06963~ 16~03068~ 18~07999~ 19~01576~ 22~0341~.'),
  (17229, 20, 28, 24, 'Whoso robbeth his father or his mother, and saith, It is no transgression; the same is the companion of a destroyer.', '&para; 1~01497~ 3~01~ 6~0517~, 8~0559~, [9 10] 12~06588~; [15] 17~02270~ 20~07843~ 21~0376~.*'),
  (654, 1, 24, 59, 'And they sent away Rebekah their sister, and her nurse, and Abraham''s servant, and his men.', '3~07971~ 4~07259~ 6~0269~, 9~03243~, 11~085~ 12~05650~, 15~0582~.'),
  (23750, 40, 18, 13, 'And if so be that he find it, verily I say unto you, he rejoiceth more of that sheep, than of the ninety and nine which went not astray.', '0~2532~ 2~1437~ 3~1096~ 6~2147~ 7~846~, 8~281~ 10~3004~ 12~3754~ 13~5213~,* 15~5463~ 16~3123~ 17~1909~ 18~846~ [19] 20~2228~ 21~1909~ 25~1768~ 26~3588~ 27~4105~ 28~3361~ 29~4105~.'),
  (27689, 44, 21, 9, 'And the same man had four daughters, virgins, which did prophesy.', '0~1161~ 3~5129~ 4~2258~ 5~5064~ 6~2364~, 7~3933~, 10~4395~.'),
  (16317, 19, 144, 3, 'LORD, what is man, that thou takest knowledge of him! or the son of man, that thou makest account of him!', '0~03068~, [2] 3~0120~, 7~03045~ [10] 12~01121~ 14~0582~, 18~02803~'),
  (7645, 9, 17, 20, 'And David rose up early in the morning, and left the sheep with a keeper, and took, and went, as Jesse had commanded him; and he came to the trench, as the host was going forth to the fight, and shouted for the battle.', '1~01732~ 4~07925~ 7~01242~, 9~05203~ 11~06629~ 14~08104~, 16~05375~, 18~03212~, 20~03448~ 22~06680~ 26~0935~ 29~04570~, 32~02428~ 35~03318~ 38~04634~, 40~07321~ 43~04421~.'),
  (22154, 28, 4, 12, 'My people ask counsel at their stocks, and their staff declareth unto them: for the spirit of whoredoms hath caused them to err, and they have gone a whoring from under their God.', '&para; 1~05971~ 2~07592~ 6~06086~, 9~04731~ 10~05046~ 15~07307~ 17~02183~ [20] 22~08582~, 28~02181~ 32~0430~.'),
  (13831, 18, 38, 29, 'Out of whose womb came the ice? and the hoary frost of heaven, who hath gendered it?', '3~0990~ 4~03318~ 6~07140~? 10~03713~ 12~08064~, 15~03205~'),
  (3309, 3, 19, 23, 'And when ye shall come into the land, and shall have planted all manner of trees for food, then ye shall count the fruit thereof as uncircumcised: three years shall it be as uncircumcised unto you: it shall not be eaten of.', '4~0935~ 7~0776~, 11~05193~ 15~06086~ 17~03978~, 21~06188~ 23~06529~ 26~06188~ 27~06190~:* 28~07969~ 29~08141~ 34~06189~ 41~0398~'),
  (19872, 24, 36, 21, 'So the king sent Jehudi to fetch the roll: and he took it out of Elishama the scribe''s chamber. And Jehudi read it in the ears of the king, and in the ears of all the princes which stood beside the king.', '2~04428~ 3~07971~ 4~03065~ 6~03947~ 8~04039~: 11~03947~ 15~0476~ 17~05608~ 18~03957~. 20~03065~ 21~07121~ 25~0241~ 28~04428~, 32~0241~ 36~08269~ 38~05975~ 39~05921~ 41~04428~.'),
  (8041, 10, 1, 12, 'And they mourned, and wept, and fasted until even, for Saul, and for Jonathan his son, and for the people of the LORD, and for the house of Israel; because they were fallen by the sword.', '2~05594~, 4~01058~, 6~06684~ 8~06153~, 10~07586~, 13~03083~ 15~01121~, 19~05971~ 22~03068~, 26~01004~ 28~03478~; 32~05307~ 35~02719~.'),
  (14545, 19, 40, 11, 'Withhold not thou thy tender mercies from me, O LORD: let thy lovingkindness and thy truth continually preserve me.', '&para; 0~03607~ 5~07356~ 9~03068~: 12~02617~ 15~0571~ 16~08548~ 17~05341~'),
  (8908, 11, 6, 4, 'And for the house he made windows of narrow lights.', '3~01004~ 5~06213~ 6~02474~ 8~0331~ 9~08261~.'),
  (4681, 4, 31, 11, 'And they took all the spoil, and all the prey, both of men and of beasts.', '2~03947~ 5~07998~, 9~04455~, [10] 12~0120~ 15~0929~.'),
  (12752, 17, 2, 19, 'And when the virgins were gathered together the second time, then Mordecai sat in the king''s gate.', '3~01330~ 6~06908~ 9~08145~, 11~04782~ 12~03427~ 15~04428~ 16~08179~.'),
  (15162, 19, 78, 40, 'How oft did they provoke him in the wilderness, and grieve him in the desert!', '&para; 0~04100~ 4~04784~ 8~04057~, [9] 10~06087~ 14~03452~!'),
  (30230, 58, 12, 2, 'Looking unto Jesus the author and finisher of our faith; who for the joy that was set before him endured the cross, despising the shame, and is set down at the right hand of the throne of God.', '0~872~ 1~1519~ 2~2424~ 4~747~ 5~2532~ 6~5051~ [8] 9~4102~; 10~3739~ 11~473~ 13~5479~ 17~4295~ 18~846~ 19~5278~ 21~4716~, 22~2706~ 24~152~, 25~5037~ 28~2523~ 29~1722~ 32~1188~ 35~2362~ 37~2316~.'),
  (3552, 3, 26, 23, 'And if ye will not be reformed by me by these things, but will walk contrary unto me;', '6~03256~ 14~01980~ 15~07147~'),
  (8526, 10, 19, 7, 'Now therefore arise, go forth, and speak comfortably unto thy servants: for I swear by the LORD, if thou go not forth, there will not tarry one with thee this night: and that will be worse unto thee than all the evil that befell thee from thy youth until now.', '2~06965~, 4~03318~, 6~01696~ 7~03820~ 10~05650~: 13~07650~ 16~03068~, 21~03318~, 25~03885~ 26~0376~ 30~03915~: 35~07489~ 41~07451~ 43~0935~ 47~05271~'),
  (18492, 23, 42, 3, 'A bruised reed shall he not break, and the smoking flax shall he not quench: he shall bring forth judgment unto truth.', '1~07533~ 2~07070~ 6~07665~, 9~03544~ 10~06594~ 14~03518~: 18~03318~ 19~04941~ 21~0571~.'),
  (25836, 42, 20, 43, 'Till I make thine enemies thy footstool.', '0~302~ 1~2193~ 2~5087~ 3~4675~ 4~2190~ 5~4675~ 6~5286~ 7~4228~.*'),
  (16189, 19, 135, 5, 'For I know that the LORD is great, and that our Lord is above all gods.', '&para; 2~03045~ 5~03068~ [6] 7~01419~, [9] 11~0113~ [12] 15~0430~.'),
  (10139, 12, 21, 12, 'Therefore thus saith the LORD God of Israel, Behold, I am bringing such evil upon Jerusalem and Judah, that whosoever heareth of it, both his ears shall tingle.', '2~0559~ 4~03068~ 5~0430~ 7~03478~, [10] 11~0935~ [12] 13~07451~ 15~03389~ 17~03063~, 20~08085~ 23~08147~ 25~0241~ 27~06750~.'),
  (25009, 42, 2, 24, 'And to offer a sacrifice according to that which is said in the law of the Lord, A pair of turtledoves, or two young pigeons.', '0~2532~ 2~1325~ 4~2378~ 5~2596~ 10~2046~ 11~1722~ 13~3551~ 16~2962~, 18~2201~ 20~5167~, 21~2228~ 22~1417~ 23~3502~ 24~4058~.'),
  (19375, 24, 17, 9, 'The heart is deceitful above all things, and desperately wicked: who can know it?', '1~03820~ [2] 3~06121~ [6] 9~0605~: 12~03045~'),
  (24451, 41, 6, 34, 'And Jesus, when he came out, saw much people, and was moved with compassion toward them, because they were as sheep not having a shepherd: and he began to teach them many things.', '0~2532~ 1~2424~, 5~1831~, 6~1492~ 7~4183~ 8~3793~, 9~2532~ 13~4697~ 14~1909~ 15~846~, 16~3754~ 18~2258~ 19~5613~ 20~4263~ 21~3361~ 22~2192~ 24~4166~: 25~2532~ 27~756~ 29~1321~ 30~846~ 32~4183~.'),
  (4170, 4, 15, 12, 'According to the number that ye shall prepare, so shall ye do to every one according to their number.', '3~04557~ 7~06213~, 8~03602~ 11~06213~ 14~0259~ 18~04557~.'),
  (6196, 6, 14, 2, 'By lot was their inheritance, as the LORD commanded by the hand of Moses, for the nine tribes, and for the half tribe.', '1~01486~ [2] 4~05159~, 7~03068~ 8~06680~ 11~03027~ 13~04872~, 16~08672~ 17~04294~, [19] 21~02677~ 22~04294~.'),
  (16491, 20, 3, 27, 'Withhold not good from them to whom it is due, when it is in the power of thine hand to do it.', '&para; 0~04513~ 2~02896~ 9~01167~, 15~0410~ 18~03027~ 20~06213~ [21]'),
  (29376, 49, 6, 23, 'Peace be to the brethren, and love with faith, from God the Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.', '0~1515~ [1] 4~80~, 5~2532~ 6~26~ 7~3326~ 8~4102~, 9~575~ 10~2316~ 12~3962~ 13~2532~ 15~2962~ 16~2424~ 17~5547~.'),
  (14214, 19, 22, 1, 'To the chief Musician upon Aijeleth Shahar, A Psalm of David. My God, my God, why hast thou forsaken me? why art thou so far from helping me, and from the words of my roaring?', '&para; [0 3~05329~ 5~0365~ 6~07837~, 8~04210~ 10] 10~01732~ 12~0410~, 14~0410~, 18~05800~ [20 23] 24~07350~ 26~03444~ [28 29] 31~01697~ 34~07581~?'),
  (23027, 38, 10, 2, 'For the idols have spoken vanity, and the diviners have seen a lie, and have told false dreams; they comfort in vain: therefore they went their way as a flock, they were troubled, because there was no shepherd.', '2~08655~ 4~01696~ 5~0205~, 8~07080~ 10~02372~ 12~08267~, 15~01696~ 16~07723~ 17~02472~; 19~05162~ 21~01892~: 24~05265~ 29~06629~, 32~06031~, [34 35] 37~07462~.'),
  (19504, 24, 23, 11, 'For both prophet and priest are profane; yea, in my house have I found their wickedness, saith the LORD.', '2~05030~ 4~03548~ 6~02610~; 10~01004~ 13~04672~ 15~07451~, 16~05002~ 18~03068~.'),
  (513, 1, 20, 14, 'And Abimelech took sheep, and oxen, and menservants, and womenservants, and gave them unto Abraham, and restored him Sarah his wife.', '&para; 1~040~ 2~03947~ 3~06629~, 5~01241~, 7~05650~, 9~08198~, 11~05414~ [12] 14~085~, 16~07725~ 18~08283~ 20~0802~.'),
  (8232, 10, 8, 16, 'And Joab the son of Zeruiah was over the host; and Jehoshaphat the son of Ahilud was recorder;', '1~03097~ 3~01121~ 5~06870~ [6] 9~06635~; 11~03092~ 13~01121~ 15~0286~ [16] 17~02142~;'),
  (23364, 40, 8, 9, 'For I am a man under authority, having soldiers under me: and I say to this man, Go, and he goeth; and to another, Come, and he cometh; and to my servant, Do this, and he doeth it.', '0~2532~ 1~1063~* 2~1473~ 3~1510~ 5~444~ 6~5259~ 7~1849~, 8~2192~ 9~4757~ 10~5259~ 11~1683~: 12~2532~ 14~3004~ 16~5129~ [17] 18~4198~, 19~2532~ 21~4198~; 22~2532~ 24~243~, 25~2064~, 26~2532~ 28~2064~; 29~2532~ 31~3450~ 32~1401~, 33~4160~ 34~5124~, 35~2532~ 37~4160~ [38]'),
  (13111, 18, 10, 16, 'For it increaseth. Thou huntest me as a fierce lion: and again thou shewest thyself marvellous upon me.', '2~01342~. 4~06679~ 9~07826~: 11~07725~ 15~06381~'),
  (13755, 18, 36, 10, 'He openeth also their ear to discipline, and commandeth that they return from iniquity.', '1~01540~ 4~0241~ 6~04148~, 8~0559~ 11~07725~ 13~0205~.'),
  (2739, 2, 40, 27, 'And he burnt sweet incense thereon; as the LORD commanded Moses.', '2~06999~ 3~05561~ 4~07004~ 8~03068~ 9~06680~ 10~04872~.'),
  (9181, 11, 12, 22, 'But the word of God came unto Shemaiah the man of God, saying,', '2~01697~ 4~0430~ 7~08098~ 9~0376~ 11~0430~, 12~0559~,'),
  (28692, 46, 13, 11, 'When I was a child, I spake as a child, I understood as a child, I thought as a child: but when I became a man, I put away childish things.', '0~3753~ 2~2252~ 4~3516~, 6~2980~ 7~5613~ 9~3516~, 11~5426~ 12~5613~ 14~3516~, 16~3049~ 17~5613~ 19~3516~: 20~1161~ 21~3753~ 23~1096~ 25~435~, 28~2673~ 30~3516~.'),
  (16197, 19, 135, 13, 'Thy name, O LORD, endureth for ever; and thy memorial, O LORD, throughout all generations.', '1~08034~, 3~03068~, [4] 6~05769~; [7] 9~02143~, 11~03068~, 13~01755~ 14~01755~.'),
  (21005, 26, 22, 20, 'As they gather silver, and brass, and iron, and lead, and tin, into the midst of the furnace, to blow the fire upon it, to melt it; so will I gather you in mine anger and in my fury, and I will leave you there, and melt you.', '[0] 2~06910~ 3~03701~, 5~05178~, 7~01270~, 9~05777~, 11~0913~, 14~08432~ 17~03564~, 19~05301~ 21~0784~ 25~05413~ [26] 30~06908~ [31] 34~0639~ 38~02534~, 42~03240~ [43 44] 46~05413~'),
  (9474, 11, 21, 15, 'And it came to pass, when Jezebel heard that Naboth was stoned, and was dead, that Jezebel said to Ahab, Arise, take possession of the vineyard of Naboth the Jezreelite, which he refused to give thee for money: for Naboth is not alive, but dead.', '6~0348~ 7~08085~ 9~05022~ 11~05619~, 14~04191~, 16~0348~ 17~0559~ 19~0256~, 20~06965~, 22~03423~ 25~03754~ 27~05022~ 29~03158~, 32~03985~ 34~05414~ 37~03701~: 39~05022~ 42~02416~, 44~04191~.'),
  (4207, 4, 16, 8, 'And Moses said unto Korah, Hear, I pray you, ye sons of Levi:', '1~04872~ 2~0559~ 4~07141~, 5~08085~, 10~01121~ 12~03878~:'),
  (10178, 12, 23, 5, 'And he put down the idolatrous priests, whom the kings of Judah had ordained to burn incense in the high places in the cities of Judah, and in the places round about Jerusalem; them also that burned incense unto Baal, to the sun, and to the moon, and to the planets, and to all the host of heaven.', '3~07673~ 6~03649~, 9~04428~ 11~03063~ 13~05414~ 16~06999~ 20~01116~ 23~05892~ 25~03063~, 31~04524~ 32~03389~; 37~06999~ 39~01168~, 42~08121~, 46~03394~, 50~04208~, 55~06635~ 57~08064~.'),
  (11771, 14, 27, 7, 'Now the rest of the acts of Jotham, and all his wars, and his ways, lo, they are written in the book of the kings of Israel and Judah.', '2~03499~ 5~01697~ 7~03147~, 11~04421~, 14~01870~, [17] 18~03789~ 21~05612~ 24~04428~ 26~03478~ 28~03063~.'),
  (20590, 26, 7, 4, 'And mine eye shall not spare thee, neither will I have pity: but I will recompense thy ways upon thee, and thine abominations shall be in the midst of thee: and ye shall know that I am the LORD.', '2~05869~ 5~02347~ 11~02550~: 15~05414~ 17~01870~ 22~08441~ 27~08432~ 33~03045~ [36] 38~03068~.'),
  (23973, 40, 24, 6, 'And ye shall hear of wars and rumours of wars: see that ye be not troubled: for all these things must come to pass, but the end is not yet.', '0~1161~ 2~3195~ 3~191~ 5~4171~ 6~2532~ 7~189~ 9~4171~: 10~3708~ 13~2360~ 14~3361~ 15~2360~: 16~1063~ 17~3956~ [18 19] 20~1163~ 23~1096~, 24~235~ 26~5056~ 27~2076~ 29~3768~.'),
  (29496, 51, 1, 15, 'Who is the image of the invisible God, the firstborn of every creature:', '0~3739~ 1~2076~ 3~1504~ 6~517~ 7~2316~, 9~4416~ 11~3956~ 12~2937~:'),
  (5979, 6, 6, 24, 'And they burnt the city with fire, and all that was therein: only the silver, and the gold, and the vessels of brass and of iron, they put into the treasury of the house of the LORD.', '2~08313~ 4~05892~ 6~0784~, [10] 14~03701~, 17~02091~, 20~03627~ 22~05178~ 25~01270~, 27~05414~ 30~0214~ 33~01004~ 36~03068~.'),
  (30329, 59, 2, 20, 'But wilt thou know, O vain man, that faith without works is dead?', '0~1161~ 1~2309~ 3~1097~, 4~5599~ 5~2756~ 6~444~, 7~3754~ 8~4102~ 9~5565~ 10~2041~ 11~2076~ 12~3498~?'),
  (18779, 23, 57, 5, 'Enflaming yourselves with idols under every green tree, slaying the children in the valleys under the clifts of the rocks?', '0~02552~ 3~0410~ 6~07488~ 7~06086~, 8~07819~ 10~03206~ 13~05158~ 16~05585~ 19~05553~?');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (11468, 14, 13, 6, 'Yet Jeroboam the son of Nebat, the servant of Solomon the son of David, is risen up, and hath rebelled against his lord.', '1~03379~ 3~01121~ 5~05028~, 7~05650~ 9~08010~ 11~01121~ 13~01732~, 16~06965~, 19~04775~ 22~0113~.'),
  (3360, 3, 21, 10, 'And he that is the high priest among his brethren, upon whose head the anointing oil was poured, and that is consecrated to put on the garments, shall not uncover his head, nor rend his clothes;', '&para; [1 3] 5~01419~ 6~03548~ 9~0251~, 12~07218~ 14~04888~ 15~08081~ 17~03332~, 21~04390~ 22~03027~* 24~03847~ 27~0899~, 30~06544~ 32~07218~, 34~06533~ 36~0899~;'),
  (11745, 14, 26, 4, 'And he did that which was right in the sight of the LORD, according to all that his father Amaziah did.', '2~06213~ [3 5] 6~03477~ 9~05869~ 12~03068~, 18~01~ 19~0558~ 20~06213~.'),
  (3046, 3, 11, 44, 'For I am the LORD your God: ye shall therefore sanctify yourselves, and ye shall be holy; for I am holy: neither shall ye defile yourselves with any manner of creeping thing that creepeth upon the earth.', '[2] 4~03068~ 6~0430~: 11~06942~, 16~06918~; [19] 20~06918~: 24~02930~ 25~05315~ 31~08318~ 33~07430~ 36~0776~.'),
  (6547, 7, 1, 31, 'Neither did Asher drive out the inhabitants of Accho, nor the inhabitants of Zidon, nor of Ahlab, nor of Achzib, nor of Helbah, nor of Aphik, nor of Rehob:', '2~0836~ 4~03423~ 6~03427~ 8~05910~, 11~03427~ 13~06721~, 16~0303~, 19~0392~, 22~02462~, 25~0663~, 28~07340~:'),
  (3675, 4, 2, 12, 'And those which pitch by him shall be the tribe of Simeon: and the captain of the children of Simeon shall be Shelumiel the son of Zurishaddai.', '3~02583~ [6 7] 9~04294~ 11~08095~: 14~05387~ 17~01121~ 19~08095~ [20 21] 22~08017~ 24~01121~ 26~06701~.'),
  (27789, 44, 24, 4, 'Notwithstanding, that I be not further tedious unto thee, I pray thee that thou wouldest hear us of thy clemency a few words.', '0~1161~, 1~3363~ 3~4119~ 4~1909~ 5~3363~* 6~4119~ 7~1465~ 9~4571~, 11~3870~ 12~4571~ 16~191~ 17~2257~ 19~4674~ 20~1932~ 23~4935~.'),
  (20540, 26, 4, 2, 'And lay siege against it, and build a fort against it, and cast a mount against it; set the camp also against it, and set battering rams against it round about.', '1~05414~ 2~04692~ 6~01129~ 8~01785~ 12~08210~ 14~05550~ 17~05414~ 19~04264~ 24~07760~ [25] 26~03733~ 30~05439~.'),
  (13766, 18, 36, 21, 'Take heed, regard not iniquity: for this hast thou chosen rather than affliction.', '1~08104~, 2~06437~ 4~0205~: 9~0977~ 12~06040~.'),
  (25481, 42, 12, 9, 'But he that denieth me before men shall be denied before the angels of God.', '0~1161~ 3~720~ 4~3165~ 5~1799~ 6~444~ 9~533~ 10~1799~ 12~32~ 14~2316~.'),
  (14564, 19, 41, 13, 'Blessed be the LORD God of Israel from everlasting, and to everlasting. Amen, and Amen.', '0~01288~ [1] 3~03068~ 4~0430~ 6~03478~ 8~05769~, 11~05769~. 12~0543~, 14~0543~.'),
  (24715, 41, 12, 31, 'And the second is like, namely this, Thou shalt love thy neighbour as thyself. There is none other commandment greater than these.', '0~2532~ 2~1208~ [3] 4~3664~, [5] 6~3778~ 7~846~,* 10~25~ 11~4675~ 12~4139~ 13~5613~ 14~4572~. 16~2076~ 17~3756~ 18~243~ 19~1785~ 20~3187~ 22~5130~.'),
  (9342, 11, 17, 17, 'And it came to pass after these things, that the son of the woman, the mistress of the house, fell sick; and his sickness was so sore, that there was no breath left in him.', '&para; 5~0310~ 7~01697~, [8] 10~01121~ 13~0802~, 15~01172~ 18~01004~, 20~02470~; 23~02483~ 25~03966~ 26~02389~, 31~05397~ 32~03498~'),
  (1190, 1, 40, 13, 'Yet within three days shall Pharaoh lift up thine head, and restore thee unto thy place: and thou shalt deliver Pharaoh''s cup into his hand, after the former manner when thou wast his butler.', '0~05750~ 2~07969~ 3~03117~ 5~06547~ 7~05375~ 9~07218~, 11~07725~ 15~03653~: 19~05414~ 20~06547~ 21~03563~ 24~03027~, 27~07223~ 28~04941~ 33~08248~.'),
  (16342, 19, 145, 13, 'Thy kingdom is an everlasting kingdom, and thy dominion endureth throughout all generations.', '1~04438~ [2] 4~05769~ 5~04438~, 8~04475~ [9] 11~01755~ 12~01755~.'),
  (29228, 49, 1, 6, 'To the praise of the glory of his grace, wherein he hath made us accepted in the beloved.', '0~1519~ 2~1868~ 5~1391~ 7~846~ 8~5485~, 9~3739~ 10~1722~ 12~5487~ 13~2248~ 14~5487~ 15~1722~ 17~25~.'),
  (12835, 17, 8, 9, 'Then were the king''s scribes called at that time in the third month, that is, the month Sivan, on the three and twentieth day thereof; and it was written according to all that Mordecai commanded unto the Jews, and to the lieutenants, and the deputies and rulers of the provinces which are from India unto Ethiopia, an hundred twenty and seven provinces, unto every province according to the writing thereof, and unto every people after their language, and to the Jews according to their writing, and according to their language.', '3~04428~ 4~05608~ 5~07121~ 8~06256~ 11~07992~ 12~02320~, [14] 16~02320~ 17~05510~, 20~07969~ 22~06242~ [23] 28~03789~ 33~04782~ 34~06680~ 37~03064~, 41~0323~, 44~06346~ 46~08269~ 49~04082~ [51] 53~01912~ 55~03568~, 57~03967~ 58~06242~ 60~07651~ 61~04082~, 64~04082~ 68~03791~ 73~05971~ 76~03956~, 80~03064~ 84~03791~, 89~03956~.'),
  (29579, 52, 1, 3, 'Remembering without ceasing your work of faith, and labour of love, and patience of hope in our Lord Jesus Christ, in the sight of God and our Father;', '0~3421~ 2~89~ 3~5216~ 4~2041~ 6~4102~, 7~2532~ 8~2873~ 10~26~, 11~2532~ 12~5281~ 14~1680~ 16~2257~ 17~2962~ 18~2424~ 19~5547~, 22~1715~ 24~2316~ 25~2532~ 26~2257~ 27~3962~;'),
  (14033, 19, 9, 3, 'When mine enemies are turned back, they shall fall and perish at thy presence.', '2~0341~ 4~07725~ 5~0268~, 8~03782~ 10~06~ 13~06440~.'),
  (6693, 7, 6, 32, 'Therefore on that day he called him Jerubbaal, saying, Let Baal plead against him, because he hath thrown down his altar.', '3~03117~ 5~07121~ 7~03378~, 8~0559~, 10~01168~ 11~07378~ 18~05422~ 20~04196~.'),
  (11664, 14, 22, 11, 'But Jehoshabeath, the daughter of the king, took Joash the son of Ahaziah, and stole him from among the king''s sons that were slain, and put him and his nurse in a bedchamber. So Jehoshabeath, the daughter of king Jehoram, the wife of Jehoiada the priest, (for she was the sister of Ahaziah,) hid him from Athaliah, so that she slew him not.', '1~03090~, 3~01323~ 6~04428~, 7~03947~ 8~03101~ 10~01121~ 12~0274~, 14~01589~ 17~08432~ 19~04428~ 20~01121~ 23~04191~, 25~05414~ 29~03243~ 32~04296~ 33~02315~.* 35~03090~, 37~01323~ 39~04428~ 40~03088~, 42~0802~ 44~03077~ 46~03548~, 51~0269~ 53~0274~,) 54~05641~ 56~06440~ 57~06271~, 61~04191~'),
  (29924, 56, 1, 16, 'They profess that they know God; but in works they deny him, being abominable, and disobedient, and unto every good work reprobate.', '1~3670~ 4~1492~ 5~2316~; 6~1161~ 8~2041~ 10~720~ [11] 12~5607~ 13~947~, 14~2532~ 15~545~, 16~2532~ 17~4314~ 18~3956~ 19~18~ 20~2041~ 21~96~.'),
  (21170, 26, 28, 4, 'With thy wisdom and with thine understanding thou hast gotten thee riches, and hast gotten gold and silver into thy treasures:', '2~02451~ 6~08394~ 9~06213~ 11~02428~, 14~06213~ 15~02091~ 17~03701~ 20~0214~:'),
  (6137, 6, 12, 1, 'Now these are the kings of the land, which the children of Israel smote, and possessed their land on the other side Jordan toward the rising of the sun, from the river Arnon unto mount Hermon, and all the plain on the east:', '&para; [2] 4~04428~ 7~0776~, 10~01121~ 12~03478~ 13~05221~, 15~03423~ 17~0776~ 21~05676~ 22~03383~ 25~04217~ 28~08121~, 31~05158~ 32~0769~ 34~02022~ 35~02768~, 39~06160~ 42~04217~:'),
  (27137, 44, 7, 5, 'And he gave him none inheritance in it, no, not so much as to set his foot on: yet he promised that he would give it to him for a possession, and to his seed after him, when as yet he had no child.', '0~2532~ 2~1325~ 3~846~ 4~3756~ 5~2817~ 6~1722~ 7~846~, 9~3761~ [10 12] 14~968~ 16~4228~ 17~968~: 18~2532~ 20~1861~ 24~1325~ 25~846~ 27~846~ 28~1519~ 30~2697~, 31~2532~ 33~846~ 34~4690~ 35~3326~ 36~846~, [38 39] 40~846~ 41~5607~ 42~3756~ 43~5043~.'),
  (18395, 23, 37, 34, 'By the way that he came, by the same shall he return, and shall not come into this city, saith the LORD.', '2~01870~ 5~0935~, 11~07725~, 15~0935~ 18~05892~, 19~05002~ 21~03068~.'),
  (1959, 2, 16, 7, 'And in the morning, then ye shall see the glory of the LORD; for that he heareth your murmurings against the LORD: and what are we, that ye murmur against us?', '3~01242~, 7~07200~ 9~03519~ 12~03068~; 16~08085~ 18~08519~ 21~03068~: [24] 25~05168~, 28~03885~'),
  (21203, 26, 29, 11, 'No foot of man shall pass through it, nor foot of beast shall pass through it, neither shall it be inhabited forty years.', '1~07272~ 3~0120~ 6~05674~ 9~07272~ 11~0929~ 14~05674~ 20~03427~ 21~0705~ 22~08141~.'),
  (28048, 45, 4, 10, 'How was it then reckoned? when he was in circumcision, or in uncircumcision? Not in circumcision, but in uncircumcision.', '0~4459~ 2~3049~ 3~3767~ 4~3049~? 7~5607~ 8~1722~ 9~4061~, 10~2228~ 11~1722~ 12~203~? 13~3756~ 14~1722~ 15~4061~, 16~235~ 17~1722~ 18~203~.'),
  (22491, 30, 8, 1, 'Thus hath the Lord GOD shewed unto me: and behold a basket of summer fruit.', '&para; 3~0136~ 4~03069~ 5~07200~ 11~03619~ 14~07019~.'),
  (18397, 23, 37, 36, 'Then the angel of the LORD went forth, and smote in the camp of the Assyrians a hundred and fourscore and five thousand: and when they arose early in the morning, behold, they were all dead corpses.', '2~04397~ 5~03068~ 7~03318~, 9~05221~ 12~04264~ 15~0804~ 17~03967~ 19~08084~ 21~02568~ 22~0505~: 27~07925~ 30~01242~, [33] 35~04191~ 36~06297~.'),
  (24335, 41, 4, 2, 'And he taught them many things by parables, and said unto them in his doctrine,', '0~2532~ 2~1321~ 3~846~ 5~4183~ 6~1722~ 7~3850~, 8~2532~ 9~3004~ 11~846~ 12~1722~ 13~846~ 14~1322~,'),
  (27996, 45, 2, 18, 'And knowest his will, and approvest the things that are more excellent, being instructed out of the law;', '0~2532~ 1~1097~ [2] 3~2307~, 4~2532~ 5~1381~ 11~1308~, 13~2727~ 15~1537~ 17~3551~;'),
  (12662, 16, 12, 29, 'Also from the house of Gilgal, and out of the fields of Geba and Azmaveth: for the singers had builded them villages round about Jerusalem.', '3~01004~ 5~01537~ 6~01019~,* 11~07704~ 13~01387~ 15~05820~: 18~07891~ 20~01129~ 22~02691~ 24~05439~ 25~03389~.'),
  (17656, 22, 8, 7, 'Many waters cannot quench love, neither can the floods drown it: if a man would give all the substance of his house for love, it would utterly be contemned.', '0~07227~ 1~04325~ 2~03201~ 3~03518~ 4~0160~, 8~05104~ 9~07857~ [12] 13~0376~ 15~05414~ 18~01952~ 21~01004~ 23~0160~, 26~0936~ 28~0936~.'),
  (21667, 26, 46, 3, 'Likewise the people of the land shall worship at the door of this gate before the LORD in the sabbaths and in the new moons.', '2~05971~ 5~0776~ 7~07812~ 10~06607~ 13~08179~ 14~06440~ 16~03068~ 19~07676~ 24~02320~.'),
  (768, 1, 27, 37, 'And Isaac answered and said unto Esau, Behold, I have made him thy lord, and all his brethren have I given to him for servants; and with corn and wine have I sustained him: and what shall I do now unto thee, my son?', '1~03327~ 2~06030~ 4~0559~ 6~06215~, 10~07760~ 13~01376~, 17~0251~ 20~05414~ 24~05650~; 27~01715~ 29~08492~ 32~05564~ 38~06213~ 39~0645~ 43~01121~?'),
  (8436, 10, 16, 3, 'And the king said, And where is thy master''s son? And Ziba said unto the king, Behold, he abideth at Jerusalem: for he said, To day shall the house of Israel restore me the kingdom of my father.', '2~04428~ 3~0559~, [6] 8~0113~ 9~01121~? 11~06717~ 12~0559~ 15~04428~, 18~03427~ 20~03389~: 23~0559~, 25~03117~ 28~01004~ 30~03478~ 31~07725~ 34~04468~ 37~01~.'),
  (27337, 44, 11, 14, 'Who shall tell thee words, whereby thou and all thy house shall be saved.', '0~3739~ 2~2980~ 3~4571~ 4~4314~* 5~4487~, 6~3739~ 7~1722~* 8~4771~ 9~2532~ 10~3956~ 11~4675~ 12~3624~ 15~4982~.'),
  (23274, 40, 5, 30, 'And if thy right hand offend thee, cut it off, and cast it from thee: for it is profitable for thee that one of thy members should perish, and not that thy whole body should be cast into hell.', '0~2532~ 1~1487~ 2~4675~ 3~1188~ 4~5495~ 5~4624~ 6~4571~, 7~1581~ 8~846~ 9~1581~, 10~2532~ 11~906~ [12] 13~575~ 14~4675~: 15~1063~ 18~4851~ 20~4671~ 21~2443~ 22~1520~ 24~4675~ 25~3196~ 27~622~, 28~2532~ 29~3361~ [30] 31~4675~ 32~3650~ 33~4983~ 36~906~ 37~1519~ 38~1067~.'),
  (5057, 5, 4, 47, 'And they possessed his land, and the land of Og king of Bashan, two kings of the Amorites, which were on this side Jordan toward the sun rising;', '2~03423~ 4~0776~, 7~0776~ 9~05747~ 10~04428~ 12~01316~, 13~08147~ 14~04428~ 17~0567~, [19] 22~05676~ 23~03383~ 26~08121~ 27~04217~;*'),
  (27483, 44, 15, 25, 'It seemed good unto us, being assembled with one accord, to send chosen men unto you with our beloved Barnabas and Paul,', '2~1380~ 4~2254~, 6~1096~ 9~3661~, 11~3992~ 12~1586~ 13~435~ 14~4314~ 15~5209~ 16~4862~ 17~2257~ 18~27~ 19~921~ 20~2532~ 21~3972~,'),
  (4470, 4, 24, 19, 'Out of Jacob shall come he that shall have dominion, and shall destroy him that remaineth of the city.', '2~03290~ 9~07287~, 12~06~ 15~08300~ 18~05892~.'),
  (14437, 19, 35, 18, 'I will give thee thanks in the great congregation: I will praise thee among much people.', '4~03034~ 7~07227~ 8~06951~: 11~01984~ 14~06099~ 15~05971~.'),
  (27621, 44, 19, 20, 'So mightily grew the word of God and prevailed.', '0~3779~ 1~2904~ 2~2596~* 3~837~ 5~3056~ 7~2962~ 8~2532~ 9~2480~.'),
  (26211, 43, 4, 40, 'So when the Samaritans were come unto him, they besought him that he would tarry with them: and he abode there two days.', '0~3767~ 1~5613~ 3~4541~ 5~2064~ 6~4314~ 7~846~, 9~2065~ 10~846~ 14~3306~ 15~3844~ 16~846~: 17~2532~ 19~3306~ 20~1563~ 21~1417~ 22~2250~.'),
  (6001, 6, 7, 19, 'And Joshua said unto Achan, My son, give, I pray thee, glory to the LORD God of Israel, and make confession unto him; and tell me now what thou hast done; hide it not from me.', '1~03091~ 2~0559~ 4~05912~, 6~01121~, 7~07760~, 11~03519~ 14~03068~ 15~0430~ 17~03478~, 19~05414~ 20~08426~ 24~05046~ 30~06213~; 31~03582~ [32]'),
  (7031, 7, 18, 31, 'And they set them up Micah''s graven image, which he made, all the time that the house of God was in Shiloh.', '4~07760~ 5~04318~ 7~06459~, 10~06213~, 13~03117~ 16~01004~ 18~0430~ 21~07887~.'),
  (882, 1, 31, 5, 'And said unto them, I see your father''s countenance, that it is not toward me as before; but the God of my father hath been with me.', '1~0559~ 5~07200~ 7~01~ 8~06440~, [11] 15~08543~ 16~08032~; 19~0430~ 22~01~ 24~01961~'),
  (13027, 18, 7, 10, 'He shall return no more to his house, neither shall his place know him any more.', '2~07725~ 7~01004~, 11~04725~ 12~05234~'),
  (21848, 27, 4, 2, 'I thought it good to shew the signs and wonders that the high God hath wrought toward me.', '1~06925~ 3~08232~ 5~02324~ 7~0852~ 9~08540~ 12~05943~ 13~0426~ 15~05648~ 16~05974~'),
  (3138, 3, 14, 22, 'And two turtledoves, or two young pigeons, such as he is able to get; and the one shall be a sin offering, and the other a burnt offering.', '1~08147~ 2~08449~, 4~08147~ 5~01121~ 6~03123~, 13~05381~ 14~03027~;* 17~0259~ 22~02403~, 25~0259~ 28~05930~.'),
  (28889, 47, 4, 14, 'Knowing that he which raised up the Lord Jesus shall raise up us also by Jesus, and shall present us with you.', '0~1492~ 1~3754~ 5~1453~ 7~2962~ 8~2424~ 11~1453~ 12~2248~ 13~2532~ 14~1223~ 15~2424~, 16~2532~ 18~3936~ [19] 20~4862~ 21~5213~.'),
  (26622, 43, 12, 27, 'Now is my soul troubled; and what shall I say? Father, save me from this hour: but for this cause came I unto this hour.', '&para; 0~3568~ 1~5015~ 2~3450~ 3~5590~ 4~5015~; 5~2532~ 6~5101~ 9~2036~? 10~3962~, 11~4982~ 12~3165~ 13~1537~ 14~5026~ 15~5610~: 16~235~ 18~5124~ 19~1223~ 21~2064~ 22~1519~ 23~5026~ 24~5610~.'),
  (15249, 19, 82, 7, 'But ye shall die like men, and fall like one of the princes.', '0~0403~ 3~04191~ 5~0120~, 7~05307~ 9~0259~ 12~08269~.'),
  (23200, 40, 2, 21, 'And he arose, and took the young child and his mother, and came into the land of Israel.', '0~1161~ 2~1453~, 4~3880~ 7~3813~ 8~2532~ 9~846~ 10~3384~, 11~2532~ 12~2064~ 13~1519~ 15~1093~ 17~2474~.'),
  (12464, 16, 7, 35, 'The children of Harim, three hundred and twenty.', '1~01121~ 3~02766~, 4~07969~ 5~03967~ 7~06242~.'),
  (30672, 63, 1, 11, 'For he that biddeth him God speed is partaker of his evil deeds.', '0~1063~ 3~3004~ 4~846~ 6~5463~ 8~2841~ 10~846~ 11~4190~ 12~2041~.'),
  (2529, 2, 34, 28, 'And he was there with the LORD forty days and forty nights; he did neither eat bread, nor drink water. And he wrote upon the tables the words of the covenant, the ten commandments.', '&para; 6~03068~ 7~0705~ 8~03117~ 10~0705~ 11~03915~; 15~0398~ 16~03899~, 18~08354~ 19~04325~. 22~03789~ 25~03871~ 27~01697~ 30~01285~, 32~06235~ 33~01697~.'),
  (21677, 26, 46, 13, 'Thou shalt daily prepare a burnt offering unto the LORD of a lamb of the first year without blemish: thou shalt prepare it every morning.', '2~03117~ 3~06213~ 6~05930~ 9~03068~ [10] 12~03532~ 15~01121~ 16~08141~ 18~08549~: 21~06213~ 23~01242~ 24~01242~.'),
  (3942, 4, 7, 87, 'All the oxen for the burnt offering were twelve bullocks, the rams twelve, the lambs of the first year twelve, with their meat offering: and the kids of the goats for sin offering twelve.', '2~01241~ 6~05930~ [7] 8~06240~ 9~08147~* 10~06499~, 12~0352~ 13~06240~ 14~08147~,* 16~03532~ 19~01121~ 20~08141~ 21~06240~ 22~08147~,* 26~04503~: 29~08163~ 32~05795~ 35~02403~ 36~06240~ 37~08147~.*'),
  (23313, 40, 6, 21, 'For where your treasure is, there will your heart be also.', '0~1063~ 1~3699~ 2~5216~ 3~2344~ 4~2076~, 5~1563~ 6~2071~ 7~5216~ 8~2588~ 9~2071~ 10~2532~.'),
  (29656, 52, 5, 19, 'Quench not the Spirit.', '0~4570~ 1~3361~ 3~4151~.'),
  (24289, 41, 2, 19, 'And Jesus said unto them, Can the children of the bridechamber fast, while the bridegroom is with them? as long as they have the bridegroom with them, they cannot fast.', '0~2532~ 1~2424~ 2~2036~ 4~846~ 5~3361~,* 6~1410~ 8~5207~ 11~3567~ 12~3522~, 13~3739~ 14~1722~ 15~3566~ 16~2076~ 17~3326~ 18~846~? 21~5550~ 22~3745~ 23~2192~ 25~3566~ 26~3326~ 27~1438~, 29~1410~ 30~3756~* 31~3522~.'),
  (1515, 1, 50, 4, 'And when the days of his mourning were past, Joseph spake unto the house of Pharaoh, saying, If now I have found grace in your eyes, speak, I pray you, in the ears of Pharaoh, saying,', '3~03117~ 6~01068~ 8~05674~, 9~03130~ 10~01696~ 13~01004~ 15~06547~, 16~0559~, 21~04672~ 22~02580~ 25~05869~, 26~01696~, 32~0241~ 34~06547~, 35~0559~,'),
  (8147, 10, 5, 8, 'And David said on that day, Whosoever getteth up to the gutter, and smiteth the Jebusites, and the lame and the blind, that are hated of David''s soul, he shall be chief and captain. Wherefore they said, The blind and the lame shall not come into the house.', '1~01732~ 2~0559~ 5~03117~, 8~05060~ 11~06794~, 13~05221~ 15~02983~, 18~06455~ 21~05787~, [22 23] 24~08130~ 26~01732~ 27~05315~, [28 33] 36~0559~, 38~05787~ 41~06455~ 44~0935~ 47~01004~.'),
  (9740, 12, 8, 5, 'And it came to pass, as he was telling the king how he had restored a dead body to life, that, behold, the woman, whose son he had restored to life, cried to the king for her house and for her land. And Gehazi said, My lord, O king, this is the woman, and this is her son, whom Elisha restored to life.', '8~05608~ 10~04428~ 14~02421~ 17~04191~ 19~02421~, 23~0802~, 25~01121~ 30~02421~, 31~06817~ 34~04428~ 37~01004~ 41~07704~. 43~01522~ 44~0559~, 46~0113~, 48~04428~, [50] 52~0802~, [55] 57~01121~, 59~0477~ 62~02421~.'),
  (17853, 23, 9, 15, 'The ancient and honourable, he is the head; and the prophet that teacheth lies, he is the tail.', '1~02205~ 3~05375~ 4~06440~,* 5~01931~ [6] 8~07218~; 11~05030~ 13~03384~ 14~08267~, [16] 18~02180~.'),
  (16597, 20, 7, 13, 'So she caught him, and kissed him, and with an impudent face said unto him,', '2~02388~ 5~05401~ [7] 10~05810~ 11~06440~ 12~0559~'),
  (9009, 11, 8, 16, 'Since the day that I brought forth my people Israel out of Egypt, I chose no city out of all the tribes of Israel to build an house, that my name might be therein; but I chose David to be over my people Israel.', '2~03117~ 6~03318~ 8~05971~ 9~03478~ 12~04714~, 14~0977~ 16~05892~ 21~07626~ 23~03478~ 25~01129~ 27~01004~, 30~08034~ 36~0977~ 37~01732~ 42~05971~ 43~03478~.'),
  (3531, 3, 26, 2, 'Ye shall keep my sabbaths, and reverence my sanctuary: I am the LORD.', '2~08104~ 4~07676~, 6~03372~ 8~04720~: [10] 12~03068~.'),
  (22258, 28, 11, 9, 'I will not execute the fierceness of mine anger, I will not return to destroy Ephraim: for I am God, and not man; the Holy One in the midst of thee: and I will not enter into the city.', '3~06213~ 5~02740~ 8~0639~, 12~07725~ 14~07843~ 15~0669~: [18] 19~0410~, 22~0376~; 25~06918~ 28~07130~ 35~0935~ 38~05892~.'),
  (13181, 18, 13, 19, 'Who is he that will plead with me? for now, if I hold my tongue, I shall give up the ghost.', '[1] [3] 5~07378~ 14~02790~, 20~01478~.'),
  (1618, 2, 4, 12, 'Now therefore go, and I will be with thy mouth, and teach thee what thou shalt say.', '2~03212~, 9~06310~, 11~03384~ 16~01696~.'),
  (24294, 41, 2, 24, 'And the Pharisees said unto him, Behold, why do they on the sabbath day that which is not lawful?', '0~2532~ 2~5330~ 3~3004~ 5~846~, 6~2396~, 7~5101~ 9~4160~ 10~1722~ 13~4521~ 15~3739~ 16~1832~ 17~3756~ 18~1832~?'),
  (17766, 23, 5, 18, 'Woe unto them that draw iniquity with cords of vanity, and sin as it were with a cart rope:', '&para; 0~01945~ 4~04900~ 5~05771~ 7~02256~ 9~07723~, 11~02403~ 17~05699~ 18~05688~:'),
  (23151, 39, 4, 3, 'And ye shall tread down the wicked; for they shall be ashes under the soles of your feet in the day that I shall do this, saith the LORD of hosts.', '4~06072~ 6~07563~; 11~0665~ 14~03709~ 17~07272~ 20~03117~ 24~06213~ [25] 26~0559~ 28~03068~ 30~06635~.'),
  (26248, 43, 5, 23, 'That all men should honour the Son, even as they honour the Father. He that honoureth not the Son honoureth not the Father which hath sent him.', '0~2443~ 1~3956~ [2] 4~5091~ 6~5207~, 8~2531~ 10~5091~ 12~3962~. 15~5091~ 16~3361~ 18~5207~ 19~5091~ 20~3756~ 22~3962~ 23~3588~ 25~3992~ 26~846~.'),
  (5159, 5, 8, 16, 'Who fed thee in the wilderness with manna, which thy fathers knew not, that he might humble thee, and that he might prove thee, to do thee good at thy latter end;', '1~0398~ 5~04057~ 7~04478~, 10~01~ 11~03045~ 16~06031~ 22~05254~ 27~03190~ 31~0319~;'),
  (25765, 42, 19, 20, 'And another came, saying, Lord, behold, here is thy pound, which I have kept laid up in a napkin:', '0~2532~ 1~2087~ 2~2064~, 3~3004~, 4~2962~, 5~2400~, [6 7] 8~4675~ 9~3414~, 10~3739~ 12~2192~ 15~606~ 16~1722~ 18~4676~:'),
  (9935, 12, 15, 2, 'Sixteen years old was he when he began to reign, and he reigned two and fifty years in Jerusalem. And his mother''s name was Jecholiah of Jerusalem.', '0~06240~ 1~08337~* 2~08141~ 3~01121~ 10~04427~, 13~04427~ 14~08147~ 16~02572~ 17~08141~ 19~03389~. 22~0517~ 23~08034~ [24] 25~03203~ 27~03389~.'),
  (29446, 50, 3, 9, 'And be found in him, not having mine own righteousness, which is of the law, but that which is through the faith of Christ, the righteousness which is of God by faith:', '&para; 0~2532~ 2~2147~ 3~1722~ 4~846~, 5~3361~ 6~2192~ 8~1699~ 9~1343~, 10~3588~ 12~1537~ 14~3551~, 15~235~ 17~3588~ 19~1223~ 21~4102~ 23~5547~, 25~1343~ 26~3588~ 28~1537~ 29~2316~ 30~1909~ 31~4102~:'),
  (30966, 66, 15, 4, 'Who shall not fear thee, O Lord, and glorify thy name? for thou only art holy: for all nations shall come and worship before thee; for thy judgments are made manifest.', '0~5101~ 1~5399~ 2~3364~ 3~5399~ 4~4571~, 6~2962~, 7~2532~ 8~1392~ 9~4675~ 10~3686~? 11~3754~ [12] 13~3441~ [14] 15~3741~: 16~3754~ 17~3956~ 18~1484~ 20~2240~ 21~2532~ 22~4352~ 23~1799~ 24~4675~; 25~3754~ 26~4675~ 27~1345~ 30~5319~.'),
  (26851, 43, 19, 11, 'Jesus answered, Thou couldest have no power at all against me, except it were given thee from above: therefore he that delivered me unto thee hath the greater sin.', '0~2424~ 1~611~, 4~2192~ 5~3756~ 6~1849~ [7 8] 9~2596~ 10~3762~* 11~1700~, 12~1508~ 14~2258~ 15~1325~ 16~4671~ 18~509~: 19~1223~ 20~5124~ 22~3860~ 23~3165~ 25~4671~ 26~2192~ 28~3187~ 29~266~.'),
  (23783, 40, 19, 11, 'But he said unto them, All men cannot receive this saying, save they to whom it is given.', '0~1161~ 2~2036~ 4~846~, 5~3956~ [6] 7~3756~ 8~5562~ 9~5126~ 10~3056~, 11~235~ [12] 14~3739~ 17~1325~.'),
  (16179, 19, 133, 1, 'A Song of degrees of David. Behold, how good and how pleasant it is for brethren to dwell together in unity!', '&para; [0 1~07892~ 3~04609~ 5] 5~01732~ 8~02896~ 11~05273~ [12 13] 15~0251~ 17~03427~ 18~03162~ 20~03162~!'),
  (29946, 56, 3, 7, 'That being justified by his grace, we should be made heirs according to the hope of eternal life.', '0~2443~ 3~1344~ 4~1565~ 5~5485~, 9~1096~ 10~2818~ 12~2596~ 14~1680~ 16~166~ 17~2222~.'),
  (6408, 6, 21, 20, 'And the families of the children of Kohath, the Levites which remained of the children of Kohath, even they had the cities of their lot out of the tribe of Ephraim.', '2~04940~ 5~01121~ 7~06955~, 9~03881~ 11~03498~ 14~01121~ 16~06955~, 21~05892~ 24~01486~ 28~04294~ 30~0669~.'),
  (30710, 65, 1, 22, 'And of some have compassion, making a difference:', '0~3303~ 1~2532~ 2~3739~ 4~1653~, 7~1252~:'),
  (14733, 19, 53, 5, 'There were they in great fear, where no fear was: for God hath scattered the bones of him that encampeth against thee: thou hast put them to shame, because God hath despised them.', '4~06343~ 5~06342~, [6] 8~06343~ 11~0430~ 13~06340~ 15~06106~ 19~02583~ [20] [25] 27~0954~, 29~0430~ 31~03988~'),
  (26910, 43, 20, 27, 'Then saith he to Thomas, Reach hither thy finger, and behold my hands; and reach hither thy hand, and thrust it into my side: and be not faithless, but believing.', '0~1534~ 2~3004~ 4~2381~, 5~5342~ 6~5602~ 7~4675~ 8~1147~, 9~2532~ 10~1492~ 11~3450~ 12~5495~; 13~2532~ 15~5342~ 16~4675~ 17~5495~, 18~2532~ 19~906~ [20] 21~1519~ 22~3450~ 23~4125~: 24~2532~ 25~1096~ 26~3361~ 27~571~, 28~235~ 29~4103~.'),
  (19118, 24, 6, 20, 'To what purpose cometh there to me incense from Sheba, and the sweet cane from a far country? your burnt offerings are not acceptable, nor your sacrifices sweet unto me.', '3~0935~ 7~03828~ 9~07614~, 12~02896~ 13~07070~ 16~04801~ 17~0776~? 20~05930~ [21] 23~07522~, 26~02077~ 27~06149~'),
  (25084, 42, 4, 9, 'And he brought him to Jerusalem, and set him on a pinnacle of the temple, and said unto him, If thou be the Son of God, cast thyself down from hence:', '0~2532~ 2~71~ 3~846~ 4~1519~ 5~2419~, 6~2532~ 7~2476~ 8~846~ 9~1909~ 11~4419~ 14~2411~, 15~2532~ 16~2036~ 18~846~, 19~1487~ 21~1488~ 23~5207~ 25~2316~, 26~906~ 27~4572~ 28~2736~ 30~1782~:'),
  (5050, 5, 4, 40, 'Thou shalt keep therefore his statutes, and his commandments, which I command thee this day, that it may go well with thee, and with thy children after thee, and that thou mayest prolong thy days upon the earth, which the LORD thy God giveth thee, for ever.', '2~08104~ 5~02706~, 8~04687~, 11~06680~ 14~03117~, 19~03190~ 25~01121~ 26~0310~ 32~0748~ [33] 34~03117~ 37~0127~, 40~03068~ 42~0430~ 43~05414~'),
  (19811, 24, 34, 1, 'The word which came unto Jeremiah from the LORD, when Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, and all his army, and all the kingdoms of the earth of his dominion, and all the people, fought against Jerusalem, and against all the cities thereof, saying,', '&para; 1~01697~ 5~03414~ 8~03068~, 10~05019~ 11~04428~ 13~0894~, 17~02428~, 21~04467~ 24~0776~ 27~04475~ 28~03027~,* 32~05971~, 33~03898~ 35~03389~, 40~05892~ 42~0559~,'),
  (10717, 13, 11, 36, 'Hepher the Mecherathite, Ahijah the Pelonite,', '0~02660~ 2~04382~, 3~0281~ 5~06397~,'),
  (1760, 2, 9, 13, 'And the LORD said unto Moses, Rise up early in the morning, and stand before Pharaoh, and say unto him, Thus saith the LORD God of the Hebrews, Let my people go, that they may serve me.', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~04872~, 8~07925~ 11~01242~, 13~03320~ 14~06440~ 15~06547~, 17~0559~ 21~0559~ 23~03068~ 24~0430~ 27~05680~, 30~05971~ 31~07971~, 35~05647~'),
  (16375, 19, 147, 15, 'He sendeth forth his commandment upon earth: his word runneth very swiftly.', '2~07971~ 4~0565~ [5] 6~0776~: 8~01697~ 9~07323~ 11~04120~.'),
  (4134, 4, 14, 21, 'But as truly as I live, all the earth shall be filled with the glory of the LORD.', '[1] 2~0199~ [3] 5~02416~, 8~0776~ 11~04390~ 14~03519~ 17~03068~.'),
  (11818, 14, 29, 18, 'Then they went in to Hezekiah the king, and said, We have cleansed all the house of the LORD, and the altar of burnt offering, with all the vessels thereof, and the shewbread table, with all the vessels thereof.', '2~0935~ 3~06441~ 5~02396~ 7~04428~, 9~0559~, 12~02891~ 15~01004~ 18~03068~, 21~04196~ 24~05930~, 28~03627~ 32~04635~ 33~07979~, 37~03627~');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (428, 1, 17, 27, 'And all the men of his house, born in the house, and bought with money of the stranger, were circumcised with him.', '3~0582~ 6~01004~, 7~03211~ 10~01004~, 12~04736~ 14~03701~ 17~05236~ 18~01121~,* 20~04135~'),
  (59, 1, 3, 3, 'But of the fruit of the tree which is in the midst of the garden, God hath said, Ye shall not eat of it, neither shall ye touch it, lest ye die.', '3~06529~ 6~06086~ [8] 11~08432~ 14~01588~, 15~0430~ 17~0559~, 21~0398~ 27~05060~ 29~06435~ 31~04191~.'),
  (4034, 4, 11, 5, 'We remember the fish, which we did eat in Egypt freely; the cucumbers, and the melons, and the leeks, and the onions, and the garlic:', '1~02142~ 3~01710~, 7~0398~ 9~04714~ 10~02600~; 12~07180~, 15~020~, 18~02682~, 21~01211~, 24~07762~:'),
  (11554, 14, 18, 3, 'And Ahab king of Israel said unto Jehoshaphat king of Judah, Wilt thou go with me to Ramothgilead? And he answered him, I am as thou art, and my people as thy people; and we will be with thee in the war.', '1~0256~ 2~04428~ 4~03478~ 5~0559~ 7~03092~ 8~04428~ 10~03063~, 13~03212~ 17~01568~ 18~07433?~* 21~0559~ [24] [27] 30~05971~ 33~05971~; [35 37] 42~04421~.'),
  (26474, 43, 9, 19, 'And they asked them, saying, Is this your son, who ye say was born blind? how then doth he now see?', '0~2532~ 2~2065~ 3~846~, 4~3004~, 5~2076~ 6~3778~ 7~5216~ 8~5207~, 9~3739~ 10~5210~ 11~3004~ 12~3754~* 14~1080~ 15~5185~? 16~4459~ 17~3767~ 19~991~ 20~737~ 21~991~?'),
  (29530, 51, 2, 20, 'Wherefore if ye be dead with Christ from the rudiments of the world, why, as though living in the world, are ye subject to ordinances,', '0~3767~ 1~1487~ 4~599~ 5~4862~ 6~5547~ 7~575~ 9~4747~ 12~2889~, 13~5101~, 15~5613~ 16~2198~ 17~1722~ 19~2889~, 24~1379~,'),
  (4621, 4, 29, 7, 'And ye shall have on the tenth day of this seventh month an holy convocation; and ye shall afflict your souls: ye shall not do any work therein:', '6~06218~ [7] 10~07637~ 11~02320~ 13~06944~ 14~04744~; 18~06031~ 20~05315~: 24~06213~ 26~04399~ [27]'),
  (15002, 19, 71, 17, 'O God, thou hast taught me from my youth: and hitherto have I declared thy wondrous works.', '1~0430~, 4~03925~ 8~05271~: 13~05046~ 16~06381~.'),
  (21581, 26, 42, 20, 'He measured it by the four sides: it had a wall round about, five hundred reeds long, and five hundred broad, to make a separation between the sanctuary and the profane place.', '1~04058~ 5~0702~ 6~07307~: 10~02346~ 12~05439~, 13~02568~ 14~03967~ [15] 16~0753~, 18~02568~ 19~03967~ 20~07341~, 24~0914~ 27~06944~ 31~02455~.'),
  (10462, 13, 5, 26, 'And the God of Israel stirred up the spirit of Pul king of Assyria, and the spirit of Tilgathpilneser king of Assyria, and he carried them away, even the Reubenites, and the Gadites, and the half tribe of Manasseh, and brought them unto Halah, and Habor, and Hara, and to the river Gozan, unto this day.', '2~0430~ 4~03478~ 6~05782~ 8~07307~ 10~06322~ 11~04428~ 13~0804~, 16~07307~ 18~08407~ 19~04428~ 21~0804~, 26~01540~, 29~07206~, 32~01425~, 35~02677~ 36~07626~ 38~04519~, 40~0935~ 43~02477~, 45~02249~, 47~02024~, 51~05104~ 52~01470~, 55~03117~.'),
  (5794, 5, 32, 30, 'How should one chase a thousand, and two put ten thousand to flight, except their Rock had sold them, and the LORD had shut them up?', '2~0259~ 3~07291~ 5~0505~, 7~08147~ 9~07233~ 10~0505~ 12~05127~, 13~03808~ 15~06697~ 17~04376~ 18~03588~, 21~03068~ 25~05462~?'),
  (14380, 19, 33, 5, 'He loveth righteousness and judgment: the earth is full of the goodness of the LORD.', '1~0157~ 2~06666~ 4~04941~: 6~0776~ 8~04390~ 11~02617~ 14~03068~.'),
  (23166, 40, 1, 12, 'And after they were brought to Babylon, Jechonias begat Salathiel; and Salathiel begat Zorobabel;', '0~1161~ 1~3326~ 4~3350~ 6~897~, 7~2423~ 8~1080~ 9~4528~; 10~1161~ 11~4528~ 12~1080~ 13~2216~;'),
  (17239, 20, 29, 6, 'In the transgression of an evil man there is a snare: but the righteous doth sing and rejoice.', '&para; 2~06588~ 5~07451~ 6~0376~ [7 8] 10~04170~: 13~06662~ 15~07442~ 17~08056~.'),
  (26426, 43, 8, 30, 'As he spake these words, many believed on him.', '1~846~ 2~2980~ 4~5023~, 5~4183~ 6~4100~ 7~1519~ 8~846~.'),
  (245, 1, 10, 10, 'And the beginning of his kingdom was Babel, and Erech, and Accad, and Calneh, in the land of Shinar.', '2~07225~ 5~04467~ 7~0894~, 9~0751~, 11~0390~, 13~03641~, 16~0776~ 18~08152~.'),
  (8974, 11, 7, 32, 'And under the borders were four wheels; and the axletrees of the wheels were joined to the base: and the height of a wheel was a cubit and half a cubit.', '1~08478~ 3~04526~ [4] 5~0702~ 6~0212~; 9~03027~ 12~0212~ [13 14] 17~04350~: 20~06967~ 22~0259~ 23~0212~ [24] 26~0520~ 28~02677~ 30~0520~.'),
  (26073, 43, 1, 15, 'John bare witness of him, and cried, saying, This was he of whom I spake, He that cometh after me is preferred before me: for he was before me.', '&para; 0~2491~ 2~3140~ 3~4012~ 4~846~, 5~2532~ 6~2896~, 7~3004~, 8~3778~ 10~2258~ 12~3739~ 14~2036~, 17~2064~ 18~3694~ 19~3450~ 21~1096~ 22~1715~ 23~3450~: 24~3754~ 26~2258~ 27~4413~ 28~3450~.'),
  (8381, 10, 14, 18, 'Then the king answered and said unto the woman, Hide not from me, I pray thee, the thing that I shall ask thee. And the woman said, Let my lord the king now speak.', '2~04428~ 3~06030~ 5~0559~ 8~0802~, 9~03582~ 17~01697~ 21~07592~ 25~0802~ 26~0559~, 29~0113~ 31~04428~ 33~01696~.'),
  (20499, 26, 1, 26, 'And above the firmament that was over their heads was the likeness of a throne, as the appearance of a sapphire stone: and upon the likeness of the throne was the likeness as the appearance of a man above upon it.', '&para; 1~04605~ 3~07549~ [5] 8~07218~ [9] 11~01823~ 14~03678~, 17~04758~ 20~05601~ 21~068~: 25~01823~ 28~03678~ [29] 31~01823~ 34~04758~ 37~0120~ 38~04605~'),
  (17572, 22, 2, 9, 'My beloved is like a roe or a young hart: behold, he standeth behind our wall, he looketh forth at the windows, shewing himself through the lattice.', '1~01730~ 3~01819~ 5~06643~ 8~06082~ 9~0354~: 12~05975~ 13~0310~ 15~03796~, 18~07688~ 21~02474~, 22~06692~ 26~02762~.'),
  (15087, 19, 75, 7, 'But God is the judge: he putteth down one, and setteth up another.', '1~0430~ [2] 4~08199~: 7~08213~ 11~07311~'),
  (25498, 42, 12, 26, 'If ye then be not able to do that thing which is least, why take ye thought for the rest?', '0~1487~ 2~3767~ 3~1410~ 4~3777~ 7~1410~ 12~1646~, 13~5101~ 16~3309~ 17~4012~ 19~3062~?'),
  (4325, 4, 20, 9, 'And Moses took the rod from before the LORD, as he commanded him.', '1~04872~ 2~03947~ 4~04294~ 6~06440~ 8~03068~, 11~06680~'),
  (16467, 20, 3, 3, 'Let not mercy and truth forsake thee: bind them about thy neck; write them upon the table of thine heart:', '2~02617~ 4~0571~ 5~05800~ 7~07194~ 11~01621~; 12~03789~ 16~03871~ 19~03820~:'),
  (11347, 14, 7, 15, 'Now mine eyes shall be open, and mine ears attent unto the prayer that is made in this place.', '2~05869~ 5~06605~, 8~0241~ 9~07183~ 12~08605~ [13 15] 18~04725~.'),
  (28353, 45, 16, 1, 'I commend unto you Phebe our sister, which is a servant of the church which is at Cenchrea:', '&para; 0~1161~ 2~4921~ 4~5213~ 5~5402~ 6~2257~ 7~79~, 9~5607~ 11~1249~ 14~1577~ 15~3588~ 17~1722~ 18~2747~:'),
  (6597, 7, 3, 22, 'And the haft also went in after the blade; and the fat closed upon the blade, so that he could not draw the dagger out of his belly; and the dirt came out.', '2~05325~ 5~0935~ 6~0310~ 8~03851~; 11~02459~ 12~05462~ 13~01157~ 15~03851~, 21~08025~ 23~02719~ 27~0990~; 30~06574~ 32~03318~.'),
  (26297, 43, 6, 25, 'And when they had found him on the other side of the sea, they said unto him, Rabbi, when camest thou hither?', '0~2532~ 4~2147~ 5~846~ 9~4008~ 12~2281~, 14~2036~ 16~846~, 17~4461~, 18~4219~ 20~1096~ 21~5602~?'),
  (11738, 14, 25, 25, 'And Amaziah the son of Joash king of Judah lived after the death of Joash son of Jehoahaz king of Israel fifteen years.', '1~0558~ 3~01121~ 5~03101~ 6~04428~ 8~03063~ 9~02421~ 10~0310~ 12~04194~ 14~03101~ 15~01121~ 17~03059~ 18~04428~ 20~03478~ 21~06240~ 22~02568~* 23~08141~.'),
  (15955, 19, 119, 48, 'My hands also will I lift up unto thy commandments, which I have loved; and I will meditate in thy statutes.', '1~03709~ 6~05375~ 9~04687~, 13~0157~; 17~07878~ 20~02706~.'),
  (4631, 4, 29, 17, 'And on the second day ye shall offer twelve young bullocks, two rams, fourteen lambs of the first year without spot:', '3~08145~ 4~03117~ [5 7] 8~06240~ 9~08147~* 10~01241~ 11~01121~* 12~06499~, 13~08147~ 14~0352~, 15~06240~ 16~0702~* 17~03532~ 20~01121~ 21~08141~ 23~08549~:'),
  (29411, 50, 2, 4, 'Look not every man on his own things, but every man also on the things of others.', '0~4648~ 1~3361~ 3~1538~ 7~1438~, 8~235~ 10~1538~ 11~2532~ 14~3588~ 16~2087~.'),
  (5380, 5, 17, 10, 'And thou shalt do according to the sentence, which they of that place which the LORD shall choose shall shew thee; and thou shalt observe to do according to all that they inform thee:', '3~06213~ 7~01697~ 8~06310~,* 13~04725~ 16~03068~ 18~0977~ 20~05046~ 25~08104~ 27~06213~ 33~03384~'),
  (6818, 7, 9, 57, 'And all the evil of the men of Shechem did God render upon their heads: and upon them came the curse of Jotham the son of Jerubbaal.', '3~07451~ 6~0582~ 8~07927~ 10~0430~ 11~07725~ 14~07218~: 18~0935~ 20~07045~ 22~03147~ 24~01121~ 26~03378~.'),
  (22170, 28, 5, 9, 'Ephraim shall be desolate in the day of rebuke: among the tribes of Israel have I made known that which shall surely be.', '0~0669~ 3~08047~ 6~03117~ 8~08433~: 11~07626~ 13~03478~ 17~03045~ 22~0539~.'),
  (16010, 19, 119, 103, 'How sweet are thy words unto my taste! yea, sweeter than honey to my mouth!', '&para; 1~04452~ 4~0565~ 7~02441~! [8 9] 11~01706~ 14~06310~!'),
  (22675, 33, 7, 2, 'The good man is perished out of the earth: and there is none upright among men: they all lie in wait for blood; they hunt every man his brother with a net.', '1~02623~ [2] 4~06~ 8~0776~: [10 11] 13~03477~ 15~0120~: 20~0693~ 22~01818~; 24~06679~ 26~0376~ 28~0251~ 31~02764~.'),
  (21008, 26, 22, 23, 'And the word of the LORD came unto me, saying,', '&para; 2~01697~ 5~03068~ 9~0559~,'),
  (559, 1, 22, 8, 'And Abraham said, My son, God will provide himself a lamb for a burnt offering: so they went both of them together.', '1~085~ 2~0559~, 4~01121~, 5~0430~ 7~07200~ 10~07716~ 14~05930~: 17~03212~ 20~08147~ 21~03162~.'),
  (3495, 3, 25, 21, 'Then I will command my blessing upon you in the sixth year, and it shall bring forth fruit for three years.', '3~06680~ 5~01293~ 10~08345~ 11~08141~, 16~06213~ 17~08393~ 19~07969~ 20~08141~.'),
  (24601, 41, 10, 2, 'And the Pharisees came to him, and asked him, Is it lawful for a man to put away his wife? tempting him.', '0~2532~ 2~5330~ 5~4334~, 7~1905~ 8~846~, 10~1487~ 11~1832~ 14~435~ 17~630~ [18] 19~1135~? 20~3985~ 21~846~.'),
  (25303, 42, 8, 46, 'And Jesus said, Somebody hath touched me: for I perceive that virtue is gone out of me.', '0~1161~ 1~2424~ 2~2036~, 3~5100~ 5~680~ 6~3450~: 7~1063~ 8~1473~ 9~1097~ 11~1411~ 13~1831~ 15~575~ 16~1700~.'),
  (18475, 23, 41, 15, 'Behold, I will make thee a new sharp threshing instrument having teeth: thou shalt thresh the mountains, and beat them small, and shalt make the hills as chaff.', '3~07760~ 6~02319~ 7~02742~ 8~04173~ 10~01167~ 11~06374~: 14~01758~ 16~02022~, [19] 20~01854~, 23~07760~ 25~01389~ 27~04671~.'),
  (4304, 4, 19, 10, 'And he that gathereth the ashes of the heifer shall wash his clothes, and be unclean until the even: and it shall be unto the children of Israel, and unto the stranger that sojourneth among them, for a statute for ever.', '3~0622~ 5~0665~ 8~06510~ 10~03526~ 12~0899~, 15~02930~ 18~06153~: 25~01121~ 27~03478~, 31~01616~ 33~01481~ 34~08432~ 38~02708~ 40~05769~.'),
  (3364, 3, 21, 14, 'A widow, or a divorced woman, or profane, or an harlot, these shall he not take: but he shall take a virgin of his own people to wife.', '1~0490~, 5~01644~, 7~02491~, [8] 10~02181~, 15~03947~: 19~03947~ 21~01330~ 25~05971~ 27~0802~.'),
  (11807, 14, 29, 7, 'Also they have shut up the doors of the porch, and put out the lamps, and have not burned incense nor offered burnt offerings in the holy place unto the God of Israel.', '4~05462~ 6~01817~ 9~0197~, 12~03518~ 14~05216~, 18~06999~ 19~07004~ 21~05927~ 23~05930~ 26~06944~ [27] 30~0430~ 32~03478~.'),
  (2685, 2, 39, 16, 'And they made two ouches of gold, and two gold rings; and put the two rings in the two ends of the breastplate.', '2~06213~ 3~08147~ 4~04865~ [5] 6~02091~, 8~08147~ 9~02091~ 10~02885~; 12~05414~ 14~08147~ 15~02885~ 18~08147~ 19~07098~ 22~02833~.'),
  (13183, 18, 13, 21, 'Withdraw thine hand far from me: and let not thy dread make me afraid.', '0~07368~ 2~03709~ 3~07368~ 10~0367~ 13~01204~.'),
  (9363, 11, 18, 14, 'And now thou sayest, Go, tell thy lord, Behold, Elijah is here: and he shall slay me.', '3~0559~, 4~03212~, 5~0559~ 7~0113~, 9~0452~ [10 11] 15~02026~'),
  (21769, 27, 2, 2, 'Then the king commanded to call the magicians, and the astrologers, and the sorcerers, and the Chaldeans, for to shew the king his dreams. So they came and stood before the king.', '2~04428~ 3~0559~ 5~07121~ 7~02748~, 10~0825~, 13~03784~, 16~03778~, 19~05046~ 21~04428~ 23~02472~. 26~0935~ 28~05975~ 29~06440~ 31~04428~.'),
  (10185, 12, 23, 12, 'And the altars that were on the top of the upper chamber of Ahaz, which the kings of Judah had made, and the altars which Manasseh had made in the two courts of the house of the LORD, did the king beat down, and brake them down from thence, and cast the dust of them into the brook Kidron.', '2~04196~ [4] 7~01406~ 11~05944~ 13~0271~, 16~04428~ 18~03063~ 20~06213~, 23~04196~ 25~04519~ 27~06213~ 30~08147~ 31~02691~ 34~01004~ 37~03068~, 40~04428~ 42~05422~, [45] 46~07323~ 50~07993~ 52~06083~ 57~05158~ 58~06939~.'),
  (25967, 42, 23, 18, 'And they cried out all at once, saying, Away with this man, and release unto us Barabbas:', '0~1161~ 3~349~ 6~3826~, 7~3004~, 9~142~ 10~5126~ [11] 12~1161~ 13~630~ 15~2254~ 16~912~:'),
  (13242, 18, 15, 30, 'He shall not depart out of darkness; the flame shall dry up his branches, and by the breath of his mouth shall he go away.', '3~05493~ 6~02822~; 8~07957~ 11~03001~ 13~03127~, 17~07307~ 20~06310~ 24~05493~.'),
  (6989, 7, 17, 2, 'And he said unto his mother, The eleven hundred shekels of silver that were taken from thee, about which thou cursedst, and spakest of also in mine ears, behold, the silver is with me; I took it. And his mother said, Blessed be thou of the LORD, my son.', '2~0559~ 5~0517~, 8~03967~ [9] 9~0505~ 11~03701~ 14~03947~ 20~0422~, 22~0559~ 27~0241~, 30~03701~ [31] 35~03947~ 39~0517~ 40~0559~, 41~01288~ [42 43] 46~03068~, 48~01121~.'),
  (8901, 11, 5, 15, 'And Solomon had threescore and ten thousand that bare burdens, and fourscore thousand hewers in the mountains;', '1~08010~ 5~07657~ 6~0505~ 8~05375~ 9~05449~, 11~08084~ 12~0505~ 13~02672~ 16~02022~;'),
  (31108, 66, 22, 12, 'And, behold, I come quickly; and my reward is with me, to give every man according as his work shall be.', '0~2532~, 1~2400~, 3~2064~ 4~5035~; 5~2532~ 6~3450~ 7~3408~ [8] 9~3326~ 10~1700~, 12~591~ 14~1538~ 16~5613~ 17~846~ 18~2041~ 20~2071~.'),
  (14201, 19, 21, 1, 'To the chief Musician, A Psalm of David. The king shall joy in thy strength, O LORD; and in thy salvation how greatly shall he rejoice!', '&para; [0 3~05329~, 5~04210~ 7] 7~01732~ 9~04428~ 11~08055~ 14~05797~, 16~03068~; 20~03444~ 22~03966~ 25~01523~!'),
  (17344, 21, 2, 2, 'I said of laughter, It is mad: and of mirth, What doeth it?', '1~0559~ 3~07814~, [4 5] 6~01984~: 9~08057~, 10~02090~ 11~06213~'),
  (27990, 45, 2, 12, 'For as many as have sinned without law shall also perish without law: and as many as have sinned in the law shall be judged by the law;', '0~1063~ 3~3745~ 5~264~ 7~460~ 8~622~ 9~2532~ 10~622~ 12~460~: 13~2532~ 16~3745~ 18~264~ 19~1722~ 21~3551~ 24~2919~ 25~1223~ 27~3551~;'),
  (11362, 14, 8, 8, 'But of their children, who were left after them in the land, whom the children of Israel consumed not, them did Solomon make to pay tribute until this day.', '[0] 3~01121~, 6~03498~ 7~0310~ 11~0776~, 14~01121~ 16~03478~ 17~03615~ 21~08010~ 24~05927~ 25~04522~ 28~03117~.'),
  (29112, 48, 2, 15, 'We who are Jews by nature, and not sinners of the Gentiles,', '0~2249~ [1 2] 3~2453~ 5~5449~, 6~2532~ 7~3756~ 8~268~ 9~1537~ 11~1484~,'),
  (7323, 9, 4, 19, 'And his daughter in law, Phinehas'' wife, was with child, near to be delivered: and when she heard the tidings that the ark of God was taken, and that her father in law and her husband were dead, she bowed herself and travailed; for her pains came upon her.', '&para; 4~03618~, 5~06372~ 6~0802~, 9~02030~, [10] 13~03205~: 17~08085~ 19~08052~ 20~0413~ 22~0727~ 24~0430~ 26~03947~, 32~02524~ 35~0376~ 37~04191~, 39~03766~ 42~03205~; 45~06735~ 46~02015~'),
  (25742, 42, 18, 40, 'And Jesus stood, and commanded him to be brought unto him: and when he was come near, he asked him,', '0~1161~ 1~2424~ 2~2476~, 4~2753~ 5~846~ 8~71~ 9~4314~ 10~846~: 11~1161~ 13~846~ 16~1448~, 18~1905~ 19~846~,'),
  (16100, 19, 122, 2, 'Our feet shall stand within thy gates, O Jerusalem.', '1~07272~ 3~05975~ 6~08179~, 8~03389~.'),
  (3997, 4, 10, 4, 'And if they blow but with one trumpet, then the princes, which are heads of the thousands of Israel, shall gather themselves unto thee.', '3~08628~ [4] 6~0259~ [7] 10~05387~, [11 12] 13~07218~ 16~0505~ 18~03478~, 20~03259~'),
  (24501, 41, 7, 27, 'But Jesus said unto her, Let the children first be filled: for it is not meet to take the children''s bread, and to cast it unto the dogs.', '0~1161~ 1~2424~ 2~2036~ 4~846~, 5~863~ 7~5043~ 8~4412~ 10~5526~: 11~1063~ 13~2076~ 14~3756~ 15~2570~ 17~2983~ 19~5043~ 20~740~, 21~2532~ 23~906~ [24] 27~2952~.'),
  (15341, 19, 89, 6, 'For who in the heaven can be compared unto the LORD? who among the sons of the mighty can be likened unto the LORD?', '4~07834~ 7~06186~ 10~03068~? [11] 14~01121~ 17~0410~ 20~01819~ 23~03068~?'),
  (29527, 51, 2, 17, 'Which are a shadow of things to come; but the body is of Christ.', '0~3739~ 1~2076~ 3~4639~ 7~3195~; 8~1161~ 10~4983~ [11] 13~5547~.'),
  (19722, 24, 31, 22, 'How long wilt thou go about, O thou backsliding daughter? for the LORD hath created a new thing in the earth, A woman shall compass a man.', '5~02559~, 8~07728~ 9~01323~? 12~03068~ 14~01254~ 17~02319~ 20~0776~, 22~05347~ 24~05437~ 26~01397~.'),
  (26122, 43, 2, 12, 'After this he went down to Capernaum, he, and his mother, and his brethren, and his disciples: and they continued there not many days.', '&para; 0~3326~ 1~5124~ 4~2597~ 5~1519~ 6~2584~, 7~846~, 8~2532~ 9~846~ 10~3384~, 11~2532~ 12~846~ 13~80~, 14~2532~ 15~846~ 16~3101~: 17~2532~ 19~3306~ 20~1563~ 21~3756~ 22~4183~ 23~2250~.'),
  (11553, 14, 18, 2, 'And after certain years he went down to Ahab to Samaria. And Ahab killed sheep and oxen for him in abundance, and for the people that he had with him, and persuaded him to go up with him to Ramothgilead.', '1~07093~ [2] 3~08141~ 6~03381~ 8~0256~ 10~08111~. 12~0256~ 13~02076~ 14~06629~ 16~01241~ 20~07230~, 24~05971~ [26 27] 31~05496~ 35~05927~ [36 37] 39~01568~ 40~07433~.*'),
  (10914, 13, 18, 16, 'And Zadok the son of Ahitub, and Abimelech the son of Abiathar, were the priests; and Shavsha was scribe;', '1~06659~ 3~01121~ 5~0285~, 7~040~ 9~01121~ 11~054~, [12] 14~03548~; 16~07798~ 18~05608~;'),
  (18552, 23, 44, 10, 'Who hath formed a god, or molten a graven image that is profitable for nothing?', '2~03335~ 4~0410~, 6~05258~ 9~06459~ [10] 12~03276~ 14~01115~?'),
  (25433, 42, 11, 16, 'And others, tempting him, sought of him a sign from heaven.', '0~1161~ 1~2087~, 2~3985~ [3] 4~2212~ 5~3844~ 6~846~ 8~4592~ 9~1537~ 10~3772~.'),
  (10944, 13, 21, 2, 'And David said to Joab and to the rulers of the people, Go, number Israel from Beersheba even to Dan; and bring the number of them to me, that I may know it.', '1~01732~ 2~0559~ 4~03097~ 8~08269~ 11~05971~, 12~03212~, 13~05608~ 14~03478~ 16~0884~ 19~01835~; 21~0935~ 23~04557~ 31~03045~ [32]'),
  (12395, 16, 5, 4, 'There were also that said, We have borrowed money for the king''s tribute, and that upon our lands and vineyards.', '1~03426~ 4~0559~, 7~03867~ 8~03701~ 11~04428~ 12~04060~, [13 15] 17~07704~ 19~03754~.'),
  (19285, 24, 13, 10, 'This evil people, which refuse to hear my words, which walk in the imagination of their heart, and walk after other gods, to serve them, and to worship them, shall even be as this girdle, which is good for nothing.', '1~07451~ 2~05971~, 4~03987~ 6~08085~ 8~01697~, 10~01980~ 13~08307~ 16~03820~, 18~03212~ 19~0310~ 20~0312~ 21~0430~, 23~05647~ 27~07812~ 34~0232~, 37~06743~'),
  (28547, 46, 8, 4, 'As concerning therefore the eating of those things that are offered in sacrifice unto idols, we know that an idol is nothing in the world, and that there is none other God but one.', '&para; 1~4012~ 2~3767~ 4~1035~ 14~1494~, 16~1492~ 17~3754~ 19~1497~ [20] 21~3762~ 22~1722~ 24~2889~, 25~2532~ 26~3754~ [27 28] 29~3762~ 30~2087~ 31~2316~ 32~1508~ 33~1520~.'),
  (4998, 5, 3, 17, 'The plain also, and Jordan, and the coast thereof, from Chinnereth even unto the sea of the plain, even the salt sea, under Ashdothpisgah eastward.', '1~06160~ 4~03383~, 7~01366~ [8] 10~03672~ 14~03220~ 17~06160~, [18] 20~04417~ 21~03220~, 23~0798~ 24~0794~* 25~04217~.'),
  (24018, 40, 24, 51, 'And shall cut him asunder, and appoint him his portion with the hypocrites: there shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth.', '0~2532~ 2~1371~ 3~846~ 4~1371~, 5~2532~ 6~5087~ [7] 8~846~ 9~3313~ 10~3326~ 12~5273~: 13~1563~ 15~2071~ 16~2805~ 17~2532~ 18~1030~ 20~3599~.'),
  (19096, 24, 5, 29, 'Shall I not visit for these things? saith the LORD: shall not my soul be avenged on such a nation as this?', '3~06485~ [6] 7~05002~ 9~03068~: 13~05315~ 15~05358~ 19~01471~'),
  (25952, 42, 23, 3, 'And Pilate asked him, saying, Art thou the King of the Jews? And he answered him and said, Thou sayest it.', '0~1161~ 1~4091~ 2~1905~ 3~846~, 4~3004~, 5~1488~ 6~4771~ 8~935~ 11~2453~? 12~1161~ 14~611~ 15~846~ 17~5346~, 18~4771~ 19~3004~ [20]'),
  (9175, 11, 12, 16, 'So when all Israel saw that the king hearkened not unto them, the people answered the king, saying, What portion have we in David? neither have we inheritance in the son of Jesse: to your tents, O Israel: now see to thine own house, David. So Israel departed unto their tents.', '&para; 0~07725~ 3~03478~ 4~07200~ 7~04428~ 8~08085~ 13~05971~ 14~01697~ 16~04428~, 17~0559~, 19~02506~ 23~01732~? [25 26] 27~05159~ 30~01121~ 32~03448~: 35~0168~, 37~03478~: 39~07200~ 43~01004~, 44~01732~. 46~03478~ 47~03212~ 50~0168~.'),
  (28686, 46, 13, 5, 'Doth not behave itself unseemly, seeketh not her own, is not easily provoked, thinketh no evil;', '0~807~ 1~3756~ 4~807~, 5~2212~ 6~3756~ 8~1438~, 9~3947~ 10~3756~ 12~3947~, 13~3049~ 14~3756~ 15~2556~;'),
  (9088, 11, 10, 1, 'And when the queen of Sheba heard of the fame of Solomon concerning the name of the LORD, she came to prove him with hard questions.', '&para; 3~04436~ 5~07614~ 6~08085~ 9~08088~ 11~08010~ 14~08034~ 17~03068~, 19~0935~ 21~05254~ 25~02420~.'),
  (13751, 18, 36, 6, 'He preserveth not the life of the wicked: but giveth right to the poor.', '4~02421~ 7~07563~: 9~05414~ 10~04941~ 13~06041~.'),
  (20015, 24, 43, 9, 'Take great stones in thine hand, and hide them in the clay in the brickkiln, which is at the entry of Pharaoh''s house in Tahpanhes, in the sight of the men of Judah;', '0~03947~ 1~01419~ 2~068~ 5~03027~, 7~02934~ 11~04423~ 14~04404~, [16] 19~06607~ 21~06547~ 22~01004~ 24~08471~, 27~05869~ 30~0582~ 32~03064~;'),
  (23938, 40, 23, 10, 'Neither be ye called masters: for one is your Master, even Christ.', '0~3366~ 3~2564~ 4~2519~: 5~1063~ 6~1520~ 7~2076~ 8~5216~ 9~2519~, [10] 11~5547~.'),
  (21528, 26, 40, 42, 'And the four tables were of hewn stone for the burnt offering, of a cubit and an half long, and a cubit and an half broad, and one cubit high: whereupon also they laid the instruments wherewith they slew the burnt offering and the sacrifice.', '2~0702~ 3~07979~ [4] 6~01496~ 7~068~ 11~05930~, 14~0520~ 17~02677~ 18~0753~, 21~0520~ 24~02677~ 25~07341~, 27~0259~ 28~0520~ 29~01363~: 33~03240~ 35~03627~ 38~07819~ 41~05930~ 44~02077~.'),
  (3831, 4, 6, 3, 'He shall separate himself from wine and strong drink, and shall drink no vinegar of wine, or vinegar of strong drink, neither shall he drink any liquor of grapes, nor eat moist grapes, or dried.', '2~05144~ [3] 5~03196~ 8~07941~, 11~08354~ 13~02558~ 15~03196~, 17~02558~ 20~07941~, 24~08354~ 26~04952~ 28~06025~, 30~0398~ 31~03892~ 32~06025~, 34~03002~.'),
  (27923, 44, 28, 8, 'And it came to pass, that the father of Publius lay sick of a fever and of a bloody flux: to whom Paul entered in, and prayed, and laid his hands on him, and healed him.', '0~1161~ 4~1096~, 7~3962~ 9~4196~ 10~2621~ 12~4912~ 14~4446~ 15~2532~ 19~1420~: 20~4314~ 21~3739~ 22~3972~ 24~1525~, 25~2532~ 26~4336~, 28~2007~ 30~5495~ 31~2007~ 32~846~, 34~2390~ 35~846~.'),
  (9500, 11, 22, 12, 'And all the prophets prophesied so, saying, Go up to Ramothgilead, and prosper: for the LORD shall deliver it into the king''s hand.', '3~05030~ 4~05012~ 6~0559~, 8~05927~ 10~01568~ 11~07433~,* 13~06743~: 16~03068~ 18~05414~ [19] 22~04428~ 23~03027~.'),
  (17573, 22, 2, 10, 'My beloved spake, and said unto me, Rise up, my love, my fair one, and come away.', '1~01730~ 2~06030~, 4~0559~ 8~06965~, 10~07474~, 13~03303~, 16~03212~.'),
  (29184, 48, 5, 6, 'For in Jesus Christ neither circumcision availeth any thing, nor uncircumcision; but faith which worketh by love.', '0~1063~ 1~1722~ 2~2424~ 3~5547~ 4~3777~ 5~4061~ 6~2480~ 8~5100~, 9~3777~ 10~203~; 11~235~ 12~4102~ 14~1754~ 15~1223~ 16~26~.'),
  (24702, 41, 12, 18, 'Then come unto him the Sadducees, which say there is no resurrection; and they asked him, saying,', '&para; 0~2532~ 1~2064~ 2~4314~ 3~846~ 5~4523~, 6~3748~ 7~3004~ 9~1511~ 10~3361~ 11~386~; 12~2532~ 14~1905~ 15~846~, 16~3004~,'),
