  (30350, 59, 3, 15, 'This wisdom descendeth not from above, but is earthly, sensual, devilish.', '0~3778~ 1~4678~ 2~2076~ 3~2718~* 4~3756~ 6~509~, 7~235~ [8] 9~1919~, 10~5591~, 11~1141~.'),
  (10756, 13, 12, 28, 'And Zadok, a young man mighty of valour, and of his father''s house twenty and two captains.', '1~06659~, 4~05288~ 5~01368~ 7~02428~, 11~01~ 12~01004~ 13~06242~ 15~08147~ 16~08269~.'),
  (7388, 9, 8, 12, 'And he will appoint him captains over thousands, and captains over fifties; and will set them to ear his ground, and to reap his harvest, and to make his instruments of war, and instruments of his chariots.', '3~07760~ 5~08269~ 7~0505~, 9~08269~ 11~02572~; [13 15] 17~02790~ 19~02758~, 22~07114~ 24~07105~, 27~06213~ 29~03627~ 31~04421~, 33~03627~ 36~07393~.'),
  (4916, 5, 1, 18, 'And I commanded you at that time all the things which ye should do.', '2~06680~ 6~06256~ 9~01697~ 13~06213~.'),
  (25986, 42, 23, 37, 'And saying, If thou be the king of the Jews, save thyself.', '0~2532~ 1~3004~, 2~1487~ 3~4771~ 4~1488~ 6~935~ 9~2453~, 10~4982~ 11~4572~.'),
  (1382, 1, 45, 19, 'Now thou art commanded, this do ye; take you wagons out of the land of Egypt for your little ones, and for your wives, and bring your father, and come.', '3~06680~, 5~06213~ 7~03947~ 9~05699~ 13~0776~ 15~04714~ 19~02945~, 23~0802~, 25~05375~ 27~01~, 29~0935~.'),
  (20675, 26, 11, 11, 'This city shall not be your caldron, neither shall ye be the flesh in the midst thereof; but I will judge you in the border of Israel:', '[1] 6~05518~, 12~01320~ 15~08432~ [17] 20~08199~ 24~01366~ 26~03478~:'),
  (7390, 9, 8, 14, 'And he will take your fields, and your vineyards, and your oliveyards, even the best of them, and give them to his servants.', '3~03947~ 5~07704~, 8~03754~, 11~02132~, [12] 14~02896~ [15 16] 18~05414~ [19] 22~05650~.'),
  (30185, 58, 10, 36, 'For ye have need of patience, that, after ye have done the will of God, ye might receive the promise.', '0~1063~ 2~2192~ 3~5532~ 5~5281~, 6~2443~, 10~4160~ 12~2307~ 14~2316~, 17~2865~ 19~1860~.'),
  (14558, 19, 41, 7, 'All that hate me whisper together against me: against me do they devise my hurt.', '2~08130~ 4~03907~ 5~03162~ 12~02803~ 14~07451~.'),
  (29129, 48, 3, 11, 'But that no man is justified by the law in the sight of God, it is evident: for, The just shall live by faith.', '0~1161~ 1~3754~ 3~3762~ 5~1344~ 6~1722~ 8~3551~ 11~3844~ 13~2316~, [14 15] 16~1212~: 17~3754~, 19~1342~ 21~2198~ 22~1537~ 23~4102~.'),
  (31016, 66, 18, 7, 'How much she hath glorified herself, and lived deliciously, so much torment and sorrow give her: for she saith in her heart, I sit a queen, and am no widow, and shall see no sorrow.', '1~3745~ 4~1392~ 5~1438~, 6~2532~ 8~4763~, 10~5118~ 11~929~ 12~2532~ 13~3997~ 14~1325~ 15~846~: 16~3754~ 18~3004~ 19~1722~ 20~846~ 21~2588~, 23~2521~ 25~938~, 26~2532~ 27~1510~ 28~3756~ 29~5503~, 30~2532~ 32~1492~ 33~3364~ 34~3997~.'),
  (17546, 21, 12, 14, 'For God shall bring every work into judgment, with every secret thing, whether it be good, or whether it be evil.', '1~0430~ 3~0935~ 5~04639~ 7~04941~, 11~05956~, [13 14] 15~02896~, [18 19] 20~07451~.'),
  (12467, 16, 7, 38, 'The children of Senaah, three thousand nine hundred and thirty.', '1~01121~ 3~05570~, 4~07969~ 5~0505~ 6~08672~ 7~03967~ 9~07970~.'),
  (19356, 24, 16, 11, 'Then shalt thou say unto them, Because your fathers have forsaken me, saith the LORD, and have walked after other gods, and have served them, and have worshipped them, and have forsaken me, and have not kept my law;', '3~0559~ 8~01~ 10~05800~ 12~05002~ 14~03068~, 17~03212~ 18~0310~ 19~0312~ 20~0430~, 23~05647~ 27~07812~ 31~05800~ 36~08104~ 38~08451~;'),
  (14671, 19, 49, 14, 'Like sheep they are laid in the grave; death shall feed on them; and the upright shall have dominion over them in the morning; and their beauty shall consume in the grave from their dwelling.', '1~06629~ 4~08371~ 7~07585~; 8~04194~ 10~07462~ 15~03477~ 18~07287~ 23~01242~; 26~06697~ 27~06736~* 29~01086~ 32~07585~ 35~02073~.'),
  (27708, 44, 21, 28, 'Crying out, Men of Israel, help: This is the man, that teacheth all men every where against the people, and the law, and this place: and further brought Greeks also into the temple, and hath polluted this holy place.', '1~2896~, 2~435~ 4~2475~, 5~997~: 6~3778~ 7~2076~ 9~444~, 11~1321~ 12~3956~ [13] 15~3837~ 16~2596~ 18~2992~, 19~2532~ 21~3551~, 22~2532~ 23~5126~ 24~5117~: 25~5037~ 26~2089~ 27~1521~ 28~1672~ 29~2532~ 30~1519~ 32~2411~, 33~2532~ 35~2840~ 36~5127~ 37~40~ 38~5117~.'),
  (28589, 46, 10, 6, 'Now these things were our examples, to the intent we should not lust after evil things, as they also lusted.', '&para; 0~1161~ 2~5023~ 3~1096~ 4~2257~ 5~5179~, 8~1519~ 9~2248~ 10~1511~ 11~3361~ 14~2556~ 15~1938~, 16~2531~ 18~2548~ 19~1937~.'),
  (25536, 42, 13, 5, 'I tell you, Nay: but, except ye repent, ye shall all likewise perish.', '1~3004~ 2~5213~, 3~3780~: 4~235~, 5~3362~ 7~3340~, 9~622~ 10~3956~ 11~3668~ 12~622~.'),
  (3602, 3, 27, 27, 'And if it be of an unclean beast, then he shall redeem it according to thine estimation, and shall add a fifth part of it thereto: or if it be not redeemed, then it shall be sold according to thy estimation.', '[2 3] 6~02931~ 7~0929~, 11~06299~ [12] 16~06187~, 19~03254~ 21~02549~ [22] 31~01350~, 36~04376~ 40~06187~.'),
  (19420, 24, 19, 4, 'Because they have forsaken me, and have estranged this place, and have burned incense in it unto other gods, whom neither they nor their fathers have known, nor the kings of Judah, and have filled this place with the blood of innocents;', '3~05800~ 7~05234~ 9~04725~, 13~06999~ 17~0312~ 18~0430~, 24~01~ 26~03045~, 29~04428~ 31~03063~, 34~04390~ 36~04725~ 39~01818~ 41~05355~;'),
  (258, 1, 10, 23, 'And the children of Aram; Uz, and Hul, and Gether, and Mash.', '2~01121~ 4~0758~; 5~05780~, 7~02343~, 9~01666~, 11~04851~.'),
  (1583, 2, 2, 24, 'And God heard their groaning, and God remembered his covenant with Abraham, with Isaac, and with Jacob.', '1~0430~ 2~08085~ 4~05009~, 6~0430~ 7~02142~ 9~01285~ 11~085~, 13~03327~, 16~03290~.'),
  (15013, 19, 72, 4, 'He shall judge the poor of the people, he shall save the children of the needy, and shall break in pieces the oppressor.', '2~08199~ 4~06041~ 7~05971~, 10~03467~ 12~01121~ 15~034~, 20~01792~ 22~06231~.'),
  (2140, 2, 22, 22, 'Ye shall not afflict any widow, or fatherless child.', '3~06031~ 5~0490~, 8~03490~.'),
  (14562, 19, 41, 11, 'By this I know that thou favourest me, because mine enemy doth not triumph over me.', '3~03045~ 6~02654~ 10~0341~ 13~07321~'),
  (7203, 8, 4, 6, 'And the kinsman said, I cannot redeem it for myself, lest I mar mine own inheritance: redeem thou my right to thyself; for I cannot redeem it.', '2~01350~ 3~0559~, 5~03201~ 6~01350~ [7] 12~07843~ 15~05159~: 16~01350~ 19~01353~ 24~03201~ 25~01350~ [26]'),
  (21799, 27, 2, 32, 'This image''s head was of fine gold, his breast and his arms of silver, his belly and his thighs of brass,', '1~06755~ 2~07217~ [3] 5~02869~ 6~01722~, 8~02306~ 11~01872~ 13~03702~, 15~04577~ 18~03410~ 20~05174~,'),
  (28185, 45, 9, 14, 'What shall we say then? Is there unrighteousness with God? God forbid.', '&para; 0~5101~ 3~2046~ 4~3767~ 5~3361?~* [6 7] 8~93~ 9~3844~ 10~2316~? 12~1096~ 13~3361~.*'),
  (23950, 40, 23, 22, 'And he that shall swear by heaven, sweareth by the throne of God, and by him that sitteth thereon.', '0~2532~ 4~3660~ 5~1722~ 6~3772~, 7~3660~ 8~1722~ 10~2362~ 12~2316~, 13~2532~ 14~1722~ 17~2521~ 18~846~ 19~1883~.*'),
  (10595, 13, 8, 12, 'The sons of Elpaal; Eber, and Misham, and Shamed, who built Ono, and Lod, with the towns thereof:', '1~01121~ 3~0508~; 4~05677~, 6~04936~, 8~08106~, 10~01129~ 11~0207~, 13~03850~, 16~01323~'),
  (13918, 18, 41, 21, 'His breath kindleth coals, and a flame goeth out of his mouth.', '1~05315~ 2~03857~ 3~01513~, 6~03851~ 8~03318~ 11~06310~.'),
  (4309, 4, 19, 15, 'And every open vessel, which hath no covering bound upon it, is unclean.', '2~06605~ 3~03627~, 7~06781~ 8~06616~ [11] 12~02931~.'),
  (7616, 9, 16, 14, 'But the spirit of the LORD departed from Saul, and an evil spirit from the LORD troubled him.', '&para; 2~07307~ 5~03068~ 6~05493~ 8~07586~, 11~07451~ 12~07307~ 15~03068~ 16~01204~'),
  (26908, 43, 20, 25, 'The other disciples therefore said unto him, We have seen the Lord. But he said unto them, Except I shall see in his hands the print of the nails, and put my finger into the print of the nails, and thrust my hand into his side, I will not believe.', '1~243~ 2~3101~ 3~3767~ 4~3004~ 6~846~, 9~3708~ 11~2962~. 12~1161~ 14~2036~ 16~846~, 17~3362~ 20~1492~ 21~1722~ 22~846~ 23~5495~ 25~5179~ 28~2247~, 29~2532~ 30~906~ 31~3450~ 32~1147~ 33~1519~ 35~5179~ 38~2247~, 39~2532~ 40~906~ 41~3450~ 42~5495~ 43~1519~ 44~846~ 45~4125~, 47~4100~ 48~3364~ 49~4100~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (10655, 13, 9, 32, 'And other of their brethren, of the sons of the Kohathites, were over the shewbread, to prepare it every sabbath.', '[1] 4~0251~, 7~01121~ 10~06956~, [11] 14~04635~ 15~03899~,* 17~03559~ [18] 20~07676~.'),
  (13947, 18, 42, 16, 'After this lived Job an hundred and forty years, and saw his sons, and his sons'' sons, even four generations.', '0~0310~ 2~02421~ 3~0347~ 5~03967~ 7~0705~ 8~08141~, 10~07200~ 12~01121~, 15~01121~ 16~01121~, [17] 18~0702~ 19~01755~.'),
  (12267, 15, 10, 6, 'Then Ezra rose up from before the house of God, and went into the chamber of Johanan the son of Eliashib: and when he came thither, he did eat no bread, nor drink water: for he mourned because of the transgression of them that had been carried away.', '&para; 1~05830~ 3~06965~ 5~06440~ 7~01004~ 9~0430~, 11~03212~ 14~03957~ 16~03076~ 18~01121~ 20~0475~: [22] 24~03212~ 28~0398~ 30~03899~, 32~08354~ 33~04325~: 36~056~ 40~04604~ 47~01473~.'),
  (27191, 44, 7, 59, 'And they stoned Stephen, calling upon God, and saying, Lord Jesus, receive my spirit.', '0~2532~ 2~3036~ 3~4736~, 5~1941~ [6] 7~2532~ 8~3004~, 9~2962~ 10~2424~, 11~1209~ 12~3450~ 13~4151~.'),
  (26854, 43, 19, 14, 'And it was the preparation of the passover, and about the sixth hour: and he saith unto the Jews, Behold your King!', '0~1161~ 2~2258~ 4~3904~ 7~3957~, 8~1161~ 9~5616~ 11~1623~ 12~5610~: 13~2532~ 15~3004~ 18~2453~, 19~2396~ 20~5216~ 21~935~!'),
  (3890, 4, 7, 35, 'And for a sacrifice of peace offerings, two oxen, five rams, five he goats, five lambs of the first year: this was the offering of Elizur the son of Shedeur.', '3~02077~ 6~08002~, 7~08147~ 8~01241~, 9~02568~ 10~0352~, 11~02568~ 13~06260~, 14~02568~ 15~03532~ 18~01121~ 19~08141~: [21] 23~07133~ 25~0468~ 27~01121~ 29~07707~.'),
  (19523, 24, 23, 30, 'Therefore, behold, I am against the prophets, saith the LORD, that steal my words every one from his neighbour.', '[3] 6~05030~, 7~05002~ 9~03068~, 11~01589~ 13~01697~ 15~0376~ 18~07453~.'),
  (11252, 14, 3, 15, 'Also he made before the house two pillars of thirty and five cubits high, and the chapiter that was on the top of each of them was five cubits.', '2~06213~ 3~06440~ 5~01004~ 6~08147~ 7~05982~ 9~07970~ 11~02568~ 12~0520~ 13~0753~, 16~06858~ [18] 21~07218~ [26] 27~02568~ 28~0520~.'),
  (26999, 44, 2, 34, 'For David is not ascended into the heavens: but he saith himself, The Lord said unto my Lord, Sit thou on my right hand,', '0~1063~ 1~1138~ 3~3756~ 4~305~ 5~1519~ 7~3772~: 8~1161~ 10~3004~ 11~846~, 13~2962~ 14~2036~ 16~3450~ 17~2962~, 19~2521~ 20~1537~ 21~3450~ 23~1188~,'),
  (7984, 9, 29, 10, 'Wherefore now rise up early in the morning with thy master''s servants that are come with thee: and as soon as ye be up early in the morning, and have light, depart.', '4~07925~ 7~01242~ 10~0113~ 11~05650~ 14~0935~ 24~07925~ 27~01242~, 30~0215~, 31~03212~.'),
  (13161, 18, 12, 24, 'He taketh away the heart of the chief of the people of the earth, and causeth them to wander in a wilderness where there is no way.', '2~05493~ 4~03820~ 7~07218~ 10~05971~ 13~0776~, 18~08582~ 21~08414~ [22 24] 26~01870~.'),
  (24445, 41, 6, 28, 'And brought his head in a charger, and gave it to the damsel: and the damsel gave it to her mother.', '0~2532~ 1~5342~ 2~846~ 3~2776~ 4~1909~ 6~4094~, 7~2532~ 8~1325~ 9~846~ 12~2877~: 13~2532~ 15~2877~ 16~1325~ 17~846~ 19~846~ 20~3384~.'),
  (16156, 19, 130, 7, 'Let Israel hope in the LORD: for with the LORD there is mercy, and with him is plenteous redemption.', '1~03478~ 2~03176~ 5~03068~: 9~03068~ [10 11] 12~02617~, [16] 17~07235~ 18~06304~.'),
  (24129, 40, 26, 65, 'Then the high priest rent his clothes, saying, He hath spoken blasphemy; what further need have we of witnesses? behold, now ye have heard his blasphemy.', '0~5119~ 3~749~ 4~1284~ 5~846~ 6~2440~, 7~3004~ 8~3754~,* 12~987~; 13~5101~ 14~2089~ 15~5532~ 17~2192~ 19~3144~? 20~2396~, 21~3568~ 24~191~ 25~846~ 26~988~.'),
  (7240, 9, 1, 21, 'And the man Elkanah, and all his house, went up to offer unto the LORD the yearly sacrifice, and his vow.', '2~0376~ 3~0511~, 7~01004~, 9~05927~ 11~02076~ 14~03068~ 16~03117~ 17~02077~, 20~05088~.'),
  (4255, 4, 17, 6, 'And Moses spake unto the children of Israel, and every one of their princes gave him a rod apiece, for each prince one, according to their fathers'' houses, even twelve rods: and the rod of Aaron was among their rods.', '1~04872~ 2~01696~ 5~01121~ 7~03478~, 13~05387~ 14~05414~ 17~04294~ 18~04294~, 21~05387~ 22~05387~* 23~0259~ 24~0259~,* 28~01~ 29~01004~, [30] 31~08147~ 32~06240~* 33~04294~: 36~04294~ 38~0175~ [39] 40~08432~ 42~04294~.'),
  (10604, 13, 8, 21, 'And Adaiah, and Beraiah, and Shimrath, the sons of Shimhi;', '1~05718~, 3~01256~, 5~08119~, 7~01121~ 9~08096~;'),
  (20010, 24, 43, 4, 'So Johanan the son of Kareah, and all the captains of the forces, and all the people, obeyed not the voice of the LORD, to dwell in the land of Judah.', '1~03110~ 3~01121~ 5~07143~, 9~08269~ 12~02428~, 16~05971~, 17~08085~ 20~06963~ 23~03068~, 25~03427~ 28~0776~ 30~03063~.'),
  (22158, 28, 4, 16, 'For Israel slideth back as a backsliding heifer: now the LORD will feed them as a lamb in a large place.', '1~03478~ 3~05637~ 6~05637~ 7~06510~: 10~03068~ 12~07462~ 16~03532~ 20~04800~.'),
  (6302, 6, 18, 2, 'And there remained among the children of Israel seven tribes, which had not yet received their inheritance.', '&para; 2~03498~ 5~01121~ 7~03478~ 8~07651~ 9~07626~, 14~02505~ 16~05159~.'),
  (15727, 19, 107, 19, 'Then they cry unto the LORD in their trouble, and he saveth them out of their distresses.', '2~02199~ 5~03068~ 8~06862~, [9] 11~03467~ 16~04691~.'),
  (470, 1, 19, 9, 'And they said, Stand back. And they said again, This one fellow came in to sojourn, and he will needs be a judge: now will we deal worse with thee, than with them. And they pressed sore upon the man, even Lot, and came near to break the door.', '2~0559~, 3~05066~ 4~01973~. 7~0559~ [8] 10~0259~ [11] 13~0935~ 15~01481~, 19~08199~ 22~08199~: 27~07489~ 35~06484~ 36~03966~ 39~0376~, [40] 41~03876~, 44~05066~ 46~07665~ 48~01817~.'),
  (17984, 23, 16, 6, 'We have heard of the pride of Moab; he is very proud: even of his haughtiness, and his pride, and his wrath: but his lies shall not be so.', '&para; 2~08085~ 5~01347~ 7~04124~; [8 9] 10~03966~ 11~01341~: [12] 15~01346~, 18~01347~, 21~05678~: [22] 24~0907~ [25] [27]'),
  (14240, 19, 22, 27, 'All the ends of the world shall remember and turn unto the LORD: and all the kindreds of the nations shall worship before thee.', '2~0657~ 5~0776~ 7~02142~ 9~07725~ 12~03068~: 16~04940~ 19~01471~ 21~07812~ 22~06440~'),
  (21239, 26, 30, 26, 'And I will scatter the Egyptians among the nations, and disperse them among the countries; and they shall know that I am the LORD.', '3~06327~ 5~04714~ 8~01471~, 10~02219~ 14~0776~; 18~03045~ [21] 23~03068~.'),
  (4004, 4, 10, 11, 'And it came to pass on the twentieth day of the second month, in the second year, that the cloud was taken up from off the tabernacle of the testimony.', '&para; 7~06242~ [8] 11~08145~ 12~02320~, 15~08145~ 16~08141~, 19~06051~ 22~05927~ 26~04908~ 29~05715~.'),
  (21117, 26, 26, 8, 'He shall slay with the sword thy daughters in the field: and he shall make a fort against thee, and cast a mount against thee, and lift up the buckler against thee.', '2~02026~ 5~02719~ 7~01323~ 10~07704~: 14~05414~ 16~01785~ 20~08210~ 22~05550~ 27~06965~ 29~06793~'),
  (5174, 5, 9, 11, 'And it came to pass at the end of forty days and forty nights, that the LORD gave me the two tables of stone, even the tables of the covenant.', '7~07093~ 9~0705~ 10~03117~ 12~0705~ 13~03915~, [14] 16~03068~ 17~05414~ 20~08147~ 21~03871~ 23~068~, [24] 26~03871~ 29~01285~.'),
  (7112, 7, 21, 3, 'And said, O LORD God of Israel, why is this come to pass in Israel, that there should be to day one tribe lacking in Israel?', '1~0559~, 3~03068~ 4~0430~ 6~03478~, 14~03478~, 20~03117~ 21~0259~ 22~07626~ 23~06485~ 25~03478~?'),
  (11234, 14, 2, 15, 'Now therefore the wheat, and the barley, the oil, and the wine, which my lord hath spoken of, let him send unto his servants:', '3~02406~, 6~08184~, 8~08081~, 11~03196~, 14~0113~ 16~0559~ 20~07971~ 23~05650~:'),
  (15841, 19, 115, 2, 'Wherefore should the heathen say, Where is now their God?', '3~01471~ 4~0559~, [6] 9~0430~?'),
  (12429, 16, 6, 19, 'Also they reported his good deeds before me, and uttered my words to him. And Tobiah sent letters to put me in fear.', '2~0559~ 5~02896~ 6~06440~ 9~03318~ 11~01697~ [14] 15~02900~ 16~07971~ 17~0107~ 22~03372~.'),
  (26428, 43, 8, 32, 'And ye shall know the truth, and the truth shall make you free.', '0~2532~ 3~1097~ 5~225~, 6~2532~ 8~225~ 10~1659~ 11~5209~ 12~1659~.'),
  (21060, 26, 23, 44, 'Yet they went in unto her, as they go in unto a woman that playeth the harlot: so went they in unto Aholah and unto Aholibah, the lewd women.', '3~0935~ 9~0935~ 12~0802~ 16~02181~: 20~0935~ 22~0170~ 25~0172~, 27~02154~ 28~0802~.'),
  (6480, 6, 23, 13, 'Know for a certainty that the LORD your God will no more drive out any of these nations from before you; but they shall be snares and traps unto you, and scourges in your sides, and thorns in your eyes, until ye perish from off this good land which the LORD your God hath given you.', '0~03045~ 3~03045~ 6~03068~ 8~0430~ 11~03254~ 13~03423~ [14 15] 17~01471~ 19~06440~ 25~06341~ 27~04170~ 31~07850~ 34~06654~, 36~06796~ 39~05869~, 42~06~ 46~02896~ 47~0127~ 50~03068~ 52~0430~ 54~05414~'),
  (14160, 19, 18, 33, 'He maketh my feet like hinds'' feet, and setteth me upon my high places.', '1~07737~ 3~07272~ 5~0355~ [6] 8~05975~ 13~01116~.'),
  (23421, 40, 9, 32, 'As they went out, behold, they brought to him a dumb man possessed with a devil.', '0~1161~ 1~846~ 3~1831~, 4~2400~, 6~4374~ 8~846~ 10~2974~ 11~444~ 15~1139~.'),
  (21364, 26, 35, 11, 'Therefore, as I live, saith the Lord GOD, I will even do according to thine anger, and according to thine envy which thou hast used out of thy hatred against them; and I will make myself known among them, when I have judged thee.', '[1] 3~02416~, 4~05002~ 6~0136~ 7~03069~, 11~06213~ 15~0639~, 20~07068~ 24~06213~ 28~08135~ 36~03045~ 42~08199~'),
  (17695, 23, 2, 1, 'The word that Isaiah the son of Amoz saw concerning Judah and Jerusalem.', '&para; 1~01697~ 3~03470~ 5~01121~ 7~0531~ 8~02372~ 10~03063~ 12~03389~.'),
  (9063, 11, 9, 4, 'And if thou wilt walk before me, as David thy father walked, in integrity of heart, and in uprightness, to do according to all that I have commanded thee, and wilt keep my statutes and my judgments:', '4~03212~ 5~06440~ 8~01732~ 10~01~ 11~01980~, 13~08537~ 15~03824~, 18~03476~, 20~06213~ 27~06680~ [29] 31~08104~ 33~02706~ 36~04941~:'),
  (15899, 19, 118, 21, 'I will praise thee: for thou hast heard me, and art become my salvation.', '2~03034~ 7~06030~ 13~03444~.'),
  (3731, 4, 3, 34, 'And those that were numbered of them, according to the number of all the males, from a month old and upward, were six thousand and two hundred.', '4~06485~ 10~04557~ 14~02145~, 17~02320~ 18~01121~ 20~04605~, [21] 22~08337~ 23~0505~ 26~03967~.'),
  (20885, 26, 18, 27, 'Again, when the wicked man turneth away from his wickedness that he hath committed, and doeth that which is lawful and right, he shall save his soul alive.', '3~07563~ [4] 6~07725~ 9~07564~ 13~06213~, 15~06213~ 19~04941~ 21~06666~, 24~02421~ 26~05315~ 27~02421~.'),
  (24458, 41, 6, 41, 'And when he had taken the five loaves and the two fishes, he looked up to heaven, and blessed, and brake the loaves, and gave them to his disciples to set before them; and the two fishes divided he among them all.', '0~2532~ 4~2983~ 6~4002~ 7~740~ 8~2532~ 10~1417~ 11~2486~, 14~308~ 15~1519~ 16~3772~, 18~2127~, 19~2532~ 20~2622~ 22~740~, 23~2532~ 24~1325~ [25] 27~846~ 28~3101~ 29~2443~ 31~3908~ 32~846~; 33~2532~ 35~1417~ 36~2486~ 38~3307~ 41~3956~.'),
  (13085, 18, 9, 25, 'Now my days are swifter than a post: they flee away, they see no good.', '&para; 2~03117~ 4~07043~ 7~07323~: 10~01272~, 12~07200~ 14~02896~.'),
  (20916, 26, 20, 12, 'Moreover also I gave them my sabbaths, to be a sign between me and them, that they might know that I am the LORD that sanctify them.', '3~05414~ 6~07676~, 10~0226~ 18~03045~ [21] 23~03068~ 25~06942~'),
  (12912, 18, 2, 12, 'And when they lifted up their eyes afar off, and knew him not, they lifted up their voice, and wept; and they rent every one his mantle, and sprinkled dust upon their heads toward heaven.', '4~05375~ 6~05869~ 8~07350~, 10~05234~ 15~05375~ 17~06963~, 19~01058~; 22~07167~ 24~0376~ 26~04598~, 28~02236~ 29~06083~ 32~07218~ 34~08064~.'),
  (13497, 18, 27, 7, 'Let mine enemy be as the wicked, and he that riseth up against me as the unrighteous.', '&para; 2~0341~ 6~07563~, 11~06965~ 16~05767~.'),
  (184, 1, 7, 24, 'And the waters prevailed upon the earth an hundred and fifty days.', '2~04325~ 3~01396~ 6~0776~ 8~03967~ 10~02572~ 11~03117~.'),
  (26737, 43, 15, 23, 'He that hateth me hateth my Father also.', '2~3404~ 3~1691~ 4~3404~ 5~3450~ 6~3962~ 7~2532~.'),
  (2868, 3, 6, 14, 'And this is the law of the meat offering: the sons of Aaron shall offer it before the LORD, before the altar.', '&para; [2] 4~08451~ 8~04503~: 10~01121~ 12~0175~ 14~07126~ 16~06440~ 18~03068~, 19~06440~ 21~04196~.'),
  (28180, 45, 9, 9, 'For this is the word of promise, At this time will I come, and Sarah shall have a son.', '0~1063~ 1~3778~ [2] 4~3056~ 6~1860~, 7~2596~ 8~5126~ 9~2540~ 12~2064~, 13~2532~ 14~4564~ 16~2071~ 18~5207~.'),
  (11683, 14, 23, 18, 'Also Jehoiada appointed the offices of the house of the LORD by the hand of the priests the Levites, whom David had distributed in the house of the LORD, to offer the burnt offerings of the LORD, as it is written in the law of Moses, with rejoicing and with singing, as it was ordained by David.', '1~03077~ 2~07760~ 4~06486~ 7~01004~ 10~03068~ 13~03027~ 16~03548~ 18~03881~, 20~01732~ 22~02505~ 25~01004~ 28~03068~, 30~05927~ 33~05930~ 36~03068~, [38 39] 40~03789~ 43~08451~ 45~04872~, 47~08057~ 50~07892~, [51 54] 55~03027~ 56~01732~.'),
  (14194, 19, 20, 3, 'Remember all thy offerings, and accept thy burnt sacrifice; Selah.', '0~02142~ 3~04503~, 5~01878~ 8~05930~; 9~05542~.'),
  (10874, 13, 17, 3, 'And it came to pass the same night, that the word of God came to Nathan, saying,', '7~03915~, 10~01697~ 12~0430~ 15~05416~, 16~0559~,'),
  (29133, 48, 3, 15, 'Brethren, I speak after the manner of men; Though it be but a man''s covenant, yet if it be confirmed, no man disannulleth, or addeth thereto.', '0~80~, 2~3004~ 6~2596~ 7~444~; [9 10] 11~3676~ 13~444~ 14~1242~, [16 18] 19~2964~, 21~3762~ 22~114~, 23~2228~ 25~1928~.'),
  (19020, 24, 3, 9, 'And it came to pass through the lightness of her whoredom, that she defiled the land, and committed adultery with stones and with stocks.', '7~06963~ 10~02184~, 13~02610~ 15~0776~, 18~05003~ 20~068~ 23~06086~.'),
  (17192, 20, 27, 14, 'He that blesseth his friend with a loud voice, rising early in the morning, it shall be counted a curse to him.', '&para; 2~01288~ 4~07453~ 7~01419~ 8~06963~, 10~07925~ 13~01242~, 17~02803~ 19~07045~'),
  (81, 1, 4, 1, 'And Adam knew Eve his wife; and she conceived, and bare Cain, and said, I have gotten a man from the LORD.', '&para; 1~0120~ 2~03045~ 3~0853~* 4~02332~ 6~0802~; 9~02029~, 11~03205~ 12~0853~* 13~07014~, 15~0559~, 18~07069~ 20~0376~ 21~0854~ 23~03068~.'),
  (228, 1, 9, 22, 'And Ham, the father of Canaan, saw the nakedness of his father, and told his two brethren without.', '1~02526~, 3~01~ 5~03667~, 6~07200~ 8~06172~ 11~01~, 13~05046~ 15~08147~ 16~0251~ 17~02351~.'),
  (17339, 21, 1, 15, 'That which is crooked cannot be made straight: and that which is wanting cannot be numbered.', '[0 2] 3~05791~ 4~03201~ 7~08626~: 12~02642~ 13~03201~ 15~04487~.'),
  (30331, 59, 2, 22, 'Seest thou how faith wrought with his works, and by works was faith made perfect?', '1~991~ 2~3754~ 3~4102~ 4~4903~ 6~846~ 7~2041~, 8~2532~ 9~1537~ 10~2041~ 11~5048~ 12~4102~ 14~5048~?'),
  (22056, 27, 11, 11, 'And the king of the south shall be moved with choler, and shall come forth and fight with him, even with the king of the north: and he shall set forth a great multitude; but the multitude shall be given into his hand.', '2~04428~ 5~05045~ 10~04843~, 14~03318~ 16~03898~ [19] 22~04428~ 25~06828~: 30~05975~ 32~07227~ 33~01995~; 36~01995~ 39~05414~ 42~03027~.'),
  (8543, 10, 19, 24, 'And Mephibosheth the son of Saul came down to meet the king, and had neither dressed his feet, nor trimmed his beard, nor washed his clothes, from the day the king departed until the day he came again in peace.', '&para; 1~04648~ 3~01121~ 5~07586~ 7~03381~ 9~07125~ 11~04428~, 14~03808~ 15~06213~ 17~07272~, 19~06213~ 21~08222~, 23~03526~ 25~0899~, 28~03117~ 30~04428~ 31~03212~ 34~03117~ 36~0935~ [37] 39~07965~.'),
  (9802, 12, 10, 1, 'And Ahab had seventy sons in Samaria. And Jehu wrote letters, and sent to Samaria, unto the rulers of Jezreel, to the elders, and to them that brought up Ahab''s children, saying,', '&para; 1~0256~ 3~07657~ 4~01121~ 6~08111~. 8~03058~ 9~03789~ 10~05612~, 12~07971~ 14~08111~, 17~08269~ 19~03157~, 22~02205~, 28~0539~ 29~0256~ [30] 31~0559~,'),
  (10420, 13, 4, 27, 'And Shimei had sixteen sons and six daughters; but his brethren had not many children, neither did all their family multiply, like to the children of Judah.', '1~08096~ 3~06240~ 4~08337~* 5~01121~ 7~08337~ 8~01323~; 11~0251~ 14~07227~ 15~01121~, 20~04940~ 21~07235~, 25~01121~ 27~03063~.'),
  (24383, 41, 5, 9, 'And he asked him, What is thy name? And he answered, saying, My name is Legion: for we are many.', '0~2532~ 2~1905~ 3~846~, 4~5101~ [5] 6~4671~ 7~3686~? 8~2532~ 10~611~, 11~3004~, 12~3427~ 13~3686~ [14] 15~3003~: 16~3754~ 18~2070~ 19~4183~.'),
  (28784, 46, 15, 50, 'Now this I say, brethren, that flesh and blood cannot inherit the kingdom of God; neither doth corruption inherit incorruption.', '0~1161~ 1~5124~ 3~5346~, 4~80~, 5~3754~ 6~4561~ 7~2532~ 8~129~ 9~1410~ 10~3756~* 11~2816~ 13~932~ 15~2316~; 16~3761~ 17~2816~ 18~5356~ 19~2816~ 20~861~.'),
  (19426, 24, 19, 10, 'Then shalt thou break the bottle in the sight of the men that go with thee.', '&para; 3~07665~ 5~01228~ 8~05869~ 11~0582~ 13~01980~'),
  (22059, 27, 11, 14, 'And in those times there shall many stand up against the king of the south: also the robbers of thy people shall exalt themselves to establish the vision; but they shall fall.', '3~06256~ 6~07227~ 8~05975~ 11~04428~ 14~05045~: 17~06530~ 18~01121~ 20~05971~ 22~05375~ 25~05975~ 27~02377~; 31~03782~.'),
  (11751, 14, 26, 10, 'Also he built towers in the desert, and digged many wells: for he had much cattle, both in the low country, and in the plains: husbandmen also, and vine dressers in the mountains, and in Carmel: for he loved husbandry.', '2~01129~ 3~04026~ 6~04057~, 8~02672~ 9~07227~ 10~0953~: 14~07227~ 15~04735~, 20~08219~, 24~04334~: 25~0406~ [26] 29~03755~ 32~02022~, 35~03760~: 38~0157~ 39~0127~.'),
  (30167, 58, 10, 18, 'Now where remission of these is, there is no more offering for sin.', '0~1161~ 1~3699~ 2~859~ 4~5130~ [5 7] 9~3765~ 10~4376~ 11~4012~ 12~266~.'),
  (26117, 43, 2, 7, 'Jesus saith unto them, Fill the waterpots with water. And they filled them up to the brim.', '0~2424~ 1~3004~ 3~846~, 4~1072~ 6~5201~ 8~5204~. 9~2532~ 11~1072~ 12~846~ 13~1072~ 14~2193~ 16~507~.'),
  (12038, 15, 2, 2, 'Which came with Zerubbabel: Jeshua, Nehemiah, Seraiah, Reelaiah, Mordecai, Bilshan, Mizpar, Bigvai, Rehum, Baanah. The number of the men of the people of Israel:', '1~0935~ 3~02216~: 4~03442~, 5~05166~, 6~08304~, 7~07480~, 8~04782~, 9~01114~, 10~04558~, 11~0902~, 12~07348~, 13~01196~. 15~04557~ 18~0582~ 21~05971~ 23~03478~:'),
  (7827, 9, 23, 10, 'Then said David, O LORD God of Israel, thy servant hath certainly heard that Saul seeketh to come to Keilah, to destroy the city for my sake.', '1~0559~ 2~01732~, 4~03068~ 5~0430~ 7~03478~, 9~05650~ 11~08085~ 12~08085~ 14~07586~ 15~01245~ 17~0935~ 19~07084~, 21~07843~ 23~05892~'),
  (9369, 11, 18, 20, 'So Ahab sent unto all the children of Israel, and gathered the prophets together unto mount Carmel.', '1~0256~ 2~07971~ 6~01121~ 8~03478~, 10~06908~ 12~05030~ 13~06908~ 15~02022~ 16~03760~.'),
  (17953, 23, 14, 16, 'They that see thee shall narrowly look upon thee, and consider thee, saying, Is this the man that made the earth to tremble, that did shake kingdoms;', '2~07200~ 6~07688~ [9] 10~0995~ [12 13] 16~0376~ 20~0776~ 22~07264~, 25~07493~ 26~04467~;'),
  (908, 1, 31, 31, 'And Jacob answered and said to Laban, Because I was afraid: for I said, Peradventure thou wouldest take by force thy daughters from me.', '1~03290~ 2~06030~ 4~0559~ 6~03837~, 10~03372~: 13~0559~, 14~06435~ 19~01497~ 21~01323~'),
  (25973, 42, 23, 24, 'And Pilate gave sentence that it should be as they required.', '0~1161~ 1~4091~ 3~1948~ 8~1096~ 9~846~ 10~155~.'),
  (11024, 13, 24, 1, 'Now these are the divisions of the sons of Aaron. The sons of Aaron; Nadab, and Abihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar.', '&para; [1 2] 4~04256~ 7~01121~ 9~0175~. 11~01121~ 13~0175~; 14~05070~, 16~030~, 17~0499~, 19~0385~.'),
  (16048, 19, 119, 141, 'I am small and despised: yet do not I forget thy precepts.', '&para; [1] 2~06810~ 4~0959~: [5] 9~07911~ 11~06490~.'),
  (26500, 43, 10, 4, 'And when he putteth forth his own sheep, he goeth before them, and the sheep follow him: for they know his voice.', '0~2532~ 1~3752~ 4~1544~ 6~2398~ 7~4263~, 9~4198~ 10~1715~ 11~846~, 12~2532~ 14~4263~ 15~190~ 16~846~: 17~3754~ 19~1492~ 20~846~ 21~5456~.'),
  (6723, 7, 7, 22, 'And the three hundred blew the trumpets, and the LORD set every man''s sword against his fellow, even throughout all the host: and the host fled to Bethshittah in Zererath, and to the border of Abelmeholah, unto Tabbath.', '2~07969~ 3~03967~ 4~08628~ 6~07782~, 9~03068~ 10~07760~ 12~0376~ 13~02719~ 16~07453~, 21~04264~: 24~04264~ 25~05127~ 27~01029~ 29~06888~, [30] 33~08193~ 35~065~, 37~02888~.'),
  (30635, 62, 4, 16, 'And we have known and believed the love that God hath to us. God is love; and he that dwelleth in love dwelleth in God, and God in him.', '0~2532~ 1~2249~ 3~1097~ 4~2532~ 5~4100~ 7~26~ 8~3739~ 9~2316~ 10~2192~ 11~1722~ 12~2254~. 13~2316~ 14~2076~ 15~26~; 16~2532~ 19~3306~ 20~1722~ 21~26~ 22~3306~ 23~1722~ 24~2316~, 25~2532~ 26~2316~ 27~1722~ 28~846~.'),
  (6642, 7, 5, 12, 'Awake, awake, Deborah: awake, awake, utter a song: arise, Barak, and lead thy captivity captive, thou son of Abinoam.', '&para; 0~05782~, 1~05782~, 2~01683~: 3~05782~, 4~05782~, 5~01696~ 7~07892~: 8~06965~, 9~01301~, 13~07628~ 14~07617~, 16~01121~ 18~042~.'),
  (20435, 25, 4, 6, 'For the punishment of the iniquity of the daughter of my people is greater than the punishment of the sin of Sodom, that was overthrown as in a moment, and no hands stayed on her.', '5~05771~ 8~01323~ 11~05971~ 13~01431~ 16~02403~ 21~05467~, 24~02015~ 28~07281~, 31~03027~ 32~02342~'),
  (17981, 23, 16, 3, 'Take counsel, execute judgment; make thy shadow as the night in the midst of the noonday; hide the outcasts; bewray not him that wandereth.', '0~0935~ 1~06098~, 2~06213~ 3~06415~; 4~07896~ 6~06738~ 9~03915~ 12~08432~ 15~06672~; 16~05641~ 18~05080~; 19~01540~ 23~05074~.'),
  (23726, 40, 17, 16, 'And I brought him to thy disciples, and they could not cure him.', '0~2532~ 2~4374~ 3~846~ 5~4675~ 6~3101~, 7~2532~ 9~1410~ 10~3756~ 11~2323~ 12~846~.'),
  (3226, 3, 16, 20, 'And when he hath made an end of reconciling the holy place, and the tabernacle of the congregation, and the altar, he shall bring the live goat:', '&para; 6~03615~ 8~03722~ 10~06944~ [11] 14~0168~ 17~04150~, 20~04196~, 23~07126~ 25~02416~ 26~08163~:'),
  (5678, 5, 28, 61, 'Also every sickness, and every plague, which is not written in the book of this law, them will the LORD bring upon thee, until thou be destroyed.', '2~02483~, 5~04347~, [7] 9~03789~ 12~05612~ 15~08451~, 19~03068~ 20~05927~ 26~08045~.'),
  (15561, 19, 103, 3, 'Who forgiveth all thine iniquities; who healeth all thy diseases;', '1~05545~ 4~05771~; 6~07495~ 9~08463~;'),
  (30203, 58, 11, 15, 'And truly, if they had been mindful of that country from whence they came out, they might have had opportunity to have returned.', '0~2532~ 1~3303~, 2~1487~ 6~3421~ 8~1565~ [9] 10~575~ 11~3739~ 14~1831~, 16~302~ 18~2192~ 19~2540~ 22~344~.'),
  (840, 1, 30, 6, 'And Rachel said, God hath judged me, and hath also heard my voice, and hath given me a son: therefore called she his name Dan.', '1~07354~ 2~0559~, 3~0430~ 5~01777~ 10~08085~ 12~06963~, 15~05414~ 18~01121~: 20~07121~ 23~08034~ 24~01835~.'),
  (14781, 19, 57, 4, 'My soul is among lions: and I lie even among them that are set on fire, even the sons of men, whose teeth are spears and arrows, and their tongue a sharp sword.', '1~05315~ [2] 3~08432~ 4~03833~: [5] 7~07901~ [8 9] 15~03857~, [16] 18~01121~ 20~0120~, 22~08127~ [23] 24~02595~ 26~02671~, 29~03956~ 31~02299~ 32~02719~.'),
  (9699, 12, 6, 17, 'And Elisha prayed, and said, LORD, I pray thee, open his eyes, that he may see. And the LORD opened the eyes of the young man; and he saw: and, behold, the mountain was full of horses and chariots of fire round about Elisha.', '1~0477~ 2~06419~, 4~0559~, 5~03068~, 9~06491~ 11~05869~, 15~07200~. 18~03068~ 19~06491~ 21~05869~ 25~05288~; 28~07200~: 32~02022~ [33] 34~04390~ 36~05483~ 38~07393~ 40~0784~ 42~05439~ 43~0477~.'),
  (27536, 44, 16, 37, 'But Paul said unto them, They have beaten us openly uncondemned, being Romans, and have cast us into prison; and now do they thrust us out privily? nay verily; but let them come themselves and fetch us out.', '0~1161~ 1~3972~ 2~5346~ 3~4314~ 4~846~, 7~1194~ 8~2248~ 9~1219~ 10~178~, 11~5225~ 12~444~ 13~4514~,* 16~906~ [17] 18~1519~ 19~5438~; 20~2532~ 21~3568~ 24~1544~ 25~2248~ 26~1544~ 27~2977~? 28~3756~ 29~1063~; 30~235~ 33~2064~ 34~846~ 36~1806~ 37~2248~ 38~1806~.'),
  (1699, 2, 7, 9, 'When Pharaoh shall speak unto you, saying, shew a miracle for you: then thou shalt say unto Aaron, Take thy rod, and cast it before Pharaoh, and it shall become a serpent.', '1~06547~ 3~01696~ 6~0559~, 7~05414~ 9~04159~ 15~0559~ 17~0175~, 18~03947~ 20~04294~, 22~07993~ [23] 24~06440~ 25~06547~, [26] 31~08577~.'),
  (17085, 20, 23, 32, 'At the last it biteth like a serpent, and stingeth like an adder.', '2~0319~ 4~05391~ 7~05175~, 9~06567~ 12~06848~.'),
  (18432, 23, 40, 3, 'The voice of him that crieth in the wilderness, Prepare ye the way of the LORD, make straight in the desert a highway for our God.', '&para; 1~06963~ 5~07121~ 8~04057~, 9~06437~ 12~01870~ 15~03068~, 17~03474~ 20~06160~ 22~04546~ 25~0430~.'),
  (18618, 23, 47, 10, 'For thou hast trusted in thy wickedness: thou hast said, None seeth me. Thy wisdom and thy knowledge, it hath perverted thee; and thou hast said in thine heart, I am, and none else beside me.', '3~0982~ 6~07451~: 9~0559~, 11~07200~ 14~02451~ 17~01847~, 20~07725~ 25~0559~ 28~03820~, [30] 33~0657~');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (23026, 38, 10, 1, 'Ask ye of the LORD rain in the time of the latter rain; so the LORD shall make bright clouds, and give them showers of rain, to every one grass in the field.', '&para; 0~07592~ 4~03068~ 5~04306~ 8~06256~ 12~04456~; [13] 15~03068~ 17~06213~ 19~02385~, 21~05414~ 23~01653~ 25~04306~, 28~0376~ 29~06212~ 32~07704~.'),
  (27818, 44, 25, 6, 'And when he had tarried among them more than ten days, he went down unto Caesarea; and the next day sitting on the judgment seat commanded Paul to be brought.', '0~1161~ 4~1304~ 5~1722~ 6~846~ 7~4119~ 8~2228~ 9~1176~ 10~2250~, 13~2597~ 14~1519~ 15~2542~; 19~1887~ 20~2523~ 21~1909~ 24~968~ 25~2753~ 26~3972~ 29~71~.'),
  (24481, 41, 7, 8, 'For laying aside the commandment of God, ye hold the tradition of men, as the washing of pots and cups: and many other such like things ye do.', '0~1063~ 2~863~ 4~1785~ 6~2316~, 8~2902~ 10~3862~ 12~444~, [13] 15~909~ 17~3582~ 18~2532~ 19~4221~: 20~2532~ 21~4183~ 22~243~ 23~5108~ 25~3946~ 27~4160~.'),
  (9090, 11, 10, 3, 'And Solomon told her all her questions: there was not any thing hid from the king, which he told her not.', '1~08010~ 2~05046~ 6~01697~: [10] 11~01697~ 12~05956~ 15~04428~, 18~05046~'),
  (30013, 58, 3, 2, 'Who was faithful to him that appointed him, as also Moses was faithful in all his house.', '1~5607~ 2~4103~ 6~4160~ 7~846~, 8~5613~ 9~2532~ 10~3475~ [11 12] 13~1722~ 14~3650~ 15~846~ 16~3624~.'),
  (16165, 19, 132, 5, 'Until I find out a place for the LORD, an habitation for the mighty God of Jacob.', '3~04672~ 5~04725~ 8~03068~, 10~04908~ 13~046~ [14] 16~03290~.'),
  (27038, 44, 3, 26, 'Unto you first God, having raised up his Son Jesus, sent him to bless you, in turning away every one of you from his iniquities.', '1~5213~ 2~4412~ 3~2316~, 6~450~ 7~846~ 8~3816~ 9~2424~, 10~649~ 11~846~ 13~2127~ 14~5209~, 15~1722~ 17~654~ 19~1538~ 21~5216~ 22~575~ 24~4189~.'),
  (7249, 9, 2, 2, 'There is none holy as the LORD: for there is none beside thee: neither is there any rock like our God.', '[0 1] 3~06918~ 6~03068~: [8 9] 11~01115~ [14 15] 17~06697~ 20~0430~.'),
  (9413, 11, 19, 18, 'Yet I have left me seven thousand in Israel, all the knees which have not bowed unto Baal, and every mouth which hath not kissed him.', '3~07604~ [4] 5~07651~ 6~0505~ 8~03478~, 11~01290~ 15~03766~ 17~01168~, 20~06310~ 24~05401~'),
  (30015, 58, 3, 4, 'For every house is builded by some man; but he that built all things is God.', '0~1063~ 1~3956~ 2~3624~ 4~2680~ 5~5259~ 6~5100~ [7] 8~1161~ 11~2680~ 13~3956~ [14] 15~2316~.'),
  (23090, 38, 14, 13, 'And it shall come to pass in that day, that a great tumult from the LORD shall be among them; and they shall lay hold every one on the hand of his neighbour, and his hand shall rise up against the hand of his neighbour.', '8~03117~, [9] 11~07227~ 12~04103~ 15~03068~ 24~02388~ 26~0376~ 29~03027~ 32~07453~, 35~03027~ 38~05927~ 41~03027~ 44~07453~.'),
  (28116, 45, 7, 9, 'For I was alive without the law once: but when the commandment came, sin revived, and I died.', '0~1161~ 1~1473~ 3~2198~ 4~5565~ 6~3551~ 7~4218~: 8~1161~ 11~1785~ 12~2064~, 13~266~ 14~326~, 15~1161~ 16~1473~ 17~599~.'),
  (16087, 19, 120, 4, 'Sharp arrows of the mighty, with coals of juniper.', '0~08150~ 1~02671~ 4~01368~, 6~01513~ 8~07574~.'),
  (4507, 4, 26, 13, 'Of Zerah, the family of the Zarhites: of Shaul, the family of the Shaulites.', '1~02226~, 3~04940~ 6~02227~: 8~07586~, 10~04940~ 13~07587~.'),
  (6312, 6, 18, 12, 'And their border on the north side was from Jordan; and the border went up to the side of Jericho on the north side, and went up through the mountains westward; and the goings out thereof were at the wilderness of Bethaven.', '2~01366~ 5~06828~ 6~06285~ 9~03383~; 12~01366~ 14~05927~ 17~03802~ 19~03405~ 22~06828~ 26~05927~ 29~02022~ 30~03220~; 34~08444~ 39~04057~ 41~01007~.'),
