  (23930, 40, 23, 2, 'Saying, The scribes and the Pharisees sit in Moses'' seat:', '0~3004~, 2~1122~ 3~2532~ 5~5330~ 6~2523~ 7~1909~ 8~3475~ 9~2515~:'),
  (19138, 24, 7, 10, 'And come and stand before me in this house, which is called by my name, and say, We are delivered to do all these abominations?', '1~0935~ 3~05975~ 4~06440~ 8~01004~, 11~07121~ 14~08034~, 16~0559~, 19~05337~ 21~06213~ 24~08441~?'),
  (12157, 15, 5, 14, 'And the vessels also of gold and silver of the house of God, which Nebuchadnezzar took out of the temple that was in Jerusalem, and brought them into the temple of Babylon, those did Cyrus the king take out of the temple of Babylon, and they were delivered unto one, whose name was Sheshbazzar, whom he had made governor;', '2~03984~ 3~0638~ 4~01768~ 5~01722~ 7~03702~ 10~01005~ 12~0426~, 14~05020~ 15~05312~ 17~04481~ 19~01965~ [21] 23~03390~, 25~02987~ 29~01965~ 31~0895~, 32~01994~ 34~03567~ 36~04430~ 37~05312~ 39~04481~ 41~01965~ 43~0895~, 47~03052~ [49] 51~08036~ [52] 53~08340~, 57~07761~ 58~06347~;'),
  (19873, 24, 36, 22, 'Now the king sat in the winterhouse in the ninth month: and there was a fire on the hearth burning before him.', '2~04428~ 3~03427~ 6~02779~ 7~01004~ 9~08671~ 10~02320~: [12 15] 18~0254~ 19~01197~ 20~06440~'),
  (3755, 4, 4, 7, 'And upon the table of shewbread they shall spread a cloth of blue, and put thereon the dishes, and the spoons, and the bowls, and covers to cover withal: and the continual bread shall be thereon:', '3~07979~ 5~06440~ 8~06566~ 10~0899~ 12~08504~, 14~05414~ 17~07086~, 20~03709~, 23~04518~, 25~07184~ 28~05262~: 31~08548~ 32~03899~'),
  (30744, 66, 2, 11, 'He that hath an ear, let him hear what the Spirit saith unto the churches; He that overcometh shall not be hurt of the second death.', '2~2192~ 4~3775~, 7~191~ 8~5101~ 10~4151~ 11~3004~ 14~1577~; 17~3528~ 18~91~ 19~3364~ 21~91~ 22~1537~ 24~1208~ 25~2288~.'),
  (7107, 7, 20, 46, 'So that all which fell that day of Benjamin were twenty and five thousand men that drew the sword; all these were men of valour.', '4~05307~ 6~03117~ 8~01144~ 10~06242~ 12~02568~ 13~0505~ 14~0376~ 16~08025~ 18~02719~; [21] 22~0582~ 24~02428~.'),
  (16104, 19, 122, 6, 'Pray for the peace of Jerusalem: they shall prosper that love thee.', '&para; 0~07592~ 3~07965~ 5~03389~: 8~07951~ 10~0157~'),
  (19815, 24, 34, 5, 'But thou shalt die in peace: and with the burnings of thy fathers, the former kings which were before thee, so shall they burn odours for thee; and they will lament thee, saying, Ah lord! for I have pronounced the word, saith the LORD.', '[0] 3~04191~ 5~07965~: 9~04955~ 12~01~, 14~07223~ 15~04428~ 18~06440~ 23~08313~ [24] 30~05594~ [32] 33~01945~ 34~0113~! 38~01696~ 40~01697~, 41~05002~ 43~03068~.'),
  (25376, 42, 10, 1, 'After these things the Lord appointed other seventy also, and sent them two and two before his face into every city and place, whither he himself would come.', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~3326~ 3~5023~ 5~2962~ 6~322~ 7~2087~ 8~1440~ 9~2532~, 10~2532~ 11~649~ 12~846~ 13~303~ 15~1417~ 16~4253~ 17~846~ 18~4383~ 19~1519~ 20~3956~ 21~4172~ 22~2532~ 23~5117~, 24~3757~ 25~3739~* 27~846~ 28~3195~ 29~2064~.'),
  (13575, 18, 30, 9, 'And now am I their song, yea, I am their byword.', '5~05058~, 10~04405~.'),
  (15055, 19, 73, 26, 'My flesh and my heart faileth: but God is the strength of my heart, and my portion for ever.', '1~07607~ 4~03824~ 5~03615~: [6] 7~0430~ [8] 10~06697~ 13~03824~, 16~02506~ 18~05769~.'),
  (29237, 49, 1, 15, 'Wherefore I also, after I heard of your faith in the Lord Jesus, and love unto all the saints,', '&para; 0~5124~ 1~1223~ 2~2504~, 5~191~ 6~2596~ 7~5209~ 8~4102~ 9~1722~ 11~2962~ 12~2424~, 13~2532~ 14~26~ 15~1519~ 16~3956~ 18~40~,'),
  (18917, 23, 65, 11, 'But ye are they that forsake the LORD, that forget my holy mountain, that prepare a table for that troop, and that furnish the drink offering unto that number.', '&para; [2] 5~05800~ 7~03068~, 9~07913~ 11~06944~ 12~02022~, 14~06186~ 16~07979~ 19~01409~ 20~01408~,* 23~04390~ 26~04469~ 29~04507~.'),
  (10694, 13, 11, 13, 'He was with David at Pasdammim, and there the Philistines were gathered together to battle, where was a parcel of ground full of barley; and the people fled from before the Philistines.', '3~01732~ 5~06450~, 9~06430~ 12~0622~ 14~04421~, 18~02513~ 20~07704~ 21~04392~ 23~08184~; 26~05971~ 27~05127~ 29~06440~ 31~06430~.'),
  (12605, 16, 11, 8, 'And after him Gabbai, Sallai, nine hundred twenty and eight.', '1~0310~ 3~01373~, 4~05543~, 5~08672~ 6~03967~ 7~06242~ 9~08083~.'),
  (30346, 59, 3, 11, 'Doth a fountain send forth at the same place sweet water and bitter?', '0~3385~ 2~4077~ 4~1032~ 5~1537~ 7~846~ 8~3692~ 9~1099~ [10] 11~2532~ 12~4089~?'),
  (14766, 19, 56, 2, 'Mine enemies would daily swallow me up: for they be many that fight against me, O thou most High.', '1~08324~ 3~03117~ 4~07602~ [5] [8 9] 10~07227~ 12~03898~ 18~04791~.'),
  (1272, 1, 42, 15, 'Hereby ye shall be proved: By the life of Pharaoh ye shall not go forth hence, except your youngest brother come hither.', '0~02063~ 4~0974~: 7~02416~ 9~06547~ 14~03318~ 18~06996~ 19~0251~ 20~0935~'),
  (318, 1, 12, 17, 'And the LORD plagued Pharaoh and his house with great plagues because of Sarai Abram''s wife.', '2~03068~ 3~05060~ 4~06547~ 7~01004~ 9~01419~ 10~05061~ 12~01697~ 13~08297~ 14~087~ 15~0802~.'),
  (5088, 5, 5, 29, 'O that there were such an heart in them, that they would fear me, and keep all my commandments always, that it might be well with them, and with their children for ever!', '4~02088~ 5~04310~ 6~03824~ 8~05414~, 12~03372~ 15~08104~ 18~04687~ 19~03117~, 24~03190~ 30~01121~ 32~05769~!'),
  (4323, 4, 20, 7, 'And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,', '2~03068~ 3~01696~ 5~04872~, 6~0559~,'),
  (7195, 8, 3, 16, 'And when she came to her mother in law, she said, Who art thou, my daughter? And she told her all that the man had done to her.', '3~0935~ 8~02545~, 10~0559~, [12] 15~01323~? 18~05046~ 23~0376~ 25~06213~'),
  (23116, 39, 2, 4, 'And ye shall know that I have sent this commandment unto you, that my covenant might be with Levi, saith the LORD of hosts.', '3~03045~ 7~07971~ 9~04687~ 14~01285~ 18~03878~, 19~0559~ 21~03068~ 23~06635~.'),
  (10698, 13, 11, 17, 'And David longed, and said, Oh that one would give me drink of the water of the well of Bethlehem, that is at the gate!', '1~01732~ 2~0183~, 4~0559~, 11~08248~ 14~04325~ 17~0953~ 19~01035~, [21] 24~08179~!'),
  (29765, 54, 4, 2, 'Speaking lies in hypocrisy; having their conscience seared with a hot iron;', '1~5573~ 2~1722~ 3~5272~; 4~2743~ 5~2398~ 6~4893~ 11~2743~;'),
  (6651, 7, 5, 21, 'The river of Kishon swept them away, that ancient river, the river Kishon. O my soul, thou hast trodden down strength.', '1~05158~ 3~07028~ 6~01640~, 8~06917~ 9~05158~, 11~05158~ 12~07028~. 15~05315~, 19~01869~ 20~05797~.'),
  (19233, 24, 10, 23, 'O LORD, I know that the way of man is not in himself: it is not in man that walketh to direct his steps.', '1~03068~, 3~03045~ 6~01870~ 8~0120~ [9] [13 14] 17~0376~ 19~01980~ 21~03559~ 23~06806~.'),
  (143, 1, 6, 5, 'And God saw that the wickedness of man was great in the earth, and that every imagination of the thoughts of his heart was only evil continually.', '1~03068~ 2~07200~ 5~07451~ 7~0120~ [8] 9~07227~ 12~0776~, [14] 16~03336~ 19~04284~ 22~03820~ [23] 24~07535~ 25~07451~ 26~03117~.'),
  (13376, 18, 21, 12, 'They take the timbrel and harp, and rejoice at the sound of the organ.', '1~05375~ 3~08596~ 5~03658~, 7~08055~ 10~06963~ 13~05748~.'),
  (7337, 9, 5, 11, 'So they sent and gathered together all the lords of the Philistines, and said, Send away the ark of the God of Israel, and let it go again to his own place, that it slay us not, and our people: for there was a deadly destruction throughout all the city; the hand of God was very heavy there.', '2~07971~ 5~0622~ 8~05633~ 11~06430~, 13~0559~, 15~07971~ 17~0727~ 20~0430~ 22~03478~, 27~07725~ 31~04725~, 34~04191~ 39~05971~: 44~04194~ 45~04103~ 49~05892~; 51~03027~ 53~0430~ 55~03966~ 56~03513~'),
  (10614, 13, 8, 31, 'And Gedor, and Ahio, and Zacher.', '1~01446~, 3~0283~, 5~02144~.'),
  (742, 1, 27, 11, 'And Jacob said to Rebekah his mother, Behold, Esau my brother is a hairy man, and I am a smooth man:', '1~03290~ 2~0559~ 4~07259~ 6~0517~, 8~06215~ 10~0251~ [11] 13~08163~ 14~0376~, [17] 19~02509~ 20~0376~:'),
  (19600, 24, 26, 19, 'Did Hezekiah king of Judah and all Judah put him at all to death? did he not fear the LORD, and besought the LORD, and the LORD repented him of the evil which he had pronounced against them? Thus might we procure great evil against our souls.', '1~02396~ 2~04428~ 4~03063~ 7~03063~ 11~04191~ 13~04191~? 17~03373~ 19~03068~, 21~02470~ 23~06440~ 24~03068~,* 27~03068~ 28~05162~ 32~07451~ 36~01696~ 39~0587~ 42~06213~ 43~01419~ 44~07451~ 47~05315~.'),
  (28862, 47, 3, 5, 'Not that we are sufficient of ourselves to think any thing as of ourselves; but our sufficiency is of God;', '0~3756~ 1~3754~ 3~2070~ 4~2425~ 5~575~ 6~1438~ 8~3049~ 10~5100~ 11~5613~ 12~1537~ 13~1438~; 14~235~ 15~2257~ 16~2426~ [17] 18~1537~ 19~2316~;'),
  (13699, 18, 34, 7, 'What man is like Job, who drinketh up scorning like water?', '1~01397~ [2] 4~0347~, [5] 7~08354~ 8~03933~ 10~04325~?'),
  (9386, 11, 18, 37, 'Hear me, O LORD, hear me, that this people may know that thou art the LORD God, and that thou hast turned their heart back again.', '0~06030~ 3~03068~, 4~06030~ 8~05971~ 10~03045~ [13] 15~03068~ 16~0430~, [18] 21~05437~ 23~03820~ 24~05437~ 25~0322~.'),
  (11268, 14, 4, 14, 'He made also bases, and lavers made he upon the bases;', '1~06213~ 3~04350~, 5~03595~ 6~06213~ 10~04350~;'),
  (29913, 56, 1, 5, 'For this cause left I thee in Crete, that thou shouldest set in order the things that are wanting, and ordain elders in every city, as I had appointed thee:', '&para; 1~5127~ 2~5484~ 4~2641~ 5~4571~ 6~1722~ 7~2914~, 8~2443~ 13~1930~ 18~3007~, 19~2532~ 20~2525~ 21~4245~ 23~2596~ 24~4172~, 25~5613~ 26~1473~ 28~1299~ 29~4671~:'),
  (23426, 40, 9, 37, 'Then saith he unto his disciples, The harvest truly is plenteous, but the labourers are few;', '0~5119~ 1~3004~ 4~846~ 5~3101~, 7~2326~ 8~3303~ [9] 10~4183~, 11~1161~ 13~2040~ [14] 15~3641~;'),
  (26985, 44, 2, 20, 'The sun shall be turned into darkness, and the moon into blood, before that great and notable day of the Lord come:', '1~2246~ 4~3344~ 5~1519~ 6~4655~, 7~2532~ 9~4582~ 10~1519~ 11~129~, 12~4250~ 13~2228~ 14~3173~ 15~2532~ 16~2016~ 17~2250~ 20~2962~ 21~2064~:'),
  (27547, 44, 17, 8, 'And they troubled the people and the rulers of the city, when they heard these things.', '0~1161~ 2~5015~ 4~3793~ 5~2532~ 10~4173~, 13~191~ 15~5023~.'),
  (12173, 15, 6, 13, 'Then Tatnai, governor on this side the river, Shetharboznai, and their companions, according to that which Darius the king had sent, so they did speedily.', '&para; 0~0116~ 1~08674~, 2~06347~ 5~05675~ 7~05103~, 8~08370~, 11~03675~, 12~06903~ 16~01868~ 18~04430~ 20~07972~, 21~03660~ 23~05648~ 24~0629~.'),
  (16392, 19, 148, 12, 'Both young men, and maidens; old men, and children:', '2~0970~, 4~01330~; 6~02205~, 8~05288~:'),
  (14902, 19, 66, 20, 'Blessed be God, which hath not turned away my prayer, nor his mercy from me.', '0~01288~ [1] 2~0430~, 7~05493~ 9~08605~, 12~02617~'),
  (8925, 11, 6, 21, 'So Solomon overlaid the house within with pure gold: and he made a partition by the chains of gold before the oracle; and he overlaid it with gold.', '1~08010~ 2~06823~ 4~01004~ 5~06441~ 7~05462~ 8~02091~: 13~05674~ 16~07572~ 17~07572~* 19~02091~ 20~06440~ 22~01687~; 25~06823~ 28~02091~.'),
  (29075, 48, 1, 2, 'And all the brethren which are with me, unto the churches of Galatia:', '0~2532~ 1~3956~ 3~80~ 6~4862~ 7~1698~, 10~1577~ 12~1053~:'),
  (12502, 16, 7, 73, 'So the priests, and the Levites, and the porters, and the singers, and some of the people, and the Nethinims, and all Israel, dwelt in their cities; and when the seventh month came, the children of Israel were in their cities.', '2~03548~, 5~03881~, 8~07778~, 11~07891~, [13] 16~05971~, 19~05411~, 22~03478~, 23~03427~ 26~05892~; 30~07637~ 31~02320~ 32~05060~, 34~01121~ 36~03478~ [37] 40~05892~.'),
  (3187, 3, 15, 14, 'And on the eighth day he shall take to him two turtledoves, or two young pigeons, and come before the LORD unto the door of the tabernacle of the congregation, and give them unto the priest:', '3~08066~ 4~03117~ 7~03947~ 10~08147~ 11~08449~, 13~08147~ 14~01121~ 15~03123~, 17~0935~ 18~06440~ 20~03068~ 23~06607~ 26~0168~ 29~04150~, 31~05414~ 35~03548~:');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (25734, 42, 18, 32, 'For he shall be delivered unto the Gentiles, and shall be mocked, and spitefully entreated, and spitted on:', '0~1063~ 4~3860~ 7~1484~, 8~2532~ 11~1702~, 12~2532~ 14~5195~, 15~2532~ 17~1716~:'),
  (14820, 19, 60, 4, 'Thou hast given a banner to them that fear thee, that it may be displayed because of the truth. Selah.', '2~05414~ 4~05251~ 8~03373~ 14~05127~ 15~06440~ 18~07189~. 19~05542~.'),
  (26574, 43, 11, 36, 'Then said the Jews, Behold how he loved him!', '0~3767~ 1~3004~ 3~2453~, 4~2396~ 5~4459~ 7~5368~ 8~846~!'),
  (22539, 31, 1, 20, 'And the captivity of this host of the children of Israel shall possess that of the Canaanites, even unto Zarephath; and the captivity of Jerusalem, which is in Sepharad, shall possess the cities of the south.', '2~01546~ 5~02426~ 8~01121~ 10~03478~ [11 12] 16~03669~, [17] 19~06886~; 22~01546~ 24~03389~, [26] 28~05614~, 30~03423~ 32~05892~ 35~05045~.'),
  (21376, 26, 36, 8, 'But ye, O mountains of Israel, ye shall shoot forth your branches, and yield your fruit to my people of Israel; for they are at hand to come.', '3~02022~ 5~03478~, 9~05414~ 11~06057~, 13~05375~ 15~06529~ 18~05971~ 20~03478~; 25~07126~ 27~0935~.'),
  (3644, 4, 1, 35, 'Those that were numbered of them, even of the tribe of Manasseh, were thirty and two thousand and two hundred.', '3~06485~ [6] 9~04294~ 11~04519~, [12] 13~07970~ 15~08147~ 16~0505~ 19~03967~.'),
  (10016, 12, 17, 25, 'And so it was at the beginning of their dwelling there, that they feared not the LORD: therefore the LORD sent lions among them, which slew some of them.', '[1] 6~08462~ 9~03427~ [11] 13~03372~ 16~03068~: 19~03068~ 20~07971~ 21~0738~ 25~02026~ [26]'),
  (21483, 26, 39, 26, 'After that they have borne their shame, and all their trespasses whereby they have trespassed against me, when they dwelt safely in their land, and none made them afraid.', '4~05375~ 6~03639~, 10~04604~ 14~04603~ 19~03427~ 20~0983~ 23~0127~, [27] 28~02729~.'),
  (30165, 58, 10, 16, 'This is the covenant that I will make with them after those days, saith the Lord, I will put my laws into their hearts, and in their minds will I write them;', '0~3778~ [1] 3~1242~ 4~3739~ 7~1303~ 8~4314~ 9~846~ 10~3326~ 11~1565~ 12~2250~, 13~3004~ 15~2962~, 18~1325~ 19~3450~ 20~3551~ 21~1909~ 22~846~ 23~2588~, 24~2532~ 25~1909~ 26~846~ 27~1271~ 30~1924~ 31~846~;'),
  (18056, 23, 21, 12, 'The watchman said, The morning cometh, and also the night: if ye will inquire, inquire ye: return, come.', '1~08104~ 2~0559~, 4~01242~ 5~0857~, 9~03915~: 13~01158~, 14~01158~ 16~07725~, 17~0857~.'),
  (20687, 26, 11, 23, 'And the glory of the LORD went up from the midst of the city, and stood upon the mountain which is on the east side of the city.', '2~03519~ 5~03068~ 7~05927~ 10~08432~ 13~05892~, 15~05975~ 18~02022~ [20] 24~06924~ 27~05892~.'),
  (24634, 41, 10, 35, 'And James and John, the sons of Zebedee, come unto him, saying, Master, we would that thou shouldest do for us whatsoever we shall desire.', '0~2532~ 1~2385~ 2~2532~ 3~2491~, 5~5207~ 7~2199~, 8~4365~ 10~846~, 11~3004~, 12~1320~, 14~2309~ 15~2443~ 18~4160~ 20~2254~ 21~1437~ 22~3739~ 24~154~.'),
  (17710, 23, 2, 16, 'And upon all the ships of Tarshish, and upon all pleasant pictures.', '4~0591~ 6~08659~, 10~02532~ 11~07914~.'),
  (27300, 44, 10, 25, 'And as Peter was coming in, Cornelius met him, and fell down at his feet, and worshipped him.', '0~1161~ 1~5613~ 2~4074~ 3~1096~ 5~1525~, 6~2883~ 7~4876~ 8~846~, 11~4098~ 12~1909~ 14~4228~, 16~4352~ [17]'),
  (25252, 42, 7, 45, 'Thou gavest me no kiss: but this woman since the time I came in hath not ceased to kiss my feet.', '1~1325~ 2~3427~ 3~3756~ 4~5370~: 5~1161~ 7~3778~ 8~846~* 9~575~ 11~3739~ 14~1525~ 15~1257~ 16~3756~ 17~1257~ 19~2705~ 20~3450~ 21~4228~.'),
  (8519, 10, 18, 33, 'And the king was much moved, and went up to the chamber over the gate, and wept: and as he went, thus he said, O my son Absalom, my son, my son Absalom! would God I had died for thee, O Absalom, my son, my son!', '2~04428~ 5~07264~, 8~05927~ 11~05944~ 14~08179~, 16~01058~: 20~03212~, 23~0559~, 26~01121~ 27~053~, 29~01121~, 31~01121~ 32~053~! 37~04191~ 39~05414~, 41~053~, 43~01121~, 45~01121~!'),
  (6158, 6, 12, 22, 'The king of Kedesh, one; the king of Jokneam of Carmel, one;', '1~04428~ 3~06943~, 4~0259~; 6~04428~ 8~03362~ 10~03760~, 11~0259~;'),
  (7619, 9, 16, 17, 'And Saul said unto his servants, Provide me now a man that can play well, and bring him to me.', '1~07586~ 2~0559~ 5~05650~, 6~07200~ 10~0376~ 13~05059~ 14~03190~, 16~0935~ [17]'),
  (17012, 20, 21, 19, 'It is better to dwell in the wilderness, than with a contentious and an angry woman.', '&para; [0 1] 2~02896~ 4~03427~ 7~04057~ 8~0776~,* 12~04079~ 13~04066~* 16~03708~ 17~0802~.'),
  (25801, 42, 20, 8, 'And Jesus said unto them, Neither tell I you by what authority I do these things.', '0~2532~ 1~2424~ 2~2036~ 4~846~, 5~3761~ 6~3004~ 7~1473~ 8~5213~ 9~1722~ 10~4169~ 11~1849~ 13~4160~ 15~5023~.'),
  (23077, 38, 13, 9, 'And I will bring the third part through the fire, and will refine them as silver is refined, and will try them as gold is tried: they shall call on my name, and I will hear them: I will say, It is my people: and they shall say, The LORD is my God.', '3~0935~ 6~07992~ 9~0784~, 12~06884~ 15~03701~ 17~06884~, 20~0974~ 23~02091~ 25~0974~: 28~07121~ 31~08034~, 35~06030~ 39~0559~, [41] 43~05971~: 47~0559~, 49~03068~ [50] 52~0430~.'),
  (4375, 4, 21, 30, 'We have shot at them; Heshbon is perished even unto Dibon, and we have laid them waste even unto Nophah, which reacheth unto Medeba.', '2~03384~ 5~02809~ 7~06~ 10~01769~, 16~08074~ 19~05302~, [21] 23~04311~.'),
  (11577, 14, 18, 26, 'And say, Thus saith the king, Put this fellow in the prison, and feed him with bread of affliction and with water of affliction, until I return in peace.', '1~0559~, 3~0559~ 5~04428~, 6~07760~ [8] 11~03608~ 12~01004~,* 14~0398~ 17~03899~ 19~03906~ 22~04325~ 24~03906~, 27~07725~ 29~07965~.'),
  (4766, 4, 32, 42, 'And Nobah went and took Kenath, and the villages thereof, and called it Nobah, after his own name.', '1~05025~ 2~01980~ 4~03920~ 5~07079~, 8~01323~ 11~07121~ 13~05025~, 17~08034~.'),
  (25115, 42, 4, 40, 'Now when the sun was setting, all they that had any sick with divers diseases brought them unto him; and he laid his hands on every one of them, and healed them.', '0~1161~ 3~2246~ 5~1416~, 6~3956~ 8~3745~ 9~2192~ 11~770~ 13~4164~ 14~3554~ 15~71~ 16~846~ 17~4314~ 18~846~; 19~1161~ 21~2007~ 23~5495~ 24~2007~ 25~1538~ 26~1520~ 28~846~, 30~2323~ 31~846~.'),
  (30395, 60, 1, 5, 'Who are kept by the power of God through faith unto salvation ready to be revealed in the last time.', '0~3588~ 2~5432~ 3~1722~ 5~1411~ 7~2316~ 8~1223~ 9~4102~ 10~1519~ 11~4991~ 12~2092~ 15~601~ 16~1722~ 18~2078~ 19~2540~.'),
  (9462, 11, 21, 3, 'And Naboth said to Ahab, The LORD forbid it me, that I should give the inheritance of my fathers unto thee.', '1~05022~ 2~0559~ 4~0256~, 6~03068~ 7~02486~ 13~05414~ 15~05159~ 18~01~'),
  (20558, 26, 5, 3, 'Thou shalt also take thereof a few in number, and bind them in thy skirts.', '3~03947~ 6~04592~ 8~04557~, 10~06696~ 14~03671~.'),
  (28344, 45, 15, 25, 'But now I go unto Jerusalem to minister unto the saints.', '0~1161~ 1~3570~ 3~4198~ 4~1519~ 5~2419~ 7~1247~ 10~40~.'),
  (2411, 2, 30, 24, 'And of cassia five hundred shekels, after the shekel of the sanctuary, and of oil olive an hin:', '2~06916~ 3~02568~ 4~03967~ [5] 8~08255~ 11~06944~, 14~08081~ 15~02132~ 17~01969~:'),
  (27336, 44, 11, 13, 'And he shewed us how he had seen an angel in his house, which stood and said unto him, Send men to Joppa, and call for Simon, whose surname is Peter;', '0~5037~ 2~518~ 3~2254~ 4~4459~ 7~1492~ 9~32~ 10~1722~ 11~846~ 12~3624~, 14~2476~ 15~2532~ 16~2036~ 18~846~, 19~649~ 20~435~ 21~1519~ 22~2445~, 23~2532~ 25~3343~ 26~4613~, 29~1941~ 30~4074~;'),
  (27060, 44, 4, 22, 'For the man was above forty years old, on whom this miracle of healing was shewed.', '0~1063~ 2~444~ 3~2258~ 4~4119~ 5~5062~ 7~2094~, 8~1909~ 9~3739~ 10~5124~ 11~4592~ 13~2392~ 15~1096~.'),
  (10804, 13, 15, 5, 'Of the sons of Kohath; Uriel the chief, and his brethren an hundred and twenty:', '2~01121~ 4~06955~; 5~0222~ 7~08269~, 10~0251~ 12~03967~ 14~06242~:'),
  (6143, 6, 12, 7, 'And these are the kings of the country which Joshua and the children of Israel smote on this side Jordan on the west, from Baalgad in the valley of Lebanon even unto the mount Halak, that goeth up to Seir; which Joshua gave unto the tribes of Israel for a possession according to their divisions;', '&para; [2] 4~04428~ 7~0776~ 9~03091~ 12~01121~ 14~03478~ 15~05221~ 18~05676~ 19~03383~ 22~03220~, 24~01171~ 27~01237~ 29~03844~ 33~02022~ 34~02510~, 37~05927~ 39~08165~; 41~03091~ 42~05414~ 45~07626~ 47~03478~ [48] 50~03425~ 54~04256~;'),
  (22465, 30, 6, 6, 'That drink wine in bowls, and anoint themselves with the chief ointments: but they are not grieved for the affliction of Joseph.', '1~08354~ 2~03196~ 4~04219~, 6~04886~ 10~07225~ 11~08081~: 16~02470~ 19~07667~ 21~03130~.'),
  (23084, 38, 14, 7, 'But it shall be one day which shall be known to the LORD, not day, nor night: but it shall come to pass, that at evening time it shall be light.', '4~0259~ 5~03117~ 9~03045~ 12~03068~, 14~03117~, 16~03915~: [23] 25~06153~ 26~06256~ 30~0216~.'),
  (14605, 19, 44, 25, 'For our soul is bowed down to the dust: our belly cleaveth unto the earth.', '2~05315~ 5~07743~ 8~06083~: 10~0990~ 11~01692~ 14~0776~.'),
  (27201, 44, 8, 9, 'But there was a certain man, called Simon, which beforetime in the same city used sorcery, and bewitched the people of Samaria, giving out that himself was some great one:', '0~1161~ 4~5100~ 5~435~, 6~3686~ 7~4613~, 9~4391~ 10~1722~ 13~4172~ 15~3096~, 16~2532~ 17~1839~ 19~1484~ 21~4540~, 23~3004~ 25~1438~ 26~1511~ 27~5100~ 29~3173~:'),
  (14947, 19, 69, 3, 'I am weary of my crying: my throat is dried: mine eyes fail while I wait for my God.', '2~03021~ 5~07121~: 7~01627~ 9~02787~: 11~05869~ 12~03615~ 15~03176~ 18~0430~.'),
  (13811, 18, 38, 9, 'When I made the cloud the garment thereof, and thick darkness a swaddlingband for it,', '2~07760~ 4~06051~ 6~03830~ 10~06205~ 12~02854~'),
  (17875, 23, 10, 16, 'Therefore shall the Lord, the Lord of hosts, send among his fat ones leanness; and under his glory he shall kindle a burning like the burning of a fire.', '3~0113~, 5~0136~ 6~03068~* 8~06635~, 9~07971~ 13~04924~ 14~07332~; 18~03519~ 21~03344~ 23~03350~ 29~0784~.'),
  (15006, 19, 71, 21, 'Thou shalt increase my greatness, and comfort me on every side.', '2~07235~ 4~01420~, 6~05162~ 10~05437~.'),
  (19625, 24, 27, 20, 'Which Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon took not, when he carried away captive Jeconiah the son of Jehoiakim king of Judah from Jerusalem to Babylon, and all the nobles of Judah and Jerusalem;', '1~05019~ 2~04428~ 4~0894~ 5~03947~ 11~01540~ 12~03204~ 14~01121~ 16~03079~ 17~04428~ 19~03063~ 21~03389~ 23~0894~, 27~02715~ 29~03063~ 31~03389~;'),
  (4719, 4, 31, 49, 'And they said unto Moses, Thy servants have taken the sum of the men of war which are under our charge, and there lacketh not one man of us.', '2~0559~ 4~04872~, 6~05650~ 8~05375~ 10~07218~ 13~0582~ 15~04421~ [17] 20~03027~, 23~06485~ 26~0376~'),
  (23363, 40, 8, 8, 'The centurion answered and said, Lord, I am not worthy that thou shouldest come under my roof: but speak the word only, and my servant shall be healed.', '1~1543~ 2~611~ 3~2532~ 4~5346~, 5~2962~, 7~1510~ 8~3756~ 9~2425~ 10~2443~ 13~1525~ 14~5259~ 15~3450~ 16~4721~: 17~235~ 18~2036~ 20~3056~ 21~3440~, 22~2532~ 23~3450~ 24~3816~ 27~2390~.'),
  (10895, 13, 17, 24, 'Let it even be established, that thy name may be magnified for ever, saying, The LORD of hosts is the God of Israel, even a God to Israel: and let the house of David thy servant be established before thee.', '4~0539~, 7~08034~ 10~01431~ 11~05704~ 12~05769~, 13~0559~, 15~03068~ 17~06635~ [18] 20~0430~ 22~03478~, [23] 25~0430~ 27~03478~: [29] 31~01004~ 33~01732~ 35~05650~ [36] 37~03559~ 38~06440~'),
  (18103, 23, 23, 17, 'And it shall come to pass after the end of seventy years, that the LORD will visit Tyre, and she shall turn to her hire, and shall commit fornication with all the kingdoms of the world upon the face of the earth.', '8~07093~ 10~07657~ 11~08141~, 14~03068~ 16~06485~ 17~06865~, 21~07725~ 24~0868~, 28~02181~ 32~04467~ 35~0776~ 38~06440~ 41~0127~.'),
  (29243, 49, 1, 21, 'Far above all principality, and power, and might, and dominion, and every name that is named, not only in this world, but also in that which is to come:', '1~5231~ 2~3956~ 3~746~, 4~2532~ 5~1849~, 6~2532~ 7~1411~, 8~2532~ 9~2963~, 10~2532~ 11~3956~ 12~3686~ 15~3687~, 16~3756~ 17~3440~ 18~1722~ 19~5129~ 20~165~, 21~235~ 22~2532~ 23~1722~ 28~3195~:'),
  (10063, 12, 18, 31, 'Hearken not to Hezekiah: for thus saith the king of Assyria, Make an agreement with me by a present, and come out to me, and then eat ye every man of his own vine, and every one of his fig tree, and drink ye every one the waters of his cistern:', '0~08085~ 3~02396~: 6~0559~ 8~04428~ 10~0804~, 11~06213~ [12 13] 18~01293~, 21~03318~ [25] 26~0398~ 29~0376~ 33~01612~, 36~0376~ 40~08384~, 42~08354~ 45~0376~ 47~04325~ 50~0953~:'),
  (25843, 42, 21, 3, 'And he said, Of a truth I say unto you, that this poor widow hath cast in more than they all:', '0~2532~ 2~2036~, 5~230~ 7~3004~ 9~5213~, 10~3754~ 11~3778~ 12~4434~ 13~5503~ 15~906~ 18~4119~ 20~3956~:'),
  (21304, 26, 33, 15, 'If the wicked restore the pledge, give again that he had robbed, walk in the statutes of life, without committing iniquity; he shall surely live, he shall not die.', '[0] 2~07563~ 3~07725~ 5~02258~, 7~07999~ 11~01500~, 12~01980~ 15~02708~ 17~02416~, 19~06213~ 20~05766~; 23~02421~ 24~02421~, 28~04191~.'),
  (23736, 40, 17, 26, 'Peter saith unto him, Of strangers. Jesus saith unto him, Then are the children free.', '0~4074~ 1~3004~ 3~846~, 4~575~ 5~245~. 6~2424~ 7~5346~ 9~846~, 10~686~ 11~1526~ 13~5207~ 14~1658~.'),
  (11619, 14, 20, 23, 'For the children of Ammon and Moab stood up against the inhabitants of mount Seir, utterly to slay and destroy them: and when they had made an end of the inhabitants of Seir, every one helped to destroy another.', '2~01121~ 4~05983~ 6~04124~ 8~05975~ 11~03427~ 13~02022~ 14~08165~, 17~02763~ 19~08045~ [20] 27~03615~ 30~03427~ 32~08165~, 34~0376~ 35~05826~ 37~04889~ 38~07453~.'),
  (12733, 17, 1, 22, 'For he sent letters into all the king''s provinces, into every province according to the writing thereof, and to every people after their language, that every man should bear rule in his own house, and that it should be published according to the language of every people.', '2~07971~ 3~05612~ 7~04428~ 8~04082~, 11~04082~ 15~03791~ 20~05971~ 23~03956~, 26~0376~ 29~08323~ 33~01004~, [36] 39~01696~ 43~03956~ 46~05971~.'),
  (399, 1, 16, 14, 'Wherefore the well was called Beerlahairoi; behold, it is between Kadesh and Bered.', '2~0875~ 4~07121~ 5~02416~ 6~0883~;* [8 9] 11~06946~ 13~01260~.'),
  (10899, 13, 18, 1, 'Now after this it came to pass, that David smote the Philistines, and subdued them, and took Gath and her towns out of the hand of the Philistines.', '&para; 2~0310~ 8~01732~ 9~05221~ 11~06430~, 13~03665~ 16~03947~ 17~01661~ 20~01323~ 24~03027~ 27~06430~.'),
  (26135, 43, 2, 25, 'And needed not that any should testify of man: for he knew what was in man.', '0~3754~ 1~2532~* 2~2192~ 3~5532~* 4~3756~ 5~2443~ 6~5100~ 8~3140~ 9~4012~ 10~444~: 11~1063~ 12~846~ 13~1097~ 14~5101~ 15~2258~ 16~1722~ 17~444~.'),
  (23396, 40, 9, 7, 'And he arose, and departed to his house.', '0~2532~ 2~1453~, 4~565~ 5~1519~ 6~846~ 7~3624~.'),
  (25989, 42, 23, 40, 'But the other answering rebuked him, saying, Dost not thou fear God, seeing thou art in the same condemnation?', '0~1161~ 2~2087~ 3~611~ 4~2008~ 5~846~, 6~3004~, 7~5399~ 8~3761~ 9~4771~ 10~5399~ 11~2316~, 12~3754~ 14~1488~ 15~1722~ 17~846~ 18~2917~?'),
  (11862, 14, 30, 26, 'So there was great joy in Jerusalem: for since the time of Solomon the son of David king of Israel there was not the like in Jerusalem.', '3~01419~ 4~08057~ 6~03389~: 10~03117~ 12~08010~ 14~01121~ 16~01732~ 17~04428~ 19~03478~ [20 21] 26~03389~.'),
  (6819, 7, 10, 1, 'And after Abimelech there arose to defend Israel Tola the son of Puah the son of Dodo, a man of Issachar, and he dwelt in Shamir in mount Ephraim.', '&para; 1~0310~ 2~040~ 4~06965~ 6~03467~ 7~03478~ 8~08439~ 10~01121~ 12~06312~, 14~01121~ 16~01734~, 18~0376~ 20~03485~; 23~03427~ 25~08069~ 27~02022~ 28~0669~.'),
  (14024, 19, 8, 3, 'When I consider thy heavens, the work of thy fingers, the moon and the stars, which thou hast ordained;', '&para; 2~07200~ 4~08064~, 6~04639~ 9~0676~, 11~03394~ 14~03556~, 18~03559~;'),
  (11978, 14, 35, 3, 'And said unto the Levites that taught all Israel, which were holy unto the LORD, Put the holy ark in the house which Solomon the son of David king of Israel did build; it shall not be a burden upon your shoulders: serve now the LORD your God, and his people Israel,', '1~0559~ 4~03881~ 6~0995~ 8~03478~, 11~06918~ 14~03068~, 15~05414~ 17~06944~ 18~0727~ 21~01004~ 23~08010~ 25~01121~ 27~01732~ 28~04428~ 30~03478~ 32~01129~; [33 34] [36] 38~04853~ [40] 41~03802~: 42~05647~ 45~03068~ 47~0430~, 50~05971~ 51~03478~,'),
  (30871, 66, 9, 15, 'And the four angels were loosed, which were prepared for an hour, and a day, and a month, and a year, for to slay the third part of men.', '0~2532~ 2~5064~ 3~32~ 5~3089~, 6~3588~ 8~2090~ 9~1519~ 11~5610~, 12~2532~ 14~2250~, 15~2532~ 17~3376~, 18~2532~ 20~1763~, 22~2443~ 23~615~ 26~5154~ 28~444~.'),
  (4240, 4, 16, 41, 'But on the morrow all the congregation of the children of Israel murmured against Moses and against Aaron, saying, Ye have killed the people of the LORD.', '&para; 3~04283~ 6~05712~ 9~01121~ 11~03478~ 12~03885~ 14~04872~ 17~0175~, 18~0559~, 21~04191~ 23~05971~ 26~03068~.'),
  (1035, 1, 35, 19, 'And Rachel died, and was buried in the way to Ephrath, which is Bethlehem.', '1~07354~ 2~04191~, 5~06912~ 8~01870~ 10~0672~, [12] 13~01035~.'),
  (25792, 42, 19, 47, 'And he taught daily in the temple. But the chief priests and the scribes and the chief of the people sought to destroy him,', '0~2532~ 2~2258~ 3~1321~* 4~2250~ 5~2596~* 6~1722~ 8~2411~. 9~1161~ 12~749~ 13~2532~ 15~1122~ 16~2532~ 18~4413~ 21~2992~ 22~2212~ 24~622~ 25~846~,'),
  (17857, 23, 9, 19, 'Through the wrath of the LORD of hosts is the land darkened, and the people shall be as the fuel of the fire: no man shall spare his brother.', '2~05678~ 5~03068~ 7~06635~ 10~0776~ 11~06272~, 14~05971~ 19~03980~ 22~0784~: 24~0376~ 26~02550~ 28~0251~.'),
  (2397, 2, 30, 10, 'And Aaron shall make an atonement upon the horns of it once in a year with the blood of the sin offering of atonements: once in the year shall he make atonement upon it throughout your generations: it is most holy unto the LORD.', '1~0175~ 5~03722~ 8~07161~ 11~0259~ 14~08141~ 17~01818~ 21~02403~ 23~03725~: 24~0259~ 27~08141~ 31~03722~ 36~01755~: [38] 39~06944~ 40~06944~ 43~03068~.'),
  (8806, 11, 2, 28, 'Then tidings came to Joab: for Joab had turned after Adonijah, though he turned not after Absalom. And Joab fled unto the tabernacle of the LORD, and caught hold on the horns of the altar.', '1~08052~ 2~0935~ 4~03097~: 6~03097~ 8~05186~ 9~0310~ 10~0138~, 13~05186~ 15~0310~ 16~053~. 18~03097~ 19~05127~ 22~0168~ 25~03068~, 28~02388~ 31~07161~ 34~04196~.'),
  (4367, 4, 21, 22, 'Let me pass through thy land: we will not turn into the fields, or into the vineyards; we will not drink of the waters of the well: but we will go along by the king''s high way, until we be past thy borders.', '2~05674~ 5~0776~: 9~05186~ 12~07704~, 16~03754~; 20~08354~ [21] 23~04325~ 26~0875~: [27] 31~03212~ 34~04428~ [35] 36~01870~, 40~05674~ 42~01366~.'),
  (3215, 3, 16, 9, 'And Aaron shall bring the goat upon which the LORD''S lot fell, and offer him for a sin offering.', '1~0175~ 3~07126~ 5~08163~ 9~03068~ 10~01486~ 11~05927~, 13~06213~ [15] 18~02403~.'),
  (1852, 2, 12, 31, 'And he called for Moses and Aaron by night, and said, Rise up, and get you forth from among my people, both ye and the children of Israel; and go, serve the LORD, as ye have said.', '2~07121~ 4~04872~ 6~0175~ 8~03915~, 10~0559~, 12~06965~, [13] 16~03318~ 18~08432~ 20~05971~, 25~01121~ 27~03478~; 29~03212~, 30~05647~ 32~03068~, 36~01696~.'),
  (19157, 24, 7, 29, 'Cut off thine hair, O Jerusalem, and cast it away, and take up a lamentation on high places; for the LORD hath rejected and forsaken the generation of his wrath.', '&para; 1~01494~ 3~05145~, [4 5] [8] 9~07993~, 12~05375~ 14~07015~ 17~08205~; 20~03068~ 22~03988~ 24~05203~ 26~01755~ 29~05678~.'),
  (25133, 42, 5, 14, 'And he charged him to tell no man: but go, and shew thyself to the priest, and offer for thy cleansing, according as Moses commanded, for a testimony unto them.', '0~2532~ 1~846~ 2~3853~ 3~846~ 5~2036~ 7~3367~: 8~235~ 9~565~, 11~1166~ 12~4572~ 15~2409~, 16~2532~ 17~4374~ 18~4012~ 19~4675~ 20~2512~, 22~2531~ 23~3475~ 24~4367~, 25~1519~ 27~3142~ 29~846~.'),
  (4898, 4, 36, 13, 'These are the commandments and the judgments, which the LORD commanded by the hand of Moses unto the children of Israel in the plains of Moab by Jordan near Jericho.', '[1] 3~04687~ 6~04941~, 9~03068~ 10~06680~ 13~03027~ 15~04872~ 18~01121~ 20~03478~ 23~06160~ 25~04124~ 27~03383~ [28] 29~03405~.'),
  (13065, 18, 9, 5, 'Which removeth the mountains, and they know not: which overturneth them in his anger.', '1~06275~ 3~02022~, 6~03045~ 9~02015~ 13~0639~.'),
  (830, 1, 29, 31, 'And when the LORD saw that Leah was hated, he opened her womb: but Rachel was barren.', '&para; 3~03068~ 4~07200~ 6~03812~ [7] 8~08130~, 10~06605~ 12~07358~: 14~07354~ [15] 16~06135~.'),
  (5046, 5, 4, 36, 'Out of heaven he made thee to hear his voice, that he might instruct thee: and upon earth he shewed thee his great fire; and thou heardest his words out of the midst of the fire.', '2~08064~ 7~08085~ 9~06963~, 13~03256~ 17~0776~ 19~07200~ 22~01419~ 23~0784~; 26~08085~ 28~01697~ 32~08432~ 35~0784~.'),
  (5670, 5, 28, 53, 'And thou shalt eat the fruit of thine own body, the flesh of thy sons and of thy daughters, which the LORD thy God hath given thee, in the siege, and in the straitness, wherewith thine enemies shall distress thee:', '3~0398~ 5~06529~ 9~0990~, 11~01320~ 14~01121~ 18~01323~, 21~03068~ 23~0430~ 25~05414~ 29~04692~, 33~04689~, 36~0341~ 38~06693~'),
  (9992, 12, 17, 1, 'In the twelfth year of Ahaz king of Judah began Hoshea the son of Elah to reign in Samaria over Israel nine years.', '&para; 2~06240~ 3~08147~* 4~08141~ 6~0271~ 7~04428~ 9~03063~ 11~01954~ 13~01121~ 15~0425~ 17~04427~ 19~08111~ 21~03478~ 22~08672~ 23~08141~.'),
  (9254, 11, 14, 28, 'And it was so, when the king went into the house of the LORD, that the guard bare them, and brought them back into the guard chamber.', '[3] 4~01767~ 6~04428~ 7~0935~ 10~01004~ 13~03068~, 16~07323~ 17~05375~ 22~07725~ 25~07323~ 26~08372~.'),
  (23015, 38, 9, 7, 'And I will take away his blood out of his mouth, and his abominations from between his teeth: but he that remaineth, even he, shall be for our God, and he shall be as a governor in Judah, and Ekron as a Jebusite.', '4~05493~ 6~01818~ 10~06310~, 13~08251~ 17~08127~: 21~07604~, [24 25] 28~0430~, 35~0441~ 37~03063~, 39~06138~ 42~02983~.'),
  (18998, 24, 2, 24, 'A wild ass used to the wilderness, that snuffeth up the wind at her pleasure; in her occasion who can turn her away? all they that seek her will not weary themselves; in her month they shall find her.', '2~06501~ 3~03928~ 6~04057~, [7] 9~07602~ 11~07307~ 14~05315~ 15~0185~;* 18~08385~ 23~07725~? 27~01245~ 31~03286~ 35~02320~ 38~04672~'),
  (23666, 40, 15, 23, 'But he answered her not a word. And his disciples came and besought him, saying, Send her away; for she crieth after us.', '0~1161~ 2~611~ 3~846~ 4~3756~ 6~3056~. 7~2532~ 8~846~ 9~3101~ 10~4334~ 12~2065~ 13~846~, 14~3004~, 15~630~ 16~846~ 17~630~; 18~3754~ 20~2896~ 21~3693~ 22~2257~.'),
  (9346, 11, 17, 21, 'And he stretched himself upon the child three times, and cried unto the LORD, and said, O LORD my God, I pray thee, let this child''s soul come into him again.', '2~04058~ 6~03206~ 7~07969~ 8~06471~, 10~07121~ 13~03068~, 15~0559~, 17~03068~ 19~0430~, 25~03206~ 26~05315~ 27~07725~ 29~07130~ 30~07725~.'),
  (6498, 6, 24, 15, 'And if it seem evil unto you to serve the LORD, choose you this day whom ye will serve; whether the gods which your fathers served that were on the other side of the flood, or the gods of the Amorites, in whose land ye dwell: but as for me and my house, we will serve the LORD.', '&para; 4~07489~ 6~04310~ 8~05647~ 10~03068~, 11~0977~ 14~03117~ 15~05869~ 18~05647~; 21~0430~ 24~01~ 25~05647~ [27] 31~05676~ 34~05104~, 37~0430~ 40~0567~, 43~0776~ 45~03427~: 52~01004~, 55~05647~ 57~03068~.'),
  (14626, 19, 46, 3, 'Though the waters thereof roar and be troubled, though the mountains shake with the swelling thereof. Selah.', '[0] 2~04325~ 4~01993~ [5] 7~02560~, [8] 10~02022~ 11~07493~ 14~01346~ 16~05542~.'),
  (25003, 42, 2, 18, 'And all they that heard it wondered at those things which were told them by the shepherds.', '0~2532~ 1~3956~ 4~191~ [5] 6~2296~ 7~4012~ 10~3588~ 12~2980~ 13~846~ 14~4314~* 15~5259~ 17~4166~.'),
  (18488, 23, 41, 28, 'For I beheld, and there was no man; even among them, and there was no counsellor, that, when I asked of them, could answer a word.', '2~07200~, [4 5] 7~0376~; [12 13] 15~03289~, 19~07592~ 23~07725~ 25~01697~.'),
  (14737, 19, 54, 3, 'For strangers are risen up against me, and oppressors seek after my soul: they have not set God before them. Selah.', '1~02114~ 4~06965~ 8~06184~ 9~01245~ 12~05315~: 16~07760~ 17~0430~ 20~05542~.'),
  (7352, 9, 6, 14, 'And the cart came into the field of Joshua, a Bethshemite, and stood there, where there was a great stone: and they clave the wood of the cart, and offered the kine a burnt offering unto the LORD.', '2~05699~ 3~0935~ 6~07704~ 8~03091~, 10~01030~, 12~05975~ [15 16] 18~01419~ 19~068~: 22~01234~ 24~06086~ 27~05699~, 29~05927~ 31~06510~ 34~05930~ 37~03068~.'),
  (11070, 13, 25, 16, 'The ninth to Mattaniah, he, his sons, and his brethren, were twelve:', '1~08671~ 3~04983~, [4] 6~01121~, 9~0251~, [10] 11~06240~ 12~08147~:*'),
  (19705, 24, 31, 5, 'Thou shalt yet plant vines upon the mountains of Samaria: the planters shall plant, and shall eat them as common things.', '3~05193~ 4~03754~ 7~02022~ 9~08111~: 11~05193~ 13~05193~, [17] 20~02490~.'),
  (1468, 1, 48, 12, 'And Joseph brought them out from between his knees, and he bowed himself with his face to the earth.', '1~03130~ 4~03318~ 6~05973~ 8~01290~, 11~07812~ 15~0639~ 18~0776~.'),
  (10371, 13, 3, 2, 'The third, Absalom the son of Maachah the daughter of Talmai king of Geshur: the fourth, Adonijah the son of Haggith:', '1~07992~, 2~053~ 4~01121~ 6~04601~ 8~01323~ 10~08526~ 11~04428~ 13~01650~: 15~07243~, 16~0138~ 18~01121~ 20~02294~:'),
  (15426, 19, 92, 6, 'A brutish man knoweth not; neither doth a fool understand this.', '1~01198~ 2~0376~ 3~03045~ 8~03684~ 9~0995~'),
  (17750, 23, 5, 2, 'And he fenced it, and gathered out the stones thereof, and planted it with the choicest vine, and built a tower in the midst of it, and also made a winepress therein: and he looked that it should bring forth grapes, and it brought forth wild grapes.', '2~05823~ 8~05619~ 11~05193~ 16~08321~, 18~01129~ 20~04026~ 23~08432~ 28~02672~ 30~03342~ 34~06960~ 39~06213~ 40~06025~, 44~06213~ 46~0891~.'),
  (10461, 13, 5, 25, 'And they transgressed against the God of their fathers, and went a whoring after the gods of the people of the land, whom God destroyed before them.', '2~04603~ 5~0430~ 8~01~, 12~02181~ 13~0310~ 15~0430~ 18~05971~ 21~0776~, 23~0430~ 24~08045~ 25~06440~'),
  (9757, 12, 8, 22, 'Yet Edom revolted from under the hand of Judah unto this day. Then Libnah revolted at the same time.', '1~0123~ 2~06586~ 6~03027~ 8~03063~ 11~03117~. 13~03841~ 14~06586~ 17~01931~ 18~06256~.');
