VALUES
  (28430, 46, 3, 4, 'For while one saith, I am of Paul; and another, I am of Apollos; are ye not carnal?', '0~1063~ 1~3752~ 2~5100~ 3~3004~, 4~3303~ 5~1473~* 6~1510~ 8~3972~; 9~1161~ 10~2087~, 11~1473~ [12] 14~625~; 15~2075~ 17~3780~ 18~4559~?'),
  (23729, 40, 17, 19, 'Then came the disciples to Jesus apart, and said, Why could not we cast him out?', '0~5119~ 1~4334~ 3~3101~ 5~2424~ 6~2398~ 7~2596~,* 9~2036~, 10~1302~ 11~1410~ 12~3756~ 13~2249~ 14~1544~ 15~846~ 16~1544~?'),
  (5514, 5, 23, 8, 'The children that are begotten of them shall enter into the congregation of the LORD in their third generation.', '1~01121~ 4~03205~ 8~0935~ 11~06951~ 14~03068~ 17~07992~ 18~01755~.'),
  (12845, 17, 9, 2, 'The Jews gathered themselves together in their cities throughout all the provinces of the king Ahasuerus, to lay hand on such as sought their hurt: and no man could withstand them; for the fear of them fell upon all people.', '1~03064~ 4~06950~ 7~05892~ 11~04082~ 14~04428~ 15~0325~, 17~07971~ 18~03027~ 22~01245~ 24~07451~: 27~0376~ 29~05975~ 30~06440~; 33~06343~ 36~05307~ 39~05971~.'),
  (4940, 5, 1, 42, 'And the LORD said unto me, Say unto them, Go not up, neither fight; for I am not among you; lest ye be smitten before your enemies.', '2~03068~ 3~0559~ 6~0559~ 11~05927~, 13~03898~; [16] 18~07130~ 23~05062~ 24~06440~ 26~0341~.'),
  (14863, 19, 64, 4, 'That they may shoot in secret at the perfect: suddenly do they shoot at him, and fear not.', '3~03384~ 5~04565~ 8~08535~: 9~06597~ 12~03384~ 16~03372~'),
  (28291, 45, 13, 9, 'For this, Thou shalt not commit adultery, Thou shalt not kill, Thou shalt not steal, Thou shalt not bear false witness, Thou shalt not covet; and if there be any other commandment, it is briefly comprehended in this saying, namely, Thou shalt love thy neighbour as thyself.', '0~1063~ 3~3431~ 4~3756~ 6~3431~, 8~5407~ 9~3756~ 10~5407~, 12~2813~ 13~3756~ 14~2813~, 16~5576~ 17~3756~ 20~5576~, 22~1937~ 23~3756~ 24~1937~; 25~2532~ [27 28] 29~1536~ 30~2087~ 31~1785~, 35~346~ 36~1722~ 37~5129~ 38~3056~, 39~1722~, 42~25~ 43~4675~ 44~4139~ 45~5613~ 46~1438~.'),
  (27091, 44, 5, 16, 'There came also a multitude out of the cities round about unto Jerusalem, bringing sick folks, and them which were vexed with unclean spirits: and they were healed every one.', '0~1161~ 1~4905~ 2~2532~ 4~4128~ [5] 8~4172~ 10~4038~ 11~1519~ 12~2419~, 13~5342~ 14~772~ 16~2532~ 20~3791~ 21~5259~ 22~169~ 23~4151~: 25~3748~ 27~2323~ 29~537~.'),
  (6450, 6, 22, 17, 'Is the iniquity of Peor too little for us, from which we are not cleansed until this day, although there was a plague in the congregation of the LORD,', '[0] 2~05771~ 4~06465~ 6~04592~ 14~02891~ 17~03117~, 22~05063~ 25~05712~ 28~03068~,'),
  (7442, 9, 10, 17, 'And Samuel called the people together unto the LORD to Mizpeh;', '&para; 1~08050~ 2~06817~ 4~05971~ 8~03068~ 10~04709~;'),
  (1447, 1, 47, 22, 'Only the land of the priests bought he not; for the priests had a portion assigned them of Pharaoh, and did eat their portion which Pharaoh gave them: wherefore they sold not their lands.', '2~0127~ 5~03548~ 7~07069~ 11~03548~ 14~02706~ [15 16] 18~06547~, 21~0398~ 23~02706~ 25~06547~ 26~05414~ 30~04376~ 33~0127~.'),
  (13492, 18, 27, 2, 'As God liveth, who hath taken away my judgment; and the Almighty, who hath vexed my soul;', '[0] 1~0410~ 2~02416~, [3] 6~05493~ 8~04941~; 11~07706~, [12] 14~04843~ 16~05315~;'),
  (22313, 29, 1, 13, 'Gird yourselves, and lament, ye priests: howl, ye ministers of the altar: come, lie all night in sackcloth, ye ministers of my God: for the meat offering and the drink offering is withholden from the house of your God.', '0~02296~ 3~05594~, 5~03548~: 6~03213~, 8~08334~ 11~04196~: 12~0935~, 15~03885~ 17~08242~, 19~08334~ 22~0430~: 26~04503~ 30~05262~ 32~04513~ 35~01004~ 38~0430~.'),
  (3662, 4, 1, 53, 'But the Levites shall pitch round about the tabernacle of testimony, that there be no wrath upon the congregation of the children of Israel: and the Levites shall keep the charge of the tabernacle of testimony.', '2~03881~ 4~02583~ 6~05439~ 8~04908~ 10~05715~, 15~07110~ 18~05712~ 21~01121~ 23~03478~: 26~03881~ 28~08104~ 30~04931~ 33~04908~ 35~05715~.'),
  (29352, 49, 5, 32, 'This is a great mystery: but I speak concerning Christ and the church.', '0~5124~ 1~2076~ 3~3173~ 4~3466~: 5~1161~ 6~1473~ 7~3004~ 8~1519~ 9~5547~ 10~2532~ 11~1519~ 12~1577~.'),
  (27067, 44, 4, 29, 'And now, Lord, behold their threatenings: and grant unto thy servants, that with all boldness they may speak thy word,', '0~2532~ 1~3569~, 2~2962~, 3~1896~ 4~1909~* 5~846~ 6~547~: 7~2532~ 9~1325~ 10~4675~ 11~1401~, 13~3326~ 14~3956~ 15~3954~ 18~2980~ 19~4675~ 20~3056~,'),
  (15680, 19, 106, 20, 'Thus they changed their glory into the similitude of an ox that eateth grass.', '2~04171~ 4~03519~ 7~08403~ 10~07794~ 12~0398~ 13~06212~.'),
  (23652, 40, 15, 9, 'But in vain they do worship me, teaching for doctrines the commandments of men.', '0~1161~ 2~3155~ 5~4576~ 6~3165~, 7~1321~ [8] 9~1319~ 11~1778~ 13~444~.'),
  (12941, 18, 4, 2, 'If we assay to commune with thee, wilt thou be grieved? but who can withhold himself from speaking?', '[0] 2~05254~ 4~01697~ 10~03811~? 13~03201~ 14~06113~ 17~04405~?'),
  (70, 1, 3, 14, 'And the LORD God said unto the serpent, Because thou hast done this, thou art cursed above all cattle, and above every beast of the field; upon thy belly shalt thou go, and dust shalt thou eat all the days of thy life:', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~0430~ 4~0559~ 7~05175~, 9~0859~ 11~06213~ [14] 15~0779~ 18~0929~, 22~02416~ 25~07704~; 28~01512~ 31~03212~, 33~06083~ 36~0398~ 39~03117~ 42~02416~:'),
  (3037, 3, 11, 35, 'And every thing whereupon any part of their carcase falleth shall be unclean; whether it be oven, or ranges for pots, they shall be broken down: for they are unclean, and shall be unclean unto you.', '[2] [4 5] 8~05038~ 9~05307~ 12~02930~; [13 15] 16~08574~, 18~03600~ 25~05422~: [26] [28] 29~02931~, 33~02931~'),
  (22139, 28, 3, 2, 'So I bought her to me for fifteen pieces of silver, and for an homer of barley, and an half homer of barley:', '2~03739~ 7~02568~ [8] 8~06240~ 10~03701~, [12] 14~02563~ 16~08184~, 20~03963~ 22~08184~:'),
  (5659, 5, 28, 42, 'All thy trees and fruit of thy land shall the locust consume.', '2~06086~ 4~06529~ 7~0127~ 10~06767~ 11~03423~.'),
  (24198, 40, 27, 59, 'And when Joseph had taken the body, he wrapped it in a clean linen cloth,', '0~2532~ 2~2501~ 4~2983~ 6~4983~, 8~1794~ 9~846~ 12~2513~ 14~4616~,'),
  (30101, 58, 7, 21, '(For those priests were made without an oath; but this with an oath by him that said unto him, The Lord sware and will not repent, Thou art a priest for ever after the order of Melchisedec:)', '0~(1063~ 2~2409~ 3~1526~ 4~3303~* 5~1096~ 6~5565~ 8~3728~; 9~1161~ 11~3326~ 13~3728~ 14~1223~ 17~3004~ 18~4314~ 19~846~, 21~2962~ 22~3660~ 23~2532~ 24~3338~ 25~3756~ 26~3338~, 27~4771~ [28] 30~2409~ 31~1519~ 32~165~ 33~2596~ 35~5010~ 37~3198~:)'),
  (24736, 41, 13, 8, 'For nation shall rise against nation, and kingdom against kingdom: and there shall be earthquakes in divers places, and there shall be famines and troubles: these are the beginnings of sorrows.', '0~1063~ 1~1484~ 3~1453~ 4~1909~ 5~1484~, 6~2532~ 7~932~ 8~1909~ 9~932~: 10~2532~ 13~2071~ 14~4578~ 16~2596~ 17~5117~, 18~2532~ 21~2071~ 22~3042~ 23~2532~ 24~5016~: 25~5023~ [26] 28~746~ 30~5604~.'),
  (2037, 2, 19, 6, 'And ye shall be unto me a kingdom of priests, and an holy nation. These are the words which thou shalt speak unto the children of Israel.', '7~04467~ 9~03548~, 12~06918~ 13~01471~. [15] 17~01697~ 21~01696~ 24~01121~ 26~03478~.'),
  (8624, 10, 22, 14, 'The LORD thundered from heaven, and the most High uttered his voice.', '1~03068~ 2~07481~ 4~08064~, 8~05945~ 9~05414~ 11~06963~.'),
  (10150, 12, 21, 23, 'And the servants of Amon conspired against him, and slew the king in his own house.', '2~05650~ 4~0526~ 5~07194~ 9~04191~ 11~04428~ 15~01004~.'),
  (18320, 23, 34, 8, 'For it is the day of the Lord''s vengeance, and the year of recompenses for the controversy of Zion.', '[1 2] 4~03117~ 7~03068~ 8~05359~, [9] 11~08141~ 13~07966~ 16~07379~ 18~06726~.'),
  (17096, 20, 24, 8, 'He that deviseth to do evil shall be called a mischievous person.', '2~02803~ 5~07489~ 8~07121~ 10~04209~ 11~01167~.'),
  (9478, 11, 21, 19, 'And thou shalt speak unto him, saying, Thus saith the LORD, Hast thou killed, and also taken possession? And thou shalt speak unto him, saying, Thus saith the LORD, In the place where dogs licked the blood of Naboth shall dogs lick thy blood, even thine.', '3~01696~ 6~0559~, 8~0559~ 10~03068~, 13~07523~, 17~03423~? 21~01696~ 24~0559~, 26~0559~ 28~03068~, 31~04725~ 33~03611~ 34~03952~ 36~01818~ 38~05022~ 40~03611~ 41~03952~ 43~01818~,'),
  (4086, 4, 13, 6, 'Of the tribe of Judah, Caleb the son of Jephunneh.', '2~04294~ 4~03063~, 5~03612~ 7~01121~ 9~03312~.'),
  (23600, 40, 13, 51, 'Jesus saith unto them, Have ye understood all these things? They say unto him, Yea, Lord.', '0~2424~ 1~3004~ 3~846~, 6~4920~ 7~3956~ 8~5023~ 9~3956~? 11~3004~ 13~846~, 14~3483~, 15~2962~.'),
  (17034, 20, 22, 10, 'Cast out the scorner, and contention shall go out; yea, strife and reproach shall cease.', '&para; 1~01644~ 3~03887~, 5~04066~ 8~03318~; 10~01779~ 12~07036~ 14~07673~.'),
  (2717, 2, 40, 5, 'And thou shalt set the altar of gold for the incense before the ark of the testimony, and put the hanging of the door to the tabernacle.', '3~05414~ 5~04196~ 7~02091~ 10~07004~ 11~06440~ 13~0727~ 16~05715~, 18~07760~ 20~04539~ 23~06607~ 26~04908~.'),
  (24741, 41, 13, 13, 'And ye shall be hated of all men for my name''s sake: but he that shall endure unto the end, the same shall be saved.', '0~2532~ 3~2071~ 4~3404~ 5~5259~ 6~3956~ [7] 8~1223~ 9~3450~ 11~3686~ 12~1223~:* 13~1161~ 17~5278~ 18~1519~ 20~5056~, 22~3778~ 25~4982~.'),
  (18234, 23, 30, 8, 'Now go, write it before them in a table, and note it in a book, that it may be for the time to come for ever and ever:', '&para; 1~0935~, 2~03789~ 8~03871~, 10~02710~ 14~05612~, 21~03117~ 23~0314~ 24~05704~ 25~05703~ 27~05769~:'),
  (28016, 45, 3, 9, 'What then? are we better than they? No, in no wise: for we have before proved both Jews and Gentiles, that they are all under sin;', '0~5101~ 1~3767~? 4~4284~ [5 6] 7~3756~, 10~3843~: 11~1063~ 15~4256~ 16~5037~ 17~2453~ 18~2532~ 19~1672~, 22~1511~ 23~3956~ 24~5259~ 25~266~;'),
  (26685, 43, 14, 2, 'In my Father''s house are many mansions: if it were not so, I would have told you. I go to prepare a place for you.', '0~1722~ 1~3450~ 2~3962~ 3~3614~ 4~1526~ 5~4183~ 6~3438~: [8 9] 10~1490~ [11] 15~2036~ 16~302~* 17~5213~. 19~4198~ 21~2090~ 23~5117~ 25~5213~.'),
  (5607, 5, 27, 16, 'Cursed be he that setteth light by his father or his mother. And all the people shall say, Amen.', '0~0779~ [1] 5~07034~ 8~01~ 11~0517~. 15~05971~ 17~0559~, 18~0543~.'),
  (26195, 43, 4, 24, 'God is a Spirit: and they that worship him must worship him in spirit and in truth.', '0~2316~ [1] 3~4151~: 4~2532~ 7~4352~ 8~846~ 9~1163~ 10~4352~ [11] 12~1722~ 13~4151~ 14~2532~ 16~225~.'),
  (10361, 13, 2, 47, 'And the sons of Jahdai; Regem, and Jotham, and Gesham, and Pelet, and Ephah, and Shaaph.', '2~01121~ 4~03056~; 5~07276~, 7~03147~, 9~01529~, 11~06404~, 13~05891~, 15~08174~.'),
  (29891, 55, 4, 5, 'But watch thou in all things, endure afflictions, do the work of an evangelist, make full proof of thy ministry.', '0~1161~ 1~3525~ 2~4771~ 3~1722~ 5~3956~, 7~2553~, 8~4160~ 10~2041~ 13~2099~, 16~4135~ 18~4675~ 19~1248~.'),
  (459, 1, 18, 31, 'And he said, Behold now, I have taken upon me to speak unto the Lord: Peradventure there shall be twenty found there. And he said, I will not destroy it for twenty''s sake.', '2~0559~, 9~02974~ 11~01696~ 14~0136~: 19~06242~ 20~04672~ 24~0559~, 28~07843~ [29] 31~06242~'),
  (1721, 2, 8, 6, 'And Aaron stretched out his hand over the waters of Egypt; and the frogs came up, and covered the land of Egypt.', '1~0175~ 3~05186~ 5~03027~ 8~04325~ 10~04714~; 13~06854~ 15~05927~, 17~03680~ 19~0776~ 21~04714~.'),
  (24467, 41, 6, 50, 'For they all saw him, and were troubled. And immediately he talked with them, and saith unto them, Be of good cheer: it is I; be not afraid.', '0~1063~ 2~3956~ 3~1492~ 4~846~, 5~2532~ 7~5015~. 8~2532~ 9~2112~ 11~2980~ 12~3326~ 13~846~, 14~2532~ 15~3004~ 17~846~, 21~2293~: 23~1510~ 24~1473~; 25~5399~ 26~3361~ 27~5399~.'),
  (16947, 20, 19, 13, 'A foolish son is the calamity of his father: and the contentions of a wife are a continual dropping.', '&para; 1~03684~ 2~01121~ [3] 5~01942~ 8~01~: 11~04079~ 14~0802~ [15] 17~02956~ 18~01812~.'),
  (30389, 59, 5, 19, 'Brethren, if any of you do err from the truth, and one convert him;', '0~80~, 1~1437~ 2~5100~ 3~1722~ 4~5213~ 6~4105~ 7~575~ 9~225~, 10~2532~ 11~5100~ 12~1994~ 13~846~;'),
  (6826, 7, 10, 8, 'And that year they vexed and oppressed the children of Israel: eighteen years, all the children of Israel that were on the other side Jordan in the land of the Amorites, which is in Gilead.', '2~08141~ 4~07492~ 6~07533~ 8~01121~ 10~03478~: 11~06240~ 12~08083~* 13~08141~, 16~01121~ 18~03478~ [20] 24~05676~ 25~03383~ 28~0776~ 31~0567~, [33] 35~01568~.'),
  (128, 1, 5, 22, 'And Enoch walked with God after he begat Methuselah three hundred years, and begat sons and daughters:', '1~02585~ 2~01980~ 3~0854~ 4~0430~ 5~0310~ 7~03205~ 8~0853~* 9~04968~ 10~07969~ 11~03967~ 12~08141~, 14~03205~ 15~01121~ 17~01323~:'),
  (15156, 19, 78, 34, 'When he slew them, then they sought him: and they returned and inquired early after God.', '2~02026~ 6~01875~ 10~07725~ 13~07836~ 15~0410~.'),
  (27357, 44, 12, 4, 'And when he had apprehended him, he put him in prison, and delivered him to four quaternions of soldiers to keep him; intending after Easter to bring him forth to the people.', '0~2532~ 1~3739~ 4~4084~ 7~5087~ [8] 9~1519~ 10~5438~, 12~3860~ [13] 15~5064~ 16~5069~ 18~4757~ 20~5442~ 21~846~; 22~1014~ 23~3326~ 24~3957~ 26~321~ 27~846~ 28~321~ 31~2992~.'),
  (19553, 24, 25, 10, 'Moreover I will take from them the voice of mirth, and the voice of gladness, the voice of the bridegroom, and the voice of the bride, the sound of the millstones, and the light of the candle.', '3~06~ 7~06963~ 9~08342~, 12~06963~ 14~08057~, 16~06963~ 19~02860~, 22~06963~ 25~03618~, 27~06963~ 30~07347~, 33~0216~ 36~05216~.'),
  (25545, 42, 13, 14, 'And the ruler of the synagogue answered with indignation, because that Jesus had healed on the sabbath day, and said unto the people, There are six days in which men ought to work: in them therefore come and be healed, and not on the sabbath day.', '0~1161~ 5~752~ 6~611~ 8~23~, 9~3754~ 11~2424~ 13~2323~ 16~4521~ 19~3004~ 22~3793~, 24~1526~ 25~1803~ 26~2250~ 27~1722~ 28~3739~ 30~1163~ 32~2038~: 33~1722~ 34~5025~ 35~3767~ 36~2064~ 39~2323~, 40~2532~ 41~3361~ 44~4521~ 45~2250~.'),
  (5507, 5, 23, 1, 'He that is wounded in the stones, or hath his privy member cut off, shall not enter into the congregation of the LORD.', '&para; 6~06481~ 7~01795~,* 12~08212~ 14~03772~, 17~0935~ 20~06951~ 23~03068~.'),
  (20174, 24, 49, 38, 'And I will set my throne in Elam, and will destroy from thence the king and the princes, saith the LORD.', '3~07760~ 5~03678~ 7~05867~, 10~06~ 14~04428~ 17~08269~, 18~05002~ 20~03068~.'),
  (11143, 13, 27, 26, 'And over them that did the work of the field for tillage of the ground was Ezri the son of Chelub:', '4~06213~ 6~04399~ 9~07704~ 11~05656~ 14~0127~ [15] 16~05836~ 18~01121~ 20~03620~:'),
  (2296, 2, 27, 19, 'All the vessels of the tabernacle in all the service thereof, and all the pins thereof, and all the pins of the court, shall be of brass.', '2~03627~ 5~04908~ 9~05656~ 14~03489~ 19~03489~ 22~02691~, [23 25] 26~05178~.'),
  (16675, 20, 10, 10, 'He that winketh with the eye causeth sorrow: but a prating fool shall fall.', '&para; 2~07169~ 5~05869~ 6~05414~ 7~06094~: 10~08193~ 11~0191~ 13~03832~.'),
  (4618, 4, 29, 4, 'And one tenth deal for one lamb, throughout the seven lambs:', '1~0259~ 3~06241~ 5~0259~ 6~03532~, 9~07651~ 10~03532~:'),
  (12272, 15, 10, 11, 'Now therefore make confession unto the LORD God of your fathers, and do his pleasure: and separate yourselves from the people of the land, and from the strange wives.', '2~05414~ 3~08426~ 6~03068~ 7~0430~ 10~01~, 12~06213~ 14~07522~: 16~0914~ 20~05971~ 23~0776~, 27~05237~ 28~0802~.'),
  (1018, 1, 35, 2, 'Then Jacob said unto his household, and to all that were with him, Put away the strange gods that are among you, and be clean, and change your garments:', '1~03290~ 2~0559~ 5~01004~, [10] 14~05493~ 16~05236~ 17~0430~ [19] 21~08432~, 24~02891~, 26~02498~ 28~08071~:'),
  (659, 1, 24, 64, 'And Rebekah lifted up her eyes, and when she saw Isaac, she lighted off the camel.', '1~07259~ 3~05375~ 5~05869~, 9~07200~ 10~03327~, 12~05307~ 13~05921~ 15~01581~.'),
  (4347, 4, 21, 2, 'And Israel vowed a vow unto the LORD, and said, If thou wilt indeed deliver this people into my hand, then I will utterly destroy their cities.', '1~03478~ 2~05087~ 4~05088~ 7~03068~, 9~0559~, 13~05414~ 14~05414~ 16~05971~ 19~03027~, 24~02763~ 26~05892~.'),
  (12016, 14, 36, 14, 'Moreover all the chief of the priests, and the people, transgressed very much after all the abominations of the heathen; and polluted the house of the LORD which he had hallowed in Jerusalem.', '3~08269~ 6~03548~, 9~05971~, 10~04603~ 11~04604~ 12~07235~ 16~08441~ 19~01471~; 21~02930~ 23~01004~ 26~03068~ 30~06942~ 32~03389~.'),
  (26916, 43, 21, 2, 'There were together Simon Peter, and Thomas called Didymus, and Nathanael of Cana in Galilee, and the sons of Zebedee, and two other of his disciples.', '1~2258~ 2~3674~ 3~4613~ 4~4074~, 5~2532~ 6~2381~ 7~3004~ 8~1324~, 9~2532~ 10~3482~ 11~575~ 12~2580~ 14~1056~, 15~2532~ [17] 17~3588~ 19~2199~, 20~2532~ 21~1417~ 22~243~ 23~1537~ 24~846~ 25~3101~.'),
  (29981, 58, 1, 2, 'Hath in these last days spoken unto us by his Son, whom he hath appointed heir of all things, by whom also he made the worlds;', '0~2980~ 1~1909~ 2~5130~ 3~2078~ 4~2250~ 5~2980~ 7~2254~ 8~1722~ [9] 10~5207~, 11~3739~ 14~5087~ 15~2818~ 18~3956~, 19~1223~ 20~3739~ 21~2532~ 23~4160~ 25~165~;'),
  (5084, 5, 5, 25, 'Now therefore why should we die? for this great fire will consume us: if we hear the voice of the LORD our God any more, then we shall die.', '5~04191~? 8~01419~ 9~0784~ 11~0398~ 15~08085~ 17~06963~ 20~03068~ 22~0430~ 24~03254~, 28~04191~.'),
  (15427, 19, 92, 7, 'When the wicked spring as the grass, and when all the workers of iniquity do flourish; it is that they shall be destroyed for ever:', '&para; 2~07563~ 3~06524~ 6~06212~, 11~06466~ 13~0205~ 15~06692~; [16 17] 22~08045~ 24~05703~:'),
  (22047, 27, 11, 2, 'And now will I shew thee the truth. Behold, there shall stand up yet three kings in Persia; and the fourth shall be far richer than they all: and by his strength through his riches he shall stir up all against the realm of Grecia.', '4~05046~ 7~0571~. 12~05975~ 14~07969~ 15~04428~ 17~06539~; 20~07243~ 23~06239~ 24~06238~ [26] 27~01419~: 31~02393~ 34~06239~ 38~05782~ 42~04438~ 44~03120~.'),
  (10917, 13, 19, 2, 'And David said, I will shew kindness unto Hanun the son of Nahash, because his father shewed kindness to me. And David sent messengers to comfort him concerning his father. So the servants of David came into the land of the children of Ammon to Hanun, to comfort him.', '1~01732~ 2~0559~, 5~06213~ 6~02617~ 8~02586~ 10~01121~ 12~05176~, 15~01~ 16~06213~ 17~02617~ 21~01732~ 22~07971~ 23~04397~ 25~05162~ 29~01~. 32~05650~ 34~01732~ 35~0935~ 38~0776~ 41~01121~ 43~05983~ 45~02586~, 47~05162~'),
  (6249, 6, 15, 40, 'And Cabbon, and Lahmam, and Kithlish,', '1~03522~, 3~03903~, 5~03798~,'),
  (14809, 19, 59, 10, 'The God of my mercy shall prevent me: God shall let me see my desire upon mine enemies.', '1~0430~ 4~02617~ 6~06923~ 8~0430~ 12~07200~ [13 14] 17~08324~.'),
  (28031, 45, 3, 24, 'Being justified freely by his grace through the redemption that is in Christ Jesus:', '1~1344~ 2~1432~ 4~846~ 5~5485~ 6~1223~ 8~629~ 11~1722~ 12~5547~ 13~2424~:'),
  (17721, 23, 3, 5, 'And the people shall be oppressed, every one by another, and every one by his neighbour: the child shall behave himself proudly against the ancient, and the base against the honourable.', '2~05971~ 5~05065~, 7~0376~ 9~0376~, 12~0376~ 15~07453~: 17~05288~ 21~07292~ 24~02205~, 27~07034~ 30~03513~.'),
  (27311, 44, 10, 36, 'The word which God sent unto the children of Israel, preaching peace by Jesus Christ: (he is Lord of all:)', '1~3056~ 2~3739~ [3] 4~649~ 7~5207~ 9~2474~, 10~2097~ 11~1515~ 12~1223~ 13~2424~ 14~5547~: 15~3778~* 17~2076~ 18~2962~ 20~3956~:)'),
  (843, 1, 30, 9, 'When Leah saw that she had left bearing, she took Zilpah her maid, and gave her Jacob to wife.', '1~03812~ 2~07200~ 6~05975~ 7~03205~, 9~03947~ 10~02153~ 12~08198~, 14~05414~ 16~03290~ 18~0802~.'),
  (9439, 11, 20, 23, 'And the servants of the king of Syria said unto him, Their gods are gods of the hills; therefore they were stronger than we; but let us fight against them in the plain, and surely we shall be stronger than they.', '2~05650~ 5~04428~ 7~0758~ 8~0559~ 12~0430~ [13] 14~0430~ 17~02022~; 21~02388~ 24~0199~ 27~03898~ 32~04334~, 34~03808~ 38~02388~'),
  (26508, 43, 10, 12, 'But he that is an hireling, and not the shepherd, whose own the sheep are not, seeth the wolf coming, and leaveth the sheep, and fleeth: and the wolf catcheth them, and scattereth the sheep.', '0~1161~ 3~5607~ 5~3411~, 6~2532~ 7~3756~ 9~4166~, 10~3739~ 11~2398~ 13~4263~ 14~1526~ 15~3756~, 16~2334~ 18~3074~ 19~2064~, 20~2532~ 21~863~ 23~4263~, 24~2532~ 25~5343~: 26~2532~ 28~3074~ 29~726~ 30~846~, 31~2532~ 32~4650~ 34~4263~.'),
  (8853, 11, 4, 1, 'So king Solomon was king over all Israel.', '&para; 1~04428~ 2~08010~ 4~04428~ 7~03478~.'),
  (20760, 26, 14, 20, 'Though Noah, Daniel, and Job, were in it, as I live, saith the Lord GOD, they shall deliver neither son nor daughter; they shall but deliver their own souls by their righteousness.', '1~05146~, 2~01840~, 4~0347~, [5] 7~08432~, [8] 10~02416~, 11~05002~ 13~0136~ 14~03069~, 17~05337~ 19~01121~ 20~0518~ 21~01323~; [24] 25~05337~ 28~05315~ 31~06666~.'),
  (18041, 23, 20, 3, 'And the LORD said, Like as my servant Isaiah hath walked naked and barefoot three years for a sign and wonder upon Egypt and upon Ethiopia;', '2~03068~ 3~0559~, 7~05650~ 8~03470~ 10~01980~ 11~06174~ 13~03182~ 14~07969~ 15~08141~ [16] 18~0226~ 20~04159~ 22~04714~ 25~03568~;'),
  (15512, 19, 99, 4, 'The king''s strength also loveth judgment; thou dost establish equity, thou executest judgment and righteousness in Jacob.', '1~04428~ 2~05797~ 4~0157~ 5~04941~; 8~03559~ 9~04339~, 11~06213~ 12~04941~ 14~06666~ 16~03290~.'),
  (25956, 42, 23, 7, 'And as soon as he knew that he belonged unto Herod''s jurisdiction, he sent him to Herod, who himself also was at Jerusalem at that time.', '0~2532~ 5~1921~ 6~3754~ 8~2076~ 9~1537~ 10~2264~ 11~1849~, 13~375~ 14~846~ 15~4314~ 16~2264~, 17~5607~ 18~846~ 19~2532~ 20~5607~ 21~1722~ 22~2414~ 23~1722~ 24~5025~ 25~2250~.'),
  (5263, 5, 12, 17, 'Thou mayest not eat within thy gates the tithe of thy corn, or of thy wine, or of thy oil, or the firstlings of thy herds or of thy flock, nor any of thy vows which thou vowest, nor thy freewill offerings, or heave offering of thine hand:', '1~03201~ 3~0398~ 6~08179~ 8~04643~ 11~01715~, 15~08492~, 19~03323~, 22~01062~ 25~01241~ 29~06629~, 34~05088~ 37~05087~, 41~05071~, 44~08641~ 47~03027~:'),
  (16776, 20, 13, 20, 'He that walketh with wise men shall be wise: but a companion of fools shall be destroyed.', '&para; 2~01980~ 4~02450~ [5] 8~02449~: 11~07462~ 13~03684~ 16~07321~.'),
  (11736, 14, 25, 23, 'And Joash the king of Israel took Amaziah king of Judah, the son of Joash, the son of Jehoahaz, at Bethshemesh, and brought him to Jerusalem, and brake down the wall of Jerusalem from the gate of Ephraim to the corner gate, four hundred cubits.', '1~03101~ 3~04428~ 5~03478~ 6~08610~ 7~0558~ 8~04428~ 10~03063~, 12~01121~ 14~03101~, 16~01121~ 18~03059~, 20~01053~, 22~0935~ 25~03389~, 28~06555~ 30~02346~ 32~03389~ 35~08179~ 37~0669~ 40~06437~ 41~08179~, 42~0702~ 43~03967~ 44~0520~.'),
  (28802, 46, 16, 10, 'Now if Timotheus come, see that he may be with you without fear: for he worketh the work of the Lord, as I also do.', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~1437~ 2~5095~ 3~2064~, 4~991~ 5~2443~ 8~1096~ 9~4314~ 10~5209~ 12~870~: 13~1063~ 15~2038~ 17~2041~ 20~2962~, 21~5613~ 22~1473~ 23~2532~ [24]'),
  (7034, 7, 19, 3, 'And her husband arose, and went after her, to speak friendly unto her, and to bring her again, having his servant with him, and a couple of asses: and she brought him into her father''s house: and when the father of the damsel saw him, he rejoiced to meet him.', '2~0376~ 3~06965~, 5~03212~ 6~0310~ 9~01696~ 10~03820~ [13] 17~07725~, 20~05288~ 25~06776~ 27~02543~: 30~0935~ 34~01~ 35~01004~: 39~01~ 42~05291~ 43~07200~ 46~08055~ 48~07125~'),
  (26734, 43, 15, 20, 'Remember the word that I said unto you, The servant is not greater than his lord. If they have persecuted me, they will also persecute you; if they have kept my saying, they will keep yours also.', '0~3421~ 2~3056~ 3~3739~ 4~1473~ 5~2036~ 7~5213~, 9~1401~ 10~2076~ 11~3756~ 13~3187~ 14~846~ 15~2962~. 16~1487~ 19~1377~ 20~1691~, 22~1377~ 23~2532~ 24~1377~ 25~5209~; 26~1487~ 29~5083~ 30~3450~ 31~3056~, 34~5083~ 35~5212~ 36~2532~.'),
  (12198, 15, 7, 16, 'And all the silver and gold that thou canst find in all the province of Babylon, with the freewill offering of the people, and of the priests, offering willingly for the house of their God which is in Jerusalem:', '1~03606~ 3~03702~ 5~01722~ 9~07912~ 11~03606~ 13~04083~ 15~0895~, 16~05974~ 19~05069~ 22~05972~, 26~03549~, 28~05069~ 31~01005~ 34~0426~ [36] 38~03390~:'),
  (16388, 19, 148, 8, 'Fire, and hail; snow, and vapours; stormy wind fulfilling his word:', '0~0784~, 2~01259~; 3~07950~, 5~07008~; 6~05591~ 7~07307~ 8~06213~ 10~01697~:'),
  (5094, 5, 6, 2, 'That thou mightest fear the LORD thy God, to keep all his statutes and his commandments, which I command thee, thou, and thy son, and thy son''s son, all the days of thy life; and that thy days may be prolonged.', '3~03372~ 5~03068~ 7~0430~, 9~08104~ 12~02708~ 15~04687~, 18~06680~ 23~01121~, 26~01121~ 27~01121~, 30~03117~ 33~02416~; 37~03117~ 40~0748~.'),
  (29855, 55, 2, 12, 'If we suffer, we shall also reign with him: if we deny him, he also will deny us:', '0~1487~ 2~5278~, 4~4821~ 5~2532~ 7~4821~ [8] 9~1487~ 11~720~ [12] 14~2548~ 16~720~ 17~2248~:'),
  (5830, 5, 33, 14, 'And for the precious fruits brought forth by the sun, and for the precious things put forth by the moon,', '3~04022~ 4~08393~ [5 6] 9~08121~, 14~04022~ 16~01645~ 19~03391~,'),
  (7253, 9, 2, 6, 'The LORD killeth, and maketh alive: he bringeth down to the grave, and bringeth up.', '1~03068~ 2~04191~, 5~02421~: 8~03381~ 11~07585~, 14~05927~.'),
  (23945, 40, 23, 17, 'Ye fools and blind: for whether is greater, the gold, or the temple that sanctifieth the gold?', '[0] 1~3474~ 2~2532~ 3~5185~: 4~1063~ 5~5101~ 6~2076~ 7~3187~, 9~5557~, 10~2228~ 12~3485~ 14~37~ 16~5557~?'),
  (16445, 20, 2, 3, 'Yea, if thou criest after knowledge, and liftest up thy voice for understanding;', '3~07121~ 5~0998~, [6] 8~05414~ 10~06963~ 12~08394~;'),
  (23124, 39, 2, 11, 'Judah hath dealt treacherously, and an abomination is committed in Israel and in Jerusalem; for Judah hath profaned the holiness of the LORD which he loved, and hath married the daughter of a strange god.', '0~03063~ 3~0898~, 6~08441~ 8~06213~ 10~03478~ 13~03389~; 15~03063~ 17~02490~ 19~06944~ 22~03068~ 25~0157~, 28~01166~ 30~01323~ 33~05236~ 34~0410~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (21940, 27, 6, 26, 'I make a decree, That in every dominion of my kingdom men tremble and fear before the God of Daniel: for he is the living God, and stedfast for ever, and his kingdom that which shall not be destroyed, and his dominion shall be even unto the end.', '0~06925~ 1~04481~* 2~07761~ 4~02942~, 7~03606~ 8~07985~ 11~04437~ 13~01934~ 14~02112~* 16~01763~ 17~06925~ 18~04481~ 19~0426~ 21~01841~: [24] 26~02417~ 27~0426~, 29~07011~ 31~05957~, 34~04437~ [35] 38~03809~ 40~02255~, 43~07985~ [44 46] 47~05705~ 49~05491~.'),
  (1141, 1, 38, 17, 'And he said, I will send thee a kid from the flock. And she said, Wilt thou give me a pledge, till thou send it?', '2~0559~, 5~07971~ [6] 8~01423~ 9~05795~ 11~06629~. 14~0559~, 17~05414~ [18] 20~06162~, 23~07971~ [24]'),
  (4049, 4, 11, 20, 'But even a whole month, until it come out at your nostrils, and it be loathsome unto you: because that ye have despised the LORD which is among you, and have wept before him, saying, Why came we forth out of Egypt?', '[0] 4~03117~ 5~02320~,* 9~03318~ 12~0639~, 16~02214~ 19~03282~ 23~03988~ 25~03068~ [27] 28~07130~ 32~01058~ 33~06440~ 35~0559~, 39~03318~ 42~04714~?'),
  (25048, 42, 3, 11, 'He answereth and saith unto them, He that hath two coats, let him impart to him that hath none; and he that hath meat, let him do likewise.', '1~611~ 2~1161~ 3~3004~ 5~846~, 8~2192~ 9~1417~ 10~5509~, 13~3330~ 17~2192~ 18~3361~; 19~2532~ 22~2192~ 23~1033~, 26~4160~ 27~3668~.'),
  (25762, 42, 19, 17, 'And he said unto him, Well, thou good servant: because thou hast been faithful in a very little, have thou authority over ten cities.', '0~2532~ 2~2036~ 4~846~, 5~2095~, 7~18~ 8~1401~: 9~3754~ 12~1096~ 13~4103~ 14~1722~ 17~1646~, 18~2192~ 20~2468~ 21~1849~* 22~1883~ 23~1176~ 24~4172~.'),
  (18960, 24, 1, 5, 'Before I formed thee in the belly I knew thee; and before thou camest forth out of the womb I sanctified thee, and I ordained thee a prophet unto the nations.', '0~02962~ 2~03335~ 6~0990~ 8~03045~ 14~03318~ 18~07358~ 20~06942~ [22] 24~05414~ 27~05030~ 30~01471~.'),
  (9189, 11, 12, 30, 'And this thing became a sin: for the people went to worship before the one, even unto Dan.', '2~01697~ 5~02403~: 8~05971~ 9~03212~ [10 11] 12~06440~ 14~0259~, [15] 17~01835~.'),
  (3915, 4, 7, 60, 'On the ninth day Abidan the son of Gideoni, prince of the children of Benjamin, offered:', '2~08671~ 3~03117~ 4~027~ 6~01121~ 8~01441~, 9~05387~ 12~01121~ 14~01144~, [15]'),
  (12261, 15, 9, 15, 'O LORD God of Israel, thou art righteous: for we remain yet escaped, as it is this day: behold, we are before thee in our trespasses: for we cannot stand before thee because of this.', '1~03068~ 2~0430~ 4~03478~, [6] 7~06662~: 10~07604~ 12~06413~, [14 15] 17~03117~: [20] 21~06440~ 25~0819~: 29~05975~ 30~06440~'),
  (3188, 3, 15, 15, 'And the priest shall offer them, the one for a sin offering, and the other for a burnt offering; and the priest shall make an atonement for him before the LORD for his issue.', '2~03548~ 4~06213~ 7~0259~ [8] 11~02403~, 14~0259~ [15] 18~05930~; 21~03548~ 25~03722~ 28~06440~ 30~03068~ 33~02101~.'),
  (13648, 18, 32, 11, 'Behold, I waited for your words; I gave ear to your reasons, whilst ye searched out what to say.', '2~03176~ 5~01697~; 8~0238~ 11~08394~, 15~02713~ 18~04405~.'),
  (9826, 12, 10, 25, 'And it came to pass, as soon as he had made an end of offering the burnt offering, that Jehu said to the guard and to the captains, Go in, and slay them; let none come forth. And they smote them with the edge of the sword; and the guard and the captains cast them out, and went to the city of the house of Baal.', '12~03615~ 14~06213~ 17~05930~, 19~03058~ 20~0559~ 23~07323~ 27~07991~, 29~0935~, [30] 31~05221~ 34~0376~ 36~03318~. 39~05221~ 43~06310~ 46~02719~; 49~07323~ 52~07991~ [54] 55~07993~, 57~03212~ 60~05892~ 63~01004~ 65~01168~.'),
  (22231, 28, 9, 14, 'Give them, O LORD: what wilt thou give? give them a miscarrying womb and dry breasts.', '0~05414~ 3~03068~: 7~05414~? 8~05414~ 11~07921~ 12~07358~ 14~06784~ 15~07699~.'),
  (10652, 13, 9, 29, 'Some of them also were appointed to oversee the vessels and all the instruments of the sanctuary, and the fine flour, and the wine, and the oil, and the frankincense, and the spices.', '[0] [4] 5~04487~ 9~03627~, 13~03627~ 16~06944~, 20~05560~, 23~03196~, 26~08081~, 29~03828~, 32~01314~.'),
  (26385, 43, 7, 42, 'Hath not the scripture said, That Christ cometh of the seed of David, and out of the town of Bethlehem, where David was?', '1~3780~ 3~1124~ 4~2036~, 5~3754~ 6~5547~ 7~2064~ 8~1537~ 10~4690~ 12~1138~, 13~2532~ 15~575~ 17~2968~ 19~965~, 20~3699~ 21~1138~ 22~2258~?'),
  (13708, 18, 34, 16, 'If now thou hast understanding, hear this: hearken to the voice of my words.', '&para; [2 3] 4~0998~, 5~08085~ 7~0238~ 10~06963~ 13~04405~.'),
  (7400, 9, 9, 2, 'And he had a son, whose name was Saul, a choice young man, and a goodly: and there was not among the children of Israel a goodlier person than he: from his shoulders and upward he was higher than any of the people.', '4~01121~, 6~08034~ [7] 8~07586~, 12~0970~, 15~02896~: [17 18] 22~01121~ 24~03478~ 26~02896~ 27~0376~ 32~07926~ 34~04605~ [35 36] 37~01364~ 42~05971~.'),
  (9366, 11, 18, 17, 'And it came to pass, when Ahab saw Elijah, that Ahab said unto him, Art thou he that troubleth Israel?', '&para; 6~0256~ 7~07200~ 8~0452~, 10~0256~ 11~0559~ [14] 18~05916~ 19~03478~?'),
  (52, 1, 2, 21, 'And the LORD God caused a deep sleep to fall upon Adam, and he slept: and he took one of his ribs, and closed up the flesh instead thereof;', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~0430~ 4~05307~ 7~08639~ 9~05307~ 11~0121~, 14~03462~: 17~03947~ 18~0259~ 21~06763~, 24~05462~ 26~01320~'),
  (14650, 19, 48, 7, 'Thou breakest the ships of Tarshish with an east wind.', '1~07665~ 3~0591~ 5~08659~ 8~06921~ 9~07307~.'),
  (17832, 23, 8, 16, 'Bind up the testimony, seal the law among my disciples.', '&para; 1~06887~ 3~08584~, 4~02856~ 6~08451~ 9~03928~.'),
  (28702, 46, 14, 8, 'For if the trumpet give an uncertain sound, who shall prepare himself to the battle?', '0~2532~ 1~1063~* 2~1437~ 4~4536~ 5~1325~ 7~82~ 8~5456~, 9~5101~ 12~3903~ 13~1519~ 15~4171~?'),
  (11753, 14, 26, 12, 'The whole number of the chief of the fathers of the mighty men of valour were two thousand and six hundred.', '2~04557~ 5~07218~ 8~01~ 12~01368~ 14~02428~ [15] 17~0505~ 19~08337~ 20~03967~.'),
  (29551, 51, 3, 18, 'Wives, submit yourselves unto your own husbands, as it is fit in the Lord.', '&para; 0~1135~, 2~5293~ 5~2398~ 6~435~, 7~5613~ 10~433~ 11~1722~ 13~2962~.'),
  (7749, 9, 20, 12, 'And Jonathan said unto David, O LORD God of Israel, when I have sounded my father about to morrow any time, or the third day, and, behold, if there be good toward David, and I then send not unto thee, and shew it thee;', '1~03083~ 2~0559~ 4~01732~, 6~03068~ 7~0430~ 9~03478~, 13~02713~ 15~01~ 18~04279~ 20~06256~, [21] 23~07992~ [24] [27 29] 30~02895~ 32~01732~, 36~07971~ 41~01540~ 42~0241~*'),
  (26174, 43, 4, 3, 'He left Judaea, and departed again into Galilee.', '1~863~ 2~2449~, 3~2532~ 4~565~ 5~3825~ 6~1519~ 7~1056~.'),
  (16859, 20, 16, 10, 'A divine sentence is in the lips of the king: his mouth transgresseth not in judgment.', '&para; 2~07081~ [3] 6~08193~ 9~04428~: 11~06310~ 12~04603~ 15~04941~.'),
  (4314, 4, 19, 20, 'But the man that shall be unclean, and shall not purify himself, that soul shall be cut off from among the congregation, because he hath defiled the sanctuary of the LORD: the water of separation hath not been sprinkled upon him; he is unclean.', '2~0376~ 6~02930~, 10~02398~ 13~05315~ 17~03772~ 19~08432~ 21~06951~, 25~02930~ 27~04720~ 30~03068~: 32~04325~ 34~05079~ 38~02236~ [42] 43~02931~.'),
  (24947, 42, 1, 42, 'And she spake out with a loud voice, and said, Blessed art thou among women, and blessed is the fruit of thy womb.', '0~2532~ 3~400~ 6~3173~ 7~5456~, 8~2532~ 9~2036~, 10~2127~ [11] 12~4771~ 13~1722~ 14~1135~, 15~2532~ 16~2127~ [17] 19~2590~ 21~4675~ 22~2836~.'),
  (15779, 19, 109, 15, 'Let them be before the LORD continually, that he may cut off the memory of them from the earth.', '5~03068~ 6~08548~, 11~03772~ 13~02143~ 18~0776~.'),
  (29978, 57, 1, 24, 'Marcus, Aristarchus, Demas, Lucas, my fellowlabourers.', '0~3138~, 1~708~, 2~1214~, 3~3065~, 4~3450~ 5~4904~.'),
  (20064, 24, 46, 10, 'For this is the day of the Lord GOD of hosts, a day of vengeance, that he may avenge him of his adversaries: and the sword shall devour, and it shall be satiate and made drunk with their blood: for the Lord GOD of hosts hath a sacrifice in the north country by the river Euphrates.', '[2] 4~03117~ 7~0136~ 8~03069~ 10~06635~, 12~03117~ 14~05360~, 18~05358~ 22~06862~: 25~02719~ 27~0398~, 32~07646~ 35~07301~ 38~01818~: 41~0136~ 42~03069~ 44~06635~ 47~02077~ 50~06828~ 51~0776~ 54~05104~ 55~06578~.'),
  (26557, 43, 11, 19, 'And many of the Jews came to Martha and Mary, to comfort them concerning their brother.', '0~2532~ 1~4183~ 2~1537~ 4~2453~ 5~2064~ 6~4314~ 7~3136~ 8~2532~ 9~4012~ 10~3137~,* 11~2443~ 12~3888~ 13~846~ 14~4012~ 15~846~ 16~80~.'),
  (12015, 14, 36, 13, 'And he also rebelled against king Nebuchadnezzar, who had made him swear by God: but he stiffened his neck, and hardened his heart from turning unto the LORD God of Israel.', '3~04775~ 5~04428~ 6~05019~, 11~07650~ 13~0430~: 16~07185~ 18~06203~, 20~0553~ 22~03824~ 24~07725~ 27~03068~ 28~0430~ 30~03478~.'),
  (11338, 14, 7, 6, 'And the priests waited on their offices: the Levites also with instruments of music of the LORD, which David the king had made to praise the LORD, because his mercy endureth for ever, when David praised by their ministry; and the priests sounded trumpets before them, and all Israel stood.', '2~03548~ 3~05975~ 6~04931~: 8~03881~ 11~03627~ 13~07892~ 16~03068~, 18~01732~ 20~04428~ 22~06213~ 24~03034~ 26~03068~, 29~02617~ [30] 32~05769~, 34~01732~ 35~01984~ 38~03027~; 41~03548~ 43~02690~ 48~03478~ 49~05975~.'),
  (19033, 24, 3, 22, 'Return, ye backsliding children, and I will heal your backslidings. Behold, we come unto thee; for thou art the LORD our God.', '0~07725~, 2~07726~ 3~01121~, [4] 7~07495~ 9~04878~. 12~0857~ [17] 19~03068~ 21~0430~.'),
  (25892, 42, 22, 14, 'And when the hour was come, he sat down, and the twelve apostles with him.', '0~2532~ 1~3753~ 3~5610~ 5~1096~, 8~377~, 9~2532~ 11~1427~ 12~652~ 13~4862~ 14~846~.'),
  (11368, 14, 8, 14, 'And he appointed, according to the order of David his father, the courses of the priests to their service, and the Levites to their charges, to praise and minister before the priests, as the duty of every day required: the porters also by their courses at every gate: for so had David the man of God commanded.', '2~05975~, 6~04941~ 8~01732~ 10~01~, 12~04256~ 15~03548~ 18~05656~, 21~03881~ 24~04931~, 26~01984~ 28~08334~ 31~03548~, 34~01697~ 37~03117~ 38~03117~: 40~07778~ 44~04256~ 47~08179~: 51~01732~ 53~0376~ 55~0430~ 56~04687~.'),
  (12873, 17, 9, 30, 'And he sent the letters unto all the Jews, to the hundred twenty and seven provinces of the kingdom of Ahasuerus, with words of peace and truth,', '2~07971~ 4~05612~ 8~03064~, 11~03967~ 12~06242~ 14~07651~ 15~04082~ 18~04438~ 20~0325~, [21] 22~01697~ 24~07965~ 26~0571~,'),
  (20067, 24, 46, 13, 'The word that the LORD spake to Jeremiah the prophet, how Nebuchadrezzar king of Babylon should come and smite the land of Egypt.', '1~01697~ 4~03068~ 5~01696~ 7~03414~ 9~05030~, 11~05019~ 12~04428~ 14~0894~ 16~0935~ [17] 18~05221~ 20~0776~ 22~04714~.'),
  (29001, 47, 10, 14, 'For we stretch not ourselves beyond our measure, as though we reached not unto you: for we are come as far as to you also in preaching the gospel of Christ:', '0~1063~ 2~5239~ 3~3756~ 4~1438~ 5~5239~ [6 7] 8~5613~ 11~2185~ 12~3361~ 13~1519~ 14~5209~: 15~1063~ 18~5348~ 21~891~ 23~5216~ 24~2532~ 25~1722~ [26] 28~2098~ 30~5547~:'),
  (5454, 5, 21, 1, 'If one be found slain in the land which the LORD thy God giveth thee to possess it, lying in the field, and it be not known who hath slain him:', '&para; [1] 3~04672~ 4~02491~ 7~0127~ 10~03068~ 12~0430~ 13~05414~ 16~03423~ 18~05307~ 21~07704~, [22] 26~03045~ 29~05221~'),
  (24250, 41, 1, 25, 'And Jesus rebuked him, saying, Hold thy peace, and come out of him.', '0~2532~ 1~2424~ 2~2008~ 3~846~, 4~3004~, 7~5392~, 8~2532~ 9~1831~ 11~1537~ 12~846~.'),
  (19530, 24, 23, 37, 'Thus shalt thou say to the prophet, What hath the LORD answered thee? and, What hath the LORD spoken?', '3~0559~ 6~05030~, 10~03068~ 11~06030~ 17~03068~ 18~01696~?'),
  (26371, 43, 7, 28, 'Then cried Jesus in the temple as he taught, saying, Ye both know me, and ye know whence I am: and I am not come of myself, but he that sent me is true, whom ye know not.', '0~3767~ 1~2896~ 2~2424~ 3~1722~ 5~2411~ 8~1321~ 9~2532~,* 10~3004~, 12~2504~ 14~1492~, 15~2532~ 17~1492~ 18~4159~ 20~1510~: 21~2532~ 23~2064~ 24~3756~ 25~2064~ 26~575~ 27~1683~, 28~235~ 31~3992~ 32~3165~ 33~2076~ 34~228~, 35~3739~ 36~5210~ 37~1492~ 38~3756~.'),
  (9642, 12, 4, 31, 'And Gehazi passed on before them, and laid the staff upon the face of the child; but there was neither voice, nor hearing. Wherefore he went again to meet him, and told him, saying, The child is not awaked.', '1~01522~ 3~05674~ 4~06440~ 7~07760~ 9~04938~ 12~06440~ 15~05288~; [17 18] 20~06963~, 22~07182~. 26~07725~ 28~07125~ 31~05046~ 33~0559~, 35~05288~ 38~06974~.'),
  (29150, 48, 4, 3, 'Even so we, when we were children, were in bondage under the elements of the world:', '0~2532~ 1~3779~ 2~2249~, 3~3753~ 5~2258~ 6~3516~, 7~2258~ 9~1402~ 10~5259~ 12~4747~ 15~2889~:'),
  (9554, 12, 1, 13, 'And he sent again a captain of the third fifty with his fifty. And the third captain of fifty went up, and came and fell on his knees before Elijah, and besought him, and said unto him, O man of God, I pray thee, let my life, and the life of these fifty thy servants, be precious in thy sight.', '2~07971~ 3~07725~ 5~08269~ 8~07992~ 9~02572~ 12~02572~. 15~07992~ 16~08269~ 18~02572~ 20~05927~, 22~0935~ 24~03766~ 27~01290~ 28~05048~ 29~0452~, 31~02603~ 34~01696~ 38~0376~ 40~0430~, 46~05315~, 49~05315~ 52~02572~ 54~05650~, 56~03365~ 59~05869~.'),
  (14184, 19, 19, 7, 'The law of the LORD is perfect, converting the soul: the testimony of the LORD is sure, making wise the simple.', '&para; 1~08451~ 4~03068~ [5] 6~08549~, 7~07725~ 9~05315~: 11~05715~ 14~03068~ [15] 16~0539~, 18~02449~ 20~06612~.'),
  (20441, 25, 4, 12, 'The kings of the earth, and all the inhabitants of the world, would not have believed that the adversary and the enemy should have entered into the gates of Jerusalem.', '1~04428~ 4~0776~, 8~03427~ 11~08398~, 15~0539~ 18~06862~ 21~0341~ 24~0935~ 27~08179~ 29~03389~.'),
  (24647, 41, 10, 48, 'And many charged him that he should hold his peace: but he cried the more a great deal, Thou son of David, have mercy on me.', '0~2532~ 1~4183~ 2~2008~ 3~846~ 4~2443~ 9~4623~: 10~1161~ 12~2896~ 14~3123~ 17~4183~, [18] 19~5207~ 21~1138~, 23~1653~ 25~3165~.'),
  (21990, 27, 8, 20, 'The ram which thou sawest having two horns are the kings of Media and Persia.', '1~0352~ 4~07200~ 5~01167~ [6] 7~07161~ [8] 10~04428~ 12~04074~ 14~06539~.'),
  (4172, 4, 15, 14, 'And if a stranger sojourn with you, or whosoever be among you in your generations, and will offer an offering made by fire, of a sweet savour unto the LORD; as ye do, so he shall do.', '3~01616~ 4~01481~ [9] 10~08432~ 14~01755~, 17~06213~ 22~0801~, 25~05207~ 26~07381~ 29~03068~; 32~06213~, 36~06213~.'),
  (28173, 45, 9, 2, 'That I have great heaviness and continual sorrow in my heart.', '0~3754~ 1~3427~ 2~2076~ 3~3173~ 4~3077~ 5~2532~ 6~88~ 8~3601~ 9~3450~ 10~2588~.'),
  (9952, 12, 15, 19, 'And Pul the king of Assyria came against the land: and Menahem gave Pul a thousand talents of silver, that his hand might be with him to confirm the kingdom in his hand.', '[0] 1~06322~ 3~04428~ 5~0804~ 6~0935~ 9~0776~: 11~04505~ 12~05414~ 13~06322~ 15~0505~ 16~03603~ 18~03701~, 21~03027~ 27~02388~ 29~04467~ 32~03027~.'),
  (18042, 23, 20, 4, 'So shall the king of Assyria lead away the Egyptians prisoners, and the Ethiopians captives, young and old, naked and barefoot, even with their buttocks uncovered, to the shame of Egypt.', '3~04428~ 5~0804~ 7~05090~ 9~04714~ 10~07628~, 13~03568~ 14~01546~, 15~05288~ 17~02205~, 18~06174~ 20~03182~, [23] 24~08357~ 25~02834~, 28~06172~ 30~04714~.'),
  (29622, 52, 4, 3, 'For this is the will of God, even your sanctification, that ye should abstain from fornication:', '0~1063~ 1~5124~ 2~2076~ 4~2307~ 6~2316~, [7] 8~5216~ 9~38~, 11~5209~ 13~567~ 14~575~ 15~4202~:'),
  (25151, 42, 5, 32, 'I came not to call the righteous, but sinners to repentance.', '1~2064~ 2~3756~ 4~2564~ 6~1342~, 7~235~ 8~268~ 9~1519~ 10~3341~.'),
  (23310, 40, 6, 18, 'That thou appear not unto men to fast, but unto thy Father which is in secret: and thy Father, which seeth in secret, shall reward thee openly.', '0~3704~ 2~5316~ 3~3361~ 5~444~ 7~3522~, 8~235~ 10~4675~ 11~3962~ 12~3588~ 14~1722~ 15~2927~: 16~2532~ 17~4675~ 18~3962~, 19~3588~ 20~991~ 21~1722~ 22~2927~, 24~591~ 25~4671~ 26~5318~ 27~1722~.*'),
  (12110, 15, 3, 4, 'They kept also the feast of tabernacles, as it is written, and offered the daily burnt offerings by number, according to the custom, as the duty of every day required;', '1~06213~ 4~02282~ 6~05521~, [8 9] 10~03789~, [12] 14~03117~ 15~03117~ 16~05930~ 18~04557~, 22~04941~, 25~01697~ 28~03117~ 29~03117~;'),
  (20215, 24, 50, 40, 'As God overthrew Sodom and Gomorrah and the neighbour cities thereof, saith the LORD; so shall no man abide there, neither shall any son of man dwell therein.', '1~0430~ 2~04114~ 3~05467~ 5~06017~ 8~07934~ [9] 11~05002~ 13~03068~; [14] 17~0376~ 18~03427~ 23~01121~ 25~0120~ 26~01481~'),
  (8949, 11, 7, 7, 'Then he made a porch for the throne where he might judge, even the porch of judgment: and it was covered with cedar from one side of the floor to the other.', '2~06213~ 4~0197~ 7~03678~ 11~08199~, [12] 14~0197~ 16~04941~: [18 19] 20~05603~ 22~0730~ 28~07172~ 31~07172~.'),
  (25153, 42, 5, 34, 'And he said unto them, Can ye make the children of the bridechamber fast, while the bridegroom is with them?', '0~1161~ 2~2036~ 3~4314~ 4~846~ 5~3361~,* 7~1410~ 8~4160~ 10~5207~ 13~3567~ 14~3522~, 15~1722~ 16~3739~ 17~3566~ 18~2076~ 19~3326~ 20~846~?'),
  (29099, 48, 2, 2, 'And I went up by revelation, and communicated unto them that gospel which I preach among the Gentiles, but privately to them which were of reputation, lest by any means I should run, or had run, in vain.', '0~1161~ 3~305~ 4~2596~ 5~602~, 6~2532~ 7~394~ 9~846~ 11~2098~ 12~3739~ 14~2784~ 15~1722~ 17~1484~, 18~1161~ 19~2398~ 20~2596~ 25~1380~, 29~4458~ 30~3381~ 32~5143~, 33~2228~ 35~5143~, 36~1519~ 37~2756~.'),
  (16905, 20, 17, 23, 'A wicked man taketh a gift out of the bosom to pervert the ways of judgment.', '&para; 1~07563~ [2] 3~03947~ 5~07810~ 9~02436~ 11~05186~ 13~0734~ 15~04941~.'),
  (3977, 4, 9, 7, 'And those men said unto him, We are defiled by the dead body of a man: wherefore are we kept back, that we may not offer an offering of the LORD in his appointed season among the children of Israel?', '1~01992~ 2~0582~ 3~0559~ [7] 8~02931~ 12~05315~ 15~0120~: 20~01639~, 25~07126~ 27~07133~ 30~03068~ 34~04150~ 35~08432~ 37~01121~ 39~03478~?'),
  (18169, 23, 27, 9, 'By this therefore shall the iniquity of Jacob be purged; and this is all the fruit to take away his sin; when he maketh all the stones of the altar as chalkstones that are beaten in sunder, the groves and images shall not stand up.', '1~02063~ 5~05771~ 7~03290~ 9~03722~; [12] 15~06529~ 18~05493~ 20~02403~; 23~07760~ 26~068~ 29~04196~ 31~01615~ 36~05310~, 38~0842~ 40~02553~ 44~06965~.'),
  (19692, 24, 30, 16, 'Therefore all they that devour thee shall be devoured; and all thine adversaries, every one of them, shall go into captivity; and they that spoil thee shall be a spoil, and all that prey upon thee will I give for a prey.', '4~0398~ 8~0398~; 12~06862~, 18~03212~ 20~07628~; 24~07601~ 29~04933~, 33~0962~ 38~05414~ 41~0957~.'),
  (5240, 5, 11, 26, 'Behold, I set before you this day a blessing and a curse;', '&para; 0~07200~, 2~05414~ 3~06440~ 6~03117~ 8~01293~ 11~07045~;'),
  (29159, 48, 4, 12, 'Brethren, I beseech you, be as I am; for I am as ye are: ye have not injured me at all.', '&para; 0~80~, 2~1189~ 3~5216~, 4~1096~ 5~5613~ 6~1473~ [7] 8~3754~ 9~2504~ [10] 11~5613~ 12~5210~ [13] 17~91~ 18~3165~ 20~3762~.'),
  (7791, 9, 21, 12, 'And David laid up these words in his heart, and was sore afraid of Achish the king of Gath.', '1~01732~ 3~07760~ 5~01697~ 8~03824~, 11~03966~ 12~03372~ 13~06440~ 14~0397~ 16~04428~ 18~01661~.'),
  (2532, 2, 34, 31, 'And Moses called unto them; and Aaron and all the rulers of the congregation returned unto him: and Moses talked with them.', '1~04872~ 2~07121~ 6~0175~ 10~05387~ 13~05712~ 14~07725~ 18~04872~ 19~01696~'),
  (14419, 19, 34, 22, 'The LORD redeemeth the soul of his servants: and none of them that trust in him shall be desolate.', '1~03068~ 2~06299~ 4~05315~ 7~05650~: 13~02620~ 18~0816~.'),
  (16627, 20, 8, 16, 'By me princes rule, and nobles, even all the judges of the earth.', '2~08269~ 3~08323~, 5~05081~, [6] 9~08199~ 12~0776~.'),
  (10386, 13, 3, 17, 'And the sons of Jeconiah; Assir, Salathiel his son,', '2~01121~ 4~03204~; 5~0617~, 6~07597~ 8~01121~,'),
  (18629, 23, 48, 6, 'Thou hast heard, see all this; and will not ye declare it? I have shewed thee new things from this time, even hidden things, and thou didst not know them.', '2~08085~, 3~02372~ 10~05046~ [11] 14~08085~ 17~02319~ 20~06258~, 23~05341~, 28~03045~'),
  (18931, 23, 65, 25, 'The wolf and the lamb shall feed together, and the lion shall eat straw like the bullock: and dust shall be the serpent''s meat. They shall not hurt nor destroy in all my holy mountain, saith the LORD.', '1~02061~ 4~02924~ 6~07462~ 7~0259~, 10~0738~ 12~0398~ 13~08401~ 16~01241~: 18~06083~ [19 20] 22~05175~ 23~03899~. 27~07489~ 29~07843~ 33~06944~ 34~02022~, 35~0559~ 37~03068~.'),
  (2974, 3, 9, 16, 'And he brought the burnt offering, and offered it according to the manner.', '2~07126~ 5~05930~, 7~06213~ 12~04941~.'),
  (4055, 4, 11, 26, 'But there remained two of the men in the camp, the name of the one was Eldad, and the name of the other Medad: and the spirit rested upon them; and they were of them that were written, but went not out unto the tabernacle: and they prophesied in the camp.', '2~07604~ 3~08147~ [4 5] 6~0582~ 9~04264~, 11~08034~ 14~0259~ [15] 16~0419~, 19~08034~ 22~08145~ 23~04312~: 26~07307~ 27~05117~ [32] 37~03789~, 41~03318~ 44~0168~: 47~05012~ 50~04264~.'),
  (27823, 44, 25, 11, 'For if I be an offender, or have committed any thing worthy of death, I refuse not to die: but if there be none of these things whereof these accuse me, no man may deliver me unto them. I appeal unto Caesar.', '0~1063~ 1~3303~ 2~1487~ 5~91~, 6~2532~ 8~4238~ 10~5100~ 11~514~ 13~2288~, 15~3868~ 16~3756~ 18~599~: 19~1161~ 20~1487~ 22~2076~ 23~3762~ 26~3739~ 28~3778~ 29~2723~ 30~3450~, 32~3762~ 33~1410~ 34~5483~ 35~3165~ 37~846~. 40~1941~ 41~2541~.'),
  (18265, 23, 31, 6, 'Turn ye unto him from whom the children of Israel have deeply revolted.', '&para; 0~07725~ [3 4] 7~01121~ 9~03478~ 11~06009~ 12~05627~.'),
  (28959, 47, 8, 11, 'Now therefore perform the doing of it; that as there was a readiness to will, so there may be a performance also out of that which ye have.', '0~1161~ 1~3570~* 2~2532~ 3~2005~ 5~4160~ [6 7] 8~3704~ 9~2509~ [10 11] 13~4288~ 15~2309~, 16~3779~ [17 19] 21~2005~ 22~2532~ 24~1537~ 28~2192~.'),
  (22481, 30, 7, 8, 'And the LORD said unto me, Amos, what seest thou? And I said, A plumbline. Then said the Lord, Behold, I will set a plumbline in the midst of my people Israel: I will not again pass by them any more:', '2~03068~ 3~0559~ 6~05986~, 8~07200~ 12~0559~, 14~0594~. 16~0559~ 18~0136~, 22~07760~ 24~0594~ 27~07130~ 30~05971~ 31~03478~: 35~03254~ 37~05674~'),
  (6521, 7, 1, 5, 'And they found Adonibezek in Bezek: and they fought against him, and they slew the Canaanites and the Perizzites.', '2~04672~ 3~0137~ 5~0966~: 8~03898~ 13~05221~ 15~03669~ 18~06522~.'),
  (23320, 40, 6, 28, 'And why take ye thought for raiment? Consider the lilies of the field, how they grow; they toil not, neither do they spin:', '0~2532~ 1~5101~ 4~3309~ 5~4012~ 6~1742~? 7~2648~ 9~2918~ 12~68~, 13~4459~ 15~837~; 17~2872~ 18~3756~, 19~3761~ 22~3514~:'),
  (10391, 13, 3, 22, 'And the sons of Shechaniah; Shemaiah: and the sons of Shemaiah; Hattush, and Igeal, and Bariah, and Neariah, and Shaphat, six.', '2~01121~ 4~07935~; 5~08098~: 8~01121~ 10~08098~; 11~02407~, 13~03008~, 15~01282~, 17~05294~, 19~08202~, 20~08337~.'),
  (27021, 44, 3, 9, 'And all the people saw him walking and praising God:', '0~2532~ 1~3956~ 3~2992~ 4~1492~ 5~846~ 6~4043~ 7~2532~ 8~134~ 9~2316~:'),
  (30109, 58, 8, 1, 'Now of the things which we have spoken this is the sum: We have such an high priest, who is set on the right hand of the throne of the Majesty in the heavens;', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~1909~ 7~3004~ [8 9] 11~2774~: 13~2192~ 14~5108~ 17~749~, 18~3739~ 20~2523~ 21~1722~ 24~1188~ 27~2362~ 30~3172~ 31~1722~ 33~3772~;'),
  (20169, 24, 49, 33, 'And Hazor shall be a dwelling for dragons, and a desolation for ever: there shall no man abide there, nor any son of man dwell in it.', '1~02674~ 5~04583~ 7~08577~, [8] 10~08077~ 11~05704~ 12~05769~: 16~0376~ 17~03427~ [20] 21~01121~ 23~0120~ 24~01481~'),
  (23376, 40, 8, 21, 'And another of his disciples said unto him, Lord, suffer me first to go and bury my father.', '0~1161~ 1~2087~ 3~846~ 4~3101~ 5~2036~ 7~846~, 8~2962~, 9~2010~ 10~3427~ 11~4412~ 13~565~ 14~2532~ 15~2290~ 16~3450~ 17~3962~.'),
  (13125, 18, 11, 8, 'It is as high as heaven; what canst thou do? deeper than hell; what canst thou know?', '[0 1] 3~01363~ 5~08064~; 9~06466~? 10~06013~ 12~07585~; 16~03045~?'),
  (27498, 44, 15, 40, 'And Paul chose Silas, and departed, being recommended by the brethren unto the grace of God.', '0~1161~ 1~3972~ 2~1951~ 3~4609~, 5~1831~, 7~3860~ 8~5259~ 10~80~ 13~5485~ 15~2316~.'),
  (30139, 58, 9, 18, 'Whereupon neither the first testament was dedicated without blood.', '0~3606~ 1~3761~ 3~4413~ [4] 6~1457~ 7~5565~ 8~129~.'),
  (28510, 46, 7, 7, 'For I would that all men were even as I myself. But every man hath his proper gift of God, one after this manner, and another after that.', '0~1063~ 2~2309~ 4~3956~ 5~444~ 6~1511~ 7~2532~ 8~5613~ 10~1683~. 11~235~ 13~1538~ 14~2192~ 16~2398~ 17~5486~ 18~1537~ 19~2316~, 20~3303~ 21~3739~ 23~3779~, 24~1161~ 25~3739~ 27~3779~.'),
  (13420, 18, 22, 22, 'Receive, I pray thee, the law from his mouth, and lay up his words in thine heart.', '0~03947~, 5~08451~ 8~06310~, 11~07760~ 13~0561~ 16~03824~.'),
  (25629, 42, 15, 28, 'And he was angry, and would not go in: therefore came his father out, and entreated him.', '0~1161~ 3~3710~, 4~2532~ 5~2309~ 6~3756~ 8~1525~: 9~3767~ 10~1831~ 11~846~ 12~3962~ 13~1831~, 15~3870~ 16~846~.'),
  (13362, 18, 20, 27, 'The heaven shall reveal his iniquity; and the earth shall rise up against him.', '1~08064~ 3~01540~ 5~05771~; 8~0776~ 11~06965~'),
  (20810, 26, 16, 39, 'And I will also give thee into their hand, and they shall throw down thine eminent place, and shall break down thy high places: they shall strip thee also of thy clothes, and shall take thy fair jewels, and leave thee naked and bare.', '4~05414~ 8~03027~, 13~02040~ 16~01354~, 20~05422~ 23~07413~: 26~06584~ 31~0899~, 34~03947~ 36~08597~ 37~03627~, 39~03240~ 41~05903~ 43~06181~.'),
  (6666, 7, 6, 5, 'For they came up with their cattle and their tents, and they came as grasshoppers for multitude; for both they and their camels were without number: and they entered into the land to destroy it.', '3~05927~ 6~04735~ 9~0168~, 12~0935~ 13~01767~ 14~0697~ 16~07230~; [17] 22~01581~ 25~04557~: 28~0935~ 31~0776~ 33~07843~'),
  (27666, 44, 20, 24, 'But none of these things move me, neither count I my life dear unto myself, so that I might finish my course with joy, and the ministry, which I have received of the Lord Jesus, to testify the gospel of the grace of God.', '0~235~ 1~3762~ 4~3056~ 6~4160~, 7~3761~ 9~2192~ 10~3450~ 11~5590~ 12~5093~ 14~1683~, 15~5613~ 19~5048~ 20~3450~ 21~1408~ 22~3326~ 23~5479~, 24~2532~ 26~1248~, 27~3739~ 30~2983~ 31~3844~ 33~2962~ 34~2424~, 36~1263~ 38~2098~ 41~5485~ 43~2316~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (16579, 20, 6, 30, 'Men do not despise a thief, if he steal to satisfy his soul when he is hungry;', '[0] 3~0936~ 5~01590~, 8~01589~ 10~04390~ 12~05315~ 16~07456~;'),
  (29368, 49, 6, 15, 'And your feet shod with the preparation of the gospel of peace;', '0~2532~ 2~4228~ 3~5265~ 4~1722~ 6~2091~ 9~2098~ 11~1515~;'),
  (11536, 14, 17, 4, 'But sought to the LORD God of his father, and walked in his commandments, and not after the doings of Israel.', '1~01875~ [4] 5~0430~ 8~01~, 10~01980~ 13~04687~, 18~04639~ 20~03478~.'),
  (3278, 3, 18, 22, 'Thou shalt not lie with mankind, as with womankind: it is abomination.', '3~07901~ 5~02145~, 7~04904~ 8~0802~: [10] 11~08441~.'),
  (10574, 13, 7, 31, 'And the sons of Beriah; Heber, and Malchiel, who is the father of Birzavith.', '2~01121~ 4~01283~; 5~02268~, 7~04439~, [9] 11~01~ 13~01269~.'),
  (23846, 40, 21, 10, 'And when he was come into Jerusalem, all the city was moved, saying, Who is this?', '0~2532~ 2~846~ 4~1525~ 5~1519~ 6~2414~, 7~3956~ 9~4172~ 11~4579~, 12~3004~, 13~5101~ 14~2076~ 15~3778~?'),
  (21779, 27, 2, 12, 'For this cause the king was angry and very furious, and commanded to destroy all the wise men of Babylon.', '0~06903~ 1~01836~ 2~03606~ 4~04430~ 6~01149~ 8~07690~ 9~07108~, 11~0560~ 13~07~ 14~03606~ 16~02445~ [17] 19~0895~.'),
  (27862, 44, 26, 23, 'That Christ should suffer, and that he should be the first that should rise from the dead, and should shew light unto the people, and to the Gentiles.', '0~1487~ 1~5547~ 3~3805~, [4] 5~1487~ 10~4413~ 13~386~ 14~1537~ 16~3498~, 18~3195~ 19~2605~ 20~5457~ 23~2992~, 24~2532~ 27~1484~.'),
  (8496, 10, 18, 10, 'And a certain man saw it, and told Joab, and said, Behold, I saw Absalom hanged in an oak.', '2~0259~ 3~0376~ 4~07200~ [5] 7~05046~ 8~03097~, 10~0559~, 13~07200~ 14~053~ 15~08518~ 18~0424~.'),
  (24724, 41, 12, 40, 'Which devour widows'' houses, and for a pretence make long prayers: these shall receive greater damnation.', '1~2719~ 2~5503~ 3~3614~, 4~2532~ 7~4392~ 8~4336~ 9~3117~ 10~4336~: 11~3778~ 13~2983~ 14~4055~ 15~2917~.'),
  (25806, 42, 20, 13, 'Then said the lord of the vineyard, What shall I do? I will send my beloved son: it may be they will reverence him when they see him.', '0~1161~ 1~2036~ 3~2962~ 6~290~, 7~5101~ 10~4160~? 13~3992~ 14~3450~ 15~27~ 16~5207~: 19~2481~ 22~1788~ [23] 26~1492~ 27~5126~.'),
  (2229, 2, 25, 29, 'And thou shalt make the dishes thereof, and spoons thereof, and covers thereof, and bowls thereof, to cover withal: of pure gold shalt thou make them.', '3~06213~ 5~07086~ 8~03709~ 11~07184~ 14~04518~ 17~05258~ 18~02004~: [19] 20~02889~ 21~02091~ 24~06213~'),
  (9233, 11, 14, 7, 'Go, tell Jeroboam, Thus saith the LORD God of Israel, Forasmuch as I exalted thee from among the people, and made thee prince over my people Israel,', '&para; 0~03212~, 1~0559~ 2~03379~, 4~0559~ 6~03068~ 7~0430~ 9~03478~, 11~03282~ 13~07311~ 16~08432~ 18~05971~, 20~05414~ 22~05057~ 25~05971~ 26~03478~,'),
  (18248, 23, 30, 22, 'Ye shall defile also the covering of thy graven images of silver, and the ornament of thy molten images of gold: thou shalt cast them away as a menstruous cloth; thou shalt say unto it, Get thee hence.', '2~02930~ 5~06826~ 9~06456~ 11~03701~, 14~0642~ 18~04541~ 20~02091~: 25~02219~ 29~01739~; 32~0559~ 37~03318~.'),
  (6534, 7, 1, 18, 'Also Judah took Gaza with the coast thereof, and Askelon with the coast thereof, and Ekron with the coast thereof.', '1~03063~ 2~03920~ 3~05804~ 6~01366~ 9~0831~ 12~01366~ 15~06138~ 18~01366~'),
  (316, 1, 12, 15, 'The princes also of Pharaoh saw her, and commended her before Pharaoh: and the woman was taken into Pharaoh''s house.', '1~08269~ 4~06547~ 5~07200~ 8~01984~ 10~0413~ 11~06547~: 14~0802~ 16~03947~ 18~06547~ 19~01004~.'),
  (7703, 9, 18, 20, 'And Michal Saul''s daughter loved David: and they told Saul, and the thing pleased him.', '1~04324~ 2~07586~ 3~01323~ 4~0157~ 5~01732~: 8~05046~ 9~07586~, 12~01697~ 13~03474~ 14~05869~*'),
  (21844, 27, 3, 28, 'Then Nebuchadnezzar spake, and said, Blessed be the God of Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego, who hath sent his angel, and delivered his servants that trusted in him, and have changed the king''s word, and yielded their bodies, that they might not serve nor worship any god, except their own God.', '&para; [0] 1~05020~ 2~06032~, 4~0560~, 5~01289~ [6] 8~0426~ 10~07715~, 11~04336~, 13~05665~, 16~07972~ 18~04398~, 20~07804~ 22~05649~ 24~07365~ 26~05922~, 29~08133~ 31~04430~ 32~04406~, 34~03052~ 36~01655~, 40~03809~ 41~06399~ 42~03809~ 43~05457~ 44~03606~ 45~0426~, 46~03861~ 49~0426~.'),
  (10258, 12, 25, 28, 'And he spake kindly to him, and set his throne above the throne of the kings that were with him in Babylon;', '2~01696~ 3~02896~ 7~05414~ 9~03678~ 12~03678~ 15~04428~ [17] 21~0894~;'),
  (22666, 33, 6, 9, 'The LORD''S voice crieth unto the city, and the man of wisdom shall see thy name: hear ye the rod, and who hath appointed it.', '&para; 1~03068~ 2~06963~ 3~07121~ 6~05892~, [8 10] 11~08454~ 13~07200~ 15~08034~: 16~08085~ 19~04294~, 23~03259~'),
  (25292, 42, 8, 35, 'Then they went out to see what was done; and came to Jesus, and found the man, out of whom the devils were departed, sitting at the feet of Jesus, clothed, and in his right mind: and they were afraid.', '0~1161~ 3~1831~ 5~1492~ 8~1096~; 9~2532~ 10~2064~ 11~4314~ 12~2424~, 13~2532~ 14~2147~ 16~444~, 18~575~ 19~3739~ 21~1140~ 23~1831~, 24~2521~ 25~3844~ 27~4228~ 29~2424~, 30~2439~, 31~2532~ 35~4993~: 36~2532~ 39~5399~.'),
  (31009, 66, 17, 18, 'And the woman which thou sawest is that great city, which reigneth over the kings of the earth.', '0~2532~ 2~1135~ 3~3739~ 5~1492~ 6~2076~ 8~3173~ 9~4172~, 10~3588~ 11~2192~ 12~932~* 13~1909~ 15~935~ 18~1093~.'),
  (3419, 3, 23, 12, 'And ye shall offer that day when ye wave the sheaf an he lamb without blemish of the first year for a burnt offering unto the LORD.', '3~06213~ 5~03117~ 8~05130~ 10~06016~ 13~03532~ 15~08549~ 18~01121~ 19~08141~ 23~05930~ 26~03068~.'),
  (358, 1, 14, 18, 'And Melchizedek king of Salem brought forth bread and wine: and he was the priest of the most high God.', '1~04442~ 2~04428~ 4~08004~ 6~03318~ 7~03899~ 9~03196~: [12] 14~03548~ 18~05945~ 19~0410~.'),
  (14865, 19, 64, 6, 'They search out iniquities; they accomplish a diligent search: both the inward thought of every one of them, and the heart, is deep.', '2~02664~ 3~05766~; 5~08552~ 7~02664~ 8~02665~: 11~07130~ [12] 15~0376~ [16 17] 20~03820~, [21] 22~06013~.'),
  (9327, 11, 17, 2, 'And the word of the LORD came unto him, saying,', '2~01697~ 5~03068~ 9~0559~,'),
  (23505, 40, 12, 6, 'But I say unto you, That in this place is one greater than the temple.', '0~1161~ 2~3004~ 4~5213~, 5~3754~ 8~5602~ [10] 10~2076~ 12~3187~ 14~2411~.'),
  (30780, 66, 3, 18, 'I counsel thee to buy of me gold tried in the fire, that thou mayest be rich; and white raiment, that thou mayest be clothed, and that the shame of thy nakedness do not appear; and anoint thine eyes with eyesalve, that thou mayest see.', '1~4823~ 2~4671~ 4~59~ 5~3844~ 6~1700~ 7~5553~ 8~4448~ 9~1537~ 11~4442~, 12~2443~ 16~4147~; 17~2532~ 18~3022~ 19~2440~, 20~2443~ 24~4016~, 25~2532~ [26] 28~152~ 30~4675~ 31~1132~ 32~5319~ 33~3361~ 34~5319~; 35~2532~ 36~1472~ 37~4675~ 38~3788~ 40~2854~, 41~2443~ 44~991~.'),
  (11182, 13, 29, 10, 'Wherefore David blessed the LORD before all the congregation: and David said, Blessed be thou, LORD God of Israel our father, for ever and ever.', '&para; 1~01732~ 2~01288~ 4~03068~ 5~05869~ 8~06951~: 10~01732~ 11~0559~, 12~01288~ [13] 15~03068~ 16~0430~ 18~03478~ 20~01~, 21~05704~ 22~05769~ 24~05769~.'),
  (7813, 9, 22, 19, 'And Nob, the city of the priests, smote he with the edge of the sword, both men and women, children and sucklings, and oxen, and asses, and sheep, with the edge of the sword.', '1~05011~, 3~05892~ 6~03548~, 7~05221~ 11~06310~ 14~02719~, 16~0376~ 18~0802~, 19~05768~ 21~03243~, 23~07794~, 25~02543~, 27~07716~, 30~06310~ 33~02719~.'),
  (5377, 5, 17, 7, 'The hands of the witnesses shall be first upon him to put him to death, and afterward the hands of all the people. So thou shalt put the evil away from among you.', '1~03027~ 4~05707~ 7~07223~ 14~04191~, 16~0314~ 18~03027~ 22~05971~. 26~01197~ 28~07451~ 29~01197~ 31~07130~'),
  (26404, 43, 8, 8, 'And again he stooped down, and wrote on the ground.', '0~2532~ 1~3825~ 3~2955~ 4~2736~, 6~1125~ 7~1519~ 9~1093~.'),
  (1905, 2, 14, 11, 'And they said unto Moses, Because there were no graves in Egypt, hast thou taken us away to die in the wilderness? wherefore hast thou dealt thus with us, to carry us forth out of Egypt?', '2~0559~ 4~04872~, [6 7] 9~06913~ 11~04714~, 16~03947~ 18~04191~ 21~04057~? 22~02063~ 25~06213~ 32~03318~ 35~04714~?'),
  (21154, 26, 27, 24, 'These were thy merchants in all sorts of things, in blue clothes, and broidered work, and in chests of rich apparel, bound with cords, and made of cedar, among thy merchandise.', '[1] 3~07402~ 6~04360~ [7 8] 10~08504~ 11~01545~, 14~07553~, 17~01595~ 20~01264~, 21~02280~ 23~02256~, 27~0729~, 30~04819~.'),
  (7815, 9, 22, 21, 'And Abiathar shewed David that Saul had slain the LORD''S priests.', '1~054~ 2~05046~ 3~01732~ 5~07586~ 7~02026~ 9~03068~ 10~03548~.'),
  (30622, 62, 4, 3, 'And every spirit that confesseth not that Jesus Christ is come in the flesh is not of God: and this is that spirit of antichrist, whereof ye have heard that it should come; and even now already is it in the world.', '0~2532~ 1~3956~ 2~4151~ 3~3739~ 4~3670~ 5~3361~ 7~2424~ 8~5547~ 10~2064~ 11~1722~ 13~4561~ 14~2076~ 15~3756~ 16~1537~ 17~2316~: 18~2532~ 19~5124~ 20~2076~ [22] 24~500~, 25~3739~ 28~191~ 29~3754~ 32~2064~; 34~2532~ 35~3568~ 36~2235~ 38~2076~ 39~1722~ 41~2889~.'),
  (15410, 19, 91, 6, 'Nor for the pestilence that walketh in darkness; nor for the destruction that wasteth at noonday.', '[0] 3~01698~ [4] 5~01980~ 7~0652~; [8] 11~06986~ [12] 13~07736~ 15~06672~.'),
  (29568, 51, 4, 10, 'Aristarchus my fellowprisoner saluteth you, and Marcus, sister''s son to Barnabas, (touching whom ye received commandments: if he come unto you, receive him;)', '0~708~ 1~3450~ 2~4869~ 3~782~ 4~5209~, 5~2532~ 6~3138~, 8~431~ 10~921~, 11~4012~* 13~3739~ 15~2983~ 16~1785~: 17~1437~ 19~2064~ 20~4314~ 21~5209~, 22~1209~ 23~846~;)'),
  (518, 1, 21, 1, 'And the LORD visited Sarah as he had said, and the LORD did unto Sarah as he had spoken.', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~06485~ 4~08283~ 8~0559~, 11~03068~ 12~06213~ 14~08283~ 18~01696~.'),
  (18503, 23, 42, 14, 'I have long time holden my peace; I have been still, and refrained myself: now will I cry like a travailing woman; I will destroy and devour at once.', '3~05769~ 6~02814~; 10~02790~, [11] 12~0662~ [14] 17~06463~ 21~03205~; 24~05395~ 26~07602~ 28~03162~.'),
  (12944, 18, 4, 5, 'But now it is come upon thee, and thou faintest; it toucheth thee, and thou art troubled.', '4~0935~ 9~03811~; 11~05060~ 16~0926~.'),
  (20858, 26, 17, 24, 'And all the trees of the field shall know that I the LORD have brought down the high tree, have exalted the low tree, have dried up the green tree, and have made the dry tree to flourish: I the LORD have spoken and have done it.', '3~06086~ 6~07704~ 8~03045~ 12~03068~ 15~08213~ 17~01364~ 18~06086~, 20~01361~ 22~08217~ 23~06086~, 25~03001~ 28~03892~ 29~06086~, 34~03002~ 35~06086~ 37~06524~: 40~03068~ 42~01696~ 45~06213~ [46]'),
  (15094, 19, 76, 4, 'Thou art more glorious and excellent than the mountains of prey.', '[1] 3~0215~ [4] 5~0117~ 8~02042~ 10~02964~.'),
  (28384, 46, 1, 5, 'That in every thing ye are enriched by him, in all utterance, and in all knowledge;', '0~3754~ 1~1722~ 3~3956~ 6~4148~ 7~1722~ 8~846~, 9~1722~ 10~3956~ 11~3056~, 12~2532~ [13] 14~3956~ 15~1108~;'),
  (29044, 47, 12, 6, 'For though I would desire to glory, I shall not be a fool; for I will say the truth: but now I forbear, lest any man should think of me above that which he seeth me to be, or that he heareth of me.', '0~1063~ 1~1437~ 4~2309~ 6~2744~, 8~2071~ 9~3756~ 10~2071~ 12~878~; 13~1063~ 16~2046~ 18~225~: 19~1161~ [20] 22~5339~, 23~3361~ 25~5100~ 27~3049~ 28~1519~ 29~1691~ 30~5228~ 32~3739~ 34~991~ 35~3165~ [36 37] 38~2228~ [39] 41~191~ 42~1537~ 43~5100~* 44~1700~.'),
  (25992, 42, 23, 43, 'And Jesus said unto him, Verily I say unto thee, To day shalt thou be with me in paradise.', '0~2532~ 1~2424~ 2~2036~ 4~846~, 5~281~ 7~3004~ 9~4671~, 11~4594~ 14~2071~ 15~3326~ 16~1700~ 17~1722~ 18~3857~.'),
  (4452, 4, 24, 1, 'And when Balaam saw that it pleased the LORD to bless Israel, he went not, as at other times, to seek for enchantments, but he set his face toward the wilderness.', '&para; 2~01109~ 3~07200~ 6~02895~ 7~05869~* 9~03068~ 11~01288~ 12~03478~, 14~01980~ 19~06471~, 21~07125~ 23~05173~, 26~07896~ 28~06440~ 31~04057~.'),
  (20921, 26, 20, 17, 'Nevertheless mine eye spared them from destroying them, neither did I make an end of them in the wilderness.', '2~05869~ 3~02347~ 6~07843~ 11~06213~ 13~03617~ 18~04057~.'),
  (856, 1, 30, 22, 'And God remembered Rachel, and God hearkened to her, and opened her womb.', '1~0430~ 2~02142~ 3~07354~, 5~0430~ 6~08085~ 10~06605~ 12~07358~.'),
  (2683, 2, 39, 14, 'And the stones were according to the names of the children of Israel, twelve, according to their names, like the engravings of a signet, every one with his name, according to the twelve tribes.', '2~068~ [3] 7~08034~ 10~01121~ 12~03478~, 13~06240~ 14~08147~,* 18~08034~, [19] 21~06603~ 24~02368~, 26~0376~ 29~08034~, 33~06240~ 34~08147~* 35~07626~.'),
  (15438, 19, 93, 3, 'The floods have lifted up, O LORD, the floods have lifted up their voice; the floods lift up their waves.', '1~05104~ 4~05375~, 6~03068~, 8~05104~ 11~05375~ 13~06963~; 15~05104~ 17~05375~ 19~01796~.'),
  (2718, 2, 40, 6, 'And thou shalt set the altar of the burnt offering before the door of the tabernacle of the tent of the congregation.', '3~05414~ 5~04196~ 9~05930~ 10~06440~ 12~06607~ 15~04908~ 18~0168~ 21~04150~.'),
  (14989, 19, 71, 4, 'Deliver me, O my God, out of the hand of the wicked, out of the hand of the unrighteous and cruel man.', '0~06403~ 4~0430~, 8~03027~ 11~07563~, 15~03709~ 18~05765~ 21~02556~.'),
  (7613, 9, 16, 11, 'And Samuel said unto Jesse, Are here all thy children? And he said, There remaineth yet the youngest, and, behold, he keepeth the sheep. And Samuel said unto Jesse, Send and fetch him: for we will not sit down till he come hither.', '1~08050~ 2~0559~ 4~03448~, 7~08552~ [8] 9~05288~? 12~0559~, 14~07604~ 17~06996~, 21~07462~ 23~06629~. 25~08050~ 26~0559~ 28~03448~, 29~07971~ 31~03947~ 38~05437~ 41~0935~ 42~06311~.'),
  (22262, 28, 12, 1, 'Ephraim feedeth on wind, and followeth after the east wind: he daily increaseth lies and desolation; and they do make a covenant with the Assyrians, and oil is carried into Egypt.', '&para; 0~0669~ 1~07462~ 3~07307~, 5~07291~ 9~06921~: 11~03117~ 12~07235~ 13~03577~ 15~07701~; 19~03772~ 21~01285~ 24~0804~, 26~08081~ 28~02986~ 30~04714~.'),
  (28647, 46, 11, 31, 'For if we would judge ourselves, we should not be judged.', '0~1063~ 1~1487~ 4~1252~ 5~1438~, 7~302~ 8~3756~ 10~2919~.'),
  (25079, 42, 4, 4, 'And Jesus answered him, saying, It is written, That man shall not live by bread alone, but by every word of God.', '0~2532~ 1~2424~ 2~611~ 3~846~ 4~4314~,* 5~3004~, 8~1125~, 9~3754~ 10~444~ 11~2198~ 12~3756~ 13~2198~ 14~1909~ 15~740~ 16~3441~, 17~235~ 18~1909~ 19~3956~ 20~4487~ 22~2316~.'),
  (11047, 13, 24, 24, 'Of the sons of Uzziel; Michah: of the sons of Michah; Shamir.', '[0] 2~01121~ 4~05816~; 5~04318~: 8~01121~ 10~04318~; 11~08053~.'),
  (14368, 19, 32, 4, 'For day and night thy hand was heavy upon me: my moisture is turned into the drought of summer. Selah.', '1~03119~ 3~03915~ 5~03027~ 7~03513~ 11~03955~ 13~02015~ 16~02725~ 18~07019~. 19~05542~.'),
  (4790, 4, 33, 24, 'And they removed from mount Shapher, and encamped in Haradah.', '2~05265~ 4~02022~ 5~08234~, 7~02583~ 9~02732~.'),
  (7979, 9, 29, 5, 'Is not this David, of whom they sang one to another in dances, saying, Saul slew his thousands, and David his ten thousands?', '[0] 3~01732~, 7~06030~ 12~04246~, 13~0559~, 14~07586~ 15~05221~ 17~0505~, 19~01732~ 22~07233~?'),
  (27355, 44, 12, 2, 'And he killed James the brother of John with the sword.', '0~1161~ 2~337~ 3~2385~ 5~80~ 7~2491~ 10~3162~.'),
  (11088, 13, 26, 3, 'Elam the fifth, Jehohanan the sixth, Elioenai the seventh.', '0~05867~ 2~02549~, 3~03076~ 5~08345~, 6~0454~ 8~07637~.'),
  (14398, 19, 34, 1, 'A Psalm of David, when he changed his behaviour before Abimelech; who drove him away, and he departed. I will bless the LORD at all times: his praise shall continually be in my mouth.', '&para; [0 1] 3~01732~, 6~08138~ 8~02940~ 9~06440~ 10~040~; 14~01644~, 17] 17~03212~.] 20~01288~ 22~03068~ 25~06256~: 27~08416~ [28] 29~08548~ [30] 33~06310~.'),
  (12746, 17, 2, 13, 'Then thus came every maiden unto the king; whatsoever she desired was given her to go with her out of the house of the women unto the king''s house.', '2~0935~ [3] 4~05291~ 7~04428~; 10~0559~ 12~05414~ 15~0935~ 21~01004~ 24~0802~ 27~04428~ 28~01004~.'),
  (27610, 44, 19, 9, 'But when divers were hardened, and believed not, but spake evil of that way before the multitude, he departed from them, and separated the disciples, disputing daily in the school of one Tyrannus.', '0~1161~ 1~5613~ 2~5100~ 4~4645~, 5~2532~ 7~544~, 10~2551~ 13~3598~ 14~1799~ 16~4128~, 18~868~ 19~575~ 20~846~, 22~873~ 24~3101~, 25~1256~ 26~2250~ 27~2596~* 28~1722~ 30~4981~ 32~5100~ 33~5181~.'),
  (1724, 2, 8, 9, 'And Moses said unto Pharaoh, Glory over me: when shall I entreat for thee, and for thy servants, and for thy people, to destroy the frogs from thee and thy houses, that they may remain in the river only?', '1~04872~ 2~0559~ 4~06547~, 5~06286~ 8~04970~ 11~06279~ 17~05650~, 21~05971~, 23~03772~ 25~06854~ 30~01004~, [31] 34~07604~ 37~02975~'),
  (4220, 4, 16, 21, 'Separate yourselves from among this congregation, that I may consume them in a moment.', '0~0914~ 3~08432~ 5~05712~, 9~03615~ 13~07281~.'),
  (19888, 24, 37, 5, 'Then Pharaoh''s army was come forth out of Egypt: and when the Chaldeans that besieged Jerusalem heard tidings of them, they departed from Jerusalem.', '1~06547~ 2~02428~ 5~03318~ 8~04714~: 12~03778~ 14~06696~ 15~03389~ 16~08085~ 17~08088~ 21~05927~ 23~03389~.'),
  (11635, 14, 21, 2, 'And he had brethren the sons of Jehoshaphat, Azariah, and Jehiel, and Zechariah, and Azariah, and Michael, and Shephatiah: all these were the sons of Jehoshaphat king of Israel.', '3~0251~ 5~01121~ 7~03092~, 8~05838~, 10~03171~, 12~02148~, 14~05838~, 16~04317~, 18~08203~: [21] 23~01121~ 25~03092~ 26~04428~ 28~03478~.'),
  (27435, 44, 14, 5, 'And when there was an assault made both of the Gentiles, and also of the Jews with their rulers, to use them despitefully, and to stone them,', '0~1161~ 1~5613~ 3~1096~ 5~3730~ 6~1096~ 7~5037~ 10~1484~, 12~2532~ 15~2453~ 16~4862~ 17~846~ 18~758~, [21] 22~5195~, 23~2532~ 25~3036~ 26~846~,'),
  (8461, 10, 17, 5, 'Then said Absalom, Call now Hushai the Archite also, and let us hear likewise what he saith.', '1~0559~ 2~053~, 3~07121~ 5~02365~ 7~0757~ 12~08085~ 16~06310~.'),
  (13629, 18, 31, 32, 'The stranger did not lodge in the street: but I opened my doors to the traveller.', '1~01616~ 4~03885~ 7~02351~: [8] 10~06605~ 12~01817~ 15~0734~.'),
  (24895, 41, 16, 11, 'And they, when they had heard that he was alive, and had been seen of her, believed not.', '1~2548~, 5~191~ 6~3754~ 9~2198~, 10~2532~ 13~2300~ 14~5259~ 15~846~, 17~569~.'),
  (16923, 20, 18, 13, 'He that answereth a matter before he heareth it, it is folly and shame unto him.', '&para; 2~07725~ 4~01697~ 7~08085~ [8] [10] 11~0200~ 13~03639~'),
  (24363, 41, 4, 30, 'And he said, Whereunto shall we liken the kingdom of God? or with what comparison shall we compare it?', '0~2532~ 2~3004~, 3~5101~ 6~3666~ 8~932~ 10~2316~? 11~2228~ 12~1722~ 13~4169~ 14~3850~ 17~3846~ 18~846~?'),
  (7648, 9, 17, 23, 'And as he talked with them, behold, there came up the champion, the Philistine of Gath, Goliath by name, out of the armies of the Philistines, and spake according to the same words: and David heard them.', '3~01696~ 9~05927~ 11~01143~ 12~0376~,* 14~06430~ 16~01661~, 17~01555~ 19~08034~, 23~04634~ 24~04630~* 27~06430~, 29~01696~ 33~0428~ 34~01697~: 36~01732~ 37~08085~ [38]'),
  (4737, 4, 32, 13, 'And the LORD''S anger was kindled against Israel, and he made them wander in the wilderness forty years, until all the generation, that had done evil in the sight of the LORD, was consumed.', '2~03068~ 3~0639~ 5~02734~ 7~03478~, 12~05128~ 15~04057~ 16~0705~ 17~08141~, 21~01755~, 24~06213~ 25~07451~ 28~05869~ 31~03068~, 33~08552~.'),
  (11056, 13, 25, 2, 'Of the sons of Asaph; Zaccur, and Joseph, and Nethaniah, and Asarelah, the sons of Asaph under the hands of Asaph, which prophesied according to the order of the king.', '2~01121~ 4~0623~; 5~02139~, 7~03130~, 9~05418~, 11~0841~, 13~01121~ 15~0623~ 18~03027~ 20~0623~, 22~05012~ 26~03027~ 29~04428~.'),
  (20436, 25, 4, 7, 'Her Nazarites were purer than snow, they were whiter than milk, they were more ruddy in body than rubies, their polishing was of sapphire:', '1~05139~ 3~02141~ 5~07950~, 8~06705~ 10~02461~, 14~0119~ 16~06106~ 18~06443~, 20~01508~ [21] 23~05601~:'),
  (23933, 40, 23, 5, 'But all their works they do for to be seen of men: they make broad their phylacteries, and enlarge the borders of their garments,', '0~1161~ 1~3956~ 2~846~ 3~2041~ 5~4160~ 6~4314~ 9~2300~ 11~444~ 12~1161~:* 15~4115~ 16~846~ 17~5440~, 18~2532~ 19~3170~ 21~2899~ 23~846~ 24~2440~,'),
  (6726, 7, 7, 25, 'And they took two princes of the Midianites, Oreb and Zeeb; and they slew Oreb upon the rock Oreb, and Zeeb they slew at the winepress of Zeeb, and pursued Midian, and brought the heads of Oreb and Zeeb to Gideon on the other side Jordan.', '2~03920~ 3~08147~ 4~08269~ 7~04080~, 8~06159~ 10~02062~; 13~02026~ 14~06159~ 17~06697~ 18~06159~, 20~02062~ 22~02026~ 25~03342~ 27~02062~, 29~07291~ 30~04080~, 32~0935~ 34~07218~ 36~06159~ 38~02062~ 40~01439~ 44~05676~ 45~03383~.'),
  (16159, 19, 131, 2, 'Surely I have behaved and quieted myself, as a child that is weaned of his mother: my soul is even as a weaned child.', '3~07737~ 5~01826~ 6~05315~, 12~01580~ 15~0517~: 17~05315~ [18] 23~01580~.'),
  (1057, 1, 36, 12, 'And Timna was concubine to Eliphaz Esau''s son; and she bare to Eliphaz Amalek: these were the sons of Adah Esau''s wife.', '1~08555~ 3~06370~ 5~0464~ 6~06215~ 7~01121~; 10~03205~ 12~0464~ 13~06002~: [15] 17~01121~ 19~05711~ 20~06215~ 21~0802~.'),
  (18461, 23, 41, 1, 'Keep silence before me, O islands; and let the people renew their strength: let them come near; then let them speak: let us come near together to judgment.', '&para; 1~02790~ 5~0339~; 9~03816~ 10~02498~ [11] 12~03581~: 16~05066~; 20~01696~: 24~07126~ 25~03162~ 27~04941~.'),
  (14687, 19, 50, 10, 'For every beast of the forest is mine, and the cattle upon a thousand hills.', '2~02416~ 5~03293~ [6] [8] 10~0929~ 13~0505~ 14~02042~.'),
  (21698, 26, 47, 10, 'And it shall come to pass, that the fishers shall stand upon it from Engedi even unto Eneglaim; they shall be a place to spread forth nets; their fish shall be according to their kinds, as the fish of the great sea, exceeding many.', '[6] 8~01728~ 10~05975~ 14~05872~ 17~05882~; [22] 25~04894~ 26~02764~; 28~01710~ 34~04327~, 37~01710~ 40~01419~ 41~03220~, 42~03966~ 43~07227~.'),
  (4321, 4, 20, 5, 'And wherefore have ye made us to come up out of Egypt, to bring us in unto this evil place? it is no place of seed, or of figs, or of vines, or of pomegranates; neither is there any water to drink.', '8~05927~ 11~04714~, 13~0935~ 18~07451~ 19~04725~? [21] 23~04725~ 25~02233~, 28~08384~, 31~01612~, 34~07416~; [36] 39~04325~ 41~08354~.'),
  (21583, 26, 43, 2, 'And, behold, the glory of the God of Israel came from the way of the east: and his voice was like a noise of many waters: and the earth shined with his glory.', '3~03519~ 6~0430~ 8~03478~ 9~0935~ 12~01870~ 15~06921~: 18~06963~ [19] 22~06963~ 24~07227~ 25~04325~: 28~0776~ 29~0215~ 32~03519~.'),
  (5622, 5, 28, 5, 'Blessed shall be thy basket and thy store.', '0~01288~ [1 2] 4~02935~ 7~04863~.'),
  (7520, 9, 14, 5, 'The forefront of the one was situate northward over against Michmash, and the other southward over against Gibeah.', '1~08127~ 4~0259~ [5] 6~04690~ 7~06828~ 9~04136~ 10~04363~, 13~0259~ 14~05045~ 16~04136~ 17~01387~.'),
  (11614, 14, 20, 18, 'And Jehoshaphat bowed his head with his face to the ground: and all Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem fell before the LORD, worshipping the LORD.', '1~03092~ 2~06915~ [6] 7~0639~ 10~0776~: 13~03063~ 16~03427~ 18~03389~ 19~05307~ 20~06440~ 22~03068~, 23~07812~ 25~03068~.'),
  (16273, 19, 140, 1, 'To the chief Musician, A Psalm of David. Deliver me, O LORD, from the evil man: preserve me from the violent man;', '&para; [0 3~05329~, 5~04210~ 7] 7~01732~ 8~02502~ 11~03068~, 14~07451~ 15~0120~: 16~05341~ 20~02555~ 21~0376~;'),
  (12906, 18, 2, 6, 'And the LORD said unto Satan, Behold, he is in thine hand; but save his life.', '2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~07854~, [8] 11~03027~; 13~08104~ 15~05315~.'),
  (27313, 44, 10, 38, 'How God anointed Jesus of Nazareth with the Holy Ghost and with power: who went about doing good, and healing all that were oppressed of the devil; for God was with him.', '0~5613~ 1~2316~ 2~5548~ 3~2424~ 4~575~ 5~3478~ 8~40~ 9~4151~ 10~2532~ 12~1411~: 13~3739~ 14~846~ 15~1330~ 17~2109~, 18~2532~ 19~2390~ 20~3956~ 23~2616~ 24~5259~ 26~1228~; 27~3754~ 28~2316~ 29~2258~ 30~3326~ 31~846~.'),
  (21529, 26, 40, 43, 'And within were hooks, an hand broad, fastened round about: and upon the tables was the flesh of the offering.', '1~01004~ [2] 3~08240~, 4~0259~ 5~02948~ 7~03559~ 9~05439~: 13~07979~ [14] 16~01320~ 19~07133~.'),
  (6892, 7, 13, 1, 'And the children of Israel did evil again in the sight of the LORD; and the LORD delivered them into the hand of the Philistines forty years.', '&para; 2~01121~ 4~03478~ 5~06213~ 6~07451~ 7~03254~ 10~05869~ 13~03068~; 16~03068~ 17~05414~ 21~03027~ 24~06430~ 25~0705~ 26~08141~.'),
  (14609, 19, 45, 3, 'Gird thy sword upon thy thigh, O most mighty, with thy glory and thy majesty.', '0~02296~ 2~02719~ [4] 5~03409~, [7] 8~01368~, 11~01935~ 14~01926~.'),
  (23855, 40, 21, 19, 'And when he saw a fig tree in the way, he came to it, and found nothing thereon, but leaves only, and said unto it, Let no fruit grow on thee henceforward for ever. And presently the fig tree withered away.', '0~2532~ 3~1492~ 4~3391~ 6~4808~ 7~1909~ 9~3598~, 11~2064~ 12~1909~ 13~846~, 14~2532~ 15~2147~ 16~3762~ 17~846~ 18~1722~,* 19~1508~ 20~5444~ 21~3440~, 22~2532~ 23~3004~ 25~846~, 27~1096~ 28~2590~ 29~1096~ 30~1537~ 31~4675~ 32~3371~ 33~1519~ 34~165~. 35~2532~ 36~3916~ 39~4808~ 41~3583~.'),
  (21818, 27, 3, 2, 'Then Nebuchadnezzar the king sent to gather together the princes, the governors, and the captains, the judges, the treasurers, the counsellors, the sheriffs, and all the rulers of the provinces, to come to the dedication of the image which Nebuchadnezzar the king had set up.', '1~05020~ 3~04430~ 4~07972~ 7~03673~ 9~0324~, 11~05460~, 14~06347~, 16~0148~, 18~01411~, 20~01884~, 22~08614~, 24~03606~ 26~07984~ 29~04083~, 31~0858~ 34~02597~ 37~06755~ 39~05020~ 41~04430~ 44~06966~.');
