  (16331, 19, 145, 2, 'Every day will I bless thee; and I will praise thy name for ever and ever.', '1~03117~ 4~01288~ 9~01984~ 11~08034~ 13~05769~ 15~05703~.'),
  (4568, 4, 27, 8, 'And thou shalt speak unto the children of Israel, saying, If a man die, and have no son, then ye shall cause his inheritance to pass unto his daughter.', '3~01696~ 6~01121~ 8~03478~, 9~0559~, 12~0376~ 13~04191~, 17~01121~, 23~05159~ 25~05674~ 28~01323~.'),
  (21366, 26, 35, 13, 'Thus with your mouth ye have boasted against me, and have multiplied your words against me: I have heard them.', '3~06310~ 6~01431~ 11~06280~ 13~01697~ 18~08085~ [19]'),
  (24908, 42, 1, 4, 'That thou mightest know the certainty of those things, wherein thou hast been instructed.', '0~2443~ 3~1921~ 5~803~ 6~4012~ 8~3056~, 9~3739~ 13~2727~.'),
  (13555, 18, 29, 14, 'I put on righteousness, and it clothed me: my judgment was as a robe and a diadem.', '1~03847~ 3~06664~, 6~03847~ 9~04941~ [10] 13~04598~ 16~06797~.'),
  (21398, 26, 36, 30, 'And I will multiply the fruit of the tree, and the increase of the field, that ye shall receive no more reproach of famine among the heathen.', '3~07235~ 5~06529~ 8~06086~, 11~08570~ 14~07704~, 18~03947~ 21~02781~ 23~07458~ 26~01471~.'),
  (13379, 18, 21, 15, 'What is the Almighty, that we should serve him? and what profit should we have, if we pray unto him?', '[1] 3~07706~, 7~05647~ 11~03276~ 17~06293~'),
  (13939, 18, 42, 8, 'Therefore take unto you now seven bullocks and seven rams, and go to my servant Job, and offer up for yourselves a burnt offering; and my servant Job shall pray for you: for him will I accept: lest I deal with you after your folly, in that ye have not spoken of me the thing which is right, like my servant Job.', '1~03947~ 5~07651~ 6~06499~ 8~07651~ 9~0352~, 11~03212~ 14~05650~ 15~0347~, 18~05927~ 23~05930~; 26~05650~ 27~0347~ 29~06419~ 33~06440~ 36~05375~: 39~06213~ [42 43] 44~05039~, 50~01696~ [53 56] 57~03559~, 60~05650~ 61~0347~.'),
  (779, 1, 28, 2, 'Arise, go to Padanaram, to the house of Bethuel thy mother''s father; and take thee a wife from thence of the daughters of Laban thy mother''s brother.', '0~06965~, 1~03212~ 3~06307~, 6~01004~ 8~01328~ 10~0517~ 11~01~; 13~03947~ 16~0802~ 21~01323~ 23~03837~ 25~0517~ 26~0251~.'),
  (27182, 44, 7, 50, 'Hath not my hand made all these things?', '0~4160~ 1~3780~ 2~3450~ 3~5495~ 4~4160~ 5~3956~ 7~5023~?'),
  (3392, 3, 22, 18, 'Speak unto Aaron, and to his sons, and unto all the children of Israel, and say unto them, Whatsoever he be of the house of Israel, or of the strangers in Israel, that will offer his oblation for all his vows, and for all his freewill offerings, which they will offer unto the LORD for a burnt offering;', '0~01696~ 2~0175~, 6~01121~, 11~01121~ 13~03478~, 15~0559~ 18~0376~ [19 20] 23~01004~ 25~03478~, 29~01616~ 31~03478~, 34~07126~ 36~07133~ 40~05088~, 46~05071~, 50~07126~ 53~03068~ 57~05930~;'),
  (29102, 48, 2, 5, 'To whom we gave place by subjection, no, not for an hour; that the truth of the gospel might continue with you.', '1~3739~ 4~1502~ 6~5292~, 8~3761~ 9~4314~ 11~5610~; 12~2443~ 14~225~ 17~2098~ 19~1265~ 20~4314~ 21~5209~.'),
  (12143, 15, 4, 24, 'Then ceased the work of the house of God which is at Jerusalem. So it ceased unto the second year of the reign of Darius king of Persia.', '0~0116~ 1~0989~ 3~05673~ 6~01005~ 8~0426~ [10] 12~03390~. 15~01934~ 16~0989~* 17~05705~ 19~08648~ 20~08140~ 23~04437~ 25~01868~ 26~04430~ 28~06540~.'),
  (14644, 19, 48, 1, 'A Song and Psalm for the sons of Korah. Great is the LORD, and greatly to be praised in the city of our God, in the mountain of his holiness.', '&para; [0 1~07892~ [2] 3~04210~ 6~01121~ 8] 8~07141~ 9~01419~ [10] 12~03068~, 14~03966~ 17~01984~ 20~05892~ 23~0430~, [24] 26~02022~ 29~06944~.'),
  (11684, 14, 23, 19, 'And he set the porters at the gates of the house of the LORD, that none which was unclean in any thing should enter in.', '2~05975~ 4~07778~ 7~08179~ 10~01004~ 13~03068~, [16 17] 18~02931~ 21~01697~ 24~0935~.'),
  (29572, 51, 4, 14, 'Luke, the beloved physician, and Demas, greet you.', '0~3065~, 2~27~ 3~2395~, 4~2532~ 5~1214~, 6~782~ 7~5209~.'),
  (19451, 24, 21, 2, 'Inquire, I pray thee, of the LORD for us; for Nebuchadrezzar king of Babylon maketh war against us; if so be that the LORD will deal with us according to all his wondrous works, that he may go up from us.', '0~01875~, 6~03068~ 8~01157~; 10~05019~ 11~04428~ 13~0894~ 15~03898~ 23~03068~ 25~06213~ 33~06381~, 38~05927~'),
  (17673, 23, 1, 10, 'Hear the word of the LORD, ye rulers of Sodom; give ear unto the law of our God, ye people of Gomorrah.', '&para; 0~08085~ 2~01697~ 5~03068~, 7~07101~ 9~05467~; 11~0238~ 14~08451~ 17~0430~, 19~05971~ 21~06017~.'),
  (681, 1, 25, 19, 'And these are the generations of Isaac, Abraham''s son: Abraham begat Isaac:', '&para; [2] 4~08435~ 6~03327~, 7~085~ 8~01121~: 9~085~ 10~03205~ 11~03327~:'),
  (826, 1, 29, 27, 'Fulfil her week, and we will give thee this also for the service which thou shalt serve with me yet seven other years.', '0~04390~ 1~02063~ 2~07620~, 6~05414~ 12~05656~ 16~05647~ 20~07651~ 21~0312~ 22~08141~.'),
  (17827, 23, 8, 11, 'For the LORD spake thus to me with a strong hand, and instructed me that I should not walk in the way of this people, saying,', '2~03068~ 3~0559~ 9~02393~ 10~03027~, 12~03256~ 18~03212~ 21~01870~ 24~05971~, 25~0559~,'),
  (30761, 66, 2, 28, 'And I will give him the morning star.', '0~2532~ 3~1325~ 4~846~ 6~4407~ 7~792~.'),
  (22510, 30, 9, 6, 'It is he that buildeth his stories in the heaven, and hath founded his troop in the earth; he that calleth for the waters of the sea, and poureth them out upon the face of the earth: The LORD is his name.', '[0 1] 4~01129~ 6~04609~ 9~08064~, 12~03245~ 14~092~ 17~0776~; 20~07121~ 23~04325~ 26~03220~, 30~08210~ 33~06440~ 36~0776~: 38~03068~ [39] 41~08034~.'),
  (17371, 21, 3, 3, 'A time to kill, and a time to heal; a time to break down, and a time to build up;', '1~06256~ 3~02026~, 6~06256~ 8~07495~; 10~06256~ 13~06555~, 16~06256~ 19~01129~;'),
  (10214, 12, 24, 4, 'And also for the innocent blood that he shed: for he filled Jerusalem with innocent blood; which the LORD would not pardon.', '4~05355~ 5~01818~ 8~08210~: 11~04390~ 12~03389~ 14~05355~ 15~01818~; 18~03068~ 19~014~ 21~05545~.'),
  (10878, 13, 17, 7, 'Now therefore thus shalt thou say unto my servant David, Thus saith the LORD of hosts, I took thee from the sheepcote, even from following the sheep, that thou shouldest be ruler over my people Israel:', '5~0559~ 8~05650~ 9~01732~, 11~0559~ 13~03068~ 15~06635~, 17~03947~ 21~05116~, [22] 24~0310~ 26~06629~, 31~05057~ 34~05971~ 35~03478~:'),
  (24831, 41, 14, 66, 'And as Peter was beneath in the palace, there cometh one of the maids of the high priest:', '&para; 0~2532~ 2~4074~ 3~5607~ 4~2736~ 5~1722~ 7~833~, 9~2064~ 10~3391~ 13~3814~ 17~749~:'),
  (29253, 49, 2, 8, 'For by grace are ye saved through faith; and that not of yourselves: it is the gift of God:', '0~1063~ 2~5485~ 4~2075~ 5~4982~ 6~1223~ 7~4102~; 8~2532~ 9~5124~ 10~3756~ 11~1537~ 12~5216~: [13 14] 16~1435~ 18~2316~:'),
  (19825, 24, 34, 15, 'And ye were now turned, and had done right in my sight, in proclaiming liberty every man to his neighbour; and ye had made a covenant before me in the house which is called by my name:', '3~03117~ 4~07725~, 7~06213~ 8~03477~ 11~05869~, 13~07121~ 14~01865~ 16~0376~ 19~07453~; 23~03772~ 25~01285~ 26~06440~ 30~01004~ 33~07121~ 36~08034~:'),
  (22513, 30, 9, 9, 'For, lo, I will command, and I will sift the house of Israel among all nations, like as corn is sifted in a sieve, yet shall not the least grain fall upon the earth.', '4~06680~, 8~05128~ 10~01004~ 12~03478~ 15~01471~, [18] 20~05128~ 23~03531~, 29~06872~ 30~05307~ 33~0776~.'),
  (12210, 15, 7, 28, 'And hath extended mercy unto me before the king, and his counsellors, and before all the king''s mighty princes. And I was strengthened as the hand of the LORD my God was upon me, and I gathered together out of Israel chief men to go up with me.', '2~05186~ 3~02617~ 6~06440~ 8~04428~, 11~03289~, 16~04428~ 17~01368~ 18~08269~. 22~02388~ 25~03027~ 28~03068~ 30~0430~ [31] 37~06908~ 40~03478~ 42~07218~ 45~05927~'),
  (30604, 62, 3, 9, 'Whosoever is born of God doth not commit sin; for his seed remaineth in him: and he cannot sin, because he is born of God.', '0~3956~ 2~1080~ 3~1537~ 4~2316~ 5~4160~ 6~3756~ 8~266~; 9~3754~ 10~846~ 11~4690~ 12~3306~ 13~1722~ 14~846~: 15~2532~ 17~1410~ 18~3756~* 19~264~, 20~3754~ 23~1080~ 24~1537~ 25~2316~.'),
  (26552, 43, 11, 14, 'Then said Jesus unto them plainly, Lazarus is dead.', '0~3767~ 1~5119~* 2~2036~ 3~2424~ 5~846~ 6~3954~, 7~2976~ 9~599~.'),
  (12509, 16, 8, 7, 'Also Jeshua, and Bani, and Sherebiah, Jamin, Akkub, Shabbethai, Hodijah, Maaseiah, Kelita, Azariah, Jozabad, Hanan, Pelaiah, and the Levites, caused the people to understand the law: and the people stood in their place.', '1~03442~, 3~01137~, 5~08274~, 6~03226~, 7~06126~, 8~07678~, 9~01941~, 10~04641~, 11~07042~, 12~05838~, 13~03107~, 14~02605~, 15~06411~, 18~03881~, 21~05971~ 23~0995~ 25~08451~: 28~05971~ [29] 32~05977~.'),
  (8219, 10, 8, 3, 'David smote also Hadadezer, the son of Rehob, king of Zobah, as he went to recover his border at the river Euphrates.', '0~01732~ 1~05221~ 3~01909~, 5~01121~ 7~07340~, 8~04428~ 10~06678~, 13~03212~ 15~07725~ 17~03027~ 20~05104~ 21~06578~.'),
  (9832, 12, 10, 31, 'But Jehu took no heed to walk in the law of the LORD God of Israel with all his heart: for he departed not from the sins of Jeroboam, which made Israel to sin.', '1~03058~ 4~08104~ 6~03212~ 9~08451~ 12~03068~ 13~0430~ 15~03478~ 19~03824~: 22~05493~ 26~02403~ 28~03379~, 31~03478~ 33~02398~.'),
  (18423, 23, 39, 2, 'And Hezekiah was glad of them, and shewed them the house of his precious things, the silver, and the gold, and the spices, and the precious ointment, and all the house of his armour, and all that was found in his treasures: there was nothing in his house, nor in all his dominion, that Hezekiah shewed them not.', '1~02396~ 3~08055~ 7~07200~ 10~01004~ 14~05238~, 16~03701~, 19~02091~, 22~01314~, 25~02896~ 26~08081~, 30~01004~ 33~03627~, 38~04672~ 41~0214~: 44~01697~ 47~01004~, 52~04475~, 54~02396~ 55~07200~'),
  (1464, 1, 48, 8, 'And Israel beheld Joseph''s sons, and said, Who are these?', '&para; 1~03478~ 2~07200~ 3~03130~ 4~01121~, 6~0559~, [8]'),
  (26391, 43, 7, 48, 'Have any of the rulers or of the Pharisees believed on him?', '1~3387~ 2~1537~ 4~758~ 5~2228~ 6~1537~ 8~5330~ 9~4100~ 10~1519~ 11~846~?'),
  (11449, 14, 12, 3, 'With twelve hundred chariots, and threescore thousand horsemen: and the people were without number that came with him out of Egypt; the Lubims, the Sukkiims, and the Ethiopians.', '2~0505~ 3~03967~* 4~07393~, 6~08346~ 7~0505~ 8~06571~: 11~05971~ [12] 14~04557~ 16~0935~ 21~04714~; 23~03864~, 25~05525~, 28~03569~.'),
  (16483, 20, 3, 19, 'The LORD by wisdom hath founded the earth; by understanding hath he established the heavens.', '1~03068~ 3~02451~ 5~03245~ 7~0776~; 9~08394~ 12~03559~ 14~08064~.'),
  (26939, 43, 21, 25, 'And there are also many other things which Jesus did, the which, if they should be written every one, I suppose that even the world itself could not contain the books that should be written. Amen.', '0~1161~ 2~2076~ 3~2532~ 4~4183~ 6~243~ 7~3745~ 8~2424~ 9~4160~, 11~3748~, 12~1437~ 16~1125~ 17~2596~ 18~1520~, 20~3633~ 22~3761~ 24~2889~ 25~846~ 27~3761~ 28~5562~ 30~975~ 34~1125~. 35~281~.'),
  (7159, 8, 2, 3, 'And she went, and came, and gleaned in the field after the reapers: and her hap was to light on a part of the field belonging unto Boaz, who was of the kindred of Elimelech.', '2~03212~, 4~0935~, 6~03950~ 9~07704~ 10~0310~ 12~07114~: 15~04745~ 18~07136~ 21~02513~ 24~07704~ [25] 27~01162~, [29] 32~04940~ 34~0458~.'),
  (31085, 66, 21, 16, 'And the city lieth foursquare, and the length is as large as the breadth: and he measured the city with the reed, twelve thousand furlongs. The length and the breadth and the height of it are equal.', '0~2532~ 2~4172~ 3~2749~ 4~5068~, 5~2532~ 7~846~ 8~3372~* 9~2076~ 11~5118~ 12~2532~ 13~3745~ 14~4114~: 15~2532~ 17~3354~ 19~4172~ 22~1909~ 23~2563~,* 24~1427~ 25~5505~ 26~4712~. 28~3372~ 29~2532~ 31~4114~ 32~2532~ 34~5311~ 36~846~ 37~2076~ 38~2470~.'),
  (7079, 7, 20, 18, 'And the children of Israel arose, and went up to the house of God, and asked counsel of God, and said, Which of us shall go up first to the battle against the children of Benjamin? And the LORD said, Judah shall go up first.', '&para; 2~01121~ 4~03478~ 5~06965~, 8~05927~ 11~01004~ 13~0430~ 14~01008~,* 16~07592~ 19~0430~, 21~0559~, 22~04310~ 27~05927~ 28~08462~ 31~04421~ 34~01121~ 36~01144~? 39~03068~ 40~0559~, 41~03063~ [42 44] 45~08462~.'),
  (20694, 26, 12, 5, 'Dig thou through the wall in their sight, and carry out thereby.', '0~02864~ 4~07023~ 7~05869~, 10~03318~'),
  (18458, 23, 40, 29, 'He giveth power to the faint; and to them that have no might he increaseth strength.', '1~05414~ 2~03581~ 5~03287~; [8 10] 12~0202~ 14~07235~ 15~06109~.'),
  (24158, 40, 27, 19, 'When he was set down on the judgment seat, his wife sent unto him, saying, Have thou nothing to do with that just man: for I have suffered many things this day in a dream because of him.', '0~1161~ 1~846~ 4~2521~ 5~1909~ 8~968~, 9~846~ 10~1135~ 11~649~ 12~4314~ 13~846~, 14~3004~ 15~2532~,* 17~4671~ 18~3367~ 22~1565~ 24~1342~: 25~1063~ 28~3958~ 30~4183~ 32~4594~ 33~2596~ 35~3677~ 36~1223~ 38~846~.'),
  (3756, 4, 4, 8, 'And they shall spread upon them a cloth of scarlet, and cover the same with a covering of badgers'' skins, and shall put in the staves thereof.', '3~06566~ 7~0899~ 9~08144~ 10~08438~,* 12~03680~ 17~04372~ 19~08476~ 20~05785~, 23~07760~ 26~0905~'),
  (6141, 6, 12, 5, 'And reigned in mount Hermon, and in Salcah, and in all Bashan, unto the border of the Geshurites and the Maachathites, and half Gilead, the border of Sihon king of Heshbon.', '1~04910~ 3~02022~ 4~02768~, 7~05548~, 11~01316~, 14~01366~ 17~01651~ 20~04602~, 22~02677~ 23~01568~, 25~01366~ 27~05511~ 28~04428~ 30~02809~.'),
  (15998, 19, 119, 91, 'They continue this day according to thine ordinances: for all are thy servants.', '1~05975~ 3~03117~ 7~04941~: [10] 12~05650~.'),
  (30638, 62, 4, 19, 'We love him, because he first loved us.', '0~2249~ 1~25~ 2~846~, 3~3754~ 4~846~ 5~4413~ 6~25~ 7~2248~.'),
  (1407, 1, 46, 16, 'And the sons of Gad; Ziphion, and Haggi, Shuni, and Ezbon, Eri, and Arodi, and Areli.', '2~01121~ 4~01410~; 5~06837~, 7~02291~, 8~07764~, 10~0675~, 11~06179~, 13~0722~, 15~0692~.'),
  (15217, 19, 80, 10, 'The hills were covered with the shadow of it, and the boughs thereof were like the goodly cedars.', '1~02022~ 3~03680~ 6~06738~ 11~06057~ [13 14] 16~0410~ 17~0730~.'),
  (27482, 44, 15, 24, 'Forasmuch as we have heard, that certain which went out from us have troubled you with words, subverting your souls, saying, Ye must be circumcised, and keep the law: to whom we gave no such commandment:', '1~1894~ 4~191~, 5~3754~ 6~5100~ 9~1831~ 10~1537~ 11~2257~ 13~5015~ 14~5209~ 16~3056~, 17~384~ 18~5216~ 19~5590~, 20~3004~, [21 22] 24~4059~, 25~2532~ 26~5083~ 28~3551~: 30~3739~ 32~1291~ 33~3756~ [34] 35~1291~:'),
  (27944, 44, 28, 29, 'And when he had said these words, the Jews departed, and had great reasoning among themselves.', '0~2532~ 2~846~ 4~2036~ 6~5023~, 8~2453~ 9~565~, 11~2192~ 12~4183~ 13~4803~ 14~1722~ 15~1438~.'),
  (2231, 2, 25, 31, 'And thou shalt make a candlestick of pure gold: of beaten work shall the candlestick be made: his shaft, and his branches, his bowls, his knops, and his flowers, shall be of the same.', '&para; 3~06213~ 5~04501~ [6] 7~02889~ 8~02091~: [9] 11~04749~ 14~04501~ 16~06213~: 18~03409~, 21~07070~, 23~01375~, 25~03730~, 28~06525~,'),
  (17569, 22, 2, 6, 'His left hand is under my head, and his right hand doth embrace me.', '2~08040~ [3] 6~07218~, 10~03225~ 12~02263~'),
  (19347, 24, 16, 2, 'Thou shalt not take thee a wife, neither shalt thou have sons or daughters in this place.', '3~03947~ 6~0802~, 11~01121~ 13~01323~ 16~04725~.'),
  (19098, 24, 5, 31, 'The prophets prophesy falsely, and the priests bear rule by their means; and my people love to have it so: and what will ye do in the end thereof?', '1~05030~ 2~05012~ 3~08267~, 6~03548~ 8~07287~ 11~03027~; 14~05971~ 15~0157~ [16 18] 24~06213~ 27~0319~'),
  (23474, 40, 11, 5, 'The blind receive their sight, and the lame walk, the lepers are cleansed, and the deaf hear, the dead are raised up, and the poor have the gospel preached to them.', '1~5185~ 4~308~, 5~2532~ 7~5560~ 8~4043~, 10~3015~ 12~2511~, 13~2532~ 15~2974~ 16~191~, 18~3498~ 21~1453~, 22~2532~ 24~4434~ 30~2097~.'),
  (28055, 45, 4, 17, '(As it is written, I have made thee a father of many nations,) before him whom he believed, even God, who quickeneth the dead, and calleth those things which be not as though they were.', '&para; 0~(2531~ 3~1125~ 4~3754~,* 7~5087~ 8~4571~ 10~3962~ 12~4183~ 13~1484~,) 14~2713~ 16~3739~ 18~4100~, [19] 20~2316~, 22~2227~ 24~3498~, 25~2532~ 26~2564~ 30~5607~ 31~3361~ 33~5613~ 35~5607~.'),
  (24930, 42, 1, 26, 'And in the sixth month the angel Gabriel was sent from God unto a city of Galilee, named Nazareth,', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~1722~ 3~1623~ 4~3376~ 6~32~ 7~1043~ 9~649~ 10~5259~ 11~2316~ 12~1519~ 14~4172~ 16~1056~, 17~3686~ 18~3739~* 19~3478~,'),
  (9556, 12, 1, 15, 'And the angel of the LORD said unto Elijah, Go down with him: be not afraid of him. And he arose, and went down with him unto the king.', '2~04397~ 5~03068~ 6~01696~ 8~0452~, 10~03381~ 15~03372~ 17~06440~. 20~06965~, 23~03381~ 28~04428~.'),
  (30460, 60, 3, 20, 'Which sometime were disobedient, when once the longsuffering of God waited in the days of Noah, while the ark was a preparing, wherein few, that is, eight souls were saved by water.', '1~4218~ 3~544~, 4~3753~ 5~530~ 7~3115~ 9~2316~ 10~1551~ 11~1722~ 13~2250~ 15~3575~, 18~2787~ 21~2680~, 22~3739~ 23~1519~* 24~3641~, 26~5123~, 27~3638~ 28~5590~ 30~1295~ 31~1223~ 32~5204~.'),
  (16932, 20, 18, 22, 'Whoso findeth a wife findeth a good thing, and obtaineth favour of the LORD.', '&para; [0] 1~04672~ 3~0802~ 4~04672~ 6~02896~ [7] 9~06329~ 10~07522~ 13~03068~.'),
  (27461, 44, 15, 3, 'And being brought on their way by the church, they passed through Phenice and Samaria, declaring the conversion of the Gentiles: and they caused great joy unto all the brethren.', '0~3767~ 1~3303~ 5~4311~ 6~5259~ 8~1577~, 11~1330~ 12~5403~ 13~2532~ 14~4540~, 15~1555~ 17~1995~ 20~1484~: 21~2532~ 23~4160~ 24~3173~ 25~5479~ 27~3956~ 29~80~.'),
  (7657, 9, 17, 32, 'And David said to Saul, Let no man''s heart fail because of him; thy servant will go and fight with this Philistine.', '1~01732~ 2~0559~ 4~07586~, 7~0120~ 8~03820~ 9~05307~ 14~05650~ 16~03212~ 18~03898~ 21~06430~.'),
  (24541, 41, 8, 30, 'And he charged them that they should tell no man of him.', '0~2532~ 2~2008~ 3~846~ 4~2443~ 7~3004~ 9~3367~ 10~4012~ 11~846~.'),
  (30462, 60, 3, 22, 'Who is gone into heaven, and is on the right hand of God; angels and authorities and powers being made subject unto him.', '0~3739~ 2~4198~ 3~1519~ 4~3772~, 6~2076~ 7~1722~ 10~1188~ 12~2316~; 13~32~ 14~2532~ 15~1849~ 16~2532~ 17~1411~ 20~5293~ 22~846~.'),
  (23537, 40, 12, 38, 'Then certain of the scribes and of the Pharisees answered, saying, Master, we would see a sign from thee.', '&para; 0~5119~ 1~5100~ 4~1122~ 5~2532~ 8~5330~ 9~611~, 10~3004~, 11~1320~, 13~2309~ 14~1492~ 16~4592~ 17~575~ 18~4675~.'),
  (28584, 46, 10, 1, 'Moreover, brethren, I would not that ye should be ignorant, how that all our fathers were under the cloud, and all passed through the sea;', '&para; 0~1161~, 1~80~, 3~2309~ 4~3756~ 6~5209~ 9~50~, 11~3754~ 12~3956~ 13~2257~ 14~3962~ 15~2258~ 16~5259~ 18~3507~, 19~2532~ 20~3956~ 21~1330~ 22~1223~ 24~2281~;'),
  (16842, 20, 15, 26, 'The thoughts of the wicked are an abomination to the LORD: but the words of the pure are pleasant words.', '&para; 1~04284~ 4~07451~ [5] 7~08441~ 10~03068~: [12 13] 16~02889~ [17] 18~05278~ 19~0561~.'),
  (28267, 45, 12, 6, 'Having then gifts differing according to the grace that is given to us, whether prophecy, let us prophesy according to the proportion of faith;', '0~2192~ 1~1161~ 2~5486~ 3~1313~ 4~2596~ 7~5485~ 10~1325~ 12~2254~, 13~1535~ 14~4394~, [15 17] 18~2596~ 21~356~ 23~4102~;'),
  (6736, 7, 8, 10, 'Now Zebah and Zalmunna were in Karkor, and their hosts with them, about fifteen thousand men, all that were left of all the hosts of the children of the east: for there fell an hundred and twenty thousand men that drew sword.', '1~02078~ 3~06759~ [4] 6~07174~, 9~04264~ 13~06240~ 14~02568~* 15~0505~ [16] 20~03498~ 24~04264~ 27~01121~ 30~06924~: 33~05307~ 35~03967~ 37~06242~ 38~0505~ 39~0376~ 41~08025~ 42~02719~.'),
  (15305, 19, 86, 12, 'I will praise thee, O Lord my God, with all my heart: and I will glorify thy name for evermore.', '2~03034~ 5~0136~ 7~0430~, 11~03824~: 15~03513~ 17~08034~ 19~05769~.'),
  (26271, 43, 5, 46, 'For had ye believed Moses, ye would have believed me: for he wrote of me.', '0~1487~ 1~1063~ 3~4100~ 4~3475~, 8~4100~ 9~302~* 10~1698~: 11~1063~ 12~1565~ 13~1125~ 14~4012~ 15~1700~.'),
  (27264, 44, 9, 32, 'And it came to pass, as Peter passed throughout all quarters, he came down also to the saints which dwelt at Lydda.', '&para; 0~1161~ 2~1096~ 5~1330~ 6~4074~ 8~1330~ 9~1223~* 10~3956~ [11] 14~2718~ 15~2532~ 16~4314~ 18~40~ 19~3588~ 20~2730~ 22~3069~.'),
  (14586, 19, 44, 6, 'For I will not trust in my bow, neither shall my sword save me.', '4~0982~ 7~07198~, 11~02719~ 12~03467~'),
  (10761, 13, 12, 33, 'Of Zebulun, such as went forth to battle, expert in war, with all instruments of war, fifty thousand, which could keep rank: they were not of double heart.', '1~02074~, 5~03318~ 7~06635~, 8~06186~ 10~04421~, 13~03627~ 15~04421~, 16~02572~ 17~0505~, 21~05737~: [22 23] 26~03820~ 27~03820~.'),
  (16254, 19, 139, 6, 'Such knowledge is too wonderful for me; it is high, I cannot attain unto it.', '[0] 1~01847~ [2] 4~06383~ 5~06383~* 10~07682~, 12~03201~ [13]'),
  (12886, 18, 1, 8, 'And the LORD said unto Satan, Hast thou considered my servant Job, that there is none like him in the earth, a perfect and an upright man, one that feareth God, and escheweth evil?', '2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~07854~, 8~07760~ 9~03820~* 11~05650~ 12~0347~, [14 15] 21~0776~, 23~08535~ 26~03477~ 27~0376~, 30~03373~ 31~0430~, 33~05493~ 34~07451~?'),
  (27321, 44, 10, 46, 'For they heard them speak with tongues, and magnify God. Then answered Peter,', '0~1063~ 2~191~ 3~846~ 5~2980~ 6~1100~, 7~2532~ 8~3170~ 9~2316~. 10~5119~ 11~611~ 12~4074~,'),
  (30843, 66, 7, 17, 'For the Lamb which is in the midst of the throne shall feed them, and shall lead them unto living fountains of waters: and God shall wipe away all tears from their eyes.', '0~3754~ 2~721~ 3~3588~ 7~3319~ 8~303~ 10~2362~ 12~4165~ 13~846~, 14~2532~ 16~3594~ 17~846~ 18~1909~ 19~2198~ 20~4077~ 22~5204~: 23~2532~ 24~2316~ 27~1813~ 28~3956~ 29~1144~ 30~575~ 31~846~ 32~3788~.'),
  (28866, 47, 3, 9, 'For if the ministration of condemnation be glory, much more doth the ministration of righteousness exceed in glory.', '0~1063~ 1~1487~ 3~1248~ 5~2633~ [6] 7~1391~, 8~4183~ 9~3123~ 12~1248~ 14~1343~ 15~4052~ 16~1722~ 17~1391~.'),
  (19605, 24, 26, 24, 'Nevertheless the hand of Ahikam the son of Shaphan was with Jeremiah, that they should not give him into the hand of the people to put him to death.', '2~03027~ 4~0296~ 6~01121~ 8~08227~ 11~03414~, 16~05414~ 20~03027~ 23~05971~ 28~04191~.'),
  (1422, 1, 46, 31, 'And Joseph said unto his brethren, and unto his father''s house, I will go up, and shew Pharaoh, and say unto him, My brethren, and my father''s house, which were in the land of Canaan, are come unto me;', '1~03130~ 2~0559~ 5~0251~, 9~01~ 10~01004~, 14~05927~, 16~05046~ 17~06547~, 19~0559~ 23~0251~, 26~01~ 27~01004~, [29] 32~0776~ 34~03667~, 36~0935~'),
  (28244, 45, 11, 19, 'Thou wilt say then, The branches were broken off, that I might be grafted in.', '2~2046~ 3~3767~, 5~2798~ 8~1575~, 9~2443~ 10~1473~ 14~1461~.'),
  (262, 1, 10, 27, 'And Hadoram, and Uzal, and Diklah,', '1~01913~, 3~0187~, 5~01853~,'),
  (14617, 19, 45, 11, 'So shall the king greatly desire thy beauty: for he is thy Lord; and worship thou him.', '3~04428~ 5~0183~ 7~03308~: [10] 12~0113~; 14~07812~'),
  (2178, 2, 23, 29, 'I will not drive them out from before thee in one year; lest the land become desolate, and the beast of the field multiply against thee.', '5~01644~ 7~06440~ 10~0259~ 11~08141~; 14~0776~ 16~08077~, 19~02416~ 22~07704~ 23~07227~'),
  (8485, 10, 17, 28, 'Brought beds, and basins, and earthen vessels, and wheat, and barley, and flour, and parched corn, and beans, and lentiles, and parched pulse,', '0~05066~ 1~04904~, 3~05592~, 5~03335~ 6~03627~, 8~02406~, 10~08184~, 12~07058~, 14~07039~ [15] 17~06321~, 19~05742~, 21~07039~ [22]'),
  (7398, 9, 8, 22, 'And the LORD said to Samuel, Hearken unto their voice, and make them a king. And Samuel said unto the men of Israel, Go ye every man unto his city.', '2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~08050~, 6~08085~ 9~06963~, 11~04427~ 14~04428~. 16~08050~ 17~0559~ 20~0582~ 22~03478~, 23~03212~ 26~0376~ 29~05892~.'),
  (22452, 30, 5, 20, 'Shall not the day of the LORD be darkness, and not light? even very dark, and no brightness in it?', '[0] 3~03117~ 6~03068~ [7] 8~02822~, 11~0216~? 14~0651~, 17~05051~'),
  (26024, 42, 24, 19, 'And he said unto them, What things? And they said unto him, Concerning Jesus of Nazareth, which was a prophet mighty in deed and word before God and all the people:', '0~2532~ 2~2036~ 4~846~, 6~4169~? 7~1161~ 9~2036~ 11~846~, 12~4012~ 13~2424~ 15~3480~, 16~3739~ 17~1096~ 19~4396~ 20~1415~ 21~435~ 22~1722~* 23~2041~ 24~2532~ 25~3056~ 26~1726~ 27~2316~ 28~2532~ 29~3956~ 31~2992~:'),
  (8809, 11, 2, 31, 'And the king said unto him, Do as he hath said, and fall upon him, and bury him; that thou mayest take away the innocent blood, which Joab shed, from me, and from the house of my father.', '2~04428~ 3~0559~ 6~06213~ 10~01696~, 12~06293~ 16~06912~ 22~05493~ 24~02600~ 25~01818~, 27~03097~ 28~08210~, 34~01004~ 37~01~.'),
  (15258, 19, 83, 8, 'Assur also is joined with them: they have holpen the children of Lot. Selah.', '0~0804~ 3~03867~ 8~02220~ 10~01121~ 12~03876~. 13~05542~.'),
  (4339, 4, 20, 23, 'And the LORD spake unto Moses and Aaron in mount Hor, by the coast of the land of Edom, saying,', '2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~04872~ 7~0175~ 9~02022~ 10~02023~, 13~01366~ 16~0776~ 18~0123~, 19~0559~,');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (8008, 9, 30, 23, 'Then said David, Ye shall not do so, my brethren, with that which the LORD hath given us, who hath preserved us, and delivered the company that came against us into our hand.', '1~0559~ 2~01732~, 7~06213~, 9~0251~, 14~03068~ 16~05414~ 20~08104~ 23~05414~ 25~01416~ 27~0935~ 32~03027~.'),
  (25627, 42, 15, 26, 'And he called one of the servants, and asked what these things meant.', '0~2532~ 2~4341~ 3~1520~ 6~3816~, 8~4441~ 9~5101~ 11~5023~ 12~1498~.'),
  (8398, 10, 15, 2, 'And Absalom rose up early, and stood beside the way of the gate: and it was so, that when any man that had a controversy came to the king for judgment, then Absalom called unto him, and said, Of what city art thou? And he said, Thy servant is of one of the tribes of Israel.', '1~053~ 4~07925~, 6~05975~ 7~03027~ 9~01870~ 12~08179~: [16] 20~0376~ 24~07379~ 25~0935~ 28~04428~ 30~04941~, 32~053~ 33~07121~ 37~0559~, 39~0335~ 40~05892~ [41] 45~0559~, 47~05650~ [48] 50~0259~ 53~07626~ 55~03478~.'),
  (13067, 18, 9, 7, 'Which commandeth the sun, and it riseth not; and sealeth up the stars.', '1~0559~ 3~02775~, 6~02224~ 10~02856~ 12~03556~.'),
  (12296, 15, 10, 35, 'Benaiah, Bedeiah, Chelluh,', '0~01141~, 1~0912~, 2~03622~,'),
  (26771, 43, 16, 30, 'Now are we sure that thou knowest all things, and needest not that any man should ask thee: by this we believe that thou camest forth from God.', '0~3568~ 3~1492~ 4~3754~ 6~1492~ 8~3956~, 9~2532~ 10~5532~ 11~2192~ 12~3756~* 13~2443~ 15~5100~ 17~2065~ 18~4571~: 19~1722~ 20~5129~ 22~4100~ 23~3754~ 26~1831~ 27~575~ 28~2316~.'),
  (23185, 40, 2, 6, 'And thou Bethlehem, in the land of Juda, art not the least among the princes of Juda: for out of thee shall come a Governor, that shall rule my people Israel.', '0~2532~ 1~4771~ 2~965~, [3] 5~1093~ 7~2448~, 8~1488~ 9~3760~ 11~1646~ 12~1722~ 14~2232~ 16~2448~: 17~1063~ 19~1537~ 20~4675~ 22~1831~ 24~2233~, 25~3748~ 27~4165~ 28~3450~ 29~2992~ 30~2474~.'),
  (24499, 41, 7, 25, 'For a certain woman, whose young daughter had an unclean spirit, heard of him, and came and fell at his feet:', '0~1063~ [2] 3~1135~, 4~846~ 5~3739~ 6~2365~ 7~2192~ 9~169~ 10~4151~, 11~191~ 12~4012~ 13~846~, 15~2064~ 17~4363~ 18~4314~ 19~846~ 20~4228~:'),
  (2331, 2, 28, 33, 'And beneath upon the hem of it thou shalt make pomegranates of blue, and of purple, and of scarlet, round about the hem thereof; and bells of gold between them round about:', '[1] 4~07757~ 9~06213~ 10~07416~ [11] 12~08504~, [14] 15~0713~, [17] 18~08438~ 19~08144~,* 21~05439~ 23~07757~ 26~06472~ 28~02091~ 29~08432~ 32~05439~:'),
  (15104, 19, 77, 2, 'In the day of my trouble I sought the Lord: my sore ran in the night, and ceased not: my soul refused to be comforted.', '2~03117~ 5~06869~ 7~01875~ 9~0136~: 11~03027~ 12~05064~ 15~03915~, 17~06313~ 20~05315~ 21~03985~ 24~05162~.'),
  (9968, 12, 15, 35, 'Howbeit the high places were not removed: the people sacrificed and burned incense still in the high places. He built the higher gate of the house of the LORD.', '3~01116~ 6~05493~: 8~05971~ 9~02076~ 12~06999~ 17~01116~. 19~01129~ 21~05945~ 22~08179~ 25~01004~ 28~03068~.'),
  (24361, 41, 4, 28, 'For the earth bringeth forth fruit of herself; first the blade, then the ear, after that the full corn in the ear.', '0~1063~ 2~1093~ 5~2592~ 7~844~; 8~4412~ 10~5528~, 11~1534~ 13~4719~, 15~1534~ 17~4134~ 18~4621~ 19~1722~ 21~4719~.'),
  (29204, 48, 5, 26, 'Let us not be desirous of vain glory, provoking one another, envying one another.', '1~1096~ 2~3361~ 3~1096~ 7~2755~, 8~4292~ 10~240~, 11~5354~ 13~240~.'),
  (24639, 41, 10, 40, 'But to sit on my right hand and on my left hand is not mine to give; but it shall be given to them for whom it is prepared.', '0~1161~ 2~2523~ 3~1537~ 4~3450~ 6~1188~ 7~2532~ 8~1537~ 9~3450~ 11~2176~ 12~2076~ 13~3756~ 14~1699~ 16~1325~; 17~235~ [18 23] 25~3739~ 28~2090~.'),
  (19587, 24, 26, 6, 'Then will I make this house like Shiloh, and will make this city a curse to all the nations of the earth.', '3~05414~ 5~01004~ 7~07887~, 10~05414~ 12~05892~ 14~07045~ 18~01471~ 21~0776~.'),
  (12629, 16, 11, 32, 'And at Anathoth, Nob, Ananiah,', '[0] 2~06068~, 3~05011~, 4~06055~,'),
  (20260, 24, 51, 39, 'In their heat I will make their feasts, and I will make them drunken, that they may rejoice, and sleep a perpetual sleep, and not wake, saith the LORD.', '2~02527~ 5~07896~ 7~04960~, 13~07937~, 17~05937~, 19~03462~ 21~05769~ 22~08142~, 25~06974~, 26~05002~ 28~03068~.'),
  (4105, 4, 13, 25, 'And they returned from searching of the land after forty days.', '2~07725~ 4~08446~ 7~0776~ 8~07093~ 9~0705~ 10~03117~.'),
  (23670, 40, 15, 27, 'And she said, Truth, Lord: yet the dogs eat of the crumbs which fall from their masters'' table.', '0~1161~ 2~2036~, 3~3483~, 4~2962~: 5~1063~ 6~2532~ 7~2952~ 8~2068~ 9~575~ 11~5589~ 12~3588~ 13~4098~ 14~575~ 15~846~ 16~2962~ 17~5132~.'),
  (7515, 9, 13, 23, 'And the garrison of the Philistines went out to the passage of Michmash.', '2~04673~ 5~06430~ 7~03318~ 10~04569~ 12~04363~.'),
  (16863, 20, 16, 14, 'The wrath of a king is as messengers of death: but a wise man will pacify it.', '&para; 1~02534~ 4~04428~ [5 6] 7~04397~ 9~04194~: 12~02450~ 13~0376~ 15~03722~'),
  (20178, 24, 50, 3, 'For out of the north there cometh up a nation against her, which shall make her land desolate, and none shall dwell therein: they shall remove, they shall depart, both man and beast.', '4~06828~ 7~05927~ 9~01471~ 14~07896~ 16~0776~ 17~08047~, 21~03427~ 25~05110~, 28~01980~, 30~0120~ 32~0929~.'),
  (25835, 42, 20, 42, 'And David himself saith in the book of Psalms, The Lord said unto my Lord, Sit thou on my right hand,', '0~2532~ 1~1138~ 2~846~ 3~3004~ 4~1722~ 6~976~ 8~5568~, 10~2962~ 11~2036~ 13~3450~ 14~2962~, 16~2521~ 17~1537~ 18~3450~ 20~1188~,'),
  (14462, 19, 37, 3, 'Trust in the LORD, and do good; so shalt thou dwell in the land, and verily thou shalt be fed.', '0~0982~ 3~03068~, 5~06213~ 6~02896~; [7] 10~07931~ 13~0776~, 15~0530~ 19~07462~.'),
  (15479, 19, 96, 5, 'For all the gods of the nations are idols: but the LORD made the heavens.', '3~0430~ 6~05971~ [7] 8~0457~: 11~03068~ 12~06213~ 14~08064~.'),
  (29675, 53, 1, 10, 'When he shall come to be glorified in his saints, and to be admired in all them that believe (because our testimony among you was believed) in that day.', '0~3752~ 3~2064~ 6~1740~ 7~1722~ 8~846~ 9~40~, 10~2532~ 13~2296~ 14~1722~ 15~3956~ 18~4100~ 20~2257~ 21~3142~ 22~1909~ 23~5209~ 25~4100~) 26~1722~ 27~1565~ 28~2250~.'),
  (3933, 4, 7, 78, 'On the twelfth day Ahira the son of Enan, prince of the children of Naphtali, offered:', '2~08147~ 3~06240~* 4~03117~ 5~0299~ 7~01121~ 9~05881~, 10~05387~ 13~01121~ 15~05321~, [16]'),
  (11125, 13, 27, 8, 'The fifth captain for the fifth month was Shamhuth the Izrahite: and in his course were twenty and four thousand.', '1~02549~ 2~08269~ 5~02549~ 6~02320~ [7] 8~08049~ 10~03155~: 14~04256~ [15] 16~06242~ 18~0702~ 19~0505~.'),
  (13077, 18, 9, 17, 'For he breaketh me with a tempest, and multiplieth my wounds without cause.', '2~07779~ 6~08183~, 8~07235~ 10~06482~ 12~02600~.'),
  (30776, 66, 3, 14, 'And unto the angel of the church of the Laodiceans write; These things saith the Amen, the faithful and true witness, the beginning of the creation of God;', '&para; 0~2532~ 3~32~ 6~1577~ 9~2994~ 10~1125~; 12~3592~ 13~3004~ 15~281~, 17~4103~ 18~2532~ 19~228~ 20~3144~, 22~746~ 25~2937~ 27~2316~;'),
  (15192, 19, 78, 70, 'He chose David also his servant, and took him from the sheepfolds:', '1~0977~ 2~01732~ 5~05650~, 7~03947~ 11~06629~ 12~04356~:*'),
  (1800, 2, 10, 18, 'And he went out from Pharaoh, and entreated the LORD.', '3~03318~ 5~06547~, 7~06279~ 9~03068~.'),
  (917, 1, 31, 40, 'Thus I was; in the day the drought consumed me, and the frost by night; and my sleep departed from mine eyes.', '[0] 5~03117~ 7~02721~ 8~0398~ 12~07140~ 14~03915~; 17~08142~ 18~05074~ 21~05869~.'),
  (5544, 5, 24, 13, 'In any case thou shalt deliver him the pledge again when the sun goeth down, that he may sleep in his own raiment, and bless thee: and it shall be righteousness unto thee before the LORD thy God.', '2~07725~ 5~07725~ 8~05667~ 9~07725~ 12~08121~ 14~0935~, 18~07901~ 22~08008~, 24~01288~ 30~06666~ 33~06440~ 35~03068~ 37~0430~.'),
  (4804, 4, 33, 38, 'And Aaron the priest went up into mount Hor at the commandment of the LORD, and died there, in the fortieth year after the children of Israel were come out of the land of Egypt, in the first day of the fifth month.', '1~0175~ 3~03548~ 5~05927~ 7~02022~ 8~02023~ 11~06310~ 14~03068~, 16~04191~ 20~0705~ 21~08141~ 24~01121~ 26~03478~ 29~03318~ 32~0776~ 34~04714~, 37~0259~ [38] 41~02549~ 42~02320~.'),
  (7604, 9, 16, 2, 'And Samuel said, How can I go? if Saul hear it, he will kill me. And the LORD said, Take an heifer with thee, and say, I am come to sacrifice to the LORD.', '1~08050~ 2~0559~, 6~03212~? 8~07586~ 9~08085~ [10] 13~02026~ 17~03068~ 18~0559~, 19~03947~ 21~05697~ 22~01241~ 23~03027~, 25~0559~, 28~0935~ 30~02076~ 33~03068~.'),
  (23564, 40, 13, 15, 'For this people''s heart is waxed gross, and their ears are dull of hearing, and their eyes they have closed; lest at any time they should see with their eyes and hear with their ears, and should understand with their heart, and should be converted, and I should heal them.', '0~1063~ 1~5127~ 2~2992~ 3~2588~ 6~3975~, 7~2532~ [8] 9~3775~ 11~917~ 13~191~, 14~2532~ 15~846~ 16~3788~ 19~2576~; 23~3379~ 26~1492~ [28] 29~3788~, 30~2532~ 31~191~ [33] 34~3775~, 35~2532~ 37~4920~ [39] 40~2588~, 41~2532~ 44~1994~, 45~2532~ 48~2390~ 49~846~.'),
  (11129, 13, 27, 12, 'The ninth captain for the ninth month was Abiezer the Anetothite, of the Benjamites: and in his course were twenty and four thousand.', '1~08671~ [2] 5~08671~ 6~02320~ [7] 8~044~ 10~06069~, 13~01145~: 17~04256~ [18] 19~06242~ 21~0702~ 22~0505~.'),
  (30209, 58, 11, 21, 'By faith Jacob, when he was a dying, blessed both the sons of Joseph; and worshipped, leaning upon the top of his staff.', '1~4102~ 2~2384~, 7~599~, 8~2127~ 9~1538~ 11~5207~ 13~2501~; 14~2532~ 15~4352~, [16] 17~1909~ 19~206~ 21~846~ 22~4464~.'),
  (7088, 7, 20, 27, 'And the children of Israel inquired of the LORD, (for the ark of the covenant of God was there in those days,', '2~01121~ 4~03478~ 5~07592~ 8~03068~, 11~0727~ 14~01285~ 16~0430~ [17] 21~03117~,'),
  (19688, 24, 30, 12, 'For thus saith the LORD, Thy bruise is incurable, and thy wound is grievous.', '2~0559~ 4~03068~, 6~07667~ [7] 8~0605~, [9] 11~04347~ [12] 13~02470~.'),
  (740, 1, 27, 9, 'Go now to the flock, and fetch me from thence two good kids of the goats; and I will make them savoury meat for thy father, such as he loveth:', '0~03212~ 4~06629~, 6~03947~ 10~08147~ 11~02896~ 12~01423~ 15~05795~; 19~06213~ 22~04303~ 25~01~, 29~0157~:'),
  (14273, 19, 25, 13, 'His soul shall dwell at ease; and his seed shall inherit the earth.', '1~05315~ 3~03885~ 5~02896~; 8~02233~ 10~03423~ 12~0776~.'),
  (7763, 9, 20, 26, 'Nevertheless Saul spake not any thing that day: for he thought, Something hath befallen him, he is not clean; surely he is not clean.', '1~07586~ 2~01696~ 5~03972~ 7~03117~: 10~0559~, 13~04745~ [16] 17~01115~ 18~02889~; [21] 23~02889~.'),
  (11491, 14, 14, 7, 'Therefore he said unto Judah, Let us build these cities, and make about them walls, and towers, gates, and bars, while the land is yet before us; because we have sought the LORD our God, we have sought him, and he hath given us rest on every side. So they built and prospered.', '2~0559~ 4~03063~, 7~01129~ 9~05892~, 12~05437~ [13] 14~02346~, 16~04026~, 17~01817~, 19~01280~, [20] 22~0776~ [23] 25~06440~ 30~01875~ 32~03068~ 34~0430~, 37~01875~ [38] 44~05117~ 47~05439~. 50~01129~ 52~06743~.'),
  (1315, 1, 43, 20, 'And said, O sir, we came indeed down at the first time to buy food:', '1~0559~, 2~0994~ 3~0113~, 6~03381~ 7~03381~ 11~08462~ 13~07666~ 14~0400~:'),
  (20357, 25, 2, 16, 'All thine enemies have opened their mouth against thee: they hiss and gnash the teeth: they say, We have swallowed her up: certainly this is the day that we looked for; we have found, we have seen it.', '2~0341~ 4~06475~ 6~06310~ 10~08319~ 12~02786~ 14~08127~: 16~0559~, [20] 21~01104~: 22~0389~ [24] 26~03117~ 30~06960~; 33~04672~, 36~07200~ [37]'),
  (29327, 49, 5, 7, 'Be not ye therefore partakers with them.', '0~1096~ 1~3361~ 2~1096~ 3~3767~ 4~4830~ 6~846~.'),
  (14136, 19, 18, 9, 'He bowed the heavens also, and came down: and darkness was under his feet.', '1~05186~ 3~08064~ 7~03381~: 9~06205~ [10] 13~07272~.'),
  (9849, 12, 11, 12, 'And he brought forth the king''s son, and put the crown upon him, and gave him the testimony; and they made him king, and anointed him; and they clapped their hands, and said, God save the king.', '3~03318~ 5~04428~ 6~01121~, 8~05414~ 10~05145~ [14 15] 17~05715~; 22~04427~, 24~04886~ 28~05221~ 30~03709~, 32~0559~, 34~02421~ 36~04428~.'),
  (11651, 14, 21, 18, 'And after all this the LORD smote him in his bowels with an incurable disease.', '1~0310~ 5~03068~ 6~05062~ 10~04578~ 13~04832~ 14~0369~* 15~02483~.'),
  (30355, 59, 4, 2, 'Ye lust, and have not: ye kill, and desire to have, and cannot obtain: ye fight and war, yet ye have not, because ye ask not.', '1~1937~, 2~2532~ 3~2192~ 4~3756~: 6~5407~, 7~2532~ 10~2206~, 11~2532~ 12~1410~ 13~3756~* 14~2013~: 16~3164~ 17~2532~ 18~4170~, 19~1161~ 21~2192~ 22~3756~, 23~1223~ 24~5209~ 25~154~ 26~3361~.'),
  (23860, 40, 21, 24, 'And Jesus answered and said unto them, I also will ask you one thing, which if ye tell me, I in like wise will tell you by what authority I do these things.', '0~1161~ 1~2424~ 2~611~ 4~2036~ 6~846~, 8~2504~ 10~2065~ 11~5209~ 12~1520~ 13~3056~, 14~3739~ 15~1437~ 17~2036~ 18~3427~, 22~2504~ 24~2046~ 25~5213~ 26~1722~ 27~4169~ 28~1849~ 30~4160~ 32~5023~.'),
  (30758, 66, 2, 25, 'But that which ye have already hold fast till I come.', '0~4133~ 2~3739~ 4~2192~ [5] 7~2902~ 8~3757~ 9~891~ 10~2240~ 11~302~.*'),
  (27955, 45, 1, 9, 'For God is my witness, whom I serve with my spirit in the gospel of his Son, that without ceasing I make mention of you always in my prayers;', '0~1063~ 1~2316~ 2~2076~ 3~3450~ 4~3144~, 5~3739~ 7~3000~ 8~1722~ 9~3450~ 10~4151~ 11~1722~ 13~2098~ 15~846~ 16~5207~, 17~5613~ 19~89~ 21~4160~ 22~3417~ 24~5216~ 25~3842~ 26~1909~ 27~3450~ 28~4335~;'),
  (12645, 16, 12, 12, 'And in the days of Joiakim were priests, the chief of the fathers: of Seraiah, Meraiah; of Jeremiah, Hananiah;', '3~03117~ 5~03113~ 7~03548~, 9~07218~ 12~01~: 14~08304~, 15~04811~; 17~03414~, 18~02608~;'),
  (16692, 20, 10, 27, 'The fear of the LORD prolongeth days: but the years of the wicked shall be shortened.', '&para; 1~03374~ 4~03068~ 5~03254~ 6~03117~: 9~08141~ 12~07563~ 15~07114~.'),
  (15769, 19, 109, 5, 'And they have rewarded me evil for good, and hatred for my love.', '3~07760~ 5~07451~ 7~02896~, 9~08135~ 12~0160~.'),
  (9390, 11, 18, 41, 'And Elijah said unto Ahab, Get thee up, eat and drink; for there is a sound of abundance of rain.', '&para; 1~0452~ 2~0559~ 4~0256~, 7~05927~, 8~0398~ 10~08354~; [12 13] 15~06963~ 17~01995~ 19~01653~.'),
  (294, 1, 11, 25, 'And Nahor lived after he begat Terah an hundred and nineteen years, and begat sons and daughters.', '1~05152~ 2~02421~ 3~0310~ 5~03205~ 6~08646~ 8~08141~ 9~03967~ 10~08672~ 11~06240~* 12~08141~, 14~03205~ 15~01121~ 17~01323~.'),
  (16817, 20, 15, 1, 'A soft answer turneth away wrath: but grievous words stir up anger.', '&para; 1~07390~ 2~04617~ 3~07725~ 5~02534~: 7~06089~ 8~01697~ 10~05927~ 11~0639~.'),
  (490, 1, 19, 29, 'And it came to pass, when God destroyed the cities of the plain, that God remembered Abraham, and sent Lot out of the midst of the overthrow, when he overthrew the cities in the which Lot dwelt.', '6~0430~ 7~07843~ 9~05892~ 12~03603~, 14~0430~ 15~02142~ 16~085~, 18~07971~ 19~03876~ 23~08432~ 26~02018~, 29~02015~ 31~05892~ 34~02004~ 35~03876~ 36~03427~.'),
  (26166, 43, 3, 31, 'He that cometh from above is above all: he that is of the earth is earthly, and speaketh of the earth: he that cometh from heaven is above all.', '2~2064~ 4~509~ 5~2076~ 6~1883~ 7~3956~: 10~5607~ 11~1537~ 13~1093~ 14~2076~ 15~1093~ 16~1537~,* 17~2532~ 18~2980~ 19~1537~ 21~1093~: 24~2064~ 25~1537~ 26~3772~ 27~2076~ 28~1883~ 29~3956~.'),
  (15255, 19, 83, 5, 'For they have consulted together with one consent: they are confederate against thee:', '3~03289~ 4~03162~ 7~03820~: 9~03772~ 10~01285~'),
  (27019, 44, 3, 7, 'And he took him by the right hand, and lifted him up: and immediately his feet and ankle bones received strength.', '0~2532~ 2~4084~ 3~846~ 6~1188~ 7~5495~, [10] 11~1453~: 12~1161~ 13~3916~ 14~846~ 15~939~ 16~2532~ 18~4974~ 20~4732~.'),
  (22983, 38, 7, 12, 'Yea, they made their hearts as an adamant stone, lest they should hear the law, and the words which the LORD of hosts hath sent in his spirit by the former prophets: therefore came a great wrath from the LORD of hosts.', '2~07760~ 4~03820~ [5] 8~08068~, 12~08085~ 14~08451~, 17~01697~ 20~03068~ 22~06635~ 24~07971~ 27~07307~ 28~03027~ 30~07223~ 31~05030~: 35~01419~ 36~07110~ 39~03068~ 41~06635~.'),
  (21830, 27, 3, 14, 'Nebuchadnezzar spake and said unto them, Is it true, O Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego, do not ye serve my gods, nor worship the golden image which I have set up?', '0~05020~ 1~06032~ 3~0560~ [6 7] 8~06656~, 10~07715~, 11~04336~, 13~05665~, 15~03809~ 16~0383~ 17~06399~ 19~0426~, 20~03809~ 21~05457~ 23~01722~ 24~06755~ 28~06966~'),
  (4956, 5, 2, 12, 'The Horims also dwelt in Seir beforetime; but the children of Esau succeeded them, when they had destroyed them from before them, and dwelt in their stead; as Israel did unto the land of his possession, which the LORD gave unto them.', '1~02752~ 3~03427~ 5~08165~ 6~06440~; 9~01121~ 11~06215~ 12~03423~ 17~08045~ 20~06440~ 23~03427~ 28~03478~ 29~06213~ 32~0776~ 35~03425~, 38~03068~ 39~05414~'),
  (10450, 13, 5, 14, 'These are the children of Abihail the son of Huri, the son of Jaroah, the son of Gilead, the son of Michael, the son of Jeshishai, the son of Jahdo, the son of Buz;', '[1] 3~01121~ 5~032~ 7~01121~ 9~02359~, 11~01121~ 13~03386~, 15~01121~ 17~01568~, 19~01121~ 21~04317~, 23~01121~ 25~03454~, 27~01121~ 29~03163~, 31~01121~ 33~0938~;'),
  (21946, 27, 7, 4, 'The first was like a lion, and had eagle''s wings: I beheld till the wings thereof were plucked, and it was lifted up from the earth, and made stand upon the feet as a man, and a man''s heart was given to it.', '1~06933~ [2] 5~0744~, 8~05403~ 9~01611~: 11~01934~ 12~02370~* 13~05705~ 15~01611~ 18~04804~, 23~05191~ 24~04481~ 26~0772~, 29~06966~ 30~05922~ 32~07271~ 35~0606~, 38~0606~ 39~03825~ 41~03052~'),
  (30602, 62, 3, 7, 'Little children, let no man deceive you: he that doeth righteousness is righteous, even as he is righteous.', '1~5040~, 2~4105~ 4~3367~ 5~4105~ 6~5209~: 9~4160~ 10~1343~ 11~2076~ 12~1342~, 14~2531~ 15~1565~ 16~2076~ 17~1342~.'),
  (18544, 23, 44, 2, 'Thus saith the LORD that made thee, and formed thee from the womb, which will help thee; Fear not, O Jacob, my servant; and thou, Jesurun, whom I have chosen.', '1~0559~ 3~03068~ 5~06213~ 8~03335~ 12~0990~, [13] 15~05826~ 17~03372~ 20~03290~, 22~05650~; 25~03484~, 29~0977~.'),
  (21166, 26, 27, 36, 'The merchants among the people shall hiss at thee; thou shalt be a terror, and never shalt be any more.', '1~05503~ 4~05971~ 6~08319~ 13~01091~, [16 17] 19~05769~ 20~05704~.*'),
  (26852, 43, 19, 12, 'And from thenceforth Pilate sought to release him: but the Jews cried out, saying, If thou let this man go, thou art not Caesar''s friend: whosoever maketh himself a king speaketh against Caesar.', '1~1537~ 2~5127~ 3~4091~ 4~2212~ 6~630~ 7~846~: 8~1161~ 10~2453~ 12~2896~, 13~3004~, 14~1437~ 16~630~ 18~5126~ 19~630~, 21~1488~ 22~3756~ 23~2541~ 24~5384~: 25~3956~ 26~4160~ 27~846~ 29~935~ 31~483~ 32~2541~.'),
  (18180, 23, 28, 7, 'But they also have erred through wine, and through strong drink are out of the way; the priest and the prophet have erred through strong drink, they are swallowed up of wine, they are out of the way through strong drink; they err in vision, they stumble in judgment.', '1~0428~ 4~07686~ 6~03196~, 10~07941~ 15~08582~; 17~03548~ 20~05030~ 22~07686~ 25~07941~, 29~01104~ 30~04480~ 31~03196~, 37~08582~ 40~07941~; 42~07686~ 44~07203~, 46~06328~ [47] 48~06417~.'),
  (27714, 44, 21, 34, 'And some cried one thing, some another, among the multitude: and when he could not know the certainty for the tumult, he commanded him to be carried into the castle.', '0~1161~ 1~243~ 2~994~ 4~5100~, 6~243~, 7~1722~ 9~3793~: 10~1161~ 13~1410~ 14~3361~ 15~1097~ 17~804~ 18~1223~ 20~2351~, 22~2753~ 23~846~ 26~71~ 27~1519~ 29~3925~.'),
  (25714, 42, 18, 12, 'I fast twice in the week, I give tithes of all that I possess.', '1~3522~ 2~1364~ 5~4521~, 8~586~ 10~3956~ 11~3745~ 13~2932~.'),
  (8988, 11, 7, 46, 'In the plain of Jordan did the king cast them, in the clay ground between Succoth and Zarthan.', '2~03603~ 4~03383~ 7~04428~ 8~03332~ 12~04568~ 13~0127~ 15~05523~ 17~06891~.'),
  (6582, 7, 3, 7, 'And the children of Israel did evil in the sight of the LORD, and forgat the LORD their God, and served Baalim and the groves.', '2~01121~ 4~03478~ 5~06213~ 6~07451~ 9~05869~ 12~03068~, 14~07911~ 16~03068~ 18~0430~, 20~05647~ 21~01168~ 24~0842~.'),
  (7982, 9, 29, 8, 'And David said unto Achish, But what have I done? and what hast thou found in thy servant so long as I have been with thee unto this day, that I may not go fight against the enemies of my lord the king?', '1~01732~ 2~0559~ 4~0397~, 9~06213~? 14~04672~ 17~05650~ 20~03117~ 25~06440~ 28~03117~, 33~0935~ 34~03898~ 37~0341~ 40~0113~ 42~04428~?'),
  (17496, 21, 9, 12, 'For man also knoweth not his time: as the fishes that are taken in an evil net, and as the birds that are caught in the snare; so are the sons of men snared in an evil time, when it falleth suddenly upon them.', '1~0120~ 3~03045~ 6~06256~: 9~01709~ 12~0270~ 15~07451~ 16~04685~, 20~06833~ 23~0270~ 26~06341~; 27~01992~ [28] 30~01121~ 32~0120~ 33~03369~ 36~07451~ 37~06256~, 40~05307~ 41~06597~'),
  (26228, 43, 5, 3, 'In these lay a great multitude of impotent folk, of blind, halt, withered, waiting for the moving of the water.', '0~1722~ 1~5025~ 2~2621~ 4~4183~ 5~4128~ 8~770~, 10~5185~, 11~5560~, 12~3584~, 14~1551~ 16~2796~ 19~5204~.'),
  (23524, 40, 12, 25, 'And Jesus knew their thoughts, and said unto them, Every kingdom divided against itself is brought to desolation; and every city or house divided against itself shall not stand:', '0~1161~ 1~2424~ 2~1492~ 3~846~ 4~1761~, 6~2036~ 8~846~, 9~3956~ 10~932~ 11~3307~ 12~2596~ 13~1438~ 17~2049~; 18~2532~ 19~3956~ 20~4172~ 21~2228~ 22~3614~ 23~3307~ 24~2596~ 25~1438~ 26~2476~ 27~3756~ 28~2476~:'),
  (4843, 4, 34, 21, 'Of the tribe of Benjamin, Elidad the son of Chislon.', '2~04294~ 4~01144~, 5~0449~ 7~01121~ 9~03692~.'),
  (12041, 15, 2, 5, 'The children of Arah, seven hundred seventy and five.', '1~01121~ 3~0733~, 4~07651~ 5~03967~ 6~07657~ 8~02568~.'),
  (5225, 5, 11, 11, 'But the land, whither ye go to possess it, is a land of hills and valleys, and drinketh water of the rain of heaven:', '2~0776~, 5~05674~ 7~03423~ [9] 11~0776~ 13~02022~ 15~01237~, [16] 17~08354~ 18~04325~ 21~04306~ 23~08064~:'),
  (25577, 42, 14, 11, 'For whosoever exalteth himself shall be abased; and he that humbleth himself shall be exalted.', '0~3754~ 1~3956~ 2~5312~ 3~1438~ 6~5013~; 7~2532~ 10~5013~ 11~1438~ 14~5312~.'),
  (30827, 66, 7, 1, 'And after these things I saw four angels standing on the four corners of the earth, holding the four winds of the earth, that the wind should not blow on the earth, nor on the sea, nor on any tree.', '&para; 0~2532~ 1~3326~ 3~5023~ 5~1492~ 6~5064~ 7~32~ 8~2476~ 9~1909~ 11~5064~ 12~1137~ 15~1093~, 16~2902~ 18~5064~ 19~417~ 22~1093~, 23~3363~ 25~417~ 26~4154~ 27~3363~ 28~4154~ 29~1909~ 31~1093~, 32~3383~ 33~1909~ 35~2281~, 36~3383~ 37~1909~ 38~3956~ 39~1186~.'),
  (9919, 12, 14, 15, 'Now the rest of the acts of Jehoash which he did, and his might, and how he fought with Amaziah king of Judah, are they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Israel?', '&para; 2~03499~ 5~01697~ 7~03060~ 10~06213~, 13~01369~, 17~03898~ 19~0558~ 20~04428~ 22~03063~, [23] 26~03789~ 29~05612~ 32~03117~ 33~01697~ 35~04428~ 37~03478~?'),
  (21024, 26, 23, 8, 'Neither left she her whoredoms brought from Egypt: for in her youth they lay with her, and they bruised the breasts of her virginity, and poured their whoredom upon her.', '1~05800~ 4~08457~ [5] 7~04714~: 11~05271~ 13~07901~ 18~06213~ 20~01717~ 23~01331~, 25~08210~ 27~08457~'),
  (28793, 46, 16, 1, 'Now concerning the collection for the saints, as I have given order to the churches of Galatia, even so do ye.', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~4012~ 3~3048~ 4~1519~ 6~40~, 7~5618~ 11~1299~ 14~1577~ 16~1053~, 17~2532~ 18~3779~ 19~4160~ 20~5210~.'),
  (2922, 3, 7, 38, 'Which the LORD commanded Moses in mount Sinai, in the day that he commanded the children of Israel to offer their oblations unto the LORD, in the wilderness of Sinai.', '2~03068~ 3~06680~ 4~04872~ 6~02022~ 7~05514~, 10~03117~ 13~06680~ 15~01121~ 17~03478~ 19~07126~ 21~07133~ 24~03068~, 27~04057~ 29~05514~.'),
  (28429, 46, 3, 3, 'For ye are yet carnal: for whereas there is among you envying, and strife, and divisions, are ye not carnal, and walk as men?', '0~1063~ 2~2075~ 3~2089~ 4~4559~: 5~1063~ 6~3699~ [7 8] 9~1722~ 10~5213~ 11~2205~, 12~2532~ 13~2054~, 14~2532~ 15~1370~, 17~2075~ 18~3780~ 19~4559~, 20~2532~ 21~4043~ 22~2596~ 23~444~?'),
  (27891, 44, 27, 20, 'And when neither sun nor stars in many days appeared, and no small tempest lay on us, all hope that we should be saved was then taken away.', '0~1161~ 2~3383~ 3~2246~ 4~3383~ 5~798~ 6~1909~ 7~4119~ 8~2250~ 9~2014~, 10~5037~ 11~3756~ 12~3641~ 13~5494~ 15~1945~ [16] 17~3956~ 18~1680~ 20~2248~ 23~4982~ 24~4014~ 25~3063~ 27~4014~.'),
  (11231, 14, 2, 12, 'Huram said moreover, Blessed be the LORD God of Israel, that made heaven and earth, who hath given to David the king a wise son, endued with prudence and understanding, that might build an house for the LORD, and an house for his kingdom.', '0~02361~ 1~0559~ 3~01288~ [4] 6~03068~ 7~0430~ 9~03478~, 11~06213~ 12~08064~ 14~0776~, 17~05414~ 19~01732~ 21~04428~ 23~02450~ 24~01121~, 25~03045~ 27~07922~ 29~0998~, 32~01129~ 34~01004~ 37~03068~, 40~01004~ 43~04438~.'),
  (6562, 7, 2, 10, 'And also all that generation were gathered unto their fathers: and there arose another generation after them, which knew not the LORD, nor yet the works which he had done for Israel.', '4~01755~ 6~0622~ 9~01~: 12~06965~ 13~0312~ 14~01755~ 15~0310~ 18~03045~ 21~03068~, 25~04639~ 29~06213~ 31~03478~.'),
  (22915, 38, 2, 7, 'Deliver thyself, O Zion, that dwellest with the daughter of Babylon.', '0~04422~ 2~01945~ 3~06726~, 5~03427~ [6] 8~01323~ 10~0894~.'),
  (23531, 40, 12, 32, 'And whosoever speaketh a word against the Son of man, it shall be forgiven him: but whosoever speaketh against the Holy Ghost, it shall not be forgiven him, neither in this world, neither in the world to come.', '0~2532~ 1~302~ 2~3739~* 3~2036~ 5~3056~ 6~2596~ 8~5207~ 10~444~, 14~863~ 15~846~: 16~3739~ 17~302~ 18~1161~* 19~2036~ 20~2596~ 22~40~ 23~4151~, 25~863~ 26~3756~ 28~863~ 29~846~, 30~3777~ 31~1722~ 32~5129~ 33~165~, 34~3777~ 35~1722~ [37] 39~3195~.'),
  (15029, 19, 72, 20, 'The prayers of David the son of Jesse are ended.', '1~08605~ 3~01732~ 5~01121~ 7~03448~ 9~03615~.'),
  (27620, 44, 19, 19, 'Many of them also which used curious arts brought their books together, and burned them before all men: and they counted the price of them, and found it fifty thousand pieces of silver.', '0~2425~ 3~1161~ 5~4238~ 7~4021~ 8~4851~ 10~976~ 11~4851~, 14~2618~ 15~1799~ 16~3956~ [17] 18~2532~ 20~4860~ 22~5092~ 24~846~, 25~2532~ 26~2147~ [27] 28~4002~ 29~3461~ [30] 32~694~.');
