  (26976, 44, 2, 11, 'Cretes and Arabians, we do hear them speak in our tongues the wonderful works of God.', '0~2912~ 1~2532~ 2~690~, 5~191~ 6~846~ 7~2980~ 9~2251~ 10~1100~ 13~3167~ 15~2316~.'),
  (24902, 41, 16, 18, 'They shall take up serpents; and if they drink any deadly thing, it shall not hurt them; they shall lay hands on the sick, and they shall recover.', '3~142~ 4~3789~; 6~2579~ 8~4095~ 9~5100~ 10~2286~ 11~5100~, 14~3364~ 15~984~ 16~846~; 19~2007~ 20~5495~ 21~1909~ 23~732~, 24~2532~ 26~2192~ 27~2573~.'),
  (31064, 66, 20, 10, 'And the devil that deceived them was cast into the lake of fire and brimstone, where the beast and the false prophet are, and shall be tormented day and night for ever and ever.', '0~2532~ 2~1228~ 4~4105~ 5~846~ 7~906~ 8~1519~ 10~3041~ 12~4442~ 13~2532~ 14~2303~, 15~3699~ 17~2342~ 18~2532~ 21~5578~ [22] 23~2532~ 26~928~ 27~2250~ 28~2532~ 29~3571~ 30~1519~ 31~165~ 33~165~.'),
  (27841, 44, 26, 2, 'I think myself happy, king Agrippa, because I shall answer for myself this day before thee touching all the things whereof I am accused of the Jews:', '1~2233~ 2~1683~ 3~3107~, 4~935~ 5~67~, 8~3195~ 11~626~ 13~4594~ 14~1909~ 15~4675~ 16~4012~ 19~3956~ 20~3739~ 23~1458~ 24~5259~ 26~2453~:'),
  (1568, 2, 2, 9, 'And Pharaoh''s daughter said unto her, Take this child away, and nurse it for me, and I will give thee thy wages. And the woman took the child, and nursed it.', '1~06547~ 2~01323~ 3~0559~ 6~03212~ 8~03206~ 9~03212~, 11~03243~ 18~05414~ [19] 21~07939~. 24~0802~ 25~03947~ 27~03206~, 29~05134~'),
  (18434, 23, 40, 5, 'And the glory of the LORD shall be revealed, and all flesh shall see it together: for the mouth of the LORD hath spoken it.', '2~03519~ 5~03068~ 8~01540~, 11~01320~ 13~07200~ [14] 15~03162~: 18~06310~ 21~03068~ 23~01696~ [24]'),
  (6758, 7, 8, 32, 'And Gideon the son of Joash died in a good old age, and was buried in the sepulchre of Joash his father, in Ophrah of the Abiezrites.', '1~01439~ 3~01121~ 5~03101~ 6~04191~ 9~02896~ 11~07872~, 14~06912~ 17~06913~ 19~03101~ 21~01~, 23~06084~ 26~033~.'),
  (24676, 41, 11, 25, 'And when ye stand praying, forgive, if ye have ought against any: that your Father also which is in heaven may forgive you your trespasses.', '0~2532~ 1~3752~ 3~4739~ 4~4336~, 5~863~, 6~1536~ 8~2192~ 9~1536~ 10~2596~ 11~5100~: 12~2443~ 13~5216~ 14~3962~ 15~2532~ 16~3588~ 18~1722~ 19~3772~ 21~863~ 22~5213~ 23~5216~ 24~3900~.'),
  (285, 1, 11, 16, 'And Eber lived four and thirty years, and begat Peleg:', '1~05677~ 2~02421~ 3~0702~ 5~07970~ 6~08141~, 8~03205~ 9~06389~:'),
  (10810, 13, 15, 11, 'And David called for Zadok and Abiathar the priests, and for the Levites, for Uriel, Asaiah, and Joel, Shemaiah, and Eliel, and Amminadab,', '1~01732~ 2~07121~ 4~06659~ 6~054~ 8~03548~, 12~03881~, 14~0222~, 15~06222~, 17~03100~, 18~08098~, 20~0447~, 22~05992~,'),
  (22755, 35, 1, 15, 'They take up all of them with the angle, they catch them in their net, and gather them in their drag: therefore they rejoice and are glad.', '2~05927~ 8~02443~, 10~01641~ 14~02764~, 16~0622~ 20~04365~: 23~08055~ 26~01523~.'),
  (6338, 6, 19, 10, 'And the third lot came up for the children of Zebulun according to their families: and the border of their inheritance was unto Sarid:', '&para; 2~07992~ 3~01486~ 5~05927~ 8~01121~ 10~02074~ 14~04940~: 17~01366~ 20~05159~ 23~08301~:'),
  (1772, 2, 9, 25, 'And the hail smote throughout all the land of Egypt all that was in the field, both man and beast; and the hail smote every herb of the field, and brake every tree of the field.', '2~01259~ 3~05221~ 7~0776~ 9~04714~ [12] 15~07704~, 17~0120~ 19~0929~; 22~01259~ 23~05221~ 25~06212~ 28~07704~, 30~07665~ 32~06086~ 35~07704~.'),
  (7117, 7, 21, 8, 'And they said, What one is there of the tribes of Israel that came not up to Mizpeh to the LORD? And, behold, there came none to the camp from Jabeshgilead to the assembly.', '2~0559~, 4~0259~ [5 6] 9~07626~ 11~03478~ 15~05927~ 17~04709~ 20~03068~? 24~0935~ 25~0376~ 28~04264~ 30~01568~ 31~03003~ 33~06951~.'),
