VALUES
  (20494, 26, 1, 21, 'When those went, these went; and when those stood, these stood; and when those were lifted up from the earth, the wheels were lifted up over against them: for the spirit of the living creature was in the wheels.', '2~03212~, [3] 4~03212~; 8~05975~, [9] 10~05975~; 16~05375~ 19~0776~, 21~0212~ 24~05375~ 26~05980~ 30~07307~ 34~02416~ [35] 38~0212~.'),
  (29457, 50, 3, 20, 'For our conversation is in heaven; from whence also we look for the Saviour, the Lord Jesus Christ:', '0~1063~ 1~2257~ 2~4175~ 3~5225~ 4~1722~ 5~3772~; 6~1537~ 7~3739~ 8~2532~ 11~553~ 13~4990~, 15~2962~ 16~2424~ 17~5547~:'),
  (5907, 6, 3, 8, 'And thou shalt command the priests that bear the ark of the covenant, saying, When ye are come to the brink of the water of Jordan, ye shall stand still in Jordan.', '3~06680~ 5~03548~ 7~05375~ 9~0727~ 12~01285~, 13~0559~, 17~0935~ 20~07097~ 23~04325~ 25~03383~, 29~05975~ 31~03383~.'),
  (24696, 41, 12, 12, 'And they sought to lay hold on him, but feared the people: for they knew that he had spoken the parable against them: and they left him, and went their way.', '0~2532~ 2~2212~ 5~2902~ 7~846~, 8~2532~ 9~5399~ 11~3793~: 12~1063~ 14~1097~ 15~3754~ 18~2036~ 20~3850~ 21~4314~ 22~846~: 23~2532~ 25~863~ 26~846~, 30~565~.'),
  (19895, 24, 37, 12, 'Then Jeremiah went forth out of Jerusalem to go into the land of Benjamin, to separate himself thence in the midst of the people.', '1~03414~ 3~03318~ 6~03389~ 8~03212~ 11~0776~ 13~01144~, 15~02505~ 20~08432~ 23~05971~.'),
  (26807, 43, 18, 7, 'Then asked he them again, Whom seek ye? And they said, Jesus of Nazareth.', '0~3767~ 2~1905~ 3~846~ 4~3825~, 5~5101~ 7~2212~? 8~1161~ 10~2036~, 11~2424~ 13~3480~.'),
  (10058, 12, 18, 26, 'Then said Eliakim the son of Hilkiah, and Shebna, and Joah, unto Rabshakeh, Speak, I pray thee, to thy servants in the Syrian language; for we understand it: and talk not with us in the Jews'' language in the ears of the people that are on the wall.', '1~0559~ 2~0471~ 4~01121~ 6~02518~, 8~07644~, 10~03098~, 12~07262~, 13~01696~, 19~05650~ 23~0762~; 26~08085~ [27] 29~01696~ 36~03066~ 39~0241~ 42~05971~ [44] 47~02346~.'),
  (29589, 52, 2, 3, 'For our exhortation was not of deceit, nor of uncleanness, nor in guile:', '0~1063~ 1~2257~ 2~3874~ [3] 4~3756~ 5~1537~ 6~4106~, 7~3761~ 8~1537~ 9~167~, 10~3777~ 11~1722~ 12~1388~:'),
  (10003, 12, 17, 12, 'For they served idols, whereof the LORD had said unto them, Ye shall not do this thing.', '2~05647~ 3~01544~, 6~03068~ 8~0559~ 14~06213~ 16~01697~.'),
  (14634, 19, 46, 11, 'The LORD of hosts is with us; the God of Jacob is our refuge. Selah.', '1~03068~ 3~06635~ [4] 8~0430~ 10~03290~ [11] 13~04869~. 14~05542~.'),
  (20700, 26, 12, 11, 'Say, I am your sign: like as I have done, so shall it be done unto them: they shall remove and go into captivity.', '0~0559~, [2] 4~04159~: 9~06213~, 14~06213~ 19~01473~ [20] 21~03212~ 23~07628~.'),
  (26865, 43, 19, 25, 'Now there stood by the cross of Jesus his mother, and his mother''s sister, Mary the wife of Cleophas, and Mary Magdalene.', '0~1161~ 2~2476~ 3~3844~ 5~4716~ 7~2424~ 8~846~ 9~3384~, 10~2532~ 11~846~ 12~3384~ 13~79~, 14~3137~ [16] 16~3588~ 18~2832~, 19~2532~ 20~3137~ 21~3094~.'),
  (22440, 30, 5, 8, 'Seek him that maketh the seven stars and Orion, and turneth the shadow of death into the morning, and maketh the day dark with night: that calleth for the waters of the sea, and poureth them out upon the face of the earth: The LORD is his name:', '[0 1] 3~06213~ 6~03598~ 8~03685~, 10~02015~ 14~06757~ 17~01242~, 21~03117~ 22~02821~ 24~03915~: 26~07121~ 29~04325~ 32~03220~, 36~08210~ 39~06440~ 42~0776~: 44~03068~ [45] 47~08034~:'),
  (4657, 4, 30, 3, 'If a woman also vow a vow unto the LORD, and bind herself by a bond, being in her father''s house in her youth;', '&para; 2~0802~ 4~05087~ 6~05088~ 9~03068~, 11~0631~ 15~0632~, [16] 19~01~ 20~01004~ 23~05271~;'),
  (28638, 46, 11, 22, 'What? have ye not houses to eat and to drink in? or despise ye the church of God, and shame them that have not? What shall I say to you? shall I praise you in this? I praise you not.', '0~1063~? 2~2192~ 3~3378~ 4~3614~ 6~2068~ 7~2532~ 9~4095~ 10~1519~? 11~2228~ 13~2706~ 15~1577~ 17~2316~, 18~2532~ 19~2617~ 22~2192~ 23~3361~? 24~5101~ 27~2036~ 29~5213~? 32~1867~ 33~5209~ 34~1722~ 35~5129~? 37~1867~ [38] 39~3756~.'),
  (10378, 13, 3, 9, 'These were all the sons of David, beside the sons of the concubines, and Tamar their sister.', '[0 1] 4~01121~ 6~01732~, 9~01121~ 12~06370~, 14~08559~ 16~0269~.'),
  (18529, 23, 43, 15, 'I am the LORD, your Holy One, the creator of Israel, your King.', '[1] 3~03068~, 6~06918~, 8~01254~ 10~03478~, 12~04428~.'),
  (30069, 58, 6, 9, 'But, beloved, we are persuaded better things of you, and things that accompany salvation, though we thus speak.', '&para; 0~1161~, 1~27~, 4~3982~ 6~2909~ 7~4012~ 8~5216~, 9~2532~ 12~2192~ 13~4991~, 14~1499~ 15~2980~ 16~3779~ 17~2980~.'),
  (25615, 42, 15, 14, 'And when he had spent all, there arose a mighty famine in that land; and he began to be in want.', '0~1161~ 2~846~ 4~1159~ 5~3956~, 7~1096~ 9~2478~ 10~3042~ 11~2596~ 12~1565~ 13~5561~; 14~2532~ 15~846~ 16~756~ 20~5302~.'),
  (24195, 40, 27, 56, 'Among which was Mary Magdalene, and Mary the mother of James and Joses, and the mother of Zebedee''s children.', '0~1722~ 1~3739~ 2~2258~ 3~3137~ 4~3094~, 5~2532~ 6~3137~ 8~3384~ 10~2385~ 11~2532~ 12~2500~, 13~2532~ 15~3384~ 17~2199~ 18~5207~.'),
  (12580, 16, 10, 22, 'Pelatiah, Hanan, Anaiah,', '0~06410~, 1~02605~, 2~06043~,'),
  (20945, 26, 20, 41, 'I will accept you with your sweet savour, when I bring you out from the people, and gather you out of the countries wherein ye have been scattered; and I will be sanctified in you before the heathen.', '2~07521~ 6~05207~ 7~07381~, 12~03318~ 15~05971~, 17~06908~ 22~0776~ 27~06327~; 32~06942~ 35~05869~ 37~01471~.'),
  (9875, 12, 12, 17, 'Then Hazael king of Syria went up, and fought against Gath, and took it: and Hazael set his face to go up to Jerusalem.', '&para; 1~02371~ 2~04428~ 4~0758~ 6~05927~, 8~03898~ 10~01661~, 12~03920~ 15~02371~ 16~07760~ 18~06440~ 21~05927~ 23~03389~.'),
  (25617, 42, 15, 16, 'And he would fain have filled his belly with the husks that the swine did eat: and no man gave unto him.', '0~2532~ 3~1937~ 5~1072~ 6~846~ 7~2836~ 8~575~ 10~2769~ 11~3739~ 13~5519~ 15~2068~: 16~2532~ 18~3762~ 19~1325~ 21~846~.'),
  (29540, 51, 3, 7, 'In the which ye also walked some time, when ye lived in them.', '0~1722~ 2~3739~ 3~5210~ 4~2532~ 5~4043~ 7~4218~, 8~3753~ 10~2198~ 11~1722~ 12~846~.'),
  (17881, 23, 10, 22, 'For though thy people Israel be as the sand of the sea, yet a remnant of them shall return: the consumption decreed shall overflow with righteousness.', '3~05971~ 4~03478~ 8~02344~ 11~03220~, [12] 14~07605~ 18~07725~: 20~03631~ 21~02782~ 23~07857~ 25~06666~.'),
  (4298, 4, 19, 4, 'And Eleazar the priest shall take of her blood with his finger, and sprinkle of her blood directly before the tabernacle of the congregation seven times:', '1~0499~ 3~03548~ 5~03947~ 8~01818~ 11~0676~, 13~05137~ 16~01818~ 17~05227~ 18~06440~ 20~0168~ 23~04150~ 24~07651~ 25~06471~:'),
  (18654, 23, 49, 9, 'That thou mayest say to the prisoners, Go forth; to them that are in darkness, shew yourselves. They shall feed in the ways, and their pastures shall be in all high places.', '3~0559~ 6~0631~, 8~03318~; [12] 14~02822~, 15~01540~ 19~07462~ 22~01870~, 25~04830~ [26 27] 31~08205~.'),
  (20022, 24, 44, 3, 'Because of their wickedness which they have committed to provoke me to anger, in that they went to burn incense, and to serve other gods, whom they knew not, neither they, ye, nor your fathers.', '0~06440~ 3~07451~ 7~06213~ 12~03707~, 16~03212~ 19~06999~, [20] 22~05647~ 23~0312~ 24~0430~, 27~03045~ [29] 34~01~.'),
  (5690, 5, 29, 5, 'And I have led you forty years in the wilderness: your clothes are not waxen old upon you, and thy shoe is not waxen old upon thy foot.', '3~03212~ 5~0705~ 6~08141~ 9~04057~: 11~08008~ 15~01086~ 20~05275~ 24~01086~ 27~07272~.'),
  (29598, 52, 2, 12, 'That ye would walk worthy of God, who hath called you unto his kingdom and glory.', '0~2532~* 1~1519~ 2~5209~ 4~4043~ 5~516~ 7~2316~, 10~2564~ 11~5209~ 12~1519~ 13~1438~ 14~932~ 15~2532~ 16~1391~.'),
  (8176, 10, 6, 12, 'And it was told king David, saying, The LORD hath blessed the house of Obededom, and all that pertaineth unto him, because of the ark of God. So David went and brought up the ark of God from the house of Obededom into the city of David with gladness.', '&para; 3~05046~ 4~04428~ 5~01732~, 6~0559~, 8~03068~ 10~01288~ 12~01004~ 14~05654~, [18] 24~0727~ 26~0430~. 28~01732~ 29~03212~ 32~05927~ 34~0727~ 36~0430~ 39~01004~ 41~05654~ 44~05892~ 46~01732~ 48~08057~.'),
  (3040, 3, 11, 38, 'But if any water be put upon the seed, and any part of their carcase fall thereon, it shall be unclean unto you.', '[2] 3~04325~ 5~05414~ 8~02233~, [10 11] 14~05038~ 15~05307~ [18 19] 20~02931~'),
  (14846, 19, 62, 10, 'Trust not in oppression, and become not vain in robbery: if riches increase, set not your heart upon them.', '0~0982~ 3~06233~, 7~01891~ 9~01498~: 11~02428~ 12~05107~, 13~07896~ 16~03820~ [17 18]'),
  (17127, 20, 25, 5, 'Take away the wicked from before the king, and his throne shall be established in righteousness.', '1~01898~ 3~07563~ [4] 5~06440~ 7~04428~, 10~03678~ 13~03559~ 15~06664~.'),
  (10846, 13, 16, 18, 'Saying, Unto thee will I give the land of Canaan, the lot of your inheritance;', '0~0559~, 5~05414~ 7~0776~ 9~03667~, 11~02256~ 14~05159~;'),
  (19109, 24, 6, 11, 'Therefore I am full of the fury of the LORD; I am weary with holding in: I will pour it out upon the children abroad, and upon the assembly of young men together: for even the husband with the wife shall be taken, the aged with him that is full of days.', '3~04392~ 6~02534~ 9~03068~; 12~03811~ 15~03557~: 20~08210~ 23~05768~ 24~02351~, 28~05475~ 31~0970~ 32~03162~: 36~0376~ 39~0802~ 42~03920~, 44~02205~ [46 48] 49~04390~ 51~03117~.'),
  (3947, 4, 8, 3, 'And Aaron did so; he lighted the lamps thereof over against the candlestick, as the LORD commanded Moses.', '1~0175~ 2~06213~ 5~05927~ 7~05216~ 10~06440~ 11~04136~ 12~04501~, 15~03068~ 16~06680~ 17~04872~.'),
  (3498, 3, 25, 24, 'And in all the land of your possession ye shall grant a redemption for the land.', '4~0776~ 7~0272~ 10~05414~ 12~01353~ 15~0776~.'),
  (261, 1, 10, 26, 'And Joktan begat Almodad, and Sheleph, and Hazarmaveth, and Jerah,', '1~03355~ 2~03205~ 3~0486~, 5~08026~, 7~02700~, 9~03392~,'),
  (28065, 45, 5, 2, 'By whom also we have access by faith into this grace wherein we stand, and rejoice in hope of the glory of God.', '0~1223~ 1~3739~ 2~2532~ 4~2192~ 5~4318~ 7~4102~ 8~1519~ 9~5026~ 10~5485~ 11~3739~ 12~1722~ 13~2476~, 14~2532~ 15~2744~ 16~1909~ 17~1680~ 20~1391~ 22~2316~.'),
  (18752, 23, 55, 3, 'Incline your ear, and come unto me: hear, and your soul shall live; and I will make an everlasting covenant with you, even the sure mercies of David.', '0~05186~ 2~0241~, 4~03212~ 7~08085~, 10~05315~ 12~02421~; 16~03772~ 18~05769~ 19~01285~ [22] 24~0539~ 25~02617~ 27~01732~.'),
  (29417, 50, 2, 10, 'That at the name of Jesus every knee should bow, of things in heaven, and things in earth, and things under the earth;', '0~2443~ 1~1722~ 3~3686~ 5~2424~ 6~3956~ 7~1119~ 9~2578~, [11] 13~2032~, 14~2532~ [15] 17~1919~, 18~2532~ [19] 22~2709~;'),
  (22928, 38, 3, 7, 'Thus saith the LORD of hosts; If thou wilt walk in my ways, and if thou wilt keep my charge, then thou shalt also judge my house, and shalt also keep my courts, and I will give thee places to walk among these that stand by.', '1~0559~ 3~03068~ 5~06635~; 9~03212~ 12~01870~, 17~08104~ 19~04931~, 24~01777~ 26~01004~, 30~08104~ 32~02691~, 36~05414~ 40~04108~ 45~05975~.'),
  (6958, 7, 16, 2, 'And it was told the Gazites, saying, Samson is come hither. And they compassed him in, and laid wait for him all night in the gate of the city, and were quiet all the night, saying, In the morning, when it is day, we shall kill him.', '[0 3] 5~05841~, 6~0559~, 7~08123~ 9~0935~ [14] 15~05437~, 18~0693~ 22~03915~ 25~08179~ 28~05892~, 31~02790~ 34~03915~, 35~0559~, 38~01242~, 42~0216~, 45~02026~'),
  (23758, 40, 18, 21, 'Then came Peter to him, and said, Lord, how oft shall my brother sin against me, and I forgive him? till seven times?', '&para; 0~5119~ 1~4334~ 2~4074~ 4~846~, 6~2036~, 7~2962~, 9~4212~ 11~3450~ 12~80~ 13~264~ 14~1519~ 15~1691~, 16~2532~ 18~863~ 19~846~? 20~2193~ 22~2034~?'),
  (10849, 13, 16, 21, 'He suffered no man to do them wrong: yea, he reproved kings for their sakes,', '1~03240~ 3~0376~ 7~06231~: 10~03198~ 11~04428~'),
  (27444, 44, 14, 14, 'Which when the apostles, Barnabas and Paul, heard of, they rent their clothes, and ran in among the people, crying out,', '[0] 1~1161~ 3~652~, 4~921~ 5~2532~ 6~3972~, 7~191~ [8] 10~1284~ 11~846~ 12~2440~, 14~1530~ 16~1519~ 18~3793~, 20~2896~,'),
  (30558, 62, 1, 2, '(For the life was manifested, and we have seen it, and bear witness, and shew unto you that eternal life, which was with the Father, and was manifested unto us;)', '0~2532~* 3~2222~ 5~5319~, 6~2532~ 9~3708~ [10] 11~2532~ 13~3140~, 14~2532~ 15~518~ 17~5213~ 19~166~ 20~2222~, 21~3748~ 22~2258~ 23~4314~ 25~3962~, 26~2532~ 28~5319~ 30~2254~;)'),
  (20896, 26, 19, 6, 'And he went up and down among the lions, he became a young lion, and learned to catch the prey, and devoured men.', '5~01980~ 6~08432~ 8~0738~, 13~03715~, 15~03925~ 17~02963~ 19~02964~, [20] 21~0398~ 22~0120~.'),
  (23812, 40, 20, 10, 'But when the first came, they supposed that they should have received more; and they likewise received every man a penny.', '0~1161~ 3~4413~ 4~2064~, 6~3543~ 7~3754~ 11~2983~ 12~4119~; 13~2532~ 15~2532~ 16~2983~ 18~303~ 19~846~ 20~1220~.'),
  (13595, 18, 30, 29, 'I am a brother to dragons, and a companion to owls.', '3~0251~ 5~08577~, 8~07453~ 10~03284~ 11~01323~.*'),
  (27909, 44, 27, 38, 'And when they had eaten enough, they lightened the ship, and cast out the wheat into the sea.', '0~1161~ 4~5160~ 5~2880~, 7~2893~ 9~4143~, 12~1544~ 14~4621~ 15~1519~ 17~2281~.'),
  (30586, 62, 2, 20, 'But ye have an unction from the Holy One, and ye know all things.', '&para; 0~2532~ 1~5210~ 2~2192~ 4~5545~ 5~575~ 8~40~, 9~2532~ 11~1492~ 13~3956~.'),
  (28964, 47, 8, 16, 'But thanks be to God, which put the same earnest care into the heart of Titus for you.', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~5485~ [2] 4~2316~, 5~3588~ 6~1325~ 8~846~ 10~4710~ 11~1722~ 13~2588~ 15~5103~ 16~5228~ 17~5216~.'),
  (13864, 18, 39, 21, 'He paweth in the valley, and rejoiceth in his strength: he goeth on to meet the armed men.', '1~02658~ 4~06010~, 6~07797~ [8] 9~03581~: 12~03318~ 14~07125~ 17~05402~.'),
  (26062, 43, 1, 4, 'In him was life; and the life was the light of men.', '0~1722~ 1~846~ 2~2258~ 3~2222~; 4~2532~ 6~2222~ 7~2258~ 9~5457~ 11~444~.'),
  (13829, 18, 38, 27, 'To satisfy the desolate and waste ground; and to cause the bud of the tender herb to spring forth?', '1~07646~ 3~07722~ 5~04875~ [6] 11~04161~ 15~01877~ 18~06779~?'),
  (21290, 26, 33, 1, 'Again the word of the LORD came unto me, saying,', '&para; 2~01697~ 5~03068~ 9~0559~,'),
  (7103, 7, 20, 42, 'Therefore they turned their backs before the men of Israel unto the way of the wilderness; but the battle overtook them; and them which came out of the cities they destroyed in the midst of them.', '2~06437~ [3 4] 5~06440~ 7~0376~ 9~03478~ 12~01870~ 15~04057~; 18~04421~ 19~01692~ [24] 28~05892~ 30~07843~ 33~08432~'),
  (28340, 45, 15, 21, 'But as it is written, To whom he was not spoken of, they shall see: and they that have not heard shall understand.', '0~235~ 1~2531~ 4~1125~, 6~3739~ 7~846~ 8~312~ 9~3756~ 10~312~ 11~4012~, 14~3700~: 15~2532~ 16~3739~ 18~191~ 19~3756~ 20~191~ 22~4920~.'),
  (17078, 20, 23, 25, 'Thy father and thy mother shall be glad, and she that bare thee shall rejoice.', '1~01~ 4~0517~ 7~08055~, 11~03205~ 14~01523~.'),
  (29812, 54, 6, 8, 'And having food and raiment let us be therewith content.', '0~1161~ 1~2192~ 2~1305~ 3~2532~ 4~4629~ 7~714~ 8~5125~ 9~714~.'),
  (11932, 14, 33, 15, 'And he took away the strange gods, and the idol out of the house of the LORD, and all the altars that he had built in the mount of the house of the LORD, and in Jerusalem, and cast them out of the city.', '3~05493~ 5~05236~ 6~0430~, 9~05566~ 13~01004~ 16~03068~, 20~04196~ 24~01129~ 27~02022~ 30~01004~ 33~03068~, 36~03389~, 38~07993~ [39] 40~02351~ 43~05892~.'),
  (3823, 4, 5, 26, 'And the priest shall take an handful of the offering, even the memorial thereof, and burn it upon the altar, and afterward shall cause the woman to drink the water.', '2~03548~ 6~07061~ 9~04503~, [10] 12~0234~ 15~06999~ [16] 19~04196~, 21~0310~ 25~0802~ 27~08248~ 29~04325~.'),
  (11026, 13, 24, 3, 'And David distributed them, both Zadok of the sons of Eleazar, and Ahimelech of the sons of Ithamar, according to their offices in their service.', '1~01732~ 2~02505~ 5~06659~ 8~01121~ 10~0499~, 12~0288~ 15~01121~ 17~0385~, 21~06486~ 24~05656~.'),
  (24977, 42, 1, 72, 'To perform the mercy promised to our fathers, and to remember his holy covenant;', '1~4160~ 3~1656~ [4] 5~3326~ 6~2257~ 7~3962~, 8~2532~ 10~3415~ 11~846~ 12~40~ 13~1242~;'),
  (22241, 28, 10, 7, 'As for Samaria, her king is cut off as the foam upon the water.', '[0 1] 2~08111~, 4~04428~ 7~01820~ 10~07110~ 11~06440~ 13~04325~.'),
  (28106, 45, 6, 22, 'But now being made free from sin, and become servants to God, ye have your fruit unto holiness, and the end everlasting life.', '0~1161~ 1~3570~ 4~1659~ 5~575~ 6~266~, 7~1161~ 9~1402~ 11~2316~, 13~2192~ 14~5216~ 15~2590~ 16~1519~ 17~38~, 18~1161~ 20~5056~ 21~166~ 22~2222~.'),
  (8969, 11, 7, 27, 'And he made ten bases of brass; four cubits was the length of one base, and four cubits the breadth thereof, and three cubits the height of it.', '2~06213~ 3~06235~ 4~04350~ 6~05178~; 7~0702~ 8~0520~ [9] 11~0753~ 13~0259~ 14~04350~, 16~0702~ 17~0520~ 19~07341~ 22~07969~ 23~0520~ 25~06967~'),
  (25170, 42, 6, 12, 'And it came to pass in those days, that he went out into a mountain to pray, and continued all night in prayer to God.', '&para; 0~1161~ 4~1096~ 5~1722~ 6~5025~ 7~2250~, 11~1831~ 12~1519~ 14~3735~ 16~4336~, 17~2532~ 20~1273~ 21~2258~* 22~1722~ 23~4335~ 25~2316~.'),
  (26233, 43, 5, 8, 'Jesus saith unto him, Rise, take up thy bed, and walk.', '0~2424~ 1~3004~ 3~846~, 4~1453~, 6~142~ 7~4675~ 8~2895~, 9~2532~ 10~4043~.'),
  (3281, 3, 18, 25, 'And the land is defiled: therefore I do visit the iniquity thereof upon it, and the land itself vomiteth out her inhabitants.', '2~0776~ 4~02930~: 8~06485~ 10~05771~ 16~0776~ 19~06958~ 21~03427~.'),
  (10109, 12, 20, 3, 'I beseech thee, O LORD, remember now how I have walked before thee in truth and with a perfect heart, and have done that which is good in thy sight. And Hezekiah wept sore.', '1~0577~ 4~03068~, 5~02142~ 10~01980~ 11~06440~ 14~0571~ 18~08003~ 19~03824~, 22~06213~ [23 25] 26~02896~ 29~05869~. 31~02396~ 32~01058~ 33~01065~* 34~01419~.'),
  (18736, 23, 54, 4, 'Fear not; for thou shalt not be ashamed: neither be thou confounded; for thou shalt not be put to shame: for thou shalt forget the shame of thy youth, and shalt not remember the reproach of thy widowhood any more.', '0~03372~ 7~0954~: 11~03637~; 19~02659~: 23~07911~ 25~01322~ 28~05934~, 32~02142~ 34~02781~ 37~0491~'),
  (6971, 7, 16, 15, 'And she said unto him, How canst thou say, I love thee, when thine heart is not with me? thou hast mocked me these three times, and hast not told me wherein thy great strength lieth.', '2~0559~ 5~0349~ 8~0559~, 10~0157~ 14~03820~ [15] 21~02048~ 24~07969~ 25~06471~, 29~05046~ 33~01419~ 34~03581~ [35]'),
  (915, 1, 31, 38, 'This twenty years have I been with thee; thy ewes and thy she goats have not cast their young, and the rams of thy flock have I not eaten.', '1~06242~ 2~08141~ [3] [5] 9~07353~ 13~05795~ 18~07921~, 21~0352~ 24~06629~ 28~0398~.'),
  (8077, 10, 2, 21, 'And Abner said to him, Turn thee aside to thy right hand or to thy left, and lay thee hold on one of the young men, and take thee his armour. But Asahel would not turn aside from following of him.', '1~074~ 2~0559~ 7~05186~ 11~03225~ 15~08040~, 19~0270~ 21~0259~ 25~05288~, 27~03947~ 30~02488~. 32~06214~ 33~014~ 36~05493~ 38~0310~'),
  (22309, 29, 1, 9, 'The meat offering and the drink offering is cut off from the house of the LORD; the priests, the LORD''S ministers, mourn.', '2~04503~ 6~05262~ 9~03772~ 12~01004~ 15~03068~; 17~03548~, 19~03068~ 20~08334~, 21~056~.'),
  (10724, 13, 11, 43, 'Hanan the son of Maachah, and Joshaphat the Mithnite,', '0~02605~ 2~01121~ 4~04601~, 6~03146~ 8~04981~,'),
  (23114, 39, 2, 2, 'If ye will not hear, and if ye will not lay it to heart, to give glory unto my name, saith the LORD of hosts, I will even send a curse upon you, and I will curse your blessings: yea, I have cursed them already, because ye do not lay it to heart.', '4~08085~, 10~07760~ [11] 13~03820~, 15~05414~ 16~03519~ 19~08034~, 20~0559~ 22~03068~ 24~06635~, 28~07971~ 30~03994~ 36~0779~ 38~01293~: 42~0779~ 49~07760~ [50] 52~03820~.'),
  (25751, 42, 19, 6, 'And he made haste, and came down, and received him joyfully.', '0~2532~ 3~4692~, 6~2597~, 7~2532~ 8~5264~ 9~846~ 10~5463~.'),
  (511, 1, 20, 12, 'And yet indeed she is my sister; she is the daughter of my father, but not the daughter of my mother; and she became my wife.', '2~0546~ [3 4] 6~0269~; [8] 10~01323~ 13~01~, 17~01323~ 20~0517~; 25~0802~.'),
  (3971, 4, 9, 1, 'And the LORD spake unto Moses in the wilderness of Sinai, in the first month of the second year after they were come out of the land of Egypt, saying,', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~01696~ 5~04872~ 8~04057~ 10~05514~, 13~07223~ 14~02320~ 17~08145~ 18~08141~ 23~03318~ 26~0776~ 28~04714~, 29~0559~,'),
  (951, 1, 32, 19, 'And so commanded he the second, and the third, and all that followed the droves, saying, On this manner shall ye speak unto Esau, when ye find him.', '1~01571~ 3~06680~ 5~08145~, 8~07992~, 12~01980~ 13~0310~* 15~05739~, 16~0559~, 19~01697~ 22~01696~ 24~06215~, 27~04672~'),
  (15300, 19, 86, 7, 'In the day of my trouble I will call upon thee: for thou wilt answer me.', '2~03117~ 5~06869~ 8~07121~ 14~06030~'),
  (9791, 12, 9, 27, 'But when Ahaziah the king of Judah saw this, he fled by the way of the garden house. And Jehu followed after him, and said, Smite him also in the chariot. And they did so at the going up to Gur, which is by Ibleam. And he fled to Megiddo, and died there.', '2~0274~ 4~04428~ 6~03063~ 7~07200~ [8] 10~05127~ 13~01870~ 16~01588~ 17~01004~. 19~03058~ 20~07291~ 21~0310~ 24~0559~, 25~05221~ 30~04818~. [31 34] 38~04608~ 40~01483~, [42] 44~02991~. 47~05127~ 49~04023~, 51~04191~'),
  (24621, 41, 10, 22, 'And he was sad at that saying, and went away grieved: for he had great possessions.', '0~1161~ 3~4768~ 4~1909~ 6~3056~, 9~565~ 10~3076~: 11~1063~ 13~2192~ 14~2258~* 15~4183~ 16~2933~.'),
  (213, 1, 9, 7, 'And you, be ye fruitful, and multiply; bring forth abundantly in the earth, and multiply therein.', '4~06509~, 6~07235~; 9~08317~ 12~0776~, 14~07235~'),
  (11562, 14, 18, 11, 'And all the prophets prophesied so, saying, Go up to Ramothgilead, and prosper: for the LORD shall deliver it into the hand of the king.', '3~05030~ 4~05012~ 6~0559~, 8~05927~ 10~01568~ 11~07433~,* 13~06743~: 16~03068~ 18~05414~ [19] 22~03027~ 25~04428~.'),
  (8202, 10, 7, 15, 'But my mercy shall not depart away from him, as I took it from Saul, whom I put away before thee.', '2~02617~ 6~05493~ 11~05493~ [12] 14~07586~, 18~05493~ 19~06440~'),
  (5827, 5, 33, 11, 'Bless, LORD, his substance, and accept the work of his hands: smite through the loins of them that rise against him, and of them that hate him, that they rise not again.', '0~01288~, 1~03068~, 3~02428~, 5~07521~ 7~06467~ 10~03027~: 11~04272~ 14~04975~ 18~06965~ 25~08130~ 29~06965~ 30~04480~ 31~06965~.'),
  (26841, 43, 19, 1, 'Then Pilate therefore took Jesus, and scourged him.', '&para; 0~5119~ 1~4091~ 2~3767~ 3~2983~ 4~2424~, 5~2532~ 6~3146~ [7]'),
  (2966, 3, 9, 8, 'Aaron therefore went unto the altar, and slew the calf of the sin offering, which was for himself.', '&para; 0~0175~ 2~07126~ 5~04196~, 7~07819~ 9~05695~ 13~02403~, [15]'),
  (21619, 26, 44, 11, 'Yet they shall be ministers in my sanctuary, having charge at the gates of the house, and ministering to the house: they shall slay the burnt offering and the sacrifice for the people, and they shall stand before them to minister unto them.', '4~08334~ 7~04720~, [8] 9~06486~ 12~08179~ 15~01004~, 17~08334~ 20~01004~: 23~07819~ 26~05930~ 29~02077~ 32~05971~, 36~05975~ 37~06440~ 40~08334~'),
  (8204, 10, 7, 17, 'According to all these words, and according to all this vision, so did Nathan speak unto David.', '4~01697~, 10~02384~, 13~05416~ 14~01696~ 16~01732~.'),
  (31070, 66, 21, 1, 'And I saw a new heaven and a new earth: for the first heaven and the first earth were passed away; and there was no more sea.', '&para; 0~2532~ 2~1492~ 4~2537~ 5~3772~ 6~2532~ 8~2537~ 9~1093~: 10~1063~ 12~4413~ 13~3772~ 14~2532~ 16~4413~ 17~1093~ 20~3928~; 21~2532~ 23~2076~ 24~3756~ 25~2089~ 26~2281~.'),
  (15847, 19, 115, 8, 'They that make them are like unto them; so is every one that trusteth in them.', '2~06213~ [8 9] 13~0982~'),
  (30018, 58, 3, 7, 'Wherefore (as the Holy Ghost saith, To day if ye will hear his voice,', '&para; 0~1352~ 1~2531~* 4~40~ 5~4151~ 6~3004~, 8~4594~ 9~1437~ 12~191~ 13~846~ 14~5456~,'),
  (1102, 1, 37, 14, 'And he said to him, Go, I pray thee, see whether it be well with thy brethren, and well with the flocks; and bring me word again. So he sent him out of the vale of Hebron, and he came to Shechem.', '2~0559~ 5~03212~, 9~07200~ 13~07965~ 16~0251~, 18~07965~ 21~06629~; 23~07725~ 25~01697~ 26~07725~. 29~07971~ 34~06010~ 36~02275~, 39~0935~ 41~07927~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (18987, 24, 2, 13, 'For my people have committed two evils; they have forsaken me the fountain of living waters, and hewed them out cisterns, broken cisterns, that can hold no water.', '2~05971~ 4~06213~ 5~08147~ 6~07451~; 9~05800~ 12~04726~ 14~02416~ 15~04325~, [16] 19~02672~ 20~0877~, 21~07665~ 22~0877~, 25~03557~ 27~04325~.'),
  (13409, 18, 22, 11, 'Or darkness, that thou canst not see; and abundance of waters cover thee.', '1~02822~, [2] 6~07200~; 8~08229~ 10~04325~ 11~03680~'),
  (21338, 26, 34, 16, 'I will seek that which was lost, and bring again that which was driven away, and will bind up that which was broken, and will strengthen that which was sick: but I will destroy the fat and the strong; I will feed them with judgment.', '2~01245~ 6~06~, 9~07725~ 14~05080~, 18~02280~ [19 21] 22~07665~, 25~02388~ 29~02470~: 33~08045~ 35~08082~ 38~02389~; 41~07462~ 44~04941~.'),
  (15519, 19, 100, 2, 'Serve the LORD with gladness: come before his presence with singing.', '0~05647~ 2~03068~ 4~08057~: 5~0935~ 8~06440~ 10~07445~.'),
  (28837, 47, 1, 21, 'Now he which stablisheth us with you in Christ, and hath anointed us, is God;', '0~1161~ 3~950~ 4~2248~ 5~4862~ 6~5213~ 7~1519~ 8~5547~, 9~2532~ 11~5548~ 12~2248~, [13] 14~2316~;'),
  (30815, 66, 6, 6, 'And I heard a voice in the midst of the four beasts say, A measure of wheat for a penny, and three measures of barley for a penny; and see thou hurt not the oil and the wine.', '0~2532~ 2~191~ 4~5456~ 5~1722~ 7~3319~ 10~5064~ 11~2226~ 12~3004~, 14~5518~ 16~4621~ 19~1220~, 20~2532~ 21~5140~ 22~5518~ 24~2915~ 27~1220~; 28~2532~ [29] 31~91~ 32~3361~ 34~1637~ 35~2532~ 37~3631~.'),
  (26847, 43, 19, 7, 'The Jews answered him, We have a law, and by our law he ought to die, because he made himself the Son of God.', '1~2453~ 2~611~ 3~846~, 4~2249~ 5~2192~ 7~3551~, 8~2532~ 9~2596~ 10~2257~ 11~3551~ 13~3784~ 15~599~, 16~3754~ 18~4160~ 19~1438~ 21~5207~ 23~2316~.'),
  (4923, 5, 1, 25, 'And they took of the fruit of the land in their hands, and brought it down unto us, and brought us word again, and said, It is a good land which the LORD our God doth give us.', '2~03947~ 5~06529~ 8~0776~ 11~03027~, [14] 15~03381~ 19~07725~ 21~01697~ 22~07725~, 24~0559~, [25 26] 28~02896~ 29~0776~ 32~03068~ 34~0430~ 36~05414~'),
  (21857, 27, 4, 11, 'The tree grew, and was strong, and the height thereof reached unto heaven, and the sight thereof to the end of all the earth:', '1~0363~ 2~07236~, 5~08631~, 8~07314~ 10~04291~ 12~08065~, 15~02379~ 19~05491~ 21~03606~ 23~0772~:'),
  (1423, 1, 46, 32, 'And the men are shepherds, for their trade hath been to feed cattle; and they have brought their flocks, and their herds, and all that they have.', '2~0582~ [3] 4~07462~ 5~06629~,* 13~04735~; 17~0935~ 19~06629~, 22~01241~,'),
  (3186, 3, 15, 13, 'And when he that hath an issue is cleansed of his issue; then he shall number to himself seven days for his cleansing, and wash his clothes, and bathe his flesh in running water, and shall be clean.', '6~02100~ 8~02891~ 11~02101~; 15~05608~ 18~07651~ 19~03117~ 22~02893~, 24~03526~ 26~0899~, 28~07364~ 30~01320~ 32~02416~ 33~04325~, 37~02891~.'),
  (15877, 19, 117, 1, 'O Praise the LORD, all ye nations: praise him, all ye people.', '&para; 1~01984~ 3~03068~, 6~01471~: 7~07623~ 11~0523~.'),
  (3214, 3, 16, 8, 'And Aaron shall cast lots upon the two goats; one lot for the LORD, and the other lot for the scapegoat.', '1~0175~ 3~05414~ 4~01486~ 7~08147~ 8~08163~; 9~0259~ 10~01486~ 13~03068~, 16~0259~ 17~01486~ 20~05799~.'),
  (15414, 19, 91, 10, 'There shall no evil befall thee, neither shall any plague come nigh thy dwelling.', '3~07451~ 4~0579~ 9~05061~ 11~07126~ 13~0168~.'),
  (7976, 9, 29, 2, 'And the lords of the Philistines passed on by hundreds, and by thousands: but David and his men passed on in the rereward with Achish.', '2~05633~ 5~06430~ 7~05674~ 9~03967~, 12~0505~: 14~01732~ 17~0582~ 19~05674~ 22~0314~ 24~0397~.'),
  (22706, 34, 1, 13, 'For now will I break his yoke from off thee, and will burst thy bonds in sunder.', '4~07665~ 6~04132~ 12~05423~ 14~04147~ 16~05423~.'),
  (29107, 48, 2, 10, 'Only they would that we should remember the poor; the same which I also was forward to do.', '0~3440~ [1 2] 3~2443~ 6~3421~ 8~4434~; 10~5124~ 11~846~* 12~3739~ 13~4704~ 14~2532~ 16~4704~ 18~4160~.'),
  (25540, 42, 13, 9, 'And if it bear fruit, well: and if not, then after that thou shalt cut it down.', '1~3303~ 2~2579~ 3~4160~ 4~2590~, [5] 8~1490~, [9] 11~3195~ 12~1519~* 15~1581~ 16~846~ 17~1581~.'),
  (11472, 14, 13, 10, 'But as for us, the LORD is our God, and we have not forsaken him; and the priests, which minister unto the LORD, are the sons of Aaron, and the Levites wait upon their business:', '5~03068~ [6] 8~0430~, 13~05800~ 17~03548~, 19~08334~ 22~03068~, [23] 25~01121~ 27~0175~, 30~03881~ [31] [33] 34~04399~:'),
  (14797, 19, 58, 9, 'Before your pots can feel the thorns, he shall take them away as with a whirlwind, both living, and in his wrath.', '2~05518~ 4~0995~ 6~0329~, 15~08175~, 17~02416~, [20] 21~02740~.'),
  (5247, 5, 12, 1, 'These are the statutes and judgments, which ye shall observe to do in the land, which the LORD God of thy fathers giveth thee to possess it, all the days that ye live upon the earth.', '&para; [1] 3~02706~ 5~04941~, 9~08104~ 11~06213~ 14~0776~, 17~03068~ 18~0430~ 21~01~ 22~05414~ 25~03423~ 29~03117~ 32~02416~ 35~0127~.'),
  (8456, 10, 16, 23, 'And the counsel of Ahithophel, which he counselled in those days, was as if a man had inquired at the oracle of God: so was all the counsel of Ahithophel both with David and with Absalom.', '2~06098~ 4~0302~, 7~03289~ 10~03117~, [11] 15~0376~ 17~07592~ 20~01697~ 22~0430~: [24] 27~06098~ 29~0302~ 32~01732~ 35~053~.'),
  (27765, 44, 23, 15, 'Now therefore ye with the council signify to the chief captain that he bring him down unto you to morrow, as though ye would inquire something more perfectly concerning him: and we, or ever he come near, are ready to kill him.', '0~3568~ 1~3767~ 2~5210~ 3~4862~ 5~4892~ 6~1718~ 10~5506~ 11~3704~ 13~2609~ 14~846~ 15~2609~ 16~4314~ 17~5209~ 19~839~, 20~5613~ 23~3195~ 24~1231~ 27~197~ 28~4012~ 29~846~: 30~1161~ 31~2249~, 33~4253~ 34~846~ 36~1448~, 37~2070~ 38~2092~ 40~337~ 41~846~.'),
  (11531, 14, 16, 13, 'And Asa slept with his fathers, and died in the one and fortieth year of his reign.', '1~0609~ 2~07901~ 5~01~, 7~04191~ 10~0259~ 12~0705~ 13~08141~ 16~04427~.'),
  (14825, 19, 60, 9, 'Who will bring me into the strong city? who will lead me into Edom?', '2~02986~ [4] 6~04692~ 7~05892~? 10~05148~ 13~0123~?'),
  (13217, 18, 15, 5, 'For thy mouth uttereth thine iniquity, and thou choosest the tongue of the crafty.', '2~06310~ 3~0502~ 5~05771~, 8~0977~ 10~03956~ 13~06175~.'),
  (28280, 45, 12, 19, 'Dearly beloved, avenge not yourselves, but rather give place unto wrath: for it is written, Vengeance is mine; I will repay, saith the Lord.', '1~27~, 2~1556~ 3~3361~ 4~1438~, 5~235~ [6] 7~1325~ 8~5117~ 10~3709~: 11~1063~ 14~1125~, 15~1557~ [16] 17~1698~; 18~1473~ 20~467~, 21~3004~ 23~2962~.'),
  (4190, 4, 15, 32, 'And while the children of Israel were in the wilderness, they found a man that gathered sticks upon the sabbath day.', '3~01121~ 5~03478~ 9~04057~, 11~04672~ 13~0376~ 15~07197~ 16~06086~ 19~07676~ 20~03117~.'),
  (4708, 4, 31, 38, 'And the beeves were thirty and six thousand; of which the LORD''S tribute was threescore and twelve.', '2~01241~ [3] 4~07970~ 6~08337~ 7~0505~; 11~03068~ 12~04371~ [13] 16~08147~ 17~07657~.*'),
  (20286, 24, 52, 1, 'Zedekiah was one and twenty years old when he began to reign, and he reigned eleven years in Jerusalem. And his mother''s name was Hamutal the daughter of Jeremiah of Libnah.', '&para; 0~06667~ [1] 2~0259~ 4~06242~ 5~08141~ 6~01121~ 11~04427~, 14~04427~ 15~06240~ 16~0259~* 17~08141~ 19~03389~. 22~0517~ 23~08034~ [24] 25~02537~ 27~01323~ 29~03414~ 31~03841~.'),
  (12097, 15, 2, 61, 'And of the children of the priests: the children of Habaiah, the children of Koz, the children of Barzillai; which took a wife of the daughters of Barzillai the Gileadite, and was called after their name:', '3~01121~ 6~03548~: 8~01121~ 10~02252~, 12~01121~ 14~06976~, 16~01121~ 18~01271~; 20~03947~ 22~0802~ 25~01323~ 27~01271~ 29~01569~, 32~07121~ 35~08034~:'),
  (27832, 44, 25, 20, 'And because I doubted of such manner of questions, I asked him whether he would go to Jerusalem, and there be judged of these matters.', '0~1161~ 2~1473~ 3~639~ 4~1519~ 5~5127~ 6~4012~ 8~2214~, 10~3004~ [11] 12~1487~ 14~1014~ 15~4198~ 16~1519~ 17~2419~, 19~2546~ 21~2919~ 22~4012~ 24~5130~.'),
  (8936, 11, 6, 32, 'The two doors also were of olive tree; and he carved upon them carvings of cherubims and palm trees and open flowers, and overlaid them with gold, and spread gold upon the cherubims, and upon the palm trees.', '1~08147~ 2~01817~ [4 5] 6~08081~ 7~06086~; 10~07049~ 13~04734~ 15~03742~ 18~08561~ 20~06362~ 21~06731~, 23~06823~ [24] 26~02091~, 28~07286~ 29~02091~ 32~03742~, 37~08561~.'),
  (14065, 19, 10, 15, 'Break thou the arm of the wicked and the evil man: seek out his wickedness till thou find none.', '0~07665~ 3~02220~ 6~07563~ 9~07451~ [10] 12~01875~ 14~07562~ [15] 17~04672~ 18~01077~.'),
  (25345, 42, 9, 32, 'But Peter and they that were with him were heavy with sleep: and when they were awake, they saw his glory, and the two men that stood with him.', '0~1161~ 1~4074~ 2~2532~ 6~4862~ 7~846~ 8~2258~ 9~916~ 11~5258~: 12~1161~ 16~1235~, 18~1492~ 19~846~ 20~1391~, 21~2532~ 23~1417~ 24~435~ 27~4921~ 28~846~.'),
  (17404, 21, 4, 14, 'For out of prison he cometh to reign; whereas also he that is born in his kingdom becometh poor.', '3~0631~ 4~01004~* 6~03318~ 8~04427~; [11 13] 14~03205~ 17~04438~ 19~07326~.'),
  (24810, 41, 14, 45, 'And as soon as he was come, he goeth straightway to him, and saith, Master, master; and kissed him.', '0~2532~ 6~2064~, 8~4334~ 9~2112~ 11~846~, 13~3004~, 14~4461~, 15~4461~; 16~2532~ 17~2705~ 18~846~.'),
  (8015, 9, 30, 30, 'And to them which were in Hormah, and to them which were in Chorashan, and to them which were in Athach,', '[2] [4] 6~02767~, [9] [11] 13~03565~, [16] [18] 20~06269~,'),
  (5198, 5, 10, 6, 'And the children of Israel took their journey from Beeroth of the children of Jaakan to Mosera: there Aaron died, and there he was buried; and Eleazar his son ministered in the priest''s office in his stead.', '2~01121~ 4~03478~ 7~05265~ 14~0885~ 16~04149~: 18~0175~ 19~04191~, 24~06912~; 26~0499~ 28~01121~ 33~03547~'),
  (11481, 14, 13, 19, 'And Abijah pursued after Jeroboam, and took cities from him, Bethel with the towns thereof, and Jeshanah with the towns thereof, and Ephrain with the towns thereof.', '1~029~ 2~07291~ 3~0310~ 4~03379~, 6~03920~ 7~05892~ 10~01008~ 13~01323~ 16~03466~ 19~01323~ 22~06085~ 25~01323~'),
  (20695, 26, 12, 6, 'In their sight shalt thou bear it upon thy shoulders, and carry it forth in the twilight: thou shalt cover thy face, that thou see not the ground: for I have set thee for a sign unto the house of Israel.', '2~05869~ 5~05375~ [6] [8] 9~03802~, [10] [12] 13~03318~ 16~05939~: 19~03680~ 21~06440~, 24~07200~ 27~0776~: 31~05414~ [33] 35~04159~ 38~01004~ 40~03478~.'),
  (24642, 41, 10, 43, 'But so shall it not be among you: but whosoever will be great among you, shall be your minister:', '0~1161~ 1~3779~ 3~2071~ 4~3756~ 5~2071~ 6~1722~ 7~5213~: 8~235~ 9~1437~ 10~3739~* 11~2309~ 12~1096~ 13~3173~ 14~1722~ 15~5213~, 17~2071~ 18~5216~ 19~1249~:'),
  (7162, 8, 2, 6, 'And the servant that was set over the reapers answered and said, It is the Moabitish damsel that came back with Naomi out of the country of Moab:', '2~05288~ 5~05324~ 8~07114~ 9~06030~ 11~0559~, [13] 15~04125~ 16~05291~ 19~07725~ 21~05281~ 25~07704~ 27~04124~:'),
  (16926, 20, 18, 16, 'A man''s gift maketh room for him, and bringeth him before great men.', '&para; 1~0120~ 2~04976~ 4~07337~ 8~05148~ 10~06440~ 12~01419~.'),
  (1600, 2, 3, 16, 'Go, and gather the elders of Israel together, and say unto them, The LORD God of your fathers, the God of Abraham, of Isaac, and of Jacob, appeared unto me, saying, I have surely visited you, and seen that which is done to you in Egypt:', '&para; 0~03212~, 2~0622~ 4~02205~ 6~03478~ 7~0622~, 9~0559~ 13~03068~ 14~0430~ 17~01~, 19~0430~ 21~085~, 23~03327~, 26~03290~, 27~07200~ 30~0559~, 33~06485~ 34~06485~ [37] 41~06213~ 45~04714~:'),
  (18946, 23, 66, 15, 'For, behold, the LORD will come with fire, and with his chariots like a whirlwind, to render his anger with fury, and his rebuke with flames of fire.', '&para; 3~03068~ 5~0935~ 7~0784~, 11~04818~ 14~05492~, 16~07725~ 18~0639~ 20~02534~, 23~01606~ 25~03851~ 27~0784~.'),
  (15111, 19, 77, 9, 'Hath God forgotten to be gracious? hath he in anger shut up his tender mercies? Selah.', '1~0410~ 2~07911~ 5~02589~? 9~0639~ 11~07092~ 14~07356~? 15~05542~.'),
  (22610, 33, 2, 6, 'Prophesy ye not, say they to them that prophesy: they shall not prophesy to them, that they shall not take shame.', '&para; 0~05197~ [3 7] 8~05197~: 12~05197~ [15] 19~05253~ 20~03639~.'),
  (4802, 4, 33, 36, 'And they removed from Eziongaber, and pitched in the wilderness of Zin, which is Kadesh.', '2~05265~ 4~06100~, 6~02583~ 9~04057~ 11~06790~, [13] 14~06946~.'),
  (22049, 27, 11, 4, 'And when he shall stand up, his kingdom shall be broken, and shall be divided toward the four winds of heaven; and not to his posterity, nor according to his dominion which he ruled: for his kingdom shall be plucked up, even for others beside those.', '5~05975~, 7~04438~ 10~07665~, 14~02673~ 17~0702~ 18~07307~ 20~08064~; 25~0319~, 30~04915~ 33~04910~: 36~04438~ 40~05428~, 43~0312~'),
  (6088, 6, 10, 18, 'And Joshua said, Roll great stones upon the mouth of the cave, and set men by it for to keep them:', '1~03091~ 2~0559~, 3~01556~ 4~01419~ 5~068~ 8~06310~ 11~04631~, 13~06485~ 14~0582~ 19~08104~'),
  (7873, 9, 25, 5, 'And David sent out ten young men, and David said unto the young men, Get you up to Carmel, and go to Nabal, and greet him in my name:', '1~01732~ 3~07971~ 4~06235~ 6~05288~, 8~01732~ 9~0559~ 13~05288~, 16~05927~ 18~03760~, 20~0935~ 22~05037~, 24~07592~ 25~07965~* 29~08034~:'),
  (12077, 15, 2, 41, 'The singers: the children of Asaph, an hundred twenty and eight.', '1~07891~: 3~01121~ 5~0623~, 7~03967~ 8~06242~ 10~08083~.'),
  (16557, 20, 6, 8, 'Provideth her meat in the summer, and gathereth her food in the harvest.', '0~03559~ 2~03899~ 5~07019~, [6] 7~0103~ 9~03978~ 12~07105~.'),
  (13373, 18, 21, 9, 'Their houses are safe from fear, neither is the rod of God upon them.', '1~01004~ [2] 3~07965~ 5~06343~, [7] 9~07626~ 11~0433~'),
  (27727, 44, 22, 7, 'And I fell unto the ground, and heard a voice saying unto me, Saul, Saul, why persecutest thou me?', '0~5037~ 2~4098~ 3~1519~ 5~1475~, 6~2532~ 7~191~ 9~5456~ 10~3004~ 12~3427~, 13~4549~, 14~4549~, 15~5101~ 17~1377~ 18~3165~?'),
  (21991, 27, 8, 21, 'And the rough goat is the king of Grecia: and the great horn that is between his eyes is the first king.', '2~08163~ 3~06842~ [4] 6~04428~ 8~03120~: 11~01419~ 12~07161~ [14] 17~05869~ [18] 20~07223~ 21~04428~.'),
  (7734, 9, 19, 21, 'And when it was told Saul, he sent other messengers, and they prophesied likewise. And Saul sent messengers again the third time, and they prophesied also.', '4~05046~ 5~07586~, 7~07971~ 8~0312~ 9~04397~, 12~05012~ 15~07586~ 16~07971~ 17~04397~ 18~03254~ 20~07992~ 24~05012~'),
  (15033, 19, 73, 4, 'For there are no bands in their death: but their strength is firm.', '[1 2] 4~02784~ 7~04194~: 10~0193~ [11] 12~01277~.'),
  (24986, 42, 2, 1, 'And it came to pass in those days, that there went out a decree from Caesar Augustus, that all the world should be taxed.', '&para; 0~1161~ 4~1096~ 5~1722~ 6~1565~ 7~2250~, 11~1831~ 13~1378~ 14~3844~ 15~2541~ 16~828~, 18~3956~ 20~3625~ 23~583~.'),
  (22281, 28, 13, 6, 'According to their pasture, so were they filled; they were filled, and their heart was exalted; therefore have they forgotten me.', '3~04830~, 7~07646~; 10~07646~, 13~03820~ 15~07311~; 19~07911~'),
  (18651, 23, 49, 6, 'And he said, It is a light thing that thou shouldest be my servant to raise up the tribes of Jacob, and to restore the preserved of Israel: I will also give thee for a light to the Gentiles, that thou mayest be my salvation unto the end of the earth.', '2~0559~, 7~07043~ 13~05650~ 16~06965~ 18~07626~ 20~03290~, 23~07725~ 25~05341~ 27~03478~: 31~05414~ 35~0216~ 38~01471~, 44~03444~ 47~07097~ 50~0776~.'),
  (9981, 12, 16, 10, 'And king Ahaz went to Damascus to meet Tiglathpileser king of Assyria, and saw an altar that was at Damascus: and king Ahaz sent to Urijah the priest the fashion of the altar, and the pattern of it, according to all the workmanship thereof.', '&para; 1~04428~ 2~0271~ 3~03212~ 5~01834~ 7~07125~ 8~08407~ 9~04428~ 11~0804~, 13~07200~ 15~04196~ [17] 19~01834~: 21~04428~ 22~0271~ 23~07971~ 25~0223~ 27~03548~ 29~01823~ 32~04196~, 35~08403~ 42~04639~'),
  (16622, 20, 8, 11, 'For wisdom is better than rubies; and all the things that may be desired are not to be compared to it.', '1~02451~ [2] 3~02896~ 5~06443~; 13~02656~ 18~07737~'),
  (5037, 5, 4, 27, 'And the LORD shall scatter you among the nations, and ye shall be left few in number among the heathen, whither the LORD shall lead you.', '2~03068~ 4~06327~ 8~05971~, 13~07604~ 14~04962~ 16~04557~ 19~01471~, 22~03068~ 24~05090~'),
  (21820, 27, 3, 4, 'Then an herald cried aloud, To you it is commanded, O people, nations, and languages,', '2~03744~ 3~07123~ 4~02429~, 9~0560~, 11~05972~, 12~0524~, 14~03961~,'),
  (25358, 42, 9, 45, 'But they understood not this saying, and it was hid from them, that they perceived it not: and they feared to ask him of that saying.', '0~1161~ 3~50~ 4~5124~ 5~4487~, 6~2532~ 8~2258~ 9~3871~ 10~575~ 11~846~, 12~3363~ 14~143~ 15~846~ 16~3363~: 17~2532~ 19~5399~ 21~2065~ 22~846~ 23~4012~ 24~5127~ 25~4487~.'),
  (21852, 27, 4, 6, 'Therefore made I a decree to bring in all the wise men of Babylon before me, that they might make known unto me the interpretation of the dream.', '0~04481~ 1~07761~ 2~04481~ 4~02942~ 6~05954~ 8~03606~ 10~02445~ [11] 13~0895~ 14~06925~ 20~03046~ 24~06591~ 27~02493~.'),
  (14276, 19, 25, 16, 'Turn thee unto me, and have mercy upon me; for I am desolate and afflicted.', '0~06437~ 6~02603~ [11] 12~03173~ 14~06041~.'),
  (14389, 19, 33, 14, 'From the place of his habitation he looketh upon all the inhabitants of the earth.', '2~04349~ 5~03427~ 7~07688~ 11~03427~ 14~0776~.'),
  (1351, 1, 44, 22, 'And we said unto my lord, The lad cannot leave his father: for if he should leave his father, his father would die.', '2~0559~ 5~0113~, 7~05288~ 8~03201~ 9~05800~ 11~01~: [13] 16~05800~ 18~01~, [19 20] 22~04191~.'),
  (27601, 44, 18, 28, 'For he mightily convinced the Jews, and that publicly, shewing by the scriptures that Jesus was Christ.', '0~1063~ 2~2159~ 3~1246~ 5~2453~, [6 7] 8~1219~, 9~1925~ 10~1223~ 12~1124~ 14~2424~ 15~1511~ 16~5547~.'),
  (4269, 4, 18, 7, 'Therefore thou and thy sons with thee shall keep your priest''s office for every thing of the altar, and within the veil; and ye shall serve: I have given your priest''s office unto you as a service of gift: and the stranger that cometh nigh shall be put to death.', '4~01121~ 8~08104~ 11~03550~ 14~01697~ 17~04196~, 19~01004~ 21~06532~; 25~05647~: 28~05414~ 31~03550~ [32 33] 36~05656~ 38~04979~: 41~02114~ 44~07131~ 49~04191~.'),
  (29543, 51, 3, 10, 'And have put on the new man, which is renewed in knowledge after the image of him that created him:', '0~2532~ 3~1746~ 5~3501~ [6] 7~3588~ 9~341~ 10~1519~ 11~1922~ 12~2596~ 16~1504~ 18~2936~ 19~846~:'),
  (12616, 16, 11, 19, 'Moreover the porters, Akkub, Talmon, and their brethren that kept the gates, were an hundred seventy and two.', '2~07778~, 3~06126~, 4~02929~, 7~0251~ 9~08104~ 11~08179~, [12] 14~03967~ 15~07657~ 17~08147~.'),
  (15492, 19, 97, 5, 'The hills melted like wax at the presence of the LORD, at the presence of the Lord of the whole earth.', '1~02022~ 2~04549~ 4~01749~ 7~06440~ 10~03068~, 13~06440~ 16~0113~ 20~0776~.'),
  (12144, 15, 5, 1, 'Then the prophets, Haggai the prophet, and Zechariah the son of Iddo, prophesied unto the Jews that were in Judah and Jerusalem in the name of the God of Israel, even unto them.', '&para; 2~05029~, 3~02292~ 5~05029~, 7~02148~ 9~01247~ 11~05714~, 12~05013~ 13~05922~ 15~03062~ [17] 19~03061~ 21~03390~ 24~08036~ 27~0426~ 29~03479~, [30] 31~05922~'),
  (30469, 60, 4, 7, 'But the end of all things is at hand: be ye therefore sober, and watch unto prayer.', '&para; 0~1161~ 2~5056~ 5~3956~ 8~1448~: 10~4993~ 11~3767~ 12~4993~, 13~2532~ 14~3525~ 15~1519~ 16~4335~.'),
  (22352, 29, 2, 32, 'And it shall come to pass, that whosoever shall call on the name of the LORD shall be delivered: for in mount Zion and in Jerusalem shall be deliverance, as the LORD hath said, and in the remnant whom the LORD shall call.', '[6] 9~07121~ 12~08034~ 15~03068~ 18~04422~: 21~02022~ 22~06726~ 25~03389~ 28~06413~, 31~03068~ 33~0559~, 37~08300~ 40~03068~ 42~07121~.'),
  (18144, 23, 26, 5, 'For he bringeth down them that dwell on high; the lofty city, he layeth it low; he layeth it low, even to the ground; he bringeth it even to the dust.', '&para; 3~07817~ 6~03427~ 8~04791~; 10~07682~ 11~07151~, 15~08213~; 19~08213~, [20] 23~0776~; 25~05060~ [27] 30~06083~.'),
  (1255, 1, 41, 55, 'And when all the land of Egypt was famished, the people cried to Pharaoh for bread: and Pharaoh said unto all the Egyptians, Go unto Joseph; what he saith to you, do.', '4~0776~ 6~04714~ 8~07456~, 10~05971~ 11~06817~ 13~06547~ 15~03899~: 17~06547~ 18~0559~ 22~04714~, 23~03212~ 25~03130~; 28~0559~ 31~06213~.'),
  (1393, 1, 46, 2, 'And God spake unto Israel in the visions of the night, and said, Jacob, Jacob. And he said, Here am I.', '1~0430~ 2~0559~ 4~03478~ 7~04759~ 10~03915~, 12~0559~, 13~03290~, 14~03290~. 17~0559~, [19]'),
  (18294, 23, 33, 6, 'And wisdom and knowledge shall be the stability of thy times, and strength of salvation: the fear of the LORD is his treasure.', '1~02451~ 3~01847~ 7~0530~ 10~06256~, [11] 12~02633~ 14~03444~: 16~03374~ 19~03068~ [20] 22~0214~.'),
  (194, 1, 8, 10, 'And he stayed yet other seven days; and again he sent forth the dove out of the ark;', '2~02342~ 4~0312~ 5~07651~ 6~03117~; 8~03254~ 11~07971~ 13~03123~ 17~08392~;'),
  (22955, 38, 5, 10, 'Then said I to the angel that talked with me, Whither do these bear the ephah?', '1~0559~ 5~04397~ 7~01696~ 13~03212~ 15~0374~?'),
  (22147, 28, 4, 5, 'Therefore shalt thou fall in the day, and the prophet also shall fall with thee in the night, and I will destroy thy mother.', '3~03782~ 6~03117~, 9~05030~ 12~03782~ 17~03915~, 21~01820~ 23~0517~.'),
  (10681, 13, 10, 14, 'And inquired not of the LORD: therefore he slew him, and turned the kingdom unto David the son of Jesse.', '1~01875~ 5~03068~: 8~04191~ 11~05437~ 13~04410~ 15~01732~ 17~01121~ 19~03448~.'),
  (11301, 14, 6, 11, 'And in it have I put the ark, wherein is the covenant of the LORD, that he made with the children of Israel.', '2~08033~ 5~07760~ 7~0727~, [9] 11~01285~ 14~03068~, 17~03772~ 20~01121~ 22~03478~.'),
  (25278, 42, 8, 21, 'And he answered and said unto them, My mother and my brethren are these which hear the word of God, and do it.', '0~1161~ 2~611~ 4~2036~ 5~4314~ 6~846~, 7~3450~ 8~3384~ 9~2532~ 10~3450~ 11~80~ 12~1526~ 13~3778~ 14~3588~ 15~191~ 17~3056~ 19~2316~, 20~2532~ 21~4160~ 22~846~.'),
  (29694, 53, 2, 17, 'Comfort your hearts, and stablish you in every good word and work.', '0~3870~ 1~5216~ 2~2588~, 3~2532~ 4~4741~ 5~5209~ 6~1722~ 7~3956~ 8~18~ 9~3056~ 10~2532~ 11~2041~.'),
  (20197, 24, 50, 22, 'A sound of battle is in the land, and of great destruction.', '1~06963~ 3~04421~ [4] 7~0776~, 10~01419~ 11~07667~.'),
  (22958, 38, 6, 2, 'In the first chariot were red horses; and in the second chariot black horses;', '2~07223~ 3~04818~ [4] 5~0122~ 6~05483~; 10~08145~ 11~04818~ 12~07838~ 13~05483~;'),
  (12684, 16, 13, 4, 'And before this, Eliashib the priest, having the oversight of the chamber of the house of our God, was allied unto Tobiah:', '1~06440~ 3~0475~ 5~03548~, 8~05414~ 11~03957~ 14~01004~ 17~0430~, [18] 19~07138~ 21~02900~:'),
  (31052, 66, 19, 19, 'And I saw the beast, and the kings of the earth, and their armies, gathered together to make war against him that sat on the horse, and against his army.', '0~2532~ 2~1492~ 4~2342~, 5~2532~ 7~935~ 10~1093~, 11~2532~ 12~846~ 13~4753~, 15~4863~ 17~4160~ 18~4171~ 19~3326~ 22~2521~ 23~1909~ 25~2462~, 26~2532~ 27~3326~ 28~846~ 29~4753~.'),
  (26996, 44, 2, 31, 'He seeing this before spake of the resurrection of Christ, that his soul was not left in hell, neither his flesh did see corruption.', '3~4275~ 4~2980~ 5~4012~ 7~386~ 9~5547~, 10~3754~ 11~846~ 12~5590~ 13~2641~ 14~3756~ 15~2641~ 16~1519~ 17~86~, 18~3761~ 19~846~ 20~4561~ 22~1492~ 23~1312~.'),
  (12984, 18, 5, 24, 'And thou shalt know that thy tabernacle shall be in peace; and thou shalt visit thy habitation, and shalt not sin.', '3~03045~ 6~0168~ [7 8] 10~07965~; 14~06485~ 16~05116~, 20~02398~.'),
  (8697, 10, 23, 36, 'Igal the son of Nathan of Zobah, Bani the Gadite,', '0~03008~ 2~01121~ 4~05416~ 6~06678~, 7~01137~ 9~01425~,'),
  (10249, 12, 25, 19, 'And out of the city he took an officer that was set over the men of war, and five men of them that were in the king''s presence, which were found in the city, and the principal scribe of the host, which mustered the people of the land, and threescore men of the people of the land that were found in the city:', '4~05892~ 6~03947~ 7~0259~ 8~05631~ 11~06496~ 14~0582~ 16~04421~, 18~02568~ 19~0582~ 23~07200~ 26~04428~ 27~06440~, 30~04672~ 33~05892~, 36~08269~ 37~05608~ 40~06635~, 42~06633~ 44~05971~ 47~0776~, 49~08346~ 50~0376~ 53~05971~ 56~0776~ [57 58] 59~04672~ 62~05892~:'),
  (19338, 24, 15, 14, 'And I will make thee to pass with thine enemies into a land which thou knowest not: for a fire is kindled in mine anger, which shall burn upon you.', '[4] 6~05674~ 9~0341~ 12~0776~ [13] 15~03045~ 19~0784~ 21~06919~ 24~0639~, [25] 27~03344~'),
  (1989, 2, 17, 1, 'And all the congregation of the children of Israel journeyed from the wilderness of Sin, after their journeys, according to the commandment of the LORD, and pitched in Rephidim: and there was no water for the people to drink.', '&para; 3~05712~ 6~01121~ 8~03478~ 9~05265~ 12~04057~ 14~05512~, 17~04550~, 21~06310~ 24~03068~, 26~02583~ 28~07508~: [30 31] 33~04325~ 36~05971~ 38~08354~.');
