VALUES
  (1569, 2, 2, 10, 'And the child grew, and she brought him unto Pharaoh''s daughter, and he became her son. And she called his name Moses: and she said, Because I drew him out of the water.', '2~03206~ 3~01431~, 6~0935~ 9~06547~ 10~01323~, 15~01121~. 18~07121~ 20~08034~ 21~04872~: 24~0559~, 27~04871~ 32~04325~.'),
  (26162, 43, 3, 27, 'John answered and said, A man can receive nothing, except it be given him from heaven.', '0~2491~ 1~611~ 2~2532~ 3~2036~, 5~444~ 6~1410~ 7~3756~* 8~2983~ 9~3762~, 10~3362~ 12~5600~ 13~1325~ 14~846~ 15~1537~ 16~3772~.'),
  (11895, 14, 32, 11, 'Doth not Hezekiah persuade you to give over yourselves to die by famine and by thirst, saying, The LORD our God shall deliver us out of the hand of the king of Assyria?', '2~03169~ 3~05496~ 6~05414~ 10~04191~ 12~07458~ 15~06772~, 16~0559~, 18~03068~ 20~0430~ 22~05337~ 27~03709~ 30~04428~ 32~0804~?'),
  (16575, 20, 6, 26, 'For by means of a whorish woman a man is brought to a piece of bread: and the adulteress will hunt for the precious life.', '3~01157~ 5~02181~ 6~0802~ [7 10] 13~03603~ 15~03899~: 18~0376~ 19~0802~ 20~06679~ 23~03368~ 24~05315~.'),
  (29907, 55, 4, 21, 'Do thy diligence to come before winter. Eubulus greeteth thee, and Pudens, and Linus, and Claudia, and all the brethren.', '2~4704~ 4~2064~ 5~4253~ 6~5494~. 7~2103~ 8~782~ 9~4571~, 10~2532~ 11~4227~, 12~2532~ 13~3044~, 14~2532~ 15~2803~, 16~2532~ 17~3956~ 19~80~.'),
  (7389, 9, 8, 13, 'And he will take your daughters to be confectionaries, and to be cooks, and to be bakers.', '3~03947~ 5~01323~ [6 7] 8~07548~, [10 11] 12~02879~, [14 15] 16~0644~.'),
  (12423, 16, 6, 13, 'Therefore was he hired, that I should be afraid, and do so, and sin, and that they might have matter for an evil report, that they might reproach me.', '[1] 3~07936~, 8~03372~, 11~06213~, 13~02398~, [15] [19] 22~07451~ 23~08034~, 27~02778~'),
  (7887, 9, 25, 19, 'And she said unto her servants, Go on before me; behold, I come after you. But she told not her husband Nabal.', '2~0559~ 5~05288~, 7~05674~ 8~06440~ 12~0935~ 13~0310~ 17~05046~ 20~0376~ 21~05037~.'),
  (8552, 10, 19, 33, 'And the king said unto Barzillai, Come thou over with me, and I will feed thee with me in Jerusalem.', '2~04428~ 3~0559~ 5~01271~, 8~05674~ 14~03557~ 19~03389~.'),
  (738, 1, 27, 7, 'Bring me venison, and make me savoury meat, that I may eat, and bless thee before the LORD before my death.', '0~0935~ 2~06718~, 4~06213~ 7~04303~, 11~0398~, 13~01288~ 15~06440~ 17~03068~ 18~06440~ 20~04194~.'),
  (14229, 19, 22, 16, 'For dogs have compassed me: the assembly of the wicked have enclosed me: they pierced my hands and my feet.', '1~03611~ 3~05437~ 6~05712~ 9~07489~ 11~05362~ 14~03738~ 16~03027~ 19~07272~.'),
  (2890, 3, 7, 6, 'Every male among the priests shall eat thereof: it shall be eaten in the holy place: it is most holy.', '1~02145~ 4~03548~ 6~0398~ 11~0398~ 14~06918~ 15~04725~: [17] 18~06944~ 19~06944~.'),
  (11371, 14, 8, 17, 'Then went Solomon to Eziongeber, and to Eloth, at the sea side in the land of Edom.', '1~01980~ 2~08010~ 4~06100~, 7~0359~, 10~03220~ 11~08193~ 14~0776~ 16~0123~.'),
  (13995, 19, 6, 1, 'To the chief Musician on Neginoth upon Sheminith, A Psalm of David. O LORD, rebuke me not in thine anger, neither chasten me in thy hot displeasure.', '&para; [0 3~05329~ 5~05058~ 7~08067~, 9~04210~ 11] 11~01732~ 13~03068~, 14~03198~ 19~0639~, 21~03256~ 26~02534~.'),
  (8628, 10, 22, 18, 'He delivered me from my strong enemy, and from them that hated me: for they were too strong for me.', '1~05337~ 5~05794~ 6~0341~, [7] 11~08130~ 17~0553~'),
  (191, 1, 8, 7, 'And he sent forth a raven, which went forth to and fro, until the waters were dried up from off the earth.', '3~07971~ 5~06158~, 8~03318~ 9~03318~ 11~07725~, 14~04325~ 17~03001~ 21~0776~.'),
  (30273, 58, 13, 16, 'But to do good and to communicate forget not: for with such sacrifices God is well pleased.', '0~1161~ 3~2140~ 4~2532~ 6~2842~ 7~1950~ 8~3361~: 9~1063~ 11~5108~ 12~2378~ 13~2316~ 16~2100~.'),
  (21101, 26, 25, 9, 'Therefore, behold, I will open the side of Moab from the cities, from his cities which are on his frontiers, the glory of the country, Bethjeshimoth, Baalmeon, and Kiriathaim,', '4~06605~ 6~03802~ 8~04124~ 11~05892~, 14~05892~ [15 16] 19~07097~, 21~06643~ 24~0776~, 25~01020~, 26~01186~, 28~07156~,'),
  (14931, 19, 68, 22, 'The Lord said, I will bring again from Bashan, I will bring my people again from the depths of the sea:', '&para; 1~0136~ 2~0559~, 6~07725~ 8~01316~, [12 13] 14~07725~ 17~04688~ 20~03220~:'),
  (29545, 51, 3, 12, 'Put on therefore, as the elect of God, holy and beloved, bowels of mercies, kindness, humbleness of mind, meekness, longsuffering;', '&para; 1~1746~ 2~3767~, 3~5613~ 5~1588~ 7~2316~, 8~40~ 9~2532~ 10~25~, 11~4698~ 13~3628~, 14~5544~, 17~5012~, 18~4236~, 19~3115~;'),
  (6044, 6, 9, 1, 'And it came to pass, when all the kings which were on this side Jordan, in the hills, and in the valleys, and in all the coasts of the great sea over against Lebanon, the Hittite, and the Amorite, the Canaanite, the Perizzite, the Hivite, and the Jebusite, heard thereof;', '&para; 8~04428~ [10] 13~05676~ 14~03383~, 17~02022~, 21~08219~, 26~02348~ 29~01419~ 30~03220~ 32~04136~ 33~03844~, 35~02850~, 38~0567~, 40~03669~, 42~06522~, 44~02340~, 47~02983~, 48~08085~ [49]'),
  (29499, 51, 1, 18, 'And he is the head of the body, the church: who is the beginning, the firstborn from the dead; that in all things he might have the preeminence.', '0~2532~ 1~846~ 2~2076~ 4~2776~ 7~4983~, 9~1577~: 10~3739~ 11~2076~ 13~746~, 15~4416~ 16~1537~ 18~3498~; 19~2443~ 20~1722~ 21~3956~ [22] 23~846~ 25~1096~ 27~4409~.'),
  (14796, 19, 58, 8, 'As a snail which melteth, let every one of them pass away: like the untimely birth of a woman, that they may not see the sun.', '2~07642~ [3] 4~08557~, [6 9] 11~01980~: [12] 15~05309~ 18~0802~, [19] 23~02372~ 25~08121~.'),
  (162, 1, 7, 2, 'Of every clean beast thou shalt take to thee by sevens, the male and his female: and of beasts that are not clean by two, the male and his female.', '2~02889~ 3~0929~ 6~03947~ 10~07651~ 11~07651~,* 13~0376~ 16~0802~: 19~0929~ [21] 23~01931~ 24~02889~ 25~08147~, 27~0376~ 30~0802~.'),
  (1010, 1, 34, 25, 'And it came to pass on the third day, when they were sore, that two of the sons of Jacob, Simeon and Levi, Dinah''s brethren, took each man his sword, and came upon the city boldly, and slew all the males.', '&para; 7~07992~ 8~03117~, 12~03510~, 14~08147~ 17~01121~ 19~03290~, 20~08095~ 22~03878~, 23~01783~ 24~0251~, 25~03947~ 27~0376~ 29~02719~, 31~0935~ 34~05892~ 35~0983~, 37~02026~ 40~02145~.'),
  (11359, 14, 8, 5, 'Also he built Bethhoron the upper, and Bethhoron the nether, fenced cities, with walls, gates, and bars;', '2~01129~ 3~01032~ 5~05945~, 7~01032~ 9~08481~, 10~04692~ 11~05892~, 13~02346~, 14~01817~, 16~01280~;'),
  (26661, 43, 13, 16, 'Verily, verily, I say unto you, The servant is not greater than his lord; neither he that is sent greater than he that sent him.', '0~281~, 1~281~, 3~3004~ 5~5213~, 7~1401~ 8~2076~ 9~3756~ 11~3187~ 12~846~ 13~2962~; 14~3761~ 18~652~ 20~3187~ 23~3992~ 24~846~.'),
  (20514, 26, 3, 3, 'And he said unto me, Son of man, cause thy belly to eat, and fill thy bowels with this roll that I give thee. Then did I eat it; and it was in my mouth as honey for sweetness.', '2~0559~ 5~01121~ 7~0120~, 10~0990~ 12~0398~, 14~04390~ 16~04578~ 19~04039~ 22~05414~ 27~0398~ [28] 34~06310~ 36~01706~ 38~04966~.'),
  (4839, 4, 34, 17, 'These are the names of the men which shall divide the land unto you: Eleazar the priest, and Joshua the son of Nun.', '[1] 3~08034~ 6~0582~ 9~05157~ 11~0776~ 14~0499~ 16~03548~, 18~03091~ 20~01121~ 22~05126~.'),
  (19673, 24, 29, 29, 'And Zephaniah the priest read this letter in the ears of Jeremiah the prophet.', '1~06846~ 3~03548~ 4~07121~ 6~05612~ 9~0241~ 11~03414~ 13~05030~.'),
  (20142, 24, 49, 6, 'And afterward I will bring again the captivity of the children of Ammon, saith the LORD.', '1~0310~ 5~07725~ 7~07622~ 10~01121~ 12~05983~, 13~05002~ 15~03068~.'),
  (18666, 23, 49, 21, 'Then shalt thou say in thine heart, Who hath begotten me these, seeing I have lost my children, and am desolate, a captive, and removing to and fro? and who hath brought up these? Behold, I was left alone; these, where had they been?', '3~0559~ 6~03824~, 9~03205~ 17~07921~, 20~01565~, 22~01540~, 27~05493~? 32~01431~ 37~07604~ 40~0375~ [41] [43]'),
  (2293, 2, 27, 16, 'And for the gate of the court shall be an hanging of twenty cubits, of blue, and purple, and scarlet, and fine twined linen, wrought with needlework: and their pillars shall be four, and their sockets four.', '3~08179~ 6~02691~ [7 8] 10~04539~ 12~06242~ 13~0520~, [14] 15~08504~, 17~0713~, 19~08438~ 20~08144~,* 23~07806~ 24~08336~, 27~07551~ 28~04639~:* [29] 31~05982~ [32 33] 34~0702~, 37~0134~ 38~0702~.'),
  (24863, 41, 15, 26, 'And the superscription of his accusation was written over, THE KING OF THE JEWS.', '0~2532~ 2~1923~ 4~846~ 5~156~ 6~2258~ 8~1924~, 10~935~ 13~2453~.'),
  (29287, 49, 3, 20, 'Now unto him that is able to do exceeding abundantly above all that we ask or think, according to the power that worketh in us,', '0~1161~ 5~1410~ 7~4160~ 8~5228~ 9~4053~ 10~1537~* 11~5228~ 12~3956~ 13~3739~ 15~154~ 16~2228~ 17~3539~, 19~2596~ 21~1411~ 23~1754~ 24~1722~ 25~2254~,'),
  (17590, 22, 3, 10, 'He made the pillars thereof of silver, the bottom thereof of gold, the covering of it of purple, the midst thereof being paved with love, for the daughters of Jerusalem.', '1~06213~ 3~05982~ [5] 6~03701~, 8~07507~ [10] 11~02091~, 13~04817~ [16] 17~0713~, 19~08432~ 22~07528~ [23] 24~0160~, 27~01323~ 29~03389~.'),
  (8965, 11, 7, 23, 'And he made a molten sea, ten cubits from the one brim to the other: it was round all about, and his height was five cubits: and a line of thirty cubits did compass it round about.', '2~06213~ 4~03332~ 5~03220~, 6~06235~ 7~0520~ 11~08193~ 14~08193~: [15 16] 17~05696~ 19~05439~, 22~06967~ [23] 24~02568~ 25~0520~: 28~06957~ 29~06961~* 31~07970~ 32~0520~ 34~05437~ 37~05439~.'),
  (26856, 43, 19, 16, 'Then delivered he him therefore unto them to be crucified. And they took Jesus, and led him away.', '&para; 0~5119~ 2~3860~ 3~846~ 4~3767~ 6~846~ 7~2443~ 9~4717~. 10~1161~ 12~3880~ 13~2424~, 14~2532~ [16] 17~520~.'),
  (15132, 19, 78, 10, 'They kept not the covenant of God, and refused to walk in his law;', '1~08104~ 4~01285~ 6~0430~, 8~03985~ 10~03212~ 13~08451~;'),
  (5140, 5, 7, 23, 'But the LORD thy God shall deliver them unto thee, and shall destroy them with a mighty destruction, until they be destroyed.', '2~03068~ 4~0430~ 6~05414~ 9~06440~, 12~01949~ 16~01419~ 17~04103~, 21~08045~.'),
  (21464, 26, 39, 7, 'So will I make my holy name known in the midst of my people Israel; and I will not let them pollute my holy name any more: and the heathen shall know that I am the LORD, the Holy One in Israel.', '5~06944~ 6~08034~ 7~03045~ 10~08432~ 13~05971~ 14~03478~; [19 20] 21~02490~ 23~06944~ 24~08034~ 29~01471~ 31~03045~ [34] 36~03068~, 39~06918~ 41~03478~.'),
  (9461, 11, 21, 2, 'And Ahab spake unto Naboth, saying, Give me thy vineyard, that I may have it for a garden of herbs, because it is near unto my house: and I will give thee for it a better vineyard than it; or, if it seem good to thee, I will give thee the worth of it in money.', '1~0256~ 2~01696~ 4~05022~, 5~0559~, 6~05414~ 9~03754~, 17~01588~ 19~03419~, [22] 23~07138~ 24~0681~ 26~01004~: 30~05414~ 35~02896~ 36~03754~ [39] 43~02896~ 45~05869~, 48~05414~ 51~04242~ 55~03701~.'),
  (16266, 19, 139, 18, 'If I should count them, they are more in number than the sand: when I awake, I am still with thee.', '[0] 3~05608~ 9~07235~ 12~02344~: 15~06974~, 18~05750~'),
  (10253, 12, 25, 23, 'And when all the captains of the armies, they and their men, heard that the king of Babylon had made Gedaliah governor, there came to Gedaliah to Mizpah, even Ishmael the son of Nethaniah, and Johanan the son of Careah, and Seraiah the son of Tanhumeth the Netophathite, and Jaazaniah the son of a Maachathite, they and their men.', '4~08269~ 7~02428~, 11~0582~, 12~08085~ 15~04428~ 17~0894~ 20~01436~ 21~06485~, 23~0935~ 25~01436~ 27~04709~, 29~03458~ 31~01121~ 33~05418~, 35~03110~ 37~01121~ 39~07143~, 41~08304~ 43~01121~ 45~08576~ 47~05200~, 49~02970~ 51~01121~ 54~04602~, 58~0582~.'),
  (6054, 6, 9, 11, 'Wherefore our elders and all the inhabitants of our country spake to us, saying, Take victuals with you for the journey, and go to meet them, and say unto them, We are your servants: therefore now make ye a league with us.', '2~02205~ 6~03427~ 9~0776~ 10~0559~ 13~0559~, 14~03947~ 15~06720~ 17~03027~ 20~01870~, 22~03212~ 24~07125~ 27~0559~ [31] 33~05650~: 36~03772~ 39~01285~'),
  (14124, 19, 17, 12, 'Like as a lion that is greedy of his prey, and as it were a young lion lurking in secret places.', '0~01825~ 3~0738~ [4] 6~03700~ 9~02963~, 16~03715~ 17~03427~ 20~04565~.'),
  (16459, 20, 2, 17, 'Which forsaketh the guide of her youth, and forgetteth the covenant of her God.', '1~05800~ 3~0441~ 6~05271~, 8~07911~ 10~01285~ 13~0430~.'),
  (60, 1, 3, 4, 'And the serpent said unto the woman, Ye shall not surely die:', '2~05175~ 3~0559~ 6~0802~, 10~04191~ 11~04191~:'),
  (5345, 5, 15, 20, 'Thou shalt eat it before the LORD thy God year by year in the place which the LORD shall choose, thou and thy household.', '2~0398~ [3] 4~06440~ 6~03068~ 8~0430~ 9~08141~ 11~08141~ 14~04725~ 17~03068~ 19~0977~, 23~01004~.'),
  (9921, 12, 14, 17, 'And Amaziah the son of Joash king of Judah lived after the death of Jehoash son of Jehoahaz king of Israel fifteen years.', '1~0558~ 3~01121~ 5~03101~ 6~04428~ 8~03063~ 9~02421~ 10~0310~ 12~04194~ 14~03060~ 15~01121~ 17~03059~ 18~04428~ 20~03478~ 21~06240~ 22~02568~* 23~08141~.'),
  (19816, 24, 34, 6, 'Then Jeremiah the prophet spake all these words unto Zedekiah king of Judah in Jerusalem,', '1~03414~ 3~05030~ 4~01696~ 7~01697~ 9~06667~ 10~04428~ 12~03063~ 14~03389~,'),
  (27142, 44, 7, 10, 'And delivered him out of all his afflictions, and gave him favour and wisdom in the sight of Pharaoh king of Egypt; and he made him governor over Egypt and all his house.', '0~2532~ 1~1807~ 2~846~ 4~1537~ 5~3956~ 6~846~ 7~2347~, 8~2532~ 9~1325~ 10~846~ 11~5485~ 12~2532~ 13~4678~ 16~1726~ 18~5328~ 19~935~ 21~125~; 22~2532~ 24~2525~ 25~846~ 26~2233~ 27~1909~ 28~125~ 29~2532~ 30~3650~ 31~846~ 32~3624~.'),
  (17931, 23, 13, 16, 'Their children also shall be dashed to pieces before their eyes; their houses shall be spoiled, and their wives ravished.', '1~05768~ 7~07376~ 10~05869~; 12~01004~ 15~08155~, 18~0802~ 19~07901~'),
  (11882, 14, 31, 19, 'Also of the sons of Aaron the priests, which were in the fields of the suburbs of their cities, in every several city, the men that were expressed by name, to give portions to all the males among the priests, and to all that were reckoned by genealogies among the Levites.', '3~01121~ 5~0175~ 7~03548~, [8 9] 12~07704~ 15~04054~ 18~05892~, 22~05892~, 24~0582~ 27~05344~ 29~08034~, 31~05414~ 32~04490~ 36~02145~ 39~03548~, 47~03187~ 50~03881~.'),
  (26780, 43, 17, 6, 'I have manifested thy name unto the men which thou gavest me out of the world: thine they were, and thou gavest them me; and they have kept thy word.', '&para; 2~5319~ 3~4675~ 4~3686~ 7~444~ 8~3739~ 10~1325~ 11~3427~ 13~1537~ 15~2889~: 16~4674~ 18~2258~, 19~2532~ 21~1325~ 22~846~ 23~1698~; 24~2532~ 27~5083~ 28~4675~ 29~3056~.'),
  (20878, 26, 18, 20, 'The soul that sinneth, it shall die. The son shall not bear the iniquity of the father, neither shall the father bear the iniquity of the son: the righteousness of the righteous shall be upon him, and the wickedness of the wicked shall be upon him.', '1~05315~ 3~02398~, 6~04191~. 8~01121~ 11~05375~ 13~05771~ 16~01~, 20~01~ 21~05375~ 23~05771~ 26~01121~: 28~06666~ 31~06662~ 38~07564~ 41~07563~'),
  (25809, 42, 20, 16, 'He shall come and destroy these husbandmen, and shall give the vineyard to others. And when they heard it, they said, God forbid.', '2~2064~ 3~2532~ 4~622~ 5~5128~ 6~1092~, 7~2532~ 9~1325~ 11~290~ 13~243~. 14~1161~ 17~191~ [18] 20~2036~, 22~1096~ 23~3361~.*'),
  (5572, 5, 25, 19, 'Therefore it shall be, when the LORD thy God hath given thee rest from all thine enemies round about, in the land which the LORD thy God giveth thee for an inheritance to possess it, that thou shalt blot out the remembrance of Amalek from under heaven; thou shalt not forget it.', '6~03068~ 8~0430~ 12~05117~ 16~0341~ 18~05439~, 21~0776~ 24~03068~ 26~0430~ 27~05414~ [29] 31~05159~ 33~03423~ [35] 39~04229~ 41~02143~ 43~06002~ 46~08064~; 50~07911~ [51]'),
  (7467, 9, 11, 15, 'And all the people went to Gilgal; and there they made Saul king before the LORD in Gilgal; and there they sacrificed sacrifices of peace offerings before the LORD; and there Saul and all the men of Israel rejoiced greatly.', '3~05971~ 4~03212~ 6~01537~; 11~07586~ 12~04427~ 13~06440~ 15~03068~ 17~01537~; 21~02076~ 22~02077~ 25~08002~ 26~06440~ 28~03068~; 31~07586~ 35~0582~ 37~03478~ 38~08055~ 39~03966~.'),
  (17783, 23, 6, 5, 'Then said I, Woe is me! for I am undone; because I am a man of unclean lips, and I dwell in the midst of a people of unclean lips: for mine eyes have seen the King, the LORD of hosts.', '&para; 1~0559~ 3~0188~ [4] 9~01820~; [12] 14~0376~ 16~02931~ 17~08193~, 20~03427~ 23~08432~ 26~05971~ 28~02931~ 29~08193~: 32~05869~ 34~07200~ 36~04428~, 38~03068~ 40~06635~.'),
  (30694, 65, 1, 6, 'And the angels which kept not their first estate, but left their own habitation, he hath reserved in everlasting chains under darkness unto the judgment of the great day.', '0~5037~ 2~32~ 4~5083~ 5~3361~ 6~1438~ 8~746~, 9~235~ 10~620~ 12~2398~ 13~3613~, 16~5083~ 18~126~ 19~1199~ 20~5259~ 21~2217~ 22~1519~ 24~2920~ 27~3173~ 28~2250~.'),
  (15511, 19, 99, 3, 'Let them praise thy great and terrible name; for it is holy.', '2~03034~ 4~01419~ 6~03372~ 7~08034~; [8] [10] 11~06918~.'),
  (24592, 41, 9, 43, 'And if thy hand offend thee, cut it off: it is better for thee to enter into life maimed, than having two hands to go into hell, into the fire that never shall be quenched:', '0~2532~ 1~1437~ 2~4675~ 3~5495~ 4~4624~ 5~4571~, 6~609~ 7~846~ 8~609~: 10~2076~ 11~2570~ 13~4671~ 15~1525~ 16~1519~ 17~2222~ 18~2948~, 19~2228~ 20~2192~ 21~1417~ 22~5495~ 24~565~ 25~1519~ 26~1067~, 27~1519~ 29~4442~ 34~762~:'),
  (21473, 26, 39, 16, 'And also the name of the city shall be Hamonah. Thus shall they cleanse the land.', '3~08034~ 6~05892~ [7 8] 9~01997~. 13~02891~ 15~0776~.'),
  (2159, 2, 23, 10, 'And six years thou shalt sow thy land, and shalt gather in the fruits thereof:', '&para; 1~08337~ 2~08141~ 5~02232~ 7~0776~, 10~0622~ 13~08393~'),
  (9646, 12, 4, 35, 'Then he returned, and walked in the house to and fro; and went up, and stretched himself upon him: and the child sneezed seven times, and the child opened his eyes.', '2~07725~, 4~03212~ 7~01004~ 8~02008~ 9~0259~ 10~02008~ 11~0259~;* 14~05927~, 16~01457~ 22~05288~ 23~02237~ 24~07651~ 25~06471~, 28~05288~ 29~06491~ 31~05869~.'),
  (24932, 42, 1, 28, 'And the angel came in unto her, and said, Hail, thou that art highly favoured, the Lord is with thee: blessed art thou among women.', '0~2532~ 2~32~ 4~1525~ 5~4314~ 6~846~, 8~2036~, 9~5463~, [10 12] 14~5487~, 16~2962~ [17] 18~3326~ 19~4675~: 20~2127~ [21] 22~4771~ 23~1722~ 24~1135~.'),
  (14895, 19, 66, 13, 'I will go into thy house with burnt offerings: I will pay thee my vows,', '&para; 2~0935~ 5~01004~ 8~05930~: 11~07999~ 14~05088~,'),
  (15062, 19, 74, 5, 'A man was famous according as he had lifted up axes upon the thick trees.', '[0 1] 3~03045~ 9~0935~ 10~04605~* 11~07134~ 14~05442~ 15~06086~.'),
  (4597, 4, 28, 14, 'And their drink offerings shall be half an hin of wine unto a bullock, and the third part of an hin unto a ram, and a fourth part of an hin unto a lamb: this is the burnt offering of every month throughout the months of the year.', '3~05262~ 6~02677~ 8~01969~ 10~03196~ 13~06499~, 16~07992~ [17] 20~01969~ 23~0352~, 26~07243~ [27] 30~01969~ 33~03532~: [35] 38~05930~ 41~02320~ 44~02320~ 47~08141~.'),
  (10528, 13, 6, 66, 'And the residue of the families of the sons of Kohath had cities of their coasts out of the tribe of Ephraim.', '[1 2] 5~04940~ 8~01121~ 10~06955~ 12~05892~ 15~01366~ 19~04294~ 21~0669~.'),
  (30044, 58, 4, 14, 'Seeing then that we have a great high priest, that is passed into the heavens, Jesus the Son of God, let us hold fast our profession.', '0~2192~ 1~3767~ 4~2192~ 6~3173~ 8~749~, 12~1330~ 14~3772~, 15~2424~ 17~5207~ 19~2316~, 23~2902~ [24] 25~3671~.'),
  (17939, 23, 14, 2, 'And the people shall take them, and bring them to their place: and the house of Israel shall possess them in the land of the LORD for servants and handmaids: and they shall take them captives, whose captives they were; and they shall rule over their oppressors.', '2~05971~ 4~03947~ 7~0935~ 11~04725~: 14~01004~ 16~03478~ 18~05157~ 22~0127~ 25~03068~ 27~05650~ 29~08198~: 35~07617~, 37~07617~ 43~07287~ 46~05065~.'),
  (22387, 30, 1, 14, 'But I will kindle a fire in the wall of Rabbah, and it shall devour the palaces thereof, with shouting in the day of battle, with a tempest in the day of the whirlwind:', '3~03341~ 5~0784~ 8~02346~ 10~07237~, 14~0398~ 16~0759~ 19~08643~ 22~03117~ 24~04421~, 27~05591~ 30~03117~ 33~05492~:'),
  (10813, 13, 15, 14, 'So the priests and the Levites sanctified themselves to bring up the ark of the LORD God of Israel.', '2~03548~ 5~03881~ 6~06942~ 10~05927~ 12~0727~ 15~03068~ 16~0430~ 18~03478~.'),
  (11918, 14, 33, 1, 'Manasseh was twelve years old when he began to reign, and he reigned fifty and five years in Jerusalem:', '&para; 0~04519~ [1] 2~06240~ 3~08147~* 4~08141~ 5~01121~ 10~04427~, 13~04427~ 14~02572~ 16~02568~ 17~08141~ 19~03389~:'),
  (13176, 18, 13, 14, 'Wherefore do I take my flesh in my teeth, and put my life in mine hand?', '3~05375~ 5~01320~ 8~08127~, 10~07760~ 12~05315~ 15~03709~?'),
  (21997, 27, 8, 27, 'And I Daniel fainted, and was sick certain days; afterward I rose up, and did the king''s business; and I was astonished at the vision, but none understood it.', '2~01840~ 3~01961~, 6~02470~ [7] 8~03117~; 12~06965~, 14~06213~ 16~04428~ 17~04399~; 21~08074~ 24~04758~, 27~0995~ [28]'),
  (26018, 42, 24, 13, 'And, behold, two of them went that same day to a village called Emmaus, which was from Jerusalem about threescore furlongs.', '&para; 0~2532~, 1~2400~, 2~1417~ 3~1537~ 4~846~ 5~2258~ 6~4198~* 7~1722~ 8~846~ 9~2250~ 10~1519~ 12~2968~ 13~3686~ 14~3739~* 15~1695~, 17~568~ 18~575~ 19~2419~ [20] 21~1835~ 22~4712~.'),
  (254, 1, 10, 19, 'And the border of the Canaanites was from Sidon, as thou comest to Gerar, unto Gaza; as thou goest, unto Sodom, and Gomorrah, and Admah, and Zeboim, even unto Lasha.', '2~01366~ 5~03669~ 8~06721~, 11~0935~ 13~01642~, 15~05804~; 18~0935~, 20~05467~, 22~06017~, 24~0126~, 26~06636~, 29~03962~.'),
  (7687, 9, 18, 4, 'And Jonathan stripped himself of the robe that was upon him, and gave it to David, and his garments, even to his sword, and to his bow, and to his girdle.', '1~03083~ 2~06584~ 6~04598~ [8] 12~05414~ 15~01732~, 18~04055~, 22~02719~, 26~07198~, 30~02289~.'),
  (1353, 1, 44, 24, 'And it came to pass when we came up unto thy servant my father, we told him the words of my lord.', '8~05927~ 11~05650~ 13~01~, 15~05046~ 18~01697~ 21~0113~.'),
  (21189, 26, 28, 23, 'For I will send into her pestilence, and blood into her streets; and the wounded shall be judged in the midst of her by the sword upon her on every side; and they shall know that I am the LORD.', '3~07971~ 6~01698~, 8~01818~ 11~02351~; 14~02491~ 17~05307~ 20~08432~ 25~02719~ 30~05439~; 34~03045~ [37] 39~03068~.'),
  (12797, 17, 5, 9, 'Then went Haman forth that day joyful and with a glad heart: but when Haman saw Mordecai in the king''s gate, that he stood not up, nor moved for him, he was full of indignation against Mordecai.', '&para; 1~03318~ 2~02001~ 3~03318~ 5~03117~ 6~08056~ 10~02896~ 11~03820~: 14~02001~ 15~07200~ 16~04782~ 19~04428~ 20~08179~, 25~06965~, 27~02111~ 30~02001~ 32~04390~ 34~02534~ 36~04782~.'),
  (5186, 5, 9, 23, 'Likewise when the LORD sent you from Kadeshbarnea, saying, Go up and possess the land which I have given you; then ye rebelled against the commandment of the LORD your God, and ye believed him not, nor hearkened to his voice.', '3~03068~ 4~07971~ 7~06947~, 8~0559~, 10~05927~ 12~03423~ 14~0776~ 18~05414~ 22~04784~ 25~06310~ 28~03068~ 30~0430~, 33~0539~ 37~08085~ 40~06963~.'),
  (13150, 18, 12, 13, 'With him is wisdom and strength, he hath counsel and understanding.', '[2] 3~02451~ 5~01369~, 8~06098~ 10~08394~.'),
  (932, 1, 31, 55, 'And early in the morning Laban rose up, and kissed his sons and his daughters, and blessed them: and Laban departed, and returned unto his place.', '1~07925~ 4~01242~ 5~03837~ 7~07925~, 9~05401~ 11~01121~ 14~01323~, 16~01288~ 19~03837~ 20~03212~, 22~07725~ 25~04725~.'),
  (7820, 9, 23, 3, 'And David''s men said unto him, Behold, we be afraid here in Judah: how much more then if we come to Keilah against the armies of the Philistines?', '1~01732~ 2~0582~ 3~0559~ 9~03373~ 12~03063~: 19~03212~ 21~07084~ 24~04634~ 27~06430~?'),
  (5440, 5, 20, 7, 'And what man is there that hath betrothed a wife, and hath not taken her? let him go and return unto his house, lest he die in the battle, and another man take her.', '2~0376~ [3 4] 7~0781~ 9~0802~, 13~03947~ 17~03212~ 19~07725~ 22~01004~, 25~04191~ 28~04421~, 30~0312~ 31~0376~ 32~03947~'),
  (30733, 66, 1, 20, 'The mystery of the seven stars which thou sawest in my right hand, and the seven golden candlesticks. The seven stars are the angels of the seven churches: and the seven candlesticks which thou sawest are the seven churches.', '1~3466~ 4~2033~ 5~792~ 6~3739~ 8~1492~ 9~1909~ 10~3450~ 12~1188~, 13~2532~ 15~2033~ 16~5552~ 17~3087~. 19~2033~ 20~792~ 21~1526~ 23~32~ 26~2033~ 27~1577~: 28~2532~ 30~2033~ 31~3087~ 32~3739~ 34~1492~ 35~1526~ 37~2033~ 38~1577~.'),
  (21741, 26, 48, 30, 'And these are the goings out of the city on the north side, four thousand and five hundred measures.', '[2] 5~08444~ 8~05892~ 11~06828~ 12~06285~, 13~0702~ 14~0505~ 16~02568~ 17~03967~ 18~04060~.'),
  (15070, 19, 74, 13, 'Thou didst divide the sea by thy strength: thou brakest the heads of the dragons in the waters.', '2~06565~ 4~03220~ 7~05797~: 9~07665~ 11~07218~ 14~08577~ 17~04325~.'),
  (26794, 43, 17, 20, 'Neither pray I for these alone, but for them also which shall believe on me through their word;', '&para; 0~3756~ 1~1161~ 2~2065~ 3~4012~ 4~5130~ 5~3440~, 6~235~ 7~4012~ 9~2532~ 12~4100~ 13~1519~ 14~1691~ 15~1223~ 16~846~ 17~3056~;'),
  (15853, 19, 115, 14, 'The LORD shall increase you more and more, you and your children.', '1~03068~ 3~03254~ 11~01121~.'),
  (26059, 43, 1, 1, 'In the beginning was the Word, and the Word was with God, and the Word was God.', '&para; 0~1722~ 2~746~ 3~2258~ 5~3056~, 6~2532~ 8~3056~ 9~2258~ 10~4314~ 11~2316~, 12~2532~ 14~3056~ 15~2258~ 16~2316~.'),
  (10683, 13, 11, 2, 'And moreover in time past, even when Saul was king, thou wast he that leddest out and broughtest in Israel: and the LORD thy God said unto thee, Thou shalt feed my people Israel, and thou shalt be ruler over my people Israel.', '3~08543~ 4~08032~, 7~07586~ 9~04428~, [11] 15~03318~ 18~0935~ 19~03478~: 22~03068~ 24~0430~ 25~0559~ 30~07462~ 32~05971~ 33~03478~, 38~05057~ 41~01571~ 42~03478~.'),
  (3304, 3, 19, 18, 'Thou shalt not avenge, nor bear any grudge against the children of thy people, but thou shalt love thy neighbour as thyself: I am the LORD.', '3~05358~, 7~05201~ 10~01121~ 13~05971~, 17~0157~ 19~07453~ 21~03644~: [23] 25~03068~.'),
  (17618, 22, 5, 11, 'His head is as the most fine gold, his locks are bushy, and black as a raven.', '1~07218~ [2 3] 5~03800~ 7~06337~, 9~06977~ [10] 11~08534~, [12] 13~07838~ 16~06158~.'),
  (30560, 62, 1, 4, 'And these things write we unto you, that your joy may be full.', '0~2532~ 2~5023~ 4~1125~ 6~5213~, 7~2443~ 8~5216~ 9~5479~ 11~5600~ 12~4137~.'),
  (1521, 1, 50, 10, 'And they came to the threshingfloor of Atad, which is beyond Jordan, and there they mourned with a great and very sore lamentation: and he made a mourning for his father seven days.', '2~0935~ 5~01637~ 7~0329~, [9] 10~05676~ 11~03383~, 15~05594~ 18~01419~ 20~03966~ 21~03515~ 22~04553~: 25~06213~ 27~060~ 30~01~ 31~07651~ 32~03117~.');
