VALUES
  (30910, 66, 12, 3, 'And there appeared another wonder in heaven; and behold a great red dragon, having seven heads and ten horns, and seven crowns upon his heads.', '0~2532~ 2~3700~ 3~243~ 4~4592~ 5~1722~ 6~3772~; 7~2532~ 8~2400~ 10~3173~ 11~4450~ 12~1404~, 13~2192~ 14~2033~ 15~2776~ 16~2532~ 17~1176~ 18~2768~, 19~2532~ 20~2033~ 21~1238~ 22~1909~ 23~846~ 24~2776~.'),
  (15338, 19, 89, 3, 'I have made a covenant with my chosen, I have sworn unto David my servant,', '2~03772~ 4~01285~ 7~0972~, 10~07650~ 12~01732~ 14~05650~,'),
  (7893, 9, 25, 25, 'Let not my lord, I pray thee, regard this man of Belial, even Nabal: for as his name is, so is he; Nabal is his name, and folly is with him: but I thine handmaid saw not the young men of my lord, whom thou didst send.', '0~07760~ 3~0113~, 7~03820~ 9~0376~ 11~01100~, [12] 13~05037~: 17~08034~ [18] [20] 22~05037~ [23] 25~08034~, 27~05039~ [28] 34~0519~ 35~07200~ 39~05288~ 42~0113~, 46~07971~.'),
  (13069, 18, 9, 9, 'Which maketh Arcturus, Orion, and Pleiades, and the chambers of the south.', '1~06213~ 2~05906~, 3~03685~, 5~03598~, 8~02315~ 11~08486~.'),
  (236, 1, 10, 1, 'Now these are the generations of the sons of Noah, Shem, Ham, and Japheth: and unto them were sons born after the flood.', '&para; [2] 4~08435~ 7~01121~ 9~05146~, 10~08035~, 11~02526~, 13~03315~: 18~01121~ 19~03205~ 20~0310~ 22~03999~.'),
  (22546, 32, 1, 6, 'So the shipmaster came to him, and said unto him, What meanest thou, O sleeper? arise, call upon thy God, if so be that God will think upon us, that we perish not.', '2~02259~ 3~07227~* 4~07126~ 8~0559~ 15~07290~? 16~06965~, 17~07121~ 20~0430~, 25~0430~ 27~06245~ 32~06~'),
  (7405, 9, 9, 7, 'Then said Saul to his servant, But, behold, if we go, what shall we bring the man? for the bread is spent in our vessels, and there is not a present to bring to the man of God: what have we?', '1~0559~ 2~07586~ 5~05288~, [8] 10~03212~, 14~0935~ 16~0376~? 19~03899~ 21~0235~ 24~03627~, [26 27] 30~08670~ 32~0935~ 35~0376~ 37~0430~:'),
  (28223, 45, 10, 19, 'But I say, Did not Israel know? First Moses saith, I will provoke you to jealousy by them that are no people, and by a foolish nation I will anger you.', '0~235~ 2~3004~, 3~1097~ 4~3378~ 5~2474~ 6~1097~? 7~4413~ 8~3475~ 9~3004~, 10~1473~ 12~3863~ 13~5209~ 15~3863~ 16~1909~ [17 19] 20~3756~ 21~1484~, [22] 23~1909~ 25~801~ 26~1484~ 29~3949~ 30~5209~.'),
  (19742, 24, 32, 2, 'For then the king of Babylon''s army besieged Jerusalem: and Jeremiah the prophet was shut up in the court of the prison, which was in the king of Judah''s house.', '3~04428~ 5~0894~ 6~02428~ 7~06696~ 8~03389~: 10~03414~ 12~05030~ 15~03607~ 18~02691~ 21~04307~, [23] 26~04428~ 28~03063~ 29~01004~.'),
  (3549, 3, 26, 20, 'And your strength shall be spent in vain: for your land shall not yield her increase, neither shall the trees of the land yield their fruits.', '2~03581~ 5~08552~ 7~07385~: 10~0776~ 13~05414~ 15~02981~, 19~06086~ 22~0776~ 23~05414~ 25~06529~.'),
  (22577, 32, 3, 10, 'And God saw their works, that they turned from their evil way; and God repented of the evil, that he had said that he would do unto them; and he did it not.', '1~0430~ 2~07200~ 4~04639~, 7~07725~ 10~07451~ 11~01870~; 13~0430~ 14~05162~ 17~07451~, 21~01696~ 25~06213~ 30~06213~ [31]'),
  (29427, 50, 2, 20, 'For I have no man likeminded, who will naturally care for your state.', '0~1063~ 2~2192~ 4~3762~ 5~2473~, 6~3748~ 8~1104~ 9~3309~ 11~5216~ 12~4012~.'),
  (23819, 40, 20, 17, 'And Jesus going up to Jerusalem took the twelve disciples apart in the way, and said unto them,', '&para; 0~2532~ 1~2424~ 3~305~ 4~1519~ 5~2414~ 6~3880~ 8~1427~ 9~3101~ 10~2398~ 11~2596~* 12~1722~ 14~3598~, 15~2532~ 16~2036~ 18~846~,'),
  (19744, 24, 32, 4, 'And Zedekiah king of Judah shall not escape out of the hand of the Chaldeans, but shall surely be delivered into the hand of the king of Babylon, and shall speak with him mouth to mouth, and his eyes shall behold his eyes;', '1~06667~ 2~04428~ 4~03063~ 7~04422~ 11~03027~ 14~03778~, 17~05414~ 19~05414~ 22~03027~ 25~04428~ 27~0894~, 30~01696~ 33~06310~ 35~06310~, 38~05869~ 40~07200~ 42~05869~;'),
  (25695, 42, 17, 30, 'Even thus shall it be in the day when the Son of man is revealed.', '0~2596~ 1~5024~ 4~2071~ 7~2250~ 8~3739~ 10~5207~ 12~444~ 14~601~.'),
  (29614, 52, 3, 8, 'For now we live, if ye stand fast in the Lord.', '0~3754~ 1~3568~ 3~2198~, 4~1437~ 5~5210~ 7~4739~ 8~1722~ 10~2962~.'),
  (14039, 19, 9, 9, 'The LORD also will be a refuge for the oppressed, a refuge in times of trouble.', '1~03068~ 6~04869~ 9~01790~, 11~04869~ 13~06256~ 15~06869~.'),
  (19094, 24, 5, 27, 'As a cage is full of birds, so are their houses full of deceit: therefore they are become great, and waxen rich.', '2~03619~ 4~04392~ 6~05775~, [8] 10~01004~ 11~04392~ 13~04820~: 18~01431~, 21~06238~.'),
  (23022, 38, 9, 14, 'And the LORD shall be seen over them, and his arrow shall go forth as the lightning: and the Lord GOD shall blow the trumpet, and shall go with whirlwinds of the south.', '2~03068~ 5~07200~ 10~02671~ 13~03318~ 16~01300~: 19~0136~ 20~03069~ 22~08628~ 24~07782~, 27~01980~ 29~05591~ 32~08486~.'),
  (2412, 2, 30, 25, 'And thou shalt make it an oil of holy ointment, an ointment compound after the art of the apothecary: it shall be an holy anointing oil.', '3~06213~ 6~08081~ 8~06944~ 9~04888~, 11~07545~ 12~04842~ 15~04639~ 18~07543~: 23~06944~ 24~04888~ 25~08081~.'),
  (9839, 12, 11, 2, 'But Jehosheba, the daughter of king Joram, sister of Ahaziah, took Joash the son of Ahaziah, and stole him from among the king''s sons which were slain; and they hid him, even him and his nurse, in the bedchamber from Athaliah, so that he was not slain.', '1~03089~, 3~01323~ 5~04428~ 6~03141~, 7~0269~ 9~0274~, 10~03947~ 11~03101~ 13~01121~ 15~0274~, 17~01589~ 20~08432~ 22~04428~ 23~01121~ [24 25] 26~04191~; 29~05641~ [31] 35~03243~, 38~04296~ 39~02315~* 40~06440~ 41~06271~, 47~04191~.'),
  (29346, 49, 5, 26, 'That he might sanctify and cleanse it with the washing of water by the word,', '0~2443~ 3~37~ 6~2511~ 9~3067~ 11~5204~ 12~1722~ 14~4487~,'),
  (24395, 41, 5, 21, 'And when Jesus was passed over again by ship unto the other side, much people gathered unto him: and he was nigh unto the sea.', '&para; 0~2532~ 2~2424~ 5~1276~ 6~3825~ 7~1722~ 8~4143~ 9~1519~ 12~4008~, 13~4183~ 14~3793~ 15~4863~ 16~1909~ 17~846~: 18~2532~ 20~2258~ 21~3844~ 24~2281~.'),
  (6418, 6, 21, 30, 'And out of the tribe of Asher, Mishal with her suburbs, Abdon with her suburbs,', '4~04294~ 6~0836~, 7~04861~ 10~04054~, 11~05658~ 14~04054~,'),
  (8881, 11, 4, 29, 'And God gave Solomon wisdom and understanding exceeding much, and largeness of heart, even as the sand that is on the sea shore.', '&para; 1~0430~ 2~05414~ 3~08010~ 4~02451~ 6~08394~ 7~03966~ 8~07235~, 10~07341~ 12~03820~, 16~02344~ [18] 21~03220~ 22~08193~.'),
  (5849, 5, 34, 4, 'And the LORD said unto him, This is the land which I sware unto Abraham, unto Isaac, and unto Jacob, saying, I will give it unto thy seed: I have caused thee to see it with thine eyes, but thou shalt not go over thither.', '2~03068~ 3~0559~ [7] 9~0776~ 12~07650~ 14~085~, 16~03327~, 19~03290~, 20~0559~, 23~05414~ 27~02233~: 33~07200~ [34] 37~05869~, 43~05674~'),
  (15730, 19, 107, 22, 'And let them sacrifice the sacrifices of thanksgiving, and declare his works with rejoicing.', '3~02076~ 5~02077~ 7~08426~, 9~05608~ 11~04639~ 13~07440~.'),
  (29212, 48, 6, 8, 'For he that soweth to his flesh shall of the flesh reap corruption; but he that soweth to the Spirit shall of the Spirit reap life everlasting.', '0~3754~ 3~4687~ 4~1519~ 5~1438~ 6~4561~ 7~2325~ 8~1537~ 10~4561~ 11~2325~ 12~5356~; 13~1161~ 16~4687~ 17~1519~ 19~4151~ 20~2325~ 21~1537~ 23~4151~ 24~2325~ 25~2222~ 26~166~.'),
  (27922, 44, 28, 7, 'In the same quarters were possessions of the chief man of the island, whose name was Publius; who received us, and lodged us three days courteously.', '0~1161~* 1~4012~ 2~1722~ 3~1565~ 4~5117~ 5~5225~ 6~5564~ 10~4413~ 13~3520~, 16~3686~ 17~4196~; 18~3739~ 19~324~ 20~2248~, 23~3579~ 24~5140~ 25~2250~ 26~5390~.'),
  (7706, 9, 18, 23, 'And Saul''s servants spake those words in the ears of David. And David said, Seemeth it to you a light thing to be a king''s son in law, seeing that I am a poor man, and lightly esteemed?', '1~07586~ 2~05650~ 3~01696~ 5~01697~ 8~0241~ 10~01732~. 12~01732~ 13~0559~, 14~05869~ [18] 19~07043~ [20] 24~04428~ 27~02859~, [31] 33~07326~ 34~0376~, 37~07034~?'),
  (8738, 11, 1, 13, 'Go and get thee in unto king David, and say unto him, Didst not thou, my lord, O king, swear unto thine handmaid, saying, Assuredly Solomon thy son shall reign after me, and he shall sit upon my throne? why then doth Adonijah reign?', '0~03212~ 4~0935~ 6~04428~ 7~01732~, 9~0559~ 16~0113~, 18~04428~, 19~07650~ 22~0519~, 23~0559~, 24~03588~ 25~08010~ 27~01121~ 29~04427~ 30~0310~ 35~03427~ 38~03678~? 42~0138~ 43~04427~?'),
  (2525, 2, 34, 24, 'For I will cast out the nations before thee, and enlarge thy borders: neither shall any man desire thy land, when thou shalt go up to appear before the LORD thy God thrice in the year.', '4~03423~ 6~01471~ 7~06440~ 10~07337~ 12~01366~: 16~0376~ 17~02530~ 19~0776~, 24~05927~ 26~07200~ 27~06440~ 29~03068~ 31~0430~ 32~07969~ 33~06471~ 35~08141~.'),
