VALUES
  (5416, 5, 19, 4, 'And this is the case of the slayer, which shall flee thither, that he may live: Whoso killeth his neighbour ignorantly, whom he hated not in time past;', '[2] 4~01697~ 7~07523~, 10~05127~ 15~02425~: 17~05221~ 19~07453~ 20~01847~ 21~01097~,* 24~08130~ 27~08543~ 28~08032~;'),
  (12653, 16, 12, 20, 'Of Sallai, Kallai; of Amok, Eber;', '1~05543~, 2~07040~; 4~05987~, 5~05677~;'),
  (904, 1, 31, 27, 'Wherefore didst thou flee away secretly, and steal away from me; and didst not tell me, that I might have sent thee away with mirth, and with songs, with tabret, and with harp?', '4~01272~ 5~02244~, 8~01589~ 14~05046~ 22~07971~ 24~08057~, 27~07892~, 29~08596~, 32~03658~?'),
  (7719, 9, 19, 6, 'And Saul hearkened unto the voice of Jonathan: and Saul sware, As the LORD liveth, he shall not be slain.', '1~07586~ 2~08085~ 5~06963~ 7~03083~: 9~07586~ 10~07650~, [11] 13~03068~ 14~02416~, 17~0518~ 19~04191~.'),
  (13244, 18, 15, 32, 'It shall be accomplished before his time, and his branch shall not be green.', '3~04390~ 4~03808~ 6~03117~, 9~03712~ 13~07488~.'),
  (27609, 44, 19, 8, 'And he went into the synagogue, and spake boldly for the space of three months, disputing and persuading the things concerning the kingdom of God.', '&para; 0~1161~ 2~1525~ 3~1519~ 5~4864~, 8~3955~ 11~1909~ 13~5140~ 14~3376~, 15~1256~ 16~2532~ 17~3982~ 20~4012~ 22~932~ 24~2316~.'),
  (690, 1, 25, 28, 'And Isaac loved Esau, because he did eat of his venison: but Rebekah loved Jacob.', '1~03327~ 2~0157~ 3~06215~, 7~06310~ [9] 10~06718~: 12~07259~ 13~0157~ 14~03290~.'),
  (22428, 30, 4, 9, 'I have smitten you with blasting and mildew: when your gardens and your vineyards and your fig trees and your olive trees increased, the palmerworm devoured them: yet have ye not returned unto me, saith the LORD.', '2~05221~ 5~07711~ 7~03420~: 10~01593~ 13~03754~ 17~08384~ 21~02132~ 22~07235~, 24~01501~ 25~0398~ [26] 31~07725~ 34~05002~ 36~03068~.'),
  (3855, 4, 6, 27, 'And they shall put my name upon the children of Israel; and I will bless them.', '3~07760~ 5~08034~ 8~01121~ 10~03478~; 14~01288~'),
  (27884, 44, 27, 13, 'And when the south wind blew softly, supposing that they had obtained their purpose, loosing thence, they sailed close by Crete.', '0~1161~ 4~3558~ 6~5285~, 7~1380~ 11~2902~ [12] 13~4286~, 14~142~ [15] 17~3881~ 19~788~ 20~2914~.'),
  (29257, 49, 2, 12, 'That at that time ye were without Christ, being aliens from the commonwealth of Israel, and strangers from the covenants of promise, having no hope, and without God in the world:', '0~3754~ 1~1722~ 2~1565~ 3~2540~ 5~2258~ 6~5565~ 7~5547~, 9~526~ 12~4174~ 14~2474~, 15~2532~ 16~3581~ 19~1242~ 21~1860~, 22~2192~ 23~3361~ 24~1680~, 25~2532~ 27~112~ 28~1722~ 30~2889~:'),
  (19829, 24, 34, 19, 'The princes of Judah, and the princes of Jerusalem, the eunuchs, and the priests, and all the people of the land, which passed between the parts of the calf;', '1~08269~ 3~03063~, 6~08269~ 8~03389~, 10~05631~, 13~03548~, 17~05971~ 20~0776~, 22~05674~ 25~01335~ 28~05695~;'),
  (12956, 18, 4, 17, 'Shall mortal man be more just than God? shall a man be more pure than his maker?', '2~0582~ 5~06663~ 7~0433~? 10~01397~ 13~02891~ 16~06213~?'),
  (11755, 14, 26, 14, 'And Uzziah prepared for them throughout all the host shields, and spears, and helmets, and habergeons, and bows, and slings to cast stones.', '1~05818~ 2~03559~ 8~06635~ 9~04043~, 11~07420~, 13~03553~, 15~08302~, 17~07198~, 19~07050~ [20 21] 22~068~.'),
  (19917, 24, 38, 13, 'So they drew up Jeremiah with cords, and took him up out of the dungeon: and Jeremiah remained in the court of the prison.', '3~04900~ 4~03414~ 6~02256~, 10~05927~ 14~0953~: 16~03414~ 17~03427~ 20~02691~ 23~04307~.'),
  (6882, 7, 12, 6, 'Then said they unto him, Say now Shibboleth: and he said Sibboleth: for he could not frame to pronounce it right. Then they took him, and slew him at the passages of Jordan: and there fell at that time of the Ephraimites forty and two thousand.', '1~0559~ 5~0559~ 7~07641~: 10~0559~ 11~05451~: 16~03559~ 18~01696~ [19] 20~03559~. 23~0270~ 26~07819~ 30~04569~ 32~03383~: 35~05307~ 38~06256~ 41~0669~ 42~0705~ 44~08147~ 45~0505~.'),
  (27451, 44, 14, 21, 'And when they had preached the gospel to that city, and had taught many, they returned again to Lystra, and to Iconium, and Antioch,', '0~5037~ 6~2097~ 8~1565~ 9~4172~, 10~2532~ 12~3100~ 13~2425~, 16~5290~ 17~1519~ 18~3082~, 19~2532~ [20] 21~2430~, 22~2532~ 23~490~,'),
  (14777, 19, 56, 13, 'For thou hast delivered my soul from death: wilt not thou deliver my feet from falling, that I may walk before God in the light of the living?', '3~05337~ 5~05315~ 7~04194~: [8] [10 11] 13~07272~ 15~01762~, 19~01980~ 20~06440~ 21~0430~ 24~0216~ 27~02416~?'),
  (15134, 19, 78, 12, 'Marvellous things did he in the sight of their fathers, in the land of Egypt, in the field of Zoan.', '1~06382~ 2~06213~ 6~05048~ 9~01~, 12~0776~ 14~04714~, [15] 17~07704~ 19~06814~.'),
  (13073, 18, 9, 13, 'If God will not withdraw his anger, the proud helpers do stoop under him.', '[0] 1~0433~ 4~07725~ 6~0639~, 8~07293~ 9~05826~ 11~07817~'),
  (19403, 24, 18, 10, 'If it do evil in my sight, that it obey not my voice, then I will repent of the good, wherewith I said I would benefit them.', '2~06213~ 3~07451~ 6~05869~, 9~08085~ 12~06963~, 16~05162~ 19~02896~, 22~0559~ 25~03190~'),
  (22462, 30, 6, 3, 'Ye that put far away the evil day, and cause the seat of violence to come near;', '4~05077~ 6~07451~ 7~03117~, 11~07675~ 13~02555~ 16~05066~;'),
  (6502, 6, 24, 19, 'And Joshua said unto the people, Ye cannot serve the LORD: for he is an holy God; he is a jealous God; he will not forgive your transgressions nor your sins.', '1~03091~ 2~0559~ 5~05971~, 7~03201~ 8~05647~ 10~03068~: [13] 15~06918~ 16~0430~; [18] 20~07072~ 21~0410~; 25~05375~ 27~06588~ 30~02403~.'),
  (11057, 13, 25, 3, 'Of Jeduthun: the sons of Jeduthun; Gedaliah, and Zeri, and Jeshaiah, Hashabiah, and Mattithiah, six, under the hands of their father Jeduthun, who prophesied with a harp, to give thanks and to praise the LORD.', '1~03038~: 3~01121~ 5~03038~; 6~01436~, 8~06874~, 10~03470~, 11~02811~, 13~04993~, 14~08337~, 17~03027~ 20~01~ 21~03038~, 23~05012~ 26~03658~, 29~03034~ 32~01984~ 34~03068~.'),
  (15216, 19, 80, 9, 'Thou preparedst room before it, and didst cause it to take deep root, and it filled the land.', '1~06437~ [2] 3~06440~ 11~08328~ 12~08327~, 15~04390~ 17~0776~.'),
  (14012, 19, 7, 8, 'The LORD shall judge the people: judge me, O LORD, according to my righteousness, and according to mine integrity that is in me.', '1~03068~ 3~01777~ 5~05971~: 6~08199~ 9~03068~, 13~06664~, 18~08537~ [19 20]'),
  (8407, 10, 15, 11, 'And with Absalom went two hundred men out of Jerusalem, that were called; and they went in their simplicity, and they knew not any thing.', '2~053~ 3~01980~ 5~03967~ 6~0376~ 9~03389~, [10 11] 12~07121~; 15~01980~ 18~08537~, 21~03045~ 24~01697~.'),
  (28401, 46, 1, 22, 'For the Jews require a sign, and the Greeks seek after wisdom:', '0~1894~ 1~2532~ 2~2453~ 3~154~ 5~4592~, 6~2532~ 8~1672~ 9~2212~ 11~4678~:'),
  (21901, 27, 5, 18, 'O thou king, the most high God gave Nebuchadnezzar thy father a kingdom, and majesty, and glory, and honour:', '1~0607~ 2~04430~, 5~05943~ 6~0426~ 7~03052~ 8~05020~ 10~02~ 12~04437~, 14~07238~, 16~03367~, 18~01923~:'),
  (6809, 7, 9, 48, 'And Abimelech gat him up to mount Zalmon, he and all the people that were with him; and Abimelech took an ax in his hand, and cut down a bough from the trees, and took it, and laid it on his shoulder, and said unto the people that were with him, What ye have seen me do, make haste, and do as I have done.', '1~040~ 4~05927~ 6~02022~ 7~06756~, 12~05971~ [14] 18~040~ 19~03947~ 21~07134~ 24~03027~, 27~03772~ 29~07754~ 32~06086~, 34~05375~ 37~07760~ [38] 41~07926~, 43~0559~ 46~05971~ [48] 54~07200~ 56~06213~, 58~04116~, [59] 60~06213~ 62~03644~ [63 64]'),
  (29818, 54, 6, 14, 'That thou keep this commandment without spot, unrebukeable, until the appearing of our Lord Jesus Christ:', '1~4571~ 2~5083~ [3] 4~1785~ 6~784~, 7~423~, 8~3360~ 10~2015~ 12~2257~ 13~2962~ 14~2424~ 15~5547~:'),
  (1472, 1, 48, 16, 'The Angel which redeemed me from all evil, bless the lads; and let my name be named on them, and the name of my fathers Abraham and Isaac; and let them grow into a multitude in the midst of the earth.', '1~04397~ 3~01350~ 7~07451~, 8~01288~ 10~05288~; 14~08034~ 16~07121~ 21~08034~ 24~01~ 25~085~ 27~03327~; 31~01711~ 34~07230~ 37~07130~ 40~0776~.'),
  (9028, 11, 8, 35, 'When heaven is shut up, and there is no rain, because they have sinned against thee; if they pray toward this place, and confess thy name, and turn from their sin, when thou afflictest them:', '1~08064~ 4~06113~, 9~04306~, 13~02398~ 18~06419~ 21~04725~, 23~03034~ 25~08034~, 27~07725~ 30~02403~, 33~06031~'),
  (12757, 17, 3, 1, 'After these things did king Ahasuerus promote Haman the son of Hammedatha the Agagite, and advanced him, and set his seat above all the princes that were with him.', '&para; 0~0310~ 2~01697~ 4~04428~ 5~0325~ 6~01431~ 7~02001~ 9~01121~ 11~04099~ 13~091~, 15~05375~ 18~07760~ 20~03678~ 24~08269~ [26]'),
  (22944, 38, 4, 13, 'And he answered me and said, Knowest thou not what these be? And I said, No, my lord.', '2~0559~ 5~0559~, 6~03045~ [11] 14~0559~, 17~0113~.'),
  (5175, 5, 9, 12, 'And the LORD said unto me, Arise, get thee down quickly from hence; for thy people which thou hast brought forth out of Egypt have corrupted themselves; they are quickly turned aside out of the way which I commanded them; they have made them a molten image.', '2~03068~ 3~0559~ 6~06965~, 9~03381~ 10~04118~ 15~05971~ 20~03318~ 23~04714~ 25~07843~ [26] 29~04118~ 31~05493~ 35~01870~ 38~06680~ 42~06213~ 46~04541~.'),
  (22835, 36, 3, 6, 'I have cut off the nations: their towers are desolate; I made their streets waste, that none passeth by: their cities are destroyed, so that there is no man, that there is none inhabitant.', '3~03772~ 5~01471~: 7~06438~ 9~08074~; 13~02351~ 14~02717~, 18~05674~: 20~05892~ 22~06658~, 28~0376~, 33~03427~.'),
  (31010, 66, 18, 1, 'And after these things I saw another angel come down from heaven, having great power; and the earth was lightened with his glory.', '&para; 0~2532~ 1~3326~ 3~5023~ 5~1492~ 6~243~ 7~32~ 9~2597~ 10~1537~ 11~3772~, 12~2192~ 13~3173~ 14~1849~; 15~2532~ 17~1093~ 19~5461~ 20~1537~ 21~846~ 22~1391~.'),
  (25727, 42, 18, 25, 'For it is easier for a camel to go through a needle''s eye, than for a rich man to enter into the kingdom of God.', '0~1063~ 2~2076~ 3~2123~ 6~2574~ 8~1525~ 9~1223~ 11~4476~ 12~5168~, 13~2228~ 17~4145~ 19~1525~ 20~1519~ 22~932~ 24~2316~.'),
  (8023, 9, 31, 7, 'And when the men of Israel that were on the other side of the valley, and they that were on the other side Jordan, saw that the men of Israel fled, and that Saul and his sons were dead, they forsook the cities, and fled; and the Philistines came and dwelt in them.', '3~0582~ 5~03478~ [7] 11~05676~ 14~06010~, [16] [18] 22~05676~ 23~03383~, 24~07200~ 27~0582~ 29~03478~ 30~05127~, 33~07586~ 36~01121~ 38~04191~, 40~05800~ 42~05892~, 44~05127~; 47~06430~ 48~0935~ 50~03427~'),
  (12849, 17, 9, 6, 'And in Shushan the palace the Jews slew and destroyed five hundred men.', '2~07800~ 4~01002~ 6~03064~ 7~02026~ 9~06~ 10~02568~ 11~03967~ 12~0376~.'),
  (2032, 2, 19, 1, 'In the third month, when the children of Israel were gone forth out of the land of Egypt, the same day came they into the wilderness of Sinai.', '&para; 2~07992~ 3~02320~, 6~01121~ 8~03478~ 11~03318~ 15~0776~ 17~04714~, 20~03117~ 21~0935~ [23] 25~04057~ 27~05514~.'),
  (16933, 20, 18, 23, 'The poor useth entreaties; but the rich answereth roughly.', '&para; 1~07326~ 2~01696~ 3~08469~; 6~06223~ 7~06030~ 8~05794~.'),
  (24139, 40, 26, 75, 'And Peter remembered the word of Jesus, which said unto him, Before the cock crow, thou shalt deny me thrice. And he went out, and wept bitterly.', '0~2532~ 1~4074~ 2~3415~ 4~4487~ 6~2424~, 7~3588~ 8~2046~ 10~846~, 11~4250~ 12~3754~ 13~220~ 14~5455~, 17~533~ 18~3165~ 19~5151~. 20~2532~ 23~1854~, 24~1831~ 25~2799~ 26~4090~.'),
  (8978, 11, 7, 36, 'For on the plates of the ledges thereof, and on the borders thereof, he graved cherubims, lions, and palm trees, according to the proportion of every one, and additions round about.', '3~03871~ 6~03027~ 11~04526~ 14~06605~ 15~03742~, 16~0738~, 19~08561~, 23~04626~ 26~0376~, 28~03914~ 30~05439~.'),
  (8887, 11, 5, 1, 'And Hiram king of Tyre sent his servants unto Solomon; for he had heard that they had anointed him king in the room of his father: for Hiram was ever a lover of David.', '&para; 1~02438~ 2~04428~ 4~06865~ 5~07971~ 7~05650~ 9~08010~; 13~08085~ 17~04886~ 19~04428~ 25~01~: 27~02438~ 29~03117~ 31~0157~ 33~01732~.'),
  (5855, 5, 34, 10, 'And there arose not a prophet since in Israel like unto Moses, whom the LORD knew face to face,', '2~06965~ 5~05030~ 6~05750~ 8~03478~ 11~04872~, 14~03068~ 15~03045~ 16~06440~ 18~06440~,'),
  (21733, 26, 48, 22, 'Moreover from the possession of the Levites, and from the possession of the city, being in the midst of that which is the prince''s, between the border of Judah and the border of Benjamin, shall be for the prince.', '3~0272~ 6~03881~, 10~0272~ 13~05892~, [14] 17~08432~ [18 19] 23~05387~, 26~01366~ 28~03063~ 31~01366~ 33~01144~, 38~05387~.'),
  (27873, 44, 27, 2, 'And entering into a ship of Adramyttium, we launched, meaning to sail by the coasts of Asia; one Aristarchus, a Macedonian of Thessalonica, being with us.', '0~1161~ 1~1910~ 4~4143~ 6~98~, 8~321~, 9~3195~ 11~4126~ 12~2596~ 14~5117~ 16~773~; [17] 18~708~, 20~3110~ 22~2331~, 23~5607~ 24~4862~ 25~2254~.'),
  (17821, 23, 8, 5, 'The LORD spake also unto me again, saying,', '1~03068~ 2~01696~ 6~03254~, 7~0559~,'),
  (16252, 19, 139, 4, 'For there is not a word in my tongue, but, lo, O LORD, thou knowest it altogether.', '[1 2] 5~04405~ 8~03956~, [9] 12~03068~, 14~03045~'),
  (29965, 57, 1, 11, 'Which in time past was to thee unprofitable, but now profitable to thee and to me:', '0~3588~ 3~4218~ 4~890~ 6~4671~ 7~890~, 8~1161~ 9~3570~ 10~2173~ 12~4671~ 13~2532~ 15~1698~:'),
  (21792, 27, 2, 25, 'Then Arioch brought in Daniel before the king in haste, and said thus unto him, I have found a man of the captives of Judah, that will make known unto the king the interpretation.', '0~0116~ 1~0746~ 3~05954~ 4~01841~ 5~06925~ 7~04430~ 9~0927~, 11~0560~ 12~03652~ 17~07912~ 19~01400~ 22~01547~ 23~01123~* 24~04481~ 25~03061~, 29~03046~ 32~04430~ 34~06591~.'),
  (30438, 60, 2, 23, 'Who, when he was reviled, reviled not again; when he suffered, he threatened not; but committed himself to him that judgeth righteously:', '0~3739~, 4~3058~, 5~486~ 6~3756~ 7~486~; 10~3958~, 12~546~ 13~3756~; 14~1161~ 15~3860~ [16] 20~2919~ 21~1346~:'),
  (597, 1, 24, 2, 'And Abraham said unto his eldest servant of his house, that ruled over all that he had, Put, I pray thee, thy hand under my thigh:', '1~085~ 2~0559~ 5~02205~ 6~05650~ 9~01004~, 12~04910~ 17~07760~, 22~03027~ 25~03409~:'),
  (7066, 7, 20, 5, 'And the men of Gibeah rose against me, and beset the house round about upon me by night, and thought to have slain me: and my concubine have they forced, that she is dead.', '2~01167~ 4~01390~ 5~06965~ 9~05437~ 11~01004~ 13~05437~ 17~03915~, [18] 19~01819~ 22~02026~ 26~06370~ 29~06031~, 33~04191~.'),
  (9448, 11, 20, 32, 'So they girded sackcloth on their loins, and put ropes on their heads, and came to the king of Israel, and said, Thy servant Benhadad saith, I pray thee, let me live. And he said, Is he yet alive? he is my brother.', '2~02296~ 3~08242~ 6~04975~, [8] 9~02256~ 12~07218~, 14~0935~ 17~04428~ 19~03478~, 21~0559~, 23~05650~ 24~01130~ 25~0559~, 31~02421~ 32~05315~.* 35~0559~, [36] 39~02416~? [41] 43~0251~.'),
  (29858, 55, 2, 15, 'Study to shew thyself approved unto God, a workman that needeth not to be ashamed, rightly dividing the word of truth.', '0~4704~ 2~3936~ 3~4572~ 4~1384~ 6~2316~, 8~2040~ 14~422~, 16~3718~ 18~3056~ 20~225~.'),
  (13441, 18, 23, 13, 'But he is in one mind, and who can turn him? and what his soul desireth, even that he doeth.', '&para; [2] 4~0259~ [5] 9~07725~ [12] 14~05315~ 15~0183~, [17] 19~06213~.'),
  (782, 1, 28, 5, 'And Isaac sent away Jacob: and he went to Padanaram unto Laban, son of Bethuel the Syrian, the brother of Rebekah, Jacob''s and Esau''s mother.', '1~03327~ 3~07971~ 4~03290~: 7~03212~ 9~06307~ 11~03837~, 12~01121~ 14~01328~ 16~0761~, 18~0251~ 20~07259~, 21~03290~ 23~06215~ 24~0517~.'),
  (18871, 23, 62, 8, 'The LORD hath sworn by his right hand, and by the arm of his strength, Surely I will no more give thy corn to be meat for thine enemies; and the sons of the stranger shall not drink thy wine, for the which thou hast laboured:', '1~03068~ 3~07650~ 7~03225~, 11~02220~ 14~05797~, 17~0518~ 20~05414~ 22~01715~ [23 24] 25~03978~ 28~0341~; 31~01121~ 34~05236~ 37~08354~ 39~08492~, 45~03021~:'),
  (3264, 3, 18, 8, 'The nakedness of thy father''s wife shalt thou not uncover: it is thy father''s nakedness.', '1~06172~ 4~01~ 5~0802~ 9~01540~: [11] 13~01~ 14~06172~.'),
  (1782, 2, 9, 35, 'And the heart of Pharaoh was hardened, neither would he let the children of Israel go; as the LORD had spoken by Moses.', '2~03820~ 4~06547~ 6~02388~, 12~01121~ 14~03478~ 15~07971~; 18~03068~ 20~01696~ 21~03027~ 22~04872~.'),
  (7586, 9, 15, 19, 'Wherefore then didst thou not obey the voice of the LORD, but didst fly upon the spoil, and didst evil in the sight of the LORD?', '5~08085~ 7~06963~ 10~03068~, 13~05860~ 16~07998~, 18~06213~ 19~07451~ 22~05869~ 25~03068~?'),
  (28898, 47, 5, 5, 'Now he that hath wrought us for the selfsame thing is God, who also hath given unto us the earnest of the Spirit.', '0~1161~ 4~2716~ 5~2248~ 6~1519~ 9~5124~ [10] 10~846~ 11~2316~, 12~3588~ 13~2532~ 15~1325~ 17~2254~ 19~728~ 22~4151~.'),
  (21511, 26, 40, 25, 'And there were windows in it and in the arches thereof round about, like those windows: the length was fifty cubits, and the breadth five and twenty cubits.', '[1 2] 3~02474~ 9~0361~ 12~05439~, 15~02474~: 17~0753~ [18] 19~02572~ 20~0520~, 23~07341~ 24~02568~ 26~06242~ 27~0520~.'),
  (20078, 24, 46, 24, 'The daughter of Egypt shall be confounded; she shall be delivered into the hand of the people of the north.', '1~01323~ 3~04714~ 6~03001~; 10~05414~ 13~03027~ 16~05971~ 19~06828~.'),
  (15467, 19, 95, 4, 'In his hand are the deep places of the earth: the strength of the hills is his also.', '2~03027~ [3] 6~04278~ 9~0776~: 11~08443~ 14~02022~ [15]'),
  (1621, 2, 4, 15, 'And thou shalt speak unto him, and put words in his mouth: and I will be with thy mouth, and with his mouth, and will teach you what ye shall do.', '3~01696~ 7~07760~ 8~01697~ 11~06310~: 18~06310~, 22~06310~, 25~03384~ 30~06213~.'),
  (17524, 21, 11, 2, 'Give a portion to seven, and also to eight; for thou knowest not what evil shall be upon the earth.', '0~05414~ 2~02506~ 4~07651~, 8~08083~; 11~03045~ 14~07451~ 19~0776~.'),
  (19158, 24, 7, 30, 'For the children of Judah have done evil in my sight, saith the LORD: they have set their abominations in the house which is called by my name, to pollute it.', '2~01121~ 4~03063~ 6~06213~ 7~07451~ 10~05869~, 11~05002~ 13~03068~: 16~07760~ 18~08251~ 21~01004~ 24~07121~ 27~08034~, 29~02930~'),
  (27354, 44, 12, 1, 'Now about that time Herod the king stretched forth his hands to vex certain of the church.', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~2596~ 2~1565~ 3~2540~ 4~2264~ 6~935~ 8~1911~ [9] 10~5495~ 12~2559~ 13~5100~ 14~575~ 16~1577~.'),
  (10851, 13, 16, 23, 'Sing unto the LORD, all the earth; shew forth from day to day his salvation.', '0~07891~ 3~03068~, 6~0776~; 8~01319~ 10~03117~ 12~03117~ 14~03444~.'),
  (23691, 40, 16, 9, 'Do ye not yet understand, neither remember the five loaves of the five thousand, and how many baskets ye took up?', '1~3539~ 3~3768~ 4~3539~, 5~3761~ 6~3421~ 8~4002~ 9~740~ 13~4000~, 14~2532~ 16~4214~ 17~2894~ 20~2983~?'),
  (8962, 11, 7, 20, 'And the chapiters upon the two pillars had pomegranates also above, over against the belly which was by the network: and the pomegranates were two hundred in rows round about upon the other chapiter.', '2~03805~ 5~08147~ 6~05982~ [7 8] 10~04605~, 12~05980~ 14~0990~ [16] 17~05676~ 19~07639~: 22~07416~ [23] 25~03967~ 27~02905~ 29~05439~ 32~08145~ 33~03805~.'),
  (7798, 9, 22, 4, 'And he brought them before the king of Moab: and they dwelt with him all the while that David was in the hold.', '2~05148~ 4~06440~ 6~04428~ 8~04124~: 11~03427~ 16~03117~ 18~01732~ 22~04686~.'),
  (5390, 5, 17, 20, 'That his heart be not lifted up above his brethren, and that he turn not aside from the commandment, to the right hand, or to the left: to the end that he may prolong his days in his kingdom, he, and his children, in the midst of Israel.', '2~03824~ 6~07311~ 9~0251~, 15~05493~ 18~04687~, [19] 22~03225~, [24] 26~08040~: 33~0748~ [34] 35~03117~ 38~04467~, 42~01121~, 45~07130~ 47~03478~.'),
  (19739, 24, 31, 39, 'And the measuring line shall yet go forth over against it upon the hill Gareb, and shall compass about to Goath.', '2~04060~ 3~06957~ 4~06961~* 8~03318~ 14~01389~ 15~01619~, 19~05437~ 21~01601~.'),
  (11066, 13, 25, 12, 'The fifth to Nethaniah, he, his sons, and his brethren, were twelve:', '1~02549~ 3~05418~, [4] 6~01121~, 9~0251~, [10] 11~06240~ 12~08147~:*'),
  (14400, 19, 34, 3, 'O magnify the LORD with me, and let us exalt his name together.', '1~01431~ 3~03068~ 9~07311~ 11~08034~ 12~03162~.'),
  (2952, 3, 8, 30, 'And Moses took of the anointing oil, and of the blood which was upon the altar, and sprinkled it upon Aaron, and upon his garments, and upon his sons, and upon his sons'' garments with him; and sanctified Aaron, and his garments, and his sons, and his sons'' garments with him.', '1~04872~ 2~03947~ 5~04888~ 6~08081~, 10~01818~ [12] 15~04196~, 17~05137~ [18] 20~0175~, [21] 24~0899~, 28~01121~, 32~01121~ 33~0899~ 37~06942~ 38~0175~, [39] 41~0899~, 44~01121~, 47~01121~ 48~0899~'),
  (26747, 43, 16, 6, 'But because I have said these things unto you, sorrow hath filled your heart.', '0~235~ 1~3754~ 4~2980~ 6~5023~ 8~5213~, 9~3077~ 11~4137~ 12~5216~ 13~2588~.'),
  (26064, 43, 1, 6, 'There was a man sent from God, whose name was John.', '1~1096~ 3~444~ 4~649~ 5~3844~ 6~2316~, 7~846~ 8~3686~ [9] 10~2491~.'),
  (942, 1, 32, 10, 'I am not worthy of the least of all the mercies, and of all the truth, which thou hast shewed unto thy servant; for with my staff I passed over this Jordan; and now I am become two bands.', '6~06994~ 10~02617~, 15~0571~, 19~06213~ 22~05650~; 26~04731~ 29~05674~ 31~03383~; 37~08147~ 38~04264~.'),
  (20782, 26, 16, 11, 'I decked thee also with ornaments, and I put bracelets upon thy hands, and a chain on thy neck.', '1~05710~ 5~05716~, 8~05414~ 9~06781~ 12~03027~, 15~07242~ 18~01627~.'),
  (9258, 11, 15, 1, 'Now in the eighteenth year of king Jeroboam the son of Nebat reigned Abijam over Judah.', '&para; 3~06240~ 4~08083~* 5~08141~ 7~04428~ 8~03379~ 10~01121~ 12~05028~ 13~04427~ 14~038~ 16~03063~.'),
  (27223, 44, 8, 31, 'And he said, How can I, except some man should guide me? And he desired Philip that he would come up and sit with him.', '0~1161~ 2~2036~, 3~4459~ 4~1063~ 5~1410~ 6~302~,* 7~3362~ 9~5100~ 11~3594~ 12~3165~? 13~5037~ 15~3870~ 16~5376~ 21~305~ 23~2523~ 24~4862~ 25~846~.'),
  (27559, 44, 17, 20, 'For thou bringest certain strange things to our ears: we would know therefore what these things mean.', '0~1063~ 2~1533~ 3~5100~ 5~3579~ 6~1519~ 7~2257~ 8~189~: 10~1014~ 11~1097~ 12~3767~ 13~5101~ 15~5023~ 16~2309~ 17~302~* 18~1511~.*'),
  (22634, 33, 4, 5, 'For all people will walk every one in the name of his god, and we will walk in the name of the LORD our God for ever and ever.', '2~05971~ 4~03212~ 6~0376~ 9~08034~ 12~0430~, 16~03212~ 19~08034~ 22~03068~ 24~0430~ 26~05769~ 28~05703~.'),
  (766, 1, 27, 35, 'And he said, Thy brother came with subtlety, and hath taken away thy blessing.', '2~0559~, 4~0251~ 5~0935~ 7~04820~, 11~03947~ 13~01293~.'),
  (3130, 3, 14, 14, 'And the priest shall take some of the blood of the trespass offering, and the priest shall put it upon the tip of the right ear of him that is to be cleansed, and upon the thumb of his right hand, and upon the great toe of his right foot:', '2~03548~ 4~03947~ [5] 8~01818~ 12~0817~, 15~03548~ 17~05414~ [18] 21~08571~ 24~03233~ 25~0241~ 32~02891~, 36~0931~ 39~03233~ 40~03027~, 45~0931~ 48~03233~ 49~07272~:'),
  (18398, 23, 37, 37, 'So Sennacherib king of Assyria departed, and went and returned, and dwelt at Nineveh.', '1~05576~ 2~04428~ 4~0804~ 5~05265~, 7~03212~ 9~07725~, 11~03427~ 13~05210~.'),
  (23272, 40, 5, 28, 'But I say unto you, That whosoever looketh on a woman to lust after her hath committed adultery with her already in his heart.', '0~1161~ 1~1473~ 2~3004~ 4~5213~, 5~3754~ 6~3956~ 7~991~ 10~1135~ 11~4314~ 13~1937~ 14~846~ 17~3431~ 19~846~ 20~2235~ 21~1722~ 22~846~ 23~2588~.'),
  (27644, 44, 20, 2, 'And when he had gone over those parts, and had given them much exhortation, he came into Greece,', '0~1161~ 5~1330~ 6~1565~ 7~3313~, 8~2532~ 10~4183~ 11~846~ 12~4183~ 13~3870~ 14~3056~,* 16~2064~ 17~1519~ 18~1671~,'),
  (6999, 7, 17, 12, 'And Micah consecrated the Levite; and the young man became his priest, and was in the house of Micah.', '1~04318~ 2~04390~ 3~03027~* 5~03881~; 9~05288~ 12~03548~, 17~01004~ 19~04318~.'),
  (19949, 24, 39, 17, 'But I will deliver thee in that day, saith the LORD: and thou shalt not be given into the hand of the men of whom thou art afraid.', '3~05337~ 7~03117~, 8~05002~ 10~03068~: 16~05414~ 19~03027~ 22~0582~ 24~06440~ [26] 27~03016~.'),
  (7756, 9, 20, 19, 'And when thou hast stayed three days, then thou shalt go down quickly, and come to the place where thou didst hide thyself when the business was in hand, and shalt remain by the stone Ezel.', '[1] 6~08027~, [7] 11~03381~ 12~03966~, 14~0935~ 17~04725~ 21~05641~ 23~03117~ 25~04639~ [27 28] 31~03427~ 32~0681~ 34~068~ 35~0237~.'),
  (30803, 66, 5, 8, 'And when he had taken the book, the four beasts and four and twenty elders fell down before the Lamb, having every one of them harps, and golden vials full of odours, which are the prayers of saints.', '0~2532~ 1~3753~ 4~2983~ 6~975~, 8~5064~ 9~2226~ 10~2532~ 11~5064~ [12] 13~1501~ 14~4245~ 16~4098~ 17~1799~ 19~721~, 20~2192~ 24~1538~ 25~2788~, 26~2532~ 27~5552~ 28~5357~ 29~1073~ 31~2368~, 32~3739~ 33~1526~ 35~4335~ 37~40~.'),
  (16835, 20, 15, 19, 'The way of the slothful man is as an hedge of thorns: but the way of the righteous is made plain.', '&para; 1~01870~ 4~06102~ [5 6] 9~04881~ 11~02312~: 14~0734~ 17~03477~ [18] 20~05549~.'),
  (14241, 19, 22, 28, 'For the kingdom is the LORD''S: and he is the governor among the nations.', '2~04410~ [3] 5~03068~: [8] 10~04910~ 13~01471~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (22611, 33, 2, 7, 'O thou that art named the house of Jacob, is the spirit of the LORD straitened? are these his doings? do not my words do good to him that walketh uprightly?', '[1 3] 4~0559~ 6~01004~ 8~03290~, 11~07307~ 14~03068~ 15~07114~? [16] 19~04611~? 23~01697~ 25~03190~ 29~01980~ 30~03477~?'),
  (25235, 42, 7, 28, 'For I say unto you, Among those that are born of women there is not a greater prophet than John the Baptist: but he that is least in the kingdom of God is greater than he.', '0~1063~ 2~3004~ 4~5213~, 5~1722~ 9~1084~ 11~1135~ 13~2076~ 14~3762~ 16~3187~ 17~4396~ 18~3187~ 19~2491~ 21~910~: 22~1161~ 26~3398~ 27~1722~ 29~932~ 31~2316~ 32~2076~ 34~3187~ 35~846~.'),
  (5001, 5, 3, 20, 'Until the LORD have given rest unto your brethren, as well as unto you, and until they also possess the land which the LORD your God hath given them beyond Jordan: and then shall ye return every man unto his possession, which I have given you.', '2~03068~ 5~05117~ 8~0251~, [15] 18~03423~ 20~0776~ 23~03068~ 25~0430~ 27~05414~ 29~05676~ 30~03383~: [32] 35~07725~ 37~0376~ 40~03425~, 44~05414~'),
  (17963, 23, 14, 26, 'This is the purpose that is purposed upon the whole earth: and this is the hand that is stretched out upon all the nations.', '[1] 3~06098~ 6~03289~ 10~0776~: [13] 15~03027~ 19~05186~ 23~01471~.'),
  (3032, 3, 11, 30, 'And the ferret, and the chameleon, and the lizard, and the snail, and the mole.', '2~0604~, 5~03581~, 8~03911~, 11~02546~, 14~08580~.'),
  (11615, 14, 20, 19, 'And the Levites, of the children of the Kohathites, and of the children of the Korhites, stood up to praise the LORD God of Israel with a loud voice on high.', '2~03881~, 5~01121~ 8~06956~, 12~01121~ 15~07145~, 17~06965~ 19~01984~ 21~03068~ 22~0430~ 24~03478~ 27~01419~ 28~06963~ 30~04605~.'),
  (13201, 18, 14, 11, 'As the waters fail from the sea, and the flood decayeth and drieth up:', '[0] 2~04325~ 3~0235~ 6~03220~, 9~05104~ 10~02717~ 13~03001~:'),
  (8321, 10, 12, 28, 'Now therefore gather the rest of the people together, and encamp against the city, and take it: lest I take the city, and it be called after my name.', '2~0622~ 4~03499~ 7~05971~ 8~0622~, 10~02583~ 13~05892~, 15~03920~ 19~03920~ 21~05892~, 25~07121~ 28~08034~.'),
  (20702, 26, 12, 13, 'My net also will I spread upon him, and he shall be taken in my snare: and I will bring him to Babylon to the land of the Chaldeans; yet shall he not see it, though he shall die there.', '1~07568~ 5~06566~ 12~08610~ 15~04686~: 19~0935~ 22~0894~ [23] 25~0776~ 28~03778~; 33~07200~ 38~04191~'),
  (28948, 47, 7, 16, 'I rejoice therefore that I have confidence in you in all things.', '1~5463~ 3~3754~ 6~2292~ 7~1722~ 8~5213~ 9~1722~ 10~3956~ [11]'),
  (15143, 19, 78, 21, 'Therefore the LORD heard this, and was wroth: so a fire was kindled against Jacob, and anger also came up against Israel;', '2~03068~ 3~08085~ [4] 7~05674~: 10~0784~ 12~05400~ 14~03290~, 16~0639~ 19~05927~ 21~03478~;'),
  (631, 1, 24, 36, 'And Sarah my master''s wife bare a son to my master when she was old: and unto him hath he given all that he hath.', '1~08283~ 3~0113~ 4~0802~ 5~03205~ 7~01121~ 10~0113~ 11~0310~ 14~02209~: 20~05414~'),
  (2491, 2, 33, 13, 'Now therefore, I pray thee, if I have found grace in thy sight, shew me now thy way, that I may know thee, that I may find grace in thy sight: and consider that this nation is thy people.', '8~04672~ 9~02580~ 12~05869~, 13~03045~ 17~01870~, 21~03045~ 26~04672~ 27~02580~ 30~05869~: 32~07200~ 35~01471~ [36] 38~05971~.'),
  (21647, 26, 45, 8, 'In the land shall be his possession in Israel: and my princes shall no more oppress my people; and the rest of the land shall they give to the house of Israel according to their tribes.', '2~0776~ 6~0272~ 8~03478~: 11~05387~ 15~03238~ 17~05971~; [19 21] 23~0776~ 26~05414~ 29~01004~ 31~03478~ 35~07626~.'),
  (30295, 59, 1, 13, 'Let no man say when he is tempted, I am tempted of God: for God cannot be tempted with evil, neither tempteth he any man:', '&para; 0~3004~ 2~3367~ 3~3004~ 7~3985~ 8~3754~,* 11~3985~ 12~575~ 13~2316~: 14~1063~ 15~2316~ 18~2076~ 19~551~* 21~2556~, 22~1161~ 23~3985~ 24~3985~ 25~846~* 27~3762~:'),
  (19150, 24, 7, 22, 'For I spake not unto your fathers, nor commanded them in the day that I brought them out of the land of Egypt, concerning burnt offerings or sacrifices:', '2~01696~ 6~01~, 8~06680~ 12~03117~ 17~03318~ 20~0776~ 22~04714~, 23~01697~ 25~05930~ 27~02077~:'),
  (4692, 4, 31, 22, 'Only the gold, and the silver, the brass, the iron, the tin, and the lead,', '2~02091~, 5~03701~, 7~05178~, 9~01270~, 11~0913~, 14~05777~,'),
  (9737, 12, 8, 2, 'And the woman arose, and did after the saying of the man of God: and she went with her household, and sojourned in the land of the Philistines seven years.', '2~0802~ 3~06965~, 5~06213~ 8~01697~ 11~0376~ 13~0430~: 16~03212~ 19~01004~, 21~01481~ 24~0776~ 27~06430~ 28~07651~ 29~08141~.'),
  (30129, 58, 9, 8, 'The Holy Ghost this signifying, that the way into the holiest of all was not yet made manifest, while as the first tabernacle was yet standing:', '&para; 1~40~ 2~4151~ 3~5124~ 4~1213~, 7~3598~ 12~39~ 13~5319~ 15~3380~ 17~5319~, 21~4413~ 22~4633~ 23~2192~ 24~2089~ 25~4714~:'),
  (30756, 66, 2, 23, 'And I will kill her children with death; and all the churches shall know that I am he which searcheth the reins and hearts: and I will give unto every one of you according to your works.', '0~2532~ 3~615~ 4~846~ 5~5043~ 6~1722~ 7~2288~; 8~2532~ 9~3956~ 11~1577~ 13~1097~ 14~3754~ 15~1473~ 16~1510~ 18~3588~ 19~2045~ 21~3510~ 22~2532~ 23~2588~: 24~2532~ 27~1325~ 30~1538~ 32~5213~ 34~2596~ 35~5216~ 36~2041~.'),
  (2530, 2, 34, 29, 'And it came to pass, when Moses came down from mount Sinai with the two tables of testimony in Moses'' hand, when he came down from the mount, that Moses wist not that the skin of his face shone while he talked with him.', '6~04872~ 8~03381~ 10~02022~ 11~05514~ 14~08147~ 15~03871~ 17~05715~ 19~04872~ 20~03027~, 24~03381~ 27~02022~, 29~04872~ 30~03045~ 34~05785~ 37~06440~ 38~07160~ 41~01696~'),
  (1808, 2, 10, 26, 'Our cattle also shall go with us; there shall not an hoof be left behind; for thereof must we take to serve the LORD our God; and we know not with what we must serve the LORD, until we come thither.', '1~04735~ 4~03212~ 11~06541~ 14~07604~; 19~03947~ 21~05647~ 23~03068~ 25~0430~; 28~03045~ 34~05647~ 36~03068~, 39~0935~'),
  (12407, 16, 5, 16, 'Yea, also I continued in the work of this wall, neither bought we any land: and all my servants were gathered thither unto the work.', '3~02388~ 6~04399~ 9~02346~, 11~07069~ 14~07704~: 18~05288~ [19] 20~06908~ 24~04399~.'),
  (20246, 24, 51, 25, 'Behold, I am against thee, O destroying mountain, saith the LORD, which destroyest all the earth: and I will stretch out mine hand upon thee, and roll thee down from the rocks, and will make thee a burnt mountain.', '[2] 6~04889~ 7~02022~, 8~05002~ 10~03068~, 12~07843~ 15~0776~: 20~05186~ 22~03027~ 28~01556~ 31~05553~, 34~05414~ 37~08316~ 38~02022~.'),
  (25020, 42, 2, 35, '(Yea, a sword shall pierce through thy own soul also,) that the thoughts of many hearts may be revealed.', '0~1161~* 3~4501~ 6~1330~ 7~4675~ 8~846~ 9~5590~ 10~2532~,) 11~3704~ 13~1261~ 14~1537~ 15~4183~ 16~302~ 17~2588~ 19~601~.'),
  (17064, 20, 23, 11, 'For their redeemer is mighty; he shall plead their cause with thee.', '2~01350~ [3] 4~02389~; 7~07378~ 9~07379~'),
  (483, 1, 19, 22, 'Haste thee, escape thither; for I cannot do any thing till thou be come thither. Therefore the name of the city was called Zoar.', '0~04116~ 2~04422~ 6~03201~ 7~06213~ 9~01697~ 13~0935~ 17~08034~ 20~05892~ 22~07121~ 23~06820~.'),
  (24798, 41, 14, 33, 'And he taketh with him Peter and James and John, and began to be sore amazed, and to be very heavy;', '0~2532~ 2~3880~ 3~3326~ 4~1438~ 5~4074~ 6~2532~ 7~2385~ 8~2532~ 9~2491~, 10~2532~ 11~756~ 15~1568~, 16~2532~ 20~85~;'),
  (12175, 15, 6, 15, 'And this house was finished on the third day of the month Adar, which was in the sixth year of the reign of Darius the king.', '1~01836~ 2~01005~ 4~03319~ 5~05705~ 7~08532~ 8~03118~ 11~03393~ 12~0144~, 14~01932~ 17~08353~ 18~08140~ 21~04437~ 23~01868~ 25~04430~.'),
  (4668, 4, 30, 14, 'But if her husband altogether hold his peace at her from day to day; then he establisheth all her vows, or all her bonds, which are upon her: he confirmeth them, because he held his peace at her in the day that he heard them.', '3~0376~ 4~02790~ 7~02790~ 11~03117~ 13~03117~; 16~06965~ 19~05088~, 23~0632~, [25] 29~06965~ 35~02790~ 40~03117~ 43~08085~ [44]'),
  (25673, 42, 17, 8, 'And will not rather say unto him, Make ready wherewith I may sup, and gird thyself, and serve me, till I have eaten and drunken; and afterward thou shalt eat and drink?', '0~235~ 2~3780~ 4~2046~ 6~846~, 8~2090~ 9~5101~ 12~1172~, 13~2532~ 15~4024~, 17~1247~ 18~3427~, 19~2193~ 22~5315~ 23~2532~ 24~4095~; 25~2532~ 26~5023~ 27~3326~* 28~4771~ 30~5315~ 31~2532~ 32~4095~?'),
  (12412, 16, 6, 2, 'That Sanballat and Geshem sent unto me, saying, Come, let us meet together in some one of the villages in the plain of Ono. But they thought to do me mischief.', '1~05571~ 3~01654~ 4~07971~ 7~0559~, 8~03212~, 11~03259~ 12~03162~ [14 16] 18~03715~ 21~01237~ 23~0207~. 26~02803~ 28~06213~ 30~07451~.'),
  (16790, 20, 14, 9, 'Fools make a mock at sin: but among the righteous there is favour.', '&para; 0~0191~ 3~03887~ 5~0817~: 9~03477~ [10 11] 12~07522~.'),
  (21441, 26, 38, 7, 'Be thou prepared, and prepare for thyself, thou, and all thy company that are assembled unto thee, and be thou a guard unto them.', '2~03559~, 4~03559~ 11~06951~ 14~06950~ 21~04929~'),
  (14524, 19, 39, 3, 'My heart was hot within me, while I was musing the fire burned: then spake I with my tongue,', '1~03820~ 3~02552~ 4~07130~ 9~01901~ 11~0784~ 12~01197~: [13] 13~0227~ 14~01696~ 18~03956~,'),
  (15049, 19, 73, 20, 'As a dream when one awaketh; so, O Lord, when thou awakest, thou shalt despise their image.', '2~02472~ [4] 5~06974~; [6] 8~0136~, 11~05782~, 14~0959~ 16~06754~.'),
  (11080, 13, 25, 26, 'The nineteenth to Mallothi, he, his sons, and his brethren, were twelve:', '1~06240~ 2~08672~ 3~04413~, [4] 6~01121~, 9~0251~, [10] 11~06240~ 12~08147~:*'),
  (16823, 20, 15, 7, 'The lips of the wise disperse knowledge: but the heart of the foolish doeth not so.', '&para; 1~08193~ 4~02450~ 5~02219~ 6~01847~: 9~03820~ 12~03684~ [13]'),
  (16261, 19, 139, 13, 'For thou hast possessed my reins: thou hast covered me in my mother''s womb.', '3~07069~ 5~03629~: 8~05526~ 12~0517~ 13~0990~.'),
  (12883, 18, 1, 5, 'And it was so, when the days of their feasting were gone about, that Job sent and sanctified them, and rose up early in the morning, and offered burnt offerings according to the number of them all: for Job said, It may be that my sons have sinned, and cursed God in their hearts. Thus did Job continually.', '6~03117~ [8] 9~04960~ 12~05362~, 14~0347~ 15~07971~ 17~06942~ 22~07925~ 25~01242~, 27~05927~ 29~05930~ [30] 33~04557~ 38~0347~ 39~0559~, 42~0194~ 45~01121~ 47~02398~, 49~01288~ 50~0430~ 53~03824~. 55~06213~ 56~0347~ 57~03117~.'),
  (27135, 44, 7, 3, 'And said unto him, Get thee out of thy country, and from thy kindred, and come into the land which I shall shew thee.', '0~2532~ 1~2036~ 2~4314~ 3~846~, 5~1831~ 7~1537~ 8~4675~ 9~1093~, 10~2532~ 11~1537~ 12~4675~ 13~4772~, 14~2532~ 15~1204~ 16~1519~ 18~1093~ 19~302~ 20~3739~ 22~1166~ 23~4671~.'),
  (23700, 40, 16, 18, 'And I say also unto thee, That thou art Peter, and upon this rock I will build my church; and the gates of hell shall not prevail against it.', '0~1161~ 2~3004~ 3~2504~ 5~4671~, 6~3754~ 7~4771~ 8~1488~ 9~4074~, 10~2532~ 11~1909~ 12~5026~ 13~4073~ 16~3618~ 17~3450~ 18~1577~; 19~2532~ 21~4439~ 23~86~ 24~2729~ 25~3756~ 27~2729~ 28~846~.'),
  (25798, 42, 20, 5, 'And they reasoned with themselves, saying, If we shall say, From heaven; he will say, Why then believed ye him not?', '0~1161~ 2~4817~ 3~4314~ 4~1438~, 5~3004~ 6~3754~,* 7~1437~ 10~2036~, 11~1537~ 12~3772~; 15~2046~, 16~1302~ 17~3767~ 19~4100~ 20~846~ 21~3756~?'),
  (4531, 4, 26, 36, 'And these are the sons of Shuthelah: of Eran, the family of the Eranites.', '[2] 4~01121~ 6~07803~: 8~06197~, 10~04940~ 13~06198~.'),
  (2422, 2, 30, 35, 'And thou shalt make it a perfume, a confection after the art of the apothecary, tempered together, pure and holy:', '3~06213~ 6~07004~, 8~07545~ 11~04639~ 14~07543~, 15~04414~ 17~02889~ [18] 19~06944~:'),
  (18053, 23, 21, 9, 'And, behold, here cometh a chariot of men, with a couple of horsemen. And he answered and said, Babylon is fallen, is fallen; and all the graven images of her gods he hath broken unto the ground.', '3~0935~ 5~07393~ 7~0376~, [8] 10~06776~ 12~06571~. 15~06030~ 17~0559~, 18~0894~ 20~05307~, 22~05307~; 27~06456~ 30~0430~ 33~07665~ 36~0776~.'),
  (516, 1, 20, 17, 'So Abraham prayed unto God: and God healed Abimelech, and his wife, and his maidservants; and they bare children.', '1~085~ 2~06419~ 4~0430~: 6~0430~ 7~07495~ 8~040~, 11~0802~, 14~0519~; 17~03205~ [18]'),
  (3128, 3, 14, 12, 'And the priest shall take one he lamb, and offer him for a trespass offering, and the log of oil, and wave them for a wave offering before the LORD:', '2~03548~ 4~03947~ 5~0259~ 7~03532~, 9~07126~ 14~0817~, 17~03849~ 19~08081~, 21~05130~ [23] 26~08573~ 27~06440~ 29~03068~:'),
  (6752, 7, 8, 26, 'And the weight of the golden earrings that he requested was a thousand and seven hundred shekels of gold; beside ornaments, and collars, and purple raiment that was on the kings of Midian, and beside the chains that were about their camels'' necks.', '2~04948~ 5~02091~ 6~05141~ 9~07592~ 12~0505~ 14~07651~ 15~03967~ [16] 18~02091~; 20~07720~, 22~05188~, 24~0713~ 25~0899~ [27] 30~04428~ 32~04080~, 36~06060~ [38] 41~01581~ 42~06677~.'),
  (29800, 54, 5, 21, 'I charge thee before God, and the Lord Jesus Christ, and the elect angels, that thou observe these things without preferring one before another, doing nothing by partiality.', '1~1263~ [2] 3~1799~ 4~2316~, 5~2532~ 7~2962~ 8~2424~ 9~5547~, 10~2532~ 12~1588~ 13~32~, 14~2443~ 16~5442~ 18~5023~ 19~5565~ 23~4299~, 24~4160~ 25~3367~ 26~2596~ 27~4346~.'),
  (1151, 1, 38, 27, 'And it came to pass in the time of her travail, that, behold, twins were in her womb.', '7~06256~ 10~03205~, 13~08380~ [14] 17~0990~.'),
  (29578, 52, 1, 2, 'We give thanks to God always for you all, making mention of you in our prayers;', '&para; 2~2168~ 4~2316~ 5~3842~ 6~4012~ 7~5216~ 8~3956~, 9~4160~ 10~3417~ 12~5216~ 13~1909~ 14~2257~ 15~4335~;'),
  (22516, 30, 9, 12, 'That they may possess the remnant of Edom, and of all the heathen, which are called by my name, saith the LORD that doeth this.', '3~03423~ 5~07611~ 7~0123~, 12~01471~, 15~07121~ 18~08034~, 19~05002~ 21~03068~ 23~06213~'),
  (27574, 44, 18, 1, 'After these things Paul departed from Athens, and came to Corinth;', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~3326~ 3~5023~ 4~3972~ 5~5563~ 6~1537~ 7~116~, 9~2064~ 10~1519~ 11~2882~;'),
  (24594, 41, 9, 45, 'And if thy foot offend thee, cut it off: it is better for thee to enter halt into life, than having two feet to be cast into hell, into the fire that never shall be quenched:', '0~2532~ 1~1437~ 2~4675~ 3~4228~ 4~4624~ 5~4571~, 6~609~ 7~846~ 8~609~: 10~2076~ 11~2570~ 13~4671~ 15~1525~ 16~5560~ 17~1519~ 18~2222~, 19~2228~ 20~2192~ 21~1417~ 22~4228~ 25~906~ 26~1519~ 27~1067~, 28~1519~ 30~4442~ 35~762~:'),
  (6596, 7, 3, 21, 'And Ehud put forth his left hand, and took the dagger from his right thigh, and thrust it into his belly:', '1~0164~ 3~07971~ 5~08040~ 6~03027~, 8~03947~ 10~02719~ 13~03225~ 14~03409~, 16~08628~ 20~0990~:'),
  (30444, 60, 3, 4, 'But let it be the hidden man of the heart, in that which is not corruptible, even the ornament of a meek and quiet spirit, which is in the sight of God of great price.', '0~235~ [1 3] 5~2927~ 6~444~ 9~2588~, 10~1722~ 15~862~, [16 18] 21~4239~ 22~2532~ 23~2272~ 24~4151~, 25~3739~ 26~2076~ 29~1799~ 31~2316~ 34~4185~.'),
  (30514, 61, 1, 19, 'We have also a more sure word of prophecy; whereunto ye do well that ye take heed, as unto a light that shineth in a dark place, until the day dawn, and the day star arise in your hearts:', '&para; 1~2192~ 2~2532~ 5~949~ 6~3056~ 8~4397~; 9~3739~ 11~4160~ 12~2573~ 16~4337~, 17~5613~ 20~3088~ 22~5316~ 23~1722~ 25~850~ 26~5117~, 27~3757~ 28~2193~ 29~2250~ 30~1306~, 31~2532~ 34~5459~ 35~393~ 36~1722~ 37~5216~ 38~2588~:'),
  (2096, 2, 21, 14, 'But if a man come presumptuously upon his neighbour, to slay him with guile; thou shalt take him from mine altar, that he may die.', '3~0376~ 5~02102~ 8~07453~, 10~02026~ 13~06195~; 16~03947~ 20~04196~, 24~04191~.'),
  (26597, 43, 12, 2, 'There they made him a supper; and Martha served: but Lazarus was one of them that sat at the table with him.', '0~3767~ 1~1563~ 2~4160~ 3~846~ 5~1173~; 6~2532~ 7~3136~ 8~1247~: 9~1161~ 10~2976~ 11~2258~ 12~1520~ 19~4873~ 21~846~.'),
  (12352, 16, 3, 16, 'After him repaired Nehemiah the son of Azbuk, the ruler of the half part of Bethzur, unto the place over against the sepulchres of David, and to the pool that was made, and unto the house of the mighty.', '0~0310~ 2~02388~ 3~05166~ 5~01121~ 7~05802~, 9~08269~ 12~02677~ 13~06418~ 15~01049~, [17 18] 22~06913~ 24~01732~, 28~01295~ 31~06213~, 35~01004~ 38~01368~.'),
  (17074, 20, 23, 21, 'For the drunkard and the glutton shall come to poverty: and drowsiness shall clothe a man with rags.', '2~05433~ 5~02151~ 9~03423~: 11~05124~ 13~03847~ [14 15] 17~07168~.'),
  (30349, 59, 3, 14, 'But if ye have bitter envying and strife in your hearts, glory not, and lie not against the truth.', '0~1161~ 1~1487~ 3~2192~ 4~4089~ 5~2205~ 6~2532~ 7~2052~ 8~1722~ 9~5216~ 10~2588~, 11~2620~ 12~3361~, 13~2532~ 15~5574~ 16~2596~ 18~225~.'),
  (7814, 9, 22, 20, 'And one of the sons of Ahimelech the son of Ahitub, named Abiathar, escaped, and fled after David.', '&para; 1~0259~ 4~01121~ 6~0288~ 8~01121~ 10~0285~, 11~08034~ 12~054~, 13~04422~, 15~01272~ 16~0310~ 17~01732~.'),
  (12900, 18, 1, 22, 'In all this Job sinned not, nor charged God foolishly.', '3~0347~ 4~02398~ 7~05414~ 8~0430~ 9~08604~.'),
  (8364, 10, 14, 1, 'Now Joab the son of Zeruiah perceived that the king''s heart was toward Absalom.', '&para; 1~03097~ 3~01121~ 5~06870~ 6~03045~ 9~04428~ 10~03820~ [11] 13~053~.'),
  (17380, 21, 3, 12, 'I know that there is no good in them, but for a man to rejoice, and to do good in his life.', '1~03045~ [3 4] 6~02896~ [11 12] 14~08055~, 17~06213~ 18~02896~ 21~02416~.'),
  (1311, 1, 43, 16, 'And when Joseph saw Benjamin with them, he said to the ruler of his house, Bring these men home, and slay, and make ready; for these men shall dine with me at noon.', '2~03130~ 3~07200~ 4~01144~ 5~0854~ 8~0559~ 14~01004~, 15~0935~ [16] 17~0582~ 18~01004~, 20~02873~ 21~02874~,* 24~03559~; [26] 27~0582~ 29~0398~ 33~06672~.'),
  (14676, 19, 49, 19, 'He shall go to the generation of his fathers; they shall never see light.', '2~0935~ 5~01755~ 8~01~; 11~05331~ 12~03808~* 13~07200~ 14~0216~.'),
  (3412, 3, 23, 5, 'In the fourteenth day of the first month at even is the Lord''s passover.', '2~06240~ [3] 3~0702~ 6~07223~ 7~02320~ 9~06153~ [10] 12~03068~ 13~06453~.'),
  (11762, 14, 26, 21, 'And Uzziah the king was a leper unto the day of his death, and dwelt in a several house, being a leper; for he was cut off from the house of the LORD: and Jotham his son was over the king''s house, judging the people of the land.', '1~05818~ 3~04428~ 6~06879~ 9~03117~ 12~04194~, 15~03427~ 17~02669~ 18~02669~* 19~01004~, [20] 22~06879~; 27~01504~ 30~01004~ 33~03068~: 35~03147~ 37~01121~ [38] 41~04428~ 42~01004~, 43~08199~ 45~05971~ 48~0776~.'),
  (14446, 19, 35, 27, 'Let them shout for joy, and be glad, that favour my righteous cause: yea, let them say continually, Let the LORD be magnified, which hath pleasure in the prosperity of his servant.', '4~07442~, 7~08055~, 9~02655~ 12~06664~: 16~0559~ 17~08548~, 20~03068~ 22~01431~, 25~02655~ 28~07965~ 31~05650~.'),
  (9567, 12, 2, 8, 'And Elijah took his mantle, and wrapped it together, and smote the waters, and they were divided hither and thither, so that they two went over on dry ground.', '1~0452~ 2~03947~ 4~0155~, [7] 8~01563~, 10~05221~ 12~04325~, 16~02673~ 23~08147~ 25~05674~ 27~02724~'),
  (786, 1, 28, 9, 'Then went Esau unto Ishmael, and took unto the wives which he had Mahalath the daughter of Ishmael Abraham''s son, the sister of Nebajoth, to be his wife.', '1~03212~ 2~06215~ 4~03458~, 6~03947~ 9~0802~ 13~04258~ 15~01323~ 17~03458~ 18~085~ 19~01121~, 21~0269~ 23~05032~, 27~0802~.'),
  (30704, 65, 1, 16, 'These are murmurers, complainers, walking after their own lusts; and their mouth speaketh great swelling words, having men''s persons in admiration because of advantage.', '0~3778~ 1~1526~ 2~1113~, 3~3202~, 4~4198~ 5~2596~ 7~846~ 8~1939~; 9~2532~ 10~846~ 11~4750~ 12~2980~ 14~5246~ [15] 18~4383~ 20~2296~ 21~5484~ 23~5622~.'),
  (21567, 26, 42, 6, 'For they were in three stories, but had not pillars as the pillars of the courts: therefore the building was straitened more than the lowest and the middlemost from the ground.', '[2] 4~08027~ [5] 9~05982~ 12~05982~ 15~02691~: [17 18] 20~0680~ 24~08481~ 27~08484~ 30~0776~.'),
  (15359, 19, 89, 24, 'But my faithfulness and my mercy shall be with him: and in my name shall his horn be exalted.', '2~0530~ 5~02617~ [6 7] 13~08034~ 16~07161~ 18~07311~.'),
  (29995, 58, 2, 2, 'For if the word spoken by angels was stedfast, and every transgression and disobedience received a just recompense of reward;', '0~1063~ 1~1487~ 3~3056~ 4~2980~ 5~1223~ 6~32~ 7~1096~ 8~949~, 9~2532~ 10~3956~ 11~3847~ 12~2532~ 13~3876~ 14~2983~ 16~1738~ 19~3405~;'),
  (6491, 6, 24, 8, 'And I brought you into the land of the Amorites, which dwelt on the other side Jordan; and they fought with you: and I gave them into your hand, that ye might possess their land; and I destroyed them from before you.', '2~0935~ 6~0776~ 9~0567~, 11~03427~ 15~05676~ 16~03383~; 19~03898~ 24~05414~ 28~03027~, 32~03423~ 34~0776~; 37~08045~ 40~06440~'),
  (29943, 56, 3, 4, 'But after that the kindness and love of God our Saviour toward man appeared,', '0~1161~ 1~3753~ 4~5544~ 5~2532~ 6~5363~ 8~2316~ 9~2257~ 10~4990~ 12~5363~ 13~2014~,'),
  (15230, 19, 81, 4, 'For this was a statute for Israel, and a law of the God of Jacob.', '[2] 4~02706~ 6~03478~, [7] 9~04941~ 12~0430~ 14~03290~.'),
  (757, 1, 27, 26, 'And his father Isaac said unto him, Come near now, and kiss me, my son.', '2~01~ 3~03327~ 4~0559~ 8~05066~ 11~05401~ 14~01121~.'),
  (1553, 2, 1, 16, 'And he said, When ye do the office of a midwife to the Hebrew women, and see them upon the stools; if it be a son, then ye shall kill him: but if it be a daughter, then she shall live.', '2~0559~, 10~03205~ 14~05680~, 16~07200~ [17] 20~070~; [23] 25~01121~, 29~04191~ [34] 36~01323~, 40~02425~.'),
  (11750, 14, 26, 9, 'Moreover Uzziah built towers in Jerusalem at the corner gate, and at the valley gate, and at the turning of the wall, and fortified them.', '1~05818~ 2~01129~ 3~04026~ 5~03389~ 8~06438~ 9~08179~, 13~01516~ 14~08179~, 18~04740~ [19 21] 23~02388~'),
  (27105, 44, 5, 30, 'The God of our fathers raised up Jesus, whom ye slew and hanged on a tree.', '1~2316~ 3~2257~ 4~3962~ 6~1453~ 7~2424~, 8~3739~ 9~5210~ 10~1315~ 12~2910~ 13~1909~ 15~3586~.'),
  (20777, 26, 16, 6, 'And when I passed by thee, and saw thee polluted in thine own blood, I said unto thee when thou wast in thy blood, Live; yea, I said unto thee when thou wast in thy blood, Live.', '&para; 3~05674~ 7~07200~ 9~0947~ 13~01818~, 15~0559~ [18 20] 23~01818~, 24~02421~; 27~0559~ [30 32] 35~01818~, 36~02421~.'),
  (5307, 5, 14, 11, 'Of all clean birds ye shall eat.', '[0] 2~02889~ 3~06833~ 6~0398~.'),
  (20003, 24, 42, 19, 'The LORD hath said concerning you, O ye remnant of Judah; Go ye not into Egypt: know certainly that I have admonished you this day.', '1~03068~ 3~01696~ 8~07611~ 10~03063~; 11~0935~ 15~04714~: 16~03045~ 17~03045~ 21~05749~ 24~03117~.'),
  (20868, 26, 18, 10, 'If he beget a son that is a robber, a shedder of blood, and that doeth the like to any one of these things,', '&para; 2~03205~ 4~01121~ [5 6] 8~06530~, 10~08210~ 12~01818~, [14] 15~06213~ 17~0251~ [19] 20~0259~ [23]'),
  (19134, 24, 7, 6, 'If ye oppress not the stranger, the fatherless, and the widow, and shed not innocent blood in this place, neither walk after other gods to your hurt:', '[0] 2~06231~ 5~01616~, 7~03490~, 10~0490~, 12~08210~ 14~05355~ 15~01818~ 18~04725~, 20~03212~ 21~0310~ 22~0312~ 23~0430~ 26~07451~:'),
  (2817, 3, 4, 17, 'And the priest shall dip his finger in some of the blood, and sprinkle it seven times before the LORD, even before the veil.', '2~03548~ 4~02881~ 6~0676~ [7 8] 11~01818~, 13~05137~ [14] 15~07651~ 16~06471~ 17~06440~ 19~03068~, [20] 21~06440~ 23~06532~.'),
  (25312, 42, 8, 55, 'And her spirit came again, and she arose straightway: and he commanded to give her meat.', '0~2532~ 1~846~ 2~4151~ 4~1994~, 5~2532~ 7~450~ 8~3916~: 9~2532~ 11~1299~ 13~1325~ 14~846~ 15~5315~.'),
  (29724, 54, 1, 12, 'And I thank Christ Jesus our Lord, who hath enabled me, for that he counted me faithful, putting me into the ministry;', '&para; 0~2532~ 2~2192~ 3~5485~* 4~5547~ 5~2424~ 6~2257~ 7~2962~, 8~3588~ 10~1743~ 11~3165~, 12~3754~ 15~2233~ 16~3165~ 17~4103~, 19~5087~ 20~1519~ 22~1248~;'),
  (18060, 23, 21, 16, 'For thus hath the Lord said unto me, Within a year, according to the years of an hireling, and all the glory of Kedar shall fail:', '4~0136~ 5~0559~ 10~08141~, 14~08141~ 17~07916~, 21~03519~ 23~06938~ 25~03615~:'),
  (9430, 11, 20, 14, 'And Ahab said, By whom? And he said, Thus saith the LORD, Even by the young men of the princes of the provinces. Then he said, Who shall order the battle? And he answered, Thou.', '1~0256~ 2~0559~, 7~0559~, 9~0559~ 11~03068~, [12] 16~05288~ 19~08269~ 22~04082~. 25~0559~, 28~0631~ 30~04421~? 33~0559~,'),
  (1726, 2, 8, 11, 'And the frogs shall depart from thee, and from thy houses, and from thy servants, and from thy people; they shall remain in the river only.', '2~06854~ 4~05493~ 10~01004~, 14~05650~, 18~05971~; 21~07604~ 24~02975~'),
  (15557, 19, 102, 27, 'But thou art the same, and thy years shall have no end.', '[2] 7~08141~ 11~08552~.'),
  (5593, 5, 27, 2, 'And it shall be on the day when ye shall pass over Jordan unto the land which the LORD thy God giveth thee, that thou shalt set thee up great stones, and plaster them with plaster:', '6~03117~ 11~05674~ 12~03383~ 15~0776~ 18~03068~ 20~0430~ 21~05414~ 28~06965~ 29~01419~ 30~068~, 32~07874~ 35~07875~:'),
  (21924, 27, 6, 10, 'Now when Daniel knew that the writing was signed, he went into his house; and his windows being open in his chamber toward Jerusalem, he kneeled upon his knees three times a day, and prayed, and gave thanks before his God, as he did aforetime.', '2~01841~ 3~03046~ 6~03792~ 8~07560~, 10~05954~ 13~01005~; 16~03551~ 18~06606~ 21~05952~ 22~05049~ 23~03390~, 25~01289~ 26~05922~ 28~01291~ 29~08532~ 30~02166~ 32~03118~, 34~06739~, 37~03029~ 38~06925~ 40~0426~, 41~03606~ 42~06903~ 43~01934~ 44~05648~* 45~06928~ 46~04481~* 47~01836~.*'),
  (9918, 12, 14, 14, 'And he took all the gold and silver, and all the vessels that were found in the house of the LORD, and in the treasures of the king''s house, and hostages, and returned to Samaria.', '2~03947~ 5~02091~ 7~03701~, 11~03627~ 14~04672~ 17~01004~ 20~03068~, 24~0214~ 27~04428~ 28~01004~, 30~08594~ 31~01121~,* 33~07725~ 35~08111~.');
